properties.name: 23 Mere
properties.description: 23 Mere was a planet in the Colonies. The Star Morning stopped at this world on its way to Motexx from Darepp.

properties.name: 2GS-91E20
properties.description: 2GS-91E20 was a pulsar located nearly five light-years Coreward from the New Republic's deep-space Anomaly 2249.

properties.name: A-Foroon
properties.description: A-Foroon was a windy world of scraggly forests located in the A-Foroon system, a part of the Arkanis sector in the Slice portion of the Outer Rim Territories. It was situated on the Triellus Trade Route hyperlane, which linked it to the B-Foroon and Piroket systems.

properties.name: Aaeton
properties.description: Aaeton was a planet of the Aaeton system, in the Core Worlds region. During the Cold War between the Galactic Republic and the reconstituted Sith Empire, an Imperial bioweapon activated on the planet. During the last days of the Republic, the government of Aaeton had authorization to allow its citizens to visit the generally off-limits neighboring world of Ragoon VI.

properties.name: Aar
properties.description: Aar was a planet in the Aar system of the Nijune sector, part of the Outer Rim Territories. It was homeworld to the Aar'aa species, reptilian sentients often employed as enforcers by the Hutts, a species known for its many crime lords.

properties.name: Aargau
properties.poi: Dawn Pyramid of Aargau, Garden of Butterflies, IBC Arcology,
properties.description: Aargau  was a planet in the Zug system of the Core Worlds region, not far from Coruscant and the Corellian Run. It was run by and served as the headquarters for the Bank of Aargau, which was part of the InterGalactic Banking Clan. Numerous other banks and corporations were also based on Aargau, including the Z-Gomot Ternbuell Guppat Corporation. Aargau was an exceptionally wealthy world, due both to its status as a financial center, as well as the planet's vast reserves of rare and precious metals.

properties.name: Aargonar
properties.poi: Separatist base, Republic base, Vondar Canyon,
properties.description: Aargonar was a dusty, desert-climate planet located in the Borderland Regions of the Mid Rim.

properties.name: Aaris
properties.description: The Aaris were one-meter-tall reptilian sentients native to the planet Aaris III in the Kathol sector of the Outer Rim Territories. Thousands of years prior to the Galactic Civil War, the Aaris built an industrial society across their homeworld, raising large cities. They had a strong tradition of oral communication, to the extent of developing a unique method of recording their knowledge. Although a peaceful race, the Aaris tore their society apart in a civil war, a conflict perpetrated by the arrival of the Plaque of Victory on their planet. The Plaque was a sentient lifeform—although it was inanimate and held within a metal ingot—that sought to influence the minds of other beings into doing its bidding. The Plaque caused the Aaris people to become violent and homicidal, turning factions against one another as they all sought to gain possession of the artifact. Eventually, the Aaris fell into decline, and their cities became ruins reclaimed by the jungle. By 8 ABY, the primitive descendants of the Aaris lived in warrens tunneled through the ruins of their former cities.

properties.name: Aaron
properties.description: Aaron was a planet located within the Aaron system of the Outer Rim Territories. It was home to a facility operated by the Fromm Gang, a crime family headquartered on the planet Annoo. The multi-level facility was involved in mining, research, and other activities. The droids C-3PO and R2-D2 were imprisoned in the complex, but they escaped and made their way to a higher story, where Thall Joben and Jord Dusat rescued them.

properties.name: Ab'Bshingh
properties.description: Ab'Bshingh was a planet in the Outer Rim Territories, home to the Farang and Waroot species, who fought each other continuously for centuries. At some point, the Imperial military strategist Crat Dakerno went to the planet to study the two native species.

properties.name: Abaarian
properties.description: Abaarian was a planet in the Abaarian system in the Mid Rim. The world joined the Galactic Alliance in the wake of the Yuuzhan Vong War, shipping bottled water to needy planets. Several of these water shipments were hijacked during the Dark Nest Crisis. The Jedi High Council dispatched Jedi Knights Tesar Sebatyne and Lowbacca to investigate.

properties.name: Abafar
properties.poi: Dr. Evazan Cosmetic Surgery, Game Go, The Void, Power Sliders, Rhydonium mining installation,
properties.description: Abafar was a remote desert world within the Outer Rim Territories of the galaxy. The planet was scarcely populated and mostly covered in a featureless expanse known as The Void.

properties.name: Abbaji
properties.description: Abbaji may refer to:

properties.name: Abhean
properties.description: Abhean was a planet located in the Mid Rim's Maldrood sector, on the Perlemian Trade Route. It was the farthest major world of the Galactic Republic during the Tionese War. At some point after the conflict began in 24,000 BBY, the Honorable Union of Desevro & Tion conquered Abhean. The planet saw fighting again in 15,480 BBY, when the Strontium Raid was carried out as part of the Second Alsakan Conflict. Around 15,000 BBY, Abhean became a major hub of the Republic Navy.

properties.name: Abo Dreth
properties.description: Abo Dreth was a planet in the Corporate Sector, thriving with lakes and rivers but with a nitrogen-based atmosphere.

properties.name: Abonshee
properties.description: Abonshee—literally, Masterhome—was a planet in the Abonshee system of Fakir sector in the Bakchou arm. It was an temperate world with hardy flora and reptilian fauna. It was home to the reptilian Anointed People, and was located in the Northern Dependencies. The name "Masterhome" was given by the Anointed People. Abonshee was discovered by the Galactic Republic some ninety years before the Battle of Yavin.

properties.name: Abraxas
properties.description: Abraxas was a planet in the Abraxas system situated within the Yushan sector of the Mid Rim Territories. Abraxas was run dry of its rich natural resources by overwhelming mining, and became a base for the Eiattu pirates. Soon after the Battle of Endor, the New Republic discovered and threw the pirates out.

properties.name: Abraxin
properties.description: Abraxin was a swampy world in the Tion Cluster. It was an exporter of Abrax cognac.

properties.name: Abregado-Rae
properties.description: Abregado-rae, also known simply as Abregado and sometimes spelled Abregado-Rae, was a trade world located in the galaxy's Core Worlds. It was situated at the beginning of the Rimma Trade Route. Abregado-rae had the reputation to be a rather lawless world, and its main spaceport was as close to a safe dock for smugglers as could be found in the Core.

properties.name: Abridon
properties.description: Abridon was a pleasant, mountainous planet with special significance to the career of Brenn Tantor. Its capital housed the Abridon Government Center, while Sayan was the center of its shipbuilding industry. It was primarily notable to the greater galaxy as the site of Luke Skywalker's capture by the Galactic Empire. It was located on the Northern Corridor's Lipsec Run.

properties.name: Abrihom
properties.description: Abrihom was a supply station platform located within the Rayter sector in the Outer Rim Territories region of the galaxy. Used by the Alliance to Restore the Republic, it was destroyed during the Galactic Civil War.

properties.name: Abrion Major
properties.description: Abrion Major was an astronomical object located in the Abrion Major system, a part of the Abrion sector in the Slice portion of the Outer Rim Territories. Abrion Major served as the capital of the Abrion sector, and the latter was represented in the Galactic Republic's Senate by Senator Esu Rotsino, who hailed from Abrion Major.

properties.name: Absit
properties.description: Absit was a planet located in the Absit system, a part of the Outer Rim Territories' Tunka sector. It was the homeworld of the sentient humanoid species known as the Yatir.

properties.name: Abyss
properties.description: Abyss was a binary star with Byss in the Byss and Abyss system of the Outer Rim. The planet Byss orbited the star in a unique figure-eight pattern.

properties.name: Ac'fren
properties.description: The Ac'fren system was a star system located in the Calaron sector of the Outer Rim Territories and the Slice regions. It shared its name with the Ac'fren Spur hyperlane.

properties.name: Achillea
properties.description: Achillea was a planet that was located within the Cadriaan Province of the Tapani sector. It was a tradeworld on the Shapani Bypass hyperspace route and was one of House Cadriaan's primary worlds.

properties.name: Adamastor
properties.description: Adamastor was a aquatic planet located in the Core Worlds of the galaxy. It was inhabited by Humans such as Tolum Harous.

properties.name: Adana
properties.description: Adana was a planet located in the Deep Core. It was the homeworld of the Faust species.

properties.name: Adari
properties.description: Adari was a mountainous, volcanic planet located in the Inner Rim's Adari sector. It was the homeworld of the sentient Adarians, although archaeologists believed evidence pointed to the species not being native to the planet. The earliest Adarians on Adari spread outward from a single region of the planet, already having a single shared culture by the time.

properties.name: Adarlon
properties.poi: Adarlon spaceport, Glow Dome, Natalar mountain range,
properties.description: Adarlon was a planet in the Minos Cluster. Colonized in 250 BBY and located on the Rimma Trade Route, it attracted many tourists, and was known for its music and holographic entertainment.

properties.name: Adikaria
properties.description: Adikaria was a water planet located in the Core Worlds of the galaxy.

properties.name: Adim
properties.description: Adim was a terrestrial planet located in the Adim system, a part of the Inner Rim's Adari sector. It was the site of a town that functioned as a mining colony.

properties.name: Adin
properties.description: Adin was a planet in the Expansion Region, located on the Corsin Run of the Hydian Way. Few in the galactic community trusted the bureaucrats that the planets put in power. With the election of Senator Meido to the New Republic Senate thirteen years after the Battle of Endor, the planets dealings were closely watched by former Chief of State Leia Organa Solo.

properties.name: Adner
properties.poi: Casinos, The Red Lisken, Pleasure houses, Theme parks, Steris-houses,
properties.description: Adner was a planet located in the Expansion Region's Yataga sector. It had two suns and was a hot world with cold, arid nights. Adner was the homeworld of the sentient Adnerem species. The base unit of the Adnerem society was the steris, a relatively small group of genetically-unbounded individuals.

properties.name: Adoris
properties.description: Adoris was a terrestrial astronomical object located in the Adoris system of the Senex sector, a part of the Senex-Juvex region in the Western Reaches portion of the Mid Rim. A hyperlane linked it to the Caltinia and Knores systems. It was home to the tooka, a species of felines also referred to as "Adoris Felines" that were famous throughout the galaxy.

properties.name: Adras
properties.description: Adras was a Galactic Empire–held world located in the Outer Rim Territories' Seswenna sector. Shortly before the Battle of Endor, a team of Sullustan Alliance Intelligence officers was tasked with meeting another group of Rebel Alliance agents in order to lead a group of combat starships to join the main Rebel Fleet.

properties.name: Aduba
properties.description: Aduba was an astronomical object located in the galaxy's Outer Rim Territories way out on the edge of Wild Space, positioned at the coordinates U-11 of the Standard Galactic Grid. It was the homeworld of Cobalt Hammer pilot Finch Dallow. Dallow flew crop-dusters and spotter rigs on Aduba before qualifying for a post in the New Republic Scout Service.

properties.name: Adumar
properties.description: Adumar was a temperate planet located near the Coreward edge of Wild Space first settled by Humans in the Ductavis Era. The settlers, who had been exiled from the Republic, lived in isolation for years, and developed into several nations that spread across the world. Their culture became obsessed with the arts of blastsword fighting and starfighter combat, to the point where skilled swordsmen and pilots were highly revered. Their society also made considerable use of formal duels as means for settling disputes or even just for entertainment, and also had a rigid social hierarchy.

properties.name: Aefao
properties.description: Aefao was the Aefan homeworld, located in the Aefao system. A remote planet, it was on the other side of the galaxy from Nar Shaddaa.

properties.name: Aeneid
properties.description: Aeneid was an astronomical object located in the Kessel sector of the galaxy's Outer Rim Territories.

properties.name: Aesolian
properties.description: Aesolian was a planet located within the Aesolian system, a part of the galaxy's Wild Space region. It was the homeworld of bulky creatures known as tretons. They had pointed ears and were capable of emitting fierce snarls.

properties.name: Aestilan
properties.description: Aestilan was a world located in the Demetras sector of the Outer Rim Territories. Following the Battle of Yavin, the world was scouted by Rebel Alliance forces seeking for a new base. Aestilan was known for its rock worms making the planetary mantle very fragile.

properties.name: Aeten
properties.description: Aeten II, also simply known as Aeten, was a volcanically turbulent planet located in Wild Space. A terrestrial planet, Aeten II held the second orbital position in its star system, and was positioned at the coordinates J-6 on the Standard Galactic Grid. It was known for its rare stygium crystals, a type of crystal that could power a starship's stealth systems.

properties.name: Affa
properties.description: Affa was a heavily mechanized planet located in the Affa system of the galaxy's Inner Rim and Trailing Sectors.

properties.name: Affavan
properties.description: Affavan was a smoggy Hutt Space gambling world that lay on the Hollastin Run hyperlane. During the Kymoodon Era, it was the site of a retaliatory attack by the Belasco Free Volunteers militia on the Utoradii clan of the Hutt species after the latter's forces attempted a raid on the planet Parcovey Minor. Millennia later, Affavan was featured in the holodrama series True Tales of the Ancient Republic, which depicted a fictionalized version of the raid and its aftermath.

properties.name: Agamar
properties.poi: Council Center, Tondatha, University of Agamar,
properties.description: Agamar was an agriworld in the Mirgoshir system of the Lahara sector. At one time part of the Rakatan Infinite Empire and home to an underwater civilization, Agamar became part of the Galactic Republic prior to the New Sith Wars and later joined the Confederacy of Independent Systems shortly before the Clone Wars. The site of fighting between Republic and Separatist forces, it was once more in Republic hands by the end of the Clone Wars, and subsequently became part of the Galactic Empire. Resistance to Imperial rule led to the destruction of the small town of Tondatha as punishment, after which the Agamar Resistance joined the Alliance to Restore the Republic. Agamar, however, remained in Imperial hands for several more years, before eventually joining the New Republic. During the early stages of the Yuuzhan Vong War, Agamar took in refugees from worlds hit by the Yuuzhan Vong, but eventually fell to the invaders. By the Second Galactic Civil War, the world was once more under Imperial control, and remained part of the Fel Empire in the following decades. During the Second Imperial Civil War, Agamar was part of deposed Emperor Roan Fel's Empire-in-exile and served as the site of a meeting between Fel and the Jedi Council.

properties.name: Agash
properties.description: Agash was a red giant and the Agash system's primary star, it was orbited by a lone planet, Ergeshui.

properties.name: Agomar
properties.description: Agomar was a planet in the Agomar system of the Seswenna sector. During the Battle of Agomar, the Confederacy of Independent Systems pitted its Droid Army against the Grand Army of the Republic, with the world eventually falling back onto Republic control. Whaladons were found on the planet during the Clone Wars.

properties.name: Agon
properties.description: Agon was an individual who lived on the planet Ridlay during the time of the Clone Wars. In one of the planet's total eclipses—which occurred every fifty years, bringing with it the appearance of beings that Ridlay's inhabitants believed to be ghosts—the beings instead attacked the inhabitants, driving them from their homes. After Jedi Master Mace Windu and a group of Galactic Republic clone troopers were dispatched to investigate the subsequent lack of communications on Ridlay, Agon was sent to warn them. Shortly after Agon's arrival, the supposed ghosts arrived, and Agon led Windu and the clones to the shelter where the displaced residents were hiding.

properties.name: Agora
properties.description: Agora was a planet in the Agora system that was located within Sluis sector of the Outer Rim of the galaxy. Remaining loyal to the Republic for centuries, the Sluis sector quickly allied with the Confederacy of Independent Systems during the Clone Wars. Not wishing to lose the territory, the Freedom's Sons, led by Zozridor Slayke attempted to hold the planet, yet it fell to forces of the Separatists about the same time as the Battle of Cerea.

properties.name: Agridorn
properties.description: Agridorn was a planet in the Agridorn system of the Colonies region. During the latter days of the Galactic Republic, Agridorn was represented in the Senate by Rhya Taloon, who pledge her world's support to the Republic at the start of the Clone Wars. When the Republic was transformed into the Galactic Empire, Senator Taloon fled into the depth of Coruscant to avoid assassination. Despite her efforts she was discovered to be a member of the Erased and was executed by stormtroopers.

properties.name: Agriworld-2079
properties.description: Agriworld-2079 in the Mid Rim was the homeworld of the Skrilling species. Agriworld-2079 was a M'shinni designation, as was Skrilling. The original names of the Skrilling people and of their homeworld were lost to history.

properties.name: Ahakista
properties.description: Ahakista was a pleasure planet located in the Myto sector of the Outer Rim Territories.

properties.name: Aida
properties.description: Aida was the sparsely-populated primary planet in the Aida system, near Lomabu III on the Mid Rim. Under the Galactic Empire, the world would be overseen by Imperial Governor Io Desnand during the Galactic Civil War. When the Wookiee Chenlambec arrived on Aida requesting help from his fellow Wookiees to trap the bounty hunter Bossk, they quickly assisted in leading him to the Lomabu system.

properties.name: Aikhibba
properties.description: Aikhibba was a Mid Rim planet in the Aikhibba system; a minor stopping point off the Gamor Run.

properties.name: Ailon
properties.description: Ailon was a heavily-fortified planet in the Ailon system of the Inner Rim.

properties.name: Aiquin
properties.description: Aiquin was a planet located in the Aiquin system, which was found in the Airam sector of the Outer Rim. During the Galactic Civil War, the Rebel Alliance staged an attack in the system to capture clan leader Ilay, who was attempting a peace settlement with the Empire that would cost the Alliance the planet. When the Rebels succeeded in capturing the clan leader, they were able to repel Imperial forces at Nocto and fortify the sector.

properties.name: Akrit'tar
properties.description: Akrit'tar was an inhospitable, barren and lifeless world of the Calaron sector of the Outer Rim Territories. An Imperial prison was established on the world for the safe keeping of political enemies of the Empire. Of the many residents of Akrit'tar's prisons one of Han Solo's former smuggling associates, Tregga, was sentenced to a life of hard labor after being caught with a smuggled cargo of chak-root. Rogue Squadron pilot Tycho Celchu was also held here after a failed attempt at "brainwashing," on the Lusankya, escaping three months later.

properties.name: Akuria
properties.description: Akuria was an astronomical object located in the galaxy's Outer Rim Territories, not far from the planet Dantooine, that was a suspected base of rebel operations. Akuria and several other locations were identified in a 3 ABY Imperial Security Bureau report that generated targets for Viper probe droid surveys by cross-referencing areas with a high degree of suspicious activity with the unsettled parts of the galaxy favored by the rebels.

properties.name: Alabash
properties.description: Alabash was a planet on the edge of the Fakir sector. Located in the Alabash system, it was a volcanic planet.

properties.name: Alakatha
properties.description: Alakatha was the primary moon of K'vath 5 in the K'vath system. It was a popular resort world for Coruscanti elite, with two semi-tropical continents. The moon was described as colored green and white from space, most likely due to plant life and cloud cover. The resort coast was located on Alakatha's northern continent.

properties.name: Alashan
properties.description: Alashan was a planet located on the fringe of the Outer Rim Territories; an area of the galaxy known as Wild Space.

properties.name: Alaspin
properties.description: Alaspin was a planet located in the Suolriep sector of the Outer Rim Territories.

properties.name: Alassa Major
properties.description: Alassa Major was a resort world located along the Enarc Run, known as a major tourist destination for people dwelling in the wealthy core regions.

properties.name: Alba
properties.description: Alba-16 was an Outer Rim planet located in the Belsmuth sector.

properties.name: Albecus
properties.description: Albecus was a planet in the Galactic Core friendly to the Jedi Order during the last years of the Galactic Republic. It was situated close to the world Ralltiir. The planet saw the establishment of a Rebel Alliance safe-house after the Battle of Yavin. The criminal Kikow tried and failed to set up an underworld empire on Albecus during the Galactic Civil War.

properties.name: Albrae-Don
properties.description: Albrae-Don was a terrestrial astronomical object located in the Albrae-Don system, a part of the Sern sector in the Southern Core portion of the Colonies. Its surface featured a sea. The Pica Rim Pipeline, an underwater monorail train transit tunnel more than 4,000 kilometers in length, was located on Albrae-Don, as was the settlement of Draeo-Kax.

properties.name: Alchenaut
properties.description: Alchenaut was a terrestrial moon that was located in the Alchenaut system of the Alchenaut sector, within the Expansion Region portion of the Western Reaches. The moon had a rich ecosystem that provided a habitat for numerous non-sentient herbivorous species, as well as at least one predator. Among the former were the o'cerrys, which cooperated with thousands of other herbivores by warning them whenever a predator approached.

properties.name: Alderaan
properties.poi: Modern:The Graveyard, Historic:Aldera Royal Palace, Apalis Coast, Castle LandsGlarus Valley, Juran Mountains, Kaamos Territory, King's Pass, Museum of Antiquities, Petrified Mounds of the Killiks, University of Alderaan
properties.description: Alderaan, located in the Core Worlds, was the second planet in the Alderaan system and the home of many famous heroes, including Leia Organa Solo, Bail Organa, and Ulic Qel-Droma. Renowned galaxy-wide for their planet's unspoiled beauty, refined culture, and commitment to peace, Alderaanians worked with and around the land to preserve as much of the natural surroundings as they could.

properties.name: Alderath
properties.description: Alderath was a planet in the Mid Rim's Alderath system. During the Galactic Civil War, the Alderath Horticultural Society was robbed of their prized Millennium blossom by a crimelord.

properties.name: Alderbathe
properties.description: Alderbathe was a Mid Rim planet, located in the Alderbathe system of the Churnis sector.

properties.name: Aldereen
properties.description: The Aldereen system was located within the Trailing Sectors portion of the Inner Rim. The system was home to the Aldereenian sentient species.

properties.name: Aldin
properties.description: Aldin was a planet in the galaxy. Jedi Masters Mace Windu and Kit Fisto once had an unpleasant, dangerous experience on one of its moons, which they later recollected during the Battle of Juma 9. It was in the Aldin system.

properties.name: Aldivy
properties.description: Aldivy was an Outer Rim Territories backwater agriworld.

properties.name: Aldraig
properties.description: Aldraig was an astronomical object in the Alderaan sector of the Core Worlds. During the early rebellion against the Galactic Empire, Senator Bail Organa of the Imperial Senate attempted to cover up the theft of a UT-60D transport shipment by having an Aldraig data clerk mistakenly route a shipment of U-wings to Coruscant through Baylagon.

properties.name: Alee
properties.description: Alee was a primarily agricultural world located in the Alee system, a part of Hutt Space in the Slice. It was situated on the Ilosian Spur hyperlane, which connected it to the Tal Nami system as well as the Boz Pity system in the Mid Rim.

properties.name: Aleen
properties.poi: Jedi chapter house, Aleen mainframe station, Aleen Underworld, Great Seal,
properties.description: Aleen was a planet located in the Mid Rim that contained two unique environs: the surface world inhabited by the Aleena and the Underworld, the domain of the Kindalo.

properties.name: Aleen Minor
properties.description: Aleen Minor, often inaccurately referred to as just Aleen, was a temperate planet located in the Inner Rim Territories. A colony world of the Aleena species, Aleen Minor was often mistaken as the species' homeworld.

properties.name: Aleron
properties.description: Aleron was a smog-covered planet in Tapani sector's Freeworlds Territory. It had domed canyon cities and underground cities. Its crust and mantle were rich in valuable minerals and ores. Discovered during the Twelve Kingdoms Era of the Tapani Empire, the world was colonized by Humans from Gilliana. Aleron was the headquarters of Aleron Trade Cooperative, Macander Heavy Ores, and LIN Corporation. With their hold of three major corporations, Aleron was given a voting member of the League of Tapani Freeworlds.

properties.name: Alfestril
properties.description: The Alfestril system was a star system located within the Inner Rim region of the galaxy.

properties.name: Algara
properties.description: Algara II, also referred to simply as Algara and Algar was a planet in the Algaran system of the Lambda sector, located in the Mid Rim with a population of approximately 1 billion. It was also the homeworld of the Xan. Algara II was orbited by four moons: Kevron, Omakaton, Radeon and Tallakron.

properties.name: Algarian
properties.description: Algarian was a planet in the Mid Rim's Dufilvian sector. It was raided by the Galactic Empire, which was attempting to defeat all Alliance support on-planet.

properties.name: Algnadesh
properties.description: The Algnadesh system was a star system that was a part of the Rifle Worlds, an area of the Hapes Cluster located within the Inner Rim and the Slice regions. The system was connected to the Wodan system by a hyperlane and shared its name with the Algnadesh Ship Graveyards, a legendary collection of disappeared starships.

properties.name: Algor
properties.description: Algor was a planet in the Algor system of the Tion Cluster famous as a homeworld of pirates, smugglers, and lawyers. The Algorian people were known for their disputatiousness, which became the subject of humor throughout the Tion Cluster. It was the homeworld of Shamus Falconi. Once part of the original Kingdom of Cron, it was absorbed into Xim's Empire before it collapsed in 25,096 BBY, though unlike many worlds in the Tion, the Algorians were not especially proud of their integration into the empire. During the Galactic Civil War, a group of Algor pirates rescued the Wookiee Grasheel and taught him starship engineering. He went on to own a share in the Airlock cantina.

properties.name: Algunnis
properties.description: Algunnis was a binary star located within the Trax sector of the Mid Rim.

properties.name: Alion
properties.description: Ailon was an astronomical object located in the galaxy's Inner Rim.

properties.name: Alis Point
properties.description:
Alis Point was a planet in the Tamarin sector of the Outer Rim Territories of the galaxy and the site of a Rebel base during the Galactic Civil War.
Shortly after the Battle of Yavin, the base had to be evacuated. During the evacuation, Zev Senesca single-handedly held off three TIE/LN starfighters, while the base's unarmed transport fled into hyperspace. Senesca's heroics earned him a spot in the newly founded Rogue Squadron.

properties.name: Alisandor
properties.description: The Alisandor system was a star system located within the Freeworlds Territory region of the Tapani sector, on the Shapani Bypass.

properties.name: Alland
properties.description: Alland was a planet located in the Core Worlds. It was situated on Metellos Trade Route.

properties.name: Allandor
properties.description: The Allandor system was star system located within the Freeworlds Territory border region of the Tapani sector in the Colonies region of the galaxy, and was situated between the Neona and Sheva systems.

properties.name: Allanteen
properties.description: Allanteen VI, also known simply as Allanteen, was an astronomical object in the galaxy's Expansion Region, located on the Corellian Run to the galactic north of Gamor and across the Foless Crossroads from Foless. During the Galactic Civil War it was the site of an Imperial shipyard. Rebel agents located nearby reported to General Airen Cracken about the status of the shipyard.

properties.name: Alliga
properties.description: Alliga was a planet located in the Outer Rim Territories' Phelleem sector. It was the homeworld of the Holwuff species. The sector was represented in the Galactic Senate by Senator Rogwa Wodrata during the Clone Wars. As the Separatist Crisis began to threaten galactic unity, Senator Wodrata pledged loyalty to the Confederacy of Independent Systems at Geonosis, days before the outbreak of the Clone Wars. A member of the Separatist Council, Wodrata allowed General Grievous' droid army to use Alliga as a staging area for the Outer Rim Sieges. Shortly before the Siege of Saleucami, Alliga was host to the Separatist Council as they plotted their war games. When the Confederacy was defeated and the Council executed on Mustafar, the world was turned over to the Galactic Empire.

properties.name: Alluuvia
properties.description: Alluuvia was a planet that was located in the Elrood sector. The mining on the planet conducted by Radell Mining Corporation was overseen by an ecologically-mindful Ithorian.

properties.name: Allyuen
properties.description: Allyuen was a remote mining world in the Allyuen system, located in the Greater Javin of the Outer Rim Territories.

properties.name: Almak
properties.description: Almak was a terrestrial world located in the Almak system, a part of the Mid Rim's Almak sector. It was the homeworld of the sentient Leffingite species and shared its name with the fruit known as the Almakian apple.

properties.name: Almania
properties.poi: Great Dome of the Je'har, Mem'Kabarr,
properties.description: Almania was a cold and windy planet located in the Almanian system. It had three moons, Pydyr, Auyemesh, and Drewwa.

properties.name: Almar
properties.description: Almar was a tropical planet located in the Elrood sector's Almaran system with beaches, marmaw-inhabited oceans, rain forests, and wide plains of orange grasses. The planet was dedicated to the tourist trade and its surface was called Almar Downside. The planet was orbited by a space station known as Almar Upside, which was considered Almar's capital.

properties.name: Almaran
properties.description: Almar was a tropical planet located in the Elrood sector's Almaran system with beaches, marmaw-inhabited oceans, rain forests, and wide plains of orange grasses. The planet was dedicated to the tourist trade and its surface was called Almar Downside. The planet was orbited by a space station known as Almar Upside, which was considered Almar's capital.

properties.name: Almera
properties.description: Almera may refer to one of the following:

properties.name: Aloxor
properties.description: Aloxor was a planet that applied for Galactic Alliance membership in 44 ABY. It missed being the fourteenth planet to submit the request by eighteen and a half standard seconds.

properties.name: Alpheridies
properties.description: Alpheridies was a planet in the Abron system, homeworld of the Alpheridians, and the adopted homeworld of the Miraluka.

properties.name: Alphoresis
properties.description: Alphoresis was a planet located within the Grumani sector in the Outer Rim region of the galaxy.

properties.name: Alsakan
properties.description: Alsakan was an ecumenopolis world in the Alsakan system in the Core Worlds. A Core Founder on the Perlemian Trade Route, Alsakan was an ancient, wealthy world that had been a major political player for centuries, and was responsible for the seventeen Alsakan Conflicts that had been fought with Coruscant over the nature and shape of the early Galactic Republic.

properties.name: Altair
properties.description: Altair 9 was a dark, swampy planet in the Altair system of the Outer Rim Territories.

properties.name: Altarrn
properties.description: Altarrn was a planet located in the Altarrn system within the Glythe sector. It was the homeworld of the rare spidery nightgliders.

properties.name: Altawar
properties.description: Altawar was the homeworld of the Corragut species, located in the Altawar system of the Corellian sector.

properties.name: Althir
properties.description: Althir III, or Althir, was a remote, independent planet in the Althir system that was located outside of the borders of the Galactic Republic. It had a system of rocky planetary rings.

properties.name: Altier
properties.description: Altier was an astronomical object located in the Altier system, a part of the Altier sector in the Slice portion of the Expansion Region.

properties.name: Altora
properties.description: Altora was an Outer Rim Territories planet located in the Dalonbian sector. It had a warm climate in its southern regions, and plains and savannahs on its surface. Those grasslands were home to the reptilian predators known as altagaks. The creatures hunted herd animals kept by the planet's ranchers, causing the latter to post large bounties on altagak hides.

properties.name: Altratonne
properties.description: Altratonne was a planet in the Altratonne system, orbiting the star Altratonne Prime.

properties.name: Altunna
properties.description: Altunna was a planet that was the source of nectar enjoyed by both Gilad Pellaeon and Feena D'Asta.

properties.name: Alurion
properties.description: Alurion was a planet located in the Outer Rim Territories' Raioballo sector. The world was covered in vast tar pits. During the Yuuzhan Vong War, the Raioballo sector lay along the initial invasion path of the Yuuzhan Vong resulting in their conquest of many of the worlds. Cut off from Republic assistance, Alurion sat behind enemy lines until the end of the war.

properties.name: Alvorine
properties.poi: Alvorine Authority Security Office, Alvorine Spaceport, Government Offices,
properties.description: Alvorine was a planet located in the Yminis sector of the Outer Rim Territories.

properties.name: Alzar
properties.description: Alzar was a planet located in the Thanium sector of the Outer Rim Territories. The Alzarian homeworld, the world was devastated during the Stenax Massacres of 4 ABY.

properties.name: Alzoc
properties.description: Alzoc III, also known as Alzoc, was a frozen planet located in the Sujimis sector of the galaxy's Outer Rim Territories that was the homeworld of the Talz species. The world was taken over by the Galactic Empire due to its exploitable mineral wealth. The pilot Praz Fateer was described as being the fastest on Alzoc III by a barker aboard the Frander's Bay space station. The Mandalorian bounty hunter Din Djarin was involved in a job on Alzoc III at some point before 9 ABY.

properties.name: Amaltanna
properties.description: Amaltanna was a rocky planet with at least three suns and one moon located in the Outer Rim Territories' Kanz sector.

properties.name: Amar
properties.description: Amar was the homeworld of the Amaran species in the Amar system.

properties.name: Amarin
properties.description: Amarin was a planet of dense forests in the Amarin system of the Allied Tion sector, and one of the busiest agriworlds of the Tion Cluster.

properties.name: Ambria
properties.poi: Ambrian Wastes, Lake Natth, Tiernvael Mountains, Meditative Canyon, BioTech Industries campus, Military Base,
properties.description: Ambria was a small desert planet in the Ambria system, located in the Stenness Node of the Inner Rim.

properties.name: Amfar
properties.description: Amfar was a aquatic vacation planet located in the Inner Rim.

properties.name: Ammuud
properties.description: Ammuud was a planet in the Corporate Sector's Kumasi system that was governed by seven feudal clans, each of which was descended from one of seven colony ships that departed from Thokos around 10,000 BBY. Although Ammuud was settled as a peaceful religious retreat, the seven clans eventually forgot their nonviolent ways and began millennia of constant warfare that racked the world. Around 100 BBY, the seven clan Mors managed to come together and forge a peace, instituting a new code of law called the Code of Ammuud that greatly regulated the planet's previously chaotic society. After generations of isolation, Ammuud joined galactic community when the Corporate Sector Authority discovered significant mineral resources under the planet's surface, and brokered a deal for mining rights in exchange for modern technology. This led to a rapid transformation of Ammuud's society, although the seven ruling clans continued their rivalries with one another.

properties.name: Amorphiia
properties.description: Amorphiia was a planet located in the Amorphiia system of the Mid Rim of the galaxy. It was the homeworld of the Amorphiians.

properties.name: Amorris
properties.description: Amorris was a small planet in the Amorris system of the Quelii sector, located in the Outer Rim Territories.

properties.name: Ampliquen
properties.description: Ampliquen was a terrestrial planet located in the Outer Rim Territories. Located in the Meridian sector, it was found in one of the Chorios systems known also as Ampliquen.

properties.name: Anantapar
properties.description: Anantapar was a tropical ocean planet located in the Yarith sector on the edge of the Ivax Nebula. Its native species seemed to be evolving around shellfish. At their current stage of evolution, the largest of these species could fit in a Human palm.

properties.name: Anaxes
properties.poi: Anaxes Citadel, , Anaxes Station, Republic Navy War College, Sirpar Hills, , Sirpar Station, Zann Remanufacturing facility,
properties.description: Anaxes was a fortress world located on the Perlemian Trade Route in the Axum system of the Core Worlds. Known as the "Defender of the Core", for millennia it was the site of the Republic Navy's primary fleet base and War College. It was considered the site of naval power, tradition and prestige by both the Galactic Republic and the Galactic Empire. Anaxes shared its sun, Solis Axum, with Selgon, Grastes, Axum, Urfon, Phlors Rex, Phlors Regina, and Ichium.

properties.name: Ancathia
properties.description: The Ancathia system was located in the Albarrio sector, in the New Territories portion of the Outer Rim Territories. It was home to the Ancathian funge-flower plant.

properties.name: Anchoron
properties.description: Anchoron was planet in the Anchoron system of the Mayagil sector. The Human Anchoroni were known for their flowery speech, genteel decorum, and politeness.

properties.name: Andalia
properties.description: The Andalia system was located in the Lorelli Reach, an area of the Hapes Cluster in the Slice portion of the Inner Rim. It was connected by the hyperlane known as the Lorell Route to the Lorell and Sennex systems. The Andalia system was the origin point of the article of clothing known as the Andalian cloak.

properties.name: Andara
properties.description: Andara was the largest planet in the Andaran system, a star system in the Core Worlds.

properties.name: Andasala
properties.description: Andasala was a mining world, located on the Llanic Spice Run in the Andasala system near Svivren.

properties.name: Ando
properties.description: Ando was an oceanic planet located in the Ando system of the Mid Rim. It was also the homeworld of the Aqualish species.

properties.name: Andooweel
properties.description: Andooweel was an Outer Rim planet in the Andooweel system of the Arkanis sector, located on the Triellus Trade Route.

properties.name: Andosha
properties.description: Andosha may refer to one of the following:

properties.name: Anduvia
properties.description: The Anduvia system was located in the Immalia sector. It was a part of the Expansion Region, being located both in the Outer Expansion Zone sub-region and the Northern Dependencies portion of that region. A hyperlane connected the system to the Immalia and Vorian systems.

properties.name: Anemcoro
properties.description: Anemcoro was a colony world located in the Anemcoro system of the Outer Rim Territories' Albarrio sector.

properties.name: Anga
properties.description: Anga was the communications officer for the Bail Organa under Garm Bel Iblis. In 27 ABY, she served under his command during the fall of Coruscant and was ordered by him to tell Fleet Command that he would not withdraw.

properties.name: Angeria
properties.description: The Angeria system was located in the Venaarian sector, in the Trans-Hydian portion of the Mid Rim. It was the origin point of the beverage known as the Angerian Fishak Surprise.

properties.name: Angor
properties.description: The Angor system was situated in close proximity to the planet Dantooine in the Outer Rim Territories and the Sinsang system.

properties.name: Angratha
properties.description: Angratha was a Mid Rim planet located in the Senex sector.

properties.name: Anic
properties.description: Anic was a planet in the Anic system in the Mid Rim. Anic was the site of the Lijarak Mines, where Alliance to Restore the Republic operative Larq Thur was killed during the Lijarak Mines Incident sometime prior to 2 ABY.

properties.name: Ank Ki'Shor
properties.description: Ank Ki'Shor was a planet in the Indrexu sector of the Outer Rim Territories.

properties.name: Ank Kit'aar
properties.description: Ank Kit'aar was a planet in the Ank Kit'aar system that was located within the Druess sector in the Mid Rim.

properties.name: Ankori
properties.description: Ankori may refer to one of the following:

properties.name: Ankus
properties.description: Ankus was a planet on the borders of the Mid Rim near the Unknown Regions.

properties.name: Annaj
properties.description: Annaj, known as Cannij Barr by the Ayrou, was a planet in the Inner Zuma Region and the capital of the Moddell sector.

properties.name: Annamar
properties.description: Annamar was a planetoid with a breathable atmosphere located within a vast asteroid field.

properties.name: Annoo
properties.description: Annoo was an Outer Rim planet located in the Tharin sector. The homeworld of the original Annoo-dat species, they were referred to by xenobiologists as Annoo-dat Prime.

properties.name: Anoat
properties.description: Anoat was one of three habitable planets in the Anoat system of the Anoat sector, located in the Greater Javin of the Outer Rim. It was located between the Hoth system and the Bespin system.

properties.name: Anobis
properties.description: Anobis was a terrestrial planet located into the Anobis system of the Bright Jewel sector in the Mid Rim Territories. It was located near Ord Mantell and was primarily known as an agriworld and a mining colony, providing major foodstuffs to the nearby and more distant star systems.

properties.name: Anoth
properties.description: Anoth was a planet located in Wild Space. The world was shattered at some point during an unknown cataclysm, but remained largely together due to its gravitational pull.

properties.name: Ansarra
properties.description: Ansarra can refer to:

properties.name: Ansata
properties.description: The Ansata were from the Ansata system located in the Core Worlds. They had particular symbols indicating devotion to knowledge and learning. Jocasta Nu, a Jedi Master and Jedi archivist for the Jedi Order, wore robes with traditional Ansata patterns, and Ansata hair sticks, indicating her personal devotion to these qualities. Atris was known to wear similar symbols on her robes.

properties.name: Ansek
properties.description: Ansek was a planet in the Mid Rim's Ansek system.

properties.name: Ansillivog
properties.description: Ansillivog was a planet in the Ansillivog system of the Expansion Region.

properties.name: Ansion
properties.poi: Awiquod, Delgerhan, Jaaruls Street, Kander Region, Niruu Plaatlas41u, Songoquin Street, Sorr-ul-Paan Plaatlas41u, Valley of the Borokii,
properties.description: Ansion was a planet in the Mid Rim near Vortex and Bilbringi, located on the Namadii Corridor.

properties.name: Anstares
properties.description: Anstares may refer to one of the following:

properties.name: Antamont
properties.description: Antamont was a nonindustrial, mountainous planet in the Antamont system of the Meridian sector.

properties.name: Antar
properties.description: Antar was a gas giant in the Prindaar system, surrounded by six moons, four of which supported life.

properties.name: Antares
properties.description: Antares can refer to:

properties.name: Anteevy
properties.poi: Imperial Robotics Construction Facility Ice Station Beta,
properties.description: Anteevy was a frigid ice world locked in a perpetual winter. Located in the Mid Rim's Esuain sector, the planet orbited a star in the Anteevy system.

properties.name: Antemeridias
properties.description: Antemeridias was the capital of the Antemeridian sector. Located in the Outer Rim Territories, it was located along the Perlemian Trade Route.

properties.name: Anthus
properties.description: Anthus was a planet in the Brema sector of the Outer Rim.

properties.name: Antipose
properties.poi: Antipose Arena, Landing field, Raskar's villa,
properties.description: Antipose was an Outer Rim Territories planet located in the Centrality sector. It had a single city where the former pirate Raskar set up a system of gladiatorial contests that had a power gem, a rare artifact that Raskar had in his possession, as their ultimate prize. In 0 ABY, the smugglers Han Solo and Chewbacca were tasked by the Rebel Alliance with obtaining a power gem for its disabling effect on starship deflector shields. The pair traveled to the Junkfort Station shadowport to acquire leads, and an agent of Raskar's pointed them to Antipose.

properties.name: Antiquity
properties.poi: Karren spaceport, South Mudflats, Twin Scales,
properties.description: Antiquity was a Mid Rim planet located in the Senex sector.

properties.name: Anto's Star
properties.description: The Sable III, originally known as the Anto's Star, was a modified Corellian CR90 corvette used by the flamboyant pirate Drek Drednar and his crew. The ship was stolen by a group of starship thieves working for Drednar who was planning a mutiny against Captain Karn Granzor.

properties.name: Anturus
properties.description: Anturus was a planet located in the Anturus system of the Senex sector, in the Mid Rim of the galaxy. It was the homeworld of House Picutorion.

properties.name: Anx Minor
properties.description: Anx Minor was an astronomical object located in the Anx Minor system, a part of the Raioballo sector in the New Territories portion of the Outer Rim Territories. It was situated on the hyperlane known as the Veragi Trade Route, which connected it to the Sinsang system as well as the Ord Trasi system in the Relgim sector. Another hyperspace route connected Anx Minor to Gravlex Med, the homeworld of the sentient Anx species that at one point colonized neighboring star systems in the Anx Space region.

properties.name: Anzat
properties.poi: Anzat Spaceport, Maggot's Cantina, Sea of Memory,
properties.description: Anzat was a legendary Mid Rim world located near the Perlemian Trade Route.

properties.name: Apatros
properties.poi: Outer Rim Oreworks Company cortosis mines,
properties.description: Apatros was a desolate world in the Apatros system of the Savareen sector, located in the Outer Rim Territories under the jurisdiction of the Galactic Republic. As of 1003 BBY, Apatros fell under the direct control of the Outer Rim Oreworks Company, which maintained a cortosis mine on the planet. Apatros was notable for being the homeworld of Darth Bane, the Dark Lord of the Sith who worked in the cortosis mines for ten years before joining the Sith army during the New Sith Wars.

properties.name: Aphran
properties.description: Aphran was the Aphran system's primary. On Aphran IV, Aphran appeared as a red-gold orb during sunset, making its green-blue lakes appear as brilliant gold.

properties.name: Aplooine
properties.description: Aplooine was a planet located in the Aplooine system along the Duros Space Run in the Grumani sector of the galaxy.

properties.name: Aquaris
properties.description: Aquaris was an inhabited aquatic planet located in the Cvetaen system of the Expansion Region's Sumitra sector. Devoid of any landmasses, the planet was one large ocean.

properties.name: Aquella
properties.description: Aquella was a Mid Rim world located in the Senex sector. By 3643 BBY, an aristocrat residing on Aquella offered valuable items as dowry to anyone who would marry his cousin. Aquella was colonized by Human settlers at one point; however, the colony was lost by the time the Senex-Juvex region came under the rule of the aristocratic Ancient Houses. The Aquellans, the descendants of the original colonists, were a culture notable for their rituals involving the dyeing and tattooing of young males' bodies.

properties.name: Aquilae
properties.description: Aquilae, or Aguilae, could refer to several things:

properties.name: Aquilaris
properties.poi: Aquilaris Classic course, Aquilaris Grand Arena, Bumpy's Breakers, Sunken City course,
properties.description: Aquilaris was an aquatic planet located in the Sanbra sector of the Outer Rim Territories. Once a flourishing resort world, the planet's economy largely revolved around podracing events by the time of the end of the Golden Age of the Galactic Republic.

properties.name: Aquilaris Minor
properties.description: Aquilaris Minor, or simply Aquilaris, was a planet in the Grumani sector of the Outer Rim.

properties.name: Arabanth
properties.description: Arabanth was a planet in the Interior Region of the Hapes Cluster.

properties.name: Aradia
properties.description: The Aradia system was located in the Negs portion of the Core Worlds. It was the origin point of the Aradian pulse-lifter anti-gravity technology.

properties.name: Aralia
properties.description: Aralia was a tiny, semi-tropical world located in the Andron system of the Outer Rim's Antemeridian sector.

properties.name: Aramand
properties.description: Aramand was the yellow primary star of the Aramand system.

properties.name: Arami
properties.description: Arami was an Outer Rim Territories planet located in the Galov sector. A part of the area dominated by the Hutt species as well as controlled by the Galactic Empire, Arami was one of three worlds where the Hutt holiday known as Boonta's Eve was celebrated, with the festivities including the Boonta Races.

properties.name: Arapia
properties.description: Arapia was the Kadri'Ra adoptive homeworld. It was located in the Arapia system.

properties.name: Arat Fraca
properties.description: Arat Fraca was a planet located in the Arat Fraca system of the Colonies. The Star Morning suddenly reappeared over Arat Fraca a year after leaving Motexx for Gowdawl. Arat Fraca was two sectors away from Motexx. From Arat Fraca, the Star Morning proceeded to Darepp, where it landed.

properties.name: Arbra
properties.description: Arbra was a densely forested planet that became the headquarters of the Rebel Alliance after the evacuation of Golrath Station, around 3 ABY. Home to the lagomorphic Hoojibs, Arbra was once inhabited by an ancient race who had resided in subterranean cities.

properties.name: Arbular
properties.description: Arbular was a planet located in the Lambda sector of the Mid Rim.

properties.name: Arcan
properties.poi: Arcan IV SpaceportLemo and Sanda's den
properties.description: Arcan IV, sometimes known simply as Arcan, was a planet located within the Tion Cluster of the Outer Rim Territories.

properties.name: Arcanum
properties.description: The Arcanum was a space station that was commissioned by the Sith Emperor for the purpose of holding dangerous Sith artifacts possessed by the reconstituted Sith Empire.

properties.name: Archae Teuthis
properties.description: Archae Teuthis was the Sulituan homeworld. It was covered in deep oceans and the Sulituans lived in large float-cities built of phrnnoc, a type of coral.

properties.name: Archais
properties.description: Archais was a planet in the Interior Region of the Hapes Cluster. Sometime before 2 ABY, Imperial lieutenant colonel Freja Covell and the Assassin's Guild fought three Rebel SpecForces units in the oriental seas of Archais during the battle of Archais. It was believed to be the site of mythical mountain peaks that were very high. On occasion, reference was made to these peaks as a form of hyperbole, such as the suggestion that if Moff Bandor's ambition were height, it would tower over the peaks.

properties.name: Arcopola
properties.description: Arcopola was a planet in the same star system as Gambolla, in the Spadja sector of the Outer Rim Territories.

properties.name: Arcura
properties.description: Arcura was an Imperial world in the Arcura system. Reina Gale once sought to pull a con job on the planet, but was hindered by AT-ATs.

properties.name: Arda
properties.description: Arda was an astronomical object located in the Gordian Reach of the regions known as the Outer Rim Territories and New Territories. The celestial body was situated in grid square Q-6 on the Standard Galactic Grid.

properties.name: Ardru
properties.description: Ardru was a planet located in the Iseno sector of the Inner Rim.

properties.name: Argai
properties.description: Argai was a planet located in the Cronese Mandate of the Outer Rim. It was best known for having been the homeworld of the ancient pre-Republic conqueror Xim the Despot, and the first capital of his empire.

properties.name: Argai Minor
properties.description: Argai Minor, also known as Argai, was a planet in the Colonies region of the galaxy.

properties.name: Argavat
properties.description: Argavat was a planet within the Argavat system, in the Colonies region of the galaxy.

properties.name: Argazda
properties.description: Argazda was the Argazdan homeworld. Around the time of the Mandalorian Wars, local Provisional Governor Myrial and her followers the Myrialites rebelled against the Republic, establishing the Argazdan Redoubt. They conquered neighboring worlds throughout the Kanz sector, including Lorrd. These events were known as the Kanz Disorders, lasting from 3970 BBY–3670 BBY. This conflict resulted in the deaths of more than five billion until combined Republic/Jedi efforts under Lorrdian Jedi Master Mari-Elan Nora overthrew the Argazdan Rebout.

properties.name: Newland
properties.description: Newland was a human male in the Galactic Empire. During the Galactic Civil War, he held the rank of major and served at the Battle of Endor in 4 ABY, where he served in an All Terrain Scout Transport with Lieutenant Blanaid.

properties.name: Argovia
properties.description: Argovia was a planet of stormy, misty, marshy wetlands in the Endocray sector, rich in minerals and ores. It was the location of an Imperial sensor network complex that analyzed data from thousands of sensor buoys, ships, and probe droids in the sector. To protect both the sensor complex and the valuable ore, the mining companies and the Empire mutually restricted any non-personnel from immigrating to the planet.

properties.name: Argul
properties.description: Argul was a planet located in the Mid Rim along the Corellian Trade Spine, near to Cerea and Belsavis.

properties.name: Argus
properties.description: Argus was a Human-inhabited planet in the Argus system. When the New Order was instituted, Argus's Celestial School of Spaceflight Engineering was closed down. At least one of the school's professors, Maggis, became a teacher at the Imperial Naval Academy on Imperial Center, rather than be blacklisted from ever teaching again.

properties.name: Ariarch-17
properties.description: Ariarch-17 was a sun that had gone nova during the Galactic Republic's reign. The cruise ship Stardust made a special trip to witness the nova, though the captain miscalculated the force of the nova, resulting in the death of many of his passengers.

properties.name: Aridka
properties.description: Aridka was a rocky planet that served as a battleground between Galactic Republic and Separatist forces during the Clone Wars. The planet was covered in abandoned cities, which were surrounded by cliffs and the ruins of temples and obelisks. At least two types of flora grew on the planet, in the crevices of the cliffs as well as in the city.

properties.name: Aridus
properties.description: Aridus was a desert planet in the Expansion Region and the homeworld of the reptilian Chubbit species.

properties.name: Aris
properties.description: Aris was a planet in the Albarrio system of the Albarrio sector of the Outer Rim Territories. It was a world of rainforests, and home to the monkey-like scavenger known as the Wok-Wok. It served as the sector capital of the Albarrio sector, and was a stop along the Relgim Run. It had no native intelligent life, but had been colonized.

properties.name: Arkania
properties.poi: Arca Jeth's praxeum, Veeshas Tuwan, Adascopolis Financial Exchange, Arkania CommandDiamond mines,
properties.description: Arkania was the adopted homeworld of the Arkanian species. It was covered with tundra and rich in diamonds and other precious minerals, which the Arkanians mined to further their offworld connections and master their technology. Arkanian cities were designed to keep the cold out and were mostly completely enclosed. Off-world visitors rarely had to deal with the frigid conditions of the planet. Many citizens were miners.

properties.name: Arkanis
properties.description: Arkanis was the sector capital of the Arkanis sector. It was inhabited by Humans such as Devon Fuller. It was the throneworld of the Arkanis Regency, which included the ancient Empress Teeda. The planet was part of the Galactic Empire. It was the location of Vensenor Flight Academy.

properties.name: Arkinnea
properties.description: Arkinnea was a planet that was located in the Axion sector in the Expansion Region of space. The planet suffered at the hands of the Separatists and at the end of the Clone Wars, it was overrun with refugees. The local militia was very hostile to refugees, in particular to those that might affiliated with the CIS. Despite promises to said refugees to offer them land on Arkinnea to start their lives anew, the militia systematically murdered many refugees by loading them onto ships, then dumping them out hundreds of feet in the air to their deaths.

properties.name: Arkuda
properties.description: Arkuda was a small rocky planet in the Gordian Reach inhabited by the Arkudans. The planet was renowned for its nighttime view of the stars, due to its proximity to the Roil, a large stellar nursery in the Reach. Arkuda was also one endpoint to the Korphir Trace which pushed through the Roil.

properties.name: Arleen
properties.description: Arleen was the callsign of a pleasure yacht that once traveled from Antipose IX piloted by a Class Five pilot droid.

properties.name: Armath
properties.description: Armath was a small planet in the Armath system of the Expansion Region and its agriculture provided the economy. Passing space travelers usually landed there to restore their stocks of food and fuel. Ambassador Zell of Majoor went on a diplomatic mission to Armath.

properties.name: Arnot Station
properties.description: Arnot Station was a commercial space platform frequented by merchants operating small and medium freighters, along with some local shipping lines, during the Galactic Civil War.

properties.name: Arorua
properties.description: Arorua was a jungle planet home to fierce natural predators, such as the squollyhawlk, and monsters spawned from Sith sorcery, such as the silan.

properties.name: Arporatal-Lanin
properties.description: Arporatal-Lanin was the planet in the Arporatal-Lanin system and the homeworld of the Arpor-Lan species.

properties.name: Arquata Station
properties.description: Arquata Station can refer to:

properties.name: Arramanx
properties.description: Arramanx was an urban world located in the Arramanx system. It was a part of the Cronese Mandate sector of the Tion Cluster, within the Slice portion of the Outer Rim Territories. Arramanx was situated between the Duinarbulon and Pasmin systems on the Greater Cronese Arc hyperlane, while the hyperspace route known as the Kismaano Bypass linked it to the Gadon system.

properties.name: Arrgaw
properties.poi: Warehouses, Corporate administrative spires, Refineries, Orbital trade rings,
properties.description: Arrgaw was a major trade planet located in the Expansion Region's Kira sector. A world orbited by impressive trade rings and featuring vast expanses on its surface taken up by warehouses and other corporate structures, Arrgaw lay at the intersection of two important hyperlanes, the Hydian Way and the Harrin Trade Corridor.

properties.name: Arrochar
properties.poi: Arrochar Rebel base, Arrochar Royal Palace,
properties.description: Arrochar was a planet on the edges of Hutt Space, located near Mon Calamari and ruled by a traditional monarchy. For long time it remained away from the central politics in the Galaxy, being a recluse planet, as the inhabitants would say, private. Around the time of the Battle of Yavin, the royalty of the planet was eager to enter a "Community of Planets" and saw the Rebellion as a way to fulfill its desires, so, in the first year after the battle, the crown prince of Arrochar offered asylum to the Rebel Alliance, in exchange for Princess Leia Organa's hand in marriage.

properties.name: Arsteni
properties.description: Arsteni is a planet in the Arsteni system.

properties.name: Artesia
properties.description: Artesia was a planet located within the Artesia system, a part of the Hangshan sector in the galactic regions known as the Slice and the Expansion Region. The Artesian space collage art form originated on the planet.

properties.name: Arthon
properties.description: Arthon was a planet located within the Ottega sector of the Mid Rim.

properties.name: Artom
properties.description: Artom was a planet located in the Reidi Artom I system, a part of the Nuon e Safyd sector in the Slice portion of the Expansion Region. Artom was the first discovery of Reidi Artom, a Galactic Republic scout who was dispatched to the Expansion Region to survey any star systems missed by previous explorers.

properties.name: Artorias
properties.poi: Artorian safe haven, Great Sea of Artorias, Artorias communications center,
properties.description: Artorias was a peace-loving Outer Rim planet with few defenses. In 25 ABY, during the onset of the Yuuzhan Vong War, the world was invaded and conquered by the titular race.

properties.name: Artus Prime
properties.description: Artus Prime was a terrestrial planet located in the Artus system of the Kwymar sector in the Outer Rim Territories. The planet primarily served as a mining colony, which was known for its Artusian crystals which could also be used in the construction of lightsabers.

properties.name: Aruza
properties.description: Aruza was a planet orbited by five moons of pale shades of tan, silver, and green. The planet was home to the peaceful Aruzans, an even-tempered society that abhorred violence. By 3 ABY, Aruza had not experienced a murder for over one hundred of their years. They were small people with light blue skin and very dark blue hair.

properties.name: Arzid
properties.description: Arzid was a planet in the Calaron sector of the Outer Rim Territories. It was inhabited by forests of giant macaab mushrooms, tentacle-bushes, and by the dangerous arachnor that feasted on the mushrooms as part of their diet.

properties.name: Asamin
properties.description: Asamin was a planet located in the Asamin system of the Mid Rim. The world was a noted spice production site.

properties.name: Asation
properties.description: Asation was the major port world of the Gree Enclave and was home to the Crafter caste of the Gree.

properties.name: Ashas Ree
properties.description: Ashas Ree was a planet in the Ashas Ree system, a star system deep within the ancient Sith Empire in the Sith Worlds region of the Outer Rim Territories's Esstran sector. Connected to other nearby worlds by Kamat Aegit and the Zorfe Trete, Ashas Ree was considered a lesser world of the Sith Empire.

properties.name: Ashash
properties.description: Ashash was a waterworld located in the Ashash system, a part of the Zarracina sector in the Trailing Sectors portion of the Expansion Region. It was home to a species of creature that could emit a harmful gas from its body—an aspect in which the creature was similar to the stinkfish of the Outer Rim Territories planet Sedri.

properties.name: Ashkas-kov
properties.description: Ashkas-kov was a planet in Shelsha sector. It was situated along a minor trade hyperroute.

properties.name: Ashteri's Cloud
properties.description: Ashteri's Cloud was a vast drift of ionized tuderium gas that floated along one edge of the Kessel sector as of 44 ABY. That year, Ashteri's Cloud was visited by Lando Calrissian and his starship, the Rockhound. There, Calrissian and Jedi Knight Jaina Solo were attacked by a group of Sith pirates looking for starships to capture for their fleet.

properties.name: Askaj
properties.description: Askaj was the home planet of the Askajians in the Outer Rim Territories, far off the Rimma Trade Route. The planet had one moon, the Moon Lady, whom the people worshiped as a deity.

properties.name: Askaria
properties.description: The Askaria system was a star system located in the Askarian sector, a part of the galactic regions known as the Expansion Region and the Slice. It was home to the creatures known as Askarian worms.

properties.name: Asmall
properties.description: Asmall was a world in the Inner Rim. By 7 ABY, the planet was allied with the New Republic, who had established a defense net around the world; the thief Tord Gamb stole information about the net, making him a fugitive wanted by New Republic Intelligence.

properties.name: Asmeru
properties.description: Asmeru was a planet in the Senex sector of the Mid Rim, on the border with the Hadar sector.

properties.name: Asran
properties.description: The Asran system was a star system located in the Brak sector within the Expansion Region of the galaxy. It was a source of high-quality prismatic crystals for Lant Mining Corporation. It contained at least three planets which were sites of LMC mining operations.

properties.name: Asrat
properties.description: Asrat was a planet where the Holy Children of Asrat were worshiped. The Children opposed the New Order and were targeted for assassination by the Galactic Empire. Dengar left service as an Imperial assassin rather than kill the Children.

properties.name: Ast Kikorie
properties.description: Ast Kikorie, also called "Down Below," was a planet in Moddell sector. It was a Galactic Republic astrocartographic research outpost with a ring of orbiting telescopes connected to Kikorie City by a skyhook. The planet was abandoned by the Republic at the onset of the Clone Wars in 22 BBY.

properties.name: Asturias
properties.description: Asturias was a factory moon in the Expansion Region that had been abandoned by the time of the Clone Wars. The nearby sun had turned into a red giant, and its radiation rose to limits too dangerous for prolonged exposure for both biological and mechanical existence. Its sand-covered surface was littered with the decaying hulks of ships and buildings.

properties.name: Asuin
properties.description: Asuin was a frost-covered planet located in Hutt Space that was populated by wampas. Whilst the surface was besieged by icestorms, there were underground caverns filled with lava.

properties.name: Atchorb
properties.description: Atchorb was a world located in the Atchorb system of the Corporate Sector, a part of the Trans-Hydian portion of the Outer Rim Territories. The hyperlane known as the Shaltin Tunnels linked Atchorb to the D'ian and Ulicia systems, while the Authority Guardian Corridor connected it to the Hiit and Tothis systems.

properties.name: Athallia
properties.description: Athallia was an astronomical object located in the Athallia system. It was a part of the Athallia sector, within the Trailing Sectors portion of the Expansion Region. Kalarcha served as Athallia's capital. Athallia shared its name with the courier starship Athallian Messenger.

properties.name: Ather
properties.description: Ather was a manufacturing world located in the Ather system, a part of the Atravis sector in the Western Reaches portion of the Outer Rim Territories. The distance between Ather and the Tamarin sector's Dravian Starport could be traversed in two days using a starship equipped with a Class 1 hyperdrive.

properties.name: Athiss
properties.poi: Excavated tomb, Ruins of Kressh, Tomb of Vodal Kressh,
properties.description: Athiss was the second planet in the Loro Babis system of the Outer Rim Territories. It was located on the Descri Wris and was close to Korriz and Ziost. The planet was a Sith sanctuary that held the sanctuary of Vodal Kressh, a powerful Sith Lord and among the most renowned alchemists the Empire had ever known.

properties.name: Atoa
properties.description: Atoa was a little-known ice planet in the Atoan system, in the Ghost Nebula. It was the homeworld of the near-Human Atoans.

properties.name: Ator
properties.description: Ator was a Core World and an ecumenopolis.

properties.name: Atorra
properties.description: Atorra was a planet located in the Atorra system. It was situated in the Back Reach area of the Gordian Reach sector, within the Trans-Hydian portion of the Outer Rim Territories. The planet was connected by the Ardan Cross hyperlane to the Troos and the Chenowei systems.

properties.name: Atraken
properties.description: Atraken was a doonium rich planet conquered by the Confederacy of Independent Systems. The Galactic Republic tried to liberate it in 22 BBY and were only successful through a series of strikes called Operation Katabatic nearly a year later. The Separatists engaged in a "poisoned well" policy, releasing a biochemical plague into the planet's water table that killed 90% of the population. The survivors mostly relocated to Trilos, if not to other neighboring worlds. Thrynka Padaunete blamed the disaster on the Jedi.

properties.name: Atrakus
properties.description: Atrakus was a planet in the Expansion Region. It was one of many worlds cited by Thrynka Padaunete as having "suffered under the atrocities of the Jedi Knights" during the Clone Wars.

properties.name: Atravis
properties.description: Atravis was an astronomical object located in the regions known as the Outer Rim Territories and the Western Reaches. It was also situated in the grid square L-19 of the Standard Galactic Grid. The super-hyperroute known as the Hydian Way connected Atravis to Rutan and Shumavar. Atravis also shared its name with the Atravis sector, which contained the nearby Mustafar system.

properties.name: Atron
properties.description: Atron was a planet located within the Atron system of the Mid Rim's Senex sector.

properties.name: Attahox
properties.description: Attahox was a world in the Expansion Region near Daalang.

properties.name: Atterol
properties.description: Atterol was a celestial body in the Atterol system. It was near Atterol that the Battle of Atterol took place during the Galactic Civil War.

properties.name: Aturi Cluster
properties.description: The Aturi Cluster was a star cluster within the Hook Nebula.

properties.name: Atzerri
properties.poi: Trader's Plaza, Talos Port Medicomplex, Jabba's Throne Room, Pemblehov District, Freeman Cantina,
properties.description: Atzerri was a tradeworld in the Inner Rim, near the Hydian Way. This planet was a member of the Association of Free Trade Worlds and only had as much government as necessary to stave off total chaos.

properties.name: Aurea
properties.description: Aurea was a planet, located in the Aurea system, well known for its expert artisans, gathered in the Aurean Glassworkers Guild. The skilled glass workers of the planet were known to make objects of outstanding beauty; luxury vessels that were considered nearly priceless. Further, if one of the vessels was broken, they were known to recreate the object with an even greater beauty than before.

properties.name: Aurimaus
properties.description: Aurimaus was an astronomical object located in Wild Space's Aurimaus system. At some point during the Galactic Civil War, the Galactic Empire's Tempest Force unit, which included stormtrooper Hume Tarl, participated in a military operation at Aurimaus.

properties.name: Austan
properties.description: The Austan Asteroid Cluster was an asteroid belt located in the Arkanis sector. It was the site of mining operations and resorts. During the Clone Wars, it was the site of a skirmish between the Galactic Republic and the Confederacy of Independent Systems.

properties.name: Avenelle
properties.description: Avenelle was a planet in the Lantillian sector. It was a luxurious world known as a place to rest while traveling along the Lesser Lantillian Route or for retirement.

properties.name: Averam
properties.description: Averam was a planet in the Seswenna sector in the Outer Rim Territories. It was one of the few planets to openly sympathize with small groups of Rebel Alliance supporters early in the Galactic Civil War.

properties.name: Averill
properties.description: Averill was a mining world in the Averill system where the Galactic Empire discovered a rich quadrenium lode beneath the crust; quadrenium was refined for starship construction. The native Humans were originally divided into autonomous mineclans dwelling in inherited mineholds. After the Empire nationalized the local mining operations, a preventable mining accident crippled Selby Jarrad's father. Selby and her cousin failed to create a resistance cell on the planet, so Selby joined New Republic Intelligence.

properties.name: Avidich
properties.description: Avidich was a planet located in the Avidich system in the Unknown Regions within the core territory of the Chiss Ascendancy. It was located on the Vagaari Corridor, a hyperlane that ran through the Unknown Regions. Avidich was a mountainous world with peaks that were considered impressive. The planet was used by the Chiss species to cultivate edible lichens.

properties.name: Aviles Prime
properties.description: Aviles Prime was a planet located in the Aviles Prime system, within the Hythrope sector of the galaxy's Expansion Region. During the Clone Wars, it was the site of a conference attended by Oviedo Engineering director Lorca Oviedo.

properties.name: AX-456
properties.description: AX-456 was an asteroid in the Barma sector.

properties.name: Axion
properties.description: Axion was a Human colony planet purchased by the Colicoids prior to the Clone Wars. It was then that it became a research and development center for the Confederacy of Independent Systems. The Battle of Axion took place there in 22 BBY, four months after the First Battle of Geonosis. Years later, pirate Reginald Barkbone escaped the Imperial Royal Guards by flying away in the midst of the destruction caused by a limpet mine he had attached to a power droid.

properties.name: Axtria
properties.description: Axtria was a planet located within the Axtria system region of the Core Worlds with an atmosphere toxic to most humanoids.

properties.name: Axxila
properties.description: Axxila was a planet in the D'Astan sector of the Outer Rim Territories.

properties.name: Ayceezee
properties.description: Ayceezee was an inhabited world in the galaxy with rolling walkways and a university as of 44 ABY. Former Wraith Squadron member Voort saBinring retired there as a mathematics professor until re-recruited by Garik Loran in 44 ABY.

properties.name: Aylayl
properties.description: Aylayl was a verdant planet that was located within the Aylayl system of the galaxy's Hutt Space region and lay on the hyperlane called the Hollastin Run, which connected it to the worlds of Hollastin and Tsyk.

properties.name: Azbrian
properties.description:
Azbrian was an agricultural world of sweeping plains and grasslands, dotted with farms that raised the eight-legged herd animals known as dray beasts. One such farm was owned by Condren Foreck, a potential suitor to Lando Calrissian.
It played a minor part in the Yuuzhan Vong War as a base for the New Republic/Galactic Alliance. After the war the Galactic Alliance abandoned the base. It was never a part of the Alliance until after the war. The Prime Minister of the planet decided to join the Alliance, so he sent two senators to Coruscant to the Galactic Alliance Senate. The planet turned out to be valuable during the Second Galactic Civil War.

properties.name: Azna
properties.description: Azna was a planet in the Azna system of the Demetras sector, near Fait d'Fait. It was between Tintel and Fodro on the Dahvil-Fodro Hyperspace Promenade.

properties.name: Aztubek
properties.description: Aztubek was a wealthy but little-developed planet lying along the Corellian Trade Spine in the Javin sector of the Outer Rim Territories. It was originally one of the eleven member worlds of Mugaari Space prior to Galactic Republic intervention, which reshaped the region's power structure.
