Aztubek became home to many corporate complexes, catering to workers who commuted from neighboring Javin, the sector capital.

properties.name: Azure
properties.description: Azure was a diminutive blue Mid Rim world at a non-strategic location where most of the landmass was taken up by a clandestine Galactic Republic facility. The rogue planet was not part of a star system and had no moons nor any useful resources. It was commanded by General Solomahal until conquered by the Separatists during the Clone Wars.

properties.name: Azzameen Station
properties.description: Azzameen Station, also known as Azzameen Home Base, was the space station residence of the Azzameen family and the headquarters for its trading company, Twin Suns Transport Services, during the Galactic Civil War. Located in orbit of a volcanic planet in the Outer Rim Territories, the station hosted a number of amenities for the Azzameens and their company's employees, including a holosimulator and a hangar large enough to store and service several YT-series light freighters, including the family's twin YT-1300s, Sabra and Selu, and their YT-2000 Otana. Azzameen Station's design was unique in the galaxy, with its distinctive semi-circular arms flanking a tall central tower.

properties.name: B-Foroon
properties.description: B-Foroon was a mucky world located in the B-Foroon system, a part of the Arkanis sector in the Slice portion of the Outer Rim Territories. It was situated on the Triellus Trade Route hyperlane, which linked it to the A-Foroon and C-Foroon systems.

properties.name: B'Knos
properties.description: B'Knos was an asteroid mining colony located within the Abran asteroid belt in the Abran system. The system was sometimes called the B'Knos system after this colony.

properties.name: B'nish
properties.description: B'nish was a planet in the galaxy. The Human girl First was held there as a slave until her escape around 41.5 ABY. The B'nishi were native to the world.

properties.name: B'trilla
properties.description: B'trilla was a planet in the Gordian Reach of the Outer Rim.

properties.name: Baarstal
properties.description: Baarstal was an astronomical object that was located within the Baarstal system.

properties.name: Babali
properties.description: Babali was a tropical planet with an Obroan Institute research base headed by Kroddok Stopa until his death on Brath Qella.

properties.name: Babbadod
properties.description: Babbadod was a colony world in the Inner Rim between the planets Darepp and Motexx. It was visited by the passenger liner Star Morning.

properties.name: Bacrana
properties.description: Bacrana was the sector capital of Brak sector at the height of the New Order.

properties.name: Badfellow Station
properties.description: The Badfellow Station was a space station located in the Core Worlds at coordinates M-10.

properties.name: Baes Logia
properties.description: Baes Logia was a planet in the Outer Rim Territories. During the Galactic Civil War, the Galactic Empire and the Rebel Alliance were engaged in a campaign there. The Alliance tried to capture an Imperial general alive on Baes Logia, but the general was killed by the insane Graf Yonna. Tamo Lan served the Alliance on Baes Logia, before serving at Massassi Station.

properties.name: Baffop
properties.description: Baffop was a planet located in the Baffop system, a part of the Tamarin sector in the Outer Rim Territories. In 32 BBY, the Human male Anselm was born on Baffop. At some point before the Battle of Yavin, the forces of the Galactic Empire ravaged Baffop, leading to extensive civilian casualties. After witnessing the devastation of his homeworld, Anselm became a member of the Rebel Alliance, which opposed the Empire. By the time of Imperial Grand Admiral Thrawn's campaign against the New Republic in 9 ABY, Baffop was situated in space either conquered by or allied with Thrawn's confederation.

properties.name: Bajic
properties.description: Bajic could refer to one of the following:

properties.name: Bakisian Drift
properties.description: The Bakisian Drift was a nebulosity located in the Tragan Cluster, a part of the New Territories portion of the Outer Rim Territories. The notoriously perilous Bakisian Drift prevented the exploration of the Tragan Cluster up until approximately three standard centuries before the Galactic Civil War, when a group of Shistavanen scouts charted the sector, discovering several new sentient species in the Cluster's star systems.

properties.name: Bakkah
properties.description: Bakkah was a desert planet located in the Bakkah system, in the Thrasybule sector of the Outer Rim.

properties.name: Bakura
properties.poi: Bakur Memorial BuildingBakuran National SymphonyBakuran power stationBraadKishh districtKishh'daarLesser GraceTelaan ValleyWest River, D'aarmontEast River
properties.description: Bakura, known in Ssi-ruuvi as Xwhee, was a rich, green and blue planet in the Bakura system of the Shiritoku Spur, located on the isolated edge of Wild Space, and was the homeworld of the indigenous Kurtzen and isolated humans colonisers known as Bakurans. The native language of Kurtzen was spoken alongside Basic.

properties.name: Bal'demnic
properties.description: Bal'demnic was an ocean planet adorned with rocky tropical islands in the Bak'rofsen system of the Auril sector, located within the Outer Rim Territories. The hostility of its native Kon'me species, together with its extremely harsh climate, discouraged most people from ever visiting the planet, despite the beauty of its giant rock cliffs, pristine beaches, and vast azure oceans. It was mostly of interest to cartographers, xenobiologists, and fisherfolk, until knowledge of the planet's rich deposits of cortosis ore fell into the hands of Sith Lords Darth Tenebrous and Darth Plagueis.

properties.name: Balamak
properties.description: Balamak was an important agriworld located in the Mid Rim's Taldot sector on the Great Kashyyyk Branch hyperlane. During the early stages of the Clone Wars, Balamak lay in space controlled by the Confederacy of Independent Systems. A Confederate flotilla containing the experimental CIS Jammer Prototype starship was deployed over Balamak during that conflict, disrupting communications in the Taldot sector.

properties.name: Balanor
properties.description: Balanor was the rainforest homeworld of the Force mite.

properties.name: Baldavia
properties.description: The Baldavia system was located in the Interior Region, an area of the Hapes Cluster in the Slice portion of the Inner Rim. It was connected via hyperlanes to the Gallinore and Theselon systems. The Baldavia system was home to the creature known as the Baldavian pocket hare and was the origin point of the group known as Baldavian lip-readers.

properties.name: Balfron
properties.description: Balfron was a small terrestrial planet in the Dolomar sector. It had several casinos where planets could be won or lost in a game of sabacc, including The High Stakes Casino, where Han Solo arranged for Lando Calrissian to meet the Tonnika sisters as part of an elaborate prank.

properties.name: Balis-Baurgh
properties.description: Balis-Baurgh was a planet in the Mid Rim's Balis-Baurgh system and the only planet in the system that could sustain life.

properties.name: Balith
properties.description: Balith was a planet located in the Inner Rim's Balith system. During the year 21 BBY, in the Clone Wars, the system erupted into civil war, and Jedi General Anakin Skywalker and Clone Captain CT-7567 were sent to the world by Jedi Master Obi-Wan Kenobi to command the Third Legion.

properties.name: Balmorra
properties.poi: Gorinth Canyon, Hazard Vault 305, Imperial Construction Yards, Markaran Plains, Sundari Flatlands,
properties.description: Balmorra was a factory world that was located within the Balmorra system, situated in a strategic position between the Colonies and the border of the Core Worlds. Due to its intense industrial manufacturing it was known as one of the most important foundry worlds in the Republic's space, where some of the most advanced weaponry and battle droids were constantly produced throughout most of the planet's history.

properties.name: Balnab
properties.description: Balnab was a planet close to the world of Patitite Pattuna.

properties.name: Balosar
properties.description: Balosar was a planet in the Core Worlds, and home to the Balosar species. It was a polluted, poverty-stricken world of grimy factories and downtrodden people, and a place where tourism was discouraged. Such an environment encouraged many of the native Balosars to become criminals.

properties.name: Balowa
properties.description: Balowa was a planet in the Mid Rim's Balowa system whose primary terrain was rainforest. This planet was the location of a duel in which the Sith Lord Kaox Krul and Jedi Knight Crian Maru, along with her Padawan, Dree Vandap, were killed in 1000 BBY, shortly before the start of the Ruusan campaign.

properties.name: Baltimn
properties.description: Baltimn was an Outer Rim planet. It was here that Ephaan Kenzon established the School of Hidden Wisdom, the only dueling academy to survive the Clone Wars and the rise of Emperor Palpatine. Despite its pleasant environment, Baltimn's remote location made it inaccessible for many tourists.

properties.name: Baltizaar
properties.description: Baltizaar was a Mid Rim planet within the Galactic Republic to which a Jedi team was sent prior to the Invasion of Naboo in 32 BBY, in response to an attack by forces of the Bando Gora. Dooku chafed at the indiscrimination employed by the Republic in assigning Jedi to such missions; immediately prior to its departure, he left the Jedi Order, becoming the latest of the Lost Twenty. However, the Jedi did not realize at the time that he was already Darth Tyranus; the task force was subsequently decimated by the Bando Gora on Baltizaar.

properties.name: Ban-Satir
properties.description: Ban-Satir II was a planet located within the Ban-Satir system in the Corporate Sector of the Outer Rim region of the galaxy. The planet was home to a distributor of Novanian grog.

properties.name: Bancar
properties.description: Bancar was a planet in the Rayter sector.

properties.name: Bandomeer
properties.poi: Great Sea, G-417, Deepsea mines, Enrichment Zone
properties.description: Bandomeer was a planet in the Outer Rim Territories, on the Braxant Run. It was known for its high concentration of ionite, as well as the many predators lurking in its wildernesses. The planet's surface was roughly divided in half by a huge landmass and the Great Sea of Bandomeer.

properties.name: Bandonia
properties.description: Bandonia was an Imperial-aligned world which was located in the Bandonian system. Moxin Tark, the son of an Imperial lieutenant, was a native of Bandonia; however, he fled the planet in order to pursue a career as a bounty hunter.

properties.name: Bannistar Station
properties.description: Bannistar Station was a major Imperial refueling station located within the Bannistar Station system in the Mid Rim's Hevvrol sector. In 0 ABY it was under the command of commander Arno D'Vox and it was running at capacity, servicing both Imperial and civilian ships. Its location and importance allowed the Empire to expand further out to remote Imperial stations. Nine months after the Battle of Yavin the Rebels accidentally happened upon the station and sent infiltrators to take out the station. In the resulting battle a large section of the station was destroyed.

properties.name: Bantu
properties.description: Bantu was one of the planets Mungo Baobab visited on his journeys across the galaxy. It was located in the Emmo sector.

properties.name: Banvhar Station
properties.description: Banvhar Station was the asteroid headquarters of the Banvhar Combine asteroid miners. Due to the fact that they were located near Trade Federation spaceways, their minerals were stolen by the CIS during the Clone Wars, and even some of the residents were used as target practice for General Grievous's droid army. Because of this, the remaining miners bore a great hatred against the cyborg general. They even assisted a group of Jedi deserters to locate Grievous and sneak into enemy territory and assassinate the General.

properties.name: Bar Neth
properties.description: Bar Neth  was a former desert planet located in the Bar Neth system, a quinary star system positioned in the Albarrio sector of the galaxy's Outer Rim Territories. By the year 4.3 ABY, Bar Neth had been turned into a "Natural Wonderland" with bountiful farmlands. As a result of its ambitious terraforming process, Bar Neth was considered pleasant to live in and was hugely apealing for galactic tourists. At that time, trips to Bar Neth were organized by the Star Tours travel agency as part of their Frontier Vacation Package.

properties.name: Barab
properties.description: Barab I, also known simply as Barab, was an irradiated planet in the Outer Rim Territories of the galaxy, connected to Teth and Dubrava via hyperspace routes. It was positioned at the coordinates U-12 on the Standard Galactic Grid and was the homeworld of the Barabel species.

properties.name: Baraboo
properties.description: Baraboo was an oceanic New Republic planet in the Core Worlds, along the Hydian Way. It was the headquarters of the Institute for Sentient Studies as well as the Biomold homeworld.

properties.name: Baradas
properties.description: Baradas was a location where the New Republic intelligence officer Nath Tensent once experienced a bad landing prior to the battle at Chadawa. The landing tore off the underside of Tensent's first Y-wing starfighter, as well as one of its nacelles.

properties.name: Baralou
properties.poi: Aqualis Base, Magl'Ikkan Temple, Krikthasi Territories:Reterri, Undrarian, Winsallu,
properties.description: Baralou was the first planet of the Baralou system. It was a warm, wet world home to two native sentient species, the Krikthasi and the Multopos, along with many aquatic species and poisonous plants. The world was nearly completely covered by oceans with only several chains of small islands above water. The planet's four moons caused violent storms and had a tremendous influence on the tides, sometimes resulting in tidal shifts of over fifty meters.

properties.name: Baramorra
properties.description: Baramorra was a temperate, dreary, rainsoaked Imperial Remnant planet governed by Admiral Llon Banjeer's nephew, the "Boss". He employed bounty hunters such as Jahnar-Kooda to keep the populace in line; when the planet's elders objected, he had them killed. The Boss was funded by Grappa the Hutt; when this was revealed, the Boss was executed as a traitor by Kir Kanos.

properties.name: Barancar
properties.description: Barancar was a planet located within the Tion Cluster. It was a part of the Kingdom of Cron, and was eventually conquered by Xer VIII. It was the site of numerous shipyards under Xim's Empire, and had been a thriving merchant port. By the Imperial Period, however, millennia of war and decay had left most of the yards derelict, but fitful industry still struggled along. Many of the ancient docks had become the lairs of smugglers and outlaws.

properties.name: Barbeen
properties.description: Barbeen was a planet that was located in the Barbeen system of the Deep Core. The Brothers of Barbeen were from this planet.

properties.name: Barcaria
properties.description: Barcaria was the primary planet of the Barcaria system. The homeworld of famous Republic soldier Jace Malcom, the planet was famous for its Barcarian claw salt.

properties.name: Barcola
properties.description: Barcola was a barren moon.

properties.name: Bardotta
properties.description: Bardotta was a planet located in the Colonies' Bardotta system that was ruled by the much beloved Queen Julia during the Clone Wars. Its inhabitants were reputed for their mysticism and attention to spiritual matters.

properties.name: Barenth
properties.description: Barenth was an Expansion Region world located in the Drannik sector. During the Waymancy Storm of 7811 BBY, its civilian population saw a near complete evacuation by the Galactic Republic as part of the defense of the world against the Signatories of Waymancy, with the Republic losing an entire battle group during the effort.

properties.name: Barison
properties.description: Barison was a water world along the Feena Run in the Gordian Reach. It supplied fish, seafood, and kelp to worlds in the Back Reach. Its inhabitants were known as the Barisoni. For religious reasons, many of the Barisoni had renounced technology.

properties.name: Barkhesh
properties.description: Barkhesh was a planet located in the Seitia sector of the Outer Rim Territories.

properties.name: Barlok
properties.poi: Covered Brush housing ringPanky'sPatameene DistrictStarbright Hotel
properties.description: Barlok was a planet in the Barlok system of the Marcol sector, between three and six days of hyperspace travel from Coruscant, and was also a member world of the Galactic Republic. It was known for tisvollt forests, inhabited by the indigenous Karfs; its agricultural produce, including delicious prisht fruit; its sprawling Patameene District, including the Starbright hotel, Panky's restaurant, and the Covered Brush housing ring; and its mines, the ownership of which was a point of dispute between the guilds of the indigenous Brolfi and the Corporate Alliance, including the Mining Guild.

properties.name: Barnaba
properties.description: Barnaba was a warm, mountainous planet in Barnaba Province. It was an important exporter of agricultural produce in the Tapani sector.

properties.name: Baroli
properties.description: Baroli was a planet inhabited by blue-haired Humans, and known for its many interesting moons.

properties.name: Baroonda
properties.poi: Baroo CoastGrabvine GatewayFire Mountain RallyInfernoAncient Nazwa Structures,
properties.description: Baroonda was a planet of varied geography. It was host to several podracing tracks which passed through many diverse locations, including volcanoes, swamps, wide, sandy beaches, spectacular waterfalls, thick jungles, sulfur geyser fields, and plateau-top cities. Some of the inhabited moons of Baroonda included Dirama, Pitrono, Metrmal, Nicale, and Promanda.

properties.name: Baros
properties.description: Baros was a planet located in the Baros system in the Dominus sector. An Outer Rim world on the farthest reaches of the Slice, the planet was home to the Brubb species. It had a high gravity, was frequented by windstorms, and possessed infertile growing soil. In 9 ABY, it was one of the New Republic worlds taken over by Grand Admiral Thrawn during his attempt to win the Galactic Civil War for the Empire.

properties.name: Barpine
properties.description: Barpine was a planet with shipyards used as the headquarters of the rogue Imperial Lieutenant Lon Donell. Donell engaged in piracy against the New Republic from the bridge of the Immobilizer 418 cruiser Detainer, of which Donell had usurped command. The surface of the planet contained a large prison facility for the crews of the starships that Donell captured. Barpine was located in the Barpine system of the Outer Rim Territories.

properties.name: Bars Barka
properties.description: Bars Barka was a planet located in Bars Barka system, within the Barsa sector of the galaxy's Mid Rim and New Territories. It was connected to the Varvva system by a hyperspace route. Several decades before the outbreak of the Clone Wars in the year 22 BBY, the planet's Ubese colonists were devastated by the lethal Intestinal Revenge of Bars Barka, a global illness believed to have been transmitted by a Neimoidian trade delegation that resulted in crippling weight loss. Between 12 and 13 ABY, Bars Barka fell within the borders of the New Republic.

properties.name: Barseg
properties.description: Barseg was a planet located in the Tion Cluster of the Outer Rim Territories, along the Perlemian Trade Route.

properties.name: Barundi
properties.description: Barundi was the homeworld of the Barundi species. The natives of Barundi were taken from their homeworld thousand of years before the Battle of Yavin and were deposited on an unnamed planet in Wild Space. There, they worshiped the Yavin Vassilika.

properties.name: Basan
properties.description: Basan could refer to one of the following:

properties.name: Basarais
properties.description: Basarais was a planet in the Expansion Region.

properties.name: Basilisk
properties.description: Basilisk was a Core world in the Arrowhead of the Slice, near Coruscant.

properties.name: Baskarn
properties.description: Baskarn was a planet in the Outer Rim. The planet was inhabited by the large, green-furred, Force-sensitive Yrashu. The planet was also home to the dangerous Razor trees. Baskarn was the site of the Battle of Baskarn in which the indigenous Yrashu instinctively fought the Galactic Empire, as they could sense its ties to the dark side of the Force. In the events leading up to the battle, a group of Rebels were adopted into a Yrashu tribe and went through a momu, in which they were taught jungle survival according to the Yrashu way. The tribe participated in the battle, and emerged victorious along with the Rebels.

properties.name: Bassadro
properties.description: Bassadro was a mining world with glassy crags on its volcanoes. It was devastated in a battle in which it was taken from the Confederacy of Independent Systems during the Clone Wars by Empatojayos Brand.

properties.name: Basteel
properties.description: Basteel was a temperate, bleak planet where Slique Brighteyes hid from Admiral Mir Tork and Doctor Leonis Murthé. Not long after the Battle of Endor, Slique hired Boba Fett to kill Mir and Leonis for 100 credits. Fett returned with their heads just before Slique died.

properties.name: Bastion
properties.poi: Imperial Remnant headquartersBastion customs stationPellaeon GardensDisra's palaceHolomap RoomImperial LibraryImperial PalaceImperial Dungeons
properties.description: Bastion, originally Sartinaynian, was the capital world of the Imperial Remnant, a successor state of the Galactic Empire, located in the Braxant sector in the Outer Rim Territories, and later the Fel Empire and Empire-in-exile. Bastion was located in the Sartinaynian system at the terminus of the trade route known as the Braxant Run.

properties.name: Bator Bai
properties.description: Bator Bai was a planet located in the Western Reaches of the Mid Rim. Part of the Senex sector's Bator Bai system, the ice world was known for the exceptional clarity of its ice cliffs and caverns.

properties.name: Batorine
properties.description: Batorine was the forested homeworld of the Blood Carver species. It joined the Galactic Republic in 110 BBY.

properties.name: Baummu
properties.description: Baummu was a planet located in the Shadola sector of the Outer Rim. It was violently attacked during the Galactic Civil War by Imperial forces led by Captain Briera. Briera was later known as the "Butcher of Baummu".

properties.name: Bavva
properties.description: Bavva was a colony world of the gold-skinned Nothoiin species. Located on the Nothoiin Corridor in the Outer Rim Territories' Anoat sector, Bavva exported a foul-tasting ale distilled from moss that Lutrillians loved and Humans hated. Sergeant Taray, a Nothoiin member of the Cloud City Wing Guard, grew up in Bavva's lawless Kaniti province.

properties.name: Baylagon
properties.description: Baylagon was a location in the galaxy. In an attempt to cover up a theft of U-wing transports during the early rebellion against the Galactic Empire, Senator Bail Organa had an Aldraig data clerk mistakenly route a shipment of U-wings to Coruscant through Baylagon.

properties.name: Baylin Cluster
properties.description: The Baylin Cluster was in Trans-Nebular sector in the Mid Rim.

properties.name: Bazaar
properties.description: The term "Bazaar" can refer to:

properties.name: Bazarre
properties.description: Bazarre was a large space station that served as a popular black market and shadowport during the Imperial Period. Located in the Outer Rim's Cademimu sector by the time of the Galactic Civil War, Bazarre was owned by gunrunner Orion Ferret, who fostered an environment where almost anything could be bought and sold aboard the station, including slaves. In 3 ABY, Ferret attempted to betray and kill Rebel leaders Lando Calrissian and Luke Skywalker over a starfighter deal aboard Bazarre, but his plot was discovered and foiled.

properties.name: Beauchen
properties.description: Beauchen was the site of a New Republic penal colony.

properties.name: Bedlam
properties.poi: Bedlam Institution for the Criminally Demented,
properties.description: Bedlam was a rocky Mid Rim planet located near the Bedlam Pulsar. The Bedlam Institution for the Criminally Demented was located on the planet. As of 67 BBY, its only direct transport connections were to Felucia, Caluula, and Abraxin.

properties.name: Bedlam Pulsar
properties.description: The Bedlam Pulsar was a pulsar in the Mid Rim near the stark whiteness that digested the fabric of hyperspace. Omnipotent, transdimensional beings called Bedlam Spirits lived in it.

properties.name: Beetle Nebula
properties.description: The Beetle Nebula was a nebula that was located within the Bon'nyuw-Luq sector, in the Trailing Sectors portion of the Outer Rim Territories.

properties.name: Begali
properties.description: Bengali, also known as Begali, was an Inner Rim planet located within the Begali system, and was a part of the Six Sisters, six Echani-dominated planets within the Inner Rim. In 1154 BBY, the planet instigated the Bengali Uprising by revolting against the Echani Command.

properties.name: Begeren
properties.description: Begeren was a planet in the Sith Worlds region of the Outer Rim Territories. It was originally part of the Sith Empire, which constructed enormous monuments dedicated to notable Sith on the planet's surface—a project that cost the lives of an estimated hundred thousand slaves. Following the Empire's defeat in the Great Hyperspace War, Begeren was claimed by the Galactic Republic. The Republic allowed the construction of a gemstone quarry at the expense of the Sith statues, which fell into ruin. In 3678 BBY, the planet was seized by a revived Sith Empire. During the Galactic Civil War, Begeren was the site of a battle between the Alliance to Restore the Republic and the Galactic Empire.

properties.name: Beheboth
properties.poi: Bothehl Desert, Anglethorn moisture farm, Outpost B-2,
properties.description: Beheboth was a desert planet located in the Sanbra sector of the Outer Rim Territories. Beheboth was home to the Tirrith, a unique empathic gaseous culture of hive-minded sentient particles, which thrived even among the planet's inhospitably arid and dry climate. Bothans, and later Humans, settled Beheboth during the Republic era, dotting the world with moisture farms and small towns. During the Imperial Period, Beheboth's fledgling economy came under heavy threat from brigands who manipulated the Tirrith into aiding them in raids on local moisture farms, a threat ended by Rebel hero Luke Skywalker and local leader Darial Anglethorn, who later became Beheboth's first representative to the New Republic Senate.

properties.name: Belasco
properties.description: Belasco was a planet in the Expansion Region of the galaxy.

properties.name: Belazura
properties.description: Belazura was a Galactic Republic member world, and one of the most visually stunning planets in the galaxy. Belazura was directly represented in the Galactic Senate.

properties.name: Belderone
properties.description: Belderone, originally known as Vartholium, was the sector capital of Belderone sector in the Outer Rim Territories. Located on the Salin Corridor, Belderone had two inhabited moons.

properties.name: Belgaroth
properties.poi: Belgar Spaceport, Upside , Xot's Megabar, Scrapyard, Czerka factory,
properties.description: Belgaroth was a planet that was located within the Core Worlds region of the galaxy, situated near the Rimma Trade Route. The planet was used by the Galactic Empire to test new weapons and combat maneuvers. It was also the homeworld of the droidbreaker, a species of hulking creatures that fed on plasteel and refined metals.

properties.name: Belial
properties.description: Belial was a Devaronian male who held the rank of Cloud in the marauder organization known as the Nihil. Serving under Lourna Dee's Tempest, Belial worked at the monitoring station aboard his commander's eponymous cruiser. During the Thirty-ninth Emergence, Belial detected that the debris leaving hyperspace did not contain the Legacy Run's flight recorder. Dee considered Belial to be smart, capable, unemotional, and cool in a crisis. She also predicted that he would soon rise up the ranks of the Nihil to become a Storm.

properties.name: Belkadan
properties.description: Belkadan was a forested planet located in the Dalonbian sector of the Outer Rim Territories. It was a world of tall dalloralla trees and small natural bodies of water.

properties.name: Bellassa
properties.description: Bellassa was a thriving, peaceful world during the final days of the Republic. The planet's capital was Ussa, a pleasant city with seven large, tranquil lakes. After the rise of the Galactic Empire, Obi-Wan Kenobi went to Bellassa after learning on Tatooine that one former Jedi survived the purge: Ferus Olin.

properties.name: Bellis
properties.description: Bellis was a Human male who lived on the planet Ord Mantell with his wife, Lin, during the Cold War between the Galactic Republic and the reconstituted Sith Empire. At the time of the Separatist War started by a group of Separatists attempting to overthrow the planet's government, Bellis and Lin lived in a house in Talloran village, a small settlement on the island of Avilatan. After the Separatists captured the village, Bellis spied on them for the Republic.

properties.name: Belnar
properties.description: Belnar was a Colonies planet. A temperate world with large swamps on its surface, it was the homeworld of the sentient Khil species. Although the Khil developed large, Core-inspired cities on Belnar, the rest of the planet was left untouched, and even the urban centers featured marshy parks and swamps. Such areas in the cities served as convenient feeding sites for the Khil, whose diet consisted of organic particles filtered from the air via special organs.

properties.name: Belovia
properties.description: Belovia was an icy Expansion Region world that was directly represented in the New Republic Senate. It was the homeworld of the Belovians.

properties.name: Belsavis
properties.poi: Ancient Prison Caverns, Belsavis prison, Corridor, Eternity Vault, Plawal Rift, Rashnoor Pass, The Scar, The Tomb,
properties.description: Belsavis, also known as Plawal, was a planet in the Ninth Quadrant, a region of the Bozhnee sector. Ice-covered, its average temperature was in the -50s. It was located on the edge of the Senex sector, at one end of the Belsavis Run.

properties.name: Belshar Othacuu
properties.description: Belshar Othacuu was a planet in the Mid Rim with a secret COMPNOR base.

properties.name: Belthu
properties.description: Belthu was a unaligned Outer Rim Territories world located near the territory of Warlord Zsinj. A wealthy planet being controlled by a coalition of mining companies led by corporate executives, it had a durasteel foundry that was owned by an alias of Zsinj. The facility was eventually destroyed by Wraith Squadron and the New Republic.

properties.name: Belukat
properties.description: Belukat was a planet in the Belukat system of the Expansion Region ruled by kings. It was said that Belukat's royal tomb builders were killed by the kings so that they would not be able to divulge the tomb's secrets to robbers.

properties.name: Bendeluum
properties.description: Bendeluum was a planet in Anoat sector's Bendeluum system which had a small Rebel Alliance cell during the Galactic Civil War. The city planet's underworld was controlled by Nothoiins.

properties.name: Bendii
properties.description: Bendii was a planet located in the Seitia sector of the Outer Rim. From space, Bendii appeared as a blue orb. Around six months after the Battle of Yavin, Han Solo, Leia Organa and Chewbacca fled Imperial and bounty hunter pursuit above Bendii while ferrying supplies for the Rebel Alliance aboard the Millennium Falcon.

properties.name: Bendone
properties.description: Bendone was the homeworld of the Howler Tree People.

properties.name: Bengat
properties.description: Bengat was an oceanic world where the Aruzan female Manaroo once danced in competitions. She also rafted the planet's stormy waters in between her participation in these events.

properties.name: Bengely
properties.description: Bengely was a seedy world with an underworld that had a dangerous reputation.

properties.name: Benja-Rihn
properties.description: Benja-Rihn was a planet in the Mid Rim. In its Temple of Tet-Ami was the Orb of Passage. At some point, Mace Windu traveled back in time using the Orb and saved Carthas from insectoids.

properties.name: Ber de Val
properties.description: Ber de Val was a planet located in the Ber de Val system within the Colonies region. It is home to a non-sentient species of hyperactive rodents.

properties.name: Berason
properties.description: Berason was a Mid Rim mining world located in the Eclorar sector. During the Galactic Civil War, Berason—the inhabitants of which politically opposed the Galactic Empire—was subjected to an Imperial blockade that cut off the world's sources of food and medical supplies. Eventually, a Rebel Alliance force led by Airen Cracken ran the blockade, performing a strike against Berason's Imperial base and paving way for an Alliance convoy to bring supplies to the world.

properties.name: Berchest
properties.description: Berchest was a major tourist destination, and later a trading planet, in the Anthos sector of the Inner Rim. It was an extremely beautiful world whose highly saline seas and strong tides result in immense crystal deposits on the planet's shores that the native Berchestians sculpted into entire cities. One of these cities was Calius saj Leeloo, or the City of Glowing Crystal. It was carved entirely from one massive crystal that was created over the centuries from salt deposits from the adjacent Leefari Sea and was considered one of the Twenty Wonders of the Galaxy.

properties.name: Berea
properties.description: The primary planet in the Berea system in the Elrood sector, Berea was a rocky, mountainous world which was owned and operated by Imperial Mining, Ltd.. Berea was often besieged by hail storms and violent winds, and the nighttime temperature often dropped below freezing. It lay in Confederacy of Independent Systems controlled space during the Clone Wars. Many Imperial prisoners captured during the Galactic Civil War were sent to labor camps on Berea. Wilek Nereus and Conn Doruggan served the Galactic Empire on Berea before being reassigned to Bakura.

properties.name: Beris
properties.description: Beris, a Mid Rim planet in the Galactic Alliance Senate composition, seceded from the Galactic Alliance during the Second Galactic Civil War. The planet was located on the Gamor Run, in the Fei Hu sector.

properties.name: Berri
properties.description: Berri was a planet in the Inner Rim. It was a hot, smog-shrouded world with high gravity and little natural food sources.

properties.name: Berrol's Donn
properties.description: Berrol's Donn was a planet in the Kriz sector of the Outer Rim Territories.

properties.name: Berrun
properties.description: Berrun was a terrestrial astronomical object located in the Berrun system, a part of the Slice portion of the Colonies. By the time of the Cold War between the Galactic Republic and the reconstituted Sith Empire, the Republic maintained a detention facility on Berrun. After being convicted of war crimes as a result of targeting the families of their Imperial targets, the members of the Republic Special Forces squad known as the Surgeons served out their life sentences in the prison.

properties.name: Besberra
properties.description: Besberra was an astronomical object located in the Besberra system in the Cegul sector of the Outer Rim Territories. It hosted a gladiatorial arena where the Houk gladiator Torog fought to the death.

properties.name: Bescane
properties.description: Bescane was a planet near Dantooine, run by Galentro Heavy Works. A cool, temperate world, it was overpopulated and covered in factories, its natural environment destroyed.

properties.name: Besero
properties.description: Besero was a mining world. Tagge Mining Company had caused many problems for the bureaucrats of the world, contributing to their negative views of the company.

properties.name: Beshka
properties.description: Beshka was a planet in the Outer Rim's Aparo sector.

properties.name: Besn
properties.description: Besn was an Imperial planet in the Outer Rim Territories known for its perfection of artistic participlays.

properties.name: Besnia
properties.description: The Besnia system was a star system located within the galactic regions known as the Colonies and the Slice. It was connected by the Hydian Way super-hyperroute to the Herzob and Koensayr systems, and was the origin point of Besnian sausage.

properties.name: Bespin
properties.poi: BesGas ThreeBespin construction platformsCloud CityFloating health spasRethin SeaTibanna gas platformsUgnaught Surface
properties.description: Bespin was a gas giant in the Bespin system of the Anoat sector on the Ison Corridor in the Greater Javin region of the Outer Rim Territories. It was also a major source of tibanna gas, which was refined for production and transport in numerous mining operations including Cloud City and Tibannopolis. It was home to several million individuals, including Humans, Ugnaughts, and Lutrillians.

properties.name: Bessimir
properties.description: Bessimir was a planet in the Galactic Core, 15 parsecs from Coruscant. Two natural satellites orbited Bessimir.

properties.name: Bestine
properties.poi: Bestine naval shipyard, Imperial military base,
properties.description: Bestine IV, also known simply as Bestine, was a planet The Shahkirin mechanic Yipsit grew up on the cliffs of Bestine IV before joining the Resistance.

properties.name: Beta Olikark
properties.description: Beta Olikark was a planet in the Outer Rim, at the tip of a galactic arm on the other side of the galaxy from the Rayter sector. Its natural stones had intricate patterns and were exported to other worlds for flooring. On one occasion, a diplomat for the New Republic, Kare Fontin was escorted to the planet from Coruscant by New Republic agents.

properties.name: Beta Rhama
properties.description: Beta Rhama was an Outer Rim planet in the Dalchon sector, on the same hyperroute as Nimba Five.

properties.name: Betal
properties.description: Betal was a Wild Space astronomical object located in the Betal system. It was the origin point of the group known as the Poraskors, who reportedly wove neural-web reflex threads by hand. Betal was mentioned in Cracken's Rebel Field Guide, a datafile authored by General Airen Cracken that documented various pieces of equipment utilized by agents of the Rebel Alliance.

properties.name: Bethal
properties.description: Bethal was a planet located in Pelagia Province of the Tapani sector in the Colonies region. It was the primary planet in the Bethal System. It housed the headquarters of Bethal AgriCorp, and its main export was apocia hardwood timber. An infestation of greddleback termites caused the economy of the planet - which was based on apocia hardwood timber - to go under. Imperial Moff Tendd declared the planet a disaster world, and helped bring Imperial funds to the planet in an effort to restore the apocia. The world also diversified its crops in an effort to revive its economy while the apocia forests regrew.

properties.name: Bethars
properties.description: Bethars was a wealthy world in the Core Worlds.

properties.name: Betolio
properties.description: The Betolio system was in Tapani sector, in the Colonies region of the galaxy. Located in the Pelagia Province until it was seized by the Calipsa Province, it was located between the Setolio system and the Netolio system.

properties.name: Betshish
properties.description: Betshish was a planet located in the Gordian Reach along the Pinooran Spur between Mogoshyn and Kli'aar. It was the homeworld of a sentient species. Betshish was discovered by a scout, Lile Gorsek, but his claim to the world had to be abandoned when the sentient species was discovered on landing. While it was interdicted by the Galactic Empire, the world escaped exploitation.

properties.name: Bettel
properties.description: Bettel was an astronomical object in the Greater Javin Region of the galaxy's Outer Rim Territories.

properties.name: Bettok
properties.description: Bettok was an astronomical object located in the Bettok system, a part of the Velcar sector in the New Territories portion of the Outer Rim Territories. The Human TIE fighter pilot Creb of the Galactic Empire was born at Bettok in 20 BBY.

properties.name: Bextar
properties.description: Bextar was one of four gas giants in the Velcar Free Commerce Zone's Bextar system. It was the site of several Amber Sun Mining Corporate gas mines. Amber Sun imported Entymal slaves as miners.

properties.name: Bezim
properties.description: Bezim was a planet in the Mid Rim. The native Bezim joined with the people of Junction V, Delaluna, and Vicondor to build the Station 88 Spaceport. This coalition of planets chose to remain loyal to the Galactic Republic during the Clone Wars.

properties.name: Bhargebba
properties.description: The Bhargebba system was a star system located within the Sith Worlds region in the Outer Rim of the galaxy.

properties.name: Bheriz
properties.description: Bheriz was a remote mining planet.

properties.name: Bhuna Sound
properties.description: Bhuna Sound was a Mid Rim planet which joined the New Republic shortly after the Battle of Endor. To help in the planet's rebuilding efforts, the New Republic sent a freighter, the Dewback's Burden, to bring supplies to Bhuna Sound. However, the vessel was attacked by the TIE Pirates, who captured the transport.

properties.name: Bianas
properties.description: The Bianas system was in the Tapani sector, in the Colonies region of the galaxy. It was located in the Mecetti Province, on the Procopian Shipping Lane.

properties.name: Bid'jerma
properties.description: Bid'jerma was a planet located in the Prefsbelt sector of the Outer Rim.

properties.name: Biewa
properties.description: Biewa was an industrial planet in the Corporate Sector used as the headquarters of the Corporate Sector Authority Picket Fleet. It was a relatively poor world, and the Biewans spent what few credits they had on clothing, shelter and food.

properties.name: Biitu
properties.poi: Fuel-ore processing plant, Pitor Processing Plantworks
properties.description: Biitu was the Biituian homeworld in the Cassandran Worlds region.

properties.name: Biivren
properties.description: Biivren was a planet located in the Expansion Region's Biivren sector. An industrial world controlled by the Galactic Empire, it was the site of a large zone of factories and refineries that gradually contaminated the planet's water supply.

properties.name: Bilbringi
properties.description: Bilbringi was a world located in the galaxy's Inner Rim. It was home to the Bilbringi shipyards, a facility which dismantled the Separatist dreadnought Lucid Voice within a year after the end of the Clone Wars. The smuggler Han Solo was fond of Bilbringi food, and shared cheesy meat pies with pepper from Bilbringi with his wife, Leia Organa, at their home on Hosnian Prime twenty-four years after the Battle of Endor.

properties.name: Bilios
properties.description: Bilios was a planet in the Bilios system of the Tapani sector's Melantha Province. The Justice Action Network once maintained a base on the planet.

properties.name: Bimin Three
properties.description: The Bimin Three system was a star system in the Majoor sector, located in the Outer Rim region of the galaxy. Its inhabitants were friendly to the Jedi.

properties.name: Bimmiel
properties.description: Bimmiel was a planet in an elliptical orbit around its primary star in the MZX33291 system. The fifth planet in the system, it was named after Bimmiel, the Imperial scout who rediscovered it. As the planet neared the sun, its ice caps melted, triggering an increase in moisture and plant growth. The heat brought the native shwpi out of hibernation to multiply. Since the carnivorous slashrats could not adapt to the heat, they retreated to the polar regions of the planet. Then when the planet got farther from the sun, its ice caps refroze, and the shwpi came into the food chain of the slashrats, returning to the equatorial regions. The slashrats brought the number of shwpi back to a manageable number. A number of natives existed on the planet, using crude wooden spears and tools.

properties.name: Bimmisaari
properties.description: Bimmisaari, the capital planet of the Halla sector, was the homeworld of the Bimms and the adopted homeworld of a near-Human species of the same name who settled the planet in 2000 BBY. The planet was directly represented in the Galactic Senate and allowed a RRM settlement in 22 BBY, prior to the Clone Wars. During the Clone Wars the planet was located within Separatist-contested space and Hutt Space. It escaped most of the turmoil of the Clone Wars and Imperial repression thanks to its remote location.

properties.name: Binaros
properties.description: Binaros was a planet located in the Kathol Outback.

properties.name: Binquaros
properties.description: The planet of Binquarous was located in the Ciutric sector of the Outer Rim Territories.

properties.name: Birgis
properties.description: Birgis was a terrestrial world in the Dalonbian sector of the Outer Rim Territories. It lay in the path of the extragalactic Yuuzhan Vong species during their invasion of the galaxy.

properties.name: Birix
properties.description: Birix was a world that Prudii Skirata went on a mission to during the Clone Wars, to destroy a Separatist reactor.

properties.name: Birsingrial
properties.description: Birsingrial was a Core Worlds planet known for its jewel-caves. Besany Wennen's family once went there on a vacation when she was about ten years old.

properties.name: Bisellia
properties.description: The Bisellia system was a star system located in the Clacis sector, within the Outer Rim Territories and New Territories regions of the galaxy. The system was connected by the Entralla Route hyperlane to the Muunilinst and Endoraan systems.

properties.name: Bissillirus
properties.description: Bissillirus was the primary star of the Bissillirus system. It was discovered sometime in 200 BBY by hyperspace scouts looking for a route through the southern outskirts of the Thornhedge Nebula.

properties.name: Bith
properties.description: Bith were a peaceful, highly evolved craniopod species native to the planet Clak'dor VII. Fully adapted to a civilized, high-technology lifestyle, Bith were found galaxy-wide at all levels of society, most notably as engineers, scientists, intellectuals, consultants, and musicians.

properties.name: Bivoli
properties.description: Bivoli can refer to:

properties.name: Black Bantha
properties.description: Black Bantha could refer to a number of different objects in the galaxy:

properties.name: Black Hole of Nakat
properties.description: The Black Hole of Nakat was a black hole located in the Inner Rim region of the galaxy. It gave rise to a common phrase that said: "trapped between the Black Hole of Nakat and the Magataran Maelstrom."

properties.name: Black Hole of Quintas
properties.description: The Black Hole of Quintas was a black hole in the Kriz sector, in the Outer Rim region of the galaxy. It was known to be very far removed from the Denarii Nova.

properties.name: Black Nebula
properties.description: The Black Nebula was a nebula located in the Colonies, in a region of space known as Parfadi.

properties.name: Black Widow Nebula
properties.description: The Black Widow Nebula was a nebula in the Mid Rim region of the galaxy. The Super Star Destroyer Executor was spotted inside the nebula in 0.5 ABY.

properties.name: Blackfel
properties.description: Blackfel was a moon located in the Blackfel system, within the Greater Plooriod sector of the galaxy's Expansion Region. The entire moon was a training facility for the Galactic Empire.

properties.name: Blair Cluster
properties.description: The Blair cluster was a vast asteroid field in the Airam sector, located in the Outer Rim region of the galaxy.

properties.name: Blenjeel
properties.description: Blenjeel was a desert planet between Ando and Kothlis, located far from the major hyperlanes. It was inhabited by enormous sand burrowers, which emerged quickly from the ground to devour unsuspecting prey. The terrain of Blenjeel was comprised mostly of wide deserts, noted for the unusual consistency of the sand, which shifted over time. Rocky outcroppings which were stable one day seemed to sink into the sand the next. These shifts were mostly attributed to the movements of the sand burrowers.

properties.name: Blimph
properties.description: Blimph was a Mid Rim gas giant in the Blimph system. One of its moons was Blimph 3, which was strategically important to the Rebel Alliance due to trading with the Jokhalli.

properties.name: Blood Nest
properties.description: M2398-3, best known as Blood Nest, was a large but dismal moon in the Mid Rim. It had half-standard gravity. It was covered in brown-and-red desert, high mountains, foothills, and craters. Local bandits made their base out of a damaged Super Transport VI, which was also named Blood Nest. The bandits were defeated by Wraith Squadron, although Jesmin Ackbar was shot down and killed in the conflict, and her astromech droid, Shiner was destroyed.

properties.name: Blyte
properties.description: The Blyte system was in the Tapani sector of the Colonies region of the galaxy. It was located in the sector's Mecetti Province, near Tumus.

properties.name: Bnach
properties.description: Bnach was a hot, desolate prison planet that housed an Imperial penal camp, and was renowned for its deadly rock quarries. Prisoners forced to labor in these quarries were said to survive no more than a year.

properties.name: Bnar
properties.description: Bnar may refer to one of the following:

properties.name: Boden
properties.description: Boden was a planet in the Boden system. Some time before 0 ABY, Leger DeMain once helped Airen Cracken escape capture during an Imperial occupation of the planet.

properties.name: Bodrin
properties.description: Bodrin was a rocky, mountainous planet in Elrood sector's Bodrin system on the Elrood-Derilyn Trade Route. Its poor inhabitants worked for the Elrood Quarry Corporation. The bodrite mines operated at full capacity during the summer. During the five local winter months, the mines were forced to shut down. Individuals could not carry weapons on Bodrin, small towns were closely knit and crime was rare. During the Clone Wars, Bodrin lay within Separatist space. The Shining Comet was headed to this planet with a group of miners when it was attacked by Consolidations Unlimited.

properties.name: Bofa
properties.description: Bofa was a sweet fruit, which when dried was considered a delicacy in the period of the Great Sith War. Later, bofa fruit was used to make a sauce that was served over hibbas breast.

properties.name: Bogden
properties.description: Bogden was a many-mooned world located in the Inner Rim, along the Hydian Way, between Arkania and Ploo.

properties.name: Bogo Rai
properties.description: Bogo Rai was a planet within the Bogo Rai system in the Unknown Regions where the Chiss fought the famous Battle of Bogo Rai. This planet resided off the Cressus Route hyperspace lane.

properties.name: Bogoa
properties.description: Bogoa was a planet covered in spires of durable coral, which could be used as ship-building materials. During the Clone Wars, the planet was under the protection of the Galactic Republic. Its coral made it a target for the Confederacy of Independent Systems, which battled the Galactic Republic for three long days and nights for control of the coral world.

properties.name: Bolad
properties.description: Bolad was a terrestrial astronomical object located in the Bolad system, a part of the Tharin sector in the Slice portion of the Outer Rim Territories. The Annoo-dat Blue crime lord Sise Fromm, based out of the planet Annoo, maintained a vacation palace on Bolad until the residence was destroyed by Fromm's son, Tig, at some point by 15 BBY.

properties.name: Boledge
properties.description: Boledge was a planet located in the Inner Rim. Boledge Downport was the planet's spaceport.

properties.name: Boltrunia
properties.description: The Boltrunia system was located in the Outer Rim Territories' Baxel sector. It was home to the sentient Boltrunian species.

properties.name: Bomis Koori
properties.description: Bomis Koori was an astronomical object located in the galaxy's Mid Rim, situated on the Corellian Trade Spine.

properties.name: Bomodon
properties.description: The Bomodons were a sentient species, native to the planet Bomodon in the Churba sector of the Mid Rim. In 0 BBY, a number of Bomodon bounty hunters were present on Tatooine and were witnessed by the Rodian bounty hunter Greedo entering Chalmun's Spaceport Cantina in Mos Eisley.

properties.name: Bompreil
properties.description: Bompreil was located within the Demetras sector of the Outer Rim Territories, in the Bompreil system.

properties.name: Bonadan
properties.description: Bonadan was the chief port world of the Corporate Sector and the primary world in the Bonadan system, boasting 10 gigantic spaceports. It was a strip-mined planet at the end of the Hydian Way. The densely populated planet housed many exotic species from around the galaxy. Bonadanians found off-world were either from wealthy corporate families or those that had escaped the life of corporate servitude.

properties.name: Boonta
properties.description: Boonta, formerly known as Ko Vari, was a planet that had been colonized by the Hutts long ago. Despite it being a devastated world, Boonta was famous in the galaxy for its podracing and speeder races.

properties.name: Boordii
properties.description: Boordii was a temperate planet in the Sumitra sector. Its central source of income came from smugglers transporting contraband offworld. After the death of King Alaric the whole sector including this planet, left the Galactic Republic and joined the Confederacy of Independent Systems.

properties.name: Bootana Shagplan
properties.description: Bootana Shagplan was a planet located in the Bootana Hutta region of Hutt Space. It was the region's most exclusive slave market, where were sold the most expensive and sought-after slaves. It also served as a clearinghouse for luxury goods that were popular on the nearby Hutt throneworlds.

properties.name: Boranall
properties.description: Boranall was a temperate world in the Mid Rim. In 3640 BBY, Boranall was attacked by the Sith Empire warship Ascendant Spear in order to suppress rebellion in the Boranall system.

properties.name: Boranda
properties.description: Boranda was a planet located in the Mid Rim's Manda sector.

properties.name: Borao
properties.description: Borao was a world within the Inner Rim that was located between Coruscant and Ramodi. Its surface was covered in yorik coral spires and forests after its Vongforming and abandonment by the Yuuzhan Vong. It was adopted as the new home world of the Ithorians, along with Felucia after the devastation of Ithor, under the Galactic Alliance.

properties.name: Borcorash
properties.description: Borcorash was a planet with incredibly beautiful sunsets with an ever-shifting array of colors brought about by atmospheric conditions. It was the blufferavian homeworld. The planet was the location of the high-tech Resinem Entertainment Complex. The bombing of a neighboring rival casino shortly before the Battle of Endor damaged the Complex's west wall, which was further damaged by erosion. The Complex was run by Mazzic. The Mistryl sent Karoly D'ulin to recover Shada D'ukal from the Complex. Shada defeated and escaped from Karoly, fleeing to Coruscant.

properties.name: Borga
properties.description: Borga was a terrestrial astronomical object that featured swamps and was located in the Borga system, a part of the Yminis sector in the Slice portion of the Outer Rim Territories. In 15 BBY, the Fromm Gang leader Tig Fromm thought about vacationing on Borga after a plan of his failed, speculating that its swamps were nearly habitable during that time of year.

properties.name: Borgo Prime
properties.description: Borgo Prime was a spaceport built into an asteroid in the Outer Rim. It was inhabited by merchants, information brokers, and all variety of unsavory individuals.

properties.name: Boriin
properties.description: Boriin was a planet in the Boriin system of the Inner Rim of the galaxy that prohibited skilled metalsmiths from leaving its territories.

properties.name: Borkyne
properties.description: Borkyne was a planet located in the Bes Ber Bikade sector of the Expansion Region.

properties.name: Borleias
properties.poi: Alderaan Biotics facility, Imperial/New Republic base, Yuuzhan Vong baseBorleias Control
properties.description: Borleias was the fourth and only inhabited planet in the Pyria system. It was located in the Colonies, at the edge of the Galactic Core and along the Namadii Corridor.

properties.name: Borlov
properties.description: Borlov was the homeworld of the feudal Borlovian species.

properties.name: Bormter
properties.description: Bormter was a Wild Space planet that was home to the four-armed reptiloid Bormterran species. Following the Battle of Endor, Moff Delurin broke with the Galactic Empire and declared himself a warlord, conquering Bormter with his warship, the Galaxy Dragon. Delurin used Bormter as a base and recruited Bormterrans to serve in the dragon trooper military unit.

properties.name: Bormus
properties.description: Bormus was a planet orbited by a Gran-run naval testing facility.

properties.name: Borosk
properties.description: Borosk was a planet in the Outer Rim Territories, one of a number of worlds along the frontier of Imperial Space fortified as strongpoints against the New Republic in the last years of the Galactic Civil War. A relatively small world, its defenses included orbiting ion minefields and planetary shields, plus heavy planetary-defense turbolasers and ion cannon batteries. It was located near Yaga Minor.

properties.name: Bortele Cluster
properties.description: The Bortele Cluster was a star cluster in the Bortele sector, located in the Mid Rim region of the galaxy. It contained the planet Ingo.

properties.name: Bortras
properties.description: Bortras was a tranquil world of lush valleys and fertile landscapes in the Brema sector of the Outer Rim Territories. It was known as the home planet of Jedi Master Jorus C'baoth.

properties.name: Boruga
properties.description: Boruga was a planet located in the Core Worlds.

properties.name: Bosch
properties.description: The Bosch system was a part of the Core Worlds. Between 16 ABY and 17 ABY, it, as well as a total of five inhabited planets and approximately one billion citizens, was represented in the New Republic Senate by Senator Tuomi. While challenging the authority of the New Republic's Chief of State Leia Organa, Tuomi rhetorically asked why should the former inhabitants of Organa's homeworld, the Alderaan system's destroyed planet Alderaan, have the same voting rights in the Senate as the Bosch system. In a discussion with Organa, however, New Republic Supreme Commander Gial Ackbar reassured her, proclaiming that Tuomi was only an "ignorant fingerling."

properties.name: Bosph
properties.description: The Bosphs were a mammalian species from the planet of Bosph in the Outer Rim Territories' Bosph sector. They had six limbs, no neck and a pair of multiple-lensed eyes that also functioned as auditory sense organs. The Bosphs were a fiercely independent and isolationist species who preferred seclusion from both the rest of the galaxy and each other. The homeworld, where most Bosphs remained, was controlled by a hierarchical government made up of various factions each consisting of Force-sensitive Bosphs. These Bosphs were the only individuals who had the right to claim ownership of any object, though any unclaimed object was equally owned by all Bosphs. The Bosphs also kept a tradition of recording the history of their travels, both on Bosph and in the galaxy by tattooing star maps on to their skin.

properties.name: Bosthirda
properties.description: Bosthirda was a planet of the Sith Empire, close to Korriban and Dromund Kaas, and was located on the Kamat Krote.

properties.name: Botajef
properties.description: Botajef was a planet located in the Belsmuth sector of the Outer Rim Territories, known for its shipyards.

properties.name: Bothawui
properties.poi: Tiaran'grast, Bothawui ShipyardsCombined Clans Center Building, Exoticalia Pet Emporium, Imperial consulate, Intergalactic Trade MissionMerchant's Square, Mesa 291,
properties.description: Bothawui ) was a cosmopolitan planet, located in the center of Bothan Space in the Mid Rim. It was the homeworld of the Bothan race as well as a major hub for information trafficking. It was also the center of the Bothan Spynet, widely agreed upon to be the best network of information gathering in the galaxy. The Imperial name for the planet was Bothawui Proper.

properties.name: Botor
properties.description: Botor was a planet located in the galaxy's Core Worlds that was home to the pirate faction known as the Flesh Mongers during the Republic Era. The youngling Lo was from Botor.

properties.name: Boudolayz
properties.description: Boudolayz was a planet in the Colonies.

properties.name: Bovo Yagen
properties.description: Bovo Yagen was a former Imperial captain who fled the Empire with his wife and four sons. After a period of wandering, the family landed on a planet with a humanoid species. Proving their good intentions to the natives, the family was allowed to settle on the world. Over time, more Humans fleeing the Empire arrived, forming a small outpost. By the time Yagen passed away, the planet bore his name.

properties.name: Boz Pity
properties.poi: Boz Pity base, Boz Pity Confederacy base, Gargantelle ruins,
properties.description: Boz Pity was a planet in the Boz Pity system of the Mid Rim. It was home to the sentient Gargantelle species, noted for their large stature. When the planet was discovered at some point before the end of the Ductavis Era, the Hutts attempted to enslave the species. After the Gargantelles repelled seven invasions and four diplomatic missions, the Hutts convinced the Electric Caliphs of Boz Pity's neighbor world Mourn to exterminate the species. The Gargantelles were slowly driven to extinction over the next decade, but erected a substantial amount of enormous gravestones to their fallen. When the species disappeared, these monuments earned Boz Pity the nickname "the graveyard planet," which prompted inhabitants of nearby systems to travel to the planet to bury their dead.

properties.name: Boztrok
properties.description: Boztrok was an Outer Rim world on the Hydian Way just outside Corporate Sector.

properties.name: Bpfassh
properties.description: Bpfassh was an arid double planet in the Sluis sector orbited by a complicated system of moons, located near Praesitlyn and Sluis Van. It was the homeworld of the Bpfasshi.

properties.name: Brachi
properties.description: Brachi was a planet located within the Brachi system of the Outer Rim Territories and the home to the Brachian Beastlord.

properties.name: Brachnis Chorios
properties.description: Brachnis Chorios was a cold, greenish-lavender planet on the outer edge of the Chorios systems, far from the triple stars and deep within the Meridian sector.

properties.name: Bragkis
properties.description: Bragkis was a gambling planet with a million-credits minimum betting parlor once visited by Han Solo.

properties.name: Bramior
properties.description: The Bramior system was a star system located within the Inner Rim. It contained at least one asteroid belt and the rogue moon Rove, which had been captured by the system's gravity well. The Luxury liner Cal Ambre and an Imperial frigate remained permanently in the system. At all times the frigate was never further than fifteen minutes away from the Cal Ambre, to provide protection.

properties.name: Branteez
properties.description: Branteez was a terrestrial world located in the Branteez system, a part of the Outer Rim Territories' Tolonda sector. At some point by the date 38:1:15, a Shrine of Kooroo, one of a number of stone structures of mysterious origins found on several Outer Rim worlds, had been uncovered on Branteez—a fact which the investigative reporter Andor Javin noted in a TriNebulon News report issued on that date.

properties.name: Brask Oto Command Station
properties.description: Brask Oto Command Station was a facility set up by the Chiss Ascendancy at the entry of The Redoubt. The station itself acted as a battle station.

properties.name: Breeka
properties.description: Breeka was a dry desert world. One of this world's native animals was a distant cousin to the dewbacks of Tatooine.

properties.name: Brella Temior
properties.description: The Brella Temior system was a star system that was located within the Colonies' Barma sector. The system shared its name with the Brella Temior crisis.

properties.name: Brentaal
properties.description: The Brentaal was a starship used by the Imperial Navy during the Imperial Era. It shared its name with the Core world Brentaal IV. In 14 BBY, the vessel was attached to Rampart Station, an Imperial marshaling depot for supply ships bound for the planet Geonosis, where the Imperial battle station later known as the Death Star was being constructed.

properties.name: Bresallis
properties.description: Bresallis was a planet located within the Bresallis system, which was located in the Cadma sector of the Outer Rim Territories. It was plagued by a criminal underworld run by the Hutts. Ambassador Walads opposed the Hutts, trying to disrupt their businesses. He was about to make a speech to the government on the subject when the Hutts hired Brahle Logris to assassinate him.

properties.name: Bresan
properties.description: Bresan was one of three primary planets in the Pimbrellan League. It was not as hospitable as nearby Dolstan. Its atmosphere could not sustain most humanoid life. Sealed dome cities were built in underground cave systems. Profits from trade with Dolstan were used to support life support facilities.

properties.name: Breshig
properties.description: Breshig was a planet in the Outer Rim Territories' Mandalore sector. Located within the Breshig system, Breshig was home to a species of small, dangerous creatures known as trill beasts. When the Mandalorian Crusaders set out from Mandalore in search of conquest, Breshig and its star system came under Mandalorian control along with the rest of what would become the Mandalore sector.

properties.name: Breshkall
properties.description: Breshkall was the refuge of arms dealer Prengahl Kreen. It was in a small and hidden fortress, located in a system of the same name in the Khuiumin sector of the Outer Rim Territories, past Lan Barell and the end of the Enarc Run. It served as home to his family, servants, and trusted associates, but was off limits for business transactions or uninvited visitation. Its location was not known by many, and the rumors of its heavy armament kept many from investigating rumors about the base.

properties.name: Bresnia
properties.description: Bresnia was a planet located in the Tandon sector of the Mid Rim.

properties.name: Breta Yaga
properties.description: Breta Yaga was an astronomical object located within the Breta Yaga system, a part of the Outer Rim Territories' Mieru'kar sector. Several art pieces called flatsculps that were produced by a non-Human species originated on Breta Yaga. The flatsculps were stored in the Mount Tantiss complex on the Ojoster sector planet Wayland by the time of the facility's destruction in 9 ABY. The New Republic historian Voren Na'al later mentioned Breta Yaga in his journal.

properties.name: Bretta
properties.description: Bretta was a location in the Ojoster sector of the Outer Rim Territories of the galaxy.

properties.name: Brevost
properties.description: Brevost was a planet in the Brevost system of the Expansion Region. It was on the Harrin Trade Corridor between the Krann system and the Cerenia system.

properties.name: Bri'ahl
properties.description: Bri'ahl was a planet located in the Bri'ahl sector of the Outer Rim Territories. It was inhabited by the Bri'ahls.

properties.name: Bridin Anchorage
properties.description: Bridin Anchorage, originally called Gallienis IV, was a planet in Portmoak sector. It was renamed after Quarlo Bridin, a con artist who took over the world shortly after Thrawn's death. It was once a lush world with beaches, but was covered in slums under Bridin's rule.

properties.name: Brightday
properties.description: Brightday was an astronomical object located in the Brightday system, in the Northern Dependencies portion of the Inner Rim. Brightday shared its name with the nearby Expansion Region celestial body Upper Brightday.

properties.name: Brigia
properties.description: Brigia was a planet in the Tion Hegemony of the Outer Rim, and the Brigian homeworld.

properties.name: Brink Station
properties.description: Brink Station was a space station orbiting outside the Chiloon Rift. The Red Ronto was situated aboard the station.

properties.name: Brint-wo
properties.description: Brint-wo was a large ringed planet that was home to the Brint-wo Colony.

properties.name: Brintooin
properties.description: Brintooin was an Outer Rim Territories planet located in the Seswenna sector. The planet's terrain included plains, marshes, and deserts, as well as scrub and woodlands. By the time of the conflict between the Galactic Empire and Rebel Alliance, Brintooin was selected as the baseworld for the Imperial Hammers Elite Armor Unit, and was populated by Humans fiercely loyal to the Empire.

properties.name: Briston
properties.description: Briston was a planet near Teardrop, in the Shelsha sector.

properties.name: Brochiib
properties.description: Brochiib was a Trianii colony planet in Trianii Space. Trianii Rangers Atuarre and Keeheen stopped thionarx dealers on the planet.

properties.name: Brodo Asogi
properties.description: Brodo Asogi, also known as the Green Planet, was a planet that was the homeworld of the Asogian species. It was located near the border of the Outer Rim Territories and Wild Space, nearby Kalee and Huk.

properties.name: Broest
properties.description: Broest was an agriworld in the Galactic Core, on the Ag Circuit. It was controlled by Salliche Ag Corporation.

properties.name: Brolsam
properties.description: Brolsam was a planet within the system of the same name in the Kathol sector of the Outer Rim Territories. An agriworld, it was located on a branch off the Trition Trade Route, between the sector capital Kal'Shebbol and Torize. Although its distance from the sector's major trade route hampered its economic growth, Brolsam developed an industry based primarily around agriculture due to the presence of a significant community of Fefze swarms. The planet also gained a reputation as an artist's retreat. In 8 ABY, the planet was on the brink of civil war following the disintegration of Imperial authority in the sector after the liberation of Kal'Shebbol by New Republic forces.

properties.name: Bromlarch
properties.description: Bromlarch was a planet in the Mid Rim's Vish sector that was linked to a planetary aqueduct system prior to 20 BBY. Naboo Senator Padmé Amidala and Scipio Senator Rush Clovis jointly prepared a Galactic Senate hearing to rescue Bromlarch's system, which was effective in saving a population from drought and famine.

properties.name: Bronsoon
properties.description: Bronsoon was a trading port on the original Gordian Reach founded by Human colonists from the Core in ancient times. Bronsoonians had strict rules about gender relations, with laws governing everything from marriage between casts to making eye contact and who could walk where. Inevitably, Bronsoonian drama was all about forbidden love between different casts. A slow, little-used route connected Bronsoon with the Maridun system.

properties.name: Bront
properties.description: Bront was a planet located within the Bront system, a part of the Outer Rim Territories' Svivreni sector. At some point by 0 ABY, the Human male Graf Yonna and his family lived on Bront.

properties.name: Brosi
properties.poi: Blan Forests, Delta 1, Delta 2, Forest Valley, Mailor, Nihun Valley, Reyno Valley, Shoengen Coast, Shoengen Delta, Shoengen Shores, Talbot Ridges, Taznel Mountains,
properties.description: Brosi was the homeworld of the Brosin species, in the Thandon Cluster, a remote place in the Corporate Sector. It was the fourth planet in the Dostra system, and one of the few homeworlds within the Corporate Sector.

properties.name: Bryexx
properties.description: Bryexx was a planet in Varvenna sector.

properties.name: Bryndar
properties.description: Bryndar was a planet that, during the Clone Wars, was in the middle of an ice age. That, along with its remoteness, made it the perfect spot for individuals such as smugglers to hide, which is what Flynn Kybo, B'dard Tone and Codi Ty did during their hunt for General Grievous.

properties.name: Bryx
properties.description: Bryx was a planet in the Bryx sector of the Mid Rim.

properties.name: Bseto
properties.description: Bseto was a white dwarf found in the Bseto system. It was orbited by three planets, Bseto I, Indikir and Sarahwiee. Between Indikir and Sarahwiee was the Lweilot Asteroid Belt.

properties.name: Buamlon Central
properties.description: Buamlon Central was a planet located in the system of the same name, situated in the Esstran sector of the Outer Rim Territories. It was a dangerous world, and was staked by Barosa Warren, a scout serving with the Republic Survey Corps.

properties.name: Bubble of the Lost
properties.description: The Bubble of the Lost was a location at the heart of the Chiloon Rift, considered an area of ghost ships by the Rift asteroid miners. The monolith at the Bubble's center bent space-time outwards , so that two points in space and time within the Bubble would maintain their distance relative to each other, while the distance between them actually grew as space-time expanded. Because of time dilation — five years spent inside Bubble was close to just one year outside in the Rift.

properties.name: Buchich
properties.description: Buchich was a planet in the Buchich system in the Outer Rim Territories. Part of the Calamari sector, the Quarren species colonized the planet for mining resources to keep up with the Mon Calamari's work in shipbuilding.

properties.name: Budpock
properties.description: Budpock was a long time supporter of the Rebel Alliance and a New Republic-aligned planet in the Meridian sector. However, the world was also a haven for pirate gangs. Many of these groups were provoked by Dzym to attack neighboring Ampliquen, breaking the truce between Budpock and Ampliquen.

properties.name: Bulano
properties.description: The Bulano system was a star system located within the Core Worlds region of the galaxy.

properties.name: Bulwark
properties.description: Bulwark was a planet located in the Bulwark system of Wild Space. During the Galactic Civil War, Bulwark served as a Rebel Alliance safe world—a designated planet where people connected with the Alliance could live free of Imperial oppression. It was also among the few sites to which the Rebels allocated one of their v-150 Planet Defender ion cannons.

properties.name: Bundil
properties.description: Bundil was a planet in the Outer Rim Territories.

properties.name: Bundim
properties.description: Bundim was a planet in Trax sector where the Rebel Alliance lost the Battle of Heg. Commander Resner believed that Bundim was base of operations for the Alliance forces that began rebelling in Trax Sector, shortly after the Battle of Yavin. The planetary government secretly attempted to remove the Imperial presence from the planet, but an inside source alerted the Empire to Bundim's plans.

properties.name: Bunduki
properties.description: Bunduki was a planet in the Pacanth Reach. It was home to the Followers of Palawa, who developed the martial art of Teräs Käsi. Many of the Followers, including Arden Lyn, fell to the dark side of the Force and joined the Minions of Xendor. The planet was conquered by the Epicanthix.

properties.name: Buoyant
properties.description: Buoyant was an Inner Rim planet that was terraformed by a sentient species millennia before 54 BBY. The alterations made to Buoyant by the terraformers included an increased rotation rate as well as lush vegetation and imported animals, among them a long-necked herd quadruped.

properties.name: Burnin Konn
properties.description: Burnin Konn was a planet that was located in the Burnin Konn system within Anoat sector, situated in the midst of the Ivax Nebula. One of the sector's four Mining Worlds, Burnin Konn was strip-mined for ore including dolovite and kammris; as a result of this, the native vegetation was completely destroyed. At the time of the Galactic Civil War, the planet was controlled by Figg business interests.

properties.name: Burska
properties.description: Burska was a little-known tundra planet located in the Mid Rim's freestanding subsectors. It had frequent, large-diameter hail and was home to a thick-hided, passive offshoot of the gundark species.

properties.name: Buruunin
properties.description: Buruunin was a planet located in the Atravis sector of the Outer Rim Territories. It was the site of an Imperial assault that resulted in heavy civilian casualties.

properties.name: Byblos
properties.poi: Byblos Starport Tower 214, University of ByblosByblos Drive Yards
properties.description: Byblos was a planet in the Colonies known for its technological advances. Byblos also made a name for itself through the company BlasTech Industries, which was founded during the era of the Old Republic. At the time of the Galactic Empire, the planet was considered one of the busiest and most important planets in the Colonies. However, Byblos was affected by the suppression of several alien species that were declared slaves by the Empire.

properties.name: Byllura
properties.description: Byllura was a forested world located within the Grumani sector in the Outer Rim region of the galaxy.

properties.name: Byrsym
properties.description: Byrsym was a planet that was located in the Mid Rim Territories.

properties.name: Byss
properties.poi: Desolation Peak, Emerald Splendor Estates, Emperor's Citadel, Imperial Freight Complex, Rakatan stronghold,
