properties.description: Byss was a planet in the Deep Core, near the center of the galaxy, discovered no earlier than 45 BBY. A local day lasted 31 standard hours, and a local year lasted 207 local days. It was the endpoint of the Byss Run.

properties.name: C-Foroon
properties.description: C-Foroon was a planet in the Arkanis sector of the Outer Rim.

properties.name: Caamas
properties.description: Caamas was a highly populated and marsh-covered Core World in the Cirius system, the second planet orbiting the star Cirius. It was notable for the devastation it suffered during an Imperial orbital bombardment which destroyed its ecosystem and nearly wiped out the native Caamasi.

properties.name: Caaraz
properties.description: Caaraz was a tide-locked, tectonically active planet in the Outer Rim. Its night-side was frozen with glaciers. Its day-side was scorching. In between was a thin, habitable region in which the Ranth race evolved. Both sides of the planet were tectonically active as well, allowing subterranean gases, lava, and steam to escape into the atmosphere. The Galactic Empire discovered the world while looking for Rebel bases, and later mined the planet. Two moons also provided illumination to the night-side of the planet.

properties.name: Caarimon
properties.description: Caarimon was a warm and steamy planet in the Outer Rim Territories.

properties.name: Caarsin Station
properties.description: Caarsin Station was a Space station located in the Lannik Wilds, in the Mid Rim.

properties.name: Cadannia
properties.description: Cadannia was a planet in the Mid Rim region of the galaxy presumably completely, or mostly covered in dense jungles or forests that produced some of the galaxy's strongest toxins.

properties.name: Cademimu
properties.description: Cademimu V, also simply referred to as Cademimu, was a planet in the Cademimu sector along the Celanon Spur.

properties.name: Cadinth
properties.description: Cadinth was one of the original worlds in the Kingdom of Cron, and later Xim's empire. At the time of the Galactic Empire, Cadinth was a wealthy port and desert world in the Allied Tion sector. Its natural beauty was destroyed by industrialization, as was that of its neighbor, Lianna, leaving deserts of black sands and howling winds. Scattered in the wastes were the ruins of ancestral civilizations. Its population was concentrated in gloomy, sharp-featured cities that self-consciously evoked the distant past.

properties.name: Cadma
properties.description: Cadma could refer to one of the following:

properties.name: Cadomai
properties.description: Cadomai Prime, also known as simply Cadomai, was a planet located in the galaxy's Outer Rim Territories, situated along the Hydian Way that was the homeworld of the Snivvian species. The winters of Cadomai Prime were very harsh for the Snivvians to survive, during which they spent the time in underground caverns in artistic pursuits. Some did escape the icy tundras to become bounty hunters offworld.

properties.name: Cal-Seti
properties.description: Cal-Seti was a planet located several sectors from N'zoth. It was at the intersection of the Agricultural Circuit and the Metellos Trade Route.

properties.name: Calast
properties.description: Calast was a civilian Golan Space Colony 2 space station in the Calast system.

properties.name: Calfa
properties.description: Calfa-5 was a planet that orbited a single star, which baked its desert moons.

properties.name: Calgon
properties.description: Calgon was a planet located in the Meridian sector of the Outer Rim Territories.

properties.name: Calipsa
properties.description: Calipsa was a planet located in the Calipsa Province of the Tapani sector. From space, it was a dull, brown, almost lifeless world. Calipsa was a brown world of little vegetation, rich in natural ores. It was dominated by mining operations which caused much air pollution and hazy air, not entirely suitable for Human consumption. The raw materials mined from the systems of the Calipsa Province were shipped to Calipsa where they were processed into alloys for export. One of its few untouched wildernesses was the Crystal Forest.

properties.name: Calline
properties.description: Calline was the primary star of the Calline system. The planets Calline I, II, and III orbited the star.

properties.name: Callonia
properties.description: Callonia was a planet in the Fakir sector of the Colonies.

properties.name: Callos
properties.poi: Callos planetary reactor, Clawfish Roaming Auction of Illicit and Illegal Weaponry,
properties.description: Callos was a planet of the Brema sector in the Outer Rim Territories. It was once teeming with animal and plant life, until it was devastated by the Galactic Empire in 3 BBY.

properties.name: Calonica
properties.description: Calonica was an Imperial planet. The planet's capital was surrounded by 50,000 LX-2 comlink mines, but a spot inspection found that less than ten percent of the mines contained explosive charges. An investigation revealed that the Alliance to Restore the Republic had discovered the mine's comm code and disarmed them remotely. Then they were dug up, the explosives removed, and buried back in the ground.

properties.name: Caloria
properties.description: Caloria was a minor tradeworld located in the Tapani sector's Caloria system in the Reena Province. It was an endpoint of the Caloria Run.

properties.name: Caltinia
properties.description: Caltinia was the lush Human-inhabited homeworld of House Elegin, famous for its hundreds of dueling fields surrounded by numerous mausoleums, temples, and museums celebrating and mourning epic duels of the past. Caltinia was once visited by Lando Calrissian.

properties.name: Calus
properties.description: Calus was a planet in the Calus system of the Inner Rim, near Bestine IV. Sweet-sand cookies were made on Calus. It was located at the end of Keller's Void, opposite Wroona.

properties.name: Caluula
properties.description: Caluula was a planet that made up part of the Kingdom of Cron and later Xim's Empire during the Pre-Republic era. After the empire's collapse, Caluula became part of the Tion Hegemony. Near the end of the Yuuzhan Vong War, the Yuuzhan Vong conquered the planet and sent approximately one-third of its population to Coruscant for sacrifice. The planet was the site of a battle between the Yuuzhan Vong and the Galactic Alliance.

properties.name: Cambria
properties.description: Cambria was an astronomical object located in the galaxy's Deep Core.

properties.name: Camden
properties.description: Camden was an Outer Rim Imperial planet in the Camden system. The Snakes' Den starport was on Camden.

properties.name: Candoria
properties.description: Candoria was a depopulated planet located in the Colonies region of the galaxy.

properties.name: Canoliss
properties.description: Canoliss may refer to one of the following:

properties.name: Canti
properties.description: Canti was a planet located in the Tapani sector's Canti system. A secret hyperlane ran from Canti out of the sector. The existence of the route was closely guarded by House Reena.

properties.name: Cantras Gola
properties.description: Cantras Gola was a planet in the Pentastar Alignment. It was a corporate planet controlled by PowerOn Conglomerate. During the Thrawn Crisis, it decided to leave the Pentastar Alignment and join the New Republic. The Alignment threatened to kill the children of the Ambassador of Cantras Gola if he had any sort of meeting with the New Republic. The children had been taken by slavers to Gabredor III. They were rescued by a Red Moons mercenary team, allowing Cantras Gola to join the New Republic.

properties.name: Canyon
properties.description: Canyon was a planet of arid mountains and plains in the Expansion Region, near Moorja.

properties.name: Capella
properties.description: Capella was a planet in the Gordian Reach of the Outer Rim.

properties.name: Caprioril
properties.poi: Doolis Podrace Arena, Swo-O'Rim racing circuit
properties.description: Caprioril was a planet located in the Core Worlds, near Chandrila. It was the site of the infamous Caprioril Massacre.

properties.name: Capza
properties.description: Capza was a lush, tropical planet in the Velcar Free Commerce Zone. It was also home to Commerce Master Commissioner Gregor Raquoran.

properties.name: Carcel
properties.description: Carcel was a planet located in the Expansion Region, and was described by Tobb Jadak as a miserable piece of rock. Carcel had a prison that Jadak and Flitcher Poste visited Rej Taunt in.

properties.name: Carconth
properties.description: A red supergiant, Carconth was five hundred times as large and a hundred thousand times as bright as Coruscant Prime, making it the second-largest and seventh-brightest of the known stars in the galaxy. At the time of the Black Fleet Crisis, the Astrographic Survey Institute and its predecessors had been maintaining supernova watch at Carconth for more than six hundred years. Carconth was the site of New Republic Intelligence Service Anomaly 1033, theorised to be something left behind by a past alien expedition to Carconth.

properties.name: Cardooine
properties.description:
Cardooine was a planet in the Jospro sector of the Outer Rim.
It was where the Rebel Alliance built A-wings used in the Battle of Endor. It was also the home of Fijisi wood, used in sections of the Imperial Palace on Coruscant and other high-class buildings. Less pleasantly, the disease Cardooine Chills also originated on this planet.

properties.name: Cargamalis
properties.description: Cargamalis was an astronomical object in the Mugaari Space's Javin Sector. At some point prior to the Battle of Endor, Cargamalis was subjected to Street Wars, in which the human "Happy" Dapp and the Aqualish Bohento Splinth fought.

properties.name: Carida
properties.poi: Carida Corsairs' baseCaridan districtForgofshar Desert, Officer's Candidate SchoolRessl River, Spinara PlateauAcademy of CaridaDean's ResidenceImperial Navy Command Officer's SchoolStorm Commando SchoolTarkin's Teeth
properties.description: Carida, originally known as Ord Carida, was a planet of the Colonies region of the galaxy, near the Perlemian Trade Route, and the homeworld of the Caridan race.

properties.name: Carlac
properties.poi: Ming Po townDeath Watch camp104th Battalion Republic Outpost, Crashed Munificent-class star frigate,
properties.description: Carlac was a peaceful, snow-covered planet in the Outer Rim Territories. A town inhabited by members of the Ming Po culture existed on the planet during the Clone Wars. However, that village was burned to the ground by the Death Watch, a radical Mandalorian terrorist group.

properties.name: Carlania
properties.description: The Carlania system was located in the Interior Region, an area of the Hapes Cluster in the Slice portion of the Inner Rim. It was connected via hyperlanes to the Arabanth and Ediorung systems. The Carlania system was the origin point of the Carlanian volcanic pipes.

properties.name: Carlix's Folly
properties.description: Carlix's Folly was one of the many planetary haunts of Captain Ellin Lah and her crew from Woebegone frequented.

properties.name: Carnovia
properties.description: Carnovia was a planet located in Hutt Space that was home to Carnovian eel-pups. It was a humid world largely covered by water. The Floating Palace, the headquarters of the Vermilic kajidic, was situated on the world.

properties.name: Carnth
properties.description: Carnth was a world ruled by the Galactic Empire.

properties.name: Carosi
properties.description: Carosi was the primary star in the Carosus system. In 200 BBY the five innermost planets were destroyed when it expanded into a red giant.

properties.name: Carratos
properties.poi: Smugglers' Bridge Tunnel, Imperial Garrison, Casinos,
properties.description: Carratos was a planet in the Inner Rim, roughly forty parsecs from Coruscant.

properties.name: Carrivar
properties.description: Carrivar was an astronomical object in the Unknown Regions' Carrivar system. The sentient species Hemes Arbora was native to Carrivar but eventually abandoned the celestial body. The Hemes Arbora migrated first to the planet Umaren'k in the Umaren'k system and later to the planet Osseriton. In 80 BBY, Succate, a chronicler from Carrivar, assembled the largest collection of information on the Sorcerers of Rhand, a group of beings who believed in the philosophical concept known as the Dark.

properties.name: Carsanza
properties.description: Carsanza was a minor industrial world located in the Carsanza system of the Juvex sector, a part of the Senex-Juvex region in the Western Reaches portion of the Mid Rim. Hyperlanes connected Carsanza to the Malador, Valorsi, and Zyluria systems. Like the rest of the Senex-Juvex worlds, Carsanza was under the control of the region's aristocratic Ancient Houses.

properties.name: Cartao
properties.description: Cartao was a planet in the Prackla sector. The siviviv vine was native to Cartao, and it was the homeworld of the Cranscoc.

properties.name: Carto
properties.description: Carto  was a male Human agent of the Imperial Intelligence of the Sith Empire. During the Galactic War he was stationed on the Vaiken Spacedock.

properties.name: Carz
properties.description: Carz was a moon in the Svivreni sector of the Outer Rim.

properties.name: Casfield
properties.description: Casfield was the Casfield system's primary star.

properties.name: Cassander
properties.description: Cassander was the chief planet of the Cassandran sectors. It was the sector capital of Cassander sector under the New Order, and it was on the Braxant Run.

properties.name: Castell
properties.description: Castell was a terrestrial planet located along the Perlemian Trade Route in the Colonies region of the galaxy. The homeworld of the Gossam, Castell was a major foundry planet for the Commerce Guild.

properties.name: Cataalda
properties.description: Cataalda was a planet in a seldom-traveled part of the Mid Rim.

properties.name: Cathar
properties.description: The Cathar were a species of feline, bipedal humanoids native to Cathar, a planet of savannas and rough uplands. They were known for their loyalty, passion, and temper. Quick and powerful, they were considered great warriors and dedicated, efficient predators.

properties.name: Cathis
properties.description: Cathis was a planet in the Jjannex sector of the Outer Rim Territories. It was the site of a Alliance to Restore the Republic starfighter base during the Galactic Civil War.

properties.name: Catlia
properties.description: Catlia was a planet that was located within the Catlia system, in the Chiss Space area of the galaxy's Unknown Regions. It was connected by the Phalanx Route hyperlane to the planet Cormit. Catlia was an outlying colony of the sentient Chiss species, and was home to one of the Ruling Families that ruled over the Chiss Ascendancy, the government of the Chiss.

properties.name: Cato Neimoidia
properties.poi: Bridge citiesNute Gunray's citadelDarga the Hutt's palaceFederation's FollyLott Dod's palace
properties.description: The oldest of the Neimoidian purse worlds, Cato Neimoidia was the location of Nute Gunray's secret redoubt. The planet was near the Neimoidian homeworld of Neimoidia, also in the Colonies region.

properties.name: Cattamascar
properties.description: Cattamascar was a planet in the Bakura sector of the Outer Rim.

properties.name: Caulbon
properties.description: Caulbon was a planet located in the Inner Rim.

properties.name: Cauldron Nebula
properties.description: The Cauldron Nebula was a nebula located within the Corva sector in the Outer Rim Territories. Consisting of seven supergiant blue stars, the nebula was home to the Eol Sha system, where a colony was set up in preparation for a mining operation intended to harvest valuable gases from the nebula through the use of ramjet mining ships.

properties.name: Caulus Tertius
properties.description: Caulus Tertius was a planet located in the Inner Rim. No life existed on the planet, although there was evidence to suggest it once supported life. An ophidian grotesque sculpture had been discovered at some point in galactic history, which had been much older than the one found on Coruscant. This sculpture, alongside its Coruscanti counterpart, were later mentioned by Dr. Insmot Bowen in a debriefing in 1 BBY on Coruscant, where he mentioned that it might have been one of the remaining hints to the Celestials. Years later, Luke Skywalker remembered several "ophidian grotesque" sculptures, which he remarked were similar to those found on Abeloth's planet.

properties.name: Cauper
properties.description: The Cauper system was a star system located in the Tapani sector's Melantha Province, between the Ricaldi and Bilios systems.

properties.name: Caursito
properties.description: Caursito was a planet in the Colonies that Lieutenant Mavron stopped at to pick up a copy of the TriNebulon News on his way back to the Star Destroyer Chimaera during the Caamas Document Crisis.

properties.name: Cegul
properties.description: Cegul may refer to one of the following:

properties.name: Cejansij
properties.description: Cejansij was the Cejansiji homeworld. It was known for its canyon dwellings.

properties.name: Cel Amiin
properties.description: Cel Amiin was a remote planet in the Expansion Region of the galaxy that defied Emperor Palpatine shortly after the formation of the Galactic Empire. Like the other worlds that refused to cooperate, Cel Amiin suffered an unspecified devastation as a result.

properties.name: Celanon
properties.poi: Arradi, , Cekbar, , Celanon Merchant Guild Medical FacilityCelanon Spaceport, , Celanon Spaceport ControlDesetur, , Gularg's Libation Emporium, Holvi, , Jelldar, , Runnor, , Teelian's Electronic EmporiumUnidentified Celanon bar
properties.description: Celanon was an important spaceport on the Celanon Spur, in the Outer Rim Territories, and was the Nalroni homeworld.

properties.name: Celdaru
properties.description: The Celdaru system was a star system that was located within the Wild Space region of the galaxy. It lay outside the borders of space controlled by the New Republic in 12 ABY. The system shared its name with the epithet "Scourge of Celdaru," which was self-assumed by the Imperial technician Sulamar.

properties.name: Celegia
properties.description: Celegia was an Expansion Region world of raging seas. Its atmosphere was rich in the toxic cyanogen gas, and it was the homeworld of the sentient Celegians. Due to oxygen being lethal to the Celegians, they had to use special life support chambers when traveling off-world. Celegia had become a part of the Galactic Republic by approximately 17,000 BBY and was a member of the Galactic Empire in 17 BBY.

properties.name: Celen
properties.description: Celen was a planet in the Halla sector of the Mid Rim of The galaxy. A terrestrial world with a Human population, they raised nerfs as well as banthas.

properties.name: Celwis
properties.description: Celwis was a planet of the Chiss Ascendancy in the Celwis system of the Unknown Regions. It was located on the Vagaari Corridor, a hyperlane that ran through the Unknown Regions. Celwis was once regularly attacked by alien aggressors, but it eventually became a demonstration of Chiss military strength shortly after the formation of the Chiss Expansionary Defense Force.

properties.name: Centares
properties.poi: Rubyflame Lake, Museum of the Old Republic, The Aviary,
properties.description: Centares was a planet in the Maldrood sector of the Mid Rim. It had a temperate climate and no moons.

properties.name: Cerea
properties.description: Cerea was a planet located in the Mid Rim region of the galaxy. The homeworld of the Cerean species, Cerea was notable for its inhabitants' harmonious relationship with nature. Technology and pollution were frowned upon by the conservative government, a major point in the planet's decision not to join the Galactic Republic. The Cerean population mainly lived in giant buildings that took up a minimum of space, allowing the remainder of the planet's area to be employed as farmland. Foreign immigrants and visitors were, with a few exceptions, only allowed in Cerea's Outsider Citadels, enormous buildings erected to let non-Cereans practice their technological ways. This ensured that the foreigners' technology did not contaminate Cerea's nature, but also led to a concentration of criminal elements within the Citadels.

properties.name: Cerenia
properties.description: Ruten, or Cerenia, was a planet in the Cerenia system of the Expansion Region. The New Republic liberated the planet from Imperial Governor Bursthed. The planet hosted the Ruten Pet Show.

properties.name: Ceriun
properties.description: Ceriun was a terrestrial world that was located in the Ceriun system of the Outer Rim Territories. Around 1000 BBY, a tattooed Sith Lord journeyed to the planet to retrieve a Sith holocron that had been taken there by a Jedi.

properties.name: Cerroban
properties.description: Cerroban was a world located in the Bon'nyuw-Luq sector of the Outer Rim Territories. Following the Battle of Yavin, the world was scouted by Rebel Alliance forces seeking for a new base. Cerroban was a waterless and airless rocky world that was pounded by asteroids regularly.

properties.name: Cesya
properties.description: The Cesya system was a star system located in the Tapani sector's Cadriaan Province, between the Listoria and Achillea systems.

properties.name: Ceti 597
properties.description: Ceti 597 was a planet in the Mid-Rim.

properties.name: Ch'hodos
properties.description: Ch'hodos was a rocky desert planet that orbited a red sun within the Outer Rim Territories' Sith Worlds region. Ch'hodos was considered a lesser world of the Sith Empire and served as the central base of the Sith Lord Shar Dakhan by the year 5000 BBY.

properties.name: Ch'manss
properties.description: The Ch'manss system was a star system located on the Gevarno Loop within the Mid Rim. Its inhabitants were Loyalists to the Galactic Republic during the Clone Wars.

properties.name: Chabosh
properties.description: Chabosh was a planet located in the Chabosh system within the galaxy's Outer Rim Territories. The planet was the site of the Battle of Chabosh where Sith Lord Tulak Hord, his apprentice Ortan Cela, and their Dashade Shadow Killers Khem Val and Veshikk Urk led Sith Empire to victory over the rebel and Jedi forces stationed on the planet following the Battle of Yn. Thousands of years later, Chabosh was home to a small Rebel Alliance base wiped out by the Galactic Empire's Captain Harsh aboard the Star Destroyer Cauldron during the Battle of Chabosh.

properties.name: Chad
properties.description: The planet Chad  or Chad III) was the homeworld of the Chadra-Fan race. It was in the Outer Rim Territories, more specifically in the Slice.

properties.name: Chalacta
properties.description: Chalacta was a Mid Rim planet, homeworld of the Chalactan Adepts.

properties.name: Chalcedon
properties.description: Chalcedon was a planet in Tashtor sector of the Mid Rim.

properties.name: Challon
properties.description: Challon was a planet in the Core Worlds that remained neutral during the Galactic Civil War. While on Challon, Leia Organa tried to convince local Governor Tchai to support the Rebel Alliance. Organa was forced to kill Giles Durane, her "weapons master," in self-defense.

properties.name: Chamble
properties.description: Chamble was a planet in the Mid Rim where Bansche Tech was headquartered. After the Battle of Yavin, the corporation was nationalized by the Empire, dealing a heavy blow to the Ralltiir Exchange.

properties.name: Chamm
properties.description: The Chamm system was located in the Southern Core portion of the Core Worlds. It was the origin point of the material known as Chammian ivory and fell within the borders of the Galactic Republic during the Clone Wars.

properties.name: Champala
properties.description: Champala, also called "Chagria," was a planet in the Inner Rim and the homeworld of the Chagrian people. Most of its starports were high and dry on plateaus, but its cities were submerged at high tide. It was a popular resort world.

properties.name: Chandaar
properties.description: Chandaar was the throneworld of the Kingdom of Cron following the death of Xim the Despot, it had been conquered by Xim's father. Many years later, it became capital of the Cronese Mandate under the Galactic Empire and was the headquarters of numerous Cronese mining companies. It was known as the "Jewel of the Tion", but by the time of the Galactic Civil War, the Cronese Kings were mere figureheads and the planet was a polluted urban world, covered with both decaying cities and ancient ruins.

properties.name: Chandrila
properties.poi: Brionelle Memorial Military Academy, Crystal Canyons, Gladean State Parks, Hanna Institute of Antiquities, Lake Sah'ot, Silver Sea,
properties.description: Chandrila was an agriworld located in the Chandrila system of the Core Worlds' Bormea sector. The planet had two continents and two moons—Chandra and Chandrakant—and lay on the Perlemian Trade Route. The world was relatively rural, though it had 1.2 billion residents and was home to several cities.

properties.name: Chanosant
properties.description: Chanosant was a world in the Expansion Region's Chanosant system. During the Clone Wars, it was the site of a Separatist convention which was attended by Count Dooku and held during the Clone Wars. Dooku and Kob Mondray attended it and tried to use it to rally more support for the CIS.

properties.name: Chardaan
properties.description: Chardaan was an Inner Rim world that lay at the intersection of the Hydian Way and Shipwrights' Trace. The planet was orbited by the Chardaan Shipyards.

properties.name: Charenthoth
properties.description: Charenthoth was a planet. It was named in the battle chant of the Legion of Alderaan, alongside mentions of Alderaan, Tatooine and Hoth.

properties.name: Charis
properties.description: Charis was a planet in the system of the same name on the Trition Trade Route in the Kathol sector of the Outer Rim Territories. An important industrial base for the sector, the population of the planet staged an uprising against the local Imperial warlord—Moff Kentor Sarne—and his forces in 4 ABY. Sarne's forces assaulted the world, laying waste to many of the major cities and reducing the planetary population from one billion to 850 million. Following the disintegration of Sarne's authority in the sector with the New Republic's liberation of the sector capital Kal'Shebbol in 8 ABY, the population of Charis prepared to stage a second uprising to free their world.

properties.name: Charmath
properties.poi: College of Astrocartography, University of Charmath
properties.description: Charmath was a planet in the Farrfin sector of the Galactic Core with one of the galaxy's most complete historical archives.

properties.name: Charra
properties.description: Charra was a planet in the Expansion Region that produced caf.

properties.name: Charros
properties.description: Charros was the primary star of the Charros system.

properties.name: Charubah
properties.description: Charubah was a technology-oriented planet located within the Hapes Cluster, and famed for their Guns of Command designed by Royal Armaments Guild of Charubah.

properties.name: Chashima
properties.description: Chashima was a temperate and forested planet with fields of drymoss in the Chashima system of the Auril sector. During the Yuuzhan Vong War, the extragalactic Yuuzhan Vong set up a research facility for shapers working on the commbuzzer, a type of beetle designed to home in on comlink transmissions. The facility was sabotaged in 29 ABY by Wraith Squadron, but the operation came at the cost of Wraiths Estoric Sandskimmer and Hohass Ekwesh.

properties.name: Chasin
properties.description: Chasin was a planet of the Core Worlds.

properties.name: Chaykin
properties.description: Delta Squad had commandeered a Separatist ship and were located in the Chaykin sector when they responded to the Red Zero distress call broadcast by Omega Squad approximately one year after the First Battle of Geonosis.

properties.name: Chazwa
properties.poi: Fallone compound, Gold Plaza, Landing Bay 29, North Market, South Market, The Clog, The Stones, Warehouse district,
properties.description: Chazwa was a cold planet in the Chazwa system of the Orus sector, located in the Inner Rim. Its location along a popular freighter traffic route made it an ideal shipping center for all sorts of goods. As such, heavy freighter traffic within the system was not an uncommon sight. However, the abundance of valuable merchandise moving through the system lent itself to strong influence by smugglers.

properties.name: Cheelit
properties.description: Cheelit was a planet in the Cheelit system, located in the Mid Rim's Semagi sector along the Cerean Reach. Cheelit was home to the J'feh, a race of sentient cephalopoids that lived within large, floating globes. Cheelit's ornate Hive Palace was the home of the Lady Dhol during the era of the Galactic Civil War, until Dhol hired the Guild of Vindicators assassin Clat the Shamer to kill the Sith Lord Darth Vader during a game of firepath—Vader anticipated her treachery and killed them both. Another J'feh, Skijid Vrescot, ruled as the Count of Cheelit during the later years of the Galactic Republic.

properties.name: Cheeyoom Matee
properties.description: Cheeyoom Matee was a planet home to a Rebel base. It was located in the Core Worlds.

properties.name: Chekria
properties.description: Chekria was a planet that was the target of attacks by pirates.

properties.name: Chelleya
properties.description: Chelleya was an astronomical object located within the Chelleya system of the Outer Rim Territories' Seswenna sector.

properties.name: Chelloa
properties.poi: The garden vale of Clains, Daiman's compound, Jenith Spaceport, Squatter's Hill,
properties.description: Chelloa was a terrestrial planet in the Grumani sector in Outer Rim Territories. It was first settled by the Galactic Republic as an agricultural world. During the Republic Dark Age, the planet was occupied by the Chagras Hegemony. Following the death of Sith Lord Chagras, the planet fell under the domain of his nephew Daiman, ruler of the Daimanate fiefdom. Daiman discovered large deposits of baradium beneath the planet's surface and implemented large scale mining and processing to supply his war effort. The mining operations depopulated much of the planet and attracted the attention of both the Jedi Order and Daiman's estranged brother Odion, fellow Sith Lord and ruler of the Odionate.

properties.name: Chennis
properties.description: Chennis was a planet in the Expansion Region that had lost its bacta manufacturing capability.

properties.name: Chenowei
properties.description: Chenowei was a planet in the Gordian Reach of the Outer Rim.

properties.name: Cheravh
properties.description: Cheravh was a planet in the Outer Rim Territories' Mandalore sector, located within the Cheravh system. Like most worlds contained within the surrounding sector, Cheravh was covered in hard frontier country, and came under the control of the Mandalorians following their expanding conquest of the sector during their time as Mandalorian Crusaders.

properties.name: Cheruba
properties.description: The Cheruba system was located in the Rifle Worlds, an area of the Hapes Cluster in the Slice portion of the Inner Rim. It was connected to the Charubah and Relephon systems via the hyperlane known as the Gallinore Reach. The Cheruba system shared its name with the competitions known as the Cheruban glach races.

properties.name: Chibias
properties.description: Chibias was a Mid Rim world near Sibisime.

properties.name: Chiloon Rift
properties.description: The Chiloon Rift was a nebula that contained one of the largest and most bountiful asteroid fields in the galaxy. There were many unclaimed asteroids filled with valuable minerals in the rift, and it was a place of opportunity for miners in 45 ABY. However, clouds of plasma and its field of asteroids made it difficult to navigate, and a pilot needed quick reflexes to avoid obstacles and land on worlds within the rift.

properties.name: Chiron
properties.description: Chiron was a lieutenant of the Galactic Empire, stationed at the Academy for Young Imperials on Lothal. He was an enthusiastic officer who would often lead Imperial cadets in song during morning runs. Chiron took a special liking to one such cadet the Academy, Zare Leonis, believing him to be a fine example of a model officer and often tried to protect Leonis from the more officious bureaucrats within the Academy.

properties.name: Chirrion
properties.description: Chirrion was a planet located in the of the Rolion sector of the Outer Rim Territories.

properties.name: Choi
properties.description: Choi was a world located in the Inner Rim. It was the homeworld of the Choi species.

properties.name: Chokan
properties.description: Chokan was a planet on the Gamor Run in the Mid Rim's Maerdocian sector.

properties.name: Cholganna
properties.poi: Indona, Tethyrr River Valley, The Retreat,
properties.description: Cholganna was a planet best known for its cool forests and dangerous creatures. It was home to the nexu, a predatory feline. Animals such as the arboreal octopus and the bark rat were also plentiful on the planet. Both were known prey of the nexu.

properties.name: Chommell Minor
properties.description: Chommell Minor was a planet near Naboo.

properties.name: Chorax
properties.description: Chorax was a planet in the Rachuk sector, which lay between Commenor and Talasea. It was the sole planet of the Chorax system, a haven for pirates and smugglers.

properties.name: Chortose
properties.description: Chortose was an astronomical object located in the Chortose system, a part of the Outer Rim Territories' Rseik sector. It was the homeworld of the sentient Chortose species, including the engineer and starship mechanic Porgo Goo.

properties.name: Chosper
properties.description: Chosper was a planet in the Lorelli Reach region of the Hapes Cluster. The phrase "Nimbus of Chosper" was used as an oath.

properties.name: Chrellis
properties.description: Chrellis was a tiny planetoid located in the Chrellis system, a part of the Lahara sector in the New Territories portion of the Outer Rim Territories. Following the foundation of the Rebel Alliance in 2 BBY, the first base of the Alliance High Command, named Chrellis Base, was established on the planetoid under the command of the Human General Jan Dodonna.

properties.name: Christophsis
properties.description: Christophsis was a crystalline world in the Outer Rim Territories' Savareen sector. Orbited by a single moon amongst the mineral-rich asteroids of the Christoph system, Christophsis was for a time a target for stray rocks because of its closeness to various asteroid belts, but the planet was refined by Tepasi nobles around 600 BBY, and later by the world's native Christophsian inhabitants, who originated as Humans from the Core. Christophsis was eventually protected from the asteroids and transformed into the center of a mining hub. By the time of the Clone Wars, the Christophsians ruled their homeworld in a mercantile oligarchy and had established Chaleydonia, also known as Crystal City, as their planet's capital. Various species also immigrated to the world, including Rodians, Kerkoidens, and lower-caste Humans who came to serve the Christophsians.

properties.name: Chroma Zed
properties.description: Chroma Zed was a terrestrial planet located in the Maerdocian sector of the galaxy's Mid Rim. Home to the wormlike humanoid Chromans, who lived in moist mountain burrows near water, the planet featured some of the most magnificent amphitheater facilities, including one with twin waterfalls.

properties.name: Chromovon
properties.description: Chromovon was a planet that contained an Imperial prison.

properties.name: Chrona
properties.description: Chrona was an agriworld in the Inner Rim, on the Vaathkree Trade Corridor. Banthas were raised and primacale crops were grown on the planet. During the final days of the Galactic Republic, chronamite was discovered on the planet.

properties.name: Chryya
properties.description: Chryya was a planet with a thriving spice business. It was located in the Mid Rim, on the Hydian Way near the border of the Outer Rim Territories. Darth Maul was once sent on a mission to this planet by Darth Sidious to convince the miners to sell to the Trade Federation. Maul's failure to convince them was his only failure prior to the Invasion of Naboo.

properties.name: Churruma
properties.description: Churruma was a planet with deposits of valuable metals that was located within the Velcar sector of the Outer Rim Territories. During the Galactic Civil War, the Galactic Empire mined Churruma's metals and captured the shaman Chrech Estha, a respected leader of the planet's natives who possessed a carved stick that served as a powerful political and religious symbol on his homeworld. The return of Estha and the stick to Churruma sparked a rebellion that ended the Empire's presence on the planet.

properties.name: Chuzalla
properties.description: Chuzalla was a backwater planet located within the Chuzalla system of the Outer Rim Territories. It was a haven for criminals.

properties.name: Cilare
properties.description: Cilare was an ice planet where the crime lord Tayand lived.

properties.name: Cilpar
properties.poi: Spacer's StreetDocking Bay 66Docking Bay 68Imperial baseThe barn
properties.description: Cilpar was an agriworld in the Colonies, nearly covered in mountains, jungles, and forests. It was characterized by the near-indestructible ancient temples scattered across the surface. Local flora and fauna included the predatory ronk.

properties.name: Cimarosa
properties.description: Cimarosa was the homeworld of the Human Von Longo and his two sons, Kale Longo and Trig Longo. They lived on the world until sometime in 1 BBY, when they were arrested by the Galactic Empire, and placed on the prison barge Purge.

properties.name: Cinnabar
properties.description: Cinnabar was a red mineral found in the planetary crust of Fiddanl. Along with lemony-orange sulfites, purple manganese, and green rock made up the crust of Fiddanl, a planet in the Yavin system.

properties.name: Cioral
properties.description: Cioral was a planet of the Chiss Ascendancy in the Unknown Regions and was located in the Cioral system. It was home of the Csapla family, one of the Chiss Ruling Families; therefore, as with many other homeworlds of Ruling Families, Cioral was located on the Path of the Houses, a hyperlane in the Ascendancy's core territory. Cioral was also a heavily urbanized planet from which a half-dozen Chiss agricultural colonies were overseen.

properties.name: Cioran
properties.description: Cioran was a planet located in the Saavin system of the Core Worlds. During the Galactic Civil War, the Imperial-class Star Destroyer Ravenous monitored the traffic around Cioran.

properties.name: Ciratu
properties.description: Ciratu was a star located in the star system of the same name, a part of the Immerian Outback sector in the Expansion Region, far from the region's trade routes. It was orbited by six spheres made up of rock and iron which were known as the Ciratu Spheres. The spheres were filled with tunnels, and were believed to have been created by an ancient species known as the Celestials.

properties.name: Circarpous
properties.description: Circarpous was a location within the galaxy. The droids C-3PO and R2-D2 were once sent on a diplomatic mission to this location, an event C-3PO would later recall to Resistance pilot Jessika Pava. It shared its name with the Circarpous sector of the Expansion Region.

properties.name: Circumtore
properties.description: Circumtore was a ring-shaped artificial planetoid located in the star system of the same name in Hutt Space. Discovered by the main galactic community by the Rianitus Period, Circumtore fell within the space controlled by the Hutt species into the reign of the Galactic Empire. Colonized by the Shell Hutts at some period, the planetoid was visited by a group of bounty hunters under the lead of Boba Fett in 1 BBY after they tracked the Lyunesi Oph Nar Dinnid and his bounty there. However, the Shell Hutt Gheeta took out his grudge against Fett by killing Dinnid and sending mercenaries to engage the bounty hunters, though the latter group prevailed. Between 26 ABY and 27 ABY, during the Yuuzhan Vong War, Circumtore was attacked by the Yuuzhan Vong invaders and seized.

properties.name: Cirra
properties.description: The Cirra was one of the four akias of Aramandi soceity that shared the planet Aram. They colonized the Cirra system, which was named after them. They were the second of the akia to settle their system.

properties.name: Cirrus
properties.description: Cirrus was a Outer Rim world orbiting two orange suns. It had golden seas and lovely cities, including the capital Ciran near a bay. It was the homeworld of Talesan Fry and his parents.

properties.name: Cirtappa
properties.description: Cirtappa was a planet in the Alui sector of the Mid Rim.

properties.name: Ciutric
properties.description: Ciutric was an astronomical object located in the galaxy's Outer Rim Territories.

properties.name: Claer
properties.description: Clær was an astronomical object located in the Claer system, a part of the Sern sector in the Southern Core portion of the Colonies. It was the site of an exclusive preparatory academy. At some point between 5 BBY and 0 BBY, Imperial Grand Moff Wilhuff Tarkin sent his niece Rivoche to Clær in order to attend the academy.

properties.name: Clak'dor
properties.description: Bith, also known as Clak'dor VII or simply Clak'dor, was a planet located in the Outer Rim Territories and situated along the Rimma Trade Route. It was the homeworld of the Bith species.

properties.name: Clantaano
properties.description: Clantaano may refer to one of the following:

properties.name: Clariv
properties.description: Clariv was a world located in the Clariv system. It was a part of the Back Spiral area of the Tion Hegemony sector, which was situated in the Tion Cluster within the Slice portion of the Outer Rim Territories. Clariv lay between the Erediss and Rudrig systems on the hyperlane known as the Tion Trade Route.

properties.name: Clendor
properties.description: Clendor was a planet in the Inner Rim, near Taanab.

properties.name: Cloak of the Sith, The
properties.description: The Cloak of the Sith was a mysterious region within the Outer Rim which included the planet Roon.

properties.name: Cmaoli Di
properties.description: Cmaoli Di was a world in the Brema sector. Between 3701 BBY and 3699 BBY, the Hydian Way was charted through the planet as part of the Seswenna Expansion. Cmaoli Di was known to receive broadcasts from the Brema News service.

properties.name: Coachelle
properties.description: Coachelle Prime was a location that was represented by the Lepi racer Thrar in the forty-eighth annual Dragonfire Air Rally. The Lepi smuggler Jaxxon T. Tumperakki was also from Coachelle Prime, and titled himself as the "Haulage King of Coachelle Prime" when attempting to start his own business, the Tumperakki Haulage Company.

properties.name: Codia
properties.description: Codia was a Mid Rim Territories planet situated in grid square H-15 of the Standard Galactic Grid. It shared its name with both the Codian Moon and the location known as New Codia. At some point, the historian Eloc Throno noted the location of Codia on a map of the galaxy included in his book Traveler's Guide to Batuu.

properties.name: Cog Hive Seven
properties.description: Cog Hive Seven was a space station prison in the Tharin sector of the Outer Rim that was used as a gladiatorial death match gambling operation by its owners in the waning years of the Galactic Republic.

properties.name: Colla
properties.description: Colla was a commentator on Gundark's Gear Datalog during the early years of the New Republic. Commenting on the entry for Mandroxan Exports' Defense Weapon EDWX-843, Cholla noted that the weapon was good for disabling a target droid and recovering any information needed.

properties.name: Colonial Station Cam'co
properties.description: Colonial Station Camco, also known as Colonial Station Cam'co, was a terrestrial planet located within the territory of the Chiss Ascendancy in the Unknown Regions. The Chiss Caregiver Mitth'ali'astov, known by the core name "Thalias," was born there before she became a sky-walker navigator.

properties.name: Colonial Station Chaf
properties.description: Colonial Station Chaf was a terrestrial planet within the territory of the Chiss Ascendancy in the Unknown Regions. It shared its name with the Chaf family, one of the Nine Ruling Families of the Chiss Ascendancy. The communications triad of Colonial Station Chaf was used for relaying communication through to the Xodlak family task force led by Senior Captain Xodlak'in'daro on their way to the planet Hoxim.

properties.name: Cols
properties.description: Cols was an ocean planet known for the oceanic region of Harvest Bay, which served as the main breeding ground for the kalaides.

properties.name: Colsassa
properties.description: Colsassa was the fourth planet orbiting the binary stars Adega Prime and Adega Besh in the Adega system. Located in the Auril sector of the Outer Rim, it was a gas giant.

properties.name: Columex
properties.description: Columex, originally known as Nardolin, was a trade planet located in relative proximity to the Vorzyd Cluster of the Outer Rim Territories, on the Perlemian Trade Route.

properties.name: Columus
properties.description: Columus was a planet in the Core Worlds's Columus system and the homeworld of the Columi species. A low-gravity, geologically-stable planet, Columus lacked any geographic features and possessed a shallow soil layer, causing its native plants to form horizontal root systems. The Columi species evolved to sentience remarkably early in the history of the galaxy, achieving interstellar travel by the year 100,000 BBY. However, the Columi were disappointed by their failure to contact any other species with intelligence on par with their own, and they retreated to Columus and remained in isolation on their homeworld. Around 24,500 BBY, during the First Great Schism, Columus was the site of the pivotal Battle of Columus between the Jedi Order and the Legions of Lettow, a battle in which the Legions' leader General Xendor was slain. Columus later joined the Galactic Republic and its successor state the Galactic Empire, though the Columi's decision to join the Empire was motivated by a desire to maintain their isolation.

properties.name: Colunda Prime
properties.description: Colunda Prime was an astronomical object located in the Colunda Prime system. It constituted a part of the Colunda sector, a subsector of the Phelleem sector in the Slice portion of the Outer Rim Territories. Senator Char Bibbeck, who represented a sector in the Galactic Republic's Senate, hailed from Colunda Prime.

properties.name: Commenor
properties.description: Commenor was a planet in the Commenor system of the Colonies, just outside of the Core Worlds.

properties.name: Comra
properties.description: Comra was a planet in the Comra system, Prefsbelt sector in the Outer Rim's "Dead Zone," near Wild Space.

properties.name: Cona
properties.description: Cona was an arid, desert world which orbited the blue giant Teke Ro, located in the Teke Ro system of the Inner Rim. The homeworld of the serpent-like Arcona species, Cona had a minimal water supply due to a geological catastrophe early in its history.

properties.name: Concord Dawn
properties.poi: Fett homestead, Sintas Vel's homestead, Sintas Vel's safe house,
properties.description: Concord Dawn was an agricultural frontier world in the Mandalore sector of the Outer Rim Territories. The planet had strong ties to the Mandalorians; its population shared many Mandalorian values, and genetic markers specific to the natives of Concord Dawn were present throughout the Mandalorian populace. Concord Dawn was a flashpoint for the Mandalorian Civil War in 58 BBY, when the Death Watch of Tor Vizsla scattered the True Mandalorians of Mandalore Jaster Mereel, a native of Concord Dawn. Mereel escaped and turned the tables on Vizsla with the help of a native boy, Jango Fett, orphaned by the Death Watch. Jango's son Boba Fett would later settle on Concord Dawn before being exiled for the murder of his superior officer.

properties.name: Condor
properties.description: Condor can refer to:

properties.name: Condular
properties.description: Condular was a planet of the Core Worlds and was home to the Grand Astrocartographic Institute.

properties.name: Constancia
properties.description: Constancia was the Constancian homeworld.

properties.name: Contruum
properties.poi: Contruum Shipyard, Contruum Moonbase, Contruum Six,
properties.description: Contruum was a planet in the Mid Rim, and was the most developed planet in the dense system of inhabited worlds that made up the Contruum system.

properties.name: Coonee
properties.description: Coonee was a planet located in the Expansion Region. Han Solo, who was in his teens, and Chewbacca traveled to Coonee where they herded coldppedas, fifteen-footed scaled domestic animals, for three years.

properties.name: Coorimbus
properties.description: The Coorimbus system contained Coorimbus IV. It was a star system located in the Tapani sector's Calipsa Province, near the Shifa system.

properties.name: Copero
properties.description: Copero was a planet of the Chiss Ascendancy in the Unknown Regions. It was the location of the Chiss' largest shipyard.

properties.name: Copperline
properties.description: Copperline was a world of poor farmers that was plagued by pirates for decades. In 18 BBY, the Imperial Navy and Army, including at least one unit of stormtroopers, cleaned out the pirates in a five-month-long operation.

properties.name: Cor I
properties.description: The Cor I system was a star system located in the Tapani sector's Barnaba Province, on the Cor Lane.

properties.name: Cor II
properties.description: The Cor II system was a star system located in the Tapani sector's Barnaba Province, on the Cor Lane.

properties.name: Cor III
properties.description: The Cor III system was a star system located in the Tapani sector's Barnaba Province, on the Cor Lane.

properties.name: Corann
properties.description: Corann was a planet in the Core Worlds.

properties.name: Corbantis
properties.description: The Corbantis was a New Republic cruiser stationed at Durren Orbital in the Meridian sector in 9 ABY. It was one of two New Republic warships dispatched to deal with pirate attacks on nearby Ampliquen. After its crew was infected with the Death Seed plague, the vessel crashed on Damonite Yors-B. The majority of the crew was lost due to the plague and the subsequent crash. Skent Graff's father was one of the survivors.

properties.name: Corbett Cluster
properties.description: The Corbett Cluster was a star cluster in the Corbett sector of the Mid Rim. It was protected by the Solar Guard during the final years of the Old Republic.

properties.name: Corbos
properties.description: Corbos was an Outer Rim planet near the Yavin system which was rich in ores. It had "Black Rain Seasons" which saw whole sections of the planet become uninhabitable due to massive thunderstorms.

properties.name: Cordes
properties.description: Cordes was an Imperial-controlled planet in the Inner Rim.

properties.name: Corellia
properties.poi: CorSec AcademyHunchuzuc DenBlack HoleAgrilat, Gold Beaches, Groola's Place, Vreni Island, Rogue CorSec Base, Afarathu Cave, Droid GraveyardKor Vella mesa, Nomad Mountains, Denendre Valley, Northern HillsDrall Patriot's Cave, Dregan's Pike, Bindreg Hills,
properties.description: Corellia was the capital planet of the Corellian system, which included Selonia, Drall, Tralus, and Talus. It was also the birthplace of smuggler and New Republic General Han Solo as well as Rogue Squadron pilot and New Republic hero Wedge Antilles, along with many other humans who played important roles in the histories of the Rebel Alliance, New Republic and Galactic Alliance.

properties.name: Corfai
properties.poi: Hel's Outfitting, Mount Lorrist, Olvergast Glacier, Salvarrn Nature Reserve, Winterdome Museum,
properties.description: Corfai was a planet in the Corellian sector of the Core Worlds.

properties.name: Coriallis
properties.description: Coriallis was a New Republic planet in the Core Worlds near Coruscant.

properties.name: Corips
properties.description: Corips was a planet in the Inner Rim of the galaxy.

properties.name: Corjain
properties.description: The planet Corjain was located within the system of the same name in the Kathol sector of the Outer Rim Territories, just off the Trition Trade Route. Barely habitable, the planet supported a large mining industry, with all settlements located deep underground. During the Galactic Civil War, the planet was also the location of a secret outpost maintained by the Bothan Spynet.

properties.name: Corlaasi
properties.description: Corlaasi was a world that was located on the Rimma Trade Route and near the Dravin Cut.

properties.name: Corlass
properties.description: Corlass was a planet of pirates, both seafaring and spacefaring. Located within the Outer Rim Territories, it was one of the original member-worlds of the Kingdom of Cron. It was absorbed into Xim's empire, and the Despot used many former Corlassi pirates as the captains of his warships.

properties.name: Corlax
properties.description: Corlax 4, or simply Corlax, was a planet located within the Allied Tion sector of the Outer Rim Territories. An unremarkable industrial world, during the Clone Wars almost 300 million Humans inhabited the planet, working mostly as laborers.

properties.name: Cormit
properties.description: Cormit was a planet of the Chiss Ascendancy in the Unknown Regions. Cormit was located near the border of the Ascendancy's core territory in the Cormit system and at the intersection of two hyperlanes, the Vagaari Corridor and the Phalanx Route. The planet was the location of one of the two major Chiss Expansionary Defense Force bases.

properties.name: Coronar
properties.description: The planet Coronar was the site of an Imperial Intelligence base during the Galactic Civil War. After the Empire's destruction of the Alliance to Restore the Republic base on Dankayo, several datapacks were recovered from the ruins. They were consigned for analysis on Coronar aboard the Imperial Armored Transport Elusive, but the shipment was intercepted by Alliance agents, and Elusive was destroyed.

properties.name: Corphelion
properties.description: Corphelion was an Expansion Region asteroid rimward of Phindar with numerous holiday resorts where honeymooners and tourists went to see the system's beautiful comets . It was the sight of the Battle of Corphelion during the New Sith Wars. Corphelion later fell under control of the Galactic Empire, and the New Republic.

properties.name: Corrdair
properties.description: Corrdair was a planet located in the Corrdair system of the Hevvrol sector in the Mid Rim. The Battle of Corrdair took place there.

properties.name: Corroth
properties.description: Corroth was a planet known for its duelists, such as Matta Tremayne.

properties.name: Corsin
properties.description: Corsin was a planet located in the Greater Plooriod sector of the Expansion Region.

properties.name: Corstris
properties.description: Corstris was a heavily-forested planet in the Quelii sector of the Outer Rim.

properties.name: Cortella
properties.description: Cortella was a Galactic Core world ruled by a hereditary monarchy. Jedi Obi-Wan Kenobi and Siri Tachi impersonated the king and queen of this world in their attempts to infiltrate the Leadership School on Andara.

properties.name: Cortilium Major
properties.description: Cortilium Major was an astronomical object located in the Cortilium Major system, a part of the Eucer sector of the Mid Rim. During the Tionese War, waged between the Galactic Republic and the Honorable Union of Desevro & Tion, Cortilium Major was situated in the region known as the Divide and was settled by Republic colonists.

properties.name: Cortina
properties.description: Cortina was a planet directly represented in the New Republic Senate. Its government attempted to push its application to the New Republic through, thinking itself superior, but eventually calmed down and earned membership.

properties.name: Corulag
properties.poi: Abersaith Canyon, Corulag Academy, , Corulag University of EconomicsDammon UniversityNorth Kallis, Resoria, Royal Galaxy HotelSienar Advanced Research Division, South Kallis,
properties.description: Corulag  was a populated terrestrial world located on the Perlemian Trade Route in the Corulus system in the Bormea sector, part of the Ringali Shell. It was the endpoint of the Corulag-Jatir Hyperroute. The planet boasted urban sprawls with the underdeveloped areas filled with bamboo forests.

properties.name: Coruscant
properties.description: Coruscant (pronounced /'kɔɹəsɑnt/ or, more rarely, /kəˈɹʌskənt/[21]), originally called Notron, also known as the Queen of the Core, or Imperial Center during the New Order and as Yuuzhan'tar under the Yuuzhan Vong, was a planet located in the Galactic Core. It was the ancient homeworld of the Taung and Zhell species, and it was generally also believed to be the original birthplace of Humans. During most of galactic history, Coruscant was the most politically important world in the galaxy. At various times, it was the capital of the Galactic Republic, the Galactic Empire, the New Republic, the Yuuzhan Vong empire, the Galactic Alliance, Darth Krayt's Galactic Empire, and the Galactic Federation Triumvirate. In controlling Coruscant, these governments controlled most of the galaxy in the process.  Over the centuries, Coruscant had developed into an ecumenopolis, with a total of 5,127 levels of city built up from the crust by the time of the Clone Wars. The actual planet-wide metropolis of Coruscant was called Galactic City. Under the Galactic Republic, the names Republic City or the City of Spires were also used to reference the city. It was also called Imperial City under the Galactic Empire, and New Republic City under the New Republic. However, in practice, Galactic City and its other names were sometimes applied to the Senate District, the central government center and de facto capital of Coruscant.

properties.name: Coruschal
properties.description: Coruschal was a planet covered in decaying cities. It was once home to the Coruschal WeaponWorks, which made the Dagger Combat Pistol during the Galactic Civil War.

properties.name: Coruscul
properties.description: Coruscul was a Galactic Core world. It had a hidden stronghold of the Order of the Silver Jedi, the only stronghold not destroyed by Tel Angor.

properties.name: Corutarn
properties.description: Corutarn was an Imperial planet in the Galactic Core. It was the homeworld of Major Perrn.

properties.name: Corva Yag
properties.description: Corva Yag was an Outer Rim Territories planet located in the Rseik sector. By 214 BBY, the Hajara gang of pirates established a presence on Corva Yag, raiding Kett Shipping convoys traveling across the Little Minos Run hyperlane.

properties.name: Corvis Minor
properties.description: Corvis Minor was the primary star of the Corvis Minor system, which was part of the Ciutric Hegemony ruled by Prince-Admiral Delak Krennel.

properties.name: Cosia
properties.description: Cosia was a planet that was located in the galaxy's Deep Core, located in the system of the same name. It was the homeworld of the Cosian species.

properties.name: Cotellier
properties.description: Cotellier  was a desert mining planet in the Rseik sector of the Outer Rim Territories.

properties.name: Council
properties.description: A council is a group of people, staffed by councilors and usually those possessing some form of governing power.

properties.name: Couronne
properties.description: The planet Couronne was the namesake of the Couronne system in the Couronne sector, located within the Slice portion of the Expansion Region. It was the homeworld of the humanoid Imzig species.

properties.name: Coveway
properties.description: Coveway was a harsh Outer Rim Territories planet situated in the Koradin sector. Colonized by the time of the reign of the Galactic Empire, it eventually became home to the Human Jak Bremen, who eventually became a constable of the village he resided in and started a family.

properties.name: Cowl Crucible
properties.description: The Cowl Crucible was a nebula that was located in the Oricho sector, on the border of the Lahara sector.

properties.name: Coyn
properties.description: Coyn was a planet in the Coyn system and the homeworld of the Coynites. It was located in Elrood sector, where the Coyn Route met the Elrood-Derilyn Run. The capital was the city of En'Tra'Tal, or "King-City". Forests, marshes, and plains broken by simple mountain ranges covered this beautiful planet. Coyn was defended by their space fleet, Coyn'Skraj'Ha.

properties.name: Craci
properties.description: Craci was a planet located in the Craci system in the Corporate Sector of the Outer Rim Territories. The planet was the home of the Cracian thumpers, a species used frequently as mounts by scouts. Controlled by the Corporate Sector Authority by the time of the Battle of Yavin, the planet had spaceports that were experience high levels of activity due to the agriculture and industry of the five worlds.

properties.name: Crakull
properties.description: Crakull was a planet located within the Crakull system of the Unknown Regions. It was home to the sentient Croke species. The Croke were diminutive in size, and had multiple legs as well as a natural ability to disguise themselves behind illusions.

properties.name: Crella
properties.description: The Crella system was a star system located in the Tapani sector's Barnaba Province, on the Cor Lane.

properties.name: Critoki
properties.description: The Critoki system was located in the Esstran sector, in the Trans-Hydian portion of the Outer Rim Territories. It was home to the sentient species known as the Critokians.

properties.name: Criton's Point
properties.poi: Library of Xer, archaeological excavation sites, scientists' settlement,
properties.description: Criton's Point was a quarantined planet in the Myto sector. Its Library of Xer was built 26,000 BBY. Not much was known of the planet, but many historians had expressed interest in gaining access to the Imperial-controlled library.

properties.name: Crombach Nebula
properties.description: The Crombach Nebula was a nebula located within the Belsmuth sector, between Botajef and Bandomeer, in the Outer Rim region of the galaxy. The planet Irmenu was located in the fringes of the nebula, which contributed to its isolation from the rest of the galaxy.

properties.name: Cron Drift
properties.description: The Cron Drift was a giant asteroid field located within the Auril sector in the Outer Rim, near the Perlemian Trade Route, the Cronese Mandate and the Tion Cluster.

properties.name: Crondre
properties.description: Crondre was a small, icy world located in the Dufilvian sector of the Mid Rim. Its surface consisted of icy glaciers.

properties.name: Crovna
properties.poi: Birtraub Brothers Storage and Reclamation CenterPeven Auction House
properties.description: Crovna was a planet in Senex sector that was home to the Peven Auction House; and Birtraub Brothers Storage and Reclamation Center, located near the main spaceport on the planet, which was a front for the Birtraub Brothers' criminal activities.

properties.name: Croyden
properties.description: Croyden was the submoon of the planet of Gipper, located in the Inner Rim. It was known to have a very inefficient postal system.

properties.name: Crseih
properties.description: Crseih was a crystallized white dwarf that was swallowed by a black hole. Influenced by the extra-dimensional entity Waru, Crseih disrupted the Force when in close proximity. It was destroyed in 14 ABY when it collapsed into the black hole.

properties.name: Crustai
properties.description: Crustai was the second planet of the Crustai system in the Unknown Regions. It was part of the Chiss Ascendancy.

properties.name: Cryon
properties.description: Cryon was a planet located in the Outer Rim Territories, in the Cryon system in the Meram sector.

properties.name: Crystal Web Station
properties.description: Crystal Web Station was a space station built around a huge crystal asteroid which floated in deep space.

properties.name: Crystan
properties.description: Crystan V was a planet located in the Deep Core. It was inhabited by a race of small green skinned beings.

properties.name: Crytal Nest
properties.description: Crytal Nest was a planet in Wild Space. It was the homeworld of the Shashay and the popular singer Crying Dawn Singer.

properties.name: Csaus
properties.description: Csaus was a planet located in the Csaus system in the core territory of the Chiss Ascendancy in the Unknown Regions. It was home of the Inrokini family, one of the Chiss Ruling Families. Like other homeworlds of Ruling Families, Csaus was located on the Path of the Houses, a hyperlane that ran through the Ascendancy. The planet was the Ascendancy's hub of sciences and communications.

properties.name: Csilla
properties.description: Csilla, the homeworld of the Chiss, was a cold world of glaciers and snowy wastes located deep within Chiss Space, and served as the capital of the Chiss Ascendancy.

properties.name: Cuirilla
properties.description: Cuirilla was a planet in the Cuirilla system. It was located within the Expansion Region.

properties.name: Cujicor
properties.description: Cujicor was a planet in the Pakuuni sector of the Outer Rim.

properties.name: Cularin
properties.poi: Cloud Mountain, Hiironi irstat, Ishkik caverns, Kiallquis Mountain Range, Kiirloor, Sacred ch'hala tree grove,
properties.description: Cularin was a planet in the Cularin system. It had two moons, the molten Rennokk and the barren Tilnes. The planet was known for its exotic hardwoods, especially the ch'hala tree. The whole planet was considered strong in the Force.

properties.name: Culroon
properties.description: The Culroon were the natives of the planet Culroon III in Wild Space.

properties.name: Curreck
properties.description: Curreck was a planet located in Outer Rim Territories. Captain Darren T. Weeb was a native of the planet.

properties.name: Cuthbern
properties.description: Cuthbern was a desolate wasted moon in the Wazta sector of the Outer Rim Territories of the galaxy. It was known for its factories that produced extremely high quality weapons, including the Star Anvil blaster rifle. It was annexed by the Empire and its population was enslaved. It was later abandoned after a Rebel attack.

properties.name: Cuvacia
properties.description: The Cuvacia system was located in the Southern Core portion of the Core Worlds. It was the origin point of the Cuvacian ambassador.

properties.name: Cybloc
properties.description: Cybloc was a greenish planet orbiting the star Erg Es 992 in the Meridian sector. During the Clone Wars there was a space station in orbit over the planet. Darth Maul and his brother Savage Opress broke into the space station and stole some credits. One of its moons, Cybloc XII, housed a New Republic trade base. However, the region was purged during the Death Seed incident.

properties.name: Cyborrea
properties.description: Cyborrea was a heavy-gravity planet that was located within the galaxy's Hutt Space region, on the hyperlane called the Sisar Run. It was the homeworld of both the sentient Cyborreans and the dog-like nek beasts. Cyborrea was a part of the Hutt Empire around the year 25,100 BBY, with Cyborreans serving in the armies of the Hutt species during that time. More than thirteen millennia later the Galactic Republic sent a battle-fleet toward Cyborrea during one of the Republic's crusades against the Hutts. At some point prior to the conflict known as the Freedon Nadd Uprising, members of the Republic Army's rocket-jumper unit dropped to Cyborrea's surface with rocket packs during a mission to the planet. During the Galactic War between the Republic and the resurgent Sith Empire, the renegade Sith Lords known as the Dread Masters attacked and destroyed entire fleets over Cyborrea using a Force phantom. During the Yuuzhan Vong War, the extra-galactic Yuuzhan Vong invaders attacked the star system Cyborrea was located in.

properties.name: Cygnus
properties.description: Cygnus Spaceworks was a manufacturer of small craft, such as shuttles and starfighters, primarily of a military nature. Approximately half of Cygnus' designs were merely modifications and upgrades to previously existing craft.

properties.name: Cyimarra
properties.description: Cyimarra was a terrestrial planet located in the Mid Rim's Senex sector. The homeworld of the the aristocratic House Araba, its surface featured cities interspersed among woodlands and mountains as well as a sea.

properties.name: Cyphar
properties.description: Cyphar was a planet in the Mid Rim between Nkllon and Belsavis, defended by the Galactic Republic from the Confederacy of Independent Systems in 22 BBY during the Clone Wars.

properties.name: Cyrillia
properties.description: Cyrillia was the homeworld of the Cyrillians, in the Expansion Region of the galaxy. It was a very industrialized world where Serv-O-Droid, Inc. constructed its DUM pit droids in large quantities.

properties.name: D'Anjon Nebula
properties.description: The D'Anjon Nebula was an expansive nebula located within the northernmost part of the Arkanis sector, a part of the galactic regions known as the Outer Rim Territories and the Slice. To the galactic south of the nebula was the starless void known as the Gulf of Tatooine.

properties.name: D'ian
properties.description: Sen III, best known as D'ian, was a planet with balmy weather and shallow seas that was located within the D'ian system of the Outer Rim Territories. After the rise of the Galactic Empire, which formed in 19 BBY, the planet came to be part of the Corporate Sector, an area of space controlled by the Corporate Sector Authority. While a part of the Corporate Sector, D'ian became a thriving merchant world with several successful business schools.

properties.name: D'Nile
properties.description: D'Nile was a planet in the D'Nile system.

properties.name: Daalang
properties.description: Daalang was a world on the Gamor Run in the Mid Rim, near Attahox.

properties.name: Dachat
properties.description: Dachat was a planet on the Hyabb-Twith Corridor. The Nelori Marauders had a base on the planet which allowed them to prey upon both the populations on Hyabb and Twith. The base was destroyed by the Jedi in 4050 BBY.

properties.name: Dactruria
properties.description: The Dactruria system was a star system located in the Clacis sector of the Outer Rim Territories.

properties.name: Daedalon
properties.description: The Daedalon system was a star system located in the Inner Rim.

properties.name: Daemen
properties.description: Daemen was a planet on the Rimma Trade Route in the Expansion Region, home to the Clarion Scholars Academy.

properties.name: Daermor
properties.description: Daermor was a planet from the Daermor system. In 0 ABY, Auditor-General Fiolla conducted an audit there.

properties.name: Dagary Minor
properties.description: Dagary Minor was the location of a battle that was fought during the early stages of the Mandalorian Wars. Both the Meetra Surik and Xaart, who later became a Republic spy, fought in the battle, though the Republic did not win.

properties.name: Dagelin Minor
properties.description: Dagelin Minor was an Outer Rim Territories celestial body located in the Cadma sector. A shipment of the flying rodents known as Bogan's brown nafen was at one point imported there for the purposes of combating an infestation of dhuru flies. The nafen, however, caused an outbreak of the Hardan plague that wiped out ninety-eight percent of the local population. In response, Imperial Senator Leia Organa visited Dagelin Minor on a mercy mission.

properties.name: Dagobah
properties.poi: Yoda's hut, Dark Side Cave, The Shelter, Mount Dagger, Dragonsnake Bog
properties.description: Dagobah ) was an Outer Rim planet in the Dagobah system. A remote world of swamps and forests, it served as a refuge for Jedi Grand Master Yoda during his exile after the events of Order 66 had taken place.

properties.name: Dagro
properties.description: Dagro was a remote planet and a noted agriworld in the years leading up to the Clone Wars.

properties.name: Dagu
properties.description: Dagu was a planet in the Outer Rim Territories and the site of a Clone Wars battle.

properties.name: Dahgee
properties.description: Dahgee was a planet where unique lightsaber crystals were mined. A small group of Jedi with unique robes also lived there. The crystals on Dahgee gave the lightsaber a strange, zigzagging blade with a black core, almost like a tree branch.

properties.name: Dahrtag
properties.poi: GraveyardsCrypt of the AncientsMeego's Starship Emporium
properties.description: Necropolis was a tombworld located on the Giju Run of the Core Worlds. Serving as a burial place for beings from all over the Core, it was also the home of boneworms and cryptberries.

properties.name: Dahvil
properties.description: Dahvil was a planet located in the Rayter sector.

properties.name: Daimar
properties.description: Daimar was a planet located in the Mid Rim.

properties.name: Daimla
properties.description: Daimla was a terrestrial world located in the Daimla system, a part of the Outer Rim Territories' Kallea sector. It was the homeworld of the sentient Daimlo species.

properties.name: Dakshee
properties.description: Dakshee was the sector capital of the Barma sector. An Imperial-held planet in the Colonies region, it was marked by constant unrest and agitation against Imperial rule. Gerald Weizel, Imperial governor of Chandrila, was once the governor of Dakshee, where he resolved the Brella Temior crisis. Weizel discovered that several union heads were ringleaders of the terrorist group Justice Action Network, and ended the situation without bloodshed.

properties.name: Dalandae
properties.description: Dalandae was the homeworld of the Human starship pilot named John D. Branon, who was part of the Alliance to Restore the Republic.

properties.name: Dalastine
properties.description: Dalastine, in the Inner Rim's Dalastine system, was a planet with a Rebel base. It was orbited by the moon Dalastine IV.

properties.name: Dalchon
properties.description: Dalchon could refer to several things:

properties.name: Dalcretti
properties.description: The Dalcretti system was a star system located in the Inner Rim.

properties.name: Daltarra
properties.description: Daltarra was a planet in the Pakuuni sector of the Outer Rim Territories.

properties.name: Daltarri
properties.description: The planet Daltarri was a terrestrial world located in the galaxy. It was covered in plant life which was the home of the plant-based Daltarri species.

properties.name: Daluba
properties.description: Daluba was a world ruled by the tyrant Tonkoss Rathba, until Rathba was thwarted by Leia Organa Solo during the time of the New Republic.

properties.name: Daluuj
properties.description: Daluuj was a lightly populated Outer Rim planet covered with barren canyons and muddy slopes.

properties.name: Damendine
properties.description: Damendine was a planet located in the Damendine system of the Outer Rim Territories.

properties.name: Daminia
properties.description: Daminia was a desert planet in the Mid Rim known for its Damind lightsaber crystals.

properties.name: Damonite Yors B
properties.description: Damonite Yors-B was a cold, icy planet in the Meridian sector that was a possible location of Princess Leia during her kidnapping nine years after the Battle of Endor.

properties.name: Damoria
properties.description: The Damoria system was a star system located within the Colonies and the Slice regions. It was connected via the Quellor Run hyperlane to the Commenor and Chorax systems.

properties.name: Dampher
properties.description: The Dampher system was a star system located in the Tapani sector's Pelagia Province until annexed by Calipsa Province. It was situated along the Calipsa Run hyperlane.

properties.name: Damualer Triac
properties.description: Damualer Triac was a planet located in the Damualer Triac system of the Inner Rim of the galaxy. The Millennium Oak grew on the world. Jedi Master Haaran Balmor retired to Damualer Triac with his second wife, Hannah Balmor. Haaran and Jedi Hart Daele, who was seven kiloparsecs away in the Samarine Province, played several games of Divoran Holochess over a forty-year period via Projective Telepathy.

properties.name: Danadine
properties.description: Danadine was a world located in the Danadine system, a part of the Outer Rim Territories' Dail sector. Around 10 ABY, it served as the homeworld of Relekin Confidential, a collection agency that constituted a part of the Tenloss Syndicate.

properties.name: Danalbeth
properties.description: Danalbeth was a water world located in the Danalbeth system, a part of the Teraab sector in the Slice portion of the Mid Rim. It was postulated by some scientists that Danalbeth was the homeworld of the Graygl, a species of aquatic sentients.

properties.name: Danchian Prime
properties.description: Danchian Prime was a planet in the Outer Rim's Dail sector. The bounty hunter Milko claimed to have a family on Danchian Prime, despite being a droid.

properties.name: Dancreti
properties.description: Dancreti was a planet of tropical jungles and swamps. Its year in local days was 333 days. It was famous for its small animals called the sanl'jek.

properties.name: Dandalas
properties.description: Dandalas was a planet in the Koornacht Cluster in the Farlax sector in the Core Worlds.

properties.name: Dandelo
properties.description: Dandelo was a planet inhabited by spotted jugadoos and a sentient, primitive avian species known as Fuzzums.

properties.name: Dandrian
properties.description: Dandrian in the Dandrian system was called the "crossroads of the galaxy". It had a single sun and was orbited by the Dandrian's Ring of asteroids, the remnants of a moon that struck the planet during formation. It had a thick atmosphere, flat marshes, and tropical grass, but no trees. It was located between Tatooine and Yavin, and between Bespin and Dantooine. It was inhabited by indigenous bonecrushers as well as Humans and Gamorreans.

properties.name: Dankayo
properties.description: Dankayo was a world in the Colonies on the Shwuy Exchange with a Alliance to Restore the Republic administrative base, known as Dankayo Base, that served three sectors for purposes of coordination and records. Part of the area within its purview was Ralltiir sector.

properties.name: Danoor
properties.description: Danoor was a planet in the Nah'Malis system located within the Kathol Outback.

properties.name: Danos
