properties.description: Danos was a Training Lieutenant in the Imperial Navy. Danos lectured on inter-service cooperation between Naval and Imperial Army forces, citing that negative attitudes toward Army personnel was counter-productive. In private, however, Danos had a low view of the Army.

properties.name: Danteel
properties.description: The planet Danteel was the capital of the Emmo sector.

properties.name: Dantooine
properties.poi: Jedi EnclaveKhoonda plainsWarren, Rakatan RuinsImperial Outpost, Mining Outpost, Agro Outpost, Matale estateSandral estateCrystal CaveDantooine base, Mosa Rishin, Taikaha Hills, Tokare Garrison, Imperial Outpost DNT-X004,
properties.description: Dantooine  was a pleasant world of grasslands, rivers and lakes. The planet was located in the Raioballo sector of the Outer Rim at an endpoint of Myto's Arrow, the other endpoint of which was in the Obtrexta sector, though Dantooine itself was still far removed from most galactic traffic. It hosted a small population spread amongst single-family settlements and small communities with large land holdings. Its sentient population consisted primarily of simple Human farmers, though Dantooine was also home to the primitive Dantari race. Native wildlife included the kath hound, the iriaz, the kinrath, and the graul. The planet had no industrial settlements or advanced technology by the time of the Galactic Civil War, save for a temporary Rebel base there.

properties.name: Danuta
properties.description: Danuta was a dull, barren brown planet in the Colavas system, thinly populated mostly by miners and hardscrabble farmers. Trid was the planet's de facto capital.

properties.name: Dar'Or
properties.description: Dar'Or, also known as OM973, was an Outer Rim Territories planet located in the Jospro sector. Its land surface was primarily covered in forests of two-hundred-meter-tall waza trees. The forests, which had multiple floor-like levels, were home to the predatory indola tree-sloths as well as the sentient flying primates Ri'Dar.

properties.name: Darada
properties.description: Darada was a planet on the edge of the Core Worlds, near Krayiss Two. Jev Sunrider was a Jedi Watchman of Darada. His grandson, Andur Sunrider, spent the first nineteen years of his life there.

properties.name: Darek
properties.description: Darek was a male Human who was a private in the Republic Army during the Galactic War, when he was stationed at Farnel Outpost on the planet Balmorra.

properties.name: Darepp
properties.description: Darepp was a planet in the Colonies, near Atzerri. It was located at the Foless Crossroads. After reappearing near Arat Fraca, the Star Morning docked at Darepp. The Morning then visited a number of colony worlds, including 23 Mere, Babbadod, Fwiis, New Polokia, and Yisgga, before returning to Motexx.

properties.name: Dargulli
properties.description: Dargulli was a planet in the Kether system in the Inner Rim.

properties.name: Dark Nebula
properties.description: The Dark Nebula was a nebula in the Outer Rim Territories' Dominus sector. It shared its name with the Dark Nebula, a Star Destroyer of the Galactic Empire.

properties.name: Darkknell
properties.poi: Sanctum Celestial, Southern Reservoir, Firtee Cluster, Continuum Void,
properties.description: Darkknell was a terrestrial planet located in the Outer Rim Territories, specifically in the Knel'char system, Grumani sector.

properties.name: Darlon
properties.description: Darlon is a planet from the Eucer sector. It was represented in the Galactic Senate by the politician Jonas Wallen.

properties.name: Darlyn Boda
properties.poi: Darlyn Boda jewel shop, Pepper's Pax,
properties.description: Darlyn Boda was a criminal trading planet and shadowport originally settled by the Galactic Republic, in the distant Darlyn Boda system of the Anoat sector, located at the far end of the Corellian Trade Spine in the Outer Rim Territories. Known for its humid, twisting jungles, bubbling mud pits, hanging clouds of steam, and a place where the credit was king, Darlyn Boda was a lawless world complementing perfectly the Greater Javin region in which it rested, an area of space negatively publicized for its pirate activity. Although Darlyn Boda fell under Imperial control during the Galactic Civil War, the planet played host to a number of groups, including the Alliance to Restore the Republic, the crime syndicate Black Sun, and the Bounty Hunters' Guild. In 3 ABY, the bounty hunters Zuckuss and 4-LOM delivered a group of ninety Echo Base refugees from the Battle of Hoth, including Toryn Farr, to Darlyn Boda's large Rebel underground.

properties.name: Daronak
properties.description: Daronak was a planet located in the Phelleem sector of the Outer Rim.

properties.name: Daroon
properties.description: Daroon was a planet represented in the Imperial Senate by Alku Vordu.

properties.name: Darsie
properties.description: Darsie was a backwater planet in between Commenor and Phorliss.

properties.name: Daruvvia
properties.description: The Daruvvia system was located in the Lorelli Reach, an area of the Hapes Cluster in the Slice portion of the Inner Rim. It was connected by the hyperlane known as the Lorell Route to the Ket and Sennex systems.

properties.name: Daslkehnt
properties.description: Daslkehnt was a planet in the Outer Rim Territories.

properties.name: Dasoor
properties.description: Dasoor was a planet in the Agarix sector of the Mid Rim. It was a largely lawless world, controlled by gangs supported by the Juvex leaders. The planet was famous for its podracing circuits.

properties.name: Datar
properties.poi: Unidentified Ghostling villageUnidentified Rebel Alliance base
properties.description: Datar was the homeworld of the Ghostling species. Its princess was kidnapped by slavers in 32 BBY, though she and several other Ghostling children were rescued by Anakin Skywalker.

properties.name: Dathomir
properties.poi: Aurilia, Dathomir Imperial PrisonDreaming RiverFrenzied RiverGreat CanyonInfinity GateJedi PraxeumMisty FallsNightsister fortressNightsister Stronghold, Quarantine Zone, Red HillsShattered RidgeSinging MountainStar TemplesSith AcademyTzarina crash site,
properties.description: Dathomir was a remote, neutral and obscure planet in the Outer Rim Territories, located in the Quelii sector. It was somewhat smaller than Coruscant in size and thus a slightly-below-standard gravity. The planetary day was close to standard though the planetary year was 491 days. Dathomir had four moons.

properties.name: Daupherm
properties.description: Daupherm was the capital world of the Daupherm Planet States. It was located in the Core Worlds, close to the Deep Core.

properties.name: Davirien
properties.description: Davirien was a jungle planet in the Corporate Sector owned by the Chiewab Amalgamated Pharmaceuticals Company. Chiewab used the planet for research, and also permitted the Galactic Empire to use the planet for training missions.

properties.name: Davnar
properties.description: Davnar II, also known as Davnar, was a planet located in the Core Worlds and the Interior regions, in grid square K-9 on the Standard Galactic Grid. The planet occupied the second orbital position in its star system. It was the homeworld of the kalidor, a predatory avian species, as well as historian Eloc Throno.

properties.name: Dayark
properties.description: Dayark was a temperate moon that orbited the gas giant Nepe in the Episol system. In 8 ABY, it served as the capital of the Kathol Republic.

properties.name: De'nel
properties.description: The De'nel system was an uninhabited star system in Brak sector of the Expansion Region. During the Galactic Civil War, the Alliance's Brak Sector Force established a secret starfighter base in the system with one full squadron of X-wings.

properties.name: Deadon
properties.description: Deadon was a planet in the Dantus sector of the Outer Rim.

properties.name: Deersheba
properties.description: Deersheba was a planet in the Iskin sector of the Mid Rim.

properties.name: Dega
properties.description: Dega was a planet in the Dega system of the Elrood sector. Its local day was 19 standard hours long; its year was 295 local days long. The planet was covered in rocky wastelands. It hosted a Radell Mining Corporation mining colony. During the early years of the Galactic Empire, the world's minerals and ores ran dry. The colony was abandoned, leaving behind a polluted planet. The old mines became smugglers' refuges.

properties.name: DeGerrillion
properties.description: DeGerrillion was a planet located in the Tamarin sector of the Outer Rim Territories where criminals Marg Sonat and Pari' Notgoth were almost killed.

properties.name: Deko Neimoidia
properties.description: Deko Neimoidia was one of the purse worlds founded by the Neimoidian race, along with Cato Neimoidia and Koru Neimoidia.

properties.name: Dela
properties.description: Dela was a female who was the sister of Lindon Javes. At some point, she was killed during hazardous maneuvers. By around 4 ABY, she was mentioned on Javes' Imperial record.

properties.name: Delacrix
properties.description: Delacrix was a planet located within the Calaron sector of the Outer Rim Territories. Originally known as Duinihiim, it was absorbed into Xim's empire as he expanded his borders from the Kingdom of Cron. Histories of the planet talked about the ancient Hutts, previous to their civil war, with horror and fear. During the Fourth Pius Dea Crusade, the Pius Dea-controlled Galactic Republic launched assaults on Delacrix and other planets to the north of Hutt Space.

properties.name: Delantine
properties.description: Delantine was a planet in the Delantine system. The Alliance sent Granit to Delantine to bolster Rebel sympathy. Trux Zissu was chosen to be the Governor of Delantine by the Alliance after the Battle of Yavin. Trux and his son Stuart Zissu traveled to the Delantine system from Yavin 4 with C-3PO, 4B-X, and R2-D2 in Timespan, but the ship was disabled by an Imperial warship when it reached the system. Trux gave himself up to the Imperials, buying Stuart time to escape to the surface of Da'nor in Escape Pod 4 with the droids. The Galactic Empire conquered the planet although Granit was able to evacuate the Rebels.

properties.name: Delderaan
properties.description: Delderaan was a terrestrial astronomical object located in the Delderaan system, a part of the Noonian sector in the New Territories portion of the Outer Rim Territories. Long before the Galactic Civil War, Delderaan's northern regions were home to several tribes that had primitive art. The gas giant–type planet Yavin Prime, due to its multi-colored bands of atmospheric gas, resembled an intricate ball of yarns woven by artists of the Delderaan tribes and thrown into the night sky.

properties.name: Delemede
properties.description: Delemede was an Outer Rim Territories astronomical object located in the Rseik sector. Overseen by a Galactic Republic governor, Delemede was struck by a plague around 3643 BBY. At that time, the governor refused to provide medical aid to Sith Empire refugees on Delemede, but he eventually changed his mind.

properties.name: Dellalt
properties.poi: J'uoch's mining camp, Xim's complex of treasure vaults, Survivors encampment
properties.description: Dellalt was a planet in the Tion Hegemony.

properties.name: Delle
properties.description: Delle was a planet located along the Perlemian Trade Route.

properties.name: Delphania
properties.description: The Delphania system was located in the Esuain sector, in the Trans-Hydian portion of the Mid Rim. It was home to the sentient Delphanian species.

properties.name: Delphon
properties.description: Delphon was a planet in the Outer Rim Territories, near the Ison Corridor. It was headquarters of the Black Hole Gang, which the Galactic Empire attempted to wipe out. The planet was represented in the Imperial Senate by Ilov Maas.

properties.name: Delrakkin
properties.description: Delrakkin was the only planet in the Delrakkin system capable of sustaining life. Home to the reptilian Delrakkin, the world was covered with mountain ranges and jungles, as well as a perpetual cloud cover that provided it with incessant storms and rain. Delrakkin City was the only civilized location on the planet and was home to the Delrakkin, until the Galactic Empire invaded.

properties.name: Delrian
properties.description: Delrian was a prison world in the Galactic Republic, Galactic Empire and New Republic. It was the second planet in its system.

properties.name: Deltooine
properties.description: Deltooine was a world in the Corporate Sector. It was home to a Corporate Sector Authority military base used to monitor Farana and Wild Space. It was part of the Tertiary Solenbaran hyperlane.

properties.name: Deltron
properties.description: Deltron was a planet in the galaxy's Inner Rim. It was best known for its spice wine.

properties.name: Demar
properties.description: Demar was the fourth planet of the Demar system.

properties.name: Demesel
properties.description: Demesel was a planet of grassy plains in the Meram sector, presumably in the Demesel system. Its local day was 22 standard hours long; its year was 285 local days long. It was a trading hub of the Outer Rim settled by a consortium of Galactic Core businesses. With the beginning of the Galactic Civil War, the planet lost its importance, becoming a backwater. It became the headquarters of the Glasfir Ring, which took over the local underworld, eliminating Hutt competition. The local government was coerced by Glasfir'a'lik to leave the crime ring alone.

properties.name: Demigue
properties.description: Demigue was a planet distant from Gascon, connected to it by the dangerous trade route known as the Demigue Terror.

properties.name: Deminol
properties.description: Deminol was a terrestrial world located in the Deminol system of the Juvex sector, a part of the Senex-Juvex region in the Western Reaches portion of the Mid Rim. The Senex-Juvex Loop hyperlane linked it to the Anstares and Ossiathora systems.

properties.name: Demnadi
properties.description: Demnadi was a Mid Rim planet located in the Far Xandil sector. During the Galactic Civil War, a planet-wide riot, believed by the Imperial Governor Cathers to have been instigated by local Rebel Alliance factions, erupted at Demnadi. In response, the Empire dispatched the CompForce Demnadi Relief Operation, which consisted of just one man, Major Fenris Sarhl, to pacify the planet.

properties.name: Demonsgate
properties.description: Demonsgate, also known as NCW-86, was a planet in the Outer Rim's Kathol Rift, near Yvara. From space the planet often appeared to be engulfed in flames due to the volcanic activity bleeding ionized particles into the atmosphere that interacted with debris attracted from the Rift. In reality, Demonsgate possessed a biosphere full of life including many indigenous, non-sapient life forms.

properties.name: Demophon
properties.description: Demophon was a planet in the Core Worlds, the primary planet of the Demophon system. The planet had two continents, Junno and Klis, which were surrounded by a vast ocean. It was named for Alres Demophon, one of the founders of the Republic Scout Service.

properties.name: Demos
properties.description: Demos Four was a planet with two moons, located in the Mid Rim. It was located on the Dustig Trace, nearby to the Tyus Cluster.

properties.name: Denab
properties.description: Denab was a planet in the Sluis sector of the Outer Rim. Prior to the Battle of Yavin, it was the site where Rebel Alliance starfighters led by Commander Grisserno defeated the Imperial Fourth Attack Squadron, composed of Victory-class Star Destroyers, at the Battle of Denab.

properties.name: Denarii Nebula
properties.description: The Denarii Nebula was a large nebula in the Gordian Reach. It was the remnant of a double-star supernova millennia before the Battle of Yavin. The Junction-Tierell Loop circumnavigated the nebula. Scouts had struggled to find a stable route between the worlds of Pinoora and Presbalin, on opposite sides of the Denarii Nebula. Denarii Station was located within the nebula.

properties.name: Denbar
properties.description: Denbar was a Human male who lived during the time of the Galactic Civil War.

properties.name: Denbo
properties.description: Denbo was a planet that hosted the Viraxo 54 orbital facility, a cargo transfer and storage station operated by Viraxo Shipping.

properties.name: Deneba
properties.description: Deneba was a reddish-orange Mid Rim planet on the Gamor Run, in the Deneba system. It hosted the Conclave at Deneba in 3997 BBY atop Mount Meru, which was disrupted by the Krath. The Krath killed Arca Jeth during their attack. Deneba was the homeworld of the Deneba bush.

properties.name: Denebia
properties.description: Denebia was an agriworld in the Senex sector of the Mid Rim. It was located on the Senex-Juvex Loop, at the junction of a hyperlane that led to the planet Suliana in The Tangles. It was a cool world, covered by dry plains which were punctuated by plantations and towns belonging to House Hax.

properties.name: Denevar
properties.description: Denevar was a planet. During the Galactic Civil War, the planet was controlled by Imperial Prefect Adar.

properties.name: Dennaskar
properties.description: Dennaskar was a forest planet located in the Mid Rim.

properties.name: Dennogra
properties.description: Dennogra, formerly known as Tialvai, was an arid world in the Outer Rim Territories. One of its cities, Zio Snaffkin, was the home of Sprool the Trader.

properties.name: Denon
properties.description: Denon, a planet located between Osarian and Nubia, was an ecumenopolis world, with city growth covering the entire surface, similar to Coruscant.

properties.name: Denova
properties.description: Denova was a planet in the Ojoster sector that consisted mostly of woods and high peaked mountains. Ancient ruins were noted to be present on the surface though details on them were largely undocumented. It was discovered during the Cold War by the Galactic Republic, who first scouted the world. This led to the discovery of extensive deposits of the ore known as baradium. In order to control this resource, the Republic hired a mercenary army due to manpower shortages in the Republic Military.

properties.name: Dentaal
properties.description: Dentaal was a planet in the Core Worlds. Its population was eradicated by an outbreak of the Candorian plague during the Galactic Civil War.

properties.name: Dentamma Nebula
properties.description: The Dentamma Nebula was located in the Varada sector of the Outer Rim Territories. At some point by 3 ABY, Archduke Monio of the Dentamma Nebula bet the ownership of the entire Unnipar system in a high-stakes sabacc game. The Teltior con artist Ceezva, who had bluffed her way into the game, managed to win the star system from Monio.

properties.name: Denubba
properties.description: Denubba was the location where General Maxine Baytor participated in the Battle of Denubba. It was located in the Mid Rim.

properties.name: Denusia
properties.description: The Denusia system was located within the Trailing Sectors portion of the Inner Rim. The system was home to the creature known as the Denusian squirmer.

properties.name: Deralia
properties.description: Deralia was a planet that was located in the Outer Rim Territories of the galaxy. After the Jedi captured the Sith Lord Darth Revan, the Jedi Council of Dantooine used the Force to heal the severe damage to Revan's mind, which he sustained after being betrayed by his apprentice, Darth Malak. But instead of restoring him, the Council opted to reprogram Revan by inserting an artificial personality into his vulnerable mind. As a result, Revan's memories of his life were buried under his subconsciousness and suppressed by false memories, thus leading him to believe that he was a common recruit in the Republic Military who was from the planet Deralia.

properties.name: Derellium
properties.description: Derellium was a planet of located within the Cronese Mandate of the Outer Rim.

properties.name: Deretta
properties.description: Deretta was a moon located in the Tarabba sector of the Outer Rim Territories, the staging point of the Deretta Destroyers, a mixed starfighter squadron of the Alliance to Restore the Republic, until their destruction prior to the Battle of Hoth.

properties.name: Derf
properties.description: Derf was a planet located in the Derf system of Sluis sector in the Outer Rim. It was the homeworld of Tik Tali Talosh, the President of the Max Rebo Fan Club.

properties.name: Derilyn
properties.poi: Base Derilysa, Derilyn Space Central, Government Palace, Moff's Palace, Park of Peace, Derilyn Space Defense Platform,
properties.description: Derilyn was a planet in Elrood sector on the Elrood-Derilyn Trade Route.

properties.name: Derra
properties.description: Derra was an astronomical object located in the galaxy's Expansion Region. During the High Republic Era, it housed the Derra Outpost which was headed by Jedi Master Tera Sinube around 231 BBY. Derra was relatively close to the Mid Rim planet Cyclor, so when the Nihil attacked the Cyclor Shipyards, the Jedi outpost there was asked to assist. Sinube sent a Drift of Jedi Vectors headed by Master Porter Engle.

properties.name: Derricon
properties.description: Derricon was a Rebel Alliance aligned planet during the Galactic Civil War.

properties.name: Deryvia
properties.description: The Deryvia system was an Inner Rim star system that was home to the creatures known as Deryvian snakes.

properties.name: Desargorr
properties.description: Desargorr was a planet located within the Allied Tion sector in the Outer Rim of the galaxy. Known for its beautiful mountain ranges, the planet was rich in minerals and was pitted by millennia of ruthless mining, as were the Desargorr system's numerous moons, asteroids and comets.

properties.name: Desevro
properties.poi: Jigani PortFar Wash, Near Wash, Inner Wash, Outer Wash, East Wash, The Swamplands,
properties.description: Desevro was a heavily-urbanized, ancient planet in the Tion Hegemony.

properties.name: Desolation Station
properties.description: Desolation Station was an asteroid-based Imperial facility that was used to assemble and transport superlaser components to the first Death Star battlestation. Commanded by an Imperial captain and overseen by the Force-sensitive clone X1, the facility became the target of a Rebel Alliance raid at some point between 2 BBY and 0 BBY. Alliance agent X2, assisted by a small group of Rebels, infiltrated the facility, rescued Wookiee prisoners being held there, and deactivated the shield corridor protecting a transport carrying the last of the superlaser components, the tributary beam. After securing the transport itself, X2 used the tributary beam to destroy Desolation Station.

properties.name: Desstious
properties.description: Desstious was a world located in the Desstious system, a part of the Lambda sector in the Trailing Sectors portion of the Mid Rim. It was the homeworld of the Human male Par Lankin, who was born in 50 BBY. Lankin's homeworld was noted in Wanted by Cracken, a datafile that served as a compilation of reports on various threats to the New Republic and was published in 7 ABY.

properties.name: Devaron
properties.poi: Blue MountainsWanderer's Path, Point of Parting, Temple of Eedit,
properties.description: Devaron was the home world of the Devaronians. It was located in the Colonies, near the Corellian Trade Spine. It was a planet of low mountains and deep valleys linked by thousands of rivers. The planet had strict capital punishment and a matriarchal government.

properties.name: Devil's Asteroid
properties.description: Devil's Asteroid was an Outer Rim Territories asteroid located within the star system of the same name.

properties.name: Devon
properties.description: The Devon were a sentient species native to Teagan. Doctor Tobias was a Devon.

properties.name: Deylerax
properties.description: Deylerax was a Mid Rim world, the homeworld of the near-Human Enu race.

properties.name: Deysum
properties.description: Deysum was an astronomical object located within the regions known as the Mid Rim Territories and the Slice. Situated in grid square Q-10 on the Standard Galactic Grid, Deysum was connected via a hyperspace route to the astronomical objects Randon and Uogo'cor.

properties.name: Di'tai'ni
properties.description: Di'tai'ni was the home of the Tai'ni, as well as many non-Tai'ni resident workers. It was two systems away from the Both system.

properties.name: Di'wor
properties.description: Di'wor was a planet that was located in Di'wor system, in the Morshdine sector of the Outer Rim region of the galaxy. The planet's singfruit groves' pollination season attracted many tourists.

properties.name: Diab
properties.description: Diab was a planet located within the Diab system of the Wild Space. Its sixth moon was orbited by the secret Jedi prison known as the Prism. Diab's electrical storms wreaked havoc with sensors and no transmissions were allowed in or out of the prison.

properties.name: Diado
properties.description: Diado was a snow-covered world in the Mid Rim.

properties.name: Diamal
properties.description: The Diamala  were a species from the planet Diamal, in the Core Worlds, who, along with their rivals the Ishori, became prominent during the crises over the Caamas Document and the apparent return of Grand Admiral Thrawn. Diamala were recognizable by their leathery skin, white manes, and fan-shaped ears, which they could move independently to gesture with. The Diamala temperament was generally calm and unemotional, with a strong sense of personal pride. They had extensive financial and business holdings, which they attributed to hard work rather than luck.

properties.name: Diatia Major
properties.description: Diatia Major was a star located within the Core Worlds and Southern Core's star system of the same name. Lying on the edge of the Deep Core region, the star was not orbited by any planets.

properties.name: Dibrook
properties.description: Dibrook was an uninhabitable planet in the Albarrio sector of the Outer Rim Territories.

properties.name: Dica
properties.description: Dica was a toxic wasteland of a planet where Qymaen jai Sheelal, better known as General Grievous, was believed to have murdered a Dark Jedi who carried Bane's Heart.

properties.name: Dilbana
properties.description: Dilbana was a planet in the Baxel sector of the Outer Rim. Located along the Triellus Trade Route, the planet was under a de facto rulership overseen by Jiliac Desilijic Tiron. This form of rule ended with the Hutt Lord's death at the hands of Durga Besadii Tai.

properties.name: Dilonexa
properties.description: Dilonexa may refer to one of the following:

properties.name: Din Nebula
properties.description: The Din Nebula, known to the Ewoks of the Endor system as the Gorax King's Heart, was a red-colored nebula located in the Outer Rim Territories' Moddell sector. Along with the Din Pulsar, it constituted the remains of the star Din, which had exploded in a supernova around 5000 BBY. At some point, survey droids penetrated the Din Nebula and reached the Din system.

properties.name: Din Pulsar
properties.description: The Din Pulsar was located in the Din system, a part of the Din Nebula in the Outer Rim Territories' Moddell sector. It was formed when a supernova destroyed the star Din around 5000 BBY, and it retained in its orbit the three cores of the former star's gas giant planets. Millennia later, the magnetic pulses emitted by the pulsar hindered travel along the nearby Trindello-Endor Route hyperlane.

properties.name: Dinlo
properties.description: Dinlo was a forest planet in the Dinlo system. It was the site of a rescue mission undertaken by Jedi Knight Etain Tur-Mukan to rescue a thousand clone troopers during the Clone Wars.

properties.name: Dioll
properties.description: Dioll was a rocky planet located in the Dioll system of the Juvex sector, a part of the Senex-Juvex region in the Western Reaches portion of the Mid Rim. The Kassido Bypass hyperlane linked it to the Kardura and Thermon systems.

properties.name: Diorda
properties.description: Diorda was a planet in the Mid Rim that contained a secret Separatist weapons factory. During the Clone Wars, Luminara Unduli was assigned to investigate the secret factory, and after a duel in Mondo-Mod the Hutt's Arena of Doom, Luminara received the coordinates of the weapons factory, and presumably used them to destroy it.

properties.name: Dirha
properties.description: Dirha was a gritty industrial planet that was located within the Dirha system of the galaxy's Hutt Space region and lay on the hyperlane called the Sisar Run, which connected it to the world of Cyborrea and the Sespe system.

properties.name: Dithanune
properties.description: Dithanune was the homeworld of the needle beast.

properties.name: Divora
properties.description: The Divora system was located in the Rifle Worlds, an area of the Hapes Cluster in the Slice portion of the Inner Rim. It was connected by the hyperlane known as the Great Rim Route to the Rifle Worlds' Wodan system and to the Jodaka system in the Corsair Outback. The Divora system was the origin point of the game known as Divoran holochess.

properties.name: Dix'thaar
properties.description: Dix'thaar was a planet in the Inner Rim of the galaxy, host to a Rebel Alliance cell during the Galactic Civil War.

properties.name: Diyu
properties.description: Diyu was a planet that was located within the Diyu system of the galaxy's Hutt Space region and lay on the hyperlane called the Shag Pabol, which connected it to the Rorak system and the world of Ylesia.

properties.name: Djurmo
properties.description: Djurmo was a volcanic planet located within the Djurmo system in the Strabin sector of the Mid Rim region of the galaxy. It was the homeworld of the reptilian Huralok species, including the pirate Redkihl Rokk. The region of space around Djurmo was explored between 3000 BBY and 1004 BBY, and it was in unaligned space during the New Sith Wars. It was within space loyal to the Galactic Republic during the Clone Wars and was under the control of the Galactic Empire until at least 11 ABY, but was outside of the Empire's territory by the following year.

properties.name: DNX-N1
properties.description: DNX-N1 was a planet located within the Wild Space DNX-N1 system. Charted but largely unexplored, it was the homeworld of the sentient gaseous species known as the Filar-Nitzan.

properties.name: Doan
properties.description: Doan was a tiny planet in the Outer Rim Territories whose sole economy was focused on mining. It was ruled by a group of nobles, the Doan Royal House, while most of its population were miners who lived in poverty.

properties.name: Doaskin
properties.description: Doaskin was a planet located in the Bruanii sector, and was the primary base for TaggeCo's operations.

properties.name: Dodz
properties.description: Dodz was a tiny planet in the Outer Rim.

properties.name: Dohlban
properties.description: Dohlban was a terrestrial planet located in the Dohlban system, a part of the Dohlbani sector in the Slice portion of the Mid Rim. The Kaaga Run hyperlane connected it to the Void Station in the Bothan sector and the Nar Kaaga system in Hutt Space.

properties.name: Dohnia
properties.description: Dohnia was a planet in the Mid Rim.

properties.name: Dohu
properties.description: Dohu VII was the seventh of eight planets in the Dohu system. It was the homeworld of the mineral-based species called the Silika. Linkaas Corporation had a warehouse near Docking Bay 71 in Skagras.

properties.name: Doldrums
properties.description: Doldrums was a star in the Inner Rim.

properties.name: Doldur
properties.description: Doldur was the Imperial-controlled sector capital of Doldur sector. Imperial Moff Eisen Kerioth considered it his personal territory and sponsored research of an antiblaster energy shield.

properties.name: Doli
properties.description: Doli was a planet in the Outer Rim rumored by 39 BBY to be the location of a Sith holocron.

properties.name: Dolis
properties.description: Dolis 3 was an Imperial Remnant planet in the Outer Rim Territories, in the influence of Yaga Minor. It was locked in perpetual winter because of its distance from its sun.

properties.name: Dolla
properties.description: Dolla was an astronomical object located in the Dolla system, a part of the Videnda sector in the Western Reaches portion of the Outer Rim Territories. It was situated at the junction of the hyperlanes known as the Nothoiin Corridor, which connected it to the Bavva system in the Anoat sector and the Eriadu system of the Seswenna sector, and the Anturi Reach, which linked it to the Senex sector's Yetoom system.

properties.name: Dolomar
properties.description: Dolomar was the sector capital of Dolomar sector. The mostly Human population lived underground to avoid the bitter cold. The largest of these underground complexes, Diflu, was located in the northernmost mountains of the planet, the L'tiri Peaks. The local day lasted 45 standard hours. The local year lasted 224 local days. Its hydrosphere was mostly solidified as glaciers and snow.

properties.name: Dolstan
properties.description: Dolstan was one of the planets of the Pimbrellan League. It was the planet originally settled by the Pinacists, and was dominant in League politics. It was a dry planet, covered in savannas, deserts and land-locked salt lakes. The land was fertile, and Dolstan provided much of the food for the League.

properties.name: Dolva Prime
properties.description: Dolva Prime was a planet located in the Semagi sector of the Mid Rim.

properties.name: Dom-Bradden
properties.description: Dom-Bradden, also known as Bradden, was a planet in the Outer Rim.

properties.name: Domgrin
properties.description: Domgrin was a planet that was located within the Domgrin system, a part of the Prefsbelt sector in the galaxy's Outer Rim Territories. It was located relatively close to the planet Gonmore.

properties.name: Dominus
properties.description: Dominus was a Jedi Master who was active up to and during the Great Sith War. A respected and venerable member of the Jedi Order, Dominus took multiple apprentices, his favorite of which was the Vultan Zona Luka. However, Luka was eventually seduced to the dark side and joined the Brotherhood of the Sith under Dark Lord Exar Kun in 3996 BBY. Not long after, Luka, who had been ordered by Kun to kill her former Master, attacked Dominus in his home. Although Dominus was shocked at his dearest apprentice's murder attempt, he still engaged the Vultan in a lightsaber duel. Luka gained the upper hand and struck Dominus down after a brief clash, although the dying Jedi Master gathered the strength to kill his former apprentice with the Force.

properties.name: Don I
properties.description: The Don I system was in the Freeworlds Territory of the Tapani sector, near the Lusk system.

properties.name: Don II
properties.description: The Don II system was in the Freeworlds Territory of the Tapani sector, near the Lusk system.

properties.name: Dona Laza
properties.description: The Dona Laza was a tapcafe in business circa 9 ABY. The smuggler Aves told Wedge Antilles that any messages left with the establishment's bartender would reach him. A large number of Boga Minawk enthusiasts frequented it.

properties.name: Donadus
properties.description: Donadus was an astronomical object located in the Donadus system, a part of the Inner Rim's Bamula sector. It shared its name with the sentient species Donadi.

properties.name: Doneer'so
properties.description: Doneer'so was the primary planet of the Doneer'so system in the Fakir sector of the Bakchou arm. It was the homeworld of the insectoid Doneer race. During the Galactic Civil War, Doneer'so served as the sector capital for the Galactic Empire, who established their headquarters in the Sotak'vik clan-city. The Empire maintained a deflector shield and nuclear-damping system over their sector capital, and the use of Sotak'vik engendered fanatic loyalty to the Empire in the Sotak city-clan. Other cities, such as Tokks'vik which was the planet's main shipyard, support the Alliance to Restore the Republic.

properties.name: Doniphon
properties.description: Doniphon was a planet in the Outer Rim's Kwymar sector, in the system of the same name. Doniphon was invaded by the Galactic Empire in 17 BBY, during the Empire's suppressions of rebel activity in the sector. An Imperial platoon succeeded in rooting out Doniphon's dissidents, although promising stormtrooper commander Beilert Valance suffered grave wounds in the process.

properties.name: Dononter Minor
properties.description: Dononter Minor was a world located in the Dononter Minor system, a part of the Mid Rim's Dononter sector. Dononter Minor had a Type I breathable atmosphere, and it was the homeworld of the plant known as the widowmaker, which could be used as a weapon.

properties.name: Donovia
properties.description: Donovia was a planet in the Hali sector of the Expansion Region. It was a mining world of constant rainfall. Many Donovian miners fled the planet to Coruscant when Donovia seceded shortly before the Clone Wars, wishing to remain Galactic Republic citizens.

properties.name: Dontamo
properties.description: Dontamo was a planet in the Radiant One system, near Alba-16. It was a jungle world in 19 BBY and it was where Ferus Olin and Clive Flax were held in captivity at Dontamo Prison for crimes against the Galactic Empire. The prisoners were compelled to work in a factory building parts of the first Death Star.

properties.name: Doornik-1142
properties.description: Doornik-1142, a brown dwarf star, was the primary star of the Doornik-1142 system, located at the edge of the Koornacht Cluster. It was orbited by four gaseous planets.

properties.name: Doornik-207
properties.description: Doornik-207 was a planet in the Koornacht Cluster. The planet was colonized by the Corasgh, settled under the Galactic Empire. However, it was wiped out by the Yevetha during the Great Purge, whereupon the Yevetha colonized the world.

properties.name: Dor Nameth
properties.description: Dor Nameth was a distant planet located in the Dor Nameth system, a part of the Bright Jewel sector in the New Territories portion of the Mid Rim. The planet was situated on the Celanon Spur hyperlane, which connected it to the Qiilura and Korvaii systems. Dor Nameth was the homeworld of Brangus Glee, an elder of a dexterous species of renowned travelers. By 12 ABY, the planet fell within the borders of the New Republic.

properties.name: Dorajan
properties.description: Dorajan was a jungle planet.

properties.name: Dorande
properties.description: Dorande was the homeworld of the Dorande race, who tried to conquer the planet R-Duba. This plan was foiled by C-3PO and R2-D2, however.

properties.name: Dorcin
properties.description: Dorcin was a planet in the Outer Rim Territories, on or near the Rimma Trade Route. It was a Dorcin trader who traded the Squibs starship technology in exchange for mineral rights to a frozen waste on Skor II.

properties.name: Dordolum
properties.poi: Solferin Shipping Company, Stand of Public Expression,
properties.description: Dordolum was a planet located in the Colonies Region of the galaxy. Its population included individuals from a number of sentient species, such as Aqualish, Barabels, Bothans, Duros, Humans and Ishori. A short distance from a spaceport on the planet was a plaza that contained the Stand of Public Expression. The plaza was lined with paved pathways and flowerbeds, and was bordered by the Bothan-owned Solferin Shipping Company. In 19 ABY, Drend Navett, Klif and several other Imperial agitators instigated a riot against the Solferin Shipping Company, ostensibly in outrage at Bothan involvement in the Destruction of Caamas in 19 BBY.

properties.name: Doreen
properties.description: Doreen was an ocean planet in the Tangles region of Senex sector in the Mid Rim. The planet was controlled by the aristocratic House Petro.

properties.name: Dorella
properties.description: Dorella was a planet in the Dorella system in the Tapani sector. It was one of the Freeworlds and one of the Three Ellas. It had a liberal government that was looser about crime and smuggling than most Tapani worlds.

properties.name: Dorellia
properties.description: The Dorellia system was a star system located in the Tapani sector's Mecetti Province, between the Lastelle and Nyssa systems.

properties.name: Dorenia
properties.description: The Dorenia system was located in the Mayagil sector of the Outer Rim Territories. It was the origin point of the musical instrument known as the Dorenian Beshniquel.

properties.name: Dorin
properties.poi: Baran Do temple, Caverns of the Hidden One, Jedi Enclave, Throne chamber,
properties.description: Dorin was a dark and dusty planet in the Expansion Region. It was the homeworld of the Kel Dors, with an atmosphere of a unique gas and helium.

properties.name: Doris
properties.description: The Doris system was in the Freeworlds Territory of the Tapani sector, near the Dorella system.

properties.name: Dorlo
properties.description: Dorlo was a planet located in the Atravis sector of the Outer Rim Territories and was controlled by the Galactic Empire.

properties.name: Dornea
properties.description: Dornea was the homeworld of the Dornean species. It was located in the Dornean system of the Dominus sector, which bordered the Calamari sector out on the Slice.

properties.name: Dorriella
properties.description: Dorriella was a terrestrial world located in the Dorriella system, a part of the Outer Rim Territories' Wazta sector. A family with three children, including the Human girl Shanna Kinn, lived there, with Kinn spending time with her two older brothers and learning to repair starships as a result.

properties.name: Dorsis
properties.description: Dorsis was a Core world in the Corellian sector sometimes referred to as "Mini-Coruscant."

properties.name: Dorvalla
properties.description: Dorvalla was a lommite mining world, located in the Videnda sector, controlled by Dorvalla Mining and initially independent of the Galactic Republic. In 33 BBY, it was the scene of a battle between the Trade Federation and the Nebula Front. Subsequently, it was taken over by the Trade Federation.

properties.name: Doshan
properties.description: Doshan was a planet in the Drannik sector of the Expansion Region. It was situated on hyperlane between the Namadii Corridor and the Hydian Way.

properties.name: Dosuun
properties.description: Dosuun was a world in the Wild Space, and was outside the control of the New Republic following the Battle of Endor. From space, the planet could be seen to possess varied terrain and several seas. It also had at least one area of hilly temperate grassland.

properties.name: Douglas
properties.description: Douglas may refer to one of the following:

properties.name: Draay
properties.description: Draay could refer to:

properties.name: Draboon
properties.description: Draboon was a Mandalorian planet located within the Mandalore sector, in the region of the galaxy known as the Outer Rim Territories. Situated within the eponymous Draboon system, Draboon was a source of high-quality lapis.

properties.name: Drackmar
properties.description: Drackmar was the Drackmarian homeworld, located in the Drackmar system. The atmosphere of Drackmar was composed of methane, requiring native Drackmarians to wear special methane helmets when traveling off-world.

properties.name: Dractu
properties.description: Dractu was a peaceful Mid Rim farming planet. It was the home of the Dractuvian people, as well as creatures mostly used as delicacies on the planet, such as Dractuvian cave slugs.

properties.name: Draflago
properties.description: The Draflago were a sentient species from the Draflago system that was active in the galaxy in the early years of the Galactic Empire. The Tion Hegemony's sole university, the University of Rudrig, had a number of luxury mud tanks available for visiting Draflago.

properties.name: Dragonflower Nebula
properties.description: The Dragonflower Nebula was a nebula located in the Doldur sector. Silver Station was rather close.

properties.name: Draik
properties.description: Draik 4 was a planet located in the Mid Rim. The Imperial-run Damorian Repair Yard was nearby.

properties.name: Dramassia
properties.description: Dramassia was a planet in the Juvex sector of the Mid Rim, near the Agarix Trade Route.

properties.name: Drannik
properties.description: Drannik was a planet in the Expansion Region. It was a member world of the New Republic and was represented in the New Republic Senate.

properties.name: Draria
properties.description: Draria was a planet. The Task Force on Alliance Security recorded it as the last known location of Granse Confederacy member Zayl Braith.

properties.name: Drash-So
properties.description: Drash-So was a planet located in the Selvatas system of the Outer Rim Territories. During the Second Imperial Civil War, the One Sith ran a prison labor camp on the planet. Ania Solo and Ramid were two of the inmates there. The camp was liberated by the Empire-in-Exile at the end of the war.

properties.name: Draukyze
properties.description: Draukyze was a planet in the Draukyze system of the Thanium sector.

properties.name: Dravian Starport
properties.description: Dravian Starport, also known as Dravian Station, was a space station located between the planets Cotellier and Syned. The station was a haven for smugglers because it was a great distance from any inhabited systems. Due to the types of people that frequented Dravian Starport, the space station eventually became full with different kinds of businesses, including casinos, hotels, and restaurants. Topatz Shipping and Skypath Industries were two such businesses. Jontz Freight was a shipping company which operated in the Dravian Starport. With a standard Class 1 hyperdrive, Dravian Spaceport was 16 days from Dreffon IV, 2 days from Ather, 23 days from Bazaar, and 5 days from Vlemoth Port.

properties.name: Dravione
properties.description: Dravione was a planet located in the Allied Tion sector of the Tion Cluster. One of the first conquests of the Pirate King Xer VIII when he expanded from Argai, its prominence was rapidly eclipsed by nearby Jaminere. By the time of the Galactic Empire, it was a bleak agricultural world notably only for a handful of Xim-era aeries in the planet's mountains that were remarkably well-preserved by the thin air.

properties.name: Drayberia
properties.description: The Drayberia system was a star system located in the Sertar sector of the Outer Rim Territories and Trans-Hydian regions. It was home to the creatures known as Drayberian hawks.

properties.name: Drearia
properties.description: Drearia was an Inner Rim world situated on the Hydian Way hyperlane. Sharing its name with the Drearian Defense Conglomerate, Drearia was a member of the Galactic Republic and later the Galactic Empire, for which it served as a fortress world. The world saw two clashes between Imperial and New Republic forces during the Galactic Civil War, and, in 10 ABY, the Mandator III-class dreadnought Aculeus was lost at Drearia due to Imperial in-fighting.

properties.name: Dreena
properties.description: Dreena was a nearly uninhabited ocean world visited by Prince Isolder and his father during Isolder's childhood, playing in the pure oceans of the planet.

properties.name: Dreighton
properties.description: Dreighton was a desert planet littered with rocks. There was an Imperial facility located on the planet. Below it, the Galactic Empire built a huge network of pipe lines and mining tunnels spanning kilometers beneath the surface.

properties.name: Dreighton Nebula
properties.description: The Dreighton Nebula was a nebula located within the Dantus sector in the Outer Rim region of the galaxy which contained the planets Aeten II, Dreighton, and Imdaar, as well as the Belt of Arah.

properties.name: Dreizan
properties.description: Dreizan was the homeworld of Imperial commander Rezi Soresh.

properties.name: Dremulae
properties.description: Dremulae was a wealthy resort world known for the natural beauty of its Sea of Translucency.

properties.name: Dresscol
properties.description: Dresscol was a location in the galaxy that was among the many places to which the Galactic Empire sent probe droids in search of the hidden base of the Alliance to Restore the Republic in 3 ABY.

properties.name: Dressel
properties.description: Dressel was the homeworld of the Dressellians and primary world of the Dressel system.

properties.name: Dreve
properties.description: Dreve was a planet.

properties.name: Drexel
properties.description: Drexel was the sole planet in the Drexel system. It was a water world, home to the sentient Sea-dragons.

properties.name: Drezzi
properties.description: Drezzi was a planet in the Drezzi system of the Outer Rim's Esstran sector that was ruled by a monarchy. At some point before 3954 BBY, the Sith Empire conquered Drezzi, and the husband of Drezzi's Queen Ressa was killed by the Dark Councilor Darth Nyriss. In gratitude for Nyriss' decision to spare her life and those of her children, Ressa sent a decorative holoprojection to the Sith Lord that was displayed in Nyriss's residence. During his career, intelligence operative Rane Kovach carried out an assignment on Drezzi at the request of Theron Shan of the Republic Strategic Information Service; Kovach was tasked with infiltrating dissident groups and fomenting revolution while minimizing casualties.

properties.name: Drgi
properties.description: Drgi was a planet located in the galaxy's Expansion Region. Drgi was also the homeworld of Rorr'hn.

properties.name: Droecil
properties.description: Droecil was a planet home to a Rebel Alliance cell.

properties.name: Drog
properties.description: Drogs were a species of large black beetle native to the planet S'krrr. Drogs could eat and digest almost anything. They usually ate plants, but would also scavenge corpses. They usually traveled in large swarms. Although they destroyed many plants, they were also the main pollinators on the planet. They will even scavenge for food, and have few natural enemies. Their only natural predators were the bat-like creatures known as shreevs. S'krrr gardeners worked to maintain a balanced population of shreevs and drogs. Drogs reproduce prolifically, so shreevs are needed to control the drog population. It was discovered that if one put two drogs in a container, in less than a standard day the drogs in the container would number more than ten. Many claimed the S'krrr were descended from the drogs, although no evidence of this was ever discovered. A cult of S'krrr worshiped the drogs because they believed this.

properties.name: Drogheda
properties.description: Drogheda was a planet rich in ore serving as a wealthy mining planet in the Teraab sector.

properties.name: Dromund Kaas
properties.poi: Dark Force Temple, Dark Temple, Imperial Citadel, Sith Academy,
properties.description: Dromund Kaas was the third planet in the Dromund system, a star system in the Sith Worlds region of the Outer Rim Territories's Esstran sector. Originally a colony of the Sith Empire, its location was lost by the time of the Great Hyperspace War with the Galactic Republic, but the Sith Emperor led his people on a twenty-year odyssey that ended with the rediscovery of Dromund Kaas in 4980 BBY. The Emperor and the remnants of the shattered Sith society reconstituted the Sith Empire with Dromund Kaas as its capital, taming the planet's savage jungles and building up their Empire's strength from the skyscrapers of Kaas City. Dromund Kaas remained safe from Republic reprisal when the Empire launched the Great Galactic War in 3681 BBY, though a Republic invasion fleet assaulted the Imperial capital in 3640 BBY during the Galactic War with the Empire while a Jedi Knight fought and defeated the Emperor in personal combat.

properties.name: Drongar
properties.poi: Republic Mobile Surgical UnitsRMSU-1RMSU-3RMSU-5RMSU-6RMSU-7RMSU-9RMSU-12RMSU-14Sea of SpongesGreat Jasserak SwampJasserak LowlandsJasserak HighlandsQarohan Steppes
properties.description: Drongar was a mostly uninhabitable tropical planet in the Outer Rim Territories, with the native airborne spores causing death to those who were not protected from them. The climate was characterized by common monsoons with devastating electrical storms, soaring temperatures, and humidity over 90%. There was also a large atmospheric oxygen content. The planet had two small moons and was located in its system with another three planets. Natural features of Drongar included the Sea of Sponges, Great Jasserak Swamp and the Qarohan Steppes.

properties.name: Dronseen
properties.description: Dronseen was a planet of the Dronseen system.

properties.name: Droxine
properties.description: Droxine was a planet located in the Esstran sector of the Outer Rim Territories. It was home to the carchar and nightmare demon species, although the latter—intelligent, telepathic killers—were believed to have been eradicated by the time of the Clone Wars. However, some survived, and one such demon, Reist, was forced to work for the Galactic Empire during the Galactic Civil War. He was sent to Lapez 3 to kill the Rebel Luke Skywalker but was defeated by the pilot.

properties.name: Droxu
properties.description: Droxu was a ringed moon in the Cignet system on the Outer Rim of the galaxy.

properties.name: Drualkiin
properties.description: Drualkiin was an astronomical object situated on the Pabol Sleheyron hyperspace route in the Outer Rim Territories.

properties.name: Druckenwell
properties.poi: BlasTech manufacturing complexBotcha'sDocking bay 1138Druckenwell Shipyard, Happy's Landing
properties.description: Druckenwell was an industrial world in the Doldur sector, on the Corellian Run. A Trade Federation world, it was loyal to the Confederacy of Independent Systems during the Clone Wars. It was best known for a BlasTech weapons manufacturing complex that was located there.

properties.name: Drunost
properties.description: Drunost was a planet located within the Shelsha sector of the galaxy. A Consolidated Shipping hub and outlet were located near the planet's largest town, Conso City, making Drunost a good stop for fuel and supplies. Nominally under the jurisdiction of the Galactic Empire, the world consisted primarily of mines and farmland as well as company towns, and was settled by both Humans and aliens. During the time of the Galactic Civil War, the planet was also home to a Rebel Alliance supply line. The planet was also the scene of pirate activity engaged in by the BloodScar group.

properties.name: Drup's Star
properties.description: Drup's Star was one of the star of the Drup's Star system, along with Drup's Companion, in the Saijo sector of the Outer Rim.

properties.name: Du Hutta
properties.description: Du Hutta was a planet located in Hutt Space. It was a Hutt colony world and was home to many private retreats owned by Nal Hutta's Hutts. After the Battle of Endor, Umpass-stay went to work for Jocoro Desilijic Tiure on Du Hutta.

properties.name: Du Mai
properties.description: Du Mai was a desert planet in the Bryx sector of the Mid Rim. During the final days of the Clone Wars, a clone trooper of the Grand Army of the Republic crashed with his ARC-170 starfighter on the planet. Having sustained head injuries, the trooper started uttering cryptic messages and took refuge in a mountain cave. His seemingly mystical behavior began to attract pilgrims to Du Mai and he became known as the "Lost Prophet". It was not until 21 ABY that the journalist Cindel Towani identified the Lost Prophet as a clone trooper, discovering that his gnomic utterances actually consisted of scrambled bits of his Kaminoan conditioning and flash-training.

properties.name: Dubrava
properties.description: Dubrava was a planet where Jal Te Gniev was placed to recruit rebel pilots. An Imperial patrol discovered him, by an accident, in a local cantina where they had tracked down a female informant. Jal's life was saved by the young humanoid Dubravan, Bobek. The planet was referred to as the galaxy's armpit hole.

properties.name: Dubrillion
properties.poi: Dubrillion Aquarium, Dubrillion superlaser facility, Lando's Folly,
properties.description: Dubrillion was a planet with beautiful oceans and lush-green continents, framed with fluffy white clouds. It was the sister world of Destrillion.

properties.name: Duhma
properties.description: The Duhma were a rare sentient species that was divided into many tribes. The tribes identified themselves through use of ceremonial tattoos. The Duhma lived on the dark side of their planet and had lost their sight over time. As a result, they wore dark visors during their occasional journeys off their planet to protect their highly sensitive eyes.

properties.name: Duinarbulon
properties.description: Duinarbulon was a planet located within the Tion Cluster in the Outer Rim Territories. One of the original member-worlds of the Kingdom of Cron, it was absorbed into Xim's empire. This planet was home to the Duinarbulon Star Lancers, the elite soldiers of Xim's empire that fought for him during the war against the Hutts. According to later legend, massive stones of polished ebon marked their Parade Grounds, though by the era of the Galactic Empire, any sign of these stones had vanished, and Ximologists considered the Parade Grounds on Duinarbulon that survived to be obvious fakes to attract tourists.

properties.name: Dulathia
properties.description: Dulathia was an Imperial planet, until it was retaken by the New Republic around 8 ABY. The Star Destroyer Tempest was one of the few ships to survive, and brought its contents to Garos IV.

properties.name: Dulin
properties.description: Dulin may refer to one of the following:

properties.name: Dulvoyinn
properties.description: Dulvoyinn was an astronomical object located in the regions known as the Deep Core and the Interior. It was also situated in the grid square K-12 of the Standard Galactic Grid.

properties.name: Dunari's Rest
properties.description: Dunari's Rest was a casino/resort space station and minor trading facility, located in the Mayagil sector of the Outer Rim Territories.

properties.name: Duneeden
properties.description: Duneeden was a planet in the Core Worlds. Despite its proximity to Coruscant, few beings ever came to Duneeden. It was home to the Cascardi Mountains, which was the location of a few private retreats.

properties.name: Dur Sabon
properties.description: The Dur Sabon were a species of amphibious, serpentine sentients from the planet of the same name. They took care of Princess Foolookoola during her time there in 33 BBY.

properties.name: Dura-Kahn
properties.description: Dura-Kahn was a planet in the Expansion Region. It was part of the Galactic Empire and inhabited by Humans who maintained a tradition of big game hunting. One young native hunter was Moradmin Bast, who became an Imperial officer.

properties.name: Durace
properties.poi: Alkaline Sea, Diamond Desert, Forest of Broken Glass, Outpost 17, Pictograph Caverns,
properties.description: Durace was a toxic, barren planet in a hostile region of space in the Unknown Regions. Although the atmosphere was breathable, Durace's hostile weather made colonization difficult.

properties.name: Durgen's Star
properties.description: Durgen's Star was a white dwarf star that was located in the Durgen's Star system. It was situated in the Loop Worlds area of the Gordian Reach sector, within the Trans-Hydian portion of the Outer Rim Territories. Durgen's Star lay on the hyperlane known as the Junction-Tierell Loop, which connected it to the Povanaria and Trinovat systems.

properties.name: Durgeon
properties.description: Durgeon was a planet in the Galov sector of the Outer Rim Territories of the galaxy. It hosted a Rebel Alliance base that was eventually destroyed by Beylyssa.

properties.name: Durkteel
properties.description: Durkteel was a Mid Rim world with a population of approximately 3.2 billion at the dawn of the Clone Wars. It was the homeworld of the Saurin, a subspecies of Trandoshan with human-like hands. Durkteel was located along the Durkteel Loop.

properties.name: Duro
properties.poi: RrudobarTayana districtGatewaySettlement 32Pri-Andylan shipyardsDuro Starshipwright ShipyardsRangelandTiercam DamValley of RoyaltyImperial Reprogramming InstituteVyrdat Stardock
properties.description: Duro  was the heavily polluted and depopulated homeworld of the Duros species. Located on the Corellian Trade Spine in the Core, the planet itself was mostly abandoned, mainly housing food processing plants. Most of the population lived in one of the twenty orbiting cities. Duro was also home to a large number of orbital shipyards.

properties.name: Durollia
properties.description: Durollia was a celestial body located in the Durollia  system, a part of the Outer Rim Territories' Kalamith sector. It had at least one spaceport. At some point during the Galactic Civil War, Yesgar's pirates, who had a hideout on the Esstran sector astronomical object Antared III, were spotted in Durollia's spaceport.

properties.name: Duron
properties.description: Duron was a planet located in the Duron system. Obo Rin first learned of the Charon race there.

properties.name: Duroon
properties.description: Duroon was a planet in Corporate Sector visited by Han Solo in 2 BBY.

properties.name: Durren
properties.description: Durren was a terrestrial planet near the border between the Meridian and Antemeridian sectors that was home to the New Republic's naval base in Meridian sector.

properties.name: Duunir
properties.description: Duunir was a planet in the Kibilini sector of the Outer Rim.

properties.name: Dwartii
properties.description: Dwartii was a planet located in the Inner Rim, in grid square N-8 on the Standard Galactic Grid. It was home to the eponymous Four Sages of Dwartii—Sistros Nevet, Faya Rodemos, Yanjon Zelmar, and Braata Danlos—who were controversial philosophers and lawgivers from the early days of the Galactic Republic. Dwartii also shared its name with a social group that had a set of glyphs associated with it. A map showing Dwartii's location in the galaxy was included in Traveler's Guide to Batuu, a guide book for the planet Batuu written by the historian Eloc Throno.

properties.name: Dweem
properties.description: Dweem was a planet in the Outer Rim Territories used as a base of operations for the Galactic Republic until abandoned because of the Order of the Terrible Glare. Around 60 BBY, Aqinos trained the Iron Knights on Dweem, where he hid with them during the later Great Jedi Purge.

properties.name: Dwor
properties.description: Dwor was a planet located in the Steniplis sector.

properties.name: Dyspeth
properties.description: Dyspeth was a shadowy moon, that was located in the Varada sector of the Outer Rim.

properties.name: Ealor
properties.description: Ealor was a temperate planet in the Bysis system of the Outer Rim Territories' Parmic sector. It was covered with grasslands and temperate forests.

properties.name: Eamus
properties.description: Eamus 6 was a terrestrial astronomical object located in the Eamus system, a part of the Southern Core portion of the Core Worlds. It had at least one sun, and occupied the sixth orbital position within the system.

properties.name: Ebaq
properties.description: Ebaq was a gas giant in the Treskov system and the fifth planet of that system, orbiting Treskov 115-W. The planet had eleven moons, including Ebaq 9.

properties.name: Ebenmal
properties.description: Ebenmal was a planetoid located in the Ebenmal system of the Mid Rim's Irnaj sector. It was on Ebenmal that a battle between the Galactic Empire and the Rebel Alliance was fought sometime between the years 2 and 1 BBY. The ancient citadel of Ebenmal, which was said to have never fallen to an invader for over ten thousand years, was attacked by eighty-five Imperial jumptroopers, who brought chaos and disarray. In one hour's time, 3,000 Rebels surrendered. The battle was later mentioned in Imperial Atrocities and Other Noble Pursuits, by historian Chen Ming-di.

properties.name: Eberon
properties.description: Eberon was a planet located in the Eberon system of the Mid Rim's Mytaranor sector. Around the time of the Great Galactic War, Eberon was engaged in the Eberon–Kashyyyk War with the nearby planet Kashyyyk, but the conflict was eventually ended by the personal intervention of the Jedi Satele Shan.

properties.name: Ebiwaan
properties.description: Ebiwaan was a planet in the Sarin sector of the Outer Rim Territories. It was the endpoint of the Leisure Corridor opposite Coruscant.

properties.name: Ebra
properties.description: Ebra, also referred to as Ebran, was a planet located in the Mid Rim's Kesh sector. Its surface was mountainous and featured caverns and large canyons such as the Grythsorin. Ebra was the homeworld of the Ebranites, six-armed humanoids who were well adapted for their environment. A relatively primitive, clan-based species, the Ebranites exported the valuable oil lu-ramin off-world.

properties.name: Ec Pand
properties.description: Ec Pand was a Mid Rim world that was located within the Ado sector, and was one of the Induparan Crown Worlds.

properties.name: Echnos
properties.description: Echnos, also known as Tinn VI-D, was a moon of Tinn VI with a nitrogen-rich atmosphere. Its sole settlement was an immense domed structure called Echnos City which arose as a way station for numerous ships that lost their magnetic bottle shielding from passing too close to Tinn VI's powerful negative magnetic field. Echnos City was the headquarters of the Mandellian Corporation, which hosted a demolition derby called the BlastBoast 2000 located at the bottom of the city inside Echnos Exhibition Dome.

properties.name: Eckless
properties.description: Eckless was a planet that was once subjugated by Hahz Fallone. It was a primitive world rich in ores and minerals. It was attacked by Fallone with a fleet supplied by Jorga Sune. Eventually the natives rebelled and drove Fallone and his men off the planet, but not until they had raided the planet's treasury.

properties.name: Eclipse
properties.description: An eclipse was an astronomical event that occurred when a celestial body was temporarily obscured by another. Having witnessed one such event once on Coruscant, the Queen of Alderaan Breha Organa initially thought she was witnessing another eclipse when the Death Star obscured Alderaan's sun. The Death Star had previously created the same scenario when it obscured Jedha's sun before destroying Jedha City in a test.

properties.name: Eczar
properties.description: Eczar was an astronomical object located within the Eczar system, a part of the Outer Rim Territories' Seswenna sector. The Filar-Nitzan infiltrator Vacander maintained a bank account on Eczar by 2 ABY.

properties.name: Edan
properties.description: Edan was a moff on the Imperial Remnant's Moff Council in 19 ABY. He was a skeptic of a proposed truce between the Remnant and the New Republic during the Galactic Civil War.

properties.name: Edatha
properties.description: Edatha was a world represented in the New Republic by Krall Praget.

properties.name: Ediorung
properties.description: Ediorung was a planet in the Interior Regions of the Hapes Cluster. The planet was known for the dynamic holosculptures it produced; however, these were strictly judged by the Commission for the Preservation of the New Order Art Group. Porcellus, the chef for Jabba the Hutt, occasionally prepared Ediorung icefish for his master.

properties.name: Edonaaris
properties.description: Edonaaris was an obscure planet of swampy jungles in the Outer Rim. The Malka'an Eternal crashed on Edonaaris.

properties.name: Edusa
properties.description: Edusa was an industrialized planet located in the same "corridor" of space as Axxila, in the Ciutric Hegemony. During the Clone Wars, the planet was located within Separatist space. It was a target for the Kavil's Corsairs.

properties.name: Eedoq
properties.description: Eedoq was a planet in the Outer Rim's Tantra sector ruled by the Camblian Order.

properties.name: Eeyyon
properties.description: Eeyyon was a planet saved by the Jedi prior to the Clone Wars. It was inhabited by a species of tall, pale-skinned humanoids.

properties.name: Ehjenla
properties.description: Ehjenla was the small homeworld of the Tuhgri species. It was located within the Kathol Outback, which was part of the Kathol sector. Homeworld of the Tuhgri species, the planet began emerging from an ice age during the last centuries of the Galactic Republic. The polar ice caps were still large following as of 8 ABY, the oceans were large and deep, and the fertile plains were rutted with fjords.

properties.name: Eiattu
properties.description: Eiattu was an astronomical object located in the galaxy's Mid Rim.

properties.name: Eibon
properties.description: Eibon was a planet located within the Tion Cluster of the Outer Rim Territories. One of the original member-worlds of the Kingdom of Cron, it was absorbed into Xim's empire. A planet known for its proud and independent people, Xer VIII and his son Xim respected Eibon, and one of Xim's flagships was named the Eibon Scimitar. After Xim's empire collapsed, Eibon would continue to thrive as a world, and when it joined the Cronese Mandate after the rise of the Galactic Empire, it was considered one of the most powerful worlds of the Cron region.

properties.name: Eilnia
properties.description: Eilnia was a planet in the Inner Rim. It was the homeworld of the Eilnian sweet fly.

properties.name: Eirrauus
properties.description: Eirrauus was a desert world populated by the Eirraucs. It was located in the Quence sector of the galaxy.

properties.name: Eislo
properties.description: Eislomi III  was a New Republic planet in the Eislomi system in Eislomi sector with a HoloNet relay station. On the planet, ratter thists were used to guard livestock in mountain valleys. Many products were exported from Eislomi III, including cordioline trehansicol, one of the only insecticides that could exterminate metalmites.

properties.name: Ejolus
properties.description: Ejolus was a planet located in the Inner Rim.

properties.name: Ekibo
properties.description: Ekibo was a Trianii colony planet in Trianii Space, famous for its farms and herdbeasts. Trianii Rangers Atuarre and Keeheen were responsible for overthrowing a herdbeast-rustling ring there.

properties.name: Elamposnia
properties.description: Elamposnia was a planet in the Gordian Reach of the Outer Rim.

properties.name: Elatha
properties.description: The Elatha system was located in the Outer Rim Territories' Stensen sector. It shared its name with the group known as the Elathan.

properties.name: Elbara
properties.description: Elbara Nine was a Mid Rim world on the Cerean Reach of the galaxy. It was an icy world and home to the Rebel GlitterFall base. The planet was near a little-used Imperial Navy staging area.

properties.name: Elcorth
properties.description: Elcorth was one of two mining colonies founded by the Morath on the edge of the Koornacht Cluster closest to Coruscant. The other was Kojash. Both were overtaken by the Yevetha during the Great Purge.

properties.name: Elegasso
properties.description: Elegasso was a minor planet under the control of the Galactic Empire. In 0 ABY, a local election was blatantly rigged, drawing the attention of the Hand of Judgment stormtrooper team and Imperial agent Mara Jade.

properties.name: Elerion
properties.description: Elerion was a notorious gambling planet located in the Outer Rim Territories near Phoebus.

properties.name: Elgit
properties.description: Elgit was a minor trade world that was located within the Elgit system of the galaxy's Hutt Space region and lay on the hyperlane called The Dead Road, which connected it to the planets of Zisia and Usk. The Elgit–M'Hanna Corridor linked Elgit to the world of Sakifwanna, and the trade planet was also joined by a hyperspace route to the Gos Hutta system.

properties.name: Eliad
properties.description: Eliad was a planet of wealthy noble exiles in the Minos Cluster.

properties.name: Elin Roe
properties.description: Elin Roe was a Colonies planet in the Elin Roe system, which was patrolled by Hallyn Phlynne during the Galactic Civil War. It had at least five moons, the fifth of which was bombarded with radioactive dust when the Krish mechanic Maniac tinkered with the drive systems of the Yagaran Four's freighter; when it attempted to enter hyperspace, the drive exploded, destroying the ship.

properties.name: Elkkasinn
properties.description: Elkkasinn was a world located in the Phelleem sector of the Outer Rim Territories. Many gunrunners of the Sendavé Shared Interest Collective were from Elkkasinn and Sunin.

properties.name: Elliirad
properties.description: Elliirad may refer to one of the following:

properties.name: Elom
properties.description: Eloms were short, stocky, bipedal sentients, with a thick pelt of oily, dark fur, native to the frigid and mineral-rich desert planet of Elom, located in the Borderland Regions. The primitive species had extremely tough skin, several layers of fat, and their hands and feet were coated by thick calluses.

properties.name: Elriss
properties.description: Elriss was a Mid Rim planet.

properties.name: Elrood
properties.description: Elrood was a planet located between the Halbara and Kidron systems on the Elrood-Derilyn Run. It functioned as capital of the Elrood sector and as its major trade and manufacturing hub. Elrood headquartered Radell Mining Corporation, the largest company in the sector. It had two moons, Sharene and Lodos. The planet was named after Senator Elrood, who secured funding for its colonization.

properties.name: Elshandruu Pica
properties.poi: 27th Hour Social Club, Margath's on Elshandruu Pica,
properties.description: Elshandruu Pica was a planet in the Elshandruu system of the Quence sector, in the Outer Rim.

properties.name: Embaril
properties.description: Embaril was a beautiful planet located within the Allied Tion sector, notable for its rolling green hills and crystalline lakes that attracted nobles from across the Tion Cluster.

properties.name: Emberlene
properties.description: Emberlene was a planet located in the Authala sector of the Expansion Region.

properties.name: Emmer
properties.description: Emmer, originally known as Umhul while it was part of Xim's empire, was a high-gravity planet in the Nilgaard sector that was covered in glowing grass and urban sprawls. The planet joined the Galactic Republic prior to 45 BBY. Emmerian walker vehicles inspired those built by Kuat Drive Yards, such as the AT-AT.

properties.name: Empartheca
properties.description: Empartheca was a planet in the Empartheca system, in the Hook Nebula of the Outer Rim Territories.

properties.name: Empress Teta
properties.poi: Core District, Great Library of Cinnagar, Hyperspace Navigator's Guildhouse, Iron Citadel, Mining Guild regional headquarters, Monument to Lost Navigators,
properties.description: Empress Teta was an ecumenopolis world located in the Empress Teta system, a star system in the Koros sector of the galaxy's Deep Core. Initially known as Koros or Koros Major, the planet's name was changed following Empress Teta's unification of the system in 5000 BBY. The extent to which the capital Cinnagar covered the world also caused many to refer to the world itself as Cinnagar, even in official documentation—a source of confusion at times. A major supplier of refined carbonite, the planet was a major hub of operations for the Mining Guild. It was located on both the Koros Trunk Line and the Carbonite Run, and for a short time on the Daragon Trail. Empress Teta was the main hub of galactic civilization in the Deep Core and was also one of the few highly urbanized planets in the region to rival Coruscant itself in fashion and amenities.

properties.name: Enaleh
properties.description: Enaleh was a planet located in the Colonies. At some point between 12,000 BBY and 11,000 BBY, Enaleh became a Galactic Republic Ordnance/Regional Depot outpost and was known by then as Ord Enaleh. The planet had a moist atmosphere, and its surface features included grasslands, freshwater seas, and lakes.

properties.name: Enarc
properties.description: Enarc was an astronomical object located in the galaxy's Mid Rim and Trailing Sectors. Situated near the planet Naboo, Enarc was located in square O-17 of the Standard Galactic Grid.

properties.name: Endex
properties.description: Endex was a world of rocky canyons. It was the Entymal homeworld. During the time of the Old Republic, the Entymals were renowned as excellent pilots across the galaxy. For centuries, many pilots were trained in the canyons which left a lot of wreckage behind.

properties.name: Endor
properties.description: Endor  was a small forested moon orbiting the gas giant planet of Endor and was the farthest moon away from it. An enchanted world, Endor was notable for being the native home of the Ewoks, and being the location of the Battle of Endor, which would result in the downfall of the Empire and the first death of the Emperor Palpatine. Due to its proximity to the Unknown Regions, Endor was a relatively quiet planetoid both prior to and after the battle.

properties.name: Endor Gate
properties.description: The Endor Gate was a black hole located several light-years off the hyperspace route between Endor and Sanyassa IV in the Moddell sector of the galaxy. It was not especially large, and had been well-scouted over the centuries of the Inner Zuma's existence. Many legends surrounded the Endor Gate: some spacers told stories of ships that had been found drifting in space whose captains swore they were on the other side of the galaxy before their ships went dead. It was through this gate that C-3PO, R2-D2, and Prince Plooz returned to their time period after accidentally traveling to the far future. It was also rumored to have been the wormhole responsible for depositing the glove of Darth Vader at the Mon Calamari system.

properties.name: Endoraan
properties.description: Endoraan was a planet that was an endpoint of the Relgim Run, opposite Mantooine.

properties.name: Endovan
properties.description: Endovan was a planet in the Sarka sector of the Mid Rim.

properties.name: Endregaad
properties.description: Endregaad, a world near the Indrexu Spiral, was the oasis mother homeworld.

properties.name: Endymion
properties.description: Endymion was a planet in the Pleiades region of the Kalamith sector in the Outer Rim Territories. Around 3660 BBY it was involved in the Great Galactic War. According to Darth Malgus in his personal journal, Sith troops were moved from Endymion, but its exact role in the war is unknown, as this part of the journal was cut out.

properties.name: Enet
properties.description: The Enet system was an isolated star system in the Brak sector, located in the Expansion Region. During the Galactic Civil War, the Brak Sector Force of the Alliance began building a secret base in the system to use as a rendezvous point in case any of their other facilities in the sector were discovered.
