properties.name: Enferm
properties.description: Enferm was a planet notable for its medical research facilities.

properties.name: Engebo
properties.description: Engebo was the primary star of the Engebo system.

properties.name: Engira
properties.description: Engira was an Outer Rim Territories gas giant located in the Jospro sector. The site of a pirate base that was destroyed more than thirty years before the Battle of Yavin, by the time of the Galactic Civil War the planet had become a supply convoy colony of the Galactic Empire. An ambush near Engira once led to the loss of three Imperial freighters transporting food and ammunition.

properties.name: Enisca
properties.description: Enisca was a planet that, along with Sern Prime and Kashyyyk, were considered prime candidates for anti-Imperial rebellion by Mon Mothma.

properties.name: Ennth
properties.description: Ennth was a planet that, every eight years, was wreaked by enormous groundquakes, tidal waves, and volcanic eruptions. Ennth's moon was pulled in an orbit so that every eight years it would get sucked so close to the planet that the two atmospheres would connect, causing huge natural disasters that lasted for several months. The colonists of Ennth usually chose to stay in crowded orbital refugee stations until the surface settled once more. Volunteers from around the galaxy would often help with the evacuation of people, supplies and belongings to the stations; Peckhum was known to have helped for at least one evacuation with his ship, the Lightning Rod.

properties.name: Ensolica
properties.description: Ensolica was a planet covered almost entirely by frozen tundra on its continents and thick ice sheets on its oceans. Along its equator lay a tiny "tropical" strip of coniferous forest and frigid sea.

properties.name: Entooine
properties.description: Entooine was a tidal locked moon of a gas giant in the Entoo system of the Outer Rim Territories. It was the only inhabited celestial body in the system and had an extreme electromagnetic field. The moon was a frigid world with ice crevasses, polar ice caves, lichen, shrubs, indigenous quohr, and two sapient species: the tribal Askhew and the blue banthas.

properties.name: Entralla
properties.description: Entralla was a planet in the Velcar Free Commerce Zone. Prior to the rise of the New Order, the planet had a diversity of religions and a rich history blended with myths. The most notable local holiday was the Lunar Night, when the Parade of Ghosts was held. After the Battle of Endor, the populace tried to regain independence. However, the world was subjugated by the Pentastar Alignment. The New Republic deemed the Alignment too powerful to tackle at the time, so an independent resistance group called the Red Moons arose under the leadership of Entrallan native Andrephan Stormcaller, a disillusioned NRI officer whom left the New Republic because it refused to help his homeworld. The planet was the headquarters of the Guild of Interstellar Merchants.

properties.name: Entrus
properties.description: Entrus was a planet in Trax sector. It was a temperate world scattered with many islands. Gambling resorts were built upon the hundreds of islands on the planet, resulting in underwater cities and repulsorlift platforms filling the oceans and skies. The cities were densely populated with entertainment complexes sometimes towering hundreds of meters. It contained the Alliance to Restore the Republic's Trax Sector Command for the Trax sector. The base only had a small number of personnel of less than 25 strategists and planners.

properties.name: Entuur
properties.description: Entuur was a planet inhabited by the Human race known as the Entuurans.

properties.name: Eol Sha
properties.description: Eol Sha was a volcanic planet in the Corva sector of the Outer Rim, near the Cauldron Nebula. Despite a rather temperate climate, the majority of the planet's surface was geologically unstable, with geysers and volcanoes dotting the surface and destructive natural phenomena, such as avalanches and groundquakes, occurring regularly.

properties.name: Eos
properties.description: Eos was a mineral-rich volcanic planet that hosted a large droid foundry belonging to the Trade Federation.

properties.name: Epica
properties.description: Epica was a naturally beautiful world with forested hills, mountain valleys, and cold water seas. During the Yuuzhan Vong War, the Hydians Auction House was relocated to Epica. At the time it was believed that Epica was too remote to attract the attention of the Yuuzhan Vong. At the wars end, many of the beings that had relocated the Hydians decided to remain on world, building rich palaces and mansion on the world. In time the planet's primary city had been transformed into an area of sophistication for the wealthy and privileged. The new level of decadence forced the native populace of Humans, Bothans, Duros, and Bimms to labor in order to satisfy the needs of the wealthy who co-opted their home.

properties.name: Epsi Nadir
properties.description: Epsi Nadir was a planet owned by The Most Honourable Guild of Armourers. Due to the fact that the guild owned the planet, they were able to perform their  business without Imperial interference.

properties.name: Equanus
properties.description: Equanus was a planet in the Outer Rim Territories. It was one of five planets in the Nharl system.

properties.name: Er'Kit
properties.description: Er'Kit was a planet in the Outer Rim Territories and the homeworld of the Er'Kit species.

properties.name: Er'stacia
properties.description: Er'stacia was a planet in Wild Space and the homeworld of the Er'stacians.

properties.name: Erai
properties.description: Erai may refer to one of the following:

properties.name: Eredenn
properties.poi: Eredenn Station, Facet Test Site, Shard Test Site,
properties.description: Eredenn Prime, also known as Eredenn IV, was a frozen planet in the Tion Hegemony.

properties.name: Eredin
properties.description: Eredin was an ice-bound planet that was located in the Astal sector of the Outer Rim Territories.

properties.name: Ereesus
properties.description: Ereesus was a planet in the Kanz sector of the Outer Rim Territories and the homeworld of the Ereesi species.

properties.name: Eriadu
properties.poi: Ja-Phelar Bay, , Eriadu Manufacturing ShipyardsEriadu SpaceportEriadu Planetary Security LaunchportJa KnollOrrineswa River, Phelar FloePhelar Port, Seswenna HallSeswenna Sector BankTarkin Memorial Conference Center
properties.description: Eriadu was the primary world in the Seswenna sector, and one of the Outer Rim's most active trade centers. It sat on the intersection of several hyperspace routes, including the Rimma Trade Route, the Hydian Way, the Lipsec Run, and the Yankirk Route.

properties.name: Eridicon
properties.description: Eridicon IV was a planet which an old "Squid-face" retired to after owning the Limping Lady.

properties.name: Erigorm
properties.description:
Erigorm was a planet in the Core Worlds. After the Great Galactic War, Erigorm was one of the planets that threatened secession from the Republic, as part of the Rift Alliance. By that time, it had recorded and administrated the Republic's finances for centuries.
The planet's representative in the Alliance council was Augin Blaesus, secretly a Child of the Emperor. Prior to the Clone Wars, the planet was represented in the Galactic Senate by Senator Gopple.

properties.name: Erilnar
properties.description: Erilnar was a planet located in the Outer Rim Territories's Centrality. Serving as the capital of the Centrality, Erilnar had three hundred thousand lakes on its surface, which forced the planet's transportation to go underwater. At some point by the reign of the Galactic Empire, a terrorist attack on Erilnar destroyed most of the world's monorail network and resulted in a million casualties. Blaming the Empire for its non-reaction to the attack, the Erilnar native Kulbart Zamoon joined the Rebel Alliance.

properties.name: Eriscot
properties.description: Eriscot was an aquatic planet that was the original homeworld of the Nejma. The Nejma were evacuated to Iskalon in 5000 BBY.

properties.name: Ermi
properties.description: The Ermi were a sentient species. According to the play Evocar, written by the Hutt playwright Direus'Pei around 671 BBY, the Ermi were driven to extinction by the Tionese warlord Xim. When Xim was captured and placed on trial by the Hutts, he justified the extinction of the Ermi on the basis that they were slavers. Xim's conquests occurred approximately between 25,130 and 25,100 BBY.

properties.name: Ertegas
properties.description: Ertegas was an agriworld located within the Anoat sector. It was believed that droids truly controlled the Human colony of the planet.

properties.name: Ertrax
properties.description: Ertrax was a Wild Space planet located within the star system of the same name. Ertrax was home to the Ertraxi, a peaceful species of multiple-eyed humanoids who were eager to make contact with other species and cultures.

properties.name: Erysthes
properties.description: Erysthes, located in the Corporate Sector in the Tingel Arm of the galaxy, was the planet to which the chak-root was native.

properties.name: Esaga
properties.description: Esaga was an astronomical object located in the Esaga system, a part of the Esaga sector in the Slice portion of the Mid Rim. After its restoration around 15,000 BBY, the navy of the Galactic Republic moved aggressively beyond the Republic's frontier to defend its colonies and commerce. Although few records survived from that time, millennia later naval songs continued to mention deeds of bravery committed by members of the Republic Navy during conflicts at Esaga, Caulbon, and the Sundered Veil. During the Pius Dea Era, a period of time lasting from approximately 12,000 BBY to 11,000 BBY, Esaga was situated outside of the Republic's borders.

properties.name: Escabar
properties.description: Escabar was a planet located in the Escabar system, a part of the freestanding subsectors of the Expansion Region. It featured the regions Khrassh and Serhan, the latter of which had deserts in its northeastern areas. Despite the fierce sandstorms of those territories, the small, quadripedal scavenger creatures known as the borcatu evolved there, adapting for digging burrows and cracking open shells.

properties.name: Escarte
properties.description: Escarte was an Outer Rim Territories asteroid in the Escarte system which orbited between massive, multi-mooned gas giants on the Rimward side of the Perlemian Trade Route. Oblate when mining operations had commenced in 39 BBY, Escarte was, by 19 BBY, a facility used by the Commerce Guild. Here the Guild mined neighboring asteroids using tractor beams, which captured small asteroids and drew them directly into the facility. They controlled the asteroid with the Escarte Judiciary and the Escarte Guard.

properties.name: Esfandia
properties.description: Esfandia was a free-floating proto-world in Wild Space. At one time, it had orbited a star, but it eventually broke away. Even without a sun, the planet had enough radioactivity in its core to support a liquid atmosphere composed mainly of methane and hydrogen.

properties.name: Eshan
properties.description: Eshan was a planet in the Inner Rim Territories and the homeworld of the Near-Human species known as Echani.

properties.name: Esooma
properties.description: Esooma was a planet located in the Esooma system, within the Sprizen sector of the galaxy's Outer Rim Territories. It was the homeworld of the sentient Esoomian species, who were considered to be among the best hired muscle in the galaxy. Esooma was quarantined by the Galactic Empire, preventing the Esoomians from leaving their homeworld, up until around the year 7 ABY, after which they were free to depart and find work. An Esoomian known as Tantor first left Esooma when he was hired as an enforcer for a pirate ship.

properties.name: Esseles
properties.poi: Esseles starport, Tralee, Togatto Speedway, Esprix Estate, Grande Hyet, Amander Public School, Qua family's villa,
properties.description: Esseles was a planet located along the Perlemian Trade Route in Darpa sector of the Ringali Shell. It was the third in position in the Essesia system and had one moon.

properties.name: Essien
properties.description: Essien was a world in the Halthor sector of the Outer Rim Territories.

properties.name: Ession
properties.description: Ession was a planet in the Corporate Sector, located at the nexus of the Shaltin Tunnels and Lucaya Cross hyperlanes. It was settled around 4000 BBY. An industrial manufacturing center, it was the headquarters of Pakkerd Light Transport, formerly a division of Sienar Fleet Systems.

properties.name: Essowyn
properties.description: Essowyn was the only planet in the Saurton system. The planet was located in the Trax sector, situated between the Kanawyn and Greawyn asteroid belts.

properties.name: Estaph
properties.description: The Estaph system was a star system located in the Tapani sector's Mecetti Province, on the Procopian Shipping Lane; it was also an endpoint of the Calipsa Run.

properties.name: Estaria
properties.description: Estaria was an Outer Rim Territories planet situated in the Indrexu sector on the Perlemian Trade Route. It was a spaceport world and during the Galactic Civil War housed Estaria Central Starport, which regulated starship travel in the entire Estaria system.

properties.name: Esyvam
properties.description: The Esyvam system, possibly also known as the Esyram system, was a star system located within the Atravis sector of the Outer Rim Territories.

properties.name: Etorasp
properties.description: Etorasp was a planet located in the Hakartha sector of the Expansion Region.

properties.name: Etti
properties.description: The Etti were a sentient species of near-Humans who were originally native to the Galactic Core.

properties.name: Euceron
properties.description: Euceron was a planet located in the Eucer sector of the Mid Rim. It was located near Anzat.

properties.name: Evas
properties.description: Evas was one of the four moons of Onderon.

properties.name: Excarga
properties.description: Excarga was a mining world in the Outer Rim Territories. The planet had ties to the Mining Guild.

properties.name: Exocron
properties.description: Exocron was a planet in the Kathol Outback, hidden in a protostar gas cloud near the Kathol Rift. It was settled by colonists who were opposed to the "plastic societies" of the Galactic Republic, and who were searching for a legendary planet called Exo. The colony grew in isolation from the rest of the galaxy, controlled by a technocracy known as the Devisors who forbade space travel. Their rule lasted until 8 ABY when the New Republic corvette FarStar assisted the local population in freeing themselves from the oppressive regime. At some point, the smuggler Jorj Car'das retired on the planet.

properties.name: Exodeen
properties.description: Exodeen was a planet located in the Colonies along the Hydian Way.

properties.name: Exodo
properties.description: Exodo was the primary star of the Exodo system.

properties.name: Extorin Minor
properties.description: Extorin Minor may refer to one of the following:

properties.name: Extrictarium Nebula
properties.description: The Extrictarium Nebula was a nebula located within the Ash Worlds sector in the Outer Rim region of the galaxy, between the Centrality and the Tion Cluster, but did not appear on any starcharts. It contained the legendary planet Iego. Ailyn Vel killed Alpha-Ø2 in the nebula.

properties.name: Eyar
properties.description: The Eyar system was a star system located in the Inner Rim. It contained the planet of Eyar.

properties.name: F'tral
properties.description: F'tral was an Outer Rim Territories waterworld located in the Calaron sector. The planet's surface was almost completely covered by freshwater oceans, with dry land being limited to chains of volcanic islands that were home to mostly predatory or parasitic plants. Cephalopods, including the sentient Iyra, were the dominant form of life in F'tral's oceans.

properties.name: Faarlsun
properties.description: Faarlsun was a yellow-white star located in the Faarlsun system, a part of Wild Space's Parthovian Cluster. The two closest orbital positions around Faarlsun were occupied by the searing-hot rock planet Jun and the asteroid belt known as the Zossi Belt. Further out, the star was circled by two terrestrial worlds, the poisonous Weken with its two moons and the habitable Pochi with three natural satellites of its own. The outer orbital positions in the Faarlsun system were occupied by the gas giant–type planets Koss and Calipp, which had eight and twelve moons, respectively.

properties.name: Fabrin
properties.description: Fabrin was a planet located in the Expansion Region.

properties.name: Fadden
properties.description: Fadden was a world located in the Fadden system, a part of the Slice portion of the Inner Rim. It was settled by colonists of the Duros species, which was native to the Core Worlds planet Duro.

properties.name: Fait d'Fait
properties.description: Fait d'Fait was a Mid Rim celestial body located in the Venaarian sector. Around 3643 BBY, criminal syndicates recruited an off-worlder to help them manipulate a governor of Fait d'Fait, who pursued anti-organized crime policies. Later, during the Galactic Civil War, the racer Siro Simito visited Fait d'Fait on a detour during the Dahvil-Fodro Hyperspace Promenade starship race. Simito, an undercover Rebel Alliance agent, had been tasked with delivering a data module from the astronomical object Dahvil to a contact on Fait d'Fait—a handoff which Simito carried out smoothly despite being briefly accosted by a Barabel mugger in Fait d'Fait's city.

properties.name: Fakir
properties.description: Fakir was the sector capital of Fakir sector in the Bakchou arm.

properties.name: Falang Minor
properties.description: Falang Minor, also known as just Falang, was a Galactic Republic fortress world located in the Outer Rim Territories' Thanium Worlds. A cold and rainy world, it was among the speculated origin points of the Jedi Order. Following the defeat of the Honorable Union of Desevro & Tion in the Tionese War, a series of fortress worlds, including Falang Minor, were established from which Jedi Knights would watch over the Tion Cluster. After the end of the war, a Republic soldier served the Jedi watchmen for a period of twelve years, monitoring starships, intelligence, and transmissions originating in the Tion Cluster. While serving on Falang Minor, the soldier imprinted an audio-visual autobiographical account on a Baragwin sense lattice.

properties.name: Faldos
properties.description: Faldos was a dirty backwater Outer Rim Territories world used by smugglers to sell stolen weapons, armor, and technology. It sat on the very edge of the galaxy, making it far more removed than most of the Outer Rim Territories.

properties.name: Falleen
properties.description: The Falleen were the indigenous reptilian sentient species of the planet Falleen.

properties.name: Fallowan
properties.description: Fallowan was an agricultural planet located within the Sujimis sector of the Outer Rim Territories.

properties.name: Fangol
properties.description: Fangol was a small frozen planet in the Mortex sector, and was the site of a secret Rebel Alliance base. It had an icy crust.

properties.name: Fanha
properties.description: Fanha was a planet located in the Seitia sector of the Outer Rim.

properties.name: Far Pando
properties.description: Far Pando was a peaceful agrarian planet in the Far Pando system of Hutt Space. It was situated along the Pando Spur hyperlane, an offshoot of the larger Hollastin Run. The planet was under the control of the sentient Yahk-Tosh species.

properties.name: Fara's Belt
properties.description: Fara's Belt, in the Outer Rim Territories's Rolion sector, was the site of a communication station used by the Galactic Empire.

properties.name: Farana
properties.description: Farana was a Wild Space world that was home to the near-Human Ocsin species. Never governed by the Galactic Republic or the Galactic Empire, by 3705 BBY it was situated at the endpoint of the Morellian Trail hyperlane.

properties.name: Farbog
properties.description: Farbog was a planet in the Galactic Empire visited by Leia Organa Solo during the Galactic Civil War.

properties.name: Farboon
properties.description: Farboon was a planet that appeared green-blue from space. It was the site where Maarek Stele, a TIE/LN starfighter pilot, rescued Imperial Admiral Mordon's shuttle from a Rebel attack of X-wing and Y-wing fighters

properties.name: Farfalla
properties.description: Valenthyne Farfalla was a noted male half-Bothan Jedi Master and Jedi Lord who served the Jedi Order during the New Sith Wars. Farfalla had a reputation for being foppish and vain. He aided Lord Hoth and the Army of Light in the Ruusan campaign, in the final years of the New Sith Wars. In the last year of the battle, Farfalla left Ruusan to gather three hundred followers to aid in the struggle for the world.

properties.name: Farnica
properties.description: The Farnica system was located in the Interior Region, an area of the Hapes Cluster in the Slice portion of the Inner Rim. It was connected via hyperlanes to the Novi and Sivoria systems. The Farnica system was the origin point of the art form known as the Farnican chime-painting.

properties.name: Faro
properties.description: Faro was a planet in the Faro system within the Colonies region of the galaxy.

properties.name: Farrfin
properties.description: Farrfin was the capital of Farrfin sector and the Farghul homeworld. It joined the Galactic Republic in 3000 BBY. It was a haven for criminals. A shakedown by the Jedi left the Farghul distrustful of Jedi.

properties.name: Farsellah
properties.description: Farsellah was a terrestrial world located in the Farsellah system, a part of the Farstey sector in the Trans-Hydian portion of the Expansion Region.

properties.name: Farstey
properties.description: Farstey was an Expansion Region astronomical object situated in the Farstey sector. During the Galactic Civil War, while the Galactic Empire was carrying out an offensive in Farstey's vicinity, the Rebel Alliance Chief of Sector Command suggested during a meeting of the Alliance High Command that the Rebel starfighter base at Farstey could be stripped to form a fighter wing for a planned assault on an Imperial base over the planet Mantooine.

properties.name: Farstine
properties.description: Farstine was a planet within the Farstine system, situated in the Mid Rim's Ryndellian sector. The planet was located on two major hyperlanes: the Five Veils Route, which connected the Mid Rim to the Svivreni and Skine sectors in the Outer Rim Territories, and the Triellus Trade Route, which spanned a large section of the Outer Rim within the Slice. Farstine possessed a methane atmosphere, requiring oxygen-breathing species to use breath masks for survival on the surface. Relatively untouched by galactic events, a battle was fought at Farstine in 19 BBY between Separatist holdout forces commanded by Trade Federation Customs Vizier Marath Vooro, and an Imperial fleet headed by the Imperial officer Octavian Grant. The planet was known to be one of the spice trade's major transshipment hubs, and was under Imperial occupation at some point during the Galactic Civil War.

properties.name: Farstone
properties.description: Farstone was a world located in the Farstone system of the Juvex sector, a part of the Senex-Juvex region in the Western Reaches portion of the Mid Rim. A hyperlane connected Farstone to the Umthyg system.

properties.name: Farwell Station
properties.description: Farwell Station was a space station. It was on there that Nescan Tal'yo killed a Rebel courier and gained a holocube detailing the Rebellion's main bases.

properties.name: Faz
properties.description: Faz was one of the original 13 planets of the Duskhan League, and was one of the many colony worlds held by the Yevetha. It was located in the Koornacht Cluster, in the Farlax sector.

properties.name: Feather Nebula
properties.description: The Feather Nebula was a nebula in the Outer Rim Territories that was the site of a battle during the Galactic Empire's retaking of the region in 17 BBY. It would later be documented in the holodrama The Charge at Feather Nebula.

properties.name: Febrini
properties.description: The Febrini system was located in the Gateworlds, an area of the Hapes Cluster in the Slice portion of the Inner Rim. It was connected by the hyperlane known as the Rynmar Trail to the Sargon system of the Gateworlds and to the Rynmar system in the Hapan Rim Worlds, and another hyperspace route linked it to the Gateworlds' Zadaria system. The Febrini system was home to the creatures known as Febrini sand-prestors.

properties.name: Fedalle
properties.description: Fedalle was a wealthy and industrious world of the Core. The New Republic Senator Hrekin Thorm was a native of Fedalle.

properties.name: Feddasyr
properties.description: Feddasyr was a planet located in the Elus sector of the Inner Rim. Rebel Agent Sarin operated undercover for 5 years on Feddasyr without her cover ever being blown.

properties.name: Fedje
properties.description: Fedje was a planet in the Outer Rim's Atrivis sector. It was home to many exotic creatures, including the rare folded ear boosqueak. The planet was visited by members of the Alliance to Restore the Republic during the Galactic Civil War. Imperial Intelligence operatives later posed as natives of the planet while carrying out sabotage on the Bothan homeworld Bothawui.

properties.name: Feena
properties.description: Feena was a world located in the Feena system. It was situated in the Back Reach area of the Gordian Reach sector, within the Trans-Hydian portion of the Outer Rim Territories. Feena lay between the B'trilla and Kalishik systems on the hyperlane known as the Ardan Cross—a portion of which already linked it to the Ethain and Vynx systems by 25,126 BBY—while the Feena Run hyperspace route connected the world to the Barison system.

properties.name: Feenicks
properties.description: The Feenicks system was a star system located in the Outer Rim Territories which contained the planet Feenicks VI.

properties.name: Feenix
properties.description: Feenix was a planet in the Mid Rim's D'Aelgoth sector. It was a member of the Galactic Republic and later the Galactic Empire.

properties.name: Fef
properties.description: Fef was a moderately large planet orbiting an orange-yellow star in the Fef system. It was one of the Galactic Alliance planets threatened by a possible Killik coup.

properties.name: Fehern
properties.description: Fehern was a planet in the Trax sector of the Mid Rim It was the homeworld of the Eddelians. In the time of the Galactic Republic, Eddelian trading ships would be seen in adjoining systems. The Galactic Empire fought a war against the Eddell, eliminated most of the technology owned by them. Only a few thousand remained with most subjugated as slaves.

properties.name: Felacat
properties.description: Felacat was the Felacatian homeworld. It was located in the Outer Rim Territories, and its inhabitants were cat people who would transform into tiger-like creatures when in hyperspace for too long. During the Clone Wars, the Confederacy of Independent Systems laid siege to Felacat.

properties.name: Feldrona
properties.description: Feldrona was one of the colonies of Zabraks from Iridonia. After the establishment of Darth Krayt's Galactic Empire this colony, along with several others, rebelled against the new order. As the punishment for the insurrection two of the colonies were completely destroyed, forcing the remaining ones to surrender. Feldrona was transformed into a prison planet and placed under tight Imperial control.

properties.name: Feldwes
properties.description: Feldwes was a planet in a system of the same name, located in the Gordian Reach sector of the Outer Rim. It sat on the Ardan Cross hyperspace route. Feldwes was the foremost industrial world in the trailing part of the sector known as the Back Reach, and the employment possibilities of its factories led numerous T'sarki, B'trillans, and Humans to seek work permits there.

properties.name: Felin
properties.description: The Felin were a sentient species originating from the planet Heleth 4.

properties.name: Felucia
properties.poi: Nigkoe Detention Facility, Shu Mai's compoundVanishing PlaceAncient AbyssRancor Graveyard
properties.description: Felucia  or /fʌ'lusiə/) was a largely unsettled terrestrial jungle planet in the Felucia system of the Thanium Worlds in the Outer Rim Territories. Located near the junction of the Perlemian Trade Route and Shaltin Tunnels, the world featured a hot and humid atmosphere and significant water resources beneath a surface irradiated by ultraviolet light of the star Felix. Native plant, fungal, and animal life evolved to dominate the environment in a deep symbiotic relationship, causing significant Force energy to permeate the ecosystem. One native species of sentient Felucians developed Force-based tribal societies in subterranean caverns while another socialized in farming communities based around nysillin crop; both were largely undisturbed by the greater galaxy until 27,000 BBY, when the planet was discovered by Gossam Couriver hyperspace explorers/colonists from Castell. After aggressive resistance from the native wildlife indicated that the world would not support large-scale colonies, the new arrivals established hard-fought, scattered resort settlements on the surface. Early populations, comprising only wealthy Gossams and their poor servants, knew the planet as Galuch and retained colonial control over it until around 25,126 BBY, when Xim the Despot absorbed the world into his empire as it expanded throughout the Tion Cluster.

properties.name: Fendry
properties.description: Fendry was a gas giant planet.

properties.name: Fenel
properties.description: Fenel was a planet located within the region of the galaxy known as the Outer Rim Territories near the border of Mandalorian Space.

properties.name: Fengrine
properties.description: Fengrine was one of several prestigious agri-industrial worlds in the latter years of the Galactic Republic. It was found in the Senex sector in the Fengrine system in the Mid Rim.

properties.name: Fenion
properties.description: Fenion was an unaligned Outer Rim planet, near warlord Zsinj's territory. It was the only planet on the Night Caller agenda not visited by Wraith Squadron.

properties.name: Fenn
properties.description: Fenn was a common name.

properties.name: Fennesa
properties.description: Fennesa was a mountainous, rocky planet located in the Inner Rim. Its fauna included avian and feline predators as well as mountain nerfs, a subspecies of the ungulate nerfs introduced by colonists millennia before the Battle of Yavin.

properties.name: Fenves
properties.description: Fenves was a planet located in the Boeus sector of the Expansion Region. It was the homeworld of the Devaronian bounty hunter Tyrn Jiton.

properties.name: Fere
properties.description: Fere, sometimes known as Feree, was the Fere homeworld.

properties.name: Feris
properties.description: Feris was a planet in the Agarix sector of the Mid Rim.

properties.name: Ferrhast
properties.description: Ferrhast was the planet in the Core Worlds and location of the Imperial Institute of Higher Studies. Despite its distance from the Sith Worlds, ruins built by members of the Massassi species were found on the world during the Galactic War.

properties.name: Ferro
properties.description: Ferro was the Ferroan homeworld. In 89 BBY, the Ferroans colonized Zonama Sekot.

properties.name: Ferrous Aurora Nebula
properties.description: The Ferrous Aurora Nebula was an area of dense, reddish gas located in the Thesme sector. During the Galactic Civil War, travel through the nebula was considered to be dangerous, due to a presence of Ni'lyahin Smugglers.

properties.name: Ferton
properties.description: Ferton was an astronomical object located in the Ferton system of the Al'Nasrl sector, a part of the Slice portion of the Outer Rim Territories. At some point by the time of the Galactic Civil War, Harbon, a sergeant with a mercenary company, visited Ferton. The sergeant later told of the visit to another member of the company.

properties.name: Fest
properties.description: Fest was the primary planet in the Fest system. It was a densely populated world with few wilderness areas beyond several steep-ridged mountain ranges and deep valleys.

properties.name: Feswe Prime
properties.description: Feswe Prime was a star located within the Gordian Reach of the Outer Rim Territories.

properties.name: Fether
properties.description: Fether was a farming world located on the Solenbaran Merchant Route hyperlane, in the Outer Rim Territories' Corporate Sector. The planet hosted a population of sentient Ocsin and was the site of a small spaceport town.

properties.name: Fhost
properties.description: Fhost was a backwater planet located in the Wild Space of the galaxy at the edge of the Unknown Regions. Mostly covered by deserts, mountains and a single ocean, Fhost had its own beauty. The largest population center, Farpoint, was built on the remains of a spaceship that crashed there long before the Yuuzhan Vong War. Fhost was so far out from the main hyperlanes that all HoloNet shows that were available were at least four months old.

properties.name: Fibuli
properties.description: Fibuli was a planet in Trianii Space annexed by the Corporate Sector Authority.

properties.name: Filby
properties.description: Filby was a planet located in the Filby system of the Core Worlds. The planet was ruled over by royalty, one of the members being Baron Logan Erstar. The government ministers eventually conspired to rid the planet of the ruling monarchy, plating stories of scandal and corruption. The citizens of the got tired and angry, resulting in the overthrow of the monarchy.

properties.name: Filordis
properties.description: Filordis was a rocky planet located in the Larrin sector of the Inner Rim. It was a harsh world of fierce winds and frequent thunderstorms. The Filordi, the planet's native species of six-limbed sentients, often either left their homeworld for better living conditions elsewhere or attempted to terraform it. The territory of space surrounding Filordis was already explored by 20,000 BBY, and the Filordi became a partner species of the Metatheran Cartel by 33 BBY.

properties.name: Filve
properties.description: Filve was the hot, dry homeworld of the Filvians in the Dufilvian sector of the Mid Rim.

properties.name: Findris
properties.description: Findris was the sector capital of the Haldeen sector. It was the headquarters of the Justice Action Network, an anti-Imperial terrorist organization founded by the Alderaanian parents of Jan Ors.

properties.name: Firrerre
properties.poi: Firrerre Church, Firrerre Government Center, Firrerre School, Firrerre Spaceport, Grand Falls,
properties.description: Firrerre was a planet located in the Firrerre system in the Outer Rim Territories. Its sole sentient indigenous species were the near-extinct Firrerreo.

properties.name: Firro
properties.description: Firro was a planet in the Farrfin sector of the Galactic Core that was brutally subjugated by the Galactic Empire prior to the Battle of Yavin.

properties.name: Fislan
properties.description: Fislan was a planet. Cene Gilvent nearly killed a new Rebel recruit under the command of Bren Derlin on this planet. Derlin was then convinced of the threat Gilvent posed.

properties.name: Fitca Prime
properties.description: Fitca Prime was in the Fitca system. The planet was subjugated by then-Imperial Intelligence interrogator Mox Slosin. A number of Rebel agents tried to help the resistance on Fitca Prime, including Colonel Shanda Dok. Dok was captured and interrogated to death by Slosin, but never broke. Even after Dok's death, the Alliance provided a new support wave to Fitca Prime.

properties.name: Fiviune
properties.description: Fiviune was a world that was located in the Grumani sector, in the Outer Rim Territories. It was considered to be a dead world and its surface consisted of rocky plates and spiky crags. However, there were rumors that Fiviune had once been ruled by an ancient civilization, which had been destroyed.

properties.name: Flankers
properties.description: Flankers was a remote planet in Fakir sector in the Colonies. Its star went nova after the Battle of Yavin, destroying the entire system. Just prior to the explosion, the Imperial garrison on the planet was abandoned.

properties.name: Flashpoint
properties.description: Flashpoint can refer to:

properties.name: Flax
properties.description: Flax was a tectonically-active planet in the Ptera system of the Sumitra sector, in the Expansion Region. Most of the surface's land masses were desert due to the high coastal mountain ranges which prevented atmospheric transference of moisture from the seas.

properties.name: Florn
properties.description: Florn, known as Tinatorn while under the control of Xim's empire, was the Lamproid homeworld. This planet was mostly dense jungles with a few large oceans. The jungles of Florn were said to be so deadly that any sentient on Florn's surface without hyperaccelerated nerve implants, or a similar level of natural reflexes, risked certain and sudden death.

properties.name: Florrum
properties.description: Florrum was a rocky, backwater planet located six parsecs from Vanqor in the Outer Rim Territories.

properties.name: Fluwhaka
properties.description: Fluwhaka was a misty planet in the Outer Rim Territories noted for its rocky spires and crags.

properties.name: Fnessal
properties.description: Fnessal was a planet located in the Inner Rim's Fnessal system. It was the homeworld of the sentient Fnessian species, including the smuggler Kn'ik Th'ronik.

properties.name: Fodro
properties.description: Fodro was an Outer Rim Territories planet located in the Clacis sector, on the Braxant Run hyperlane. During the Galactic Civil War, it served as the endpoint of the Dahvil-Fodro Hyperspace Promenade, a popular interstellar racing route. The racer Siro Simito once participated in the race, during which he estimated that his rival, Seeg, would arrive at Fodro several hours earlier than himself. Fodro later fell within the borders of the Pentastar Alignment.

properties.name: Fodurant
properties.description: Fodurant was a New Republic prison world.

properties.name: Foerost
properties.description: Foerost was a Core planet on the Koros Trunk Line between Kuar and Kaikielius. It was orbited by the Foerost Shipyards, which was one of the Republic's largest and oldest shipyards. It even held the title of largest, and highest quality ships in the galaxy till Kuat later usurped the title in the Clone Wars. The shipyards' engineers removed raw materials from the planet and transported them to the shipyards in high orbit.

properties.name: Fokask
properties.description: Fokask was a planet within the Fokask system in Outer Rim Territories. It was home to one of Han Solo's old smuggling friends. This retired smuggler sent Solo a copy of the Fokask Banner, which had a rather slanderous article written about Chief of State Leia Organa Solo.

properties.name: Folende
properties.description: Folende was an agriworld located in the Folende system of the Tion Hegemony, within the Slice portion of the Outer Rim Territories. The Desevran Trace hyperlane linked Folende to the worlds of Desevro and Omman. For centuries, Folende's agricultural output was moderate, with Omman being considered its competitor.

properties.name: Foless
properties.description: Foless was a planet in the Colonies on the periphery of the Inner Rim, near Atzerri. It sat at the interscetion of the Shipwrights' Trace with the Corellian Trade Spine, known as the Foless Crossroads.

properties.name: Fondor
properties.poi: Fondor ShipyardsOrbital Shipyard 1321Fondor Academy of Engineering and DesignFondor's underground steam tubes
properties.description: Fondor was a planet in the Freeworlds Territory of the Tapani sector, famous throughout the galaxy for its extensive orbital shipyards, outclassed only by those at Corellia and Kuat. The Fondor Shipyards were associated with the Techno Union prior to the Clone Wars, and were vast enough to construct major flagships, such as the Executor, Darth Vader's Executor-class Star Dreadnought. The capital city was Fondor City, and later, it was Oridin City.

properties.name: Foran Tutha
properties.description: Foran Tutha was a barren planet in the Cronese Mandate on the edge of the Tion Cluster, located in the Outer Rim. Otherwise unremarkable and beneath notice, Foran Tutha shot to prominence after the discovery of the Foran Tutha star probe in the system sometime around 500 BBY. Despite centuries of debate, academics never came to an agreement on the nature of the probe's origins. In the millennia after the Cron Supernova, Foran Tutha hosted a cottage industry of treasure hunters that made the dangerous jumps in the direction of Ossus.

properties.name: Forlonis Minor
properties.description: Forlonis Minor was a planet located in the Forlonis Minor system of the Outer Rim Territories.

properties.name: Formos
properties.description: Formos, originally known as Xoloch, was a planet in the Kessel sector.

properties.name: Fornax
properties.poi: Fire Rings of Fornax, Fornax Station ,
properties.description: Fornax was a planet in the Glythe sector, well known throughout the galaxy as being home to the Fire Rings of Fornax.

properties.name: Fornow
properties.description: Fornow was a planet within the Fornow system in the Pacanth Reach of the Outer Rim Territories.

properties.name: Forntay
properties.description: Forntay was a planet in the Forntay system of the Core Worlds. It was once the homeworld of a sentient species. The natives defeated a group of oppressors in an uprising, according to an ancient text translated by Emiel Skoff. They later became extinct.

properties.name: Forsen
properties.description: Forsen was a lush agriworld in the Outer Rim. It was part of the Cassandran Worlds.

properties.name: Fostin
properties.description: Fostin was a black-colored world that was located in the Grumani sector, in the Outer Rim Territories. It was orbited by at least nine moons, including Fostin Nine.

properties.name: Foundry
properties.description: Foundry was a planet in the Colonies.

properties.name: Fradian
properties.description: Fradian was an ore terminal planet located in the Mid Rim. It was an industrial place that looked like it was designed by an architect who wanted to lose his job. Former Jedi Bardan Jusik thought the place was ugly.

properties.name: Freda
properties.description: Freda was a terrestrial world within the Freda system, located near Jante on the Mid Rim of the galaxy, and home to the Freda. During the Galactic Civil War, it was under the control of the Galactic Empire.

properties.name: Frego
properties.description: Frego was a wealthy planet controlled by a crime ring led by the Cobral family since 61 BBY. However, after Lena Cobral testified in front of the Galactic Senate in 41 BBY, exposing Cobral's patronage from Frego's Senator Crote, Frego started on the road to a new beginning. Nevertheless, the Cobral ring survived on Naboo.

properties.name: Freliq
properties.description: Freliq was an Outer Rim Territories planet located in the Calaron sector. It was home to the lepusa, a type of semi-sentient burrowing rodents who were able to manufacture crude tools. At some point, the farmers who had introduced off-world grain crops on Freliq first encountered the lepusa, whose herbivorous nature and burrowing habits soon made them little more than vermin in the farmers' eyes. The local farm manager Yasil Senerio once had an encounter with a lepusa which saved his daughter, and Senerio subsequently recounted the incident to the Imperial Investigation Committee on Lepusan Intelligence.

properties.name: Fremond
properties.description: The Fremond was a spacetug used by the Imperial Navy during the Imperial Era. In 14 BBY, the ship was part of the flotilla belonging to the Imperial facility known as Sentinel Base, which was commanded by Moff Wilhuff Tarkin and oversaw the construction of the Imperial battle station later known as the Death Star.

properties.name: Fresia
properties.description: Fresia was a Core World that served as headquarters for Incom Corporation.

properties.name: Frewwil
properties.description: Frewwil was a planet located in the Frewwil system, a part of the freestanding subsectors portion of the Expansion Region. An inhospitable world, Frewwil was explored by the Republic Survey Corps scout Barosa Warren. More than fifty years later, by 2 ABY, Frewwil was controlled by the Galactic Empire and was considered to be one of the most dangerous planets under the Empire's jurisdiction.

properties.name: Friijillis
properties.description: Friijillis was a planet in the Dail sector. The Hutt-sponsored news network, the Friij News Services—the clearing house of illegal information and data replication, controlled by the Tenloss Criminal Syndicate—was based on this planet.

properties.name: Frisal
properties.description: Frisal was a terrestrial planet located in the Frisal system, a part of the Atrisian Commonwealth in the Southern Core portion of the Core Worlds. It was the homeworld of loirbniggs, a species of eight-legged reptilian creatures.

properties.name: Frithia
properties.description: Frithia was a Mid Rim world colonized by the Zabrak. The herd animal krag and the carnivorous poth were native to this planet.

properties.name: Fromiria
properties.description: The Fromiria system was located in the Mortex sector, in the Trans-Hydian portion of the Outer Rim Territories. It was the origin point of the Fromirian roast queg dish.

properties.name: Frommon
properties.description: Frommon may refer to one of the following:

properties.name: Froswythe
properties.description: Froswythe was a planet in the Colonies. It was a major source of meat and animal-based textiles for the Colonies and Core Worlds. Roaming herds of livestock included banthas and nerfs. Ycaqt were used for transportation.

properties.name: Froz
properties.description: Froz was the homeworld of the Frozian species. It was on the Corellian Run. It was a pristine low-gravity planet.

properties.name: Fusai
properties.description: Fusai was a planet in the remote Fusai sector. It was the location of a branch of the Obroa-skai library, where a BRT supercomputer called Mistress Mnemos was installed about 200 BBY. Although Obroa-skai closed the branch, it was maintained locally. Fusai became a Rebel Alliance safe world, and it was here C-3PO reported to Mistress Mnemos the incidents that occurred to Luke Skywalker and Leia Organa on Vorzyd V, where they faced the minion of Blackhole. In addition to recording mission details, Mistress Mnemos helped the Alliance with tactics and long-term planning.

properties.name: Futility Station
properties.description: LMCTS-25452 was a mining survey site built by the Lant Mining Corporation during the Galactic Civil War.

properties.name: Fwatna
properties.description: Fwatna was a planet in the Subterrel sector near the site where Lando Calrissian found the abandoned freighter Spicy Lady. The ship belonged to his smuggling associate Jarril. This also led to the discovery of Dolph.

properties.name: Fwiis
properties.description: Fwiis was a colony world between Darepp and Motexx visited by the Star Morning after it departed Teyr. It was more than 150 light-years away from Atzerri.

properties.name: Fwillsving
properties.description: Fwillsving was a planet near Kessel and Honoghr. It was sometimes used by smugglers as a repair depot and a hideaway from Imperial patrol starships while smuggling spice on the Kessel Run.

properties.name: Fyodos
properties.description: Fyodos, also known as Tatrang IV, was an Outer Rim planet that was located within the Tatrang system. The world's surface was devastated during the Great Cleansing, a war of mass destruction that took place in 350 BBY. Prior to the cataclysm, the surface possessed two main seas, one of which was called the Othlorian Sea.

properties.name: G'haris
properties.description: G'haris was a planet from which the rare saass worm originated.

properties.name: G'rho
properties.description: G'rho was a small Chandrilan colony world in Wild Space on the Shiritoku Spur, under only nominal control of the Galactic Empire. Forests of juvica grew there. The colonists raised duncows and built Boku Settlement near a rich vein of crimson ore. Dev Sibwarra's family moved there shortly after his birth in 11 BBY when they fled Chandrila.

properties.name: G'wenee
properties.description: G'wenee was an Imperial tradeworld whose operations were overseen by Tarrant Snil, who proved to be an adversary to Grappa the Hutt. Snil was captured by bounty hunter Kenix Kil.

properties.name: Gabredor
properties.description: Gabredor III was a planet situated between Dantooine and Obtrexta sector, in Myto's Arrow. It had a Karazak Slavers Cooperative transfer center under the authority of slave master Greezim Trentacal. Trentacal kidnapped the children of the Ambassador of Cantras Gola to force the PowerOn Conglomerate to remain with the Alignment; in exchange, the Alignment agreed not to interfere with Karazak operations. The center was destroyed by the Red Moons, who rescued the children and other slaves.

properties.name: Gacerian
properties.description: Gacerian was the fourth planet in the Gacerian system. It was home to many Gacerite mines and was the homeworld of the Gacerite species. During Imperial reign, the Imperial governor of the planet, Ulbrek Gostech, was compassionate and kind, allowing the general populace to run the planet. Thus, the Gacerites were happy to abide by Imperial values and obey the laws dictated to them through their governor.

properties.name: Gadon
properties.description: Gadons were a race from Gadon 3.

properties.name: Gaftikar
properties.description: Gaftikar was a planet in the Outer Rim. Some time before the Galactic War between the Galactic Republic and the reconstituted Sith Empire, the mercenaries known as the Brig Stompers wiped out the planet's entire defense force during a coup.

properties.name: Gagrew Station
properties.description: The Gagrew Station was a space station located in area of Si'Klaata Cluster, Hutt Space.

properties.name: Gailea
properties.description: Gailea was a planet, home to the Marqua Spas.

properties.name: Gaios
properties.description: Gaios was a planet in Core Worlds in the grid coordinates K-9. Its philosophers' statement "a seed does not know the flower that produced it," was well known.

properties.name: Gal Milnor
properties.description: Gal Milnor was a planet that housed the main supply base used by the Alliance to Restore the Republic to store food, munitions and fuel. The base, along with a sizeable fleet of Alliance freighters, was destroyed by the Galactic Empire shortly before the Battle of Endor. This setback forced the Alliance to seek supplies from Dunari and the Hurrim.

properties.name: Gala
properties.description: Gala was a beautiful and wealthy world at one point ruled by the Beju-Tallah dynasty. It was fairly close to Phindar.

properties.name: Galaan
properties.poi: New Republic communications and intelligence base,
properties.description: Galaan was a gas giant in Corva sector's Galaanus system. Its local day lasted 132 standard hours; its year lasted 479 local days.

properties.name: Galand
properties.description: Galand was a Core world. It was homeworld of the near-Human Galandans, including the religious martyr H'kig. His teachings formed the basis of the H'kig philosophy. To escape persecution, the H'kig fled to distant Rishi.

properties.name: Galantos
properties.poi: Al'solib'minet'ri CityGal'fian'deprisi City, Gar'glum SeaNet'lseb Toli park,
properties.description: Galantos was the second planet in the Utos system on the Widek Bypass, near the Koornacht Cluster. Its first contact with the galactic community was quite ancient, as at least one Fian served as a Jedi 500 years before the First Great Schism.

properties.name: Galboron
properties.description: Galboron was a planet located in the Hertae sector of the Mid Rim.

properties.name: Galidraan
properties.description: Galidraan was a planet of snow-capped mountains and large pine forests, and was controlled by a planetary governor, who resided in an opulent castle in the midst of a forest.

properties.name: Gall
properties.description: Gall was a terrestrial moon of the gas giant Zhar in the Zhar system. It had a population of 57 million, mainly Humans.

properties.name: Gallinore
properties.description: Gallinore was a planet in the Interior Regions of the Hapes Cluster that was famed for its rainbow gems. Gallinore was also home to a number of high-tech labs, including a lockdown facility where imprisoned researchers, including a former Jedi, were allowed to continue some work.

properties.name: Gallion
properties.description: Gallion was a planet that was located in the Grumani sector. Gallion was one of the largest rocky planets in the sector and had low gravity, allowing lifeforms on the world to develop to titanic sizes.

properties.name: Galltine
properties.description: Galltine was a Human-inhabited planet in the Galltine system of the Thesme sector.

properties.name: Galshebbis Prime
properties.description: Gallshebbis Prime was a planet in the Nilgaard sector of the Outer Rim Territories.

properties.name: Galsol
properties.description: Galsol was a planet in the Belderone sector of the Outer Rim.

properties.name: Galtea
properties.description: Galtea was a planet in the system of the same name, located within the Outer Rim Territories' Kathol sector. The world was situated near the edge of known space, on the border of the Marcol Void, an empty region of space thirty light-years across. Neutral in galactic politics, Galtea was only of cursory interest to the Galactic Empire, which established a small outpost on the planet and allowed the population a degree of autonomy.

properties.name: Gama
properties.description: A planet in the Gama system was the Gama-Senn homeworld. Its populace was intimidated into swearing loyalty to the clone Emperor Palpatine after witnessing the Galaxy Gun in action.

properties.name: Gammalin
properties.description: Gammalin was a planet in the Vish sector of the Mid Rim. Its populace was wiped out by the Emperor's Plague. Unknowingly released by Fonterrat, he had brought it from an Imperial storehouse and booby-trapped by Nolaa Tarkona. After poisoning the populace of Gammalin, he was arrested and died of malnutrition, as his captors died of the plague.

properties.name: Gamor
properties.description: Gamor was an astronomical object located in the regions known as the Expansion Region and the Slice. It was also situated in the grid square O-14 of the Standard Galactic Grid. The super-hyperroute known as the Corellian Run connected Gamor to Allanteen VI and Bacrana, and another hyperspace route linked it to the world Aridus. Gamor shared its name with the trade route known as the Gamor Run.

properties.name: Gamorr
properties.poi: Jugsmuk Station, NudskutchJugsmukCarnuss GorgullField of Legend, Ruins of Carnuss Gorgull, Sith AcademyWatchtower Run,
properties.description: Gamorr was an agrarian planet located in the Opoku system of the Outer Rim Territories. It was the homeworld of a porcine sentient species, the Gamorreans. Its varied terrain ranged from frozen tundra to deep forests, and was considered quite pleasant by off-worlders. Nevertheless, tourism was highly discouraged to Gamorr because of the vicious lifestyle of ferocious, bloody warfare constantly being waged between rival Gamorrean clans. Prominent mushrooms were also found on Gamorr, as were native coolsap trees.

properties.name: Ganath
properties.description: Ganath was a planet hidden within the unchartered depths of a cloud of intensely radioactive interstellar gas near Nal Hutta.

properties.name: Gand
properties.description: The Gands, or Gand , were a sentient species of humanoids that xenobiologists believed to have evolved from an insect genus that inhabited the ammonia-gas planet of Gand. Several physical varieties of the species existed, differing from one another in the structure of the head and the texture and color of the exoskeleton, but the species was usually divided into two main subspecies: those with lungs and those without. Gands with such organs were adapted to their homeworld's atmosphere, but like Kel Dors, required specialized breathing gear if they wanted to leave Gand to manage potentially poisonous offworld gas mixtures. Gands without lungs, however, did not respire and were immune to poisonous gases; thus they could venture offworld without worry of suffocation. Both races possessed an exoskeleton and regenerative properties.

properties.name: Gandalla
properties.description: Gandalla was a planet located in the Boeus sector of the Expansion Region.

properties.name: Gandeal
properties.description: Gandeal was a Planet in the Core Worlds and partner planet to the world of Fondor, a fortress world situated on the Corellian Trade Spine.

properties.name: Gandle Ott
properties.description: Gandle Ott was the fourth planet of the Ott system, located in the Kathol sector of the Outer Rim Territories. The terminus of the Trition Trade Route, Gandle Ott was considered to be the farthest major settled world in the sector. Settled around 592 BBY, Gandle Ott quickly grew into a thriving colony and became the most prominent world in the Kathol sector until Kal'Shebbol was settled two hundred years later. When the Kathol sector was inducted into the Galactic Republic, Kal'Shebbol was designated as the sector capital since it was closer to Republic space. Gandle Ott slid out of prominence, although it was still regarded as a mature civilization despite its relative age. The inhabitants of Gandle Ott were fiercely independent, and the planet was self-sufficient but credit-poor, leading to the world's marginalization in sector politics.

properties.name: Gandolo
properties.description: Gandolo IV was a barren, rocky moon in the Gandolo system of the Lahara sector, in the Outer Rim Territories. Shortly before 1 BBY, a group of several dozen fugitive Wookiee slaves, including the famous Chewbacca, attempted to establish a safe colony on the moon but was discovered by the Trandoshan bounty hunter Bossk. Paid in advance by the Imperial sector governor, Bossk and a team of hunters landed on Gandolo IV to capture the renegade Wookiees. The hunt proved particularly opportunistic for Bossk, who finally got a chance to capture Chewbacca after the Wookiee had continuously eluded him for some time. Before the Trandoshan could secure his quarry, however, Chewbacca's smuggling partner, Han Solo, returned to Gandolo IV from business elsewhere to find the Wookiees detained. Careful not to harm Chewbacca and the other Wookiees, Solo strafed the camp in the Millennium Falcon and proceeded to land his ship directly on top of Bossk's own ship, crushing it. The Wookiees overpowered Bossk's group in the mayhem.

properties.name: Gania
properties.description: The Gania system was a star system located in the Tapani sector's Melantha Province, near the Shella system.

properties.name: Ganlihk
properties.description: Ganlihk was a planet in the Dantus sector of the Outer Rim.

properties.name: Gannaria
properties.description: Gannaria was a terrestrial planet located in the Trilon sector, a part of the Outer Rim Territories. Situated in grid square H-15 of the Standard Galactic Grid, it was linked by hyperspace routes to the Batuu and Zaddja systems and shared its name with the route known as the Gannarian Run.

properties.name: Ganthel
properties.description: Ganthel was a planet located in the system of the same name in the Core Worlds' Bormea sector. It was the homeworld of Grandon Holleck, who served as Governor of the planet Chandrila before he resigned and was replaced by Gerald Weizel. Holleck cited poor health and a desire to return to Ganthel as reasons for his resignation.

properties.name: Gantho
properties.description: Gantho was a planet located in the Gantho system. The planet was represented in the New Republic Senate by Senator Arastide. In 13 ABY the New Republic was in the middle of an investigation into Loronar Corporation and their supposed depletion of the world's resources.

properties.name: Ganzik
properties.description: Ganzik was a world located in the Ganzik system, a part of the Mid Rim's Maldrood sector. It was situated near the hyperlane known as the Perlemian Trade Route. The primary shipyards of the starship manufacturing company Mesens Corporation were located in orbit around Ganzik.

properties.name: Garban
properties.description: Garban was the homeworld of the Jenet species and the fourth planet in the Tau Sakar system. It was located in the Abrion sector of the Outer Rim Territories, in the region between the Perlemian Trade Route and Corellian Run known as the Slice.

properties.name: Garcornia
properties.description: Garcornia was a planet in the Garcornia system of the Mid Rim's Ado sector.

properties.name: Gardaji Rift
properties.description: The Gardaji Rift was a region of the Outer Rim, within the Gardaji sector of the galaxy's Tingel Arm. It was surveyed and charted by several expeditions in approximately 229 BBY; sometime between then and 89 BBY, Zonama Sekot arrived in the Rift and settled in orbit around a yellow dwarf star in a "triple star system" of a hidden region at the far spinward and galactic north side of the Rift.

properties.name: Garen
properties.description: Garen was a member of Republic class-seven retrieval team capable of handling ZR-57 orbital strike bombs. After one such bomb was almost set off on Voss, Garen and Jak were brought in to safely retrieve it.

properties.name: Garfin
properties.description: The Garfin was a New Republic warship sent to aid General Garm Bel Iblis, Booster Terrik, and the Errant Venture at Yaga Minor in an attempt to steal a copy of the Caamas Document.

properties.name: Gargon
properties.description: Gargon was a planet in Mandalore sector.

properties.name: Garia
properties.description: Garia was a planet in the Garia system of the Brak sector. It was the site of a battle during the Clone Wars.

properties.name: Garis
properties.description: Garis was a planet in the Tamarin sector of the Outer Rim Territories.

properties.name: Garn
properties.description: Garn was a desolate world of craggy rocks and dead trees shrouded in a dense yellow fog, located in the Cadma sector of the Outer Rim. The planet was once home to the Force-wielding order known as the Order of the Terrible Glare thousands of years before the Galactic Civil War, until the Jedi Order laid waste to Garn at the climax of a war between the two organizations. Although the Terrible Glare was completely wiped out, their High Shaman, Rur, preserved an aspect of his consciousness by uploading his personality to a computer system in his citadel on ruined Garn. A vengeful Rur lured a number of passing Jedi to their demise with false distress calls over a period of thousands of years, until aspiring Jedi Luke Skywalker broke the news that the Great Jedi Purge had destroyed the Jedi Order—unable to comprehend that his vengeance was out of reach, the remnants of Rur's mind self-destructed.

properties.name: Garobi
properties.description: The Garobi system was a star system located in the Tapani sector's Barnaba Province, between the Barnaba and Hellios systems.

properties.name: Garollia
properties.description: The Garollia system was a star system located in the Baroli sector of the galactic regions known as the Expansion Region and the Trailing Sectors. It was home to the creatures known as Garollian ghost vipers.

properties.name: Garos
properties.description: Garos was an astronomical object located in the galaxy's Mid Rim. It was the location of a university and Imperial facility five years after the Clone Wars.

properties.name: Garqi
properties.poi: Garqi Agricultural University, , Vlassy River, Vlassy Nature Preserve, , Pesktda Xenobotanical Garden, , Garqi Agricultural Combine,
properties.description: Garqi was an agriworld and the sector capital of Tadrin subsector, in the Outer Rim Territories. Natural elements in Garqi's crust gave the native plant life a purple coloration. From space, the planet appeared a beautiful, hypnotic violet color. It was the source of the beans used to make caf.

properties.name: Garr'lst
properties.description: Garr'lst was a planet in the Inner Rim. Members of the planet's native sentient feline species were massacred at some point before or during the Republic Dark Age.

properties.name: Garrthinius
properties.description: Garrthinius was a planet that was ruled by the Galactic Empire by the time of the Battle of Endor. It became the site of a lot of Rebel Alliance activity, and the Alliance tried to establish a cell network there in order to overthrow the Imperial leaders.

properties.name: Gascon
properties.description: Gascon was a wealthy and powerful planet located in the Mid Rim's Trans-Gascon sector. Ruled by a king and his queen, Marilla, following the formation of the New Republic, Gascon remained neutral yet strategically important during the Galactic Civil War between the New Republic and the Galactic Empire. At one point, the pro–New Republic Marilla, who had given a unique ring as a gift to her lover, the Prime Minister of the planet Demigue, tasked a group of individuals with retrieving the ring in time for a ball given by Gascon's king so that her affair would not be exposed.

properties.name: Gastrula
properties.description: Gastrula was a planet in the Rayter sector of the Outer Rim Territories. The homeworld of the Gastrulan species, it was the terminus of the short-lived Great Bantha Breakfast Biscuit Run during the Galactic Civil War. Captain Bungo Bung had established the trade route in an effort to make credits by selling the popular snack Bantha Breakfast Biscuits to the locals. However, when combined with certain elements in the environment of Gastrula, preservatives in the biscuits caused the snacks to mutate into the Giant Amorphous Bantha Breakfast Biscuit. The resulting lifeform was a ravenous creature that set out to consume the entire planet.

properties.name: Gathus
properties.description: Gathus was a planet in the Tynquay sector in the Outer Rim Territories. The local smashball team played against a team from Lafra.

properties.name: Gaulus
properties.description: Gaulus was a planet near Tatooine, that at one time hosted a Alliance to Restore the Republic base. An espionage droid infiltrated the base and transmitted the location to the Galactic Empire, and thus the base was destroyed shortly after.

properties.name: Gaurick
properties.description: Gaurick was a planet in Corporate Sector. It was controlled by a religious cult, with leaders known as muftis.

properties.name: Gavens
properties.description: Gavens was a human-inhabited planet located in the Expansion Region's Gavens system. It was the birthplace of Akanah Norand Goss Pell. Its capital city was Torlas.

properties.name: Gavos
properties.description: Gavos was a small planet located in the Kastolar sector of the Mid Rim. It was the location of a poorly productive oridium mining operation that was won in a game of sabacc sometime during the Galactic Civil War by Bargos the Hutt—a gambling, middle-ranked Hutt Cartel crime lord living on hard times in a palace somewhere on the Outer Rim. Bargos called in a debt of obligation from a group of adventurers and had them travel to Gavos to assess the quality and worth of the mines.

properties.name: Gavryn
properties.description: Gavryn was a planet with a powerful magnetic pole. Ensign Gilad Pellaeon first distinguished himself while commanding an escort for a convoy to Gavryn. As the convoy entered orbit, pirates attacked. Pellaeon flew his ship into the magnetic pole, obscuring his ship from the pirates' sensors. As the pirate vessel moved to board the convoy ships, Pellaeon emerged from the pole and destroyed them. His quick thinking in this incident earned him the first in a string of promotions.

properties.name: Gaxxa
properties.description: The Gaxxa system was a star system located in the galactic regions known as the Inner Rim and the Slice. It was home to the creatures known as gaxxan brain-slugs.

properties.name: Gazzari
properties.description: Gazzari was a planet that was located in the Grumani sector. Gazzari had a breathable atmosphere, but the planetary surface was inhospitable, due to the presence of volcanoes, tectonic activity and acid rain.

properties.name: Gbu
properties.description: Gbu was a planet in the Outer Rim Territories, located in the Tion Cluster's Keldrath sector.

properties.name: Geedon
properties.description: Geedon was a convoy of seven CR90 corvettes containing food for the Galactic Empire. The entire convoy was destroyed by X-wings and Y-wings stolen from Overlord Ghorin's arsenal before the Remoh could arrive to assist it.

properties.name: Gelgelar
properties.poi: Drop Point GelgelarFarmers' LandingGreat Shore MarshesKrevk SettlementShrine of Kooroo
properties.description: Gelgelar was a cold, cloud-covered swamp planet in the Outer Rim Territories. It was the homeworld of the Glarsaurs.

properties.name: Gellefon
properties.description: Gellefon was a planet in the Korness system of the Outer Rim. It was the location of Kig Dannen Spaceport. It was a planet of cool, rocky crags, mountains, and crevasses. It was inhabited by Humans and other sapients as well as the indigenous, semi-sentient gellbeasts known as wardogs. The planet was ruled by Imperial Governor Schennt from his domicile in the center of Kig Dannen. Pinnacle Keep, an Imperial detention center, was also located on this planet.

properties.name: Gelviddis Cluster
properties.description: The Gelviddis Cluster was a star cluster that contained a planet with sands that the Jedi Order discovered would assume the shape of what an observer was thinking.

properties.name: Genassa
properties.description: Genassa was an agriworld in M'shinni sector. The native M'shinni colonized many worlds in the sector, including Agriworld-2079. The planet was represented in the Galactic Senate by R'shinnos Sh'neel.

properties.name: Gendoraan
properties.description: Gendoraan was a planet in the Core Worlds. Imperial Security Bureau Agent Dal Rogos claimed to be a languages teacher from Gendoraan as part of his cover identity.

properties.name: Gendrah-Narvin
properties.description: The Gendrah-Narvin system was a star system located in the Inner Rim.

properties.name: Generis
properties.poi: Generis orbital base, Generis base, ORCC, Rakatan Temple ruins, ,
properties.description: Generis was a high-gravity planet located in the Generis system of the Atrivis sector. It had rugged terrain and was covered with grassy plains and vast jungles. This natural beauty attracted offworld travelers keen to experience its wilderness. Prior to the formation of the Galactic Republic, the world was settled by the Rakata as part of their galaxy-spanning Infinite Empire. Following the collapse of their society, scattered temples were all that remained of their time on Generis. The planet was later settled by a mix of Humans and other species, as was another planet in the system, Atrivis 7.

properties.name: Genesia
properties.description: Genesia was the second planet in the Genesia system of the Brak sector, orbited by a multitude of space stations known as G-Stations. Genesia was located on a popular hyperlane, and received an influx of spacers and other visitors on their way to various destinations.

properties.name: Genian
properties.description: Genian was a Mid Rim world. The planet remained neutral during the Clone Wars due to its vast corporate holdings, research labs, and secure banks. Many Senators, both Separatists and Republic alike, would store their money here, due to its neutrality. Its large, prosperous cities included Bruit, located near a rocky desert surrounded by mountain ranges. Fry Industries was headquartered on Genian.

properties.name: Genon
properties.description: Genon was a planet not far from Imperial commercial centers but it was nearly devoid of settlement because of its most infamous inhabitant: Grappa the Hutt. Grappa used Genon as his base of operations, and his own reputation combined with his well-known connections to Black Sun kept the Empire and others at bay.

properties.name: Geonosis
properties.poi: Badlands of N'g'ziEbon SeaGolbah's PitCaltrop fieldE'Y-Akh DesertDroid foundries, Spires, War Room, Im'g'twe HillsProgate TempleN'ge'u ValleyPetranaki arena, Dooku's hangar, N'rakti Lava FieldsGeonosian eastern barrier fortressGeonosian caves
properties.description: Geonosis, called Geonosia by some natives, was a ringed, rocky planet in the Arkanis sector of the Outer Rim Territories. The home planet of the insectoid Geonosians, it was known for its droid factories and violent gladiatorial games. The desert world was the Confederacy of Independent Systems' first capital, hosting its major droid foundries. It was the site of the Battle of Geonosis, the opening conflict of the Clone Wars, in 22 BBY.

properties.name: Gepparin
properties.description: Gepparin was a planet in the Gepparin system of the Shelsha sector. It was the headquarters of the BloodScar pirate gang, who had taken control of the large mining outpost on planet's surface during the Galactic Civil War, while the smaller farming outposts remained free. The base was attacked in 0.5 ABY by the Galactic Empire, and was completely destroyed.

properties.name: Geran
properties.description: Geran was a planet located in the Calaron sector of the Outer Rim.

properties.name: Geridard
properties.description: Geridard was a Mid Rim world in the Geridard system of Doldur sector. It was known for its retirement and medical facilities, catering to renowned corporate officials. Augusta I'att was to enter the Geridard Convalescent Center, though she was executed before ever attending.

properties.name: Geroon
properties.description: Geroon was an astronomical object in the galaxy's Outer Rim Territories.

properties.name: Gerrard
properties.description: Gerrard was a male Human who served as a captain in the Imperial Military of the reconstituted Sith Empire during the Cold War with the Galactic Republic. A dark-skinned Human with black eyes and black hair cut in a series of stripes, Gerrard was assigned to Watcher One of Imperial Intelligence in the search for the Republic scientist Doctor Nasan Godera on the planet Taris in 3643 BBY. He carried a blaster rifle in combat and wore the standard armor for Imperial soldiers. However, Captain Gerrard and many of his men were killed on a raid on one of Godera's research facilities when a young Jedi Knight, who was also looking for Godera, encountered the Imperials in the subterranean laboratory.

properties.name: Gerrenthum
properties.description: Gerrenthum was a planet along the Corellian Trade Spine and the capital of the Anoat sector.

properties.name: Gerres Gule
properties.description: Gerres Gule was the Kulless homeworld.

properties.name: Gerzob
properties.description: Gerzob was an astronomical object located in the Outer Rim Territories' Gerzob system. It was the homeworld of the creature known as the Yellow-Bellied Green-Proboscis Marsupial.

properties.name: Gesaril
properties.description: Gesaril was an Imperial prison planet, found in the Gesaril system of the Minos Cluster. It was the site of a series of accidents concerning Imperial warships.

properties.name: Geska Prime
properties.description: Geska Prime was a planet in the Lifh sector of the Mid Rim.

properties.name: Gestron
properties.description: Gestron was a planet in the Tennuutta sector of the Mid Rim.

properties.name: Gevarno Cluster
properties.description: The Gevarno Cluster was a collection of star systems located in the Outer Rim Territories along the Gevarno Loop.

properties.name: Ghaina
properties.description: Ghaina, a Core World, was one of the earliest settled colony worlds in the Galactic Republic. Remotely situated, it was not considered important to galactic society and produced only one Jedi: Taria Damsin.

properties.name: Ghishi
properties.description: Ghishi was a planet located in the Ghishi system and was the homeworld of the Ghishi species.

properties.name: Gholondreine
properties.description: The Gholondreine were the natives of the planet Gholondreine-β. The scholars and philosophers of the Gholondreine were renowned across the galaxy, and held that all beings owed their highest loyalty to truth, regardless of temporal consequences. Consequently, they were reluctant to implement the changes of the New Order, and around 10 BBY, began circulating critiques of the Galactic Empire's rule. As punishment, Palpatine had all the water stripped from their homeworld and taken to Coruscant. The dying desert world was subsequently abandoned as they moved to nearby systems.

properties.name: Ghorman
properties.description: Ghorman was a planet in the Sern sector of the Colonies region. It was the site of the infamous Ghorman Massacre. Fang Zar had a residence on the planet.

properties.name: Ghost Nebula
properties.description: The Ghost Nebula was a nebula and a sector in the Slice portion of Expansion Region that blocked light from most of the stars beyond and within it, isolating it from the galaxy and inspiring its name. Ultraviolet radiation from massive stars at its center ionized the surrounding gases to form plasma, which bathed the planets within the nebula in their ultraviolet light. It surrounded the inhabited planets of Umbara and Atoa, respective homeworlds of the near-Humans Umbaran and Atoan peoples.

properties.name: Gibad
properties.description: Gibad was one of the few planets that defied Emperor Palpatine shortly after the formation of the Galactic Empire. Home to parks and beautiful cities, the Gibadan Academy of Life Sciences was a well respected university in the Outer Rim.

properties.name: Gibbela
properties.description: Gibbela was a remote Outer Rim Territories planet located in the Atrivis sector. It was the homeworld of the shapeshifting Dazouri species, members of which engaged in simple farming on Gibbela.

properties.name: Gigor
properties.description: Gigor was a cold, mountainous planet and the homeworld of the Gigoran species. The Gigorans evolved from group-oriented primates who lived in caves. As they developed intelligence, they took to living as hunter-gatherers while keeping their cavern homes. The species divided itself into home-clans made up of around 50 members who divided themselves into three to five family groups. There was no higher government than the home-clan on Gigor, each under the leadership of the most skillful hunter.
