The world was largely unsettled, and it had very little in the way of high-technology. The Gigorans themselves had access to few items higher than stone-age technology.

properties.name: Giju
properties.description: Giju was the Herglic homeworld. Located in the Colonies, it was on the Rimma Trade Route and was one endpoint of the Giju Run. Giju was an aquatic-type world with large bodies of water and associated terrain including: expansive oceans, islands, marshes, and glaciers. Giju had many spaceports and manufacturing centers.

properties.name: Gilliana
properties.description: Gilliana was a planet in the Tapani sector's Gilliana system in the Cadriaan Province. Settlers from Gilliana colonized Aleron.

properties.name: Ginn Jump
properties.description: The Ginn Jump was a location in the Core Worlds.

properties.name: Gizer
properties.description: Gizer was a planet famed for the manufacturing of the Gizer L-6 freighter and gizer ale.

properties.name: Glade
properties.description: Glade was a planet in the Gordian Reach. It was a polluted industrial world plagued by acidic rains that rusted machinery within weeks.

properties.name: Glakka
properties.description: Glakka was an ice-covered planet in the Outer Rim Territories where Jabba the Hutt had a gun-running operation along with Chevin criminal Ephant Mon. The two tried to steal an Imperial weapons cache, but were ambushed by an Imperial squad. They barely survived the attack and almost died in the subzero temperatures at night.

properties.name: Glee Anselm
properties.description: Glee Anselm ) was a peaceful water planet in the Mid Rim. The planet's surface was largely covered in water or swamps, with only a few clear landmasses dotting its surface. The planet had very frequent season changes, causing it to be ravaged by intense storms with some of them turning cyclonic. The climate was moderate most of the standard year round.

properties.name: Gligger
properties.description: Gligger was a planet in the Outer Rim's Ash Worlds. During the Clone Wars, 563 LIN demolitionmech autonomous minelayers were destroyed while trying to clear mines from Marrow's Moor.

properties.name: Glithnos
properties.description: Glithnos was a Galactic Republic planet represented in the Galactic Senate by Jannie Ha'Nook.

properties.name: Glom Tho
properties.description: Glom Tho was a planet in Hevvrol sector, and the location of the Battle of Glom Tho.

properties.name: Glottal
properties.description: Glottal was a planet located within the Glottal system in the Baxel sector of the Outer Rim region of the galaxy. It was the Glottalphib homeworld. It was a hot and humid planet, making it a perfect habitat for the 'Phibs.

properties.name: Glova
properties.poi: Borke's Cantina, The Dive, Government Compound, The Orchid, New Republic Embassy,
properties.description: Glova was a semi-tropical planet in the Glova system colonized around 195 BBY. When its precious metals ran dry, its mines were abandoned, and the inhabitants turned to farming, becoming a leading supplier of food for planets in the region.

properties.name: Gmar Askilon
properties.description: Gmar Askilon was a star in the Krenhner sector of the Inner Rim.

properties.name: Gobindi
properties.description: Gobindi was an Outer Rim planet in the Noonian sector, with an Imperial bioweapons lab. Human siblings Zak and Tash Arranda visited the planet seeking medical aid after Zak contracted a stomach virus. Zak was taken to the hospital and treated. While Tash and her droid DV-9 went for a walk, they encountered a blob, unaware it was hostile until it lunged at them and almost crushed the droid. This was their first encounter with the blob, one of the experiments in Borborygmus Gog's Project Starscream.

properties.name: Godo
properties.description: Godo was a planet in the Outer Rim Territories. It was the source of flame gems. The world was saved by Lando Calrissian and Han Solo. The Godoans refused to save Lando from a deadly disease in return until Han threatened to attack Godo with the Alliance of Free Planets fleet, although Godo was a member world.

properties.name: Goelitz
properties.description: Goelitz was a rival of nearby Ylix. The planet became embroiled in a war with its neighbor that lasted for a number of years. Goelitz and Ylix both used underhand tactics in the conflict, with either side employing increasingly vicious acts of barbarism and terrorism to outdo the other. The local Imperial Moff promised to bring a peaceful end to the civil war, but this vow went unfulfilled.

properties.name: Golh
properties.description: Golh was a planet located within the Golh system of the Outer Rim Territories. An aquatic planet, it was owned by Hydrospeare Corporation, who used Golh as a test site for its aquatic projects, commonly aquatic weapons and military vehicles.

properties.name: Golkus
properties.description: Golkus was a planet between Carratos and Coruscant. Akanah Norand Goss Pell stopped there to get false identification papers from Talon Karrde's organization before she first met Luke Skywalker on Coruscant.

properties.name: Golrath
properties.description: Golrath was a planet located in the Sanbra sector of the Outer Rim Territories. A heavily volcanic world, Golrath was at one point home to a magma smelting industry that was largely abandoned after the planet underwent a phase of global cooling—the planet's volcanic bedrock had unique light-absorbing properties that allowed it to play back images it collected in a manner similar to a holoprojector. In 3 ABY, an abandoned magma smelting plant on Golrath became home to Golrath Station, a temporary Rebel Alliance base at the height of the Galactic Civil War.

properties.name: Goluud Minor
properties.description: Goluud Minor was a mining world located within the Goluud Minor system of the Core Worlds. By 5000 BBY, a new mining colony had been established on the planet, and merchant lord Ssk Kahorr sent the drone ship Zeta Five to deliver much-needed mining technology and equipment to the colony and sell them to the wealthiest miners. However, the Zeta Five never arrived at Goluud Minor, as it was destroyed by a solar flare from the unstable red supergiant star Primus Goluud during a stopover in the Primus Goluud system.

properties.name: Gon Tiek
properties.description: Gon Tiek was a world located within the Gon Tiek system, a part of the Atravis sector in the Western Reaches portion of the Outer Rim Territories. At some point after the establishment of the Galactic Empire in 19 BBY, the 501st Legion, an elite Imperial stormtrooper unit, fought on Gon Tiek.

properties.name: Gondagali
properties.description: Gondagali was the first planet attacked with the MS-19 shield buster, during the time of the New Republic.

properties.name: Gonmore
properties.description: Gonmore was a planet in the Gonmore system in the Outer Rim. It was the location of a clearinghouse of Talon Karrde.

properties.name: Goorla
properties.description: Goorla was a planet in the Goorla system of the Corellian sector in the Core Worlds. It was the source of the Goorlish light source.

properties.name: Gorbah
properties.description: Gorbah was a planet and the location of four secret fighter bases under control of a rogue group attempting to take out invading Imperial forces. When they realized there was no hope in beating the Empire, they fled their bases immediately.

properties.name: Gorm
properties.description: Gorm was an Outer Rim Territories planet located in the Meerian sector. Located on the galactic frontier by 4000 BBY, it was the homeworld of the venomous reptiles known as gorm-worms, which were exported across the galaxy. Around 3643 BBY, an individual visited the ancient Gorm Academy in order to study its secrets.

properties.name: Gormen
properties.description: Gormen was a planet that became embroiled in a battle between the Galactic Empire and the Alliance to Restore the Republic. The battle was decided with the appearance of All Terrain Armored Transport walkers, which marched out of the fog, scattering locals, and decimated the Rebel front lines.

properties.name: Gorno
properties.description: Gorno was a planet in the Outer Rim, along the Corellian Run near Tatooine. The Galactic Empire had a secret research facility used to design the Superlaser for the second Death Star, codenamed Hammertong. A spaceport there was used as an embarkation point from which the Hammertong was to depart, shortly before the Battle of Yavin.

properties.name: Gorobei
properties.description: Gorobei was a planet in the galaxy's Inner Rim that was the homeworld of the Frenk species.

properties.name: Goroth
properties.description: Goroth, also known as Goroth Prime, was a location in the galaxy. When Agent Alecia Beck of the Imperial Security Bureau requested a meeting with Senator Mon Mothma, Mothma's aide, Hendri Underholt, lied to Beck and told her that Mothma had already left Coruscant and had gone on a fact-finding mission to Goroth.

properties.name: Gorsh
properties.poi: Calimondo PlateauGenetech Laboratories Orbiting Research Station
properties.description: Gorsh was the third planet of the Gorsh system, located in Wild Space 100,000 light years away from the Core. The watery planet had a population of 100,000.

properties.name: Gos Hutta
properties.description: The Gos Hutta system, also called Gos Hutta, was a Hutt Space star system that lay within the Bootana Hutta area. The system contained three planets and several space stations, and it served as a gateway to the Bootana Hutta, being frequently patrolled by warships of the Hutt species. The system was used at some point by Hutt clan leaders to meet privileged foreigners.

properties.name: Gosfambling
properties.description: Gosfambling was a planet in the Mid Rim, and was the homeworld of the Gosfamlings. C-Gosf represented the world in the New Republic Senate.

properties.name: Goshyn
properties.description: Goshyn could refer to one of the following:

properties.name: Gotida
properties.description: Gotida was a planet in the Goti system. It was home of a Rebel cell led by Lieutenant Commander Detta Rotan.

properties.name: Gottlegoob
properties.description: Gottlegoob was a planet in the New Republic. During the Presidency of Leia Organa Solo, its people suffered from famine.

properties.name: Govia
properties.description: Govia was a planet in the Govia system, a star system in the Corellian sector of the Core Worlds. It was the homeworld of the Govian species.

properties.name: Gowdawl
properties.description: Gowdawl was a planet to which the Koqus Design Syndic passenger liner Star Morning, fully loaded with passengers, was headed from Motexx. The ship never arrived, rather appearing at Arat Fraca empty of passengers 300 days later.

properties.name: Gra Ploven
properties.description: Gra Ploven was a planet in the Colonies.

properties.name: Graador
properties.description: Graador was a Mid Rim planet that featured caverns large enough to fit entire fleets of starships in them. The caverns were home to both immense exogorths and mynocks that could survive in the planet's atmosphere. Graador was also inhabited by two sentient species: the agrarian Graadorians and a mutated type of intelligent mynocks.

properties.name: Graal'diin
properties.description: Graal'diin was a planet under the control of the Galactic Empire. Brenn and Dellis Tantor were told that their father died in a Rebel attack while delivering grain to the planet, but that was in fact a lie designed to cover the fact that the Empire had had him executed for losing his cargo to pirates. The Empire wished to make an example of him to ensure that other freighter pilots would go to great lengths to protect their cargo.

properties.name: Grakouine
properties.description: Grakouine was a world on which an Alliance to Restore the Republic storage depot was located. It was here that Boba Fett's ship Slave I was impounded by the New Republic after he was presumed killed by the Sarlacc on Tatooine. Sometime after escaping the Sarlacc, he made his way to Grakouine and recovered Slave I.

properties.name: Grandeel
properties.description: Grandeel was a planet within the Tynna sector of the Expansion Region of the galaxy. It was the location of a fish farm and was the homeworld of Imperial Major Reskik.

properties.name: Grandine
properties.description: Grandine may refer to one of the following:

properties.name: Granna
properties.description: Granna was the Grannan homeworld, controlled by the Galactic Empire.

properties.name: Grathus
properties.description: Grathus was a terrestrial planet located in the Grathus system, a part of the Jospro sector in the Slice portion of the Outer Rim Territories. The planet featured several large mud basin settlements, including one which contained a tavern owned by Xig Rollem.

properties.name: Gravdinia
properties.description: The Gravdinia system was located in the Slice portion of the Colonies. It was the origin point of the beverage known as Gravdinian Ale.

properties.name: Gravlex Med
properties.description: Gravlex Med was a terrestrial planet in the Outer Rim Territories. With an above-average gravity, the planet's native species, the Anx, had a stooped stature and other species found the world uninhabitable. Gravlex Med quickly became the heart of Anx Space as the spacefaring species expanded their borders throughout the Raioballo sector. During the reign of the Galactic Empire, Gravlex Med became so polluted by Imperial mismanagement of waste that the world no longer proved suitable for habitation.

properties.name: Greater Marianas
properties.description: Greater Marianas was a little known dust-swept planet in the Outer Rim Territories subjugated by the Galactic Empire some time before the Battle of Yavin. It contained at least one settlement of Humans and was also home to the yaggie, a creature hunted for its skin and meat.

properties.name: Gree
properties.description: Gree was a planet located within the Gree Enclave, a small region in the Veragi sector of the Outer Rim Territories. It was the homeworld of the Gree species, a race of six-tentacled cephalopods who, despite having an advanced form of technology, allowed their society to fall into ruin when they began prizing an individual's mastery of their advanced devices over improving them or creating new ones. As the Operator caste became more powerful within Gree society, they guarded the secrets of operating and manipulating their devices, sometimes dying before they could pass the knowledge on to their apprentices.

properties.name: Gree Baaker
properties.description: Gree Baaker was a planet in the Gree Baaker system of the Outer Rim's Atrivis sector. Under the Galactic Empire, it was home to the Gree Baaker Labor Camp. Many of the camp's prisoners were transferred to work detail on the Death Star, and later perished with its destruction in 0 ABY.

properties.name: Greeb-Streebling Cluster
properties.description: The Greeb-Streebling Cluster was located in the Ninth Quadrant, which was part of the Bozhnee sector of the Outer Rim Territories, near the Senex and Juvex sectors.

properties.name: Greeve
properties.description: Greeve was an agricultural planet with heavy gravity that was located in the Grumani sector. The population of Greeve were often considered to be "yokels", and over the years they provided manpower for many different armies.

properties.name: Grehollo
properties.description: Grehollo may refer to one of the following:

properties.name: Grella
properties.description: Grella was a planet located in the Tapani sector's Grella system.

properties.name: Greyman's Planet
properties.description: Greyman's Planet was an Imperial industrial world located within the Soarin system in the Outer Rim Territories. It was the location of Da'Harrin Spaceport and, during the Galactic Civil War, it was home to a Rebel Alliance base.

properties.name: Grizmallt
properties.poi: Old Quarter, Palazzo Reina, Heroine Hall,
properties.description: Grizmallt was a planet in the Core Worlds, inhabited by Humans called the Grizmallti. Queen Elsinoré den Tasia began her reign of Grizmallt around 3950 BBY, launching an era of colonization and exploration. Although many of the expeditions failed, Grizmallti colonists populated various planets around the galaxy, including eight in the Renatasia system and Nam Chorios. Around 3900 BBY, Grizmallt was engulfed in a civil war, and Tasia sponsored a final expedition of refugees that resulted in the Human colonization of the planet Naboo.

properties.name: Gromas
properties.description: Gromas was a gas giant located in the Gromas system, within the Perkell sector of the Mid Rim. Gromas was only notable for its 32 multicolored moons, including the "Blood Moon," Gromas 16. Its moons were the primary source of phrik. And-Yees, a Gran assassin, was known to have visited Gromas before being captured by Jango Fett at Outland Transit Station.

properties.name: Groth
properties.description: Groth was a planet that was located within the star system of the same name and lay deep within the Bootana Hutta area of the galaxy's Hutt Space region. A former throneworld of the Hutt species, the planet eventually became a resort that was the site of gladiatorial exhibitions and gambling. During the Cold War between the Galactic Republic and the resurgent Sith Empire in the year 3643 BBY, an information broker on Groth sliced into the military database of the Empire.

properties.name: Gruvia
properties.description: Gruvia was a planet in the Expansion Region. It was the homeworld of the Gruvian species, whom exported Gruvian Tovash. The planet was part of the Empire.

properties.name: Gryphon
properties.description: Gryphon was a mountainous planet located in the Inner Rim with an indigenous species who lived in clans and were constantly at war with each other. Brock Lar was one such individual, though he left the planet when his youngest son died.

properties.name: Guiteica
properties.poi: l'Quar'ta, s'Korth'an, Standard-class spaceport, Upper Bal'ta'ran Cluster, u'Tal'ac Range,
properties.description: Kadok III-D, commonly known as Guiteica, was a harsh planet located in Wild Space's Kadok Regions. It featured forests, mountains, glaciers, and huge waterfalls. The planet possessed rich reserves of metal ores and minerals such as feldspar, yttrium, and Bal'ta'ran crystals. Guiteica was inhabited by creatures such as j'kuutak and roggwart. Guiteica was also the homeworld of the Bitthævrians, a warlike yet isolationist sentient species. The sixteen primary continents of Guiteica were each governed by a separate military force, which made up the planetary defense force known as the Guiteica Militia. The dominant army on Guiteica was the m'Yalfor'ac Order of the l'Quar'ta continent.

properties.name: Gulf of Tatooine
properties.description: The Gulf of Tatooine was a near-starless region that formed a part of the Outer Rim Territories' Arkanis sector. The Trans Gulf Route hyperlane traversed the area, with the Vuzsa system being located on the hyperspace route. At some point by 6 ABY, a transgalactic starliner was forced to stop at the Gulf of Tatooine so that its crew could clean the ship's cockpit viewport after it had become obscured as a result of a food fight initiated by the vessel's droid service crew.

properties.name: Gulma
properties.description: Gulma was a planet located within the Gulma system in Wild Space and was the homeworld of the Gulmarid species. The planet was covered by swampy terrain.

properties.name: Gulvitch
properties.description: Gulvitch was a mining planet located in the Gordian Reach. It sat on the Junction-Tierell Loop, between Bronsoon and Arkuda. The planet was home to a struggling colony founded by the Povanarians and Bagmims. Gulvitch was rarely visited by those who could afford to go elsewhere.

properties.name: Gurrisalia
properties.description: Gurrisalia may refer to one of the following:

properties.name: Gwar
properties.description: Gwar was a planet that was orbited by the the platform Supply Base. In 4 ABY, Gwar was the site of a battle during the Zaarin insurrection.

properties.name: Gwori
properties.description: Gwori was a planet located in the Clacis sector of the Outer Rim Territories.

properties.name: Gymelo
properties.description: Gymelo was an astronomical object located within the Gymelo system, a part of the Bakura sector within the Outer Rim Territories and Wild Space.

properties.name: Gyndine
properties.poi: Gyndine Shipyards, , , Tendrando Refueling and Repair Station,
properties.description: Gyndine was a planet in the Expansion Region. It was a local administrative center, and had mid-sized, advanced shipyards.

properties.name: Gyosha
properties.description: Gyosha was an Imperial resort world in the Galactic Core. Wilek Nereus had hoped to be appointed Governor of Gyosha, but got stuck on Bakura instead. OrulShai III was a moon of Gyosha.

properties.name: H'ken
properties.description: H'ken was the primary planet in the H'ken system. Located within the H'ken asteroid belt, a 20 kilometer wide navigational nightmare, the planet was difficult to access.

properties.name: H'nemthe
properties.description: H'nemthe was the homeworld of the H'nemthe species.

properties.name: H'ratth
properties.description: H'ratth was a lush planet with a Jedi Academy where Jedi Master Chamma taught Andur Sunrider the Jedi ways in 4001 BBY. It was the homeworld of Vima Sunrider. The academy was known for its training of Jedi healers.

properties.name: Haariden
properties.description: Haariden was a volcanic world and the lava crab homeworld. It was orbited by a sole moon, which appeared pink from the planet's surface.

properties.name: Haaridin
properties.description: Haaridin was a world located in the Kwymar sector of the Outer Rim Territories.

properties.name: Haashimut
properties.description: Haashimut was an Outer Rim planet. It was a Republic fortress world colonized c. 24,000 BBY from which the Jedi kept a watchful eye on the hostile Tion Cluster from their stronghold there.

properties.name: Habassa
properties.description: The Habassa was the Habassa system's primary race.

properties.name: Had Abbadon
properties.description: Had Abbadon was an ancient lost mythic planet, located in the Deep Core. According to some legends, the planet may have been linked to the origin of the Jedi Order or its forerunners.

properties.name: Hadlress
properties.description: Hadlress was an astronomical object located in the Hadlress system, a part of the Trailing Sectors portion of the Inner Rim. Jasis Temm, the owner and Chief Executive Officer of the company Hadlress Defense Systems, Limited, was based on Hadlress. At some point between 2 BBY and 2 ABY, Temm sold his company for 4.6 billion credits and eventually became a bounty hunter.

properties.name: Haffrin
properties.description: Haffrin was a planet in the Haffrin system of the Esstran sector in the Outer Rim. Built millennia ago, a Shrine of Kooroo was fabricated on the planet using native stone.

properties.name: Hakara
properties.description: Hakara was a swamp planet native to the insectoid Hakarans. It was previously believed to be uninhabited by the Galactic Republic.

properties.name: Hakartha Space Station
properties.description: Hakartha Space Station, or simply Hakartha Station, was an Imperial-controlled space station at the height of the Galactic Civil War.

properties.name: Hakassi
properties.description: Hakassi was a planet located in the Deep Core.

properties.name: Halanit
properties.description: Halanit was an ichthyoculture moon colonized around 20 BBY. The moon orbited a large gas giant, and was covered with a thick ice crust, but beneath it crust the inner heat of the moon's core created pockets of breathable atmosphere. The primary settlement was just below the ice, in a fissure that was covered by a double-paneled transparisteel dome. It was an insignificant world for the Galactic Empire and Alliance to Restore the Republic with a low population just over 10.000 people.

properties.name: Halbara
properties.description: Halbara was a planet in the Elrood sector. It was known for its monsoons and hairstyles. The planet was owned by Radell Mining.

properties.name: Haldeen
properties.description: Haldeen was the sector capital of Haldeen sector. Earnst Kamiel, a Justice Action Network terrorist, was extradited to Haldeen after his capture on Elrood.

properties.name: Hali
properties.description: Hali was a temperate planet in the Expansion Region with three suns and at least two moons. It was the homeworld of Marit Dice.

properties.name: Hallion
properties.description: Hallion was a planet located in the Sith Worlds of the Outer Rim. The planet featured lava fields that produced obsidian, and decorative spheres made of polished obsidian from the lava fields were prized for their dark luster.

properties.name: Hallitron
properties.description: Hallitron-7 was an Imperial planet in the Mid Rim.

properties.name: Halm
properties.description: Halm was an arid desert world, famous for its extensive mines. These mines contained rare Adegan crystals, which were used in the construction of lightsabers.

properties.name: Halmad
properties.poi: Fellon base, Fellon's marina, Halmad's spaceport, Ola's, Quelii Sector Academy, Rojio's, Victory Base,
properties.description: Halmad was a planet in Quelii sector of the Outer Rim Territories.

properties.name: Halowan
properties.poi: Trans-system data storage libraryHolowan LaboratoriesHolowan Mechanicals
properties.description: Halowan was a barren planet in the Fakir sector of the Bakchou arm. It was the location of Holowan Laboratories, the creators of the IG-series droids.

properties.name: Halpat
properties.description: Halpat was a planet in the Core Worlds, not far from the Koornacht Cluster. It was the New Republic supply depot for the New Republic Fifth Battle Group's blockade of the Cluster. Etahn A'baht did not consider it close enough to the Cluster.

properties.name: Halthor
properties.description: Halthor was a planet invaded by the Mandalorian Neo-Crusaders under the command of Dorjander Kace during the Mandalorian Wars at the Battle of Halthor.

properties.name: Handooine
properties.description: Handooine was an Outer Rim Territories planet located on the Triellus Trade Route as part of the Phelleem sector. Known as Gwynhes during the reign of the conqueror Xim twenty millennia before the Battle of Yavin, by the time of the Clone Wars, Handooine was a sparsely populated world. During that conflict, the Galactic Republic used Handooine as a staging area for its upcoming military campaign on the nearby planet Jabiim. Separatist agents also introduced a computer virus onto Republic's prototype Tector-class Star Destroyer Gibbon at Handooine at some point during the war.

properties.name: Hanna
properties.description: Hanna could refer to the following:

properties.name: Hanod
properties.description: Hanod was a terrestrial astronomical object located in the Hanod system, a part of the Corva sector in the New Territories portion of the Outer Rim Territories. At some point by 38 ABY, military bunkers on Hanod were identified by letters from the ancient Common Sith writing system, a fact which was noted by the xenolinguist Doctor Milanda Vorgan in her publication "The Written Word: A Brief Introduction to the Writing Systems of Galactic Basic."

properties.name: Hanofar
properties.description: Hanofar was a terrestrial world located in the Hanofar system, a part of the Southern Core portion of the Colonies. During the early years of the Galactic Civil War, a conflict fought between the Galactic Empire and the Rebel Alliance, Hanofar was held by the Empire.

properties.name: Hapes
properties.poi: Fountain Palace, Reef Fortress, Lorell Hall
properties.description: Hapes was the homeworld of the Hapans, a near-Human race known for their beauty, and the administrative capital of the Hapes Consortium. Surrounded by shimmering nebulae, and with seven moons in the sky after sunset, Hapes never knew the darkness of true night, and the Hapan people had relatively poor night-vision.

properties.name: Hapor
properties.description: Hapor was a planet under the control of the Galactic Empire in 0 ABY. The planet was visited by the Hand of Judgment stormtrooper team, who became involved in a water dispute in Griren Province.

properties.name: Hapuntep
properties.description: Hapuntep was a planet ruled by a monarchy. At least one of the nobles from the planet held the title of "Crown Prince."

properties.name: Har Binande
properties.description: Har Binande was the primary planet in the Har system. Invaded by the Lahag Erli during the early years of the Galactic Republic, their forces occupied the planet for many years until they were finally deposed. They left in their wake cities of exquisite architecture on many of the Har worlds. These cities would become profitable as tourist attractions, erasing memory of the occupation.

properties.name: Harbin-re
properties.description: Harbin-re was a planet located in the Harbin-re system of the Inner Rim. It was famous for productions of operas from the Neoclassical period, including several compositions favored by the Galactic Emperor Palpatine. On the date 35:10:16, the Harbin-re opera was mentioned in an Imperial HoloVision news report.

properties.name: Hardex
properties.description: The Hardex were a sentient species native to the Hardex system in the Jubilar sector of the Outer Rim Territories. Prior to 5.5 BBY, the Hardex sent an ambassador to the Targonnian leader Craw. Craw told a joke involving three Hardex and a bantha which was poorly received by the Hardexian ambassador. Consequently, Craw had the protocol droid who translated his joke deactivated and turned into a water fountain.

properties.name: Hargeeva
properties.description: Hargeeva was an Expansion Region world, the third of five planets in the Pelonat system located near Garen IV. Its local day was 23 standard hours long, while its year was 380 local days long. It was colonized in 2000 BBY, but was neglected. Its society evolved to a feudal state. Nobles sent their sons to serve in the local royal guard for military training.

properties.name: Harix
properties.description: Harix was a planet in the Colonies that was a strong center of Rebel activity during the Galactic Civil War. In 1 ABY, Imperial Major Stafuv Rahz captured a Harix schoolteacher and a number of children to serve as bait for Rebel leaders. However, Rebels Luke Skywalker and Han Solo led a rescue mission that saved them before fleeing the planet.

properties.name: Harko Station
properties.description: Harko Station was a space station located within the D'Astan sector in the Outer Rim Territories of the galaxy. It served as the base of operations for Tofen Vane's squadron, as well as a production facility for the new Tempest Zero advanced fighters. It was destroyed by Republic forces.

properties.name: Harlequin Station
properties.description: Harlequin Station was a Bengel Shipbuilders XQ1 Platform located in the Garis sector of the Outer Rim Territories. It was a trade center making business with the Azzameen Station.

properties.name: Harloen
properties.description: Harloen was a planet in the Belsmuth sector of the Outer Rim Territories. It was considered to be the swoop racing capital of the Outer Rim.

properties.name: Harpori
properties.description: Harpori was a planet that was located in the Druess sector near the Balowa system within the Mid Rim of the galaxy. It hosted a Duros colony that was wiped out by Kaox Krul in 1000 BBY, shortly before the Battles of Ruusan.

properties.name: Harrandarr
properties.description: Harrandarr was a planet located in the Harrandarr system, a part of the Outer Rim Territories' Bosph sector. It was the homeworld of the sentient Buzchub species. Und'l, a Buzchub who worked for Galactic Empire sympathizers on the Expansion Region astronomical object Roldalna shortly after the establishment of the New Republic in 4 ABY, hailed from Harrandarr.

properties.name: Harridan
properties.description: The name "Harridan" referred to:

properties.name: Harrin
properties.description: Harrin was a planet located in the Inner Rim sector of the same name. It was situated on the Corellian Trade Spine super-hyperroute and served as the endpoint of the Harrin Trade Corridor hyperlane.

properties.name: Harrod's Planet
properties.description: Harrod's Planet was an Outer Rim Territories world located in the Oplovis sector. During the Galactic Civil War, the base of the Oplovis Sector Fleet of the Galactic Empire was located on the planet's surface. When the Sector Fleet was defeated by the Rebel Alliance in the Yuvern system, it regrouped at Harrod's Planet. The smuggler Cane Adiss, whose starship was being inspected by Imperial officers at the time of the attack, was also forced to rendezvous with the fleet there.

properties.name: Harswee
properties.description: Harswee was a Mandalorian planet located within the Mandalore sector of the galaxy's Outer Rim. Luxurious loom-woven carpets were manufactured on Harswee, considered among the finest produced by the Mandalorian worlds. The starliner known as the Coronet—the personal starship of Duchess Satine Kryze of the New Mandalorians—made extensive use of Harswee carpeting.

properties.name: Harterra
properties.description: Harterra was a planet in the Interior Regions of the Hapes Cluster. It was home to the Harterran moonstone.

properties.name: Haruun Kal
properties.poi: Korunnal HighlandGrandfather's ShoulderCloudseaHighland Green WasheteriaGrandmother's TearsGreat DownrushDownrush FallsTrundur WallLorshan PassDeath hollows
properties.description: The planet Haruun Kal , located in the Dustig sector of the Mid Rim on the Gevarno Loop, was the homeworld of the famed Jedi Master Mace Windu. Its capital was Pelek Baw.

properties.name: Hasaq
properties.description: Hasaq was a planet located in the Askarian sector of the Expansion Region of the galaxy. It was known for the orange sun that it orbited. The Jedi Exile may have visited this planet at one point in her life.

properties.name: Hassaria
properties.description: The Hassaria system was a star system that was located within the Wazta sector, a part of the galaxy's Outer Rim Territories. It was home to the sentient Hassarian species.

properties.name: Hast
properties.description: Hast was a planet in the galaxy. It  was the site of a secret New Republic shipyard that came under Imperial attack.

properties.name: Haurgab
properties.description: Haurgab was a planet in the Mid Rim that allied itself with the Separatists during the Clone Wars. The Galactic Republic sent Omega squad to the planet, who battled the local forces in the Battle of Haurgab.

properties.name: Haven
properties.description: The Haven was a secret hideout built by Kanan Jarrus' rebel cell on the Outer Rim planet of Lothal, some five years before the Battle of Yavin. As its name implied, the hideout was designed as a haven for defenseless citizens who were targeted by the Galactic Empire. Some of its inhabitants were Keri Belab, Lorvo Derigo, Jimnaj, Angmi Lihosh, Ossin Nandar, Rance Lojo, Rodd Nertu, Dorthu Santim, Nuj Sorwin, Lornto Teswam, Rylou Watmill, an Ugnaught droid maker, and a chef.

properties.name: Haverling
properties.description: Haverling was a planet in the Albarrio sector of the Outer Rim Territories, near the world of Morishim. It joined the New Republic, aiding the government by providing new shipyards to support the New Republic Navy.

properties.name: Havricus
properties.description: Havricus was a Galactic Republic planet that was infested with stone mites in 22 BBY, prior to the Clone Wars.

properties.name: Hazzard
properties.description: Hazzard was a planet located within the Lahara sector of the Outer Rim that was the homeworld of Boo Rawl.

properties.name: Heffrin
properties.description: Heffrin was a planet located in the Arkanis sector of the Outer Rim. This mountainous world was a small mining colony maintained by the Galactic Empire. The planet held important ruins from a vanished civilization, including the Heffrin Aqueducts, which spanned Heffrin's continents; research during the Cold War between the Galactic Republic and the Sith Empire identified the Aqueducts' builders as early Ithorian explorers.

properties.name: Hefi
properties.description: Hefi was a  planet located in the Hefi system of the Abrion sector, within the Slice portion of the Outer Rim Territories. Covered by landmasses and oceans, Hefi's surface featured varied climates and was capable of supporting various forms of humanoid life.

properties.name: Helleguth
properties.description: Helleguth was a planet located in the Helleguth system of the Inner Rim. Obi-Wan Kenobi intended to bring the criminal T'mott Zoat there, to stand trial for his crimes. One of those crimes was the murder of a woman named Jesef in 41 BBY, who Obi-Wan Kenobi failed to protect.

properties.name: Hellios
properties.description: The Hellios system was a star system located in the Tapani sector's Barnaba Province, between the Garobi system and the Mennaalii system. House Barnaba had holdings in the system during the Galactic Empire's reign.

properties.name: Helska
properties.description: Helska was the primary star of the Helska system.

properties.name: Hendrix
properties.description: Hendrix was a world located in the Iska sector of the Mid Rim. Prior to the Battle of Hoth, Han Solo planned to run weapons from Minoth to Hendrix for the Rebel Alliance.

properties.name: Hensara
properties.description: Hensara was the sun that was orbited by the planet of Hensara III.

properties.name: Heptalia
properties.description: Heptalia was a planet located in the Heptalia system, a part of the Trailing Sectors portion of the Inner Rim. Heptalia's artisans produced furniture coverings and embroidered rugs that were considered to be exquisite and lent renown to the planet.

properties.name: Heptooine
properties.description: Heptooine was a planet located in the south quadrant of the galaxy. During the Kymoodon Era, areas of space grew around Heptooine, as well as Aplooine, Mantooine and Sestooine.

properties.name: Herdessa
properties.description: Herdessa was a Mid Rim planet on the Corellian Run. A peaceful world, many diplomats and others of affluence could remain neutral in debates. It was represented in the Galactic Senate by Shea Sadashassa.

properties.name: Herego
properties.description: Herego was the husk lizard homeworld.

properties.name: Heriston
properties.description: Heriston was a planet in the Atravis sector of the Outer Rim Territories.

properties.name: Hermos
properties.description: Hermos was a planet in the Spadja sector of the Outer Rim.

properties.name: Herzob
properties.description: Herzob was an agriworld in the Colonies. It exported grains to several worlds in the Galactic Core and Mid Rim. The planet was infested with jevesects, which tore through the planet-spanning farms.

properties.name: Hestria
properties.description: Hestria was a thriving agriworld in the Senex sector known for its wines.

properties.name: Heterkus
properties.description: Heterkus was a planet in the Heterkus system, located in the Tharin sector of Outer Rim Territories. Around 0 BBY, the Galactic Empire's Commander Westen of the Relentless clashed with Adar Tallon and the Rebel Alliance at Heterkus.

properties.name: Hethar
properties.description: Hethar was a forested planet located in the Outer Rim Territories' Atrivis sector. It was the homeworld of the omnivores known as gornts, whose meat was a staple in the diet of the local colonists. Shortly before the Battle of Yavin, the Galactic Empire annexed the planet and instituted a gornt breeding and processing program, wherein Sullustan ranchers provided gornt meat as supplies for the Imperial Navy.

properties.name: Hettitite
properties.description: Hettitite was a planet that was located within the star system of the same name, a part of the Dalonbian sector in the Outer Rim Territories region of the galaxy. It was the homeworld of a sentient Near-Human species that had pale skin, white hair, and red eyes.

properties.name: Hettsk
properties.description: Hettsk was a New Republic world located in the Borderland Regions. It was conquered by Imperial forces during the Thrawn campaign. It was also the location of a successful rescue mission undertaken by Page's Commandos.

properties.name: Hewett
properties.description: The Hewett were a non-humanoid, sentient species from the Hewett system. In 34 BBY, an official banquet was held for Hewett senators, at which Konkeel pie was served on the menu. The pie was toxic to humanoids, and the Jedi Master Qui-Gon Jinn almost ate some before his contemporary Adi Gallia stopped him.

properties.name: Hewl
properties.description: Hewl was an astronomical object located within the Hewl system, a part of the Mid Rim's Eidoloni sector. Karap Valley was located on Hewl, and it featured fog banks that were considered to be infamous by the Rebel Alliance Lieutenant Colonel Palpatine Essex Yerac.

properties.name: Hidden Tegoor
properties.description: Hidden Tegoor was a planet located in the Albanin sector of the Outer Rim.

properties.name: Hiffis
properties.description: Hiffis was a planet with a lightly guarded Imperial warehouse. The Rebel Alliance raided the warehouse and stole a huge number of Ultra-Light Assault Vehicles.

properties.name: High Chunah
properties.description: High Chunah was a planet on the Corellian Trade Spine in the Javin sector of the Outer Rim Territories. Once an outlying colony world of the Mugaari species, High Chunah became a profitable speeder-manufacturing planet once the Galactic Republic capitalized on the region's economic potential. High Chunah was best known for the phosphorescent rocks littering its surface, which gave the planet an unusual green glow when seen from space.

properties.name: Hiit
properties.description: Hiit was a desolate moon which orbited the gas giant of Maal. It was located at the intersection of the Authority Guardian Corridor and the Trianii Shunt, in space annexed by the Corporate Sector in 5 BBY.

properties.name: Hijado
properties.description: Hijado was a planet on the Hydian Way, halfway to Bonadan. The Human natives of Hijado were called Hijadoans. It was located in the Hijado system of the Thesme sector.

properties.name: Hijarna
properties.description: Hijarna was a planet that was located near or in Orus sector, within the Inner Rim of the galaxy. The planet was once part of the Rakatan Infinite Empire, and was discovered by the Fifth Alderaanian Expedition, which also discovered the one thousand-year old remains of an ancient civilization. The civilization had fallen to alien invaders. Their last stronghold was the Fortress of Hijarna, made of what was dubbed Hijarna stone, similar to the Hand of Thrawn on Nirauan. The Fortress was used as a rendezvous by Talon Karrde's organization. Karrde assembled the leaders of the Smugglers' Alliance at the Fortress to plan locating the crystal gravfield trap Thrawn had set for the New Republic. At the assembly, Niles Ferrier was revealed as a traitor.

properties.name: Hijo
properties.description: Hijo was an astronomical object located in the Hijoian system, a part of the Expansion Region's Hijoian Space. By 12 ABY, it fell within the territory controlled by the New Republic.

properties.name: Hikil
properties.description: Hikil was a tropical planet from which lulari trees were exported.

properties.name: Hillindor
properties.description: The Hillindor system was located within the Trailing Sectors portion of the Inner Rim. The system was home to the creature known as the Hillindor game fowl.

properties.name: Hilo
properties.description: Hilo was a planet located in the Hilo sector of the Expansion Region.

properties.name: Hinakuu
properties.description: Hinakuu was a planet located in the Hinakuu system of the Calamari sector. It was settled by the Mon Calamari at some point between 4400 BBY and 4200 BBY, and lay along the Tidal Circuit hyperlane.

properties.name: Hindasar
properties.description: Hindasar was a planet in the Hindasar system of the Expansion Regions' Corpheli sector. After escaping the prison on Delrian, Doctor Cornelius Evazan purchased a forged medical license and established himself as a personal surgeon. Charging exorbitant fees with the promise of droid-free surgery, Evazan scarred hundreds of beings, with several dozen dying of their wounds.

properties.name: Hirsi
properties.description: Hirsi was a planet on the Cerean Reach in the Mid Rim.

properties.name: Hishyim
properties.description: Hishyim was a planet covered by a vast desert, located in the Abrion sector of the Outer Rim Territories.

properties.name: Hitaka
properties.description: Hitaka was a farming planet located in the Cademimu sector of the Outer Rim Territories, with a lush landscape of forests and mountains.

properties.name: Hjaff
properties.description: Hjaff was a planet located in the Colonies. It was the homeworld of the Tarc, a species of sentient crustacean creatures. Hjaff had three continents.

properties.name: Hleua
properties.description: Hleua was an astronomical object located in the Hleua system, a part of the Eucer sector of the Mid Rim. During the Tionese War, waged between the Galactic Republic and the Honorable Union of Desevro & Tion, the Republic-settled celestial body Okator VIII was regularly visited by courier starships on business errands from Hleua.

properties.name: Hok
properties.description: Hok was a planet located in the Colonies. The planet was split into two sides. One side was the desert wasteland that looked like Tatooine, while the other half was surrounded by pure darkness. This area also had a rich supply of crystals on which the people mined and traded.

properties.name: Holador
properties.description: Holador was a remote planet. It had a crashed colony of Squibs living on it.

properties.name: Holageus
properties.description: Holageus was a planet in the Expansion Region.

properties.name: Holess
properties.description: Holess was a planet in the Galactic Federation of Free Alliances and the Holessian homeworld. It had more laws than any other world. Its capital city was the location of the Mount of Justice. Most of the population lived in towering cities built with the wealth derived from thousands of years of exporting the planet's rich local deposits of duranium.

properties.name: Hollastin
properties.description: Hollastin was a busy Hutt Space trade world. At one point, the smuggler Han Solo experienced an instance of good fortune there. Hollastin emerged unscathed from the Yuuzhan Vong invasion of Hutt Space and subsequently rose in importance.

properties.name: Hologram Fun World
properties.poi: Adminidome, Anywhere Room, Asteroid Theater, Enchanted Lagoon, Gravity Well, Hall of Reflections, Joy Domes, Maker's Workshop, Nightmare Machine, Star Chamber, Sweetsand Lagoon, Volcano Slide,
properties.description: Hologram Fun World, often abbreviated to HFW, was an amusement park space station located near the Zabian system and Koaan. Held in a transparent dome 40 kilometers in diameter, it floated in a cloud of blue helium.

properties.name: Homon
properties.poi: Alliance to Restore the Republic starfighter base,
properties.description: The world of Homon was the site of an Alliance to Restore the Republic starfighter base during the Galactic Civil War. This planet was in Homon sector in the Mid Rim.

properties.name: Honoghr
properties.description: Honoghr  was the homeworld of the Noghri, and the only one of the Honoghr system's seven planets with a permanent population.

properties.name: Horn Station
properties.description: Horn Station was a backwater world in the Lahara sector of the Outer Rim Territories. It was neglected by the Galactic Republic until a Jedi Knight, nicknamed "Pinky", liberated the planet from Shoto Eyefire, a Defel crime lord and blastfighter. Horn Station was the homeworld of a species of hulking, green-skinned, reptilian humanoids.

properties.name: Horob
properties.description: Horob was a planet with an Rebel Alliance research lab discovered by the Galactic Empire. The planet was taken by the Victory-class Star Destroyer Imperial Hazard.

properties.name: Horos
properties.description: Horos was a planet located in the Lambda sector of the Mid Rim.

properties.name: Horska
properties.description: Horska was a planet in the Colonies. It was location of an Imperial Remnant HoloNet relay station.

properties.name: Horthav
properties.description: Horthav was a planet located in the Kuat sector of the Core Worlds.

properties.name: Horuz
properties.description: Horuz was a planet located in the galaxy's Outer Rim Territories. Shortly before the Battle of Scarif, Imperial forces were deployed to Horuz. In the lead-up to the Battle of Jakku in 5 ABY, Horuz was reportedly to still be in the thrall of some Imperial remnant or criminal syndicates or gangs.

properties.name: Hosko
properties.description: Hosko was an agricultural planet located in Hutt Space. During the Hutt Cataclysms, the factions of the Hutt Empire fought a battle on Hosko with ancient weapons and battle droids. It was orbited by a space station frequented by traders and smugglers.

properties.name: Hosrel
properties.description: Hosrel was the Hosrel system's primary star, located within the Outer Rim Territories of the galaxy.

properties.name: Hoszh Iszhir
properties.description: Hoszh Iszhir was the homeworld of the Gektl species. Half of the planet was covered in waterless deserts, while the other half was shrouded in a poisonous atmosphere. There were rich lodes of guerrerite on planet, forcing the Gektl to build planetary defenses. It wasn't until Stafuv Rahz traded the shield codes to the Galactic Empire that the planet was subjugated.

properties.name: Hoth
properties.poi: Abandoned Rebel Base, Echo Base, Moorsh Moraine, Clabburn Range, Cirque Glacier, Hanging Valley, North RidgeMount Ison, Lanteel Glacier, Nev Ice Flow, Kerane Valley, South Ridge, Ceyan Range, Outpost BetaWampa Valley, Dorn Base, Drift Hills Imperial Outpost, Rakata monument, Sadow'een Temple, Hoth Star Fortress, Highmount Ridge,
properties.description: Hoth was the sixth planet of the remote Hoth system. A desolate world covered with ice and snow, located in the Anoat sector, a rarely-traveled portion of the Outer Rim Territories, it became famous as the one-time location of the Alliance to Restore the Republic's Echo Base during the Galactic Civil War. The base was discovered by the Empire in 3 ABY, precipitating the Battle of Hoth, a major engagement during which the Rebels suffered heavy casualties and lost Echo Base.

properties.name: Houche
properties.description: Houche was a planet in the Zuma sector, which surrounded the Moddell sector. Houche was an endpoint of the Annaj-Houche Run.

properties.name: Hoven
properties.description: Hoven was a planet located in the Inner Rim.

properties.name: Hoylin
properties.description: Hoylin was a world located in the Hoylin system, a part of the Fei Hu sector in the Slice portion of the Mid Rim. It was situated on the Gamor Run hyperlane, which connected it to the Aikhibba and Beris systems.

properties.name: Hraki
properties.description: Hraki was a planet in the Vorzyd Cluster of the Outer Rim.

properties.name: Hrasskis
properties.description: Hrasskis were a sentient race from the planet of Hrasskis. They were distinguished by large, veined air sacs on their backs; they were represented in the New Republic Senate by the belligerent Senator Cian Marook.

properties.name: Hrill
properties.description: Hrill was a planet reputed to be peaceful, quiet, and dull. In 15 BBY, the merchant Mungo Baobab was assigned a mission to Hrill by the Merchant Council of his homeworld, Manda. Nevertheless, Baobab ignored the order and ventured off in search of the Roon system and its fabled Roonstones. He brought the droids R2-D2 and C-3PO with him.

properties.name: Hrthging
properties.description: Hrthging was a planet in the Hrthging system of Mandalore sector in the Outer Rim. It was home to the Hrthgingian Firegem. It became part of Mandalorian Space.

properties.name: Huk
properties.description: Huk was the home planet of the Yam'rii species, also known as the Huk . The planet was mostly covered with dense forests.

properties.name: Huldamun
properties.description: Huldamun was an industrialized planet in the Arkanis sector of the Outer Rim. It was one of the Regency Worlds.

properties.name: Hull's Star
properties.description: The Hull's Star system was a part of the Wild Space region of Farana. The star system, which contained no planets, was connected by the Tertiary Etti Route hyperlane to the Farana and Mytus systems, and its only significance was due to it being a jumping-off point for the Stars' End prison, which was located on a planetoid within the Mytus system.

properties.name: Huloon
properties.description: Huloon was a planet located in the Huloon system within Bootana Hutta near the center of Hutt Space. A part of Hutt Space, it was formerly the home to a slave species also called Huloons before it was depopulated by the Hutts and turned into a nature preserve. After the massacre, pockets of Huloons resided in systems near their homeworld and yearned to return, but they would often suffer ridicule and torment at the hands of the Hutts.

properties.name: Humbarine
properties.description: Humbarine was an ecumenopolis located in the Core Worlds region of the galaxy. The capital of the heavily-industrialized Humbarine sector, the planet Humbarine was a promising hub of commerce as early as 25,000 BBY, when it became a founding member of the Galactic Republic. Prior to the outbreak of the Clone Wars in 22 BBY, the world was largely unaffected by galactic conflicts but nonetheless possessed a sector fleet of large warships for defense.

properties.name: Hurd's Moon
properties.description: Hurd's Moon was a desert world to where Guri traveled in order to be reprogrammed following the Battle of Endor. Massad Thrumble owned a cantina on Hurd's Moon, drawing the Human replica droid, Guri, there for a chance at reprogramming.

properties.name: Hurikane
properties.description: Hurikane was a planet located in Wild Space. It was inhabited by a species of sentient beings made of stone and purple Hurrikaine crystals, who were almost insectoid in appearance.

properties.name: Huro
properties.description: Huro was a planet in Ciutric sector of the Outer Rim Territories.

properties.name: Hurrim
properties.description: The Hurrim were an Outer Rim based pirating group, led by Golov Nakhym, which had a mutual agreement with Dunari and the Rebellion in 3 ABY until an incident in the Nezni system.

properties.name: Hutlar
properties.description: Hutlar was a small, chilly world located in the Mid Rim's Senex sector. Orbiting a red dwarf star, it was the homeworld of the sentient Hutlarians. They served the aristocratic Ancient Houses of the Senex-Juvex region in various roles until 553 BBY, when their home was liberated from the nobles' control.

properties.name: Huulia
properties.description: Huulia was a planet located in the Huulia system in the Colonies. It was the homeworld of Kit Valent, and produced starfighters.

properties.name: Hyabb
properties.description: Hyabb was a planet in the Core Worlds' Krenher sector. It lay on the Hyabb-Twith Corridor hyperlane, which connected it to the planet Twith. Hyabb and Twith were engaged in a continuous war lasting nearly since the foundation of the Galactic Republic and were both members of the Republic by 17,000 BBY. During the Alsakan Conflicts, Hyabb remained loyal to the world of Coruscant in its struggle against the planet Alsakan, with which Twith had allied itself.

properties.name: Hyder
properties.description: Hyder was a planet. The New Republic agent Trask Lucan was born there

properties.name: Hydra
properties.description: Hydra may refer to:

properties.name: Hynah
properties.description: Hynah was an industrial world located in the Kalamith sector of the Outer Rim Territories, on the Hydian Way hyperlane. It was home to the Hynese, a cosmopolitan population of various different species. Prior to the evacuation of the Rebel Alliance's Yavin system base, Rebel scouts charted an escape hyperlane leading from the Feswe Corridor star system to Hynah.

properties.name: Hypori
properties.description: Hypori  was a planet located in the Hypori system of the Ferra sector in the Outer Rim Territories. It was home to no sentient species, though it was host to windrails and massiffs. Its surface was covered in rocky landscapes and small oceans.

properties.name: Hypotria
properties.description: Hypotria was a planet located in the Bortele sector of the Mid Rim. The droid R2z-DL was stationed there.

properties.name: Hyrol Preen Beta
properties.description: Hyrol Preen Beta was a planet in the Outer Rim. Its populace was wiped out by Imperial Storm commandos and ZQ infantry droids because of suspected Rebel activity. A spacer, Johin, brought news of the devastation.

properties.name: Hysalria
properties.description: The Hysalria system was a star system located within the Sluis sector in the Outer Rim Territories of the galaxy.

properties.name: Ibanjji
properties.description: Ibanjji was a terrestrial world located in the Ibanjji system, a part of the Mieru'kar sector in the New Territories portion of the Outer Rim Territories. The conditions on Ibanjji were harsh, and it was home to packs of creatures known as varns. During the reign of the Galactic Empire, it was the site of a special motivational camp used to harden Imperial recruits.

properties.name: Ichalin Station
properties.description: Ichalin Station was a space station situated in the Expansion Region's Hijoian Space. In an example described in the Bounty Hunters Guild Handbook, a Glottalphib pyromaniac smuggled a flamethrower through Ichalin Station customs, earning himself a bounty posting. Around 2 ABY, the Ho'Din terrorist Yansan sabotaged a Rebel Alliance starship present in Ichalin Station, leading to the capture and death of the Rebel agents attempting to pilot the crippled vessel.

properties.name: Ichtor
properties.description: Ichtor 8 was a planet in the Ichtor system that was the site on an Imperial resort for wealthy Humans. The planet was very icy and also had abundant natural resources. The planet also contained a ski resort on Mount Quavaar. The stohl creature, a popular guard pet, was native to Ichtor 8. The species was first discovered by Imperial scouts. Hunters were soon enamored of the inquisitive creatures, and the creatures were exported at a high price. Holovid star Shantee Ree made attack stohls fashionable. When her pet attack stohl Needla bit a fan wanting an autograph, the resulting media coverage made the attack stohl a popular target for daredevil hunters. Ree then started a Save the Stohl campaign.

properties.name: Idolia
properties.description: The Idolia system was a star system located within the Halthor sector in the Outer Rim Territories of the galaxy. It was the place of origin of the Idolian fever.

properties.name: Iego
properties.poi: The Boneyard, The Choir Alignment, Rawk's Nest, The Scatter,
properties.description: Iego, named the Planet of a Thousand Moons, was a planet located in the Extrictarium Nebula in the Outer Rim Territories. Due to the obscurity of the Nebula, Iego did not appear on any star-charts. Iego did not orbit a sun; rather, it was warmed by local stellar gases. It was home to the subterranean Maelibi species, as well as thousands of stranded spacefarers who had been lured to the planet by the Diathim—a spaceworthy species that resided on Iego's forty-two moons. Although Iego appeared to have no noteworthy natural resources, the concepts of aging and hunger somehow eluded its residents.

properties.name: Ifron
properties.description: Ifron was a planet located in the Thuris sector of the Outer Rim. Mara Jade visited the seedy Bovris Tapcafe on Ifron during her search for Dequc.

properties.name: Ihopek
properties.description: Ihopek was a planet evacuated by Imperials after the Battle of Endor, along with Narth. While they were being evacuated, the Star Destroyer Gnisnal was demolished by internal explosions. This provided enormous amounts of information to the New Republic, giving them a complete copy of the Imperial Order of battle.

properties.name: Ikon
properties.description: Ikon was a red dwarf star in the Ikon system of the Majoor sector, located within the Trailing Sectors portion of the Expansion Region. It was orbited by an asteroid belt, where Rebel Alliance sympathizers had gained a foothold under the nose of the Galactic Empire in the aftermath of the Battle of Yavin.

properties.name: Iktotchon
properties.description: Iktotchon, or Iktotchan, was a gas giant in the Iktotch system. Its moons included Iktotch.

properties.name: Ilamna
properties.description: Ilamna was an astronomical object located in the star system of the same name, which was a part of the Eucer sector of the Mid Rim. The celestial body was situated in the region known as the Divide during the Tionese War, fought between the Galactic Republic and the Honorable Union of Desevro & Tion. During that time, Ilamna had been settled by Republic colonists.

properties.name: Iliabath
properties.description: Iliabath was a planet located in the Mortex sector of the Outer Rim Territories.

properties.name: Ilimardon
properties.description: Ilimardon was a planet located in the Mid Rim's Nicandra sector. It was governed by the Regal Hierarchy, which maintained a wildlife division and a fleet of starships. When the Regal Hierarchy became interested in the use of domesticated mynocks as weapons against starships, it employed the Human Gres Ople, former mynock trainer of the Trandoshan pirate Chorssk's organization, to train a new flock of the creatures. By 12 ABY, Ilimardon was a member of the New Republic.

properties.name: Illarreen
properties.description: Illarreen was a planet discovered in 100 BBY. It joined the galactic community in 90 BBY.

properties.name: Illodia
properties.description: Illodia was the sector capital of Illodia sector and home to the Illodian culture of Humans. The Illodians colonized 20 planets in Illodia sector.

properties.name: Ilos
properties.description: Ilos was a bland agricultural world that was located within the Ilos system of the galaxy's Hutt Space region and lay on the hyperlane called the Pabol Sleheyron, which connected it to the planets of Chalacta and Ilos Minor.

properties.name: Ilos Minor
properties.description: Ilos Minor was a planet that was located within the Ilos Minor system of the galaxy's Hutt Space region and lay on the hyperlane called the Pabol Sleheyron, which connected it to the planets of Ilos and Nar Kreeta. Another hyperspace route called the Ilosian Spur linked Ilos Minor to the world of Tal Nami. Ilos Minor was colonized by the sentient Ilosian species and served as a transfer point for goods that were transported from the planets of the Ilosian Spur.

properties.name: Ilum
properties.poi: Fray Landing Base, Holenesh Canyon, Imperial Firebase 3, Emperor's Fortress, Ilum Temple, Icefall Cavern, The Circle, Cross-Shelf Corridor, Crystal Caves, Republic Recon Post, Snowdrift Cave, Western Ice Shelf,
properties.description: Ilum was an ice planet in the Unknown Regions, one of the main sources of the valuable Adegan crystals used in the construction of Jedi lightsabers. The caverns containing the crystals were long ago turned into a Jedi temple. Unlike the crystals of other planets, the crystals of Ilum were limited to blue, green and purple in color. The planet was over ninety percent-covered by ice.

properties.name: Imdaar
properties.description: Imdaar was a planet in the Dreighton Nebula with surface features reminiscent of Dagobah. It was the base of the TIE Phantom project, in which the production facility was located on Imdaar Alpha.

properties.name: Imerria
properties.description: Imerria was a world located in the Expansion Region that was known for its windstorms.

properties.name: Immalia
properties.description: Immalia was an Expansion Region celestial body located in the Immalia sector, home to the Humans known as Immalians. During the Waymancy Storm, the Signatories of Waymancy carried out an orbital bombardment of Immalia, which was halted by the Galactic Republic via the use of the experimental cannonship Squintpipe.

properties.name: Imram
properties.description: Imram was a Mid Rim world located within Lannik Space. During the Kymoodon Era, Galactic Republic colonists settled Imram, which members of the Hutt species viewed as an act of war.

properties.name: Imynusoph
properties.description: Imynusoph was an Outer Rim Territories world that, according to the opera The Kallea Cycle, was the site of rumored treasures around 3694 BBY, when the hyperspace scout Freia Kallea charted the final segment of the super-hyperroute that would become known as the Hydian Way. In the opera, Imynusoph was the homeworld of the peaceful Imyni species.

properties.name: Inat Prime
properties.description: Inat Prime was a planet in the Outer Rim's Quiberon sector. Boba Fett had microscopic subdermal trackers placed on Rivo Xarran on Inat Prime.

properties.name: Indellian
properties.description: Indellian was a low-gravity planetoid that served as a trade world, manufacturing hub, and government center for the Yarith sector in the Outer Rim Territories. It was originally settled by the Galactic Republic centuries prior to the Galactic Civil War as commerce developed around the Corellian Trade Spine in the Outer Rim's Greater Javin region. Indellian's placement along the zigzagging border between the Yarith and Anoat sectors was part of an intentional Republic effort to cut off neighboring worlds and check local political power.

properties.name: Indoumodo
properties.description: A terrestrial planet located in the Indoumodo system of Wild Space, Indoumodo was a lush world with jungles and forests that were home to kouhuns, poisonous arthropods that dwelled in damp caves and passages underground. The creatures were also known to dwell in vast, hollow trees and hunted dog-sized creatures that lived in the trees' crevices. Located near the end of the Corellian Run, Indoumodo was a destination for assassins and poisoners who would venture to capture the kouhuns for use as untraceable killers.

properties.name: Indu San
properties.description: Indu San was an Outer Rim Territories planet in the Indu San system inhabited by Humans. It was part of the Galactic Republic.

properties.name: Indupar
properties.description: Indupar was a Mid Rim world in Ado sector. It was the capital of the Induparan Crown Worlds. It was ruled by the Induparan Monarchy and House Indupar, including King Dahon Indupar during the New Order. During the Clone Wars, Indupar was located within Separatist space. The Imperial Governor of the Induparan Crown Worlds was Mirash Peet. Imperial Commodore Soleric commanded the 16th Escort Force, escorting merchant convoys through the Induparan to protect them from the Free Lance.

properties.name: Ingo
properties.poi: Ingo speeder shopJarl forestVaj DesertTig Fromm's base
properties.description: Ingo was a backwater Mid Rim world in the Bortele sector.

properties.name: Injopan
properties.description: Injopan was a planet. The One Two Many once visited there, before departing for the Maw.

properties.name: Intran
properties.description: Intran was an uninhabited planet in the Intran system of the Brak sector. An Alliance to Restore the Republic military base was established on the planet shortly before the Battle of Yavin. The base housed a squadron of BTL Y-wing starfighters.

properties.name: Intuci
properties.description: Intuci was a planet in the Abrion sector of the Outer Rim Territories under the control of the Galactic Empire.

properties.name: Inysh
properties.description: Inysh was a Core Worlds planet that was home to the Abinyshi. A sentient, passive species of reptilians, the natives of Inysh were among the first species to achieve space travel, although their interstellar colonization was limited. The Galactic Empire eventually discovered the planet had vast reserves of the kalonterium ore and proceeded to strip-mine the world.

properties.name: Iol
properties.description: Iol was a lifeless planet in the Unknown Regions.

properties.name: Ione
properties.description: Ione was a thriving spaceport world lying along the Corellian Trade Spine in the Anoat sector of the Outer Rim Territories. Originally settled by the Galactic Republic centuries before the Galactic Civil War, Ione occupied a key intersection on the Trade Spine that made it the sole hyperspace link to the Greater Javin region's four Mining Worlds.

properties.name: Iope
properties.description: Iope was the third moon of the planet Rinn, in the Baxel sector. It was here that the assassin X-7 hired a team of mercenary pilots to hunt down and kill Luke Skywalker.

properties.name: Iotra
properties.description: Iotra was the fifth planet in the Iotran system and the temperate, industrial homeworld to the militant Iotran species. The planet was ruled by the Joint Council, eight top-ranking leaders of the Iotran Police Force .

properties.name: Iphar
properties.description: The Iphar system was a star system that was located in the Inner Rim.

properties.name: Iphigin
properties.description: Iphigin was a planet in the Iphigin system of the Core Worlds and the homeworld of the Iphigini species.

properties.name: Iridia
properties.description: Iridia was a Zabrak colony-world. It was the home of Donloor and Oorn Noth.

properties.name: Iridium
properties.description: Iridium was a planet in the Atrivis sector of the Outer Rim Territories. It was home to the infamous Pirates of Iridium, who utilized Iridium "power gems" to disable the shields of their victims' starships, raiding Atrivis space lanes for a year. However, a task force of Jedi and Galactic Republic Judicials routed the pirates in a battle over Vuchelle in 22 BBY.

properties.name: Iridonia
properties.poi: Capital Square, Laboratory of Drell Kahmf, Sith Academy,
properties.description: Iridonia was the homeworld of the Zabrak species. Due to the harsh living conditions, the Zabrak were a hardy species. They took to flight and then space travel as soon as they could develop the technology, and by the time the Duros encountered them, they had already colonized five systems. Notable Iridonians included Agen Kolar, Bao-Dur, Drell Kahmf, Sirak, and Maris Brood.

properties.name: Irith
properties.description: Irith was a polluted, motley and overcrowded planet located in the Irith system of Hutt Space, a region of the galaxy controlled by the Hutt species. The world was a stop on the Ootmian Pabol, a hyperlane that ran through the Hutt controlled area and connected Irith to the planets Du Hutta abd Nar Bo Sholla. Irith was the homeworld of the criminal Romort Raort, and while growing up there he acted as a bully, stealing other childrens' lunch money.

properties.name: Irmenu
properties.description: Irmenu was an oceanic planet located in the the fringes of the Crombach Nebula, in the Belsmuth sector of the Outer Rim Territories. Isolated from the rest of the galaxy for millennia, it was a feudal world known for its seafaring and stern religious traditions.

properties.name: Iscera
properties.description: Iscera was an Outer Rim planet near Issor and Nysza III. Fable Astin saw Jaalib Brandl perform in a play on this planet. Iscera was a dry planet lacking any legal establishments that sold alcohol.

properties.name: Iseno
properties.description: Iseno was a planet in the Inner Rim, on the Corellian Run. Its people had a strong military tradition and maintained a large army mostly used for ornamental honor guard purposes.

properties.name: Isde Naha
properties.description: Isde Naha was the capital of the Yarith sector of the Greater Javin region.

properties.name: Isen
properties.description: Isen was a young gas giant and the sole planet in the Isen system. Its five moons included Isen IV.

properties.name: Iseno
properties.description: Iseno was a planet in the Inner Rim, on the Corellian Run. Its people had a strong military tradition and maintained a large army mostly used for ornamental honor guard purposes.

properties.name: Ishanna
properties.description: Ishanna was a location where the Ishanna inversion occurred, which hampered the performance of the rebel starship Nautilian.

properties.name: Isht
properties.description: Isht was the Ishori homeworld. It was directly represented in the New Republic Senate.

properties.name: Isiring
properties.description: Isiring was an Outer Rim Territories world located in the Cassander sector. An ore-rich mining world, Isiring became a part of the domain known as the Cassandran Worlds, founded by the former businessman Cassander Tadrin during the reign of the Galactic Republic. When the Galactic Empire later divided the domain into subsectors, Isiring became the capital of the Tendrannan sector. The world was subsequently a part of the Pentastar Alignment and the Imperial Remnant.

properties.name: Isis
properties.description: Isis was a terrestrial planet in the Anoat sector of the Outer Rim Territories. The homeworld of the Gutretee, it was a secret Rebel Alliance safe world during the Galactic Civil War, and later became one of the Mining Worlds under the control of the Figg conglomerate.

properties.name: Iska
properties.description: The Iska system was located in the Iska sector of the Mid Rim. It was the origin point of Iska pirates. In 17 BBY, the system fell within the territory held by Separatist holdouts.

properties.name: Iskallon
properties.description: The Iskalloni, or Iskallons, were a sentient species of short, blue-skinned, humanoid cyborgs indigenous to the Wild Space planet of Iskadrell. Possessing a physiology that allowed their bodies to integrate foreign matter, the Iskalloni experimented with cybernetic implants, sometimes replacing entire limbs with prosthetics. An isolated civilization with a technological base fusing biotechnology with mechanical devices, they rarely came into contact with the rest of the galaxy. Since their technology produced deadly toxic waste and they did not want to risk their own lives processing it, the Iskalloni resorted to slaving raids on other species, whom they transformed into cyborgs and forced to work with the dangerous waste. Viewing Humans as inferior, the cyborgs were intent to enslave them in particular. Unable to develop safer technology by themselves, the Iskalloni also studied captured Human starships in the hopes of finding a way to build machinery that would not be so deadly to operate.

properties.name: Iskalon
properties.description: Iskalon was a planet in the Mid Rim.

properties.name: Ison
properties.description: Ison was a cold, desolate planet in the Ison system, and little more than an obscure waypoint on the dangerous Ison Corridor.

properties.name: Issagra
properties.description: Issagra was a planet in the Issagra system. It was located approximately twelve hours hyperspace travel from Fether. Its most notable location was a large space station. Over three kilometers long, the station was devoted to trade and gambling, and could house tens of thousands of visitors and hundreds of freighters at a time. The station's atmosphere was often regarded as grand and exotic, though organized crime held sway in the background and contraband could be found in numerous locations.

properties.name: Issor
properties.description: Issor was the most powerful planet in the Trulalis system, and the homeworld of the Issori and Odenji.

properties.name: Italbos
properties.description: Italbos was a planet located in the Mid Rim that had been discovered circa 3963 BBY. The rights for it were about to be sold by the Metellos Exchange on the auction, when Marn Hierogryph, Jarael and Rohlan Dyre had tried to run a con there, claiming that a native of Italbos was there to claim their share of money from the deal. After Gryph dealt with Nunk Plaarvin, Zayne Carrick told the people at the auction that Italbos was presumably inhabitable, and that weren't any confirmed mineral riches, but the rights to the planet had been sold anyway.

properties.name: Itani
properties.description: Itani may refer to:

properties.name: Ithor
properties.poi: Tafanda Bay Falls of DessiarMother JungleHouse of the HealersCathor Hills
properties.description: Ithor was the fourth planet located in Ottega system of the Mid Rim. One of the oldest members of the Galactic Republic, it was a planet full of lush life, and the planet's surface had not a touch of civilization on it. The Ithorians themselves, otherwise known as "Hammerheads," built great floating cities that did not harm the surface, which they considered to be sacred. Entry upon the surface was forbidden, unless one stayed there permanently. Some Ithorians such as the Oracle were compelled to go down to the planet surface, however, as they "heard the call" of Mother Jungle, the Ithorian religion's personification of Ithor's world-spanning jungle. The surface of the planet of Ithor played host to numerous plants, including the bafforr tree, which possessed telepathic capabilities. The planet contained andurite stone, and every three Ithorian years was the center of the Time of Meeting. The planet had many moons in its night sky.

properties.name: Ithull
properties.description: Ithull was the gigantic homeworld of the Ithullans and the colossus wasps. The Ithullans were almost wiped out by the Mandalorians in the year 200 BBY.

properties.name: Ivatch
properties.description: Ivatch was a planet within the Kathol sector's Ivatch system, located within the Outer Rim Territories. Connected to the neighboring planets of Shintel and Peirs by hyperlanes, Ivatch supported a small colony whose economy was based around supplying ore and natural resources to Gandle Ott.

properties.name: Ividal
properties.description: Ividal was an astronomical object located in the Ividal system, a part of the Slice portion of the Mid Rim. During the Clone Wars, the Foxfire Squadron, a unit of the Ividal Sector Forces equipped with Z-95 Headhunter starfighters, was stationed at Ividal.

properties.name: Ixtlar
properties.description: Ixtlar was a planet in the Ixtlar system on of the Core Worlds, situated on the Corellian Run in the Ixtlar sector. It was covered in holographic advertisement signs. Almost any merchandise could be found on Ixtlar. In 20 BBY, it was the site of the Battle of Ixtlar. It was conquered by the Yuuzhan Vong, but the Yuuzhan Vong were driven out of the Core after the fall of Yuuzhan'tar.

properties.name: Iyred
properties.description: Iyred was a planet in the Kibilini sector of the Outer Rim Territories.

properties.name: Iyuta
properties.description: Iyuta was a planet with an Imperial Communications Center located near the city of Takari.

properties.name: J't'p'tan
properties.description: An almost untouched world in the Koornacht Cluster, J't'p'tan  was settled by the H'kig, fleeing a conflict on Rishi.
