The planet was named after four sacred glyphs: "Jeh" , "Teh" , "Peh" , and "Tan" . Only the last of these glyphs was considered secular enough to be spelled out fully.

properties.name: Jabiim
properties.poi: Shelter BaseMonsoon MesaCobalt StationRazor CoastJobreth PlainsHyber CanyonHigh Rock Canyon
properties.description: Jabiim  was a small, muddy, Outer Rim world. It was most notably the site of three fierce Battles of Jabiim.

properties.name: Jabor
properties.description: Jabor was a planet where Ferus Olin worked for the Galactic Republic during the Clone Wars. Ferus sent double agent Clive Flax undercover into the local Separatist base, thus disrupting a spy ring that had taken root throughout the Mid Rim. Its subsequent destruction saved many lives.

properties.name: Jaciprus
properties.description: The Jaciprus system was located in the Arrowhead, a region in the Slice portion of the Core Worlds. It was situated on the super-hyperroute known as the Hydian Way, between the Bellassa and Voktunma systems, and was home to the sentient species known as the Jacipri.

properties.name: Jaemus
properties.description: Jaemus was a planet with Galentro Heavy Works shipyards comparable in size to Sluis Van.

properties.name: Jafan
properties.description: Jafan was a general and eventual king of the Royal House of the planet Naboo. During the Time of Suffering, a roughly two-century-long civil war between Naboo city-states, General Jafan united the factions through force of will and military strength, ushering in the Great Time of Peace, a golden age for Naboo.

properties.name: Jaga's Cluster
properties.description: Jaga's Cluster, also known as the Jaga's Cluster System or the Jagomir System, was a star cluster in the Esstran sector of the Outer Rim Territories.

properties.name: Jaguada
properties.description: Jaguada was a desert planet and the only inhabited world of the Jaguada system, located in the Sith Worlds region of the Outer Rim Territories' Esstran sector. It orbited a star and had one moon. A colony world of the Sith species that was settled around 27,700 BBY, Jaguada remained a part of both the ancient Sith Empire and the old Sith Empire. By 533 BBY, it was the site of a bastion constructed by the Sith Master Darth Gravid and his apprentice, Darth Gean. Around that year, they fought a duel there that cost Gravid his life.

properties.name: Jakelia
properties.description: Jakelia was a planet in the Jakelia system, located within the region of the galaxy known as the Outer Rim Territories, at the galactic grid coordinates O-7. The homeworld of the Jakelian race, the planet Jakelia became a target of the Mandalorian Crusaders during their era of conquest. Rather than war against the Mandalorians, however, the Jakelians welcomed the Taung warriors and Jakelia willing became a Mandalorian world, one of the first to comprise Mandalorian space.

properties.name: Jalarren
properties.description: Jalarran was a planet in the Senex sector of the Mid Rim.

properties.name: Jaminere
properties.description: Jaminere was a planet located in the Tion Cluster of the Outer Rim Territories, along the Cadinth Run. A powerful manufacturing world known for its efficiency, Jaminere was the capital of the Allied Tion sector.

properties.name: Jamiron
properties.description: Jamiron was a Chiss Ascendancy planet in the Jamiron system of the Unknown Regions. The surface of Jamiron was barren, but its porous crust contained hydroponic agricultural facilities.

properties.name: Janako
properties.description: The Janako was a model of MaKing-class transport built under a local license from General Spacetronics.

properties.name: Janara
properties.description: Janara can refer to:

properties.name: Jandoon
properties.description:
Jandoon was a planet in the Outer Rim Territories, in the Corva sector.
It was said to be a haunted world. It was home to the ancient ruins of a civilization that disappeared.

properties.name: Jandur
properties.description: Jandur was a planet in the Inner Rim and was represented in the New Republic Senate.

properties.name: JanFathal
properties.description: JanFathal was a planet in the Outer Rim Territories and was once part of the Republic. The city of Athar was its capital.

properties.name: Jangelle
properties.description: Jangelle was a planet in the Kathol sector. A temperate world of sandy lowlands, it was crossed with many interlinking rivers, streams and deltas, although it had few large bodies of water.

properties.name: Janguine
properties.description: Janguine was a jungle planet in the Outer Rim. Its natives spoke Janguine and were overrun by the Mooloolians around 275 BBY.

properties.name: Jankok
properties.description: Jankok was a warm planet, and the homeworld of the Srrors'tok

properties.name: Janodral Mizar
properties.description: Janodral Mizar was a planet in Outer Rim Territories in the Indrexu sector.

properties.name: Jante
properties.description: Jante was a planet in the Jante system, near Freda.

properties.name: Jappe
properties.description: Jappe was a planet located in the Tapani sector's Jappe system. It was a smugglers' haven.

properties.name: Jaresh
properties.description: Jaresh was a remote rainforest moon in the Jaresh system in Corva sector of the Outer Rim. Its indigenous trees grew hundreds of meters in height. Its local day lasted 29 standard hours, and its local year lasted 98 local days. The Twi'lek Ree Shala purchased Jaresh as a smuggling base.

properties.name: Jarnollen
properties.description: Jarnollen was a planet in close proximity to Ord Mantell in the Mid Rim. It was covered in tropical jungle, and its trees possessed overgrown vines.

properties.name: Jarsatt
properties.description: Jarsatt was a planet located in the Hakartha sector of the Expansion Region.

properties.name: Jarvanam
properties.description: Jarvanam was a planet located within the star system of the same name, a part of the Outer Rim Territories' Astal sector. Around the year 10 ABY, it served as the homeworld of the Baradis School of Technology, a covert criminal training organization and member of the Tenloss Syndicate.

properties.name: Jatir
properties.description: Jatir was a planet in the Jatir system within the Colonies. It was one endpoint of the Corulag-Jatir Hyperroute, which was plied by Trade Federation freighters.

properties.name: Javin
properties.description: Javin was the capital and namesake of Javin sector and the subsequent Greater Javin Region, along the Corellian Trade Spine.

properties.name: Javis
properties.description: Javis was a planet in located in the Tapani sector's Javis system.

properties.name: Jaxus
properties.description: Jaxus was a planet that supported life despite orbiting closely to its sun.

properties.name: Jazbina
properties.description: Jazbina was a planet with luxurious aromatic baths and sun crystals.

properties.name: Jebble
properties.poi: Ice Citadel, Jebble Data Center, Pulsipher's laboratory,
properties.description: Jebble was a frozen world located in the Ojoster sector of the Outer Rim. A target for ice miners, Jebble served as a resource world for the nearby ecumenopolis of Taris, and fell under threat when the Mandalorian Neo-Crusader hordes began encroaching upon Taris in the early weeks of their war with the Galactic Republic. When the Mandalorians finally struck, they swiftly captured Jebble and turned it into one of their main Outer Rim staging points, the place where the Mandalorians gathered thousands of local recruits for a planned raid on Alderaan. However, that army met with disaster in 3963 BBY: after the Mandalorian scientist Pulsipher brought a mysterious Sith artifact known as the Muur Talisman back to Jebble, the Talisman's dark influence turned nearly the entire population of Mandalorians into monstrous, mutated rakghoul beasts. Mandalorian Field Marshal Cassus Fett elected to deal with the problem by obliterating Jebble's surface with a massive salvo of nuclear bombs, wiping out all life on the planet and drastically altering Jebble's ecosystem. The only survivor of the blasts was the current holder of the Talisman, Jedi Shadow Celeste Morne, safely ensconced in the life-preserving stasis chamber called Dreypa's Oubliette—by the time Jebble had regained its icy landscape, the capsule was unearthed and the "Jebble Box" became an object of intense intrigue around the galaxy for years.

properties.name: Jendar
properties.description: Jendar was a planet located in the Nembus sector of the Outer Rim Territories. During the Galactic Civil War, it was the site of a campaign between the forces of the Rebel Alliance and the Galactic Empire for the control of the planet.

properties.name: Jendorn
properties.description: Jendorn was an Expansion Region planet located in the Farstey sector. It was situated in the Borderland Regions, an area over which the confederation led by Imperial Grand Admiral Thrawn had control. In 9 ABY, a fierce battle was fought at Jendorn between the Imperial and New Republic forces, in which the Empire was victorious.

properties.name: Jenenma
properties.description: Jenenma was a planet with many starshipwrights. The Hutt's Last Laugh cantina was on the planet, as was the headquarters of a syndicate run by Pal-Nada, a Cerean Force adept.

properties.name: Jerijador
properties.description: Jerijador, located in the Calaron sector of the Outer Rim Territories, was a planet teeming with a variety of lifeforms that was hospitable to humanoids. In the aftermath of the Battle of Yavin, a fleet of Imperial warships led by Moff Vensell staged at Jerijador in preparation for an assault on the Rebel Alliance. This attracted many scavengers who came to salvage the junk that the departing Imperial vessels left behind upon entering hyperspace.

properties.name: Jermac
properties.description: Jermac was a world located in the Portmoak sector of the Outer Rim. Located along the Llanic Spice Run, Jermac was a notable spice producer.

properties.name: Jerne
properties.description: Jerne was the Jerni homeworld, until their extinction. It was later home to Human colonists who exhausted its natural resources. During the Galactic Civil War, it was home to an Imperial base.

properties.name: Jerrilek
properties.description: Jerrilek was a tropical vacation world in the Jerrilek system.

properties.name: Jestan
properties.description: Jestan was a planet located in the Corpheli sector of the Expansion Region.

properties.name: Jevelet
properties.description: Jevelet was a planet located in the Core of the galaxy that housed a prison/mental facility.

properties.name: Jeyell
properties.description: Jeyell was a Mid Rim planet located in the Roche sector, on the Perlemian Trade Route hyperlane. It housed the headquarters of Reiber Manufacturing, a company that manufactured assassin droid components until it was nationalized by the Galactic Empire on 36:4:20.

properties.name: Jhantoria
properties.description: Jhantoria was a planet located in the Allied Tion sector.

properties.name: Jhensrus
properties.description: Jhensrus was a jungle frontier world in the Trax sector. The inhabitants of the planet were often confronted by the native creatures, hence a population of fighters and survivors was shaped.

properties.name: Jiaan
properties.description: During the early years of the New Order, Jiaan was one of many planets which were subjugated and decimated by Imperial forces. Tyneir Renz was a native of this planet.

properties.name: Jidlor
properties.description: The Jidlor system was located in the Jidlor Marches, a part of the Mid Rim. The system was home to the sentient Swaze species. Each standard year, the rulers of the Swaze were sent to Rellnas Minor, a moon in the Expansion Region's Rell system. There, the Swaze rulers sought advice from the un'Yala, chiefs of the indigenous Rellarin species who were widely known for their wisdom.

properties.name: Jilrua
properties.description: Jilrua was a desert planet that orbited a blue giant star within the Jilrua system of the galaxy's Hutt Space region, in the immediate vicinity of the Oktos Nebula.

properties.name: Jinda
properties.description: The Jindas were a bipedal sentient species who were herbivorous and could be easily recognized by their characteristic pom-pom tufts of hair and the markings which covered their bodies. Jindas were noted for their energetic nature and desire to entertain others with their natural performing skills which included juggling, magic, dancing, music, and storytelling. However, the species suffered from a poor long-term memory and sense of direction which gave them a reputation for getting lost.

properties.name: Jinet
properties.description: Jinet was an uninhabited planet in the Jinet system of the Brak sector. The Alliance to Restore the Republic established a starfighter base on the planet shortly before the Battle of Yavin. The base was home to a squadron of BTL Y-wing starfighters.

properties.name: Jiroch
properties.description: Jiroch was an astronomical object located in the galaxy's Mid Rim on the Corellian Trade Spine.

properties.name: Jodaka
properties.description: Jodaka was a planet of the Jodaka system, within the Corsair Outback area in the Hapes Cluster, a remote region on the Inner Rim of the galaxy. The vast saltwater seas of Jodaka were home to many strange yet deadly creatures, including the Jodakan needler crab, a deceptive and dangerous crustacean non-sentient species. The planet's surface was also composed of many rocky reefs, which the Needler crabs would hop on and use their poisonous projectile needles to take down gulls—a seabird species also native to Jodaka—or to be preyed upon by the birds instead. As with most worlds within the Hapes Cluster, Jodaka was part of the Hapes Consortium, a hereditary monarchy based on the capital world of Hapes.

properties.name: Jofoger
properties.description: Jofoger was a planet on the Sisar Run in the Outer Rim Territories near Hutt Space. It was the homeworld of Risiev Credal.

properties.name: Joiol
properties.description: Joiol was a planet located in the Orus sector of the Inner Rim that teemed with life.

properties.name: Jomark
properties.description: Jomark was one of six worlds in the Jomark system. Originally known as Bynas, it was absorbed into Xim's Empire as he expanded his borders from the Kingdom of Cron.

properties.name: Jonsior
properties.description: Jonsior was a planet orbited by moons colonized by Humans as a vassal colony of Kaikielius. The moons achieved full Republic membership by 11,000 BBY.

properties.name: Joodrudda
properties.description: Joodrudda was a barren, nearly uninhabited world located on the Tingel Route, just outside the borders of the Corporate Sector. Its only point of interest was a sprawling palace constructed hundreds of years before the Battle of Yavin by a clan of eccentric Hutts.

properties.name: Joralla
properties.description: Joralla was a jungle planet located in the Mid Rim's Mektrun sector. It orbited the red giant star Jaska and had an unstable climate that displayed considerable weather and seasonal changes. The planet's surface was divided between vast oceans and three main continents, whose terrain included high mountains, forests, and verdant jungles. The latter featured remarkably diverse plant life, including tequa bushes, sio trees, redspar fruits, and kewafi flowers. Various animal species also inhabited Joralla, such as the herbivorous oslets and the predatory wulkarsks.

properties.name: Joran Station
properties.description: Joran Station was a space station that was used as stopover point between Phindar and Vjun. Jai Maruk, Maks Leem, Tallisibeth Enwandung-Esterhazy and Whie Malreaux traveled through it on their way to Vjun, during the Clone Wars.

properties.name: Joruna
properties.description: Joruna was a planet in the Farlax sector of the Core Worlds.

properties.name: Jovan
properties.description: Jovan was a male human who served in the military forces of the Galactic Empire in the years prior to the Battle of Yavin. He used his station within the Imperial military to enrich his own life, which resulted in his arrest by his former friend, Agent Kallus of the Imperial Security Bureau.

properties.name: Jovaria
properties.description: The Jovaria system was located in the Interior Region, an area of the Hapes Cluster in the Slice portion of the Inner Rim. It was connected via hyperlanes to the Lemmi, Selab, and Thrakia systems. The Jovaria system was home to the species of fern known as the Jovarian sun fern.

properties.name: Jubalene
properties.description: Jubalene was was the capital world of the Odionate in the Grumani sector. It was a foundry world where millions of slave laborers of various species were used to build Odion's war machines.

properties.name: Jubilar
properties.description: Jubilar was a planet in the Outer Rim Territories used as a penal colony by half a dozen of its neighboring worlds, resulting in many civil wars throughout its history. The thriving spice trade within this planet's sector was controlled by the Hutts.

properties.name: Julio
properties.description: Julio was a planet in the Julio system within the Marcol sector. It was known for its mountainous environment.

properties.name: Juma
properties.description: Juma may refer to one of the following:

properties.name: Jumus
properties.description: Jumus was a planet in the Corellian sector conquered by the Yuuzhan Vong.

properties.name: Junction
properties.description: Junction may refer to:

properties.name: Junction
properties.description: Junction may refer to:

properties.name: Junkfort Station
properties.description: Junkfort Station was an Outer Rim Territories space station located in the Tharin sector at the junction of three hyperlanes. A notable shadowport and spice-smuggling point, Junkfort Station was often visited by starships in order to receive illegal modifications and equipment. Historically located in an area of space influenced by the Hutt species, by 17 BBY Junkfort Station was a part of the Galactic Empire.

properties.name: Jurio
properties.description: Jurio was a planet in the Jurio system, a part of the Corva sector in the New Territories portion of the Outer Rim Territories. It was home to the winged creature known as the Juriod fang-flier.

properties.name: Jurzan
properties.description: Jurzan was a planet in the Expansion Region, on the Harrin Trade Corridor.

properties.name: Jutrand
properties.description: Jutrand was a city-planet that was located in the Grumani sector, in the Outer Rim Territories. Hundreds of corporations had their headquarters on the world.

properties.name: Juvex
properties.description: Juvex was the sector capital of Juvex sector. It was ruled by House Sreethyn which engaged in the slave trade, and thus was denied Galactic Republic membership until shortly before the formation of the New Order. It was later part of the New Republic.

properties.name: K'ath
properties.description: K'ath was a planet located in the K'ath system of the Juvex sector, in the Mid Rim of the galaxy. An agriworld, K'ath was most notable for its seashells, which local artisans would craft into figurines. In addition to these trinkets, visitors knew K'ath for its wide beaches and terraced hills.

properties.name: k'Farri
properties.description: k'Farri was a planet known to grow crystals. It was located in the Hapes Cluster.

properties.name: K'taktaxka
properties.description: The K'taktaxka system was a star system located in the Inner Rim region of the galaxy.

properties.name: Ka'Dedus
properties.description: Ka'Dedus was an ultraviolet supergiant star that was the primary of the Ka'Dedus system in which Af'El was located.

properties.name: Kaa
properties.description: Kaa was a planet in the Colonies.

properties.name: Kaal
properties.description: A former Rakata colony in the Pre-Republic era, Kaal was a tropical resort world. It was a popular destination for Imperial personnel on leave, though military presence was minimal. Following the Battle of Endor, it was the site of a confrontation between the New Republic, Imperial Admiral Kermen, and the warlord Utoxx Prentioch. The New Republic took control of the world.

properties.name: Kabaira
properties.description: Kabaira was an Imperial Outer Rim Territories planet in the Teilcam system with damp, foggy weather. Its vast oceans were interrupted by some 2 million volcanic islands, of which only a few in the southern hemisphere were active during the Galactic Civil War. There were two northern island-continents: Belshain and Madieri. Some of the planet's mountains were capped with snow and home to snow-wolves. Delgas Medical and Hydrospeare Corporation were headquartered on Kabaira. The capital city was Eponte Spaceport, which was known for Drayhar's Cantina. The local day consisted of 23 standard hours; the local year of 341 local days. Humans and Twi'leks inhabited the planet. There was a Rebel Alliance cell on the planet. This planet was also the birthplace of the Aquatic Terrain Armored Transport, which had been an extensive modification of the All Terrain Armored Transport executed by the Imperial Army garrison stationed on the planet.

properties.name: Kabal
properties.description: Kabal was an Outer Rim planet in Mayagil sector, on the Sharlissian Trade Corridor.

properties.name: Kabieroun
properties.description: Kabieroun was a planet in the Outer Rim Territories.

properties.name: Kabray
properties.description: Kabray was a Mid Rim forest world orbited by the Kabray Station, a neutral meeting place for diplomats from all over the galaxy.

properties.name: Kadavo
properties.description: Kadavo was a planet in the Kadavo system of Wild Space. During the Clone Wars, it was under the control of the Zygerrian Slave Empire.

properties.name: Kadril
properties.description: Kadril was an inhospitable, irregularly-shaped world colonized by the reptilian Kadrillians 6 BBY. It was the source of kunda stones. It was here that Darth Vader developed pacifog. The reptilian Kadrillians were the only inhabitants of the planet to survive the planet's bombardment during the Stenax Massacres of 4 ABY.

properties.name: Kafane
properties.description: Kafane was a poor agricultural planet that was located within the Kafane system of the galaxy's Hutt Space region. Kafane was connected to the worlds of Nimia and Ulmatra by the hyperlane called The Dead Road.

properties.name: Kaikielius
properties.description: Kaikielius was a planet in the Kaikielius system of the Core Worlds. A regional power before the rise of the Republic and a Core Founder, it was situated on the Koros Trunk Line, just outside of the Deep Core. The planet was the homeworld of the influential political dynasty House Praji.

properties.name: Kail
properties.description: Kail was a planet in the Corporate Sector. Torm Dadeferron, an associate of Han Solo, had family on Kail who controlled several large tracts of land known as the Kail Ranges. Torm's father and brother disappeared after a dispute with the Corporate Sector Authority over land-use rights and stock prices.

properties.name: Kailion
properties.description: Kailion was the main port world for the 77 Sectors. It was the location of the Kailion caves.

properties.name: Kaisa
properties.description: Kaisa was a planet that was once home to the Buro species. However, it was accidentally driven to extinction by the actions of Human geologists.

properties.name: Kal'Shebbol
properties.poi: Imperial Government Complex, Sorbiss Valley, Kal'Shebbol starport,
properties.description: Kal'Shebbol was the primary planet of the Kal'Shebbol system, in the Kathol sector of the Outer Rim Territories. Kal'Shebbol was located on the Trition Trade Route, the hyperlane that connected the major worlds of the sector to the nearby Minos Cluster. The planet was home to a colony during the Third Galactic War, but was also settled around 392 BBY by escaped Twi'lek slaves from Ryloth. Kal'Shebbol grew from a small settlement into a major trading world only fifty years after the Twi'lek colonization as sizable Human and alien communities emigrated to the planet in search of a fresh start. Once the Kathol sector entered the Galactic Republic, Kal'Shebbol, being the closest planet to Republic space, was appointed as the sector capital.

properties.name: Kalaan
properties.description: Kalaan was a planet in the Kalaan system and home to a large Rebel base as of 0 BBY. Shortly before the Battle of Yavin, the Galactic Empire launched an invasion of the planet. The Battle of Kalaan reduced Kalaan City to rubble and routed the Rebels.

properties.name: Kalab
properties.description: Kalab was a planet located within the Sluis sector in the Outer Rim Territories. The planet was known to be frequented by smugglers.

properties.name: Kalarba
properties.poi: Great Sea, Three Peaks of Tharen,
properties.description: Kalarba was a planet in the Mid Rim.

properties.name: Kalee
properties.poi: Abesmi, Grendaju, Jenuwaa Sea, Kunbal jungle, Shrupak,
properties.description: Kalee was the home planet of the Kaleesh, including General Grievous. It was located on the border of the Kadok Regions.

properties.name: Kalidorn
properties.description: Kalidorn was a planet located in Wild Space. It was the homeworld of the Muttani.

properties.name: Kaliida Nebula
properties.description: The Kaliida Nebula was a large nebula that spanned several sectors in the Mid Rim and Outer Rim Territories of the galaxy, located along the smuggler route known as the Balmorra Run. Several parsecs in size, it extended at least into the Ryndellia system and was sometimes home to neebray mantas, who often migrated along the Balmorra Run.

properties.name: Kaliida Shoals
properties.description: Kaliida Shoals was a Mid Rim planet located near the Kaliida Nebula. In 22 BBY, a battle took place close to it.

properties.name: Kalinda
properties.description: Kalinda was the primary star of the Kalinda system.

properties.name: Kalishik
properties.description: Kalishik was a planet in a system of the same name, located in the Gordian Reach sector of the Outer Rim. It sat on the Ardan Cross hyperspace route. Kalishik was the homeworld of the phocine T'sarki species.

properties.name: Kaliska
properties.description: Kaliska was a planet in the Mid Rim. The Techno-priests of Kaliska developed the Visualization engine.

properties.name: Kalist
properties.description: Kalist VI, also known as Kalist, was a world located in the galaxy's Deep Core where the Galactic Empire had a penal colony. It was the homeworld of the Rebel pilot Dak Ralter, who was born to a family of political prisoners in the colony. Ralter escaped the world with bright ambitions, but was killed in the Battle of Hoth.

properties.name: Kalki Nebula
properties.description: The Kalki Nebula was a treacherous Outer Rim Territories nebula located in the Cassander sector. Long before 3643 BBY, a frigate became adrift in the nebula. When the unresponsive starship emerged from the nebula around that year, an individual boarded it and recovered its navigational data as well as some of its cargo. The Kalki Nebula later became a part of the Tendrannan sector of the Galactic Empire.

properties.name: Kalkovak
properties.description: Kalkovak was a remote planet populated by various species including a large sector populated by Quarren. It was a port world for travelers going to the Outer Rim Territories. Illyan Webble was left on the planet after he irritated the crew he was traveling with. Han Solo and Lando Calrissian once frequented the world in search of Webble and his information on the whereabouts of the Yavin Vassilika.

properties.name: Kalla
properties.poi: University of Kalla, Unlimited Horizons Inc.,
properties.description: Kalla VII, also simply known as Kalla, was a planet in the Corporate Sector. It was the location of the University of Kalla, an Imperial base, and the headquarters of Unlimited Horizons Inc.

properties.name: Kallakea
properties.description: The Kallakea system was located in the Authala sector, a part of the Slice portion of the Expansion Region. It shared its name with the phenomenon known as Kallakean rainbows.

properties.name: Kallidah
properties.description: Kallidah was a planet that was the homeworld of the Kallidahin species located in the Subterrel sector of the Outer Rim Territories. The planet's Archaeological Research Council established a Research Base on the nearby Polis Massa asteroid colony to try and uncover evidence of an evolutionary link between the Kallidahin and the extinct Eellayin natives. Later, the entire population of Kallidah abandoned their homeworld and moved to Polis Massa to work on the project.

properties.name: Kallistas
properties.description: Kallistas was a mining colony next to the Revkinn system in the Parmel sector. Its low mountains covered radioactive elements and rare gemstones. Numerous pirate bases were located on the planet. Grand Admiral Osvald Teshik spent part of his childhood, especially during the summers, on this planet.

properties.name: Kalsunor
properties.description: Kalsunor was a planet conquered by the Sith Empire sometime prior to the Golden Age of the Sith. It was close to Begeren and Ashas Ree and was located on the Kamat Aegit.

properties.name: Kalzeron
properties.description: Kalzeron was a planet with a feudal civilization. It was the homeworld of the Kalzerian people.

properties.name: Kamar
properties.description: Kamar was a dry and arid planet located in Wild Space near the Corporate Sector, home to the insectoid Kamarian species and the howlrunner. It had deserts and mountains across its surface that scorched under the hot-white sun. Various plant life such as the miser-plant, barrel-scrub, and sting-brush sprouted up.

properties.name: Kamasto
properties.description: Kamasto was a frigid world that was located in the Grumani sector, along the Hydian Way hyperlane, where it orbited an orange dwarf. The world was the site of a number of monasteries that were operated by the Children of Mani, before the religion was divided by a schism. The world was later the site of a number of unsuccessful acts of diplomacy. Between 3701 BBY and 3699 BBY the Hydian Way was charted through Kamasto as part of the Seswenna Expansion.

properties.name: Kamgeddon
properties.description: Kamgeddon may refer to one of the following:

properties.name: Kamino
properties.poi: Baran WuSu DesSlici CanyonTal An FissuresGlascretiaRazoral Reefs
properties.description: Kamino , called Big Stormy by some clone troopers, also known as the Planet of Storms, was an aquatic planet located in a remote star system in Wild Space, beyond the Outer Rim and was straggled south of the Rishi Maze, a dwarf satellite galaxy. Due to it position past the rim of the galaxy, it was sometimes regarded as extra-galactic. It was inhabited by a race of tall, elegant beings called the Kaminoans and the capital world of the Ruling Council, headed by the Prime Minister. Kaminoans kept to themselves and were known for their cloning technology, and for the creation of a clone army for the Galactic Republic.

properties.name: Kammia
properties.description: Kammia was a planet in the extremely remote Drynn system, among the sparsely populated Shiritoku Spur of Wild Space. Kammia was a Human colony world of the Galactic Empire, notable for its rich soil. In the years following the Battle of Yavin, Emperor Palpatine ceded a number of colony worlds, including Kammia, to the Ssi-ruuvi Imperium in exchange for the aliens' species-enslaving entechment technology. The Empire released a news report claiming that a mysterious virus had wiped out the Kammia colony to hide the truth.

properties.name: Kamori
properties.description: Kamori was a planet. Its populace was decimated by earthquakes shortly after the Battle of Yavin. An ensuing tidal wave further damaged its cities.

properties.name: Kamparas
properties.poi: Kamparas Jedi Training Center, Imperial archives,
properties.description: Kamparas was a planet in the Dolomar sector of the Core Worlds covered with rainforests, grasslands, rolling hills, and deep valleys.

properties.name: Kampe
properties.description: Kampe was a Deep Core planet with a Type II atmosphere and an arid climate. By 12 ABY, Superior General Sander Delvardus, a warlord of the Galactic Empire, maintained a fortress in one of Kampe's labyrinthine canyons. Armed presence was light on the Deep Core world, however, due to nearly all of the warlord's money being funneled into the construction of the Super Star Destroyer Night Hammer elsewhere in the system.

properties.name: Kamper
properties.description: The Kamper system was a star system located in the Tapani sector's Pelagia Province, between the Calipsa and Setolio systems. It was seized by Calipsa Province after the rise of the New Order.

properties.name: Kamur
properties.description: Kamur was an agricultural world owned by House Petro, and the homeworld of the Thanu species, which inhabited the planet's volcanic regions.

properties.name: Kanaver
properties.description: Kanaver was one of the worlds once ruled by the Livien League, before being conquered by Xim the Despot in 25,130 BBY. Located within the Tion Hegemony, on the Outer Rim of the galaxy, it would later join the Galactic Republic, and eventually the Galactic Empire.

properties.name: Kant
properties.description: Kant was a planet located deep within Bothan space. Kant had two moons, which themselves had many asteroid companions. In 3643 BBY, Sith Lord Darth Chratis stationed his division near there.

properties.name: Kaon
properties.description: Kaon was a planet in the Tion Cluster. It was inhabited by scranges.

properties.name: Kar'a'katok
properties.description: Kar'a'katok was a mist-enshrouded planet in the Core Worlds known to be the homeworld of the Shimholt species.

properties.name: Karatha
properties.description: Karatha was a planet in the Expansion Region that was the location of the Rebel Alliance base Eyrie Base. The Eyrie was located in a natural sinkhole on the surface of Karatha.

properties.name: Karavis
properties.description: Karavis was a location in the Outer Rim Territories. It was depicted on a map included with the Rebel Alliance collection of non-electronic documents known as The Rebel Files.

properties.name: Karazak
properties.description: Karazak was the primary planet in the Karazak system of the Sujimis sector in the Outer Rim Territories. Its surface was riddled with tunnels and caves which the Karazak Slavers Cooperative used as a base of operations. Along with Zygerria and the Thalassian system, Karazak was one of the Outer Rim's slavery capitals.

properties.name: Kardura
properties.description: The Kardura system was located in the Juvex sector, a part of the Senex-Juvex region in the Western Reaches portion of the Mid Rim. The Kassido Bypass hyperlane linked it to the Dioll and Yhifar systems. The system was home to the Kardurans, a sentient species that were subservient to House Kassido, a noble house based on the nearby world of Kassido.

properties.name: Kareas
properties.description: Kareas was a planet in the Prefsbelt sector of the Outer Rim.

properties.name: Karfeddion
properties.description: Karfeddion was a planet in the Senex sector. It was the homeworld of House Vandron. A large bountiful world, rich with plantations and ranches, it was used as a breeding ground for slaves of various species, including Ossans, Balinaka, and Humans.

properties.name: Karideph
properties.description: Karideph was a planet in the Karideph system, a star system in the Outer Rim Territories's resource-rich Minos Cluster. Home of the insectoid Kari species, Karideph's surface was almost entirely dominated by gardens and agricultural fields that provided for the planet's population of more than 88 billion. Discovered by the greater galaxy alongside the rest of the Minos Cluster between 3956 BBY and 3681 BBY, Karideph was the next stop along the Rimma Trade Route after Elrood, and the Trition Trade Route branched off Karideph to connect the Minos Cluster and the Kathol sector to the Rimma. Karideph was invaded by the reconstituted Sith Empire during the Great Galactic War, but a Galactic Republic counterattack under the command of Jedi Master Orgus Din and the Special Forces' Lieutenant Harron Tavus drove back the Imperial assault.

properties.name: Kariek
properties.description: Kariek was a planet located in Wild Space near the Unknown Regions.

properties.name: Karinda
properties.description: Karinda was a planet in the Outer Rim's Karinda system. It was the location of a Rebel base called Karinda Outpost and an Imperial garrison. The planet was mostly dry, covered in red-brown dust, but had lakes, small seas, and valleys.

properties.name: Karka
properties.description: Karka was a pilot in the Rebel Alliance who served aboard the MC80 Home One type Star Cruiser Independence. Frequently seen in the presence of fellow pilots Dontal and Misch'an, Karka's absence was noted by Keyan Farlander after the pilot was killed in the Battle of Brigia during Operation Strike Fear.

properties.name: Karkaris
properties.description: Karkaris was a planet located in the Nilgaard sector and the homeworld of the Karkarodons, a species of sentient aquatics.

properties.name: Karlinus
properties.description: Karlinus was a prosperous planet located in the Chommell sector of the galaxy's Mid Rim, known for its agricultural industry and its workforce with a high turnover rate. When Padmé Amidala wished to rescue slaves from Tatooine, she and Sabé chose to let them live a new life on Karlinus. Sabé managed to rescue twenty-five slaves, giving them jobs on Karlinus with the help of the planet's governor, Kelma.

properties.name: Karnak Alpha
properties.description: Karnak Alpha was a planet situated beyond the Hapes Cluster and near the Core Worlds. It was the home of the Karnak Alphans. Because the Karnak Alphans were very fond of strange and exotic animals; the planet was home to a number of large alternate environment zoos.

properties.name: Karnst
properties.description: Karnst was in the Karstaxon Regions of the Outer Rim Territories. It was the location of a Xizor Transport Systems refueling depot.

properties.name: Karra
properties.description: Karra was the Karran homeworld. It was briefly colonized by the Mineral Assets Partnership in 500 BBY. Later, the Galactic Empire established varmigio mines on the planet. Both offworld settlements were destroyed by swarms of insects controlled by the Karran hive mind.

properties.name: Karthrexia
properties.description: Karthrexia was a planet in the Kriz sector of the Outer Rim.

properties.name: Karvoss
properties.description: Karvoss may refer to:

properties.name: Kashir
properties.description: Kashir was a planet in the Expansion Region that applied for membership in the Galactic Republic. Its application was somewhat controversial, given its system of government , and the facts that its inhabitants, the Kashirim, were a primitive race and could be somewhat suspicious. In fact, according to Obi-Wan Kenobi, Kashirim were known throughout the galaxy as thieves and pick-pockets, since stealing was an honored tradition and practiced art on their home planet.

properties.name: Kashoon
properties.description: Kashoon was a planet that was conquered by the Galactic Empire, and later freed with the help of the Rebel Alliance. The Kashoonara were left to their own devices afterwards.

properties.name: Kashyyyk
properties.poi: Kkowir Forest, Myyydril Caverns, Shadowlands, Wawaatt Archipelago, Wartaki Islands, Western Forest,
properties.description: Kashyyyk , also known as Wookiee Planet C, Edean, G5-623, and Wookiee World, was a Mid Rim planet. It was the lush, wroshyr tree-filled homeworld of the Wookiees. It was a member of the Galactic Republic, endured enslavement under the Galactic Empire, and later joined the New Republic.

properties.name: Kasiol
properties.description: Kasiol was the primary star of the Kasiol system.

properties.name: Kassido
properties.description: Kassido was a terrestrial world located in the Kassido system of the Juvex sector, a part of the Senex-Juvex region in the Western Reaches portion of the Mid Rim. The Senex-Juvex Loop hyperlane linked it to the Manforgon and Ossiathora systems, while the Kassido Bypass and the D'Aelgoth Trade Route connected it to the Yhifar system and the D'Aelgoth sector's Selenius system, respectively.

properties.name: Katalla
properties.description: Katalla was a planet in the Kastolar sector of the Mid Rim.

properties.name: Katarr
properties.description: Katarr was a planet in the Mid Rim and a Miraluka colony world. It was completely devastated circa 3952 BBY, during the First Jedi Purge.

properties.name: Katchan
properties.description: Katchan was a world that was located on the edge the Outer Rim Territories. It was the homeworld of the Katchani, a species of olive-skinned, elfish humanoids that were ruled by a monarchy. Katchan's surface was covered with forests, valleys, highlands and low mountains, and the planet was made up of two large continents separated only by a narrow sea. Katchan sat on the Corellian Trade Spine, near to the border of the Saijo sector.

properties.name: Kath
properties.description: Kath was a planet in the Dustig sector of the Mid Rim and the Kath homeworld.

properties.name: Kathol
properties.description: Kathol can refer to:

properties.name: Kathol Rift
properties.description: The Kathol Rift was an area of space inside the Kathol sector. It was difficult to maneuver through, as it consisted of a dense accretion of nebulaic material. It was home to both the Aing-Tii monks, who were able to easily navigate through it, and the DarkStryder. It was believed to be a construct of the Celestials, although another source had it as the result of a launch gate explosion caused by the Dark Jedi Halbret.

properties.name: Katraasii
properties.poi: Katraasii Droid Ballet StudioUnidentified Katraasii cantina
properties.description: Katraasii was a planet in Outer Rim Territories.

properties.name: Kattada
properties.description: Kattada was a planet on the Commenor Run in the Colonies.

properties.name: Kaump
properties.description: Kaump heavyworlders were native to Kaump III. Adapting to their planet's heavy gravity, they were short and dense, with characteristic flat faces. Chanchaz Iryt was a criminal of this species.

properties.name: Kauron
properties.description: Kauron was a planet that was located in Kauron system within Meram sector in the Outer Rim Territories of the galaxy. The world was home to the Kauronian species and served as a hideout for the Cavrilhu Pirates.

properties.name: Kayuk
properties.description: Kayuk was a planet. Ferus Olin once visited there and had a holoconference with Obi-Wan Kenobi.

properties.name: Kazarak
properties.description: Kazarak was a planet in the Mahrusha sector of the Outer Rim.

properties.name: Kebolar
properties.description: Kebolar was a planet that was used for the removal of colonists from Qiilura. The Republic had already established farms for the colonists.

properties.name: Kedorzha
properties.description: Kedorzha was a planet in the Mid Rim inhabited by the species known as the Kedorzhans. Kedorzhans were commonly found enslaved by House Garonnin, working in the mines.

properties.name: Keeara Major
properties.description: Keeara Major was a world that Sargo VenHalgon had once encountered some trouble.

properties.name: Keedad
properties.description: Keedad was the Keed homeworld.

properties.name: Keeper's World
properties.description: Keeper's World, located in the Outer Rim Territories, was the homeworld of The Keeper. It used to be inhabited by the Keeper's makers until they fled the planet during an ancient war.

properties.name: Kegan
properties.description: Kegan was a planet located in the Outer Rim Territories. The planet was run by the Benevolent Guides, who isolated the planet from the rest of the galaxy after having visions of the destruction of Kegan. During the Yuuzhan Vong War, Kegan was conquered by the extragalactic Yuuzhan Vong.

properties.name: Keitum
properties.description: Keitum was a planet located in the galaxy's Mid Rim, connected via hyperspace route to Ansion. Cartherston was a city located on the planet.

properties.name: Kejim
properties.description: Kejim was the planet where the Kejim Outpost, an Imperial Remnant base believed to be abandoned after the destruction of the first Death Star, was located.

properties.name: Kelada
properties.description: Kelada was a planet in the Anarid Cluster. It was controlled by the Galactic Empire during the Galactic Civil War. As the Rebel opposition grew stronger, an increasing number of smugglers frequented the planet, many of them hanging out at Lorana's Labyrinth.

properties.name: Kelarea
properties.description: Kelarea was a planet located in the Tynna sector of the Expansion Region.

properties.name: Keldooine
properties.description: Keldooine was a minor trade world that was located within the Keldooine system in Hutt Space, a region of the galaxy controlled by the Hutt species. The planet lay on the Ootmian Pabol hyperlane, which connected it to the planets of Kwenn and Nar Bo Sholla. During the rule of the Galactic Empire, Keldooine served as a customs stop for starships that left Hutt Space.

properties.name: Keller's Void
properties.description: Keller's Void was an empty area of the Inner Rim used as a shortcut between the Wroona and Calus systems. It was named for Keller, the trader who discovered it.

properties.name: Kelrodo-Ai
properties.description: Kelrodo-Ai was a planet with famous gelatin mines and known for its water-sculptures. In 12 ABY, its Baron Administrator was Drom Guldi.

properties.name: Kem Stor Ai
properties.description: Kem Stor Ai was a planet located in the Tennuutta sector of the Mid Rim.

properties.name: Kemal Station
properties.description: Kemal Station was a damp, foggy, terrestrial moon orbiting the gas giant–type planet Kemal in the Kemal Station system, a part of the Arkanis sector in the Slice portion of the Outer Rim Territories. It was situated on the Triellus Trade Route hyperlane, which connected it to the Andooweel and New Ator systems.

properties.name: Kemix
properties.description: Kemix was a barren planet in the Kemix system. It had some minor glitterstim deposits located on it and Riboga the Hutt established a spice mine there to mine these. However, the mines were destroyed during the Clone Wars, by the Heroes of Cularin.

properties.name: Kemla
properties.description: Kemla was a planet in the Dantus sector of the Outer Rim Territories.

properties.name: Kendamar
properties.description: Kendamar was a terrestrial planet located in the Kendamar system, a part of the Outer Rim Territories' Dail sector. Around 10 ABY, it served as the homeworld of Kendamari Casinos, a chain of casinos that constituted a part of the Tenloss Syndicate.

properties.name: Kenosha
properties.description: Kenosha was a planet in the Expansion Region, known for its cliffs.

properties.name: Keral
properties.description: Keral was a kind of firegem named for its star system of origin, the Keral system.

properties.name: Kerensik
properties.description: Kerensik was a terrestrial planet located in the Kerensik system, a part of the Southern Core portion of the Core Worlds. Kerensik was a part of the Allied Region known as the Botor Enclave.

properties.name: Keresia
properties.description: Keresia was an astronomical object located within the Keresia system, a part of the Demetras sector within the Outer Rim Territories and Trans-Hydian regions of the galaxy.

properties.name: Kerest
properties.description: Kerest was a terrestrial Outer Rim world in the midst of a vast ice age throughout the history of the Galactic Republic and Galactic Empire. The homeworld of the Kerestian species, those Kerestians who had not moved offworld devolved into savages in the frozen wastes.

properties.name: Kerig'En
properties.description: Kerig'En was Alara Fax's homeworld. It was located in the Brema sector of the Outer Rim Territories.

properties.name: Kerkoidia
properties.description: Kerkoidia was the homeworld of the Kerkoiden species and was located in the Expansion Region.

properties.name: Keros
properties.description: Keros was the homeworld of the predatory species cidwen.

properties.name: Kes
properties.description: Kes can refer to:

properties.name: Kesh
properties.poi: Keshtah Minor, Tahv, Circle Eternal, capitol building, Ragnos Lakes, Takara Mountains, Sith Temple, Ship of Destiny, Temple courtyard, Alanciar, Sus'mintri, Vaal Hall, Kerebba, Six Claws, Point Defiance, Eshkrene, City of the Doomed,
properties.description: Kesh was a remote planet located in Wild Space. It was the homeworld of the Near-Human Keshiri species and an offworld immigrant community of Human Sith known as the Lost Tribe of Sith. Kesh was a terrestrial world with a wide range of different climates and environments including mountains, plains, forests, ocean, and tundra. It had at least three continents in its southern hemisphere: Keshtah, the dominion of the Sith Tribe, Alanciar, and Eshkrene, which was at the South Pole. Kesh was isolated from the rest of the galaxy due to a strange magnetic field that limited hyperspace travel and offworld signals communications.

properties.name: Keskin
properties.description: Keskin was a planet which was the site of a battle during the Galactic Civil War between the Galactic Empire and Alliance to Restore the Republic.

properties.name: Kesmere
properties.description: Kesmere may refer to one of the following:

properties.name: Kesmere Minor
properties.description: The Kesmere Minor system was located in the Raioballo sector, a part of the New Territories portion of the Outer Rim Territories. It shared its name with the Kesmere and Tertiary Kesmere systems. The star system fell within the borders of the Pentastar Alignment between 4 ABY and 12 ABY and was a part of the Imperial Remnant between 18 ABY and 35 ABY.

properties.name: Kessel
properties.poi: Abandoned mine, Ancient machinery, Detention Center A, Detention Center B, Detention Center C, Calrissian-Nunb Mines, Spice Mines of Kessel
properties.description: Kessel, originally known as Xo's Eye while under Xim's empire, was a planet located in the Kessel sector, in the Outer Rim Territories, near Hutt Space and the dangerous celestial bodies of the Maw. It was a prison world, and was home to the galaxy's largest glitterstim spice mining operation. Under Imperial rule, slave labor was in extensive use.

properties.name: Kestos Minor
properties.description: Kestos Minor was a planet. It was represented directly in the Galactic Senate by Ivor Drake.

properties.name: Ket
properties.description: Ket was a planet in the Lorelli Reach region of the Hapes Cluster. It was the homeworld of the nomadic Ketton species.

properties.name: Ketal
properties.description: Ketal was a planet located in the Ketal system in the Inner Rim Territories.

properties.name: Ketaris
properties.description: Ketaris was a planet in the Outer Rim which boasted the University of Ketaris. A major trade center, it had a few large continents surrounded by great oceans.

properties.name: Keyorin
properties.description: Keyorin, also known as the Hunter's World, was a common destination for retired or semi-retired smugglers seeking second careers as entrepreneurs or bank-rollers of those who still flew. Smugglers who decided it was time to go dirtside but couldn't bear getting out of the game sometimes ended up on this planet. The most respected such retiree was typically given informal rule over Keyorin, and known as the Boss. Boss Tinketh Fo controlled the planet as of 4 ABY. Alas, retirement rarely meant escaping from one's past indiscretions, due to the many available bounties which earned Keyorin its nickname.

properties.name: Khadaji Singularity
properties.description: The Khadaji Singularity was one of the more active black holes known in the galaxy, during the final years of the Old Republic. Sometime during the final stages of the Clone Wars, it consumed a shipment of gemstones owned by the Jalorian Sodality.

properties.name: Khar Delba
properties.description: Khar Delba was an icy, snowy planet in the Sith Worlds, which was part of the Sith Empire as of 5000 BBY. Khar Delba had one moon, Khar Shian, and was located at the edge of Sith Space. It was the home to the Sith war behemoth. Naga Sadow placed a citadel there, but unbeknownst to the rest of the Sith at large, Sadow's Khar Delba citadel was a mere decoy; his real base was on Khar Shian. In 5000 BBY, with Naga Sadow in the midst of a power struggle with his rival, Ludo Kressh, Khar Delba was attacked from orbit by forces loyal to Kressh. Although the citadel was badly damaged in Kressh's orbital bombardment of the planet, Sadow emerged victorious after calling in his secret fleet from the far side of Khar Shian to counterattack Kressh. In the following months, Khar Delba was rebuilt and was established as the center of Naga Sadow's power as he gathered a force to invade the Galactic Republic, in a conflict that became known as the Great Hyperspace War.

properties.name: Kharmort's Miasma
properties.description: Located within the Unknown Regions, the nebula known as Kharmort's Miasma was the site of the Vagar Praxut system. The star system contained the planet Vagar Praxut, homeworld of the sentient Vagaari species.

properties.name: Kheedar
properties.description: Kheedar was an Outer Rim Territories planet in the Kheedar system. It had hydrocarbon processing facilities.

properties.name: Khemerion
properties.description: Khemerion was a planet in the Expansion Region, on which the Separatist Ruusaan Skirata was detained by the Galactic Republic during the Clone Wars.

properties.name: Kho Nai
properties.description: Kho Nai was an astronomical object located in the Outer Rim Territories. It was the Khotta homeworld.

properties.name: Khoan
properties.description: The Khoan were a species who, though shorter than Humans, weighed twice the average Wookiee. They had yellow skin, a dorsal fin, and spikes on their faces. These spikes fanned around the face, forming a spiked collar around their faces. Khoan imagined themselves as the fairest of all intergalactic races.

properties.name: Kholes
properties.description: Kholes was a planet in Imperial space and the home of a Rebel outpost. In 1 ABY, soon after an outbreak of Bledsoe's disease on the nearby planet Tay'ah'loo, the Rebel outpost was wiped out by Imperial forces.

properties.name: Khomm
properties.poi: Khomm Central Population Planning, Mmos Lake,
properties.description: Khomm was a planet in the Khomm system on the edge of the Deep Core with wide blue seas, great land masses, and an abundance of oxygen. It was the home planet to the Khommites and the Khommite striders.

properties.name: Khomr
properties.description: Khomr was an agriworld colonized by Corellians shortly after the invention of the hyperdrive.

properties.name: Khorm
properties.description: Khorm was a frozen planet located in the Mid Rim, home to the Khormai species. It was one of the few planets that contained an extremely rare ore called Agrocite that could be used to enhance the power of turbolasers. During The Clone Wars between the Galactic Republic and the Confederacy of Independent Systems, Khormai warlord Unger Gout betrayed his people and enslaved them to mine Agrocite for Dooku. This resulted in a major Republic offensive led by Plo Koon, Kit Fisto, and Tauht at the Battle of Khorm. During the battle, both Gout and Tauht were killed, but in the end the Republic won with the help of native Khormai and air support from Republic Admiral Wieler, who, along with Fisto and Captain "Sharp", destroyed Gout's powerful Agrocite cannons.

properties.name: Khubeaie
properties.description: Khubeaie was an industrial world that was located within the Arkanis sector of the galaxy's Outer Rim Territories region. The planet lay on the hyperlanes called the Old Corellian Run and the Vaschean Way, and it was better known as a stopover for spice smugglers. Members of such species as Humans, Hutts, Rodians and Twi'leks could all be encountered on Khubeaie.

properties.name: Khuiumin
properties.description: Courkrus, also called Khuiumin IV, was the primary planet of the Khuiumin system in the Khuiumin sector, located in the Outer Rim.

properties.name: Kiamurr
properties.description: Kiamurr was a world located in the Likasha sector of the Mid Rim.

properties.name: Kidiet Olgo
properties.description: Kidiet Olgo was a planet located in the Galactic Core. It was both a hotbed of slavery and a shadowport during the time of the Old Republic. Smugglers who did business with slave trader Graxol Kelvyyn operated out of Kidiet Olgo.

properties.name: Kidron
properties.poi: Orfa City High City of Refuge
properties.description: Kidron was a planet in Elrood sector, on the Elrood-Derilyn Run. It was the homeworld of the sentient Orfite species as well as the quamin and slork creatures. Attakril Meats also operated on the planet.

properties.name: Kiffex
properties.description: Kiffex was the smaller sister planet of Kiffu in the Azurbani system of the Inner Rim. It had rich soil, giving Kiffex the potential to become a major agriculture producing planet.

properties.name: Kiilimaar
properties.description: Kiilimaar was a planet in the Outer Rim Territories.

properties.name: Kile
properties.description: Kile was a moon of the gas giant Zhar in the Zhar system. Rogue Squadron established a base on the moon, from where they organized the mission to rescue Han Solo from Boba Fett's Slave I. The other moon, Gall, was a populated, terrestrial world home to an Imperial enclave.

properties.name: Killaniri
properties.description: Killaniri was a gas giant world that was located within the Killaniri system. It was the second of two orbital bodies around its star. The planet possessed fifteen known moons.

properties.name: Kilmauls
properties.description: Kilmaulsias was a planet in the Vorzyd Cluster. It was the homeworld of the Kilmaulsi.

properties.name: Kimanan
properties.description: Kimanan was a planet in the Orus sector of the the galaxy's Inner Rim. It was where the pets known as furballs came from.

properties.name: Kimm Aurek
properties.description: Kimm Aurek was a planet located in the Kimm Aurek system of the Juvex sector, in the Mid Rim of the galaxy. It was one of a trio of dingy industrial worlds belonging to House Sreethyn.

properties.name: Kimm Besh
properties.description: Kimm Besh was a planet located in the Kimm Besh system of the Juvex sector, in the Mid Rim of the galaxy. It was one of a trio of dingy industrial worlds belonging to House Sreethyn.

properties.name: Kimm Cresh
properties.description: Kimm Cresh was a planet located in the Kimm Cresh system of the Juvex sector, in the Mid Rim of the galaxy. It was one of a trio of dingy industrial worlds belonging to House Sreethyn.

properties.name: Kindlabethia
properties.description: Kindlabethia was a planet in the Braxant sector of the Outer Rim.

properties.name: King's Galquek
properties.description: King's Galquek, or "Kay-Gee" for short, was a planet located in the Meridian sector of the Outer Rim Territories.

properties.name: Kinooine
properties.description: Kinooine was a planet located in Wild Space, beyond the end of the Hydian Way. It was there that Lumiya and the Nagai set up their combined forces' headquarters.

properties.name: Kinoss
properties.poi: Chiss Expansionary Defense Fleet base, Armory and munitions depot,
properties.description: Kinoss was a planet that was located within the Kinoss system, in the Chiss Space sector of the galaxy's Unknown Regions. It was connected by the Cressus Route hyperlane to the Bogo Rai system, and other hyperspace routes linked the planet to the Avidich system and to regions lying west of the core territory of the Chiss Ascendancy, the government of the Chiss species.

properties.name: Kintan
properties.poi: Basin of Torturous Flame, Canyon of Despair, Burning Moon Range, River of Fire, Gluss'elta Archipelago, Glussa Island, Gluss'elta Sea, Fortress Kh'aris, Wannschok Desert,
properties.description: Kintan was the homeworld of the Nikto. After a supernova explosion near the system, evolution of the Nikto divided into five subspecies. Kintan was located within the Si'Klaata Cluster, on the Ac'fren Spur.

properties.name: Kintoni
properties.description: Kintoni was a planet in the Outer Rim Territories that contained a single city with several towns, the rest being farmland. It contained Tinegris Street. New Republic forces occupied a former Imperial garrison on Kintoni circa 4 ABY, where Governor Barkale was held prisoner. Mara Jade infiltrated the base and assassinated Barkale on the behalf of Palpatine for stealing credits over the past ten years.

properties.name: Kinun Depot
properties.description: Kinun Depot was a location where the Rodian slaver Malak made a stop sometime before 0 ABY, to refuel her ship. During this time her captured prey, Myo, escaped from his custody. Myo then met the musician Lirin Car'n, and the two became associates. Car'n helped Myo to reach Tatooine.

properties.name: Kinyen
properties.description: Kinyen was an agriworld in the Expansion Region, located on the Corellian Trade Spine at the junction to the Great Gran Run. It was the Gran homeworld, with a recorded history dating back to 10,000 BBY. Though it was an outpost of the violent Rakata during the Pre-Republic era, during its recorded history, the planet has had no local wars. At the time of the Clone Wars, Senator Kharrus represented Kinyen in the Galactic Senate.

properties.name: Kip
properties.description: Kip was a planet in the Outer Rim's Chorlian sector and the homeworld of the Kip species. It was a source of ulikuo gemstones. It was a damp mud-ball riddled with caves. Zorba Desilijic Tiure was imprisoned on Kip in 22 BBY, shortly before the Clone Wars. After the Battle of Endor, in 5 ABY, Ysanne Isard arranged for pirates to take over Kip and free Zorba. Kip years were roughly equal to three standard years.

properties.name: Kir
properties.description: Kir was a planet that was located within the Corporate Sector. A mineral found on this planet was used in the production of crystalline vertex.

properties.name: Kira
properties.description: Kira was an astronomical object located in the Expansion Region and the Trailing Sectors regions, in grid square N-16 of the Standard Galactic Grid. Hyperspace routes linked Kira to the celestial bodies Bacrana, Kalinda, Pax, and Wroona.

properties.name: Kirdo
properties.description: Kirdo III was a planet in the Tamarin sector of the Outer Rim Territories, located on the Sanrafsix Corridor between Sevarcos II and Ma'ar Shaddam. It was the home world of the Kitonak race.

properties.name: Kiribi
properties.description: Kiribi was a planet located in the Colonies. Its galactic coordinates were 099,099,011. Although it was located 5000 light-years away from Coruscant, because Kiribi's coordinates were positive and began with zero, it was part of the Imperial Center Oversector during the Imperial Period.

properties.name: Kiros
properties.description: Kiros was an idyllic world filled with vast green valleys and flowing waterfalls. Located in the Expansion Region, the planet served as the site of a colony of Togruta artists.

properties.name: Kirtania
properties.description: Kirtania was the homeworld of the spider-like, pacifist Araquia people. The Kubaz crime lord Schnil Hakoon settled on the planet and centered his operations in Kinkosa City.

properties.name: Kirtarkin
properties.description: Kirtarkin was a smoky world of pollution and machinery that traditionally served as the customs checkpoint for the Twin Nebulae sectors in the Greater Javin region of the Outer Rim Territories. Located along the Corellian Trade Spine in the Anoat sector, Kirtarkin collected billions in revenue annually from import/export taxes. During the Galactic Empire's rule, the Imperial Star Destroyer Desolator staged from Kirtarkin while patrolling the Greater Javin.

properties.name: Kishpaugh
properties.description: Kishpaugh was a planet located within the Kishpaugh system of the Mid Rim.

properties.name: Kismaano
properties.description: Kismaano was a world in the Tion Cluster of the Outer Rim Territories.

properties.name: Kitaros Nebula
properties.description: The Kitaros Nebula was a nebula that was located in the Prefsbelt sector, within the Outer Rim Territories and New Territories regions of the galaxy.

properties.name: Kitel Phard
properties.description: Kitel Phard was an astronomical object located in the regions known as the Core Worlds and the Interior, in the grid square J-12 of the Standard Galactic Grid. A hyperspace route connected it to the planet Giju. Kitel Phard shared its name with the Kitel Phard dynasty. During the reign of the Galactic Empire, the latter was associated with a style of expensive vases.

properties.name: Kiva
properties.poi: Ion Turrent, and Borborygmus Gog's secret Lab
properties.description: Kiva was a planet that was located within the Mid Rim. Its indigenous Kivan people were wiped out by Project Starscream, to the utter horror of Shi'ido anthropologist Mammon Hoole. The only remnants of the people were shadowy wraiths.

properties.name: Kktkt
properties.description: Kktkt was a planet in the Farlax sector in the Galactic Core.

properties.name: Klasse Ephemora
properties.description: Klasse Ephemora, also known as Mobus, was an astronomical object within the territory of the Chiss Ascendancy in the Unknown Regions.

properties.name: Klatooine
properties.poi: Derelkoos Desert, Fountain of Ancients, Klatooine paddy-frog plantation,
properties.description: Klatooine was the arid homeworld of the Klatooinian species. It was located within the Si'Klaata Cluster, under Hutt control. It was covered with deserts and, to a lesser extent, savannas.

properties.name: Kleeva
properties.description: Kleeva was a gas giant world that was orbited by Boonda's Moon. It was located in Hutt Space in the Mid Rim of the galaxy.

properties.name: Kler'terria
properties.description: The Kler'terria system was a Core Worlds star system that was home to the sentient Kler'terrian species.

properties.name: Kli'aar
properties.description: Kli'aar was a planet located on the Pinooran Spur in the Gordian Reach. It was inhabited by the Kli'aari, a four-armed species that were largely known for their mechanical skills. Many Kli'aari enclaves could be found on planets around the Reach.

properties.name: Kloodavia
properties.description: The Kloodavia system was located in the Southern Core portion of the Core Worlds. It was home to the sentient Kloodavian species.

properties.name: Kloper
properties.description: Kloper was a New Republic member planet, and the homeworld of the Kloperian species.

properties.name: Kluistar
properties.description: Kluistar was a planet on the border of the Colonies region, and was considered a comfortable if undistinguished world.

properties.name: Knolstee
properties.description: Knolstee was a near-virgin planet in the Corporate Sector owned by Park Holdings Inc.. Park Holdings used the planet as a layover for traveling tourists. Sightseers were welcome to stay in small luxurious orbital stations then descend to Knolstee's surface where they could take tours lead by Park Holdings mostly Ithorian staff.

properties.name: Knores
properties.description: Knores was a Mid Rim world located in the Senex sector that was famous for its red seas. The world also featured a deep equatorial trench, appealing cities, and violent weather. By 3637 BBY, the seismologist Fez Burba hypothesized that a civilization once existing on Knores had been rendered extinct due to shifts in Knores' crust. Millennia later, the world was ruled by the aristocratic House Viholn.

properties.name: Knot Holes
properties.description: Knot Holes was an area of the Transitory Mists that got its name from the jumble of hyperspace routes that passed through it.

properties.name: Koaan
properties.description: Koaan was a planet near Nar Shaddaa. It was temperate and had many green hills. It was home to the Galactic Research Academy. Whenever an exploration party discovered a new planet, they sent information to this facility for processing. Under the Galactic Empire, the processing was greatly slowed down and it was considered by some as a convenient source for uninhabited planets.

properties.name: Koba
properties.description: Koba was a planet on the Cerean Reach in the Mid Rim. It was ravaged by Tulak the Advozse warlord, but later protected from his son Kalut by Jedi Knight Yaddle.

properties.name: Kobal's World
properties.description: Kobal's World was a planet in the Koradin sector of the Outer Rim Territories. Kobal's World was the site of significant Imperial atrocities during the era of the Galactic Civil War, including the slaughter of a number of women and children by stormtroopers. One of those stormtroopers later accompanied Darth Vader to Cheelit, where the Guild of Vindicators assassin Clat the Shamer used the memories to compel the soldier to commit suicide.

properties.name: Kobaria
properties.description: The Kobaria system was located in the Emmo sector, a part of the Southern Core portion of the Core Worlds. It was home to the creatures known as Kobarian swamp dogs.

properties.name: Kobbahn
properties.description: Kobbahn was an Outer Rim planet near the border of the Unknown Regions. It was the location of one of the earliest Rebel cells in the days following the declaration of the New Order.

properties.name: Koboth
properties.description: Koboth was the Kobok homeworld. It was located in the Outer Rim Territories, on the fringe of the Tingel Arm. It bordered the Corporate Sector.

properties.name: Koda Space Station
properties.description: Koda Space Station, sometimes referred to simply as Koda, was a tiny spaceport in a backwater corner of the Outer Rim Territories.

properties.name: Kodai
properties.description: Kodai was a remote planet in the Belderone sector of the Outer Rim Territories. Some time prior to 29 BBY, its entire surface had been flooded save for the city of Rena.

properties.name: Koensayr
properties.description: Koensayr was a planet in the Colonies region. It was the headquarters of Koensayr Manufacturing.

properties.name: Koiogra
properties.description: Koiogra was a world which had been visited by the New Republic pilot Chass na Chadic. While on Koiogra, she discovered a recording of Jyn Erso's speech prior to the Battle of Scarif, realizing she had previously met the rebel on Uchinao a year earlier.

properties.name: Kojash
properties.description: Kojash was one of two mining colonies on the perimeter of the Koornacht Cluster, founded by the Morath. Along with the other settlement on Elcorth, it was conquered and depopulated by the Yevetha during the Great Purge.

properties.name: Kokash
properties.description: The Kokash system was a star system located within the Kokash sector, a part of the galaxy's Core Worlds region. It was visited in the year 27 BBY by the colonization and exploration vessel Outbound Flight on a shakedown cruise through the territory of the Galactic Republic.

properties.name: Kol Atorn
properties.description: Kol Atorn was an astronomical object located in the Outer Rim Territories' Kanz sector. It was settled by Mandalorian emigrants and exiles. An individual grew up in the alleys of Kol Atorn and learned an accented version of the Mando'a language from the celestial body's settlers. The individual eventually became a famed Mandalorian leader with the title Mandalore the Hammerborn.

properties.name: Kol Huro
properties.description: Kol Huro was a terrestrial astronomical object. The journalist Caern Adan was detained and imprisoned by the Galactic Empire after he published a story about droid production forecasts on Kol Huro.

properties.name: Kolaador
properties.description: Kolaador was a planet in the Kolaador system of the Outer Rim Territories.

properties.name: Kolanda Station
properties.description: Kolanda Station was located on Latharra in the Yminis sector. During the Galactic Civil War, it was the site of a massacre of Rebel soldiers by Imperial forces acting on intelligence supplied by Krova the Hutt.

properties.name: Kolatill
properties.description: Kolatill was a planet located in the Kolatill system within the Kathol sector of the Outer Rim Territories. A stopping point for ships plying their business on the Trition Trade Route, the planet was located several days' travel from the sector capital, Kal'Shebbol. Noted as one of the sector's major repulsorlift manufacturing centers, Kolatill was ruled by the Kolatill Council until Imperial Moff Kentor Sarne was appointed to administer the Kathol sector in 2 BBY. In 0 ABY, the planet was placed under martial law, and most of the repulsorlift industry was ordered to produce combat speeders for Moff Sarne's forces.

properties.name: Koltine
properties.description: Koltine was a Wild Space world located within the star system of the same name as part of the Jahilid Drift region. More than a decade after the establishment of the Galactic Empire, the Kaleesh Imperial General Bentilais san Sk'ar led a strike force in conquering Koltine and other worlds along the Jahilid Drift. Sk'ar's victories there led to a boost in his reputation among Imperial admirals.

properties.name: Komnor
properties.description: Komnor was a planet located within the Outer Rim Territories. The planet was absorbed into Xim's Empire as he expanded his borders from the Kingdom of Cron. A few years before the Galactic Civil War, Han Solo met Chewbacca during a skirmish near Komnor. A vicious warlord later arrived in the system and evicted the Hutts from their home. The homeless Hutts complained to Jabba Desilijic Tiure, who assigned Dyyz Nataz with the job of assassinating the warlord.

properties.name: Kooda
properties.description: Kooda may refer to one of the following:

properties.name: Kooriva
properties.description: Kooriva was a terrestrial, tropical planet located within the Kooriva system of the Inner Rim. The adopted homeworld of the Koorivar species, the planet was purchased by the horned-humanoids after a lengthy legal battle with the Galactic Republic. While the planet suffered an economic crisis under the reign of the Humanocentric-biases of the Galactic Empire, Kooriva recovered and thrived under both New Republic and Galactic Alliance rule.

properties.name: Koovis
properties.description: Koovis was a planet in the Inner Rim. During the Galactic Civil War, Alliance operative Klev Natasken was captured by Imperial forces on the world, prompting the Alliance to commit Infiltrator squads to try and rescue him.

properties.name: Koozebane
properties.description: Koozebane was a planet located in the Outer Rim Territories.

properties.name: Kor Anjiliac
properties.description: Kor Anjiliac was a planet located in the Bootana Hutta region of Hutt Space. It was the throneworld of the Anjiliac kajidic.

properties.name: Kor Besadii
properties.description: Kor Besadii was a planet located in the Bootana Hutta region of Hutt Space. It was the throneworld of the Besadii kajidic. Ancient palaces of the Besadii kajidic sprawled across its surface.

properties.name: Kor Desilijic
properties.description: Kor Desilijic was a planet located in the Bootana Hutta region of Hutt Space. It was the throneworld of the Desilijic kajidic.

properties.name: Kor Gejalli
properties.description: Kor Gejalli was a planet located in the Bootana Hutta region of Hutt Space. It was the throneworld of the Gejalli kajidic, until the Anjiliacs crushed the Gejallis during a clan war and took over their throneworld. The sole survivor of the Gejalli kajidic, Vago Gejalli Thokka, was adopted by Popara Anjiliac Diresto.

properties.name: Kor Hestilic
properties.description: Kor Hestilic was a planet located in the Bootana Hutta region of Hutt Space. It was the throneworld of the Hestilic kajidic.

properties.name: Kor Hunamma
properties.description: Kor Hunamma was a planet located in the Bootana Hutta region of Hutt Space. It was a Hutt throneworld.

properties.name: Kor Jiramma
properties.description: Kor Jiramma was a planet located in the Bootana Hutta region of Hutt Space. It was the throneworld of the Jiramma kajidic.

properties.name: Kor Nasirii
properties.description: Kor Nasirii was a planet located in the Bootana Hutta region of Hutt Space. It was the throneworld of the Nasirii kajidic. A hyperlane connected Kor Nasirii to the planet of Kor Vosadii. During the Cold War between the Galactic Republic and the resurgent Sith Empire in 3643 BBY, Kor Nasirii housed databases belonging to members of the Hutt species. The information contained within the databases was used to blackmail prominent figures throughout the galaxy.

properties.name: Kor Nijiladii
properties.description: Kor Nijiladii was a planet located in the Bootana Hutta region of Hutt Space. It was a Hutt throneworld.

properties.name: Kor Oktanivii
properties.description: Kor Oktanivii was a planet located in the Bootana Hutta region of Hutt Space. It was a Hutt throneworld.

properties.name: Kor Trinivii
properties.description: Kor Trinivii was a planet located in the Bootana Hutta region of Hutt Space. It was the throneworld of the Trinivii kajidic.

properties.name: Kor Usilic
properties.description: Kor Usilic was a planet located in the Bootana Hutta region of Hutt Space. It was a Hutt throneworld.

properties.name: Kor Utoradii
properties.description: Kor Utoradii was a planet located in the Bootana Hutta region of Hutt Space. It was a throneworld of the Utoradii kajidic.

properties.name: Kor Vosadii
properties.description: Kor Vosadii was a planet located in the Bootana Hutta region of Hutt Space. It was the throneworld of the Vosadii kajidic.

properties.name: Korad
properties.description: Korad was a planet in Elrood sector on the Elrood-Derilyn Trade Route. It was covered with starship and vehicle wrecks and was, in essence, a massive salvage yard operated during the Old Republic era by a corporation called Renew which eventually went bankrupt. During the Rebellion era many refugees and scavengers inhabited the planet. It was the homeworld of Slythor, a Squib crime lord.

properties.name: Korbin
properties.poi: Korbin Equatorial Range, Gornt Seron's castleRefin, Selenfer, Korbin Starport, Kyrf plantation, Last Call,
properties.description: Korbin was a planet in the Inner Rim.

properties.name: Korda
properties.description: Visler Korda was a male human officer in the military of the Galactic Empire, first serving as a captain and then as a commodore. A cruel man, he once set up a trap to capture Milo and Lina Graf, two younglings whose parents had been abducted by Imperial agents some time earlier.

properties.name: Kordu
properties.description: Kordu was a planet located in the Mid Rim's Kordu sector. The Kriss were native to the planet.

properties.name: Korev
properties.description: Korev VII was an astronomical object that occupied the seventh orbital position in the Korev system, a part of the Zaric sector in the Slice portion of the Inner Rim.
