At some point between 0 ABY and 4 ABY, Moff Linis of the Galactic Empire issued from Korev VII a bounty on the Wookiee Cherioer.

properties.name: Korfo
properties.description: Korfo II was a planet in the Korfo system of the Core Worlds. The Imperial Bank of Korfo II included the planet's name in its title. The Galactic Empire kept an Imperial Liaison Officer on Korfo II. At one point during the Galactic Civil War, the Liaison Officer was Lieutenant Pandur.

properties.name: Korlings
properties.description: Korlings was a planet in the Korlings system, located in the Outer Rim, and home to a noble family. It was rumored to be the homeworld of the notorious pirate Faarl the Conqueror.

properties.name: Kormoran
properties.description: Kormoran was a planet located in the galaxy's Outer Rim Territories that was a site of an Imperial attack. During the blitz, TIE Fighters were sent in to clear the roads of over 90,000 refugees. After the attack, one of the TIE pilots went AWOL and joined the Rebellion. He later became an X-wing pilot.

properties.name: Korphir
properties.description: Korphir was an Imperial planet during the Galactic Civil War.

properties.name: Korriz
properties.description: Korriz was an industrial planet in the Korriz system in the Sith Worlds, a region of space within the Stygian Caldera nebula in the Outer Rim's Esstran sector. Located on the Descri Wris hyperlane, Korriz was part of the Sith Empire before its collapse in the Great Hyperspace War of 5000 BBY, and around that time, it was the site of a workshop owned by the Sith Lord Tritos Nal. Agents of the Sith Lord known as the Patron went to Korriz in order to steal Garu's Warblade, a Sith sword that Tritos Nal had made for the Sith Lord Garu, and they successfully stole the weapon despite the efforts of Garu's agents to stop them. Korriz became a part of the reconstituted Empire by the time of the Cold War between the Empire and the Galactic Republic, when an Imperial cargo ship was diverted from its flight plan by pirates after departing Korriz.

properties.name: Koru Neimoidia
properties.description: Koru Neimoidia was one of the purse worlds founded by the Neimoidian race, along with Deko Neimoidia and Cato Neimoidia.

properties.name: Korvaii
properties.description: Korvaii was a small agriworld located in the Mid Rim's Kordu sector.

properties.name: Kostra
properties.description: Kostra was a planet located in the Mid Rim.

properties.name: Kothlis
properties.description: Kothlis was a Bothan colony world located in the Kothlis system of the Bothan sector in the Mid Rim. It was the fourth of seven planets in the star system, and was orbited by three small moons and an asteroid field.

properties.name: Kovor
properties.description: Kovor was a planet where a battle occurred during the Galactic War between the reconstituted Sith Empire and Galactic Republic, which the latter won thanks to the intervention of the Coruscant Aegis squadron.

properties.name: Kowak
properties.description: Kowak was a tropical planet in the Outer Rim and the homeworld of the Kowakian monkey-lizard species.

properties.name: Krake's Planet
properties.description: Krake's Planet was a planet in the Outer Rim's Demetras sector that was home to the Imperial Krake Data Vault during the Galactic Civil War. A small, rocky world, Krake's Planet was home to a species of large slugs that carved massive, twisting tunnels through the planet's surface. Krake Data Vault was formed out of a type of crystal cocoon created by the slugs, and repurposed by the Imperials to control the slugs' movements and conain the main personnel records for the Imperial military. Krake's Planet was visited by Rebel heroes Luke Skywalker and Chewbacca in 3 ABY, on a mission to retrieve information on Imperial double agent Shira Brie that resulted in the vault's destruction.

properties.name: Krann
properties.poi: Black Jungle, Cathedral of Shade, Mon Tondievz Mine, Tagge camp, Wages of Phy'r,
properties.description: Krann was a planet in the Expansion Region, on the Harrin Trade Corridor. It was taken over by the Galactic Empire for its nova crystals, and the native Kluuzot were enslaved. Following the Battle of Endor, the sector governor seceded and established a neutral terrority. The Kluuzot were freed, and various commercial investors moved to the planet.

properties.name: Krant
properties.poi: Ghost Base, Camp Sagol, Camp Kaxol, Jedi ruins, Sith temples, ,
properties.description: Krant was a wilderness planet in the Bothan sector. It saw action from the Clone Wars and the Galactic Civil War, and the Jedi Master Echuu Shen-Jon hid on Krant during decades until Princess Leia Organa appeared on the planet, searching for the Bothan agent Utric Sandov.

properties.name: Krayiss
properties.description: Krayiss II, also referred to as Krayiss Two, was a planet in the Outer Rim, in the remote Sith Worlds region of the Stygian Caldera nebula. Connected to other nearby worlds by the Nache Bhelfia hyperlane, Krayiss II was considered one of the five sacred Sith planets that formed the heart of the Sith Empire. In ancient times, Krayiss II was home to a massive library-temple that was a place of meditation and study for Sith sorcerers. However, after 14,000 BBY, it was buried and largely forgotten, with its large obelisk being all that remained above ground. Still, Krayiss II attracted a number of Jedi seeking to learn the secrets of the ancient temple. In 4000 BBY, a Jedi Knight named Vara Nreem traveled to the world for this purpose, but she was deemed unworthy by the Sith spirits that dwelled within the ruin. As a result, Nreem was killed and made to suffer in torment for eternity.

properties.name: Kreeling
properties.description: Kreeling was a planet where Moranda Savich managed to avoid capture by Hal Horn.

properties.name: Krenhner
properties.description: Krenhner was a planet located in the Krenhner sector of the Inner Rim.

properties.name: Krevas
properties.description: Krevas was a swampy planet in the Outer Rim and the homeworld of the Krevaaki.

properties.name: Kriekaal
properties.description: Kriekaal was a planet in the Kriekaal system, and the homeworld of the Krieks. Its continents were composed of hardened duranium and its shallow oceans of molten duranium.

properties.name: Kril'Dor
properties.description: Kril'Dor was a gas giant planet that was located on the Mid Rim. It was a known source of tibanna.

properties.name: Krinemonen
properties.description: Krinemonen was a gas giant planet in Calamari sector orbited by the oceanic moon of Krinemonen III.

properties.name: Krintrino
properties.description: Krintrino was a planet. During the early stages of the Galactic Civil War, Imperial forces were responsible for the destruction of an Rebel Alliance resistance cell that was based there, about five years prior to the Battle of Yavin.

properties.name: Kriselist
properties.description: Kriselist was a planet in the Wornal sector of the Mid Rim.

properties.name: Krmar
properties.description: Krmar may refer to one of the following:

properties.name: Krnay
properties.description: Krnay was a planet within the Mid Rim. Rith Murisson was from Krnay.

properties.name: Kroctar
properties.description: Kroctar was the homeworld of the Kroctari, and the capital and merchant center of the Shataum sector.

properties.name: Kromus
properties.description: Kromus was the fourth planet in the Kro'eval system. It had a rich biosphere, and by the time of the Clone Wars, it had a sentient population of 1.3 billion.

properties.name: Krozurbia
properties.description: Krozurbia was a planet located in the Outer Rim's Shadola sector. It was the homeworld of the Krozurbian species. They were engaged in two hundred years of war until peace was brought about due to the intervention of the Ithorian Zorneth.

properties.name: Kruskan
properties.description: Kruskan was a planet located on the far fringes of the Colundra sector of the Outer Rim Territories.

properties.name: Krylon
properties.description: Krylon was a planet in the Gordian Reach. It was the dominant planet of the Pinooran Spur, a polluted, industrial world dominated by Hynese companies, however it was not very important in this region of space.

properties.name: Ktil
properties.description: Ktil was an Inner Rim planet that was the homeworld of the Ktilac species. It was a part of the Ktilac Regions, a group of star systems which the Ktilac co-inhabited with the Murachauns and the Tocoyans. Ktil had become a member of the Galactic Republic by 17,000 BBY, and it eventually became a part of the Galactic Empire and the New Republic as well.

properties.name: Kuar
properties.description: Kuar was a Deep Core world of flat, rocky, dusty plains.

properties.name: Kuat
properties.poi: Gardens of Tralala, Nebula OrchidTekshar Falls
properties.description: Kuat was a planet located in the Core Worlds and one of the earliest members of the Galactic Republic. It was best known as the home of Kuat Drive Yards. These famous shipyards, used to build ships for both the Galactic Republic and later the Galactic Empire, circled the planet for thousands of kilometers.

properties.name: Kubindi
properties.description: Kubindi was a terrestrial world and home to the Kubaz. Kubindi orbited a blue giant star that emitted powerful solar flares. The planet was regularly hit with this radiation, causing erratic weather patterns and making the world dry and arid.

properties.name: Kumru
properties.description: Kumru was a thriving industrial world positioned along the Corellian Trade Spine in the Javin sector of the Outer Rim Territories. The planet was originally governed by the Mugaari species, who surrendered their territorial holdings to the Galactic Republic following hostilities. To the aversion of many of their kin, Kumru's substantial Mugaari population coexisted well with Humans, Lutrillians, and Nothoiins.

properties.name: Kuna's Eye
properties.description: Kuna's Eye was a blue giant star in the star system of the same name, located within the Moddell subsector of the Outer Rim Territories' Zuma sector. It was less than 1,000 light-years above the galactic plane, within the thin disk and the Inner Zuma Region. In 43 ABY, it was still relatively young and was surrounded by a protoplanetary disk, which contained minerals, metals, and alloys. The parent system of Kuna's Eye was frequented by prospectors, whose needs were served by the space station and shadowport known as the Mote.

properties.name: Kuna's Fist
properties.description: Kuna's Fist was a red giant–type star located in the Kuna's Fist system. It lay within the Outer Moddell systems area of the Moddell sector, one of the subsectors making up the Inner Zuma Region within the Outer Rim Territories' Zuma sector. It was connected by hyperlanes to the Kuna's Eye, Kuna's Horn, and Kuna's Tail systems.

properties.name: Kuna's Horn
properties.description: Kuna's Horn was a red giant–type star located in the star system of the same name. It was situated in the Outer Moddell systems area of the Moddell sector, one of the subsectors constituting the Inner Zuma Region within the Outer Rim Territories' Zuma sector. A hyperlane connected the star to the Kuna's Fist system.

properties.name: Kuna's Tail
properties.description: Kuna's Tail was a location in the Moddell sector of the Outer Rim Territories. Before the Battle of Endor in 4 ABY, Kuna's Tail was featured as part of a map composed by Corporal Ractivelle of the Stardust unit for the preparation of the Rebel Alliance's attack on the second Death Star.

properties.name: Kuna's Tooth
properties.poi: Doestes High Port , Rokna Blue cookhouses,
properties.description: Kuna's Tooth, also known as the Tooth, was a cool Outer Rim Territories mining planet located in the Moddell sector. The site of an orbital shipyard called Doestes High Port, the planet was governed by a bureaucracy and inhabited by members of the Ayrou, Human, and Vashan species. Years after the Battle of Endor, Kuna's Tooth hosted backalley cookhouses where smuggled-in Rokna tree fungus from the Endor system was processed into the Rokna Blue drug before being transported into the wider galaxy.

properties.name: Kur Minor
properties.description: The Kur Minor system was a part of Wild Space. It contained the Kur forests.

properties.name: Kuras
properties.description: Kuras was the Kuras system's primary star. It was a white dwarf. The system's primary was given the name "Kuras" by the ancient Coynite species, who placed the star in the constellation of Kezz'Sreik'Kuras.

properties.name: Kuratooine
properties.poi: Black Crest MountainChakham Army BaseRimsaw Station , Skifter Station
properties.description: Kuratooine was a planet in Wild Space. Though it was home to several Galactic Alliance Army bases and a Galactic Alliance embassy, it was not officially part of the Alliance and continued to maintain its own system of laws and its own government. Its capital was Kura City. Turman Durra and Myri Antilles traveled to the city, disguised as honeymooners, as the other members of Wraith Squadron in different disguises traveled in pairs or threes, in order to set up their new temporary HQ for their operation.

properties.name: Kurdavvia
properties.description: Kurdavvia was a planet in the Core Worlds of the galaxy known for its bright sunrises. Princess Kalieva K'ntarr's face lit up like one when Sienn Sconn agreed to help her gain passage off of Rydonni Prime.

properties.name: Kursid
properties.poi: Kursid arid plateau, Kursid totemic figures, Principal city of the Sith cult, Sith ships replicas,
properties.description: Kursid was a planet in Esstran sector of the Outer Rim Territories of the galaxy. It was inhabited by a species of primitive humanoids whose sole contact with the greater galaxy was through training missions conducted to the planet by the Order of the Sith Lords.

properties.name: Kushibah
properties.description: Kushibah was a planet in the Gordian Reach sector of the Outer Rim Territories. It was home to the primitive lagomorph Kushiban species, most notably the Jedi Master Ikrit. The planet had no cities and limited technology.

properties.name: Kutag
properties.description: Kutag was an Imperial factory farm world that was maintained by droids. It was in the Doornik-881 system and orbited the star Doornik-881 in the Koornacht Cluster. Its inhabitants were killed in the Great Purge by the Yevetha, who took over the planet.

properties.name: Kvabja
properties.description: Kvabja was a planet which was ruled over by a monarch called a Mrahash. Presumably, the Mrahash and the planet itself had little military power during the time of the New Republic, and was controlled by a Drach'nam named Chay Praysh and his slaver consortium. Praysh didn't dwell on Kvabja, though, and lived in his headquarters on the planet Torpris.

properties.name: Kwannot
properties.description: Kwannot was a Mid Rim planet where Aurra Sing killed Mana Veridi sometime prior to 32 BBY.

properties.name: Kwapi
properties.description: Kwapi may refer to one of the following:

properties.name: Kwenn Space Station
properties.description: The Kwenn Space Station, sometimes called Space Station Kwenn, was a space station that orbited the world of Kwenn.

properties.name: Kwevron
properties.description: Kwevron was an Outer Rim Territories agriworld. It was a lightly populated world, with almost of all of its people engaged in farming. An Imperial Prefect oversaw its starport during the Galactic Civil War. Hills and fields covered most of its surface.

properties.name: Kwookrrr
properties.description: Kwookrrr was a planet where the Galactic Empire used enslaved Wookiee children for labor in factories and farms. It had previously been a Wookiee colony world.

properties.name: KyLessia
properties.description: KyLessia was located within the KyLessia system. It was the homeworld of wulfruit trees, KyLessian fruit bats, and KyLessian feather mites. Its exports included KyLessian Fruit Distillate, a popular Outer Rim alcohol.

properties.name: Kynachi
properties.description: Kynachi was a remote Wild Space planet and the base of KynachTech Industries. In 32 BBY, the world was seized by the Trade Federation, and the Skakoan Overseer Umbrag took over the KynachTech factory, also imposing a frequency jammer on the world. The planet's isolation led the rest of the galaxy to believe that it had simply become isolated out of choice. The planet's captive inhabitants were liberated in 21 BBY from the KynachTech factory prison by the Galactic Republic self-proclaimed Breakout Squad unit.

properties.name: Kyoloria
properties.description: The Kyoloria system was a star system that was located within the Xappyh sector, which was a part of the Outer Rim Territories region of the galaxy. The system was the origin point of the Kyolorian snake-god deity.

properties.name: Kyrouac
properties.poi: Montalvia cantina, Montalvia city jail, Montalvia spaceport, Rebel lodgings,
properties.description: Kyrouac was a backwater Inner Rim farming planet held by the Galactic Empire. The planet's fauna included brush bats and a shelled creature residing in the Spiral Sea. The Kyrouaquian population was governed by the Kyrouaquian High Council, and the planet's capital of Montalvia was the only settlement with a spaceport.

properties.name: Kyrska
properties.description: Kyrska may refer to one of the following:

properties.name: Kyryll's World
properties.description: Kyryll's World was a terrestrial planet located in the Kyryll's World system, a part of the Phelleem sector in the Slice portion of the Outer Rim Territories. It was the homeworld of the sentient Pui-ui species, members of which communicated in the Pui-ui language and which was known to the wider galaxy by 671 BBY.

properties.name: Laakteen Depot
properties.description: Laakteen Depot, located just off the Giju Run hyperlane in the Colonies region, was a pirate base and later the Rebel Alliance's closest outpost to the planet Fondor early during the Galactic Civil War against the Galactic Empire. The Rebellion fought nearly a year to win Laakteen Depot, capturing the base through the efforts of ace starship mechanic Kufra Ahara and the Sanjin Green Hawks.

properties.name: Laboi
properties.description: The Laboi were a species of sentient, fur-covered, serpentine mammals. They ranged from two to ten meters long, but despite their size, a lack of limbs limited them to manipulating only simple technology that depended on grasping basic tools with the tail or mouth. Some female Laboi had natural telekinetic powers that augmented their ability to interact with their surroundings. The Laboi hailed from the planet Laboi II, a world that took 4,040 hours to rotate on its axis. Although this long day resulted in blistering heat in the daytime and biting cold in the night, the Laboi were well adapted to both extremes. Their fur changed color; it turned white in the day to reflect heat and turned bright primary colors at night as camouflage against Laboi II's mineral forests.

properties.name: Ladarra
properties.description: Ladarra was a desert planet in the Gordian Reach along the Pinooran Spur. It was the location of the Human colony of New Hope Settlement. The planet was colonized during the days of the Old Republic and ended up becoming a failed chromium mine. By the time of the Galactic Empire, the planet's people were dying out. All that was left were poor farmers, hermits and fugitives, as well as some dust balls from the rust-colored desert.

properties.name: Ladro
properties.description: Ladro was a planet in the Colonies that supported the Rebel Alliance during the Galactic Civil War.

properties.name: Laertos
properties.description: Laertos was a planet the primary spaceport of which had a Rebel Alliance drop point.

properties.name: Lafra
properties.description: Lafra was a planet in the Wyl sector of the Outer Rim with a variety of terrains. It was the home world of the Lafrarians, gray-skinned, avian humanoids who were once flyers but lost this ability over eons of evolutionary change. They built their homes in high, inaccessible locations on the planet . Nearly everyone on the world owned a flying conveyance, with few land or water transports seeing use.

properties.name: Lahag Erli
properties.description: Lahag Erli was a planet whose natives attacked and occupied the Har system for many years.

properties.name: Lahsbane
properties.description: Lahsbane was a planet located in the Onatos sector of the Mid Rim. It was the homeworld of the Lahsbees and Huhks.

properties.name: Laim
properties.description: The Laim system was a star system located within Rayter sector of the Outer Rim Territories. The system was devoid of planets, but had a subspace relay station which was part of the Rayter Sector Subspace Broadcast Network. It was four hours' hyperspace travel from the Najarka system and six hours' travel from the Narg system with a standard hyperdrive.

properties.name: Lakra
properties.description: The Lakra  were a sentient species native to the Lakra system in Wild Space. They had torso plates and large hands, and were possibly insectile. At some point, their species, or a group of their species, were hired as mercenaries by the Warlord and aided him in conquering Kariek around 28 BBY. They served him until his defeat by the Eickarie's and the Empire of the Hand in the Battle of Kariek.

properties.name: Lalmy'ash
properties.description: The Lalmy'ash system was located in the Interior Region, an area of the Hapes Cluster in the Slice portion of the Inner Rim. It was connected via hyperlanes to the Archais and Millinar systems. The Lalmy'ash system was the origin point of the gemstones known as Lalmy'ashian pearls.

properties.name: Lamaredd
properties.poi: Little Mon Cal, ORO Mining Station LM0228, The Rank,
properties.description: Lamaredd, also known as Great Menahua, was a planet in the Lamaro system of the Outer Rim Territories. With water covering 85% of its surface, Lamaredd was rich in minerals and seafood, as well as having its own native sentient species, the primitive Menahuun.

properties.name: Lamuir
properties.poi: Green Mist tavernHerglic archeological ruinsLake Aire hotel
properties.description: Lamuir IV was a planet in the Tapani sector's Freeworlds Territory. It was formerly part of the Herglic Trade Empire. The Priole Danna Festival was held there.

properties.name: Lamus
properties.description: Lamus was a moon of an Outer Rim Territories planet. It was inhabited by the A'Mar people. Its equator was forested; its poles were deserts with sinkholes. Gundarks inhabited the moon. One of the moon's settlements was the town of Vidge-Ribu, a low-tech agrarian community.

properties.name: Lan Barell
properties.description: Lan Barell was a dusty, dry neutral backwater planet located on the Outer Rim of the galaxy near Breshkall. Heavy iron content in the soil gave the planet a faint blue sheen, and when combined with the red glare of its sun, gave the planet a garish and gloomy atmosphere.

properties.name: Langhesa
properties.description: Langhesa was the Langhesi homeworld presumably found in the Langhesa system, conquered in 129 BBY by the Tsinimals. This led to a mass migration of Langhesi offworld.

properties.name: Langoona
properties.description: Langoona was a remote world located in the Bootana Hutta region of Hutt Space.

properties.name: Lanjer
properties.description: Lanjer was a remote planet that defied Emperor Palpatine shortly after the formation of the Galactic Empire. Like the other worlds that refused to cooperate, Lanjer suffered an unspecified devastation as a result.

properties.name: Lankashiir
properties.description: Lankashiir was a planet of the Lankashiir system, within the Colonies region of the galaxy. During the Imperial Period, Lankashiir was under the control of the Galactic Empire. A planet thriving with forests, Lankashiir was home to Adion Lang, a lieutenant serving with the Imperial Security Bureau, and the Durasha family, a Human family with strong Imperial ties.

properties.name: Lannik
properties.description: Lannik was the home planet of the Lannik species, located in Lannik Space of the Mid Rim.

properties.name: Lanos
properties.description: Lanos was a member world of the Galactic Republic during the Clone Wars. Around 22 BBY, it was attacked by the Confederacy of Independent Systems and became the subject of propaganda on the Republic's HoloNet News, which claimed that the Separatists were liberating it from a "crushing servitude to the corrupt and decayed Republic."

properties.name: Lansono
properties.description: Lansono was a planet represented in the Galactic Senate of the Galactic Republic by Candabrine Bu during the leadup to the Clone Wars. Senator Bu voiced his doubts over Supreme Chancellor Palpatine's leadership to HoloNet News reporters, following the attempted assassination of Senator Padmé Amidala.

properties.name: Lant
properties.description: Lant was the planet in the Lant system, a star system in the Periphery, a sector in the Outer Rim within Hutt Space. Lant was a trade world with extensive Hutt holdings.

properties.name: Lanteeb
properties.description: Lanteeb was a neutral pastoral planet in the Malor-77 system. While aligned with the Galactic Republic, it did not have a representative in the Galactic Senate. It was located equidistant between Rattatak and Bespin. It was located in Bri'ahl sector.

properties.name: Lanthe
properties.description: Lanthe was a planet in the Mid Rim's Var Hagen sector. It was the original headquarters of Lanthe Artifice, but when the local Imperial Moff nationalized all corporations, Lanthe Artifice relocated to the Tapani sector.

properties.name: Lanthrym
properties.poi: Bars, clubs, casinos, arenas for gladiatorcombat, hotels,
properties.description: Lanthrym was a planet in the Elrood sector. It was on this planet that Cermack Rustill boarded the Shining Comet which was en route to Bodrin. It was considered a good port for pirates. There was a sizable Gamorrean population living there.

properties.name: Lantillies
properties.description: Lantillies was a planet in the Lantillies system and the sector capital of the Lantillian sector in the Mid Rim. Located along the Perlemian Trade Route and at the head of the Randon Run, Lantillies was heavily involved in the shipping and shipbuilding industries, and its Human natives were well-known for their emphasis on reliability over elegance. Lantillies was conquered by the Honorable Union of Desevro & Tion early in galactic history, though the planet was a member of the Galactic Republic through much of the government's history. Lantillies later became a stronghold of the New Republic during the Yuuzhan Vong War of 25–29 ABY.

properties.name: Laramus
properties.description: Laramus was the location of Laramus Base, headquarters of the Laramus Base Irregulars, as well as a rapidly-growing Rebel cell. The Visseon II led a Rebel ambush of an Imperial convoy over Laramus. The Empire later destroyed much of the planet's surface, forcing the Irregulars to leave.

properties.name: Laria
properties.description: Laria was an Outer Rim Territories celestial body located in the Rseik sector. By 3643 BBY, dozens of star-charts, accompanied by notes in a forgotten language, had been stored in computer banks inside ancient ruins on Laria. Around that year, archaeologists were able to restore the charts. Millennia later, the Trade Federation improved the facilities of Laria's spaceport.

properties.name: Las Lagon
properties.description: A planet in the Galactic Alliance Senate composition, Las Lagon seceded from the Galactic Alliance during the Second Galactic Civil War.

properties.name: Lasan
properties.description: Lasan was a Wild Space planet. An arid and warm world, its surface featured desert and plains as well as high mountains. Lasan was inhabited by herbivorous banthas and the sentient, humanoid Lasat.

properties.name: Lastelle
properties.description: The Lastelle system was a star system located in the Tapani sector's Mecetti Province, on the Procopian Shipping Lane.

properties.name: Latoma
properties.description: Latoma was a planet in the Latoma system in the Brak sector of the Expansion Region. It was a small rocky planetoid and covered in impact craters. The planet was used by Byro Ti'mere to distract visitors and bounty hunters searching for his secret base on Brugga. Ti'mere established the ruins of an outpost on the planet to throw off suspicions that he was still operating out of the Latoma system and convince them he had moved elsewhere.

properties.name: Laud
properties.description: The Laud system was a star system in the Brak sector of the Expansion Region. The system contained at least one gas giant, which Lant Mining Corporation conducted gas mining operations.

properties.name: Lavisar
properties.description: A planet in the Strabin sector, Lavisar was once part of a larger high-gravity world. It was a medium-sized world of reddish-brown rock with an abundance of heavy metal ores and a few dark seas and abundant mining and refining industries. It remained neutral in the Galactic Civil War until conquered by Warlord Zsinj. It was the headquarters of Skyrung Manufacturing, a licensed builder of Lambda-class shuttles. The main port city was known as Syward.

properties.name: Lazerian
properties.description: Lazerian or Lazeria can refer to the following:

properties.name: Leafar
properties.description: The Leafar were a group involved in merchant shipping based out of the Leafar system. Shortly after the Battle of Yavin, they began to challenge the Galactic Empire. The Empire responded by sending the Imperial-class Star Destroyer Badi Dea to attack their shipping convoys. The ambush was foiled by the Alliance to Restore the Republic, which, initially, sent five X-wing starfighters to protect Leafar shipping. Three separate groups of Leafar ships were defended by the Alliance, which called in reinforcements as the battle continued. The Leafar later aided the Alliance by supplying it with information on a new shield technology being produced by the Empire.

properties.name: Lelmra
properties.description: Lelmra was a mountainous planet in the Churba sector of the Mid Rim. At one time, it was the headquarters of Garm Bel Iblis, and also served as a backup base for the smuggler organization of Mazzic.

properties.name: Lemmi
properties.description: Lemmi VI was a rainforest planet in the Lemmi system of the Hapes Cluster. It was home to the carnivorous Millennium blossom, as well as several other huge creatures. One beast moved about on pogo-stick legs, crushing all its path.

properties.name: Lenniera
properties.description: Lenniera was a planet in the Core Worlds.

properties.name: Lenthalis
properties.description: Lenthalis was the sector capital of the Spirva sector. Its largest continent was Basin. The capital city was Hreas Port City. It was the headquarters of Galladinium Galactic Exports, one of the galaxy's largest shipping corporations, founded by Galladinium around 50 BBY, from which it published annuals of Galladinium's Galactic Datalog of Fantastic Technology. The Galactic Empire banned the Datalog since it was being used by the Rebel Alliance to purchase weapons. Hreas contained the Commerce Concourse, where a series of gang-rivalry riots broke out shortly before the Battle of Hoth.

properties.name: Lequabis
properties.description: The Lequabis system was an Expansion Region star system. Following the Imperial occupation of Cloud City on the planet Bespin in 3 ABY, the Rebel Alliance was forced to search for other sources of the important Tibanna gas. Alliance Captain Eedan therefore tasked a group of Rebel agents with surveying gas giant planets in several star systems. The exploration of the Lequabis system eventually proved fruitless, and the Rebel scouts continued with their search in the Poviduze system.

properties.name: Lerct
properties.description: Lerct was a planet in the Prackla sector of the Expansion Region. It was the site of the Lerct Historical Institute.

properties.name: Leresen
properties.description: The Leresai  of the Mid Rim were a species which sided against the Bothans during the Caamas Document crisis in 19 ABY. When two Leresai were killed in a riot on Bothawui, Leresen law  demanded retribution. According to the Leresai, since the Bothans refused to turn over the guilty security guards, the Leresai were entitled to kill twenty innocent Bothans. They accomplished this by destroying a zero-gravity crystal factory in Bothawui orbit, carrying a crew of twenty-one. General Wedge Antilles and Rogue Squadron attempted to stop the Leresai warships, but the weapons systems on their X-wings had been sabotaged by Leresai on Di'tai'ni. The Leresai openly admitted this sabotage - in their view, it was an honorable action that prevented neutral New Republic forces from harm.

properties.name: Leria Kerlsil
properties.poi: Melilla Sea, Keri Sea, Remel Sea,
properties.description: Leria Kerlsil was a planet in the Core Worlds. It allowed Refugee Relief Movement settlement in 22 BBY, shortly before the Clone Wars, but only by wealthy single men. At the time of the New Republic, the planet had a population of 300,000. Leria Kerlsil was the only planet known to be home to Life-bearers, also known as life-witches.

properties.name: Leritor
properties.description: Leritor was a mineral-rich Mid Rim planet of rolling plains and oceans. The native Sauvax engaged in aquaculture; Human colonists mined the minerals. Amid a brewing war between the colonists and the Sauvax, Profex Rynalla attempted to excavate a Sith artifact buried within the planet's mountainous Bleaks.

properties.name: Lessuris
properties.description: Lessuris was a backwater planet located within the Lessuris system of the Outer Rim Territories. Luskin Exovar was born on Lessuris.

properties.name: Lesu
properties.description: Lesu was a world located in the Lesu system, a part of the Outer Rim Territories' Dail sector. Around 10 ABY, it served as the homeworld of Malakin Enterprises, a criminal organization that constituted a part of the Tenloss Syndicate.

properties.name: Letaki
properties.description: The Letaki were a species of sentient beings distinguished by eight tentacles, an egg-shaped head, four eyes, and a sharp beak. Two sets of gills allowed them to breathe in both air and water. They were able to focus their eyes on more than one object at a time, and to use their limbs to manipulate several items independently. As carnivores, Letaki gutted their dinners. The Letaki vocal range was higher than that of most species. The musician Evar Orbus, leader of Evar Orbus and His Galactic Jizz-Wailers, was a Letaki, and his species hailed from the Letaki system in the Outer Rim.

properties.name: Letev
properties.description: The Letev system was a star system that was located within the Freeworlds Territory of the Tapani sector in the Colonies region of the galaxy. It was situated between the Tavya and Jappe systems.

properties.name: Lettow
properties.description: Lettow was a planet in the Lettow system of the Core Worlds, just on the border of the Deep Core. Early in the Galactic Republic's history, the planet served as the headquarters of the Dark Jedi of the Legions of Lettow, though the First Great Schism between the Legions and the Jedi Order ended in a final battle on Lettow.

properties.name: Lexas Prime
properties.description: The Lexas Prime system was located in the Kessel sector, a part of the Slice portion of the Outer Rim Territories. It was one of the Lexas systems.

properties.name: Lexrul
properties.description: Lexrul was an urban planet located in the Trax sector of the Mid Rim.

properties.name: Lialic
properties.description: Lialic was an astronomical object located in the regions known as the Deep Core and the Interior. It was also situated in the grid square K-12 of the Standard Galactic Grid.

properties.name: Lianna
properties.poi: Santhe/Sienar Technologies Corporate Headquarters, SessweSantheship 23NorthwestPorthartonPlutrefin 734Lasarcompfac 5MelfordMelford Star Academy, Bantha TraxxLandraAnai
properties.description: Lianna was the fourth planet of the Lianna system in the Allied Tion sector of the Outer Rim Territories. The ecumenopolis was the homeworld of House Santhe and the headquarters of Santhe/Sienar Technologies. Located on the junction of the Perlemian Trade Route, the Cadinth Run and the Shaltin Tunnels, Lianna was one of the busiest ports in the Tion Cluster.

properties.name: Liaq
properties.description: Liaq was a planet where Rebel officer Beryl Chiffonage had a casual fight with mercenaries.

properties.name: Licha In
properties.description: Licha In was a world of the Gree Enclave and the first to suffer from the degeneration of Gree society. This resulted in the reputation that this world's inhabitants were both wild and backward; an example of what happened to the Gree during their decline, an example at least seen by the Gree of other worlds.

properties.name: Liintaar
properties.description: Liintaar Station was an Alliance communication base during the Galactic Civil War. The base was attacked by the Empire during the war.

properties.name: Linuri
properties.description: Linuri was a planet in the Doldur sector with a diverse ecosystem. Most of the planet's regions could support humanoid life.

properties.name: Liok
properties.description: Liok was a planet in Ciutric sector in Outer Rim Territories, where archaeologists discovered the Shadow Traproom.

properties.name: Lipsec
properties.description: Lipsec was an Outer Rim Territories astronomical object located in grid square I-18 of the Standard Galactic Grid. A hyperspace route connected it to the Virgillia system. Lipsec shared its name with the Expansion Region route known as the Lipsec Run.

properties.name: Lirra
properties.description: Lirra was an Outer Rim planet with mineral pools and mud flats on its surface. Located within the Baxel sector close to the border with Hutt Space, Lirra was originally colonized by Human settlers, but almost a century prior to 2 ABY, the Humans on Lirra became outnumbered by members of the Hutt Jhank Shel clan.

properties.name: Lisal
properties.description: Lisal was a planet in the Mid Rim, rumored to be home to a Sith holocron.

properties.name: Listehol
properties.description: Listehol was a planet located in the Listehol system within the Outer Rim Territories.

properties.name: Listoria
properties.description: The Listoria system was a star system located in the Tapani sector's Cadriaan Province, between the Pavia system and the Cesya system.

properties.name: Little Atullus
properties.description: Little Atullus was an Inner Rim astronomical object located in the Anthos sector. It was the homeworld of a Galactic Republic soldier. During the soldier's childhood at the time of the Tionese War, traders from the planet Brentaal sold the boy's parents some farmland on the celestial body Okator VIII. After moving to his new home on Okator VIII, the boy eventually forgot about Little Atullus despite still seeing it in his dreams.

properties.name: Little Capella
properties.description: Little Capella was a planet in the Little Capella system in the Gordian Reach, a region in the Outer Rim Territories. In 2 ABY, the company Rapora Mining operated the Rapora Mining Center on Little Capella as one of many new facilities throughout the Outer Rim.

properties.name: Little Kessel
properties.description: Little Kessel was a planet located in the Kessel sector of the Outer Rim Territories.

properties.name: Little Petrovi
properties.description: Little Petrovi was a planet located in the Yushan sector of the Mid Rim.

properties.name: Little Talhovi
properties.description: Little Talhovi was a world located in the Little Talhovi system of the Juvex sector, a part of the Senex-Juvex region in the Western Reaches portion of the Mid Rim. A hyperlane connected it to the Talhovi system. Little Talhovi was considered to be a promising agriworld by 43 ABY and, like the rest of the Senex-Juvex worlds, was under the control of the region's aristocratic Ancient Houses.

properties.name: Liul
properties.description: Liul was a planet where RC-5108/8843 blew up a gas storage facility in 21 BBY.

properties.name: Livien
properties.description: Livien was a planet located within the Outer Rim Territories and the founding world of the Livien League.

properties.name: Llanic
properties.description: Llanic was a planet in the Karthakk sector of the Outer Rim.

properties.name: Llon Nebulae
properties.description: The Llon Nebulae, located in the Expansion Region, was the site of the Battle of the Llon Nebulae, where the Storm Fleet incurred some losses.

properties.name: Llorkan
properties.description: Llorkan was a planet and home to an Imperial army garrison. Llorkan was the original destination of Captain Norello's ship, Happer's Way, during his interrupted delivery of fifty AT-ST walkers.

properties.name: Lo'Uran
properties.description: Lo'Uran was a planet located in the Aparo sector of the Outer Rim Territories. Its governor was Blithane.

properties.name: Lobaoc
properties.description: Lobaoc was an Outer Rim Territories planet located in the Mieru'kar sector. Its surface featured lakes and marshes, which were home to the tentacled and omnivorous dianogas. Human and Near-Human farmers maintained several settlements on Lobaoc. At some point between 67 BBY and 19 BBY, the Jedi High Council of the Jedi Order learned of the existence of a young Force-sensitive girl on Lobaoc. The Jedi Council dispatched the Mon Calamari Jedi Ambaln to investigate the situation and bring the child back to the Order for Jedi training. Upon realizing that Ambaln had fallen to the dark side of the Force during a prior assignment, the Council also sent a group of individuals to Lobaoc after the fallen Jedi.

properties.name: Lobaq Station
properties.description: Lobaq Station was one of 752 Imperial military bases in the Outer Rim Territories' Rolion sector.

properties.name: Loce
properties.description: Loce was a planet in the galaxy that was the homeworld of the Locan species.

properties.name: Loedorvia
properties.description: Loedorvia was a celestial body located in the Core Worlds' Weemell sector. During the Clone Wars, it was the site of a battle between the Galactic Republic and the Confederacy of Independent Systems. During that confrontation, Confederate General Grievous ordered the release on Loedorvia of the disease known as the Brainrot Plague. The act killed tens of thousands of individuals and led to the deaths of nearly every Human in the Weemell sector.

properties.name: Loj
properties.description: Loj was a planet and the source of T'iil-T'iil, which was manufactured in the vicinity of its Moss Caverns.

properties.name: Lokondo
properties.description: Lokondo was an icy world in the Braxant sector of the Outer Rim.

properties.name: Lol
properties.description: Lol was a male native of Solem, living during the Galactic Civil War. He was part of a resistance movement against the planetary Governor, Malvander Bren.

properties.name: Lola Sayu
properties.description: Lola Sayu was a sulfurous, cracked planet that was home to the Citadel, a prison engineered to hold Jedi, during the Clone Wars.

properties.name: Lolnar
properties.description: Lolnar was a planet in the Core Worlds. Moff Lesan Ramier, commander of the Imperial forces in the Brak sector during the Galactic Civil War, was from Lolnar.

properties.name: Lonatro
properties.description: Lonatro was a world located within the Gree Enclave and served as the primary provider of foodstuffs to the Gree. During the height of the Gree civilization, this world's surface was dominated by farms and food producation facilities but after the decline of the Gree, 90% of the planet's surface was given over to game preserves and botanical gardens. The few remaining parcels of land still provided food for the Enclave.

properties.name: Londor
properties.description: The Londor system was located in the Londori sector, a part of the New Territories portion of the Mid Rim. The star system was connected by hyperlanes to the Ariarch, Valrar, Darkon, and Glee Anselm systems. It was the site of the Londori Mental Facility. By 12 ABY, the Londor system lay within territory controlled by the New Republic.

properties.name: Longwind
properties.description: Longwind was a planet located in the Trax sector of the Mid Rim.

properties.name: Lonnaw
properties.description: Lonnaw was a Mid Rim planet located on the Entralla Route. It served as the first scheduled stop on the shakedown cruise of the Galactic Republic exploratory vessel Outbound Flight in 27 BBY. Thirty-nine years later, Lonnaw was temporarily captured from the New Republic by the Imperial Remnant.

properties.name: Lontar
properties.description: The Lontars were a sentient species. They aggressively attacked Batorine, the homeworld of the Blood Carvers, several hundred years before the fall of the Galactic Republic. Intervention by the Galactic Senate was all that prevented the Lontars from eradicating the Blood Carvers.

properties.name: Loovria
properties.description: Loovria was a planet in the Juvex sector of the Mid Rim along the Senex-Juvex Loop known for its gladiator pits.

properties.name: Lopor Station
properties.description: Lopor Station was a planet in the Spirva sector of the Mid Rim. The bounty hunter Quantana started out his career as a child in the streets of the planet.

properties.name: Lorahns
properties.description: Lorahns was a Mid Rim planet near the Gamor Run.

properties.name: Lorardia
properties.description: Lorardia, or Lorardian, was a planet located in the D'Astan sector of the Outer Rim Territories.

properties.name: Loratus
properties.description: Loratus Manufacturing was a manufacturer of mobile weapons systems and related droids during the early years of the Galactic Empire. The company was known to be sympathetic to the Alliance to Restore the Republic, and many of its products found their way into the Alliance's military.

properties.name: Lorell
properties.description: Lorell was located just outside the Hapes Cluster. It was once base of the Lorell Raiders. It was later known for its kickboxing.

properties.name: Lorenz
properties.description: The Lorenz system was a star system located in the Tapani sector's Pelagia Province, situated along the Calipsa Run. It was annexed into Calipsa Province with the rise of the New Order.

properties.name: Loretto
properties.description: Loretto was the homeworld of the famed artist, Duos'tine.

properties.name: Lorimax
properties.description: Lorimax was a planet in Fakir sector. It was noted for growing grain.

properties.name: Lorista
properties.description: Lorista was a Mid Rim world of harsh wastelands. It was a Zabrak colony.

properties.name: Lorn
properties.description: Lorn could refer to:

properties.name: Loronar
properties.description: Loronar was the headquarters of Loronar Corporation and the site of the Loronar shipyards.

properties.name: Lorpfan
properties.description: Lorpfan was a city located amidst a vast desert on the planet Trandosha.

properties.name: Lorrad
properties.description: Lorrad was a dirty, urbanised planet in Allied Tion sector. Prior to 300 BBY it had been dominated by Barseg for millennia, enslaving the Lorradians in harrowing condition and forcing them to work in heavy-machinery factories producing tools, speeders, and H-12 copters. The Galactic Republic liberated Lorrad from the Kingdom of Barseg in 300 BBY, but Barseg's economic domination of the planet continued.

properties.name: Lorrd
properties.poi: Crypt of Martyrs, Lorrd Academy for Aquatic StudiesLorrd City SpaceportLorrd UniversityPerformance SquareSlave Pits of Lorrd, School of Conceptual DesignUniversity of Pangalactic Cultural Studies
properties.description: Lorrd was located in the Kanz sector and was home to the unique Lorrdian culture of baseline Humans. Lorrd was close to Bimmiel and its capital city was Lorrd City.

properties.name: Lorta
properties.description: Lorta was a Mid Rim world located on the Cerean Reach, near Jiroch-Reslia. It was was home to the violent and expansionist Lortans.

properties.name: Lota
properties.description: The Lota was one of the four akias of Aramandi society. They were based on the planet Aram, and the Lota system has been earmarked for the akia's future colonization. Preparations were underway for the Lota to begin colonization during the early years of the Galactic Civil War.

properties.name: Loth
properties.description: Loth was a planet located within the Loth system of the Inner Rim. It was home to a lifeform known as rubygrub cyst, which were similar to organocrystalline structures found in open water in the comet Stroiketcy.

properties.name: Lotho Minor
properties.description: Lotho Minor, also known as the Junk World or simply Lotho, was a planet located in the galaxy's Outer Rim Territories that was the homeworld of the Junker species. Used as a dumping ground, its surface was covered with junk and trash amassed over a number of generations, which brought salvage operations to the planet to find junk that could still be used. Following his defeat during the Battle of Naboo, the Sith Lord Darth Maul went into exile in the bowels of Lotho Minor, where he lost his mind until he was found by his brother, Savage Opress, over a decade later.

properties.name: Lotide
properties.description: Lotide was a planet in the Mortex sector of the Outer Rim Territories.

properties.name: Lovola
properties.description: The Lovola system was located in the Rifle Worlds, an area of the Hapes Cluster in the Slice portion of the Inner Rim. It was connected by the hyperlane known as the Great Rim Route to the Rifle Worlds' Maires system as well as the Ket system in the Lorelli Reach. The Lovola system was the origin point of the company known as Lovolan.

properties.name: Low'n
properties.description: Low'n was a populous world in the Romintine sector of the Mid Rim. It was the homeworld of the Lowen.

properties.name: Lowick
properties.description: Lowick was the homeworld of the Pa'lowick species.

properties.name: Lubang Minor
properties.description: Lubang Minor was a jungle planet widely considered nameless located in the Illisurevimurasi sector of the Outer Rim Territories.

properties.name: Lucazec
properties.description: Lucazec was a planet located within the Outer Rim Territories. Originally known as Far Thanium, it was absorbed into Xim's Empire as he expanded his borders from the Kingdom of Cron. Lucazec was a potential candidate for one of the lost thrones of Xim. After the fall of the empire in 25,100 BBY, it would eventually join the Galactic Republic. Lucazec was the Fallanassi world of origin. During the Clone Wars the planet was located within Separatist space. The Fallanassi fled the planet when Cassio Tagge tried to recruit them to the Empire.

properties.name: Lucrenn
properties.description: Lucrenn was a world located within the star system of the same name, a part of the Outer Rim Territories' Skine sector. Around the year 10 ABY, it served as the homeworld of Galindas Exports, a fencing operation and member of the criminal Tenloss Syndicate.

properties.name: Lujo
properties.description: Lujo was a planet in the Core. It had a temperate climate, and was home to magnificent oceans and landscapes.

properties.name: Lupani
properties.description: Lupani was a planet located in the Tapani sector's Lupani system.

properties.name: Luptoom
properties.description: Luptoom was an Outer Rim Territories planet situated in the Seswenna sector. The planet's Human population, known as Luptoomians, was known for its unusual style of clothing. During the Separatist Crisis, the Luptoomian Nar Hida opened a fashion store on the planet Coruscant.

properties.name: Lur
properties.description: Lur was an icy planet on the Outer Rim, known for the native Lurrian species, who were masters of genetic engineering. Located near the Corporate Sector, Lur was racked by severe storms and high winds, and the planet's dangerous wildlife forced the Lurrians to band into tight family groups as they evolved. As the planet's harsh environment limited their technological development, Lurrians advanced their society by mastering the flora and fauna around them, breeding and cloning purposely designed creatures that helped them build cities within Lur's glaciers. The Lurrians' genetic mastery attracted much attention to their beloved homeworld, especially in the aftermath of the Clone Wars, when the Galactic Empire quarantined the world due to fears their knowledge could be used for ill. That notoriety made Lur a popular target for slavers, as Lurrian genetic experts became valuable properties on the Invisible Market due to galaxy-wide restrictions on genetic experimentation.

properties.name: Lurania
properties.description: The Lurania system was located in the Slice portion of the Colonies. It was the origin point of the beverage known as Luranian brandy.

properties.name: Lurr
properties.description: Lurr was a planet in the Outer Rim's Rayter sector. One of the stormtroopers that accompanied the Sith Lord Darth Vader to Cheelit killed a young woman while on the planet. The Guild of Vindicators assassin Clat the Shamer later used the memories of that event to compel the soldier to commit suicide.

properties.name: Lusaanda
properties.description: Lusaanda was a planet in the Meram sector of the Outer Rim.

properties.name: Lusdu
properties.description: The Lusdu system was a star system located in the Core Worlds region of the galaxy. The system was located one hour from the Alderaan system via lightspeed. Several months after the Destruction of Alderaan, the Ithorian Herdship Bazaar visited the system, orbiting the main planet in the system.

properties.name: Lusk
properties.description: The Lusk system was in the Freeworlds Territory of the Tapani sector, near the Mennaalii, Don I, and Don II systems.

properties.name: Lust
properties.description: The Lust system was a star system that was located within the galaxy's Wild Space region. It was the origin point of the group known as the Lost Sultans of Lust.

properties.name: Lutrillia
properties.description: Lutrillia was a planet in the Yarith sector of the Outer Rim, on the Lutrillian Cross hyperlane. An important export of Lutrillia was ochroid dust.

properties.name: Luuhar
properties.description: Luuhar was a planet in the Luuhar system, within the Hapes Cluster. It possessed ancient forests, misty rains and rushing rivers.

properties.name: Luuq
properties.description: Luuq was the Luuq system's primary star.

properties.name: Luxiar
properties.description: Luxiar may refer to one of the following:

properties.name: Lwhekk
properties.description: Lwhekk was the capital planet of the Ssi-ruuvi Imperium, located beyond the main disk of the galaxy in the remote Ssi-ruuk Star Cluster.

properties.name: Lybeya
properties.description: Lybeya was the primary star of the Lybeya system.

properties.name: Lynx
properties.description: The Lynx system was in the Freeworlds Territory of the Tapani sector, near the Lamuir system.

properties.name: Lyran
properties.description: Lyran was a world in the galaxy where Chass na Chadic, pilot in the New Republic's Alphabet Squadron, had once visited. Several weeks after the Battle of Endor in 4 ABY, Chadic and her squadron visited a Jedi temple on the moon of the planet Harkrova I, where they found a holographic map of the galaxy. Chadick recognized Lyran in the map.

properties.name: M'Bardi
properties.description: M'Bardi was a water planet located in the Kalamith sector of the Outer Rim Territories. It was also the site of the M'Bardi Prison.

properties.name: M'dweshuu Nova
properties.description: M'dweshuu, also called M'dweshuu Nova,   was a nova in Hutt Space. The Nikto homeworld of Kintan was in a neighboring system. Radiation from M'dweshuu caused a high mutation rate in the inhabitants of Kintan. Some Nikto, understanding the effect that M'dweshuu had on their species, formed sects such as the violent Cult of M'dweshuu to worship the star.

properties.name: M'haeli
properties.poi: W'eston Falls, Demon's Brow, D'olop Mountain Range, Selon Mountain, Red Rock,
properties.description: M'haeli was an agriworld in the Expansion Region ruled by a hereditary Human monarchy, despite its indigenous species being the H'drachi. Under the New Order, the planet was under the authority of Governor Grigor and Grand Moff Lynch Hauser. It was the homeworld of Ixidro Legorburu.

properties.name: M'Hanna
properties.description: M'Hanna was a desolate planet that was located within the M'Hanna system in Hutt Space, a region of the galaxy controlled by the Hutt species. The planet was connected to the worlds of Tisht and Varl by the hyperlane called The Dead Road, while the Elgit–M'Hanna Corridor linked M'Hanna to the planet of Sakifwanna. M'Hanna was a world of black dust that was scoured by supersonic winds, and its history was the subject of various rumors and legends.

properties.name: M2934738
properties.description: M2934738 system was a sparse star system in the Outer Rim, its only distinction being that it was on the hyperlane between Liinade III and the New Republic. In 9 ABY, it was the site of the Battle of M2934738.

properties.name: M4-78
properties.description: M4-78 was a legendary planet of droids, supposedly dating back to the Old Republic. I-5YQ once joked about being the deposed ruler of the planet while he was on Drongar.

properties.name: Ma'ar Shaddam
properties.description: Ma'ar Shaddam was a remote Outer Rim planet, home to the armorers who served Boba Fett. The planet was settled by Galactic Republic Master Weaponsmiths not only for the quality of its ore, but because its remoteness made it difficult for the authorities to police the sale of illegal weaponry.

properties.name: Maarka
properties.description: Maarka was a planet located in the Perkell sector of the Mid Rim. During the Clone Wars, it was the site of a Republic base. While on a mission to deliver a data file with important intelligence for the Republic base on Maarka, Ahsoka Tano was ambushed by six Vulture droid starfighters in an asteroid field near the planet.

properties.name: Maccent
properties.description: Maccent was a planet located in the Phelleem sector of the Outer Rim Territories, along the Sisar Run.

properties.name: Mackar
properties.description: Mackar was a water world located in the Mackar system, a part of the Hewett sector in the New Territories portion of the Mid Rim. It was the homeworld of the Frid, a species of telepathic, fish-like aquatic sentients.

properties.name: Maelstrom Nebula
properties.description: The Maelstrom Nebula was a nebula located in the galaxy. During the Age of the Empire, the pirate Gunda Mabin operated from a location in the nebula.

properties.name: Magagran
properties.description: Magagran was an Imperial planet in the Halthor sector of the Outer Rim Territories.

properties.name: Magar's World
properties.description: Magar's World was a brutal, inconsequential backwater planet that did not appear on many star-charts. It was said there were only two real reasons why someone might know of it: that individual either went to see the gladiatorial games, or they were among the unlucky beings forced to fight in them.

properties.name: Magataran Maelstrom
properties.description: The Magataran Maelstrom was some kind of energy phenomenon.

properties.name: Magravia
properties.description: Magravia was a world located in the Magravia system, a part of the Karthakk sector in the Trailing Sectors portion of the Outer Rim Territories. It was situated on the hyperlane known as the Llanic Spice Run, which connected it to the Llanic system as well as the Socorro system in the Kibilini sector.

properties.name: Maicombe
properties.description: Maicombe was a planet in the Mid Rim's Corthenia sector. In 21 ABY, Luke and Mara Jade Skywalker spent their second honeymoon on Maicombe.

properties.name: Maill
properties.description: Maill was a planet located within the Maill system of the Outer Rim Territories. The planet was well-known for having produced one of the rarest coins in the galaxy; the world's King had commissioned the coin in honor of his wife. The coin was minted from a special alloy to have the color of a flaming sunset—to match the color of the lady's hair. The alloy ended up destroying the minting machines and only a few hundred coins were produced.

properties.name: Maires
properties.description: Maires was the Mairan homeworld. It was an ocean world located in the Hapes Cluster.

properties.name: Mairne
properties.description: Mairne, situated within the system of the same name, was a planet in the Kathol sector of the Outer Rim Territories. Connected to the neighboring planets of Charis and Gandle Ott by hyperlanes, Mairne was located just off the Trition Trade Route that ran through the sector. By 8 ABY, the world supported a small colony whose economy was based around supplying ore and natural resources to Gandle Ott.

properties.name: Majilop
properties.description: Majilop was a world located within the star system of the same name, a part of the Outer Rim Territories' Lol sector. Around the year 10 ABY, it served as the homeworld of the Lucin Syndicate, a major producer and distributor of illegal holoporn.

properties.name: Majoor
properties.description: Majoor was the homeworld of a native sentient species. It was located in the Expansion Region.

properties.name: Makeb
properties.poi: Avesta Plantation, Archon PalaceCartel mining mesa, Cloudside Resorts, Frinn Mesa, Giant's Spear, Solida Hesk's resort, Stronghold One, Toborro's Palace, Sanctuary research complex,
properties.description: Makeb was a planet invaded by the Hutt Cartel during the Galactic War. It was a major source of isotope-5, one of the rarest minerals in the galaxy.

properties.name: Makem Te
properties.description: Makem Te was the dry homeworld of the Swokes Swokes species, on the Perlemian Trade Route.

properties.name: Makksre
properties.description: Makksre was the planet on which Sansia Bardrin and her ship were captured by pirates some time prior to 18 ABY.

properties.name: Makthierse
properties.description: Makthierse was a colony world noted for ranches, farms, crystal caves, and Quantrax Creek. Native creatures included lacas and preying makthiers.

properties.name: Malachor
properties.description: Malachor was a rocky, hellish wasteland planet located in the Chorlian sector of the galaxy's Outer Rim Territories region. It was a planet shrouded in mystery, and the location of an event known as the Great Scourge of Malachor, which took place thousands of years before the rise of the Empire. The Great Scourge was an ancient battle at Malachor's Sith temple between the Sith and the Jedi Order, which saw a superweapon activated, killing and petrifying all the participants of the battle, remaining for years after.

properties.name: Maladi
properties.description: Maladi could refer to one of the following:

properties.name: Malador
properties.description: Malador was an overpopulated urban planet located in the Mid Rim's Juvex sector. Cappabellor beetles were native to Malador, and it served as the homeworld of the aristocratic House Kellermin. Over time, Malador's ecosystem was ruined by industrial pollution, and many House Kellermin nobles left the planet for the nearby world of Resti Kel, leaving slaves and client species to work in Malador's factories.

properties.name: Malagarr
properties.description: Malagarr was located in Wild Space. Its primary terrain was red sand. It was home to droids of Q-7N's type. In 0 ABY, an Imperial incursion took place there.

properties.name: Malanose
properties.description: Malanose was a world within the Gree Enclave, on the Outer Rim of the galaxy, which served as the primary world containing the Crafter and Researcher castes of the Gree civilization.

properties.name: Malastare
properties.description: Malastare was the high-gravity homeworld of the quadrupedal Dug race, on the Hydian Way.

properties.name: Maldra
properties.description: The Maldra system was a system in the Outer Rim Territories in the Shadola sector. It contained Maldra IV.

properties.name: Malkii
properties.description: Malkii was a remote planet. It commonly served as a refuge for mercenaries, insurrectionists and terrorists, but perhaps it was most notorious for its reputation as the training ground of the infamous assassins known as Malkite Poisoners.

properties.name: Mall'ordian
properties.description: Mall'ordian was a planet in the Corporate Sector. A popular tourist destination, it was renown for its crystalline forests. The Corporate Sector Authority was interested in the planet for its potential resources.

properties.name: Malo
properties.description: Malo was a Rodian smuggler and an associate of Han Solo. He and another Rodian sometimes employed Solo to smuggle spice. Malo and his partner made one such exchange with Solo in 0 ABY, allowing Imperial prisoner Mira Volz to sneak aboard Solo's Millennium Falcon.

properties.name: Malrev
properties.description: Malrev IV was a planet located in the Thrasybule sector of the Outer Rim Territories. Its history was strongly associated with the Sith.

properties.name: Maltha Obex
properties.description: Maltha Obex was an astronomical object located in the galaxy's Outer Rim Territories.

properties.name: Malthor
properties.description: Malthor was a Mid Rim tradeworld with a large Reigat population. Reginna Bel Typolla was a native of Malthor.

properties.name: Mamendin
properties.description: Mamendin was a planet located in the Farrfin sector of the Core Worlds. It was the homeworld of a sentient species that was humanoid in form. The criminal gang known as the Slams was composed of several members of this species, such as Roper Slam and Valadon.

properties.name: Manaan
properties.poi: Ahto City swoop track, Ahto Luxury Resorts, Hrakert Rift, Hrakert Station, Wreck of the Prince of Waves,
properties.description: Manaan was an aquatic planet in the Pyrshak system. It was home to the Selkath, an amphibious species. The planet was completely covered in water and was the only known source of the medicinal substance kolto in the galaxy. Controlled by the Rakata during pre-Republic history, it became independent following the collapse of their Infinite Empire. In the years leading up to and during the Jedi Civil War, kolto was so important to the galaxy that the Selkath were able to use their monopoly to enforce their policy of neutrality and autonomy. The only above-surface settlement on Manaan was the floating Ahto City, built above Hrakert Rift, an abundant source of Kolto. Hiding in the depths of the rift lay a station where the Republic was trying to harvest Kolto at its source, aided by rebellious Selkath who saw the evil of the Sith Empire. This station fell in ruins when a Giant Firaxan Shark believed to be the source of Kolto and Selkath on the planet made the Selkath in the station go mad and rapidly kill the rest of the Crew. Eventually, Revan would find one of the star maps leading to the Star Forge. The map completed other maps found on Kashyyyk, Dantooine, Korriban, and Tatooine. During the Jedi Civil War, both the Sith Empire and the Galactic Republic attempted to get an upper hand in the war by creating secret deals that would give them more kolto. Since the Selkath preferred to stay neutral, they did not favor the Republic or the Sith, however some rebellious Selkath did. Ultimately, however, the Selkath banned the Sith from Manaan for trying to overthrow the government.

properties.name: Manari
properties.description: Manari was a planet in the Manari system of the Brevost sector in the Expansion Region. During the time of the Great Galactic War between the Galactic Republic and the Sith Empire, Manari was ruled by tradition-bound leaders who had a very delicate political etiquette. In 19.5 BBY, during the Clone Wars between the Republic and the Confederacy of Independent Systems, Republic forces fought in the Battle of Manari against an anti-Republic force. Jedi General Roan Shryne lost his second Padawan during the battle and as a result, the Jedi Master became disillusioned about the war and lost hope in the Jedi Council. After the end of the war, Manari was part of the Republic's successor regime, the Galactic Empire.

properties.name: Manda
properties.poi: Baobab Archives, Baobab Merchant Fleet Complex, Baobab Merchant Marine Academy, The Blue Nebula, Manda spaceport,
properties.description: Manda was a planet located in the Mid Rim region of the galaxy.

properties.name: Mandalore
properties.poi: Kelita River, MandalMotors Tower, City of Bone, Kyrimorut,
properties.description: Mandalore was the fifth planet in the Mandalore system of the Outer Rim Territories, not far from the Hydian Way trade route. The homeworld of the multi-species cultural group known as the Mandalorians, the planet was known as Manda'yaim in the Mandalorian language, and was named after the legendary conqueror of the vibrant world, Mandalore the First. Mandalore the First's Taung warriors slew the indigenous mythosaurs and tamed the savage landscape, solidifying Mandalore's place as a powerbase and the center of Mandalorian space for millennia to come. Mandalore was covered in a rich natural landscape, largely unspoiled due to its sparse sentient population. The world was blanketed in lush veshok tree forests, dense jungle, sprawling hills and grassland well suited to farming, inhospitable deserts of white sand, and numerous rivers, lakes, and seas. It was also the only known world in the galaxy, with the exception of its moon Concordia, to possess the unique, nearly indestructible iron ore known as beskar, an element capable of withstanding blows from even a lightsaber.

properties.name: Mandell
properties.description: Mandell was a Bothan colony world. It was once devastated by drought, requiring grain shipments from Bothawui. Unfortunately, these shipments contained radarks, which infested the planet.

properties.name: Mandrine
properties.description: Mandrine was a celestial body located in the Outer Rim Territories's Kessel sector. It featured several bars, including Maizie's. During the Galactic Civil War, the crew of the smuggling starship Capri Nitari visited Mandrine's bars to celebrate a successful spice trafficking run. At Maizie's, the vessel's Captain Scarlet Bloodhawk met the mercenary Kelly Vermillion and his companions Tyric and Nana, who became involved in a bar fight against Kronus and his thugs, which resulted in Kronus's death. Bloodhawk later visited the same bar on Mandrine on several occasions.

properties.name: Manforgon
properties.description: Manforgon was a planet located in the Mid Rim's Senex sector. It was used for centuries as a penal colony of the Senex-Juvex region. Eventually becoming a lawless world fought over by warlords, Manforgon was turned over to the Galactic Empire by the noble houses of the Senex-Juvex. The Empire used the planet for military purposes, and during the Galactic Civil War, Imperial Customs Officer Tellix served there.

properties.name: Mangez
properties.description: The Mangez system was a star system in the Expansion Region's Brak sector. The system contained at least two planet upon which Lant Mining Corporation conducted underground metal mining operations. Two orbital Lormar-class Refinery Stations were also present in the system, one of which was designated Lormar 23. Lant Mining Corporation planned on transporting a third Lormar-class station to the system to assist with refinery operations.

properties.name: Mannova
properties.description: Mannova was an industrial dumping ground located within the Mannova system in the Gordian Reach of the Outer Rim Territories region of the galaxy. It was the home to the Mannovans, a sardonic gray-furred species that seemingly unruffled by the ecological disaster their homeworld has become. The mountains of junk were picked over by speculators, scavengers and those looking for impossible-to-find parts. The fighting after the Battle of Yavin made fortunes on Mannova as scavengers hauled wrecked ship parts and equipment there in bulk.

properties.name: Manpha
properties.description: Manpha was a planet in the Outer Rim Territories, on the Corellian Trade Spine. It was inhabited by the amphibian Shawda Ubb species.

properties.name: Manress
properties.description: Manress was the Stokhli homeworld. The Stokhli were hunters whom invented Stokhli spray sticks.

properties.name: Mantan
properties.description: The world of Mantan was located in the Mantan system of the Calamari sector.

properties.name: Mantarran
properties.description: Mantarran was a planet where Moranda Savich managed to avoid capture by Hal Horn.

properties.name: Mantessa
properties.description: Mantessa was a planet in the Orus sector of the Inner Rim. The world was encased in forests and treacherous jungles. The wilderness was extremely dangerous due to the existence of Mantessan panthacs, predatory animals who stalked and killed quite efficiently in their home environment.

properties.name: Mantooine
properties.poi: Imperial orbital base, Imperial garrison base,
properties.description: Mantooine was a planet in the Atrivis sector, on the Relgim Run. Despite their xenophobia, the natives were sympathetic to the Rebel Alliance.

properties.name: Maphus Tria
properties.description: Maphus Tria was a planet in the Outer Rim Territories where the con artist Tord Gamb ran a con that netted him several hundred thousand credits.

properties.name: Mapuzo
properties.description: Mapuzo was a planet in the Mid Rim. It was the location of the Mapuzo break-in.

properties.name: Maramere
properties.description: Maramere was a planet located in the Outer Rim Territories. It was the homeworld of the sentient Mere species. The planet fell under the domination of Lord Toat of the Trade Federation, which used it as a repository of stygium crystals from Aeten II.

properties.name: Marasai
properties.description: Marasai was a planet in the Marasa Nebula, near the Trellen Trade Route. It was the homeworld of the Marasans, a species of cyborgs. It was notable for a gentle ecology, despite the sometimes difficult to predict weather which resulted from Marasai's location within the chaotic nebula.

properties.name: Marca
properties.description: Marca, the Sekct homeworld, was a planet in the Marcellus Nebula.

properties.name: Marcelan Prime
properties.description: Marcelan Prime was a celestial body located in the Wild Space star system of the same name. During the Galactic Civil War, the Tempest Force unit of the Galactic Empire's armed forces, which included the stormtrooper Hume Tarl, participated in a military operation at Marcelan Prime.

properties.name: Marcol Void
properties.description: The Marcol Void was an expanse of empty space in the Kathol sector. Measuring roughly thirty light-years across, the Void had no planetary systems and very little debris. The Marcol Void separated the Imperial controlled region of the sector, centered around Kal'Shebbol, from the independent Kathol Outback. Ships with a Class One hyperdrive took fourteen days to cross the Void, and pirates would often blind-jump into the region since there was virtually no chance of hitting anything.

properties.name: Marfa
properties.description: Marfa was a planet in the Core Worlds that housed Jedi AgriCorps facilities during the Cold War. Hestizo Trace and the Murakami orchid she had created a bond with were kidnapped here by the Whiphid bounty hunter Tulkh. Later, Jedi Knight Rojo Trace came to the planet in search of Hestizo.

properties.name: Maridun
properties.description: Maridun was the grassy and forested homeworld of the Amanin species. Maridun went unnoticed for many millennia, and so was considered a haven by those who knew of of its existence. The planet came to support a colony of Lurmen who sought to escape the Clone Wars, and was the site of a battle when Confederate General Lok Durd arrived on the planet to test an experimental weapon. Amani could be found on the planet of Utapau, where many of them were refugees from Maridun.

properties.name: Markbee's Star
properties.description: Markbee's Star was the primary star of the planet Zeffliffl, the fourth planet of the system.

properties.name: Markon
properties.description: Markon was an individual who served as a General in the Galactic Empire in 14 BBY, when they led the 201st Squadron on Zeffo.

properties.name: Marleyvane
properties.description:
Marleyvane was a planet in the galaxy that hosted an Imperial Academy.
Lieutenant Chiron and Sergeant Currahee were stationed on Marleyvane before being transferred to the Academy for Young Imperials on Lothal.

properties.name: Marmoth
properties.description: Marmoth was a planet located in the Albarrio sector of the Outer Rim Territories, and was a part of the Relgim Run. It was one of the ports of call of the luxury liner Kuari Princess.

properties.name: Maro Della
properties.description: Maro Della was a terrestrial astronomical object located in the Maro Della system of the Mektrun sector, a part of the Western Reaches portion of the Mid Rim. At some point by the date 38:4:1:02, the individual Hyannis was involved in a firefight on Maro Della. During the skirmish, Hyannis prepared to fire a Model MGL-1 micro-grenade launcher. The magnetic rings that propelled the weapon's projectiles, however, had degraded due to lack of maintenance and failed. As a result, a micro-grenade was jammed in the weapon's barrel, and Hyannis had to throw the launcher away before the grenade detonated within seconds. Hyannis later mentioned the incident on Maro Della in the illegal database Gundark's Gear Datalog.

properties.name: Marotan
properties.description: Marotan was a planet located in the Inner Rim.

properties.name: Marquarra
properties.description: Marquarra was an Outer Rim planet with a weapons cache of the Ubiqtorate. It was allied with the Imperial Remnant.

properties.name: Marrovia
properties.description: Marrovia was an agriworld located in the Marrovia system, a part of the Gordian Reach sector in the Trans-Hydian portion of the Outer Rim Territories. The Pinooran Spur hyperlane connected the world to the Kli'aar and Ladarra systems.

properties.name: Maryo
properties.description: Maryo was a resort world in the Corporate Sector. It was well known for its bazaars and was often visited by idle wealthy beings. Those who visited the planet also enjoyed hunting the native peckvas and fishing for colossus fish amongst the world's vast seas.

properties.name: Maryx Minor
properties.poi: Maryb WastesAncient Order of Pessimists hermitage
properties.description: Maryx Minor was a volcanic planet in the Outer Rim Territories, covered in geysers and pits of lava. It was the location of the hermitage of the Ancient Order of Pessimists, beyond the Maryb Wastes. Abal Karda fled to the hermitage with the head of Selestrine the prophet; while there, the terrified Karda threatened the hermits living there and killed one, named Mabob. Later, Darth Vader destroyed the hermitage by Star Destroyer barrage.

properties.name: Masposhani
