properties.description: Masposhani was a planet in the Mid Rim. According to Beldorion the Hutt, the Jedi Order had once maintained a training facility in its caves.

properties.name: Massiff Nebula
properties.description: The Massiff Nebula was a nebula near the planet Coruscant in the Coruscant sector. It shared its name with the reptilian massiffs of Geonosis.

properties.name: Massoss
properties.description: Massoss was a planet of the Chiss Ascendancy in the Unknown Regions. It was home of a former Ruling Family. Although it was a homeworld of a Ruling Family, Massoss wasn't located on the Path of the Houses, probably due to its distance from the core territory of the Ascendancy.

properties.name: Masterra
properties.description: Masterra, originally known as Ord Masterra, was a planet in the Hertae sector of the Mid Rim.

properties.name: Matabre
properties.description: Matabre was an astronomical object located in the Eucer sector's Matabre system. It was considered a part of the Mid Rim, although it was situated in the region known as the Divide during the Tionese War, which was fought between the Galactic Republic and the Honorable Union of Desevro & Tion. Matabre had been settled by Republic colonists by that time.

properties.name: Matacorn
properties.description: Matacorn was a terrestrial world located in the Matacorn system, a part of the Mid Rim's Lambda sector. A nondescript trade world, it was the homeworld of the Human Hurst Romodi. Matacorn also shared its name with the Matacorn campaign, a conflict fought during the Galactic Civil War.

properties.name: Mataou
properties.description: Mataou was the ro hypa homeworld on the edge of the Ivax Nebula. It was the primary entry point for ships leaving the Corellian Trade Spine to enter the Ison Corridor at its Ison end. Ro hypa wranglers exported ro hypa venom for its medicinal value.

properties.name: Matarri
properties.description: Matarri was a planet noted for its sudden, monsoon rainstorms that contained pounding raindrops that could kill small animals.

properties.name: Mattri
properties.description: The Mattri Asteroid was an asteroid that once served as a location for the headquarters of Garm Bel Iblis's private, anti-Imperial resistance movement, dubbed Peregrine's Nest.

properties.name: Mauk
properties.description: Mauk was a planet where Asajj Ventress was worshiped as a goddess of death.

properties.name: Maun Digitalis
properties.description: Maun Digitalis was a planet located in the Colonies.

properties.name: Mavva
properties.description: The Mavva system was located in the Aparo sector of the Outer Rim Territories. It shared its name with the Mavvan Conflict, which was fought at some point between 19 BBY and 15 BBY.

properties.name: Maw Cluster
properties.description: The Maw Cluster, also known simply as the Maw, was a cluster of churning black holes that could confound navigation computers located in the Akkadese Maelstrom. The largest and the worst of these, was The Maw, and it was given wide berth by sensible travelers.

properties.name: Mawan
properties.description: Mawan was a Galactic Core world.

properties.name: Maxca
properties.description: The Maxca system was an isolated star system in the Brak sector, located in the Expansion Region. During the Galactic Civil War, the Rebel Alliance's Brak Sector Force began construction on a secret base in the system to act as a safe fallback position in case any main Alliance bases in the sector were compromised.

properties.name: Maya Kovel
properties.description: Maya Kovel was a windswept Outer Rim Territories desert planet located in the Moddell sector. It was the homeworld of the sentient Ayrou species, which had already developed spaceflight technology prior to its first contact with the Galactic Republic by 50 BBY. The Ayrou went on to have a significant presence throughout the larger Zuma sector's Inner and Outer Zuma regions, including control over the Vashan-worked mines on the planet Vasha.

properties.name: Mayagil
properties.description: Mayagil may refer to one of the following:

properties.name: Mazhar
properties.description: Mazhar was a jungle planet, located along the Gordian Reach. Embra the Hutt based his operations there.

properties.name: Mazuma
properties.description: Mazuma was a planet located in the Mazuma system, within the Nuiri sector of the galaxy's Outer Rim Territories, that was site of the Lucre Cosminational Bank.

properties.name: Meastrinnar
properties.description: Meastrinnar was a planet that was subject to a pacification campaign by the Galactic Empire during the Galactic Civil War as a result of an insurgency against Imperial authority on the planet. During this period in Meastrinnar's history, a squad of stormtroopers led by Vin Northal attacked an orphanage while mistakenly believing that it was the headquarters of a cell of spies affiliated with the Alliance to Restore the Republic due to faulty intelligence provided by the Imperial Security Bureau. The stormtroopers killed many children in their sleep, and though the planet's media networks hailed the raid as a "military victory" and Northal was congratulated by his superiors, the incident ultimately led him to leave the Imperial military to join the Alliance.

properties.name: Mechis
properties.description: Mechis was an astronomical object in the galaxy's Inner Rim.

properties.name: Medepiest
properties.description: Medepiest may refer to one of the following:

properties.name: Media
properties.description: Media are the channels and tools used for storing and transmitting information.

properties.name: Medth
properties.description: Medth was a planet. The privateer Urias Xhaxin once raided the planet's region in his ship, the Free Lance.

properties.name: Meedis Minor
properties.description: Meedis Minor was an astronomical object located in the Meedis Minor system, a part of the Tandon sector in the Slice portion of the Mid Rim. At one point, a pair of dour ladies were traveling aboard the starliner Pendrake's Horizons that was captured by Thalassian slavers off Phibia, in the Haserian sector. The ladies from Meedis Minor were eventually rescued by the Corellian Security Force agent Bey.

properties.name: Meglumine
properties.description: Meglumine was a planet. In 0 ABY, Imperial stormtrooper TK329 was serving on the Imperial Star Destroyer Vector, which had a stopover near Meglumine. A small number of the ship's crew went planetside, while the rest enjoyed some recreation time aboard the ship.

properties.name: Mek va Uil
properties.description: Mek va Uil was a planet in the Expansion Region. The Regent of Mek va Uil was from this world.

properties.name: Mektrun Cluster
properties.description: The Mektrun Cluster was in the Mid Rim's Mektrun sector. The cluster contained the planet Veron Minor.

properties.name: Melasaton
properties.description: Melasaton was a low-tech planet devastated by a great plague. It was saved from the plague when Arbor Industries developed an antidote, even though it was Arbor Industries that secretly unleashed the plague in the first place.

properties.name: Meldazar
properties.description: Meldazar was a planet that was visited by Siri Tachi and her Padawan, Ferus Olin, sometime before the outbreak of the Clone Wars.

properties.name: Melida/Daan
properties.description: Melida/Daan was a planet in the Outer Rim Territories. For centuries, it was engulfed in a civil war between the Melida and the Daan factions which could not even agree on a name for the planet. The Melida called it Melida and the Daan called it Daan so the Galactic Senate used Melida and Daan separated by a slash. Eventually, a group called the Young, led by various children of the Melida and Daan, rose up and ended the civil war in 44 BBY. Obi-Wan Kenobi temporarily left the Jedi Order to aid the Young in their quest, helping to end the war. Parts of the planet were scarred from the war.

properties.name: Melinz
properties.description: Melinz was a Galactic Core world of little influence. It was the homeworld of the Shad Furies, a shockball team.

properties.name: Melldia
properties.description: Melldia was a planet located in the Melldia system of the Outer Rim Territories's Esstran sector. In 3950 BBY, the Sith Lord Darth Nyriss claimed to be "the destroyer of Melldia."

properties.name: Melnea's World
properties.description: Melnea's World was a murky, swampy planet located in the Melnea's World system, a part of the Arkanis sector in the Slice portion of the Outer Rim Territories. Melnea's World was located on the Cranan-Excarga Route.

properties.name: Mendavi
properties.description: Mendavi was an astronomical object where the 291st Legion established a vanguard for urban combat, utilizing AT-DPs.

properties.name: Mendicat
properties.description: Mendicat was a scrap mining and recycling space station that orbited a star within a Wild Space system. The station was located outside the borders of space controlled by the New Republic by 12 ABY. By that date, the individual Sulamar served aboard the station. When he made an error in programming Mendicat's orbital computers, the space station diverted from its previous course and, as a result, fell into the star it was orbiting.

properties.name: Mengjini
properties.description: Mengjini was a planet in the Bright Jewel sector of the Mid Rim.

properties.name: Mentanar Vosk
properties.description: Mentanar Vosk was a planet in the Nijune sector.

properties.name: Mepha'as Prime
properties.description: Mepha'as Prime was an Outer Rim planet in the Belsmuth sector. It had many casinos, gaming halls, arenas, and racing tracks.

properties.name: Mephitis
properties.description: Mephitis was the Mephitisian homeworld. The indigenous people had no sense of smell. Offworlders found the entire planet's atmosphere to have a foul stench.

properties.name: Mephout
properties.description: Mephout was a Wild Space celestial body located in grid square H-20 of the Standard Galactic Grid.

properties.name: Merakai
properties.description: Merakai was a colony of the Khil species.

properties.name: Meridian
properties.description: Meridian was a planet in the Meridian sector in the Outer Rim Territories.

properties.name: Merikon
properties.description: Merikon was a planet. The Galactic Empire operated a training facility on the planet during the height of the New Order. Ivhin Jayme, a member of the Imperial Military, received intensive training by the Merikon instructors while at the facility.

properties.name: Merisee
properties.poi: Merisee Dispatch, Merisee Agra, Merisee Grand Medical Facility, Merisee Asylum, Utozz Prime Brewery, Tozzin Foods
properties.description: Merisee, also known as Merisee Prime, was an agriworld in the Elrood sector, located along the Elrood-Derilyn Run, and was known as the "breadbasket" for the entire sector.

properties.name: Merren
properties.description: Merkat was a trade world located in the Merren system, in the Chaykin sector of the Expansion Region. It was an endpoint of the Harrin Trade Corridor.

properties.name: Merson
properties.description: Merson was a planet that was located in the Stenness Node within the Inner Rim, near the Merson asteroid belt.

properties.name: Meruud
properties.description: Meruud was a planet in the Meruud system. It was home to the Meruud Memorial Spaceport.

properties.name: Mes Cavoli
properties.description: Mes Cavoli was a planet in the Mid Rim.

properties.name: Meserian
properties.description: Meserian was a planet on the Outer Rim.

properties.name: Messert
properties.description: Messert was a planet in the Mytaranor sector. It was the financial hub of the sector. Loans from Messert financed many mining, agricultural and industrial companies in the Kashyyyk Region

properties.name: Metalorn
properties.description: Metalorn was an industrial world in the Talcene sector of the Mid Rim, between Anzat and Roche. Once a hot jungle planet, its rich veins of ore attracted heavy industry, and by the time of the Clone Wars Metalorn had become a polluted factory world covered with industrial plants, mines and ore refineries. Metalorn was one of the Confederacy of Independent System's most productive industrial planets during the Clone Wars, and under the Galactic Empire became a penal colony for dissidents. The planet was occupied during the Yuuzhan Vong War and was heavily Vongformed, reversing many centuries of pollution and turning it into a prime recruiting ground for the Peace Brigade.

properties.name: Metellos
properties.description: Metellos was the fourth of seven planets in the Metellos system of the Coruscant sector in the Core Worlds region. The planet orbited one star, also called Metellos, and in turn was orbited by three moons.

properties.name: Metharian Nebula
properties.description: The Metharian Nebula was a nebula located within the Outer Rim Territories of the galaxy. It contained the Metharian Nebula Territories, which consisted of Elrood sector, Tantra sector, and Danjar sector.

properties.name: Mev
properties.description: Mev was an astronomical object in the Greater Javin Region of the galaxy's Outer Rim Territories.

properties.name: Mexeluine
properties.description: Mexeluine was a thriving trade world lying along the Corellian Trade Spine in the Anoat sector of the Outer Rim Territories. Originally settled during the Galactic Republic's efforts to harvest the economic potential of the Greater Javin region centuries before the Galactic Civil War, Mexeluine grew wealthy as a result of Figg & Associates' commercial development of the region. Mexeluine successfully positioned itself as a cheaper alternative to neighboring Gerrenthum, the region's commercial capital.

properties.name: Mezeg
properties.description: Mezeg was a planet located in the Mezeg sector. Aligned with the Galactic Republic, it had strict enforcement at its freighter terminals, sometimes guarding them with akk dogs.

properties.name: Mhatma
properties.description: Mhatma 5 was a cold terrestrial world that occupied the fifth orbital position in the Mhatma system, a part of the freestanding subsectors portion of the Mid Rim. During the Galactic Civil War, Mhatma 5 was situated on the galactic frontier.

properties.name: Midani
properties.description: Midani was an Outer Rim planet near Andasala. It was a favored destination of hunters.

properties.name: Miele Nova
properties.description: Miele Nova was a planet. The PanGalactic Arts Conservatory was located there.

properties.name: Mijos
properties.description: Mijos was a swampy world in the Anoat sector of the Outer Rim Territories and a stopover point for travel between the planets Lutrillia and Gerrenthum on the Lutrillian Cross hyperlane. A number of Lutrillian-run spaceports could be found on Mijos, but poor structural planning had caused many of these settlements to sink into the planet's muck.

properties.name: Mika
properties.description: Mika might refer to:

properties.name: Miko
properties.description: Miko was a planet located in the Esaga sector of the Mid Rim. The Jedi of the planet were knowe to wear a unique gear in addition using the unique pulsing crystals to produce powerful Lightsabers.

properties.name: Mil Velay
properties.description: Mil Velay was a planet that prohibited individuals with criminal records from entering their space.

properties.name: Mila
properties.description: Mila was a human fortune-teller who lived at Takodana Castle on the planet Takodana by the time of the First Order-Resistance War. Mila used the ancient, historically forbidden Bakurat card deck to tell fortunes.

properties.name: Milagro
properties.description: The planet Milagro lay at the confluence of two important hyperroutes, the Corellian Run and the Harrin Trade Corridor.

properties.name: Milarian
properties.description: Milarian was the sector capital of the Trans-Nebular sector.

properties.name: Mileva
properties.description: Mileva was the homeworld of the Siniteen species. Confederacy of Independent Systems Senator Bec Lawise and bounty hunter Bric, both Siniteens, hailed from Mileva.

properties.name: Millinar
properties.description: Millinar was an elusive planet believed to be only a myth by the galaxy at large. The myth of Millinar was often compared to those of the Lost City of the Jedi and the Valley of the Jedi. The "mythic" planet was actually located in the Interior Region of the Hapes Cluster, a region which itself had become almost legendary by the era of the Galactic Civil War.

properties.name: Milvayne
properties.description: Milvayne was a planet in the Gyrica system of the Inner Rim.

properties.name: Mima
properties.description: Mima II, also referred to as Mima Two or simply Mima, was a tropical planet located in the Mid Rim's D'Aelgoth sector. The gravitational influence of Lar, the planet's star, caused the tectonic plates on Mima II to be constantly moving across its surface in various directions, leading to the active creation of new landforms, such as mountains and seas. The accompanying release of chemical elements vital to the development of life resulted in the planet being abundant with plant and animal species, including the sentient Bilars.

properties.name: Minashee
properties.description: Minashee was an industrial planet in the Outer Rim's Tadrin subsector. It served as the sector capital.

properties.name: Minavar
properties.description: The Minavar system was a star system located within the Outer Rim Territories' Bheriz sector. At some point, an expedition that included the Human infant Reina Gale and her family established a colony within the system. By 0 ABY, however, the colony was ravaged by a virus that killed nearly its entire population, including Gale's parents, and the girl was left in the care of her uncle.

properties.name: Mindabaal
properties.description: Mindabaal was a planet located in the Inner Rim of the galaxy.

properties.name: Mindemir
properties.description: Mindemir was the primary planet of the Mindemir system. Jenna Zan Arbor wanted to use the planet's water supplies in her experiments, but was blocked from doing so by the Galactic Senate.

properties.name: Mindor
properties.poi: Election CenterMelter cryptShadow BaseShadow EggShadow ThroneSorting Center
properties.description: Mindor, also known as Taspan I, was a planet in the Inner Rim with vast landmasses covered in grasslands. It had little to offer the galactic community other than its landmasses, which would have been ideal for farming. Mindor had four medium sized moons in very close proximity to the planet.

properties.name: Minkring
properties.description: Minkring was a planet in the Shelsha sector. By 0.5 ABY it was home to one of the only two remaining Imperial army garrisons in the sector .

properties.name: Minntaa
properties.description: Minntaa was a Human-inhabited planet liberated by the Rebel Alliance when Imperial Colonel Jeph Shannessi was assassinated by the Alliance Special Forces.

properties.name: Minntooine
properties.poi: Free Dac Volunteers Engineering Corps shipyards,
properties.description: Minntooine was an Outer Rim Territories waterworld located in the Calamari sector. It was one of the several worlds settled by the Quarren species of the planet Dac. During the Clone Wars, Minntooine hosted a population of Quarren who had been exiled from Dac and allied itself with the Confederacy of Independent Systems. At shipyards maintained on Minntooine, the Free Dac Volunteers Engineering Corps subsequently constructed warships for the Confederacy.

properties.name: Minoth
properties.description: Minoth was a world located in the Masla sector of the Mid Rim. Prior to the Battle of Hoth, Han Solo planned to run weapons from Minoth to Hendrix for the Rebel Alliance.

properties.name: Mirak Major
properties.description: Mirak Major was a planet. During the Clone Wars, the Confederacy of Independent Systems triggered this planet's mega-volcanos. The planet's population of at least six billion, however, was safely evacuated by General Gentis.

properties.name: Mirial
properties.description: Mirial was the homeworld of the Mirialans, including Luminara Unduli and Barriss Offee, and was a cold, dry planet located near the Hydian Way.

properties.name: Mirit
properties.description: Ord Mirit was originally one of the Republic's Ordnance/Regional Depots. After the Battle of Endor, the planet's Imperial garrison relocated to Corellia. During the Yuuzhan Vong War, the planet was a strategic world of the New Republic. It was the homeworld of Habeer Zignean.

properties.name: Mirnic
properties.description: Mirnic could refer to one of the following:

properties.name: Mirshaf
properties.description: Mirshaf was a planet with an ancient culture that was venerated in the galaxy. Captain Dorja, who served under Grand Admiral Thrawn, used the culture's victory gestures in battle.

properties.name: Mirshilan
properties.description: Mirshilan was a planet within the Mirshilan system in the Outer Rim, near to Nishr.

properties.name: Misnor
properties.description: Misnor was an ice planet which unlike other frozen planets, had water. Chiilaks were native to Misnor.

properties.name: Mittoblade
properties.description: Mittoblade was an Inner Rim celestial body. During the Waymancy Storm, Chief Sergeant Saens Sukko was among a Galactic Republic group that scaled a magnetic cliff on Mittoblade. There, Sukko helped trigger the destruction of the Clowse Glowstack, associated with the Republic's enemy, the Signatories of Waymancy. The naval officer Ruthbert Ozzel eventually came to be known as the "Savior of Mittoblade."

properties.name: Mizra
properties.description: Mizra was a planet. In 1466 BBY, it was the site of the New Sith Wars Battle of Mizra, a great Sith victory.

properties.name: Miztoc
properties.description: Miztoc was a planet liberated from the Galactic Empire by the Rebel Alliance.

properties.name: Mobetta
properties.description: The Mobetta system was located in the Airam sector of the Outer Rim Territories. It was apparently one of the more industrialized Airam systems.

properties.name: Modus
properties.description: The Modus system was located in the Rifle Worlds, an area of the Hapes Cluster in the Slice portion of the Inner Rim. It was connected by the hyperlane known as the Rynmar Trail to the Vergill system of the Rifle Worlds and to the Sargon system in the Gateworlds.

properties.name: Moer
properties.description: Moer was a terrestrial astronomical object located in the Dalon system, a part of the Hewett sector in the New Territories portion of the Mid Rim. It was the homeworld of the Human female Liadden, who by the age of eighteen had become a free-trader and the partner of the Twi'lek trader To'iir.

properties.name: Mogoshyn
properties.description: Mogoshyn was a run-down industrial world located in the Mogoshyn system, a part of the Gordian Reach sector in the Trans-Hydian portion of the Outer Rim Territories. The world lay between the Betshish and Kushibah systems on the Pinooran Spur hyperlane.

properties.name: Mokk
properties.description: The Mokk were a Dantari tribe that lived on the planet Dantooine. Many Mokk, including their tribal leader, resided in the Mokk Stronghold. Soothsayers and shamen were also part of the tribe.

properties.name: Molavar
properties.description: Molavar was a backwater, desert world in the Outer Rim Territories, with a number of seedy spaceports and low-income moisture farms. It was inhabited by beings of various species, but especially by the native Molavaran race. Darca Nyl chased Lycan to the planet. During the Clone Wars, the planet lay within Separatist space.

properties.name: Moltok
properties.description: Moltok was a planet located in the Atrivis sector of the Outer Rim Territories. Orbiting close to its sun, the planet was quite warm, kept habitable only by the shielding action of active volcanoes. Beneath the ash they spewed forth, moist rain-forests covered the planet, home to a countless array of plant species. The planet was home to two sentient species, the Ho'Din and the Makurth. The former were known throughout the galaxy for their botanical skills, while the latter often found employment as bodyguards in the criminal underworld.

properties.name: Mon Calamari
properties.description: The Mon Calamari  were one of the sentient species indigenous to the world of Dac.

properties.name: Mon Gazza
properties.description: Mon Gazza was a planet located in the Mon Gazza system in the Mid Rim. It was a famous shadowport and featured podracing.

properties.name: Mon Torri
properties.description: Mon Torri was a snowy, mountainous and glacier-covered world that was located within the Mid Rim of the galaxy. Situated between Ord Mantell and Tatooine, it was surrounded by seven rings, each of them a different color and composition.

properties.name: Monastery
properties.poi: Crystal Valley, Temple of the Sacred Circle,
properties.description: Monastery was a planet in the Mid Rim that was home to the religious order known as the Order of the Sacred Circle, who originally settled the world and ruled it for thousands of years. Distinguished by its massive ring, Monastery had a number of dangerous native predators, and its topography itself could be deadly—for instance, the planet's Crystal Valley could mean certain death to most visitors, as jagged crystals burst from the ground without warning. Monastery remained cloistered and neutral from most galactic affairs throughout much of its history, but Sacred Circle priestess Domina Tagge brought it into Imperial intrigues during the Galactic Civil War. In 0 ABY, it hosted a lightsaber duel between Rebel hero Luke Skywalker and Tagge's brother Orman, which Skywalker won in deadly fashion.

properties.name: Monhudle
properties.description: Monhudle was a mining planet in the Cassandran sectors region. During the Outer Rim Sieges of the Clone Wars, Jedi General Traavis led clone forces to war against the Separatists on this planet.

properties.name: Monic
properties.description: Monic was a Trianii colony planet.

properties.name: Monor
properties.description: Monor II, also called Kline's Colony, was the Sunesi homeworld. It was ruled by a monarchy of priest-princes. The tenth, Agapos the Tenth, ascended in 24 ABY. This planet was where Nom Anor infected various diplomats and Mara Jade Skywalker with coomb spores, killing many of them.

properties.name: Monsua Nebula
properties.description: The Monsua Nebula was a nebula in Moddell sector between Inner Zuma and the area known as Wild Space. A large core of blue giants and brown dwarfs produced high levels of radiation in the nebula. The radiation made Monsua almost unnavigable and impossible to scan, making it home to heavy pirate activity in the decade preceding the Clone Wars. Even during the early years of the New Republic, Monsua remained uncharted and its stars unnamed beyond the alphanumeric codes assigned millennia earlier by the Old Republic.

properties.name: Montitia
properties.description: Montitia was a poverty-stricken planet in the Montitia system of the Montitian Grant sector, located within the Expansion Region of the galaxy. The region of space around Montitia was explored between 1000 and 25 BBY, and during the Extorin Minor skirmishes, the world's populace was threatened by the Extorin aggressors and evacuated. Montitia was within unaligned space during the Clone Wars, and by the Imperial Period the planet was inhabited again and was controlled by the Galactic Empire. Its alien residents were often recruited by the Corporate Sector Authority to work on the Corporate Sector world of Duroon, where they were kept in near-slavery. The Human fringer Bash Fateau was born on Montitia.

properties.name: Mooga
properties.description: Mooga was a planet in the Mooga system of the Perkell sector. It was the homeworld of the Moogan species.

properties.name: Moonflower Nebula
properties.description: The Moonflower Nebula was a nebula located within the Wild Space region of the galaxy, near Pzob. It was speckled with asteroids.

properties.name: Moonus Mandel
properties.description: Moonus Mandel was a planet in the Mid Rim's Bothan sector, and the homeworld of the Veknoid species.

properties.name: Moorja
properties.poi: Confederate base, Crumbling Lands, New Republic base,
properties.description: Moorja was a small Inner Rim world on the Corellian Trade Spine. It was owned by the Salliche Agricultural Corporation, which ran an agricultural and mining colony there. Though the planet was frequently swept by fierce ion storms capable of interfering with electronic equipment, it was a major exporter of foodstuffs.

properties.name: Moorjhone
properties.description: Moorjhone was a planet located in the galaxy's Outer Rim Territories, within the Jospro sector and was the homeworld of felinoid Moorjhoni. It was in a trinary star system. It was normally lit and heated by two of the three suns at a given time, once every ten years, however, all three suns would rise on the same side of the planet, resulting in the Day of Three Suns.

properties.name: Morado
properties.description: Morado was a planet located in the Hune sector of the Mid Rim.

properties.name: Moraband
properties.poi: Sith temple , Valley of the Dark Lords, Sith temple ,
properties.description: Moraband, known in antiquity as Korriban, was an Outer Rim planet that was home to the ancient Sith. The desolate and mountainous world was abandoned after many ancient wars. The Valley of the Dark Lords on the planet's surface was the final resting place of Darth Bane, the Sith Lord who created the Rule of Two. During the Clone Wars, Yoda ventured to the abandoned world as part of his journey to discover the secrets of eternal consciousness.

properties.name: Moralan
properties.description: Moralan was a Hutt Space planet that was home to the Moralans, a slave species of the Hutt Empire. During the conflict between the Hutts and the Tionese conqueror Xim twenty-five millennia before the Battle of Yavin, the forces of the latter entered the Moralan system.

properties.name: Morath Nebula
properties.description: The Morath Nebula was a volume of space located in the Galactic Core, in the Hatawa sector. In 17 ABY, it had still not been fully explored, and was thus considered as a possible hiding-place for the Black Fleet.

properties.name: Mordagon
properties.description: Mordagon was a planet in the Expansion Region, and was the homeworld of the Mordageen, bipedal sentients that had pink skin and pointy ears. One Mordageen from Mordagon was Bendix Fust, who became a smuggler working for the Dug crime lord Sebolto.

properties.name: Morellia
properties.description: Morellia was an astronomical object located within the Morellia system, a part of the Wild Space star cluster known as the Morellian Commonwealth. It was the homeworld of the Morellian lawman and scout Barosa Warren.

properties.name: Morishim
properties.poi: Tatmana Mountains, High Tatmana, New Republic Starfighter Base, Old Recluse's cave,
properties.description: Morishim was a planet in the Albarrio sector of the Outer Rim and the homeworld of the Morish species.

properties.name: Morning's Bell
properties.description: Doornik-319  Morning's Bell and Preza) was a planet in the Doornik-319 system. The planet was known to the Kubaz as Morning's Bell and to the Yevetha as Preza. Originally a Kubaz colony world, it was taken over by the Yevetha during the Great Purge, during which the Yevetha wiped out the Kubaz colonists.

properties.name: Moro
properties.description: Moro was a male Human officer in the Corellian Security Force during the Galactic War. During the Battle of Corellia, he informed fellow officer Danod about the death of Ben Kahob at the hands of the Coronas gang.

properties.name: Morseer
properties.description: Morseer was a Morseerian colony in the Outer Rim Territories. It was controlled by the Drackmarians, to whom the Morseerians were underlings. The actual location of the Morseerians' homeworld was unknown, as was its name.

properties.name: Morton
properties.description: Morton was a male Human who lived during the waning years of the Galactic Republic, serving sergeant within the Office of Peace and Security, a law enforcement agency that operated on the planet Cularin. He was a contact of the Thaereian military captain Drom Virbilge and in circa 31 BBY, Virbilge contacted Morton, warning him that there was going to be some trouble at the house of Krol-Pek, a male Cerean who lived in the city Gadrin on Cularin. Virbilge also gave Morton a datacard and told him to give it to the Heroes of Cularin, a group of freelance agents who possessed a datapad containing some information regarding three data transmitters that had been placed on Cularin by the Metatheran Cartel. Morton and a number of OPS troopers then made their way to Krol-Pek's house and captured a group of mercenaries that were attacking the building.

properties.name: Morvogodine
properties.description: Morvogodine was a planet crawling with life that was located in the Calaron sector of the Outer Rim Territories. The Galactic Empire occupied Morvogodine during the Galactic Civil War and hosted a notoriously vicious stormtrooper training facility on the planet. Shortly before the Battle of Yavin, the Empire arrested famous musician Maxa Jandovar on Morvogodine to suppress her politically outspoken artistic endeavors.

properties.name: Moseum
properties.description: Moseum was a planet located in the Moseum system within the Thesme sector of the Outer Rim Territories.

properties.name: Moshaw
properties.description: The Moshaw Dark Star was a black hole located on the edge of the Outer Rim Territories' Seswenna sector. The swoop gang known as the Dark Star Hellions originated in the space neighboring the black hole.

properties.name: Mossak
properties.description: Mossak was a planet in the Outer Rim Territories' Thanium sector, located at the end of the Perlemian Trade Route and at the start of the Tingel Arm. It was located near Felucia and Galidraan. It was part of Xim's Empire.

properties.name: Motexx
properties.description: Motexx was a planet located in the Colonies region on the other side of the Black Nebula from Arat Fraca.

properties.name: Movris
properties.description: Movris was a planet located in the Noonian sector of the Outer Rim Territories.

properties.name: Mowgle
properties.description: Mowgle was a low-tech agriworld in the Core Worlds, one day and three hours from Demophon with a Class 1 hyperdrive. It was responsible for much of the consumables produced for Demophon during the Galactic Civil War. Thadius Black arranged for political prisoners from Demophon to be smuggled here as cargo soon before the Demophon system was destroyed in a supernova.

properties.name: Mrisst
properties.description: Mrisst was a mid-sized planet, located in the Fakir sector of the Colonies. It had a mild climate, and its four continents were dotted with small lakes and rivers. Jungle made up the majority of the terrain, consisting of spinetrees, spirepines, and a variety of other flora. It was the homeworld of the Mrissi.

properties.name: Mrlsst
properties.poi: Mrlsst Spaceport, Artists' High Commune, Mrlsst Trade and Science Academy, The Soundmound, Central Academic Hospital, Falken's Lab, JAN Camp, Mrlsst Center for Linguistic Studies,
properties.description: Mrlsst was a planet located in the Tapani sector's Freeworlds Territory on the Shapani Bypass. It was the homeworld of the Mrlssi and a voting member of the League of Tapani Freeworlds.

properties.name: Msst
properties.description: Msst was a Mid Rim planet, and the homeworld of Brakiss. It was a small planet in the Msst system, which had an Imperial stronghold. The Empire had theoretically abandoned it after the Invasion of Bakura. Luke Skywalker came to Msst in search of Brakiss, where, shortly after landing, he was attacked by a group of mistmakers.

properties.name: Mugaar
properties.description: Mugaar was the Mugaari homeworld. It was localized in Mugaari Space, on the Corellian Trade Spine.

properties.name: Mulatan
properties.description: Mulatan was a planet located in the Bootana Hutta region of Hutt Space. It served as a guardian world dedicated to the defense of the Bootana Hutta and its throneworlds.

properties.name: Mullan
properties.description: Mullan was a terrestrial world located in the Mullan system. It was a part of the Keldrath sector in the Greater Tion historical region, which in turn was situated within the Slice portion of the Outer Rim Territories. The hyperlane known as the Pakuuni Drift connected Mullan to the Gbu system as well as the Brigia system in the neighboring Tion Hegemony sector.

properties.name: Mulvar Sensor Station
properties.description: The Mulvar Sensor Station was a space station located in the Obtrexta sector of the Outer Rim Territories.

properties.name: Munlali Mafir
properties.description: Munlali Mafir was a planet in the Unknown Regions.

properties.name: Munto Codru
properties.description: Munto Codru was a remote and backwater world in the Outer Rim Territories located within the Codru system on the Overic Griplink, between Pakuuni and the Calamari sector. Its sole sentient species were the Codru-Ji, who were born as canine wyrwulfs before metamorphosis upon reaching maturity.

properties.name: Murgo
properties.description: Murgo was an astronomical object located in the galaxy's Mid Rim.

properties.name: Murk
properties.description: Murk was an astronomical object located in the Moddell sector of the Outer Rim Territories in grid square H-16 of the Standard Galactic Grid. It lay on the Sanctuary Pipeline, a hyperspace route that connected the Moddell sector moon of Endor to the Sullust sector planet Sullust. Murk was depicted on a map of the Moddell sector included with the Rebel Alliance collection of non-electronic documents known as The Rebel Files.

properties.name: Murkhana
properties.description: Murkhana was a planet in the Auril sector on which the Battle of Murkhana was fought during the Outer Rim Sieges.

properties.name: Murninkam
properties.description: Murninkam was a tropical world far from the space lanes. The Kajiin Swamp can be found there.

properties.name: Muskree
properties.description: Muskree was a backwater planet in the Outer Rim Territories. Its lone settlement was the failed mining colony Hardscrabble.

properties.name: Mussubir
properties.description: Mussubir III, or simply Mussubir, was a planet located in the Mussubir system of the Senex sector, in the Mid Rim of the galaxy. It was an important industrial world controlled by House Araba.

properties.name: Mustafar
properties.poi: Klegger Corp Mining FacilityDamask Holdings Mustafar accounting facilityBlack Sun fortressBerken's FlowTulrus IslandBurning PlainsSmoking ForestCrystal FlatsGizor Dellso's droid foundryMensix Mining FacilityJedi Enclave
properties.description: Mustafar was a small planet located in the Mustafar system of the Outer Rim Territories, coreward of Rutan, between the Hydian Way and the Ninth Quadrant.

properties.name: Muunilinst
properties.poi: High Port Space Center, InterGalactic Banking Clan HeadquartersSan Hill's ruling citadelWestern SeaDamask Holdings superspire
properties.description: Muunilinst , nicknamed Moneylend, was the temperate, mineral-rich Muun colony world and the headquarters of the InterGalactic Banking Clan. It was located on the Braxant Run. It was a member of the Confederacy of Independent Systems under Chairman San Hill.

properties.name: Muzara
properties.description: Muzara was a planet in the Expansion Region. Humans from Brentaal colonized the planet in 4000 BBY, barely avoiding conflict with the native Muzaran people, who were also known as the Muza.

properties.name: Mycroft
properties.poi: Intergalactic Zoological Society, Repair Station M13,
properties.description: Mycroft was a planet in the Fakir sector.

properties.name: Mygeeto
properties.poi: Dressian Kiolsh Merchant Bank, Rebel outpost,
properties.description: Mygeeto was a wealthy InterGalactic Banking Clan colony between Ord Biniir and Morishim under the control of the Confederacy of Independent Systems.

properties.name: Mylok
properties.description: Mylok was the Mylok system's primary star.

properties.name: Myomar
properties.description: Myomar was a planet in the Deadalis sector of the Expansion Region, and the site of Imperial starship maintenance facilities. After the inception of the Galactic Empire, Grand Admiral Ishin-Il-Raz conducted a massacre on the planet. Years later, Han Solo and Chewbacca stole the Millennium Falcon's deflector shield generators from an Imperial facility on Myomar.

properties.name: Myrenia
properties.description: The Myrenia was Coh Veshiv's personal Lambda-class shuttle, stationed aboard the Empire Forever. When Veshiv was captured by Dhas Fenoep Vedij and the crew of the Far Orbit, they also took control of the Myrenia.

properties.name: Myrkr
properties.description: Myrkr was a forested world, located fairly close to the galaxy's major population centers in the outskirts of the Inner Rim Territories. It was close to the borders with the Expansion Region and relatively near to the planet of Wayland. It was believed to be the homeworld of the Neti species, although the Neti established a colony on Ryyk some time prior to 4000 BBY, apparently abandoning Myrkr.

properties.name: Mytaranor
properties.description: Mytaranor was a bleak industrial world located in the Mytaranor system, a part of the Kashyyyk Region's Mytaranor sector in the Slice portion of the Mid Rim. The hyperlane known as the Nightroad linked it to the Tholatin system as well as the Terr'skiar sector's Pizilis system.

properties.name: Mytus
properties.description: Mytus was an astronomical object located in the regions known as the Outer Rim Territories and the New Territories. It was located within grid square S-3 on the Standard Galactic Grid.

properties.name: MZX32905
properties.description: The MZX32905 system was a star system in the Outer Rim. It was located in the Kanz sector, near Bimmiel and Lorrd. The system contained an asteroid field that itself contained The Home—an asteroid home to first Darth Vectivus, and later Dark Lady of the Sith Lumiya.

properties.name: N'dian
properties.description: N'dian was a planet located in the N'dian system, a part of the Spadja sector within the Outer Rim Territories and Trans-Hydian regions.

properties.name: N'ildwab
properties.description: N'ildwab was a rocky planet in the Outer Rim with many canyons. The inhabitants of N'ildwab lived very simple lives. Because of this, in an effort to control the people, Nobam Nol terrorized the inhabitants and claimed to be a Sith. He was able to mimick Force powers because of his wired gloves. Because of his terrorism, the people of N'ildwab hired Boba Fett to kill Nol. Fett was successful.

properties.name: N'zoth
properties.poi: Black Fifteen, Hariz Downside, Valley of Rejection,
properties.description: N'zoth was the fifth planet in the N'zoth system, located in the Farlax sector in the Koornacht Cluster, near the Core Worlds. It was most well known for being the home world of the Yevetha.

properties.name: Naalol
properties.description: Naalol was a sparsely-inhabited backwater planet, third in the Naalol system, with a small Imperial garrison. It was the Oquan headquarters. It had high peaks, winding ridges, with small towns in the mountains, and larger cities in the plains below.

properties.name: Naboo
properties.poi: Lianorm Swamp, Lake Paonga, Emperor's Retreat, Imperial Weapon Research Facility, Great Grass Plains, Gallo Mountains, Solleu River, Caves of Eleuabad, Gungan Caves, Gungan Sacred Place, Lake Country, Sacred Forest of Naboo, Theed Royal Palace, Ranchlands, Lors, Lasay Swamp,
properties.description: Naboo  was a planet that was the sector capital of the Chommell sector in the Mid Rim, near the border with the Outer Rim Territories. The planet had an unusual plasma core, and its surface was a largely unspoiled world with large plains, swamps and seas.

properties.name: Nadhe
properties.description: Nadhe was a remote planet that defied Emperor Palpatine shortly after the formation of the Galactic Empire. Like the other worlds that refused to cooperate, Nadhe suffered an unspecified devastation as a result.

properties.name: Nadiem
properties.description: Nadiem was a remote planet in the Outer Rim Territories. It was close to Teth.

properties.name: Nahsu Minor
properties.description: Nahsu Minor was a temperate, grassy planet located in the Ktilac Regions, an Allied Region in the Inner Rim. It was the homeworld of the Murachaun species, who, along with the Ktilacs and Tocoyans, two other species native to the region, developed a quasi-religion in which each species was seen as complementary to the other two and constructed a network of cities, towns, and farms. At some time during the Galactic Civil War, the Galactic Empire took thousands of Murachaun off world to work as slaves due to their industrious nature. The planet remained peaceful, although thousands of off-world Murachauns secretly joined the Rebel Alliance. The Ktilac Regions retained Allied Region status under the New Republic and the Galactic Federation of Free Alliances.

properties.name: Najarka
properties.description: Najarka was a planet located in the Outer Rim's Rayter sector.

properties.name: Najiba
properties.description: Najiba was the Najib homeworld. It was a remote world covered with wetlands and its surface was lashed with atmospheric electrical discharges and frequent rainstorms.

properties.name: Nak Shimor
properties.description: Nak Shimor was a planet in the Colonies, on the Perlemian Trade Route near the border with the Inner Rim. Andur Sunrider purchased the Lightside Explorer on Nak Shimor from a Vultan dealer.

properties.name: Nakrikal Singularity
properties.description: The Nakrikal Singularity was a black hole that lay in the Outer Rim Territories' Grumani sector. It affected the navigation computers of starships traveling along the nearby Sanrafsix Corridor hyperlane. In 1032 BBY, the Sith Lord Arkadia Calimondra attempted to dispose of the mercenary transport Diligence by providing the vessel's commander, Brigadier Jarrow Rusher, with hyperspace coordinates that would unknowingly lead his ship into the Nakrikal Singularity.

properties.name: Nal Hutta
properties.poi: Eastern GrimeWinter PalaceGardulla the Hutt's PalaceHutt PalacesJabba's Nal Hutta PalaceMama the Hutt's houseNem'ro's PalaceFa'athra's PalaceJiguuna,
properties.description: Nal Hutta , also known simply as Hutta, was the capital of Hutt Space and was located in the Y'Toub system. It was formerly known as Evocar and was the original home world of the Evocii, who were ousted by the Hutts in 15,000 BBY, who migrated from their original home world of Varl along with their servants the t'landa Til. The planet was controlled by the ancient ruling Hutt families, who also ruled its moon Nar Shaddaa from Nal Hutta and became the new capital of Hutt Space.

properties.name: Naldar
properties.description: Naldar was an Outer Rim world in the Phelleem sector.

properties.name: Nalrith
properties.description: Nalrith was a terrestrial planet located in the Nalrith system, a part of the Outer Rim Territories' Rseik sector. It was the homeworld of the Nalrithians, a species of sentient insectoids.

properties.name: Nalyd
properties.description: Nalyd was a planet, and home of the Nalydians. It was a planet of swirling orange fog and its surface was covered by towering mesas and pinnacles. Nalyd's cities were built around these pinnacles. The planet was also home to two non-sentient giant spider and a floating jellyfish species. The inhabitants practiced death penalties on citizens who had broken the law, and it was here that Ania Solo and Jao Assam, went to look for Darth Wredd's minion Dieben in 138 ABY.

properties.name: Nam Chorios
properties.poi: Bleak Point StationRuby GulchAdmirable AdmiralCrystal ValleyKesla VeinThurmikOuter DistanceSalvation PointBlue Blerd of Happiness Tavern
properties.description: Nam Chorios was a planet in the Chorios system. Though desolate, it was able to support Human life. It was even able to grow vegetation, such as brachniel and gomex moss. The planet was in a constant state of dusk due to its dim sun.

properties.name: Nam Priax
properties.description: Nam Priax was an oceanic planet located within the Nam Priax system of the Outer Rim Territories.

properties.name: Nam'ta
properties.description: Nam'ta was a gas giant located in the Nam'ta system, a part of the Outer Rim Territories' Atrivis sector. Its clouds formed bands of red, orange, and white. The planet was inhabited during the Galactic War between the Galactic Republic and the resurgent Sith Empire, and governed by a local government. At that time a local organization planned to leak thousands of Republic diplomatic dispatches, prompting a Republic-allied individual to urge the local government to clamp down on the organization.

properties.name: Namadii
properties.description: Namadii was an astronomical object located in the Namadii system, a part of the Churnis sector in the New Territories portion of the Mid Rim. It lay at the endpoint of the hyperlane known as the Namadii Corridor, which connected it to the Ansion system.

properties.name: Namore
properties.description: Namore was a planet located in the Namore system, a part of the Southern Core portion of the Colonies. Gerom was an official on the planet who held the title of Prefect. Hailey LaMelle was considered to be Namore's most notable holonews reporter, while Dasar Zorm was a notorious local racketeer.

properties.name: Nanta-Ri
properties.description: Nanta-Ri was a planet in the Farlax sector of the Core Worlds. The New Republic Fourth Battle Group was sent to blockade it during the Black Fleet Crisis.

properties.name: Nantama
properties.description: Nantama was a wealthy resort world, controlled by House Elegin, renowned for the natural beauty of its fields. The Third Nantama Synod was held there.

properties.name: Nanth'ri
properties.description: Nanth'ri was a planet found along the Nanth'ri Route. Celis Mott hailed from this world.

properties.name: Nantuker
properties.description: Nantuker was a planet in the Corsair Outback region of the Hapes Cluster. It was the source of premium Nantuker dates.

properties.name: Naos
properties.description: Naos was an astronomical object located in the regions known as the Outer Rim Territories and the Slice. It was situated in grid square S-18 on the Standard Galactic Grid.

properties.name: Naporar
properties.description: Naporar was a planet located in the Naporar system of the Unknown Regions' Chiss Space. The hyperlane known as the Path of the Houses linked it to the Ornfra and Sposia systems, while the Chasdemonus Route connected it to the Colonial Station Cam'co system.

properties.name: Naps Fral Cluster
properties.description: The Naps Fral Cluster was located on the hyperlanes that connected Ryloth to Nal Hutta. It was the frequent stage of ambushes masterminded by the Karazak Slavers Cooperative who attacked ships in search of Twi'lek women to enslave.

properties.name: Nar Bo Sholla
properties.description: Nar Bo Sholla was a Hutt Space world that was the homeworld of the poisonous spor crawler insect. It was a part of the Hutt Empire twenty-five millennia before the Battle of Yavin. In 25 BBY, the Human Morteos was born on Nar Bo Sholla. Three years later, it became one of the worlds that suffered damage from an infestation of the structure-damaging arthropods known as stone mites. The Nar Bo Sholla system was later conquered by the extra-galactic Yuuzhan Vong during their invasion of the galaxy.

properties.name: Nar Chunna
properties.description: Nar Chunna was a planet located in the Bootana Hutta region of Hutt Space. It served primarily as a trade outpost and was said to be awash in priceless artifacts.

properties.name: Nar Haaska
properties.description: Nar Haaska was a Hutt Space trade world. It was a part of the territory controlled by the Hutts by 25,000 BBY, and by 17 BBY, the world became a part of the Galactic Empire. During the Yuuzhan Vong War, the extra-galactic Yuuzhan Vong conquered the Nar Haaska system.

properties.name: Nar Kaaga
properties.description: Nar Kaaga was a planet located in Hutt Space. It was a cold, swampy world that survived on trade. It was home to the H'uun and Shell Hutt clans.

properties.name: Nar Kreeta
properties.description: Nar Kreeta was a Hutt colony and major trade world, located at the nexus of the Pabol Kreeta and Pabol Sleheyron.

properties.name: Nara
properties.description: The Nara system was a star system located in the Colonies region of the galaxy.

properties.name: Narg
properties.description: Narg was an isolated planet in the Rayter sector of the Outer Rim Territories. Its Human inhabitants were known to be xenophobic. During the Galactic Civil War, the planet was controlled by TransGalMeg Industries, Incorporated.

properties.name: Nars
properties.description: Nars was a terrestrial planet located in the Nars system of the Senex sector, a part of the Senex-Juvex region in the Western Reaches portion of the Mid Rim. A hyperlane linked it to the Knores system.

properties.name: Narth
properties.description: Narth was a planet evacuated along with Ihopek after the Battle of Endor by the Galactic Empire. The Star Destroyer Gnisnal was crippled by internal explosions and had to be scuttled. The wreckage later gave the New Republic the complete copy of the Imperial Order of battle.

properties.name: Narvath
properties.description: Narvath was the Narvath homeworld. Many members of its local underground joined the Rebel Alliance. It was later a member world of the New Republic.

properties.name: Nath Goordi
properties.description: Nath Goordi was a planet located within the Nath Goordi system of the Mid Rim that was home to a procession of royal heirs.

properties.name: Nathema
properties.description: Nathema, originally known as Medriaas, was a fertile agriworld located in the Nathema system of the Outer Rim Territories' Chorlian sector. During the reign of the Sith Empire in 5103 BBY, the planet's ruler, Sith Lord Dramath, was deposed in by his own illegitimate son Tenebrae, who received the title of Lord Vitiate and rulership of Medriaas from the reigning Dark Lord of the Sith, Marka Ragnos. Renaming the planet Nathema, Vitiate kept his world isolated from the power plays of his fellow Sith over the next century, and his isolation spared Nathema from the Great Hyperspace War in 5000 BBY. The following year, Vitiate summoned the eight thousand remaining Sith Lords to Nathema in order to save the crumbling Sith Empire and dominated their minds, proceeding to combine their strength and a superweapon known as Zildrog in a complex ritual of Sith magic that granted him immortality while stripping the Force from the entire planet.

properties.name: Natinati
properties.description: Natinati was a planet in Wild Space. One of the main cities was Poborandurannum, where Jabba the Hutt once rented a secret chamber.

properties.name: Nativum
properties.description: Nativum was a planet. During the Clone Wars, the Confederacy of Independent Systems changed their plans — instead of attacking Nativum, they changed to Azure.

properties.name: Nazzri
properties.poi: Hall of Edification, Prrit Qabaq's palace,
properties.description: Nazzri was a Mid Rim planet that was located in the Lantillian sector and was the homeworld of the sentient Nazzar species. The planet had become a member of the Galactic Republic by 17,000 BBY and was one of the worlds that provided it with armies during the Great Hyperspace War of 5000 BBY. Around that time, the Nazzar government, which was originally a monarchy, and Emperor-King Prrit Qabaq of Nazzri, had became corrupted by the use of dark magic. Eventually, the return of Qabaq's daughter, Princess Ikree, to Nazzri from a self-imposed exile precipitated a civil war between the government and opposing rebels. Qabaq was killed in battle, and Ikree became the first queen-praefect of a new theocratic government based on the Ulizra religion.

properties.name: NCW-781
properties.poi: Approach Route Alpha, Target Bantha, Target Dewback, Target Tallon, Target Yavin,
properties.description: NCW-781 was an unexplored Wild Space planet. A terrestrial world, its surface featured mountains, canyons, and woods. During the Galactic Civil War, the Rebel Alliance operative Kala Kevv was shot down over NCW-781, where he crash-landed while carrying a data plaque with information vital to the Alliance.

properties.name: Near Indosa
properties.description: Near Indosa was a mining planet that was situated in the north-eastern quadrant of the galaxy and located within the Near Indosa system on the Junction-Tierell Loop hyperlane. The hyperlane was situated in the Gordian Reach sector of the Outer Rim Territories. Near Indosa had been heavily excavated by miners for millennia, which was the reason why most of the planet's mineral resources almost completely disappeared. It was also the reason that many of the miners went to the Far Indosa system during the last days of the Galactic Republic.

properties.name: Near Pando
properties.description: Near Pando was an emerging trade world that was located within the Near Pando system in Hutt Space, a region of the galaxy controlled by the Hutt species. The planet lay on the hyperlane called the Pando Spur that connected it to the world of Far Pando. Near Pando was the site of ancient and mysterious ruins known as the Malabar Construct.

properties.name: Neary
properties.description: Neary was a celestial body located in the Neary system, a part of the Calaron sector in the Slice portion of the Outer Rim Territories. Around 2 ABY, the Rebel Alliance Task Force on Alliance Security compiled a SecuriDex datafile on the former scout Yurdak Fav, and the file named Neary as Fav's last known location.

properties.name: Nebula Forso
properties.description: Nebula Forso was a nebula located within the Meram sector of the Outer Rim Territories.

properties.name: Nedij
properties.description: Nedij was a planet in the Outer Rim on the eastern spiral arm of the galaxy. It had thin air in which its native species evolved. Natural terrain included snowy mountains which the Nediji preferred, and lowlands. The planet was inhabited by a species of humanoids which served as prey for the Nediji. The Black Sun operative Kaird hailed from this planet.

properties.name: Needan
properties.description: Needan was a Wild Space planet. A jungle world featuring massive oceans and numerous species of plants and animals, it was the homeworld of the sentient Geelan. Just as the Geelan civilization on Needan had entered the information age, a passing comet struck the planet, causing the climate to become permanently cold.

properties.name: Neelabi
properties.description: The Neelabi were a shy, fish-like species from Neelabi who could only breathe in water. They can be easily identified by their beady eyes and short stature. The podracer Occo Ninebar was forced to race in a podracer with a water filled bubble. Thus, if he crashed, he could not escape quickly if his cockpit was thrust into a wall.

properties.name: Neelanon
properties.description: Neelanon was a planet located in the Neelanon system of the Senex sector, a part of the Senex-Juvex region in the Western Reaches portion of the Mid Rim. The Senex Trace hyperlane linked it to the Fengrine and Senex systems, while another hyperspace route connected it to the Crovna system.

properties.name: Neelgaimon
properties.description: Neelgaimon was a hot, drought-ridden planet in the Xappyh sector of the Outer Rim Territories.

properties.name: Neimoidia
properties.poi: Communal Hives Fungus Farms Neimoidian shipyards,
properties.description: Neimoidia, also called Pure Neimoidia to avoid confusion with the Neimoidian purse worlds, was a planet in the Colonies region that the Duros from Duro colonized sometime around 25,000 BBY, bringing it into the Galactic Republic.

properties.name: Neka
properties.description: Neka was a planet in the Outer Rim. During the Jedi Civil War, it was subject to a Sith blockade which stopped incoming and outgoing space traffic. The Sith then virus-bombed the world, killing all of its intelligent life. Only a few fortunate individuals, including the Hutt businessman Shuma, were able to bypass the blockade and escape the devastation.

properties.name: Nelfrus
properties.description: Nelfrus was a planet in the Elrood sector.

properties.name: Nella
properties.description: The Nella system was a star system located in the Tapani sector's Mecetti Province, on the Calipsa Run.

properties.name: Nellac Kram
properties.description: Nellac Kram was planet in Outer Rim Territories in the Bon'nyuw-Luq sector. The New Republic freighter Nartissteu was based out of Nellac Kram.

properties.name: Nelvaan
properties.description: Nelvaan was a planet in the Koobi system in the Savareen sector of the Outer Rim Territories and was located at galactic coordinates Q-16. A frigid world, Nelvaan was home to the sentient Nelvaanian people. The Nelvaanians were considered primitive to many, as they lived in tribal villages, one of which was named Rokrul. Each village was led by a chieftain and their bond-mate along with a shaman who served as consultant on most matters. Religion was central in Nelvaanian culture, and the planet itself was referred to as the Great Mother. Therefore, when the Techno Union built a laboratory during the galactic Clone Wars that was powered by a siphon generator, a machine that absorbed geothermal energy, and the planet was plunged into an ice age, the locals became very concerned. The villagers sent all their male warriors to discover the cause of the Mother's plight, but none returned.

properties.name: Nelvana Gas Cluster
properties.description: The Nelvana Gas Cluster was a gas cluster in the Mid Rim. In 0 ABY, a group of Rebel agents claimed to be a survey crew heading to the cluster when they were challenged by Bannistar Station officials.

properties.name: Nentan
properties.description: Nentan was a terrestrial planet located in the Nentan system of the Glythe sector. Nentan was a barren planet, and the main point of interest was the ancient ruins of a city built by an unknown alien species. During the Galactic Civil War, Nentan briefly hosted an Alliance base. The facility was evacuated after being discovered two months after going operational. Captain Bren Derlin's actions during the evacuation earned him a promotion to the rank of Major.

properties.name: Neona
properties.description: Neona was a temperate planet in the Tapani sector's Freeworlds Territory, populated by an indigenous sentient species. In 19,997 BBY, the planet experienced a period of intense geological warming that melted the ice caps and plunged the landmass below massive oceans, sparing only two ice-continents, one located at each pole. The native species was consumed by the tides and succumbed to extinction, leaving behind only extravagent ruins interred beneath the waves as proof of their existence.

properties.name: Nepoy
properties.description: Nepoy was a Mid Rim planet in the Nepoy system, Senex sector known for its legendary fruit fields. Nectarwine and other sugary alcoholic beverages were the planets' chief exports.

properties.name: Neree
properties.description: Neree was a planet found in the Suolriep sector of the Outer Rim Territories.

properties.name: Nerrif
properties.description: Nerrif was a Galactic Republic space station on the Mid Rim.

properties.name: Neshtab
properties.description: Neshtab was a planet of snowy ice plains located in the Inner Rim region of the galaxy.

properties.name: Nessem
properties.description: Nessem was a Trade Federation planet in the Expansion Region. It was orbited by the modest Nessem Shipyards.

properties.name: Netolio
properties.description: The Netolio system was a star system located in the Tapani sector's Pelagia Province, near Betolio system. It was annexed by Calipsa Province with the rise of the New Order.

properties.name: New Agamar
properties.description: New Agamar was a high-gravity planet in the Galactic Republic. At least one native was enlisted in the Republic military by the time of the late Clone Wars.

properties.name: New Alderaan
properties.description: New Alderaan was a planet in the Outer Rim Ash Worlds. It was home to thousands of former residents of Alderaan that moved to after the Destruction of Alderaan by the first Death Star.

properties.name: New Apsolon
properties.description: Apsolon, later renamed New Apsolon, was a world located in the Terr'skiar sector of the Mid Rim. During the Great Sith War, it was a part of the Sith Empire.

properties.name: New Ator
properties.description: New Ator was an agriworld located in the New Ator system, a part of the Arkanis sector in the Slice portion of the Outer Rim Territories. It was situated on the Triellus Trade Route hyperlane, which linked it to the Kemal Station and Trulalis systems. New Ator was a part of the informal grouping of planets known as the Regency Worlds, and it was settled by Atorese colonists in approximately 80 BBY.

properties.name: New Bakstre
properties.description: New Bakstre was a planet located within the Tendrannan subsector of the Outer Rim's New Territories. Part of the loosely affiliated domain known as the Cassandran Worlds, New Bakstre was a planet dominated by industry situated on the important Braxant Run hyperlane that served much of the galaxy's northern quadrant. One of New Bakstre's major settlements, Havridam City, was partially destroyed in 22 BBY after activists from the Mechanical Liberation Front accidentally detonated a shipment of Vindicator XM-15 "brilliant" missiles. The planet was involved in the later stages of the Clone Wars when Jedi-led Galactic Republic forces engaged the military of the Confederacy of Independent Systems on the world's surface. Annexed by the Galactic Empire along with the entirety of the Cassandran Worlds roughly twenty years later, New Bakstre remained under Imperial control during the Galactic Civil War and the Second Galactic Civil War, with a brief intermediate spell, during which it was allied with the New Republic. New Bakstre possessed seven moons, a rapid rotation rate, and a sky that was colored purple.

properties.name: New Balosar
properties.description: New Balosar was a planet in the Expansion Region, located on the Great Gran Run. It was the location of The Kindest Cut, a beauty salon run by Zenn Bien.

properties.name: New Bornalex
properties.description: New Bornalex was an Outer Rim planet that was aligned with the Confederacy of Independent Systems during the Clone Wars. Cyl Sant and her daughter Rystáll were from this world.

properties.name: New Brampis
properties.description: New Brampis was the site of the New Brampis Starship Museum.

properties.name: New Brigia
properties.description: New Brigia was a planet in the Koornacht Cluster.

properties.name: New Canistel
properties.description: New Canistel was a planet located in the Demetras sector of the Outer Rim Territories.

properties.name: New Cov
properties.description: New Cov was the third planet in the Churba system of the Churba sector, located in the Mid Rim.

properties.name: New Cylimba
properties.description: New Cylimba was a planet within a star system in the D'Aelgoth sector of the Mid Rim region of the galaxy. It was situated on the Veron Route, which connected it to Veron. It was an industrial world whose badlands were the location of an Alliance base during the Galactic Civil War. The base and its crew would likely have been crushed by Imperial forces, had Rivoche Tarkin not provided the necessary intelligence to avoid the attack.

properties.name: New Heurkea
properties.description: The New Heurkea system was a star system located in Mon Calamari Space of the Outer Rim Territories. It lay between the Mantan and Sanctuary systems on the Prously's Rim Run hyperlane. The system shared its name with Heurkea, a city on the planet Mon Calamari.

properties.name: New Holgha
properties.description: New Holgha was a terrestrial planet in the Outer Rim Territories' Ciutric sector, known for its Five Holy Cities. During the Yuuzhan Vong War, it was easily conquered by the extragalactic invaders after the New Republic, believing Mandalorian intelligence on the upcoming attack to be untrustworthy, relocated New Holgha's defense force elsewhere.

properties.name: New Holstice
properties.description: New Holstice was a Mid Rim hospital world between Belderone and Roche. It was part of the Galactic Republic since before 4000 BBY, and contained a monument to all Jedi killed since the formation of the Republic.

properties.name: New Javis
properties.description: The New Javis system was a star system located in the Tapani sector's Pelagia Province, on the Calipsa Run. Prior to the rise of the Galactic Empire, the system was part of Pelagia Province. After House Mecetti decimated House Pelagia, New Javis system was taken over by House Calipsa. The system had the second highest population in Calipsa Province next only to Calipsa itself. After the rise of the New Order, the system was annexed by Calipsa Province.

properties.name: New Plympto
properties.description: New Plympto was a temperate terrestrial planet in the Core Worlds region populated by Nosaurians. It was discovered by Corellians around 10,000 BBY - although the Jedi Order apparently had contact with it since at least 25,000 BBY, using the native population as potential recruits. The planet was also the homeworld of podracer pilot Clegg Holdfast. Its capital was the city of Phemiss.

properties.name: New Polokia
properties.description: New Polokia was a colony world between Darepp and Motexx visited by the Star Morning.

properties.name: New Ralltiir
properties.description: New Ralltiir was a planet on which Han Solo, Leia Organa Solo, and Chewbacca rested after the first defeat of the clone of Palpatine. While there, Voren Na'al interviewed Han about his exploits in the Corporate Sector years before.

properties.name: New Shella
properties.description: The New Shella system was in the Freeworlds Territory of the Tapani sector, between the Lamuir and Procopia systems.

properties.name: Nexus Ortai
properties.description: Nexus Ortai was a Mid Rim planet located at the intersection of two hyperlanes. It was considered a peaceful world.

properties.name: Nez Peron
properties.description: Nez Peron was an Outer Rim agriworld and the homeworld of the powerful D'Asta family.

properties.name: Nezni
properties.description: The Nezni system was an Outer Rim system located in the Mayagil Sector. An incident between the pirate group, Hurrim and the Rebel Alliance occurred here, after the Hurrim started attacking the Imperial citizens that the combined forces were scavenging.

properties.name: Nfolgai
properties.description: Nfolgai was a world on the Descri Wris in Sith Space. Sorzus Syn encountered a Mrlssi slave on this world, burdened with stones and nearly unrecognizable under its soot-slicked feathers.

properties.name: Nibiru
properties.description: Nibiru was a forest world, which also boasted at least one large lake. It was located in the Outer Rim's Kakani sector.

properties.name: Nicandra
properties.description: Nicandra may refer to one of the following:

properties.name: Nichen
properties.description: Nichen was a planet found in the Outer Rim Territories. Kettemoor jumped to this location after its encounter with the Teljkon Vagabond.

properties.name: Nicht Ka
properties.description: Nicht Ka was a planet in the Sith Worlds, a region of space within the Stygian Caldera, which was located in the Esstran sector of the Outer Rim Territories.

properties.name: Niele
properties.description: Niele may refer to one of the following:

properties.name: Nieuth
properties.description: Nieuth Four was a terrestrial astronomical object located in the Nieuth system, a part of the Wyloff sector in the Northern Dependencies portion of the Colonies. At some point by the time the Battle of Yavin was fought, the Rebel Alliance operative and Imperial defector Colonel Vin Northal contacted Colonel Ilo Jev, the commanding officer of the Wyloff sector Imperial Intelligence ExComm facility, who was on leave at the time.

properties.name: Niian
properties.description: Niian was a tropical planet of the Niian system, located within the Thaere sector, in the Expansion Region of the galaxy. In 0 BBY, the smuggler Dannen Lifehold was on the planet doing an errand for his mentor, another smuggler named Twolz. While Lifehold was on the errand, Twolz and his crew were killed by stormtroopers, the elite soldiers of the Galactic Empire.

properties.name: Nilash
properties.poi: Daimanite munitions factory, Nilash Imperial Impound Facility,
properties.description: Nilash III, also called simply Nilash, was the third planet in the Nilash system, located close to the baradium-rich planet Chelloa. It was home to a tree-dwelling, telepathic native species and a known source of anthracite. During the New Sith Wars the jungle-covered planet housed a Daimanite munitions plant while, under the rule of the Galactic Empire, the Nilash Imperial Impound Facility was established in an orbit around the world. It was on this world that the later-famous smuggling freighter the Millennium Falcon, at the time known as the Second Chance, first came into Rebel possession. During the following years, the control over Nilash was repeatedly transferred between the Empire and Rebellion's respective incarnations.

properties.name: Nilg
properties.description: The Nilg system was a star system located in the Alderath sector of the Mid Rim.

properties.name: Nim Drovis
properties.poi: Sector Medical FacilityThousand Stinking DitchesChug 'n' ChuckWookiee's Codpiece
properties.description: The world of Nim Drovis was located in the Drovian system in the Meridian sector, and was a rainy planet which boasted a Sector Medical Facility and Medical Research Facility attended to by the Ho'Din physician Doctor Ism Oolos, along with a small New Republic base. The largest free port on Nim Drovis was Bagsho, which was originally settled by colonists from Alderaan turned into a link between the sector's neutral worlds and the New Republic.

properties.name: Nimban
properties.poi: Delban Faxicorp headquarters, Hoersch-Kessel Drive headquarters,
properties.description: Nimban was the homeworld of the Nimbanese species. It was located in Hutt Space, along the Pabol Sleheyron.

properties.name: Nimia
properties.description: Nimia was a planet located in the Hutt Space between Klatooine and Yoribuunt. It was located near the Si'Klaata Cluster. A lackluster industrial world, Nimia was occasionally used as a meeting place between Hutt servants and outlanders who had failed to attract much favor with the Hutts.

properties.name: Ninn
properties.description: Ninn was a small planet located in the Ninn system of the Outer Rim Territories. The world was despoiled and depopulated in an ancient conflict, but was later resettled by a group that became known as the Priests of Ninn. Ninn came to be part of the Corporate Sector following that region's expansion, and so fell under the control of the Corporate Sector Authority.

properties.name: Niran
properties.description: Niran was a world located within the Niran system, a part of the Outer Rim Territories' Tunka sector. It was the homeworld of the Human male Viran Qol.

properties.name: Nirauan
properties.poi: Hand of Thrawn, Lake of Small Fish, Nirauan cliffs,
properties.description: Nirauan was a planet located in second of three inner planets in the Nirauan system. It was inhabited by the indigenous avian Qom Jha and Qom Qae species, and due to it role of being the headquarters of the Empire of the Hand, it housed a large garrison of Chiss and human personnel.

properties.name: Niro
properties.description: Niro was a planet that was owned by the InterGalactic Banking Clan before the end of the Clone Wars.

properties.name: Nishr
properties.description: Nishr was a planet in the Outer Rim, home to a near-Human species known as the Nish. It was the scene of a conflict between the Empire and the Alliance during the Rebellion.

properties.name: Nista
properties.description: Nista was a planet in the Tapani sector's Nista system. It was located in the Cadriaan Province and was the base of the Rebel Alliance cell, the Pelagia Freedom Force.

properties.name: Nivek
properties.description: Nivek, also know as Night Planet, was a planet in the Expansion Region, known as a "night planet" due to the perpetual darkness which shrouded its surface.

properties.name: Nixor
properties.description: Nixor was a planet located in the Mid Rim, coreward of Hutt Space. It was the homeworld of the Nixor species.

properties.name: Nkllon
properties.description: Nkllon was a small, mineral rich, harsh world in the Athega system. Its surface was covered in plains of searing rock, impact craters, and volcanic features.

properties.name: Nocto
properties.description: Nocto was located in the Airam sector of the Outer Rim Territories. Prior to the Clone Wars, pirates from Nocto attacked Ochotl's orbital depots.

properties.name: Noctralis
properties.description: Noctralis was a planet where Trachta was grievously injured during the Clone Wars. He and a group of clone troopers were hunting a Jedi Padawan who defected to the Confederacy of Independent Systems when the Padawan threw a thermal detonator, killing the troopers and injuring Trachta. The planet was dark and had spindly-looking dead trees.

properties.name: Noe'ha'on
properties.description: Noe'ha'on was a jungle planet located in the Expansion Region's Piryn Shar sector. Its fauna included poisonous insects and k'lor'slugs—ferocious, worm-like swamp predators. Noe'ha'on also had large fossil beds rich with the preserved remains of organisms.

properties.name: Nolar
properties.description: Nolar was a wealthy planet in the Inner Rim, a commercial center plagued by thieves. Mining equipment was manufactured on the planet.

properties.name: Nooli
properties.description: Nooli was a world located in the Nooli system in the Noolian sector in the Mid Rim.

properties.name: Noonar
properties.description: Noonar was a planet located in the Noonian system of the Outer Rim Territories. During the Cold War between the Galactic Republic and the Sith Empire, Noonar was host to the pacifist Noonar Confederacy, which controlled a key stretch of territory between the two galactic powers. During the Galactic Civil War, Noonar was run by Imperial governor Trophan Thanis.

properties.name: Noori
properties.description: Noori was a terrestrial planet in the Noori sector's Noori system within the galaxy's southeast quadrant, located in an area of the Expansion Region overlapping with a part of space known as the Slice. The Galactic Republic began scouting the region during the Great Manifest Period, resulting in widespread colonization in the following millennia. Noori was the homeworld of the Noorians, a sentient humanoid species with striped eyes. Tahl, a Noorian Jedi Master who lived during the last decades of the Republic, hailed from the planet.

properties.name: Nopsin
