properties.description: Nopsin was a planet in the Mid Rim.

properties.name: Noquivzor
properties.description: Noquivzor was a planet located in the Colonies.

properties.name: Norah
properties.description: Norah was a planet where Soara Antana and Darra Thel-Tanis went on a mission.

properties.name: Norat
properties.description: The Norat were a group ruled by the Norat Sovereignty. Crandor Ijjix was a Norat. The Norat were destroyed by the Yevetha.

properties.name: Norclune
properties.description: Norclune was a planet in the Colonies and the holy world of the Norclu Order.

properties.name: Nord
properties.description: The Nord were a dwarf-like, three-foot-tall humanoid species native to Nordra. They were a hardy race that had learned to live under constant threat of danger from the harsh environment of their homeworld.

properties.name: Nordra
properties.description: Nordra was a cold, tectonically-active planet in the Inner Rim Territories. Though located along the famous Hydian Way trade route, it was often bypassed by travelers following the Itani Run that detoured around the nearby Itani Nebula.

properties.name: Noremac
properties.description: Noremac was a planet within the Kanz sector. Following the end of the Kanz Disorders in 3670 BBY, the Jedi Watchman Mari-Elan Nora was killed by slavers on that world.

properties.name: Noris
properties.description: Noris was a planet that was located within the Noris system, in the Chiss Space sector of the galaxy's Unknown Regions. It was connected to the planets Schesa and Sharb via the hyperlane known as the Path of the Houses, and to the planet Ornfra by another hyperspace route.

properties.name: Norkronia
properties.description: The Norkronia system was a star system located within the galaxy's regions known as the Core Worlds and the Negs. It was connected to the Alland and Metellos systems by the Metellos Trade Route hyperlane, and was home to the creatures known as Norkronian whistle-snakes.

properties.name: Norne
properties.description: Norne was a planet taken over by the Empire. The orphans on the world were exploited as slaves and indentured laborers. An orphan named Mygo Skinto created a series of underground warrens to hide and protect the world's orphans, and became a Rebel informant.

properties.name: Norulac
properties.description: Norulac was a planet in the Inner Rim with numerous mountain ranges strewn all over its surface. Its lack of a strong government enabled various groups avoiding authorities elsewhere to take refuge on the planet.

properties.name: Norval
properties.description: Norval was the primary star of the Norval system. Norval II orbited it.

properties.name: Noryath
properties.description: Noryath was a planet in the Nuiri sector of the Outer Rim.

properties.name: Nosken
properties.description: Nosken was a gas giant planet. The TriGas Corporation attempted to set up a dirigible mining operation on this world, which ultimately failed.

properties.name: Notak
properties.description: Notak was an Imperial stronghold throughout the Galactic Civil War. The planet fell eight months after the Battle of Endor.

properties.name: Nothoiin
properties.description: Nothoiin was the Nothoiin homeworld, on the Nothoiin Corridor and Nothoiin Route. It was a planet with limited development beyond the ur-diamond mining operations conducted on its crystal moon. In the years leading up to and following the Clone Wars, Nothoiin's affairs were dominated by a crushing fifty-year-long drought leading to rampant, uncontrollable wildfires.

properties.name: Nouane
properties.description: Nouane was a planet located in the Nouane system of the Inner Rim. It served as the capital world of the eponymous Allied Region Nouane, a semi-independent government of 212 star systems that was one of countless mini-empires during the early days of the Galactic Republic. Though isolated, Nouane had a strong presence in the early Republic—Nouanese ministers could be found on worlds throughout the galactic government, and Nouane's libraries attracted many philosophers and artists from the Core Worlds.

properties.name: Novar
properties.description: Novar was a planet in the Expansion Region. On the 1,000th year since the world was settled, a large tract of land was turned over to House Korden.

properties.name: Novi
properties.description: The Novi system was located in the Interior Region, an area of the Hapes Cluster in the Slice portion of the Inner Rim. It was connected via hyperlanes to the Farnica and Gallinore systems. The Novi system was the origin point of the gemstones known as Novian rubies.

properties.name: Novoil Cluster
properties.description: The Novoil Cluster was a star cluster located in the Colonies.

properties.name: Novolek Beacon
properties.description: The Novolek Beacon was a pulsar star located in the Periphery between Nwarcol Point, Sriluur and Sedri. It was a trans-dimensional energy streamer, sending out pulses of radiation, heat and matter. Gravitational, multidimensional, curves passed through the star, creating a massive hyperspace shadow. The star did not have the mass to cause a collapse into a singularity. A strange phenomenon called the Ei'shuun Aa Effect caused fragments of stellar plasma to break off from the Beacon, dragging disproportionate hyperspace shadows, at unpredictable intervals. Further, subspace itself was distorted. To the protected natural eye, however, the star was merely a typical particle fountain. Every 28 days, 12 hours and 42 minutes the star flared, though the flare itself might have lasted a few minutes up to as much as two days.

properties.name: Novor
properties.description: Novor was an astronomical object that was the site of a children's medcenter ran by the Sisters of the Ninth Plane. During the High Republic Era, the Hutts sent the enforcer Ola Hest to Novor to collect protection money from the medcenter. When the Sisters refused to pay, Hest responded by aiming her frigate's thrusters at the building, killing everyone inside.

properties.name: Nuala
properties.description: The Nuala system was located in the Trans-Gascon sector, a part of the Trans-Hydian portion of the Mid Rim. It was the origin point of the pirate group known as the Nuala Marauders.

properties.name: Nubia
properties.poi: Imperial research facility, Nubian Collective Museum of Engineering and Design, Nubian PalaceTallera Downs
properties.description: Nubia was a small, temperate world located in the Nubus system on the outer edge of the Core Worlds. It was the headquarters of Nubian Star Drives, Inc., developers of parts for starships, including the hyperdrive for the Naboo cruisers. It also was headquarters for Industrial Automaton, TradeCo, Inc., and the massive PharmCorp. Although not heavily urbanized and with a relatively rural landscape and economic backbone , Nubia was always considered a deserving member of the title of 'Core World' and all its associated connotations. It was viewed as a planet whose population appreciated great beauty  and a close relationship with the natural environment of their world, as well as enjoying the cosmopolitan lifestyle and pursuits of their counterparts on planets such as Coruscant or Kuat. Its capital was Nuba City.

properties.name: Null
properties.description: Null was an arboreal world and the only inhabited planet in the Null system.

properties.name: Numatra
properties.description: Numatra was a creature whose valuable hide was used to make clothing and footwear.

properties.name: Nummunr
properties.description: Nummunr was a world located in the Ash Worlds, in the Outer Rim Territories.

properties.name: Nuralee
properties.description: Nuralee was a Mid Rim world in the Tyus sector. It had an economic breakdown shortly before the Clone Wars. It was represented in the Galactic Senate by Bog Divinian, a wealthy landowner with ties to the Commerce Guild.

properties.name: Nuswatta
properties.poi: Forbidden Gardens of NuswattaHigh Fane of Xo
properties.description: Nuswatta was a planet in the Tion Cluster of the Outer Rim Territories.

properties.name: Nuvar
properties.description: Nuvar was a planet in the Mid Rim near the modern Hydian Way. In 3701 BBY, Freia Kallea's scoutship Hope crash-landed on uncharted Nuvar after it was crippled by the Neimoidians Thoax and Farge Osaax, leaving her stranded for six standard years. Banu Hydia located her on the planet and found her in a wild state.

properties.name: Nyara
properties.description: Nyara was a planet containing a class-3 toxic weapons dump. In 13 ABY a team of thieves hired by Nom Anor raided the dump to retrieve a chunk of zinethium.

properties.name: Nyarikan Nebula
properties.description: The Nyarikan Nebula was a nebula near Garos IV and Sundari. It was found in the Mid Rim.

properties.name: Nyasko
properties.description: Nyasko was a terrestrial planet located in the Nyasko system. It constituted a part of the Colunda sector, a subsector of the Phelleem sector in the Slice portion of the Outer Rim Territories. During the Galactic Civil War between the Galactic Empire and the Rebel Alliance, a battalion of Imperial All Terrain Armored Transport walkers was stationed on Nyasko.

properties.name: Nyemari
properties.description: Nyemari was a planet. By 1 ABY, the planet's capital city Anem had the most modern, sophisticated spaceport in the Meridian sector. The planet was also host to Galactic Empire military installation. The indigenous species was the Nyemarians. It was visited by a team of Rebel Alliance operatives to steal the Duchess' access codes to the installation. After the mission, the Rebel's encounter with a mysterious messenger led them to Rezi Soresh in the Sixela system.

properties.name: Nyny
properties.description: Nyny was a planet represented in the New Republic Senate. It was home to a three-headed sentient species.

properties.name: Nyriaan
properties.poi: Corporate City SectorFinal RestDeluge ControlDeluge DeviceHyperspace Navigator's Guild SectorMining Guild SectorNeutral ZoneProsperity MineRepublic SectorSteamfieldsTemperance Arena
properties.description: Nyriaan was a planet that was located in the Luire system of the Mid Rim.

properties.name: Nyssa
properties.description: Nyssa was a planet in the Tapani sector's Nyssa system, in the Mecetti Province. The Sith cult of assassins known as the Mecrosa Order arose on the planet thousands of years before the Battle of Yavin, backed by House Mecetti.

properties.name: O'reen
properties.description: O'reen was an Unknown Regions planet with a surface featuring thick fog and tall mesas and plateaus. It was inhabited by the near-Human O'reenians. The planet was colonized after the Great Hyperspace War as a Galactic Republic advance warning outpost, based on a self-sufficient military garrison. Eventually, the colonists were stranded and isolated from the rest of the galaxy. Following a coup led by Magnus, the colony's military leader, O'reenian society transformed itself into a caste-based military dictatorship devoted to the planet's military buildup under the rule of a leader holding the title of Magnus. Only those who served with O'reen's military were granted full citizenship and rights.

properties.name: Oaka Prime
properties.description: Oaka Prime was a wildlife preserve planet in the Inner Rim. It was once part of the Infinite Empire ruled by the Rakata. It was briefly visited by Han Solo, Luke Skywalker, Chewbacca, and Leia Organa in about 0 ABY when they rescued Seren Song, Organa's friend and a Rebel spy.

properties.name: Obana
properties.description: The Obana system was a star system located within the Outer Rim Territories which contained an asteroid belt.

properties.name: Obas
properties.description: Obas was a superheated volcanic planet located in the Expansion Region's Andirma sector. During the Galactic Civil War, the Alliance to Restore the Republic operated a base on the planet, the environmental control systems of which at one point malfunctioned. As a result, the base faced imminent melt-down due to the extremely high temperatures of Obas. The personnel of the base tasked a group of Rebel agents that had arrived in the Obas system to retrieve critical replacement parts from an Imperial supply depot in the nearby Rainos Cluster.

properties.name: Obelia
properties.description: The Obelia system was a star system located in the Tapani sector's Pelagia Province, near Pelagon.

properties.name: Oben
properties.description: Oben was a resource-rich planet colony of the Kaleesh.

properties.name: Obica
properties.description: Obica was a planet that was located in the Grumani sector.

properties.name: Obinipor
properties.description: Obinipor was an unaligned planet in the Outer Rim, near Warlord Zsinj's territory. Its volcanoes spewed out metals used to fabricate power generators.

properties.name: Obran Cluster
properties.description: The Obran Cluster was an asteroid cluster where the Rebel Alliance had hidden cargo storage containers full of warheads. However, the Imperials learned of the cargo containers and placed a mine field at the location, intending to lure the rebels into an ambush to inflict losses and acquire warheads at the same time. Despite the minefield and Imperial Assault Gunboats lying in wait for an ambush, which the rebels were fully aware of, the rebels sent A-wings to remove the mine-field and attempted to hold off the imperial forces long enough for their Heavy Lifters of flight group Beetle to pick up the containers.

properties.name: Obredaan
properties.description: Obredaan was a planet in the Irishi sector of the Mid Rim and was known to have large deposits of cortosis ore, which made the mining industry the planet's main income source. Since Obredaan was located on the Entralla Route, it was known as one of the most active trading posts in the Irishi sector alongside Orinda and Ord Tessebok

properties.name: Obroa-skai
properties.poi: Obroan Institute for ArchaeologyMuseum of Applied PhotonicsCelebratus Archive, Aurora Medical FacilityJedi Academy
properties.description: Obroa-skai was a planet in the Obroa-skai system within a strategic position in the Borderland Regions of the Inner Rim.

properties.name: Obulette
properties.description: Obulette was a planet in the Tapani sector's Obulette system. It was the capital of Mecetti Province and throneworld of House Mecetti. It was in perpetual twilight due to its dim red star. Its orbital shipyards were smaller than those of Tallaan but nonetheless successful. Most of the planet was covered in cities, ash-colored rock, and shallow seas. The planet was the headquarters of Shimper Ale, a small Rebel cell consisting of amateur warriors from House Mecetti.

properties.name: Ochotl
properties.description: Ochotl was an Outer Rim Territories agriworld located in the Airam sector. The company Ochotl Ag harvested the chak-root plant on the planet, which was also the homeworld of the galaxy-renowned shockball player Kob Mondray.

properties.name: Ocsin
properties.description: The Ocsin, also known as the Ocsinin, were a Near-Human species from planet Farana, near the Corporate Sector. Due to this proximity, the Ocsin history was always related with this sector.

properties.name: Odacer-Faustin
properties.description: Odacer-Faustin was a planet with a cold harsh terrain. Heavy snow and high winds constantly buffeted the world.

properties.name: Odik
properties.description: Odik was an astronomical object located in the galaxy's Deep Core.

properties.name: Odos
properties.description: Odos was a gas cloud that was located in the Meridian sector, near Exodo II.

properties.name: Odryn
properties.description: An isolated planet in the Outer Rim Noonian sector, Odryn was the chief colony world of the warlike Feeorin species. Known as a world of climatic extremes, Odryn was covered in jungles and mountains, into the sides of which the Feeorin built their settlements. Although commonly believed to be the Feeorin homeworld, the Feeorin's original home was lost—by the time of the Mandalorian Wars, more Feeorin lived on Odryn than anywhere else in the galaxy, and developed an extremely traditionalistic and insular society. Feeorin life on Odryn was largely tribal until the legendary warrior Feln unified the warring villages under his banner, becoming the hallowed Exalted in the process. Feln later left Odryn to train with the Jedi Order, and eventually returned to his homeworld as a Jedi Master and a member of the shadowy Jedi cabal known as the Jedi Covenant. Feln ended up earning the ire of his people by volunteering Odryn's sacred Sanctum of the Exalted for Covenant use as a storehouse for Sith artifacts, and was eventually slaughtered by his people after he destroyed the Sanctum in an effort to ensure knowledge of the Covenant's work would not leave the planet.

properties.name: Oetrago
properties.description: Öetrago was a planet covered with plant life, located in the Mayagil sector of the Outer Rim. It was known for its flowers.

properties.name: Off-Canau
properties.description: Off-Canau was a planet. It was one of the favorite tourist destinations of the galaxy.

properties.name: Ogden Minor
properties.description: Ogden Minor was the homeworld of the savage terbeasts. It mainly consisted of a jungle-type terrain, though was not as swampy as Dagobah.

properties.name: Ogem
properties.description: Ogem was the homeworld of the near-Human Ogemite species. It was in the D'Aelgoth sector of the Mid Rim, along the D'Aelgoth Trade Route. It was a busy trade world that generally avoided involvement in galactic politics.

properties.name: Ogoth Tiir
properties.description: Ogoth Tiir was a planet in the Atravis sector of the Outer Rim.

properties.name: Ohratuu
properties.description: Ohratuu was a terrestrial planet located within the Ohratuu system of the Expansion Region's Piryn Shar sector. It was home to a species of docile land-based herd creatures known as deripors.

properties.name: OHS1782-03
properties.description: The OHS1782-03 system was a star system that was located within the Outer Rim Territories' Ash Worlds sector and was a part of the region known as the Slice. Between the years 25,120 BBY and 25,096 BBY, the system was known as the Xoraes system and was situated within the Kiirium Reaches region, a part of the empire of the Human warlord Xim. During that time, the Xoraes system was connected by hyperlanes to the Turallun, Gwynhes Minor, and Ulonsus systems, and Xim moved his forces to the system from Ulonsus.

properties.name: OHS2132-04
properties.description: The OHS2132-04 system was located in the Ash Worlds sector, a part of the Slice portion of the Outer Rim Territories. Between 25,120 BBY and 25,096 BBY, it was known as the Ulonsus system and was situated in the Kiirium Reaches region, a part of the empire of the Tionese conqueror Xim. During that time, the Ulonsus system was connected by hyperlanes to the Balshebr, Pakuuni, and Xoraes systems, and Xim moved his forces from Pakuuni to Ulonsus and then to Xoraes.

properties.name: OHS3842-03
properties.description: OHS3842-03 was a planet located within the Outer Rim Territories. Originally known as Astigone, it was absorbed into Xim's Empire as he expanded his borders from the Kingdom of Cron.

properties.name: OHS4140-02
properties.description: The OHS4140-02 system was located in the Ash Worlds sector, a part of the Slice portion of the Outer Rim Territories. Between 25,120 BBY and 25,096 BBY, it was known as the Balshebr system and was situated in the Kiirium Reaches region, a part of the empire of the Tionese conqueror Xim. During that time, the Balshebr system was connected by hyperlanes to the Astigone, Dellalt, and Ulonsus systems, and Xim moved his forces from the Dellalt system to the Balshebr.

properties.name: Ojom
properties.description: Ojom was a frozen ocean planet located within the Deep Core and the homeworld of the Besalisk. Largely inhospitable, several space stations hung in orbit so as to accommodate other species less acclimated to the cold.

properties.name: Okator
properties.description: Okator may refer to one of the following:

properties.name: Oko E
properties.description: Oko E was a resort world in the Oko system. It was known for its "wild-water" rafting on rivers of molten sulfur. The cyborg Lobot partook in this activity, likening it to maneuvers he performed on the elusive Teljkon Vagabond ship with Lando Calrissian in 16 ABY.

properties.name: Olabria
properties.description: The Olabria system was an Outer Rim Territories star system located within the Seitia sector. It was home to the Olabrian trichoid parasite.

properties.name: Olanji
properties.description: Olanji was a high-tech planet located in the Hapes Cluster.

properties.name: Old Barag
properties.description: Old Barag was a planet located in the Old Barag system of the Epsi Collective, within the galaxy's Expansion Region. In the year 11,591 BBY, the Baragwin homeworld was attacked by the Pius Dea Republic during the Fifteenth Pius Dea Crusade. By the publication of The University of Sanbra Guide to Intelligent Life's first draft in 0 BBY, Old Barag had long since been forgotten, even by the Baragwin themselves.

properties.name: Old Mankoo
properties.description: Old Mankoo was a planet located in the Old Mankoo system, a part of the Quess sector in the Trailing Sectors portion of the Mid Rim. The planet was impoverished, and by 23 BBY, the royal family of Old Mankoo had been overthrown.

properties.name: Oligtaz
properties.description: Oligtaz was a planet in the Oligtaz system within the Core Worlds region of the galaxy. It was a jungle world and where the Esraza Temple, a mysterious and exotic structure, was located.

properties.name: Omar
properties.description: Omar was a planet located in the system of the same name.

properties.name: Omman
properties.description: Omman was a planet located in the Tion Hegemony of the Outer Rim.

properties.name: Omman Minor
properties.description: Omman Minor, best known as Omman, was a planet located in the Kibilini sector of the Outer Rim.

properties.name: Omonoth
properties.description: Omonoth was an Inner Rim white dwarf type star in the Omonoth system, ringed with asteroids mined by Adascorp during the Mandalorian Wars. The ring became infested with exogorths, which devoured the droid mining stations. The star was in a region contested by the Mandalorians and Republic.

properties.name: Ompersan
properties.description: Ompersan was an Outer Rim planet located within Imperial Remnant space. It was the site of the Imperial Navy fleet records center.

properties.name: Omwat
properties.description: Omwat was a planet in the Garis sector of the Outer Rim Territories. It was a world of grasslands and mountains and the homeworld of the native Omwati.

properties.name: Onadax
properties.description: Onadax was a planet in the Minos Cluster. It was the location of an ODT compound that was infiltrated by Jaina Solo. The small world was thick with dust, which drifted knee-deep into corners, fouled machines and droids, and irritated the eyes.

properties.name: Ondara
properties.description: Lieutenant Commander Ondara was a Black Sun starfighter ace during the Galactic Civil War. Circa 1 ABY, he commanded, along with Lieutenant Commander Chaen, the Dual Moons, two of the Black Sun starfighter bases in the Bright Jewel system. Ondara was killed in the Battle of Tansarii Point Station by Dartas Pytin's Car'das forces.

properties.name: Onderon
properties.poi: Hunting lodge of the Beast Riders, Iziz Royal PalaceKira FortressMalgan MarketOmmin's subterranean fortressOnderon highlandsShatoon MonasteryUnifar TempleRoyal Hunting Lodge
properties.description: One of eight planets in the Japrael system, Onderon had a temperate climate, and was once home to a primitive race of Humanoids.

properties.name: Ondos
properties.description: Ondos was a planet lost long ago. It was located in the Core Worlds. Along with Had Abbadon, it was one of a handful of candidates believed to be the planet of origin for either the Jedi Order or their Force-using predecessors.

properties.name: Ongella
properties.description: Ongella was an Inner Rim planet of the Galactic Empire.

properties.name: Ookbat
properties.description: Ookbat was the site of a botched mission by bounty hunters Tinian I'att and Chenlambec the Wookiee. A warren-like network of dank caves existed under the planet's surface.

properties.name: Ool
properties.description: Ool was a forested planet located in the Ool system of the Unknown Regions' Chiss Space. A hyperlane linked the world to the Avidich and Shihon systems. The sentient Chiss of the Chiss Ascendancy established large circular plots of farmland across the surface of Ool.

properties.name: Oolex Pulsar
properties.description: The Oolex Pulsar was a pulsar in the Sumitra sector of the Expansion Region.

properties.name: Oolidi
properties.description: Oolidi was a planet that was located in the Expansion Region. Oolidi was also the Oolid homeworld.

properties.name: Oon Tien
properties.description: Oon Tien was a planet in the Kathol sector of the Outer Rim Territories, and the homeworld of the Jarell species. Discovered by Galactic Republic colonists roughly 300 years before the Galactic Civil War, the planet was settled by Humans. The native Jarell monarchies traded with the new Human settlers, acquiring weapons and high technology that fueled a change in Jarell society. In the decades preceding the Galactic Civil War, Oon Tien was integrated into the Kathol sector, and became a major manufacturing and agricultural hub.

properties.name: Ooo-sek
properties.description: Ooo-sek was one of the first Rodian colony worlds. Its swamps were home to a carnivorous species of plant known as yo'uqiol, Rodese for "Hand of Death." Ooo-sek also boasted vast jungles rife with flora and fauna, making it an ideal hunting ground for adventurous Rodians to train as bounty hunters.

properties.name: Ooo-temiuk
properties.description: Ooo-temiuk was a forested world located in the Ooo-temiuk system, a part of the Arkanis sector in the Slice portion of the Outer Rim Territories. It was situated on the Triellus Trade Route hyperlane, which linked it to the C-Foroon and Tatoo systems.

properties.name: Oorn Tchis
properties.description: Oorn Tchis was an Outer Rim planet near Agamar. It was a small, Human-inhabited rural world best known for exporting colorful fabrics and a rare ore used in guidance system design. It joined the Confederacy of Independent Systems in 22 BBY, and eventually became part of the Galactic Empire.

properties.name: Ootoola
properties.description: Ootoola was the vastly oceanic homeworld of the Ootoolan race. The world was located in the Morshdine sector of the Outer Rim Territories.

properties.name: Oovo
properties.description: Oovo was a gas giant located in the Oovo system of the Outer Rim's Tharin sector. It was orbited by an asteroid belt which contained the asteroid Oovo IV, which housed the maximum security prison named Desolation Alley.

properties.name: Opari
properties.description: Opari was a planet in the Opari system of the Mid Rim. It provided the Balawai government on Haruun Kal with gunships.

properties.name: Opatajji
properties.description: Opatajji was a planet in the Alsaka sector of the Core Worlds. Neera Opatajji-Hirken was the daughter of the Duke of Opatajji.

properties.name: Open Sea
properties.description: The Open Sea was a region of space largely devoid of stars in the Centrality, a government rimward of Hutt Space, though it also stretched southward into Wild Space. It contained the ThonBoka—a sack-shaped nebula, whose name could be translated as "StarCave"—and the lost Human colony world Renatasia III, one of fourteen colonization projects sponsored by Queen Tasia of Grizmallt in 3950 BBY. The Oswaft species nested in the ThonBoka, with the entire Open Sea being their domain.

properties.name: Ophideraan
properties.poi: Great Well, Slave level, Cavern of the Serpents,
properties.description: Ophideraan was an arid desert planet in the Colonies that, by the era of the Galactic Civil War, was ruled by a group of bandits known as the Serpent Masters. Ophideraan's skies were dominated by a unique species of flying serpent that communicated through ultrasonic tones not audible to the Human ear—it was through discovery of these tones that the Serpent Masters learned to control and mount these fearsome beasts. The Serpent Masters maintained a society through salvaging wrecks and enslaving those unfortunates that crashed onto Ophideraan, using them to maintain the few sources of water on the planet. The Serpent Masters' rule was overthrown in 0 ABY, through the efforts of Rebel agent Luke Skywalker.

properties.name: Opiteihr
properties.description: Opiteihr was one of the four red giants in the Opiteihr system.

properties.name: Oplovis
properties.description: Oplovis was a world located in the Oplovis system, a part of the Oplovis sector in the New Territories portion of the Outer Rim Territories. It was the point of origin of the fine material known as Oplovis linens, and the Oplovian love poems composed by Sumi Zanthe were a part of classic literature.

properties.name: Oranessan
properties.description: Oranessan was a planet that was located in the Grumani sector.

properties.name: Orax
properties.description: Orax was a planet in the Outer Rim Territories, and was the homeworld of the crystalline Shard.

properties.name: Ord Adinorr
properties.description: Ord Adinorr was a snow-covered planet in the Meridian sector.

properties.name: Ord Antalaha
properties.description: Ord Antalaha was a planet located along the Shwuy Exchange, in the Colonies region of the galaxy, that was colonized and established as an Ordnance/Regional Depot by the Galactic Republic during the Clone Wars. As a military outpost, Ord Antalaha was primarily used for storage and recreational purposes, prompting the construction of thousands of warehouses across the planet. After the Clone Wars, all military forces abandoned the planet, leaving the civilian colonists as the planet's only inhabitants. The colonist population, however, quickly declined over the years and Ord Antalaha soon became a regular stopover and haven for pirates, smugglers, and other space-faring criminals.

properties.name: Ord Biniir
properties.description: Ord Biniir was a planet located in the Outer Rim Territories.

properties.name: Ord Bueri
properties.description: Ord Bueri was a planet in the Ord Bueri system of the Outer Rim's Nilgaard sector. The Rebel Alliance's base on Yavin 4 used H-60 Tempest bombers from here.

properties.name: Ord Canfre
properties.description: Ord Canfre was a planet in the Outer Rim Territories. It was once an Ordnance/Regional Depot.

properties.name: Ord Cantrell
properties.description: Ord Cantrell was an Outer Rim planet. It was originally an Ordnance/Regional Depot under the Galactic Republic. It was one of the galaxy's most exclusive resorts. During the early days of Duros exploration, it was settled by a colony of Duros that lost contact with the galaxy and reverted to simple technology before dying out.

properties.name: Ord Celbus
properties.description: Ord Celbus was a world located in the Ord Celbus system, a part of the Karthakk sector in the Trailing Sectors portion of the Outer Rim Territories. Ord Celbus served as an Ordnance/Regional Depot outpost for the Galactic Republic during the Pius Dea Era, a period of time that lasted between approximately 12,000 BBY and 11,000 BBY. During that time, Ord Celbus was situated just outside the borders of Republic space.

properties.name: Ord Cestus
properties.poi: Dashta MountainsGrand ChikatLikKibo SandsCleft HeadKibo LakeKibo PlateauTolmea MountainsYal-NoyKibo Geothermal StationTolmeatekZantay HillsCestus PenitentiaryNight ShadeBadlandsOre BoulevardZantay Caves
properties.description: Ord Cestus, also known simply as Cestus, was a planet that was home to the X'Ting species.

properties.name: Ord Dalet
properties.description: Ord Dalet was one of several Ordnance/Regional Depot planets identified by Common Sith letters. During the Cold War between the Galactic Republic and the Sith Empire, a member of the mysterious shapeshifting Shi'ido species was hospitalized on Ord Dalet.

properties.name: Ord Dorlass
properties.description: Ord Dorlass was a planet in the Ord Dorlass system, a star system in the Iskin sector of the Mid Rim.

properties.name: Ord Dycoll
properties.description: Ord Dycoll was a planet located within the Ord Dycoll system of the Mid Rim that was destroyed by an ancient drill ship at some point during the Imperial Period.

properties.name: Ord Fanthal
properties.description: Ord Fanthal was a world located in the Ord Fanthal system, a part of the Ojoster sector in the Trans-Hydian portion of the Outer Rim Territories. Ord Fanthal served as an Ordnance/Regional Depot outpost for the Galactic Republic during the Pius Dea Era, a period of time that lasted between approximately 12,000 BBY and 11,000 BBY, despite it being located outside the borders of Republic space.

properties.name: Ord Grovner
properties.description: Ord Grovner was a planet in the Outer Rim Territories near Courkrus. Originally an Ordnance/Regional Depot, the planet served as a staging area for the Imperial task force, led by Admiral Freeda, which wiped out the Eyttyrmin Batiiv pirates.

properties.name: Ord Gustald
properties.description: Ord Gustald was a world located in the Ord Gustald system. It was situated in the Mytaranor sector, a part of the Kashyyyk Region in the Slice portion of the Mid Rim. Ord Gustald served as an Ordnance/Regional Depot outpost for the Galactic Republic during the Pius Dea Era, a period of time that lasted between approximately 12,000 BBY and 11,000 BBY.

properties.name: Ord Hout
properties.description: Ord Hout was an Ordnance/Regional Depot in the Outer Rim Territories. It was colonized by the Galactic Republic sometime before the Pius Dea Era.

properties.name: Ord Ibanna
properties.description: Ord Ibanna was a gas giant in the Outer Rim Territories. The planet once housed a Tibanna mining colony, which was abandoned sometime prior to the Invasion of Naboo as well as being the site of an intense naval engagement between the Galactic Republic and Sith Empire during the Great Galactic War.

properties.name: Ord Ivarn
properties.description: Ord Ivarn was a world located in the Ord Ivarn system, a part of the Hakartha sector in the Western Reaches portion of the Expansion Region. Ord Ivarn served as an Ordnance/Regional Depot outpost for the Galactic Republic during the Pius Dea Era, a period of time that lasted between approximately 12,000 BBY and 11,000 BBY, despite it being located outside the borders of Republic space.

properties.name: Ord Janon
properties.description: Ord Janon was an Outer Rim Territories planet located within the Spinward sector. During the Pius Dea Era, it served as an Ordnance/Regional Depot for the Galactic Republic. Millennia later, when the Republic was at war with the Confederacy of Independent Systems, Ord Janon was occupied by Confederate forces.

properties.name: Ord Klina
properties.description: Ord Klina was a world located in the Ord Klina system, a part of the Klina sector in the Slice portion of the Outer Rim Territories. Ord Klina served as an Ordnance/Regional Depot outpost for the Galactic Republic during the Pius Dea Era, a period of time that lasted between approximately 12,000 BBY and 11,000 BBY, despite it being located outside the borders of Republic space. When the Republic launched the Thirty-Fourth Pius Dea Crusade against the Hutt species in 11,057 BBY, Republic forces moved from Ord Klina toward Hutt Space.

properties.name: Ord Lithone
properties.description: Ord Lithone was a planet in the Ord Lithone system, part of the Inner Rim. In the years preceding the Clone Wars, it was the site of a Baktoid Armor Workshop droid manufacturing facility. Baktoid left the planet in 22 BBY, intending to move its factories to the Outer Rim Territories.

properties.name: Ord Lonesome
properties.description: Ord Lonesome was a world located in the Ord Lonesome system, a part of the Albanin sector in the Slice portion of the Outer Rim Territories. Ord Lonesome served as an Ordnance/Regional Depot outpost for the Galactic Republic during the Pius Dea Era, a period of time that lasted between approximately 12,000 BBY and 11,000 BBY, despite it being located outside the borders of Republic space. When the Republic launched the Thirty-Fourth Pius Dea Crusade against the Hutt species in 11,057 BBY, Republic forces moved from Ord Lonesome to the Riileb system, in the vicinity of Hutt Space.

properties.name: Ord Mantell
properties.poi: Avilatan, Casino District, First Galactic Bank of Ord Mantell, Jubilee Wheel, Nobody's Inn, Scraplands,
properties.description: Ord Mantell was a terrestrial planet which was located into the Bright Jewel system of the Bright Jewel sector in the Mid Rim Territories. It was located near Anobis and was originally settled by the Galactic Republic circa 12,000 BBY as an Ordnance/Regional Depot.

properties.name: Ord Marsax
properties.description: Ord Marsax was an Ordnance/Regional Depot in the Outer Rim Territories. It was colonized by the Galactic Republic sometime before the Pius Dea Era.

properties.name: Ord Mynock
properties.poi: Ord Mynock FreeportComNet Corporation headquartersLast Stand Casino
properties.description: Ord Mynock was a planet in the Mynockra system of the Outer Rim Territories' Prefsbelt sector. It was originally settled during the Old Republic as a communication relay. As trade lanes shifted elsewhere, the planet fell into relative obscurity.

properties.name: Ord Namurt
properties.description: Ord Namurt was an Outer Rim planet in the Galactic Republic, and the site of an Ordnance/Regional Depot.

properties.name: Ord Ortag
properties.description: Ord Ortag was a world located in the Ord Ortag system, a part of the Slice. Ord Ortag served as an Ordnance/Regional Depot outpost for the Galactic Republic during the Pius Dea Era, a period of time that lasted between approximately 12,000 BBY and 11,000 BBY, despite it being located outside the borders of Republic space. When the Republic launched the Thirty-Fourth Pius Dea Crusade against the Hutt species in 11,057 BBY, Republic forces moved from Ord Ortag to the Hollastin system, in the vicinity of Hutt Space. Eventually, Ord Ortag itself became incorporated into that region.

properties.name: Ord Pardron
properties.description: Ord Pardron was a tiny planet with a thin atmosphere in the Ord Pardron system of the Dufilvian sector, located in the Mid Rim.

properties.name: Ord Pentala
properties.description: Ord Pentala was a world located in the Ord Pentala system of the Inner Rim. Ord Pentala served as an Ordnance/Regional Depot outpost for the Galactic Republic during the Pius Dea Era, a period of time that lasted between 12,000 BBY and 11,000 BBY, despite it being located just outside the borders of Republic space.

properties.name: Ord Radama
properties.poi: Commerce District, Scarlet Sword, Cultural District, Borrigan's, Imperial Opera House, Imperial Intelligence Service command center, Livien Magnus palace, Livien Magnus spaceport, Hangar C-46, Livien Magnus's southern gate, Livien Magnus's western wall, Narek Manor, Noble District, Imperial Palace, Ord Radama Republic stronghold, Residential District, The Barrows, Rialla Way, Aleos Narek's shop, Temple of Magnus,
properties.description: Ord Radama was a planet in the Radama Void of the Outer Rim Territories' Esstran sector.  Once a world of marshes and wetlands, it was built up with cities and streets over the years. The planet was the homeworld of the Devlikk species.

properties.name: Ord Sabaok
properties.description: Ord Sabaok was a planet in the Core Worlds and, as its name suggests, an Ordnance/Regional Depot. The planet was also known for its exclusive night clubs.

properties.name: Ord Sedra
properties.description: Ord Sedra was originally an Ordnance/Regional Depot located in the Clacis sector of the Outer Rim Territories.

properties.name: Ord Segra
properties.description: Ord Segra was a Galactic Republic world in the Mid Rim's Ord Segra system.

properties.name: Ord Sigatt
properties.description: Ord Sigatt was an Outer Rim Territories mining planet in the Galactic Republic. The planet was originally settled by the Republic militia as an Ordnance/Regional Depot, but upon the discovery of carvanium by one of the settlers, it quickly evolved into a mining colony.

properties.name: Ord Simres
properties.description: Ord Simres was a planet in the Outer Rim's Brema sector.

properties.name: Ord Tessebok
properties.description: Ord Tessebok was a Mid Rim world on the Entralla Route. Originally an Ordnance/Regional Depot, the planet was open to immigration sponsored by the Refugee Relief Movement in 22 BBY, shortly before the Clone Wars. At that time, its population had already grown to 2.5 billion people.

properties.name: Ord Thabl
properties.description: Ord Thabl was a world located in the Ord Thabl system. It was situated in the Halla sector, a part of the Kashyyyk Region in the Slice portion of the Mid Rim. Ord Thabl served as an Ordnance/Regional Depot outpost for the Galactic Republic during the Pius Dea Era, a period of time that lasted between approximately 12,000 BBY and 11,000 BBY. When the Republic launched the Third Pius Dea Crusade against the Hutt species in 11,939 BBY, Republic forces moved from Ord Thabl toward Hutt Space, including the Cyborrea system in the region's vicinity.

properties.name: Ord Thoden
properties.description: Ord Thoden was a tectonically active planet in the Dynali sector. Its capital was Domitree, and it was represented in the Galactic Senate by Boganni Hrul prior to the Clone Wars. It was the headquarters of Bengel Shipbuilders, and relied on the company's XQ1 Space Platforms as stopover points for travelers to alleviate space transport traffic. The Tenloss Syndicate also had dealings on the planet. It was the site of a deadly groundquake 23 BBY, and was the homeworld of Aris-Del Wari and her mother, Jonava Billane.

properties.name: Ord Tiddell
properties.description: Ord Tiddell was a Mid Rim planet established as an Ordnance/Regional Depot by the Galactic Republic during the Pius Dea Era. In 22 BBY, the planet, home to a population of four million, became one of many worlds in the Mid Rim and Colonies regions to be affected by stone mites, genetically-engineered aggressive arthropods that fed on building materials. Unlike the other affected worlds, which reported only minor damage from the arthropods, Ord Tiddell was devastated. The mites ate through the foundation of Lagabee, Ord Tiddell's capital city, leaving the area in ruins and forcing the planet's population to flee off-world. The widespread destruction caused by the mites cost Ord Tiddell billions of credits, and many believed it was too late for any assistance from either the Republic or the Jedi Order to be effective.

properties.name: Ord Torrenze
properties.description: Ord Torrenze was a planet in the Sertar sector of the Outer Rim.

properties.name: Ord Traga
properties.description: Ord Traga was a planet, possibly the location of an Imperial base.

properties.name: Ord Trasi
properties.description: Ord Trasi was a planet in the Relgim sector of the Outer Rim and a major shipbuilding world.

properties.name: Ord Varee
properties.description: Ord Varee was a Republic Ordnance/Regional Depot world located in the Belshar sector of the Mid Rim. In 22 BBY, Ord Varee was one of the ten planets of the Refugee Relief Coalition, which allowed beings that were displaced by the ongoing Separatist Crisis to resettle on their worlds.

properties.name: Ord Vaug
properties.description: Ord Vaug was a planet in the Expansion Region.

properties.name: Ord Vaxal
properties.description: Ord Vaxal was a planet on the outer periphery of the Inner Rim, near Hutt Space.

properties.name: Ord Wylan
properties.description: Ord Wylan was a world located in the Mid Rim's Oktos sector. During the Pius Dea Era, between 12,000 BBY and 11,000 BBY, it served as an Ordnance/Regional Depot outpost for the Galactic Republic. Shortly after the Battle of Yavin, the gambler Lando Calrissian won the license rights for the taxi service on Ord Wylan in a sabacc game but lost them shortly afterward.

properties.name: Ord Yndar
properties.description: Ord Yndar was a planet in the Mid Rim that served as an Ordnance/Regional Depot for the Galactic Republic. During the Pius Dea Era, Ord Yndar lay at the border between Republic and Hutt Space, and the planet was used as a staging point for an assault on the Hutts when Supreme Chancellor Contispex I—a member of the religious cult Pius Dea—launched the First Pius Dea Crusade in 11,965 BBY.

properties.name: Ord Zat
properties.description: Ord Zat was a world located in the Ord Zat system, a part of the Jospro sector in the Slice portion of the Outer Rim Territories. It served as an Ordnance/Regional Depot outpost for the Galactic Republic during the Pius Dea Era, a period of time that lasted between 12,000 BBY and 11,000 BBY.

properties.name: Ord Zeuol
properties.description: Ord Zeuol was a planet in the Ord Zeuol system, a part of the Vilonis sector in the Trailing Sectors portion of the Mid Rim. The planet served as an Ordnance/Regional Depot outpost for the Galactic Republic during the Pius Dea Era, a period of time that lasted between approximately 12,000 BBY and 11,000 BBY, despite being located outside the Republic's borders.

properties.name: Ord Zynthar
properties.description: Ord Zynthar was a world located in the Ord Zynthar system. It was situated in the Lambda sector, a part of the Trailing Sectors portion of the Mid Rim.

properties.name: Ordo
properties.description: Ordo was the homeworld of the Mandalorian Clan Ordo, including Canderous Ordo, who became Mandalore in 3954 BBY. Mostly a barren desert planet, Ordo had some vegetation around its equator.

properties.name: Orelon
properties.description: Orelon was a terrestrial astronomical object located in the galaxy that was the site of a weapons trade involving the Wookiee smuggler Chewbacca and Big Quince. During the weapons trade on Orelon, Big Quince's Wookiee bodyguard gave Chewbacca the pirate Maz Kanata's Smuggler's Guide. When Chewbacca's partner, Han Solo, learned where he had acquired the Smuggler's Guide months later, Solo recorded an account of the incident in the book.

properties.name: Oricho
properties.description: Oricho may refer to one of the following:

properties.name: Oricon
properties.description: Oricon was a moon in the Outer Rim Territories just outside the Seat of The Empire.

properties.name: Orimanther
properties.description: Orimanther was a world in the Quelii sector that was visited by the Chevin slaver Phylus Mon during the waning years of the Galactic Republic. According to a rumor, Mon attempted to capture a flock of Orimanther's battlebirds, but was initially unsuccessful, so he meditated and created a Force storm, to knock the birds from out of the sky.

properties.name: Orinackra
properties.description: Orinackra was an infamous prison planet located within the Wild Space of the galaxy. Crix Madine, an Imperial general who had attempted to defect to the Rebel Alliance after the Evacuation of Yavin, was kept there during the Dark Trooper crisis for leaking valuable information to the Alliance to Restore the Republic. Kyle Katarn daringly rescued him.

properties.name: Orinda
properties.description: Orinda was a small Mid Rim planet in the Irishi sector. It was located along the Entralla Route and on the border of the Mid Rim and the Outer Rim Territories.

properties.name: Oriolanis
properties.description: Oriolanis was a terrestrial planet located in the Oriolanis system, a part of the Mid Rim's Oriolan sector. The minor technology company Oriolanis Defense Systems, which existed by 27 BBY, was based on Oriolanis. Shortly before the Battle of Endor of 4 ABY, Oriolanis was the site of a Class II military shipyard used by the Galactic Empire. The output of the facility was limited to Imperial-class Star Destroyers.

properties.name: Orion
properties.description: Orion was the Orion system's primary star.

properties.name: Oristrom
properties.description: Oristrom was a world that was inhabited by the Stromma species. At some point, Oristrom was captured by the forces of the alien warlord Nuso Esva, and Esva was later driven from the world by Grand Admiral Thrawn.

properties.name: Orixon Nebula
properties.description: The Orixon Nebula was a nebula in the Phelleem sector, that was the location of a black halo. The black halo was the remnant of a star—which the planet Kashi once orbited—which went supernova around 25,053 BBY. Prior to this event, it was referred to as the Kashi System. It was located at S-7 on the Galactic grid. Formerly located in Hutt Space, the Hutts eventually drew back their borders.

properties.name: Orleon
properties.description: Orleon was a rainy planet in the Mid Rim. The rain was torrential and never stopped, leaving the planet covered in mud.

properties.name: Orma
properties.description: Orma was a junk planet in the Aramand Cluster of the Brak sector. Junkers had covered the world in scrapyards which contained many cultural artifacts including some toys and tech. Further within the planet were items of amazing value. Around the time of the Cold War, an individual was sent to look for the valuable artifacts, discovering a relic from the height of the Tion Hegemony. Several hundred years before the Galactic Civil War, the Orma akia colonized the planet.

properties.name: Orn Kios
properties.description: Orn Kios was a planet located in the Corellian Trade Spine. It had a few small settlements built on giant lily pads. Constructed mostly of wood and canvas, these shelters formed the basis of the various fishing communities on the planet.

properties.name: Ornfra
properties.description: Ornfra was a planet located in the Ornfra system of the Unknown Regions' Chiss Space. The hyperlane known as the Path of the Houses linked the world to the Naporar and Sharb systems, and a smaller hyperspace route also connected it to the Noris system. Ornfra was an outlying colony of the sentient Chiss species and was home to one of the Ruling Families that ruled over the Chiss Ascendancy, the government of the Chiss.

properties.name: Orocco
properties.description: Orocco was a planet located within the Orocco system of the Mid Rim.

properties.name: Orondia
properties.description: Orondia was a bleak planet located near Nal Hutta, within Hutt Space, in the Outer Rim Territories. A fueling depot was located on the planet's surface. The depot was run by a Bith scammer, in league with his brother on Nal Hutta.

properties.name: Orooturoo
properties.description: Orooturoo was the home of a race of titanic purple-colored sluglike beings, most notably Princess Nampi. It was an endpoint of both the Metellos Trade Route and the Widek Bypass.

properties.name: Orroman
properties.description: Orroman was an astronomical object that was located within the Wild Space Orroman system. At some point, a group of mercenaries caused a water crisis there, with information about the disaster eventually becoming general knowledge across the galaxy. During the New Republic's reign, the New Republic Scout Service captain Korren Starchaser compared in his datafiles the mercenary group Happy Blasters with the group that had caused the water crisis, considering them both disreputable.

properties.name: Orryxia
properties.description: Orryxia was a planet in the Orryxia system, in the Outer Rim Territories near Eriadu. It was home to the Orryxians, a sentient species sometimes given the derogatory nickname "Cats." It was also home to the orycat, a small woodland predator. Wilek Nereus, the Imperial Governor of Bakura, visited the planet and obtained a dental specimen of the orycat but was unable to complete a comprehensive survey of the creature's environment due to adverse conditions.

properties.name: Orsis
properties.description: Orsis was a planet that had jungles, oceans and at least one volcano. It was home to the Orsis Academy, which was famous for training trackers, spys and assassins; among its most famous graduates was a young Darth Maul.

properties.name: Orthellin
properties.description: Orthellin may refer to one of the following:

properties.name: Orto
properties.description: Orto was a small planet in the Orto system of the Sluis sector, located in the Outer Rim Territories. It was the homeworld of the Ortolan race.

properties.name: Orvax
properties.description: Orvax was an astronomical object located in the galaxy's Outer Rim Territories.

properties.name: Osadia
properties.description: Osadia was a planet located within the Core Worlds. Its location was kept secret and removed off the star-charts so that the mysterious school that was located there could not be disturbed.

properties.name: Osara
properties.description: Osara was a planet located in the Inner Rim.

properties.name: Oseon
properties.description: Oseon was an astronomical object located in the Centrality, a sector of the galaxy's Outer Rim Territories. It was connected by the Sanity Skip hyperspace route to the planet Kessel and to Junkfort Station by another hyperspace route. The former pirate Queen Maz Kanata marked it as a point of interest on a map she included in the book that would become known as the Smuggler's Guide.

properties.name: Osirrag
properties.description: Osirrag was the home planet of the Onahk species. It was a small planet, boasting a pleasant climate of light breezes, perfumed air, and moderate temperatures.

properties.name: Osmani
properties.description: Osmani was a planet located in the Western Reaches of the Mid Rim. Part of the Senex sector's Osmani system, is a minor trade world owing to its location in the Tangles.

properties.name: Osseriton
properties.description: Osseriton was the only planet in the Osseriton system of the Unknown Regions. The Hemes Arbora settled there after abandoning their homeworld of Carrivar.

properties.name: Ossiathora
properties.description: Ossiathora was an agriworld located in the Ossiathora system of the Juvex sector, a part of the Senex-Juvex region in the Western Reaches portion of the Mid Rim. The Senex-Juvex Loop hyperlane linked it to the Deminol and Kassido systems. Ossiathora was the origin point of Ossiathoran noodles and was controlled by House Kassido, a noble house based on the world of Kassido.

properties.name: Osssorck Nebulae
properties.description: The Nebulas of Osssorck, also known as the Osssorck Nebulae, were a series of nebulosities located in the Core Worlds. During the Galactic Civil War, an aging yet legendary gunfighter resided in the city of Buerhoz on the Outer Rim Territories' planet Clak'dor VII. When a group of individuals encountered the gunfighter at Buerhoz, he claimed to have witnessed the destruction of several cruisers of the Galactic Empire in the Nebulas of Osssorck.

properties.name: Ossus
properties.poi: Jedi Academy, Imhar Canyon, Eocho Mountains, Knossa Spaceport, Gardens of T'alla, Great Jedi Library, Jedi Colony, Strike Base XR-484,
properties.description: Ossus, known as Idux while under the control of Xim's empire, was the third planet in the Adega system in the Auril sector. Known to the galaxy since before 25,000 BBY, when the Jedi expanded there from the planet Tython and established a Jedi Academy, Ossus would become a popular world of the Galactic Republic. This world would also become a place of great importance to the Jedi, as the site where they stored the sum of their knowledge, though such attentions came at a price. When the Jedi Knight Exar Kun turned to the dark side and became the Dark Lord of the Sith, catapulting the galaxy into the Great Sith War, he attacked Ossus, desiring Sith secrets hidden by the Jedi. During the events this action incited, the Cron Cluster was detonated, spreading a shockwave around the galaxy. Originally a rich, lush world, Ossus was ravaged into an arid and toxic planet when the wave struck the planet.

properties.name: Ostega
properties.description: Ostega was a planet located in the Grohl sector of the Outer Rim Territories. A civil war occurred on this planet before the Clone Wars.

properties.name: Ostor
properties.description: Ostor was an arid terrestrial planet located in the Ostor system, at the fringe of the Outer Rim Territories in the Koradin sector. It was a barren planet composed of red soil, deep canyons, and various wind-sculpted rock formations.

properties.name: Ota
properties.description: Ota was a frozen world in the Kashyyyk Region of the Mid Rim which was the home of the furry sentient species known as the Snogars. The Snogars lived in cities built within the planet's ice canyons by their ancestors, a highly intelligent race referred to as the "Old Ones." By 1 ABY the heating machines that kept the Snogar cities warm began to fail, leading Ota's natives to seek out offworlders who could repair the devices and help them survive the planet's biting cold.

properties.name: Otavon
properties.description: Otavon XII, also written Otavon 12 and sometimes called simply "Otavon", was a forested planet inhabited by the Ovoni.

properties.name: Otavon
properties.description: Otavon XII, also written Otavon 12 and sometimes called simply "Otavon", was a forested planet inhabited by the Ovoni.

properties.name: Otor's Hub
properties.description: Otor's Hub was a black market space station in the Outer Rim Territories' Ojoster sector. Located close to a planet, it was fairly large and served as a way station within the Outer Rim. During the Clone Wars, Jedi Master Obi-Wan Kenobi and Sith assassin–turned–bounty hunter Asajj Ventress stopped on Otor's Hub together after losing a confrontation with the Sith brothers Darth Maul and Savage Opress over Raydonia.

properties.name: Otranto
properties.description: Otranto was the base of the Church of the First Frequency. It was ordered to be closed by Imperial Grand Inquisitor Torbin.

properties.name: Ottabesk
properties.description: Ottabesk was a planet in the Deep Core.

properties.name: Ottethan
properties.description: Ottethan was a planet located in the Outer Rim Territories's Ottethan system, in the Ottethan Empire. It was ruled by a warlord who married Neema-Da-Boda, but later fed her to the rancors that roamed the planet.

properties.name: Otunia
properties.description: Otunia was a planet that was the Imperial sector capital of the Bosph sector, and the home of the Kabul family. It was covered in deserts and had mineral-rich soil, perfect for mining.

properties.name: Oulanne
properties.description: Oulanne was a jungle planet in the Inner Rim of the the galaxy.

properties.name: Outland Transit Station
properties.description: Outland Transit Station was a massive space outpost owned by a Toydarian named Rozatta. Its key attractions were the pit beast fighting arenas and Merchant Row. It was colloquially known as simply Outland Station.

properties.name: Ova
properties.description: Ova was an Outer Rim Territories planet that presumably was sucked into infinity by an Infinity Wave in 30 BBY.

properties.name: Ovise
properties.description: Ovise was an astronomical object located in the galaxy's Moddell sector.

properties.name: Oyokal
properties.description: Oyokal was a terrestrial planet located in the Oyokal system of the Unknown Regions' Chiss Space. A hyperlane linked the world to the Shihon system. A quadrupedal species was native to Oyokal.

properties.name: Oznek
properties.poi: Oznek power plant, Oznek Republic base, Oznek ruins,
properties.description: Oznek was a planet located in the Cademimu sector of the Outer Rim Territories.

properties.name: Ozu
properties.description: Ozu was a quiet planet of farmers. Ozu rarely received visitors outside of those who frequented a small fuel station built on a mountaintop.

properties.name: Pa Tho
properties.description: Pa Tho was an astronomical object located in the Inner Rim's Pa Tho system. It shared its name with the alien culture known as the Pa Tho, which had vanished at some point by 16 ABY. Pa Tho was also the homeworld of the Human Rebel pilot Nala Hetsime, who participated in the Battle of Hoth in 3 ABY.

properties.name: Pa'hir'al
properties.description: Pa'hir'al could refer to one of the following:

properties.name: Paarin Minor
properties.description: Paarin Minor was a planet located in the Cademimu sector of the Outer Rim Territories. A stronghold of the Galactic Republic during the Clone Wars, the planet was the target of an unsuccessful attack by the Confederacy of Independent Systems. It later fell within the territory of the Galactic Empire, and eventually within Supreme Commander Gilad Pellaeon's Imperial Remnant from 12 ABY to 17 ABY.

properties.name: Paecia
properties.description: Paecia was an ancient location in the the galaxy. It shared its name with the Paecian language.

properties.name: Paig
properties.description: Paig was a planet located in the Expansion Region

properties.name: Paigu
properties.description: Paigu was a planet in the Vorzyd Cluster of the Commonality in the Outer Rim Territories. It was the homeworld of the Paigun species.

properties.name: Paklan
properties.description: Paklan was a forest planet, located in the Paklan system in the Nuiri sector of the Outer Rim. In 20 BBY, the Nightbrothers Darth Maul and Savage Opress took refuge on the planet after having a bounty posted on their heads by the Gossam Ja'Boag, the leader of the Rim Commercial Mining corporation. After Zika led a band of bounty hunters to the two's location in a local diner, Savage and Maul brutally killed their assailants before fleeing the planet.

properties.name: Pako Ramoon
properties.description: Pako Ramoon was a planet located in the Rayter sector in the Outer Rim.

properties.name: Pakuuni
properties.description: Pakuuni was a planet in the Outer Rim Territories near Munto Codru in the Codru system, Argoon in the Newland system, and the Crseih system.

properties.name: Pal Goral
properties.description: Pal Goral was a planet in the Mortex sector of the Outer Rim.

properties.name: Palanhi
properties.description: Palanhi was a Colonies world that was located within the Fakir sector, situated on the Bakchou arm of the galaxy.

properties.name: Palawa
properties.description: Palawa was a planet in the Core Worlds. It was the planet of origin of two mystic Force traditions, the Followers of Palawa and the Chatos Academy.

properties.name: Pallaxides
properties.poi: Ort Hoogra-D'En's base, Imperial research facility, TaggeCo. starport,
properties.description: Pallaxides was a planet of the Ojoster sector in the Outer Rim. It was owned by TaggeCo, who used it as a resort world.

properties.name: Pamina Prime
properties.description: Pamina Prime was a planet in the Inner Rim. It was home to shellfish that were responsible of a deadly disease when eaten, the Borotavi syndrome. Jedi Master Taria Damsin was diagnosed with this disease after eating a local blue-shelled mollusk with a green stripe.

properties.name: Pammant
properties.description: Pammant was a tunneled planet located in the Calamari sector of the Outer Rim Territories. The Quarren of nearby Dac staked claims to Pammant and other worlds located in the sector, using them as bases for starship construction. During the Clone Wars between the Galactic Republic and the Confederacy of Independent Systems, the Pammant shipyards were used by the Quarren-dominated Free Dac Volunteers Engineering Corps to produce Separatist warships such as the Malevolence and the Invisible Hand, both used as flagships by the Separatist General Grievous. However, before the Battle of Coruscant in 19 BBY, Pammant was devastated when the Republic Praetor-class Star Battlecruiser Quaestor suffered a hyperspace accident and collided with the planet, fracturing Pammant and dousing it with radiation.

properties.name: Pamorjal
properties.description: Pamorjal was a planet located in the Pamorjal system in the Expansion Region.

properties.name: Panatha
properties.description: Panatha, also known as Epicanthix was a jungle planet in the Pacanth Reach in the Outer Rim Territories. It was the homeworld of the Epicanthix. It was close to the Unknown Regions.

properties.name: Panna
properties.description: Panna was a planet in the Outer Rim's Tion Cluster, orbited by Panna Prime and two other moons.

properties.name: Pantolomin
properties.poi: Coral VandaTowers of Pantolomin, Jervo's World
properties.description: Pantolomin, also known as Panto Prime, was the primary planet of the Panto system, in the Dolomar sector of the Core Worlds. It was an aquatic world known as one of the greatest tourist places of the galaxy.

properties.name: Pantora
properties.description: Pantora was the principal moon of the Outer Rim Territories' Pantora system, orbiting the ice planet Orto Plutonia. Pantora was covered by terrestrial land, with marshes on the outskirts of its cities. It was a member of the Galactic Republic and had full senatorial representation on Coruscant.

properties.name: Paonid
properties.description: The Paonid system was a star system located within the Inner Rim of the galaxy.

properties.name: Paqwepor Major
properties.description: Paqwepor Major, also known as Paqwepor, was a planet in the Mid Rim off the Corellian Run. It was within the region of Paqwepori. Paqwepor Major was the Paqwe homeworld and it was ruled by the Paqwe family. During the Clone Wars, Paqwepor Major was located within Separatist space.

properties.name: Parabaw Station
properties.description: Parabaw Station was a space station that was located in the Jospro sector of the Outer Rim Territories. It was used as a holding station for troops and supplies before all of the station's pilots and troops went out to help against the Empire. After that, Parabaw Station was used for holding supplies for those who needed it until it was accidentally destroyed due to some major malfunctions.

properties.name: Parada
properties.description: Parada was an agriworld located in the Parada system of the Hadar sector, a part of the Western Reaches portion of the Mid Rim. The Senex Trace hyperlane linked it to the Rindao system as well as the Bortras system of the Outer Rim Territories' Brema sector.

properties.name: Paradise
properties.description: The name Paradise could refer to:

properties.name: Paradise Station
properties.description: Paradise was a space station located on a small hyperspace route branching off of the Corellian Trade Spine. It was known for pirates and slavers more than it was for shipping or commercial goods. It was also well known for its gambling, pleasure slaves, and sales of various illegal narcotics. Lucia met with the Iktotchi assassin Huntress at Paradise in 980 BBY to hire her to assassinate the rebel leader Gelba and later to hire her again for a mission to capture Darth Bane.

properties.name: Paramatan
properties.description: Paramatan was a primitive terrestrial world located in the Mid Rim's Senex sector. Its surface featured forests and jungles as well as plains and oceans. The world's fauna included birds, reptiles, and great oopiks, a species having both avian and reptilian traits. The oopiks were a relic species of flightless creatures that made their home in the Paramatan fruit trees of the continent of Grxy. Paramatan was discovered by scouts of the aristocratic House Elegin and eventually came to be used by the nobles of the Senex-Juvex region as a destination for hunting safaris.

properties.name: Parcelus Minor
properties.description: Parcellus Minor was a planet in the Expansion Region. Its small amount of landmass was almost entirely covered with swamp jungles; the natives of the planet spent much time simply pushing the edge of the swamp back. All plant life on Parcellus Minor exuded tzeotine, a combustible resin used by the native population for heating and fuel.

properties.name: Parcovey Minor
properties.description: Parcovey Minor was a planet considered part of the outlying domains of the Hutt species during the time at which the world was settled during the Kymoodon Era.

properties.name: Pargaux
properties.description: Pargaux was a planet located in the Core Worlds of the galaxy. The planet's society had been matriarchal since before the Seventh Battle of Ruusan. It was the homeworld of the stormtrooper TD-5144.

properties.name: Parkis
properties.description: The Parkis system was a star system located in the Colonies that contained a Human colony.

properties.name: Parliock
properties.description: Parliock was a location somewhere in the galaxy. Peacekeeping involving the Jedi Order once took place there. During the Clone Wars, the peacekeeping was recalled by the architect droid Huyang.

properties.name: Parmel
properties.description: The Parmel system was located in the Parmel sector.

properties.name: Parmic
properties.description: The Parmic system was found in the Parmic sector.

properties.name: Parshoone
properties.description: Parshoone was a planet in the Outer Rim Territories, controlled by the Imperial Remnant. It was an Ubiqtorate contact station.

properties.name: Parthovian Cluster
properties.description: The Parthovian Cluster was in Wild Space. It contained the Faarlsun system.

properties.name: Partold
properties.description: The Partold were a sentient species.

properties.name: Parwa
properties.description: Parwa was a world that was located in the Seswenna sector, in the Outer Rim Territories. The Parwan bounty hunter Derrown originated on Parwa.

properties.name: Pas'sic
properties.description: Pas'sic was a planet in the Oricho sector of the Outer Rim Territories.

properties.name: Pashvi
properties.description: Pashvi was a planet that was located on the edge of Wild Space and had thousands of rock pillars scattered across its landscape. Both nutritional plants and dangerous predatory avians could be found on the tops of the pillars. As a result, the native Pashvi, a sentient humanoid species, were both drawn to and afraid of the pillars, and had a distanced emotional state. The Pashvi also created works of art that were sought after in the Corporate Sector, and the Human smuggler Dubrak Qennto had visited the world a few times by the year 27 BBY.

properties.name: Pasmin
properties.description: Pasmin was a planet located within the Outer Rim Territories. One of the original member-worlds of the Kingdom of Cron, it was absorbed into Xim's Empire. After the fall of the empire in 25,100 BBY, it would eventually join the Galactic Republic. It would continue to thrive as a world, eventually joining the Cronese Mandate after the rise of the Galactic Empire. Known for its weavers, they created extremely light, yet warm, blankets and clothes.

properties.name: Pastil
properties.description: The planet Pastil, located in the Pastil system, was a location of one of the Galactic Republic's listening posts during the Clone Wars.

properties.name: Patch
properties.description: Patch was a male Human who served as a lieutenant with the Oquan, a bounty hunter group that operated on the planet of Naalol. During the time of the Galactic Civil War, the Rebel Alliance procurement officer Lieutenant Talnar crash-landed on Naalol and the Oquan planned to capture him, so that they could sell him to the Galactic Empire. Patch and the Oquan lieutenant Selana subsequently led a group of fifteen Oquan who subdued Talnar and took him captive.

properties.name: Patitite Pattuna
properties.description: Patitite Pattuna was a planet close to the world Balnab that was home to the diminutive Patitite species.

properties.name: Patriim
properties.description: Patriim was the sun that the planet Hockaleg orbited. It was the homeworld of Siward Cass. The system was the construction site of the Galactic Empire's Tarkin superweapon.

properties.name: Patrolia
properties.description: Patrolia was the aquatic homeworld of the Patrolian species. The planet was located in the Inner Rim.

properties.name: Paulking
properties.description: The Paulking system in the Centrality contained the planet Paulking XIV.

properties.name: Pavia
properties.description: Pavia was a planet in the Pavia system. It was located in the Cadriaan Province of the Tapani sector.

properties.name: Pavo Prime
properties.description: Pavo Prime was a warm gambling planet in the Inner Rim.

properties.name: Pax
properties.description: Pax was an astronomical object located in the Expansion Region and the Trailing Sectors regions in grid square N-16 of the Standard Galactic Grid. The hyperspace route known as the Hydian Way linked Pax to the Chardaan system and the celestial body ZeHeth, while another route connected it to the astronomical objects Kira and Vondarc.

properties.name: PDC3141-02
properties.description: PDC3141-02 was a Mid Rim planetoid located in the Trax sector. For centuries, the Trade Federation used it for dumping radioactive industrial waste. Shortly prior to 13:3:21, University of Sanbra scientists discovered on the planetoid a native unicellular lifeform, and a subsequent temporary injunction prevented further Federation dumping. At the time of the discovery, however, a Trade Federation scow had been transporting a cargo of hazardous waste to PDC3141-02. Since the injunction against dumping on the planetoid endangered the vessel's crew, the Federation subsequently attempted to bypass the restriction.

properties.name: Pedd
properties.description: Pedd could refer to one of the following:

properties.name: Pedducis Chorios
properties.description: Pedducis Chorios was a planet in the Meridian sector in the Pedducis Chorios system. After her initial retirement from the Imperial Starfleet, Admiral Daala led a group of Imperial Remnant settlers on the world. It was also the world were Warlord K'iin resided and was home to several pirate bases.

properties.name: Pegg
properties.description: Pegg was a planet in the Tynquay sector of the Outer Rim.

properties.name: Peirs
properties.description: Peirs was a planet within the Peirs system of the Outer Rim Territories' Kathol sector. Connected to the neighboring planets of Gandle Ott, Shintel and Ivatch by hyperlanes, Peirs supported a small colony whose economy was based around supplying ore and natural resources to Gandle Ott.

properties.name: Pelagon
properties.description: Pelagon was a planet in the Pelagia Province of the Tapani sector and was the capital world of House Pelagia. It was a planet with a long tradition of providing many Jedi, such as Taj Junak. As a result, it was stripped of much of its power during the Great Jedi Purge.

properties.name: Peldon Minor
properties.description: Peldon Minor was an astronomical object located within the Peldon Minor system. It was located in the star cluster that eventually became the Cassander subsector, a part of the Cassander sector in the New Territories portion of the Outer Rim Territories. During the Clone Wars, Galactic Republic colonel Hurst Romodi participated in military actions at Peldon Minor and was later decorated for his efforts while fighting there.

properties.name: Pelemax
properties.description: Pelemax was a planet in the Colonies. The Pelemaxians were native to this planet.

properties.name: Pelgrin
properties.description: Pelgrin was a planet in the Outer Rim. Over two million years before the Battle of Yavin, an indigenous species, the Pelgrin, built the Oracle on the planet, a merging of technology and the Force. The Pelgrin went extinct, leaving many mysterious ruins and artifacts.

properties.name: Pella
properties.description: Pella was a planet in the Pella system in the Mecetti Province of the Tapani sector. It was probably named after the Pella Compact. The planet produced vast harvests of grain and vegetables each year and was an important agricultural producer of the sector.

properties.name: Pellastrallas
properties.description: Pellastrallas was a planet that was at least partially covered in wilderness, as it was populated by wild, native arqets, vicious predatory beasts that dwelt in the mountainous regions of the planet. It was also home to species such as the uthori breix.

properties.name: Pendal
properties.description: Pendal was a planet inhabited by Humans who lagged behind most of the galaxy in weapons technology, as they still used slugthrowers rather than blasters. Its capital was Tilam City, and the inhabitants often survived off street crime.

properties.name: Pendari
properties.description: Pendari was a planet in the Expansion Region, located on the Corellian Trade Spine rimward of the Kinyen system.

properties.name: Pendaxa
properties.description: Pendaxa was a planet located in the Jjannex sector of the Outer Rim.

properties.name: Penegelen
properties.description: Penegelen was a star located in the star system of the same name, which was a part of the Inner Rim region of the galaxy. It was orbited by a spherical cloud of debris known as the Penegelen Shards, which consisted of tumbling fragments of alloy, rock, and flash frozen dirt. Scientists believed that these shards once made up a shell which enclosed Penegelen. This shell was thought to have been a creation of an ancient species known as the Celestial.

properties.name: Pengalan
properties.description: Pengalan was an astronomical object located in the galaxy's Inner Rim.

properties.name: Peppel
properties.description: Peppel was a swampy planet in the Outer Rim Territories. Boba Fett took the Slave IV to this planet, where he captured the resident Kardue'sai'Malloc.

properties.name: Per Lupelo
properties.description: Per Lupelo was a cosmopolitan planet in the Per Lupelo system. It was dotted by a number of clean cities and bodies of water, and it was also dotted with a number of mountain ranges. A crime organization led by the gangster Raze had its headquarters on the planet at the height of the Galactic Civil War.

properties.name: Peragus
properties.description: Peragus may refer to:

properties.name: Peregrine's Nest
properties.description: Peregrine's Nest was the secret military base of Garm Bel Iblis's private army, named for its commander's flagship. The encampment included many camouflaged structures, with everything from small living quarters to larger admin and supply sheds to even larger maintenance and tool buildings and, largest of all, a refurbishing hangar. While Peregrine's Nest was designed as a temporary facility which was regularly moved to avoid detection, it eventually became a permanent, fixed base. However, the location of the Nest remained a carefully guarded secret, despite the fact that it was on a planet within 150 light-years of New Cov, which was located on a major hyperlane in the Mid Rim.

properties.name: Pergitor
properties.description: Pergitor was a planet in the Minos Cluster settled by Jesa Corporation miners. Excessive mining resulted in volcanic eruptions that poisoned the atmosphere and destroyed the ecosystem. The inhabitants were forced to retreat to sealed cities.

properties.name: Peridon's Folly
