properties.description: Peridon's Folly was a weapons depot that was operated by traders who sold obsolete arms to crime lords. Sectors were controlled by gunrunners and were separated by wastelands where the weapons were tested. IG-88B collected his first bounty there.

properties.name: Perilious
properties.description: Perilious was a planet that was located within the Outer Rim Territories of the galaxy. It was home to a large criminal element, which including a large slaving ring that dealt in Twi'leks. The world was continually covered by storms.

properties.name: Perilix
properties.description: Perilix was an oceanic world inhabited by thinking clams.

properties.name: Perin
properties.description: Perin was a Trianii colony planet in Trianii Space.

properties.name: Perithal
properties.description: Perithal was a location which the New Republic Senator Wyl Lark visited around 11 ABY, before he traveled over to Spirana to meet Yrica Quell and Chass na Chadic, who he had fought with as a New Republic pilot in the Galactic Civil War six years before.

properties.name: Perlemia
properties.description: Perlemia was a planet located in the Perlemia system in the Core Worlds.

properties.name: Perma
properties.description: Perma was a planet in the galaxy's Core Worlds.

properties.name: Pernam Minor
properties.description: Pernam Minor was a planet in the Pernam Minor system.

properties.name: Pernella
properties.description: Pernella was a planet in the Pernella system in Tapani sector. It was one of the Freeworlds. It was also one of the Three Ellas, with a liberal government looser about crime and smuggling than most Tapani worlds.

properties.name: Persavi
properties.description: The Persavi system was located in the Taldot sector, a part of the Kashyyyk Region in the Slice portion of the Mid Rim. During the Clone Wars, the Persavi system followed the lead of the worlds Antar, Ando, and Sy Myrth, which had previously seceded from the Galactic Republic, and also broke its ties with the Republic. The Confederacy of Independent Systems, which the Persavi system joined, came to heavily rely on the system's military forces during the former's conflict with the Republic.

properties.name: Pesfavri
properties.description: Pesfavri was a planet in the Unknown Regions claimed by the Chiss Ascendancy.

properties.name: Peshara
properties.description: Peshara was a planet. In 4 BBY, Arden Lyn compared the Jedi Order at the time of the First Great Schism to a sewing circle of widows on Peshara.

properties.name: Pesitiin
properties.description: Pesitiin was an Expansion Region gas giant in the Pesitiin system with massive atmospheric storms. It had an abandoned Bosken & Bosken mining center which attempted to harvest the planet's gases, but failed due to the storms, going bankrupt.

properties.name: Petabys Station
properties.description: Petabys Station was a space station housing a black market in the Mid Rim's Halm sector. It was a Rendili StarDrive FireStar Orbital Defense Station originally used to defend mining operations on a small moon located at the edge of a binary system. After a cost/benefit analysis, the parent company of the mine chose to sell the station rather than move it, a decision bolstered by an aggressive sales campaign by space station developer Golan Arms. The station was purchased by Rodian black marketeer Uopled at a bargain price. Uopled modified the station to better serve its new role, converting cargo shuttle landing bays into freighter bays for his buyers and sellers, maintaining half of the stations fighter bays to house three squadrons of Z-95 Headhunters, and converting many core levels of the station into sales centers. All of the station's defensive systems were retained, ensuring anyone laying siege to it faced a protracted and challenging fight.

properties.name: Petrakis
properties.description: Petrakis was the site of the first engagement between Rebel Alliance B-wing starfighters and Imperial forces. During an attack on an imperial convoy that carried a squadron of Fighters, the escorting TIEs were so panicked when they first encountered the attacking B-Wings that they left formation and fled. So the rebel starfighters managed to destroy the whole convoy consisting of several Freighters, Transports and Shuttlecraft despite the arrival of imperial reinforcements, a full wing of assault gunboats.

properties.name: Phaeda
properties.poi: Collo Fauale, Collo Fauale Pass, Phaeda spaceport,
properties.description: Phaeda was a planet in the Outer Rim Territories, with two rocky moons. Of little strategic or commercial importance, its Imperial garrison was corrupt, and so the planet provided haven for many smugglers, thieves and other fringers. This led to diverse species finding a home on the planet, in addition to the many Human inhabitants.

properties.name: Phaseera
properties.description: Phaseera was a manufacturing planet that was the location of a battle near the end of the New Sith Wars. It had been occupied by the Galactic Republic before the conflict, but after the Republic defeat, it became Sith occupied. Its terrain included jungles, valleys, and plateaus. It orbited a yellow sun, and cydera trees grew on it.

properties.name: Phateem
properties.description: Phateem was an Inner Rim planet which housed a Jedi library and storehouse known as the Halls of Knowledge, within the planet's Ashlendu Mountains.

properties.name: Phatrong
properties.description: Phatrong was the homeworld of the Kyuzo species.

properties.name: Phattro
properties.description: Phattro was an alcoholic drink sold in bottles in cantinas and diners, like Moshi Bar, Trueping's and Plop Dribble's. The name was printed in Aurebesh on the label. It was advertised on posters in the Coruscant underworld.

properties.name: Phelarion
properties.description: Phelarion was a planet located in the Seswenna sector, in the Outer Rim Territories. In was the homeworld of the wealthy Motti family, which included figures prominent in the Galactic Empire such as Lady Thalassa Tarkin, wife of Grand Moff Wilhuff Tarkin, and Conan Antonio Motti, Admiral of the Imperial Navy. The Motti family were wealthy citizens in the megonite moss mining business, established in the centuries prior to 60 BBY, using slave labor.

properties.name: Phelope
properties.description: The Phelope system was located in the Gateworlds, an area of the Hapes Cluster in the Slice portion of the Inner Rim. It was connected via hyperlanes to the Gateworlds' Zadaria system and the Ediorung system in the Interior Region. The Phelope system was the origin point of the beverage known as A Walk in the Phelopean Forest.

properties.name: Phemis
properties.poi: The Grand Cavern, Spiremount, Endless Tunnels, Undersea,
properties.description: Phemis was a backwater planet in the Core Worlds region of the galaxy, within the Corellian sector. Phemis was the only planet where rubat crystals, a type of kyber crystal, could be found. The crystal was historically used by the Jedi Order to craft lightsabers during the Old Republic. Phemis was only sparsely inhabited, due to its harsh terrain. Overall, the planet only had a population of approximately ten thousand, largely made up of mining settlements and a military garrison.

properties.name: Phibia
properties.description: Phibia was a planet located in the Haserian sector of the Mid Rim.

properties.name: Phindar
properties.description: Phindar was a planet in the Outer Rim Territories, near the Mandalore sector. It was controlled by a criminal organization, the Syndicat, until 44 BBY, when it was overthrown by the Jedi Knights Qui-Gon Jinn and Obi-Wan Kenobi. The Phindians then elected a Governor. The planet was orbited by Phindar Station, which was twice attacked by the Confederacy of Independent Systems in 20 BBY, during the Clone Wars. It was here that, in 19 BBY, Dark Jedi Asajj Ventress confronted Yoda, Jedi Knights Maks Leem and Jai Maruk, and their respective Padawans "Scout"  and Whie Malreaux while they were en route to Vjun.

properties.name: Phinel's Folly
properties.description: Phinel's Folly was a small moon located in the Auril sector, in the Outer Rim Territories.

properties.name: Pho Ph'eah
properties.description: Pho Ph'eah was a mountainous world in the Outer Rim Territories, that served as the homeworld for the four-armed Pho Ph'eahian species. Located far from its star, Pho Ph'eah relied on its heavy natural geothermal activity to provide heat to its native lifeforms. Pho Ph'eahians were naturally adept with technology, and turned Pho Ph'eah into a hub of technological development in the years after contact with the Galactic Republic.

properties.name: Phoebus
properties.description: Phoebus was an Outer Rim planet near Elerion.

properties.name: Phorliss
properties.description: Phorliss was a planet in the Dolomar sector of the Core Worlds that could support almost any kind of life.

properties.name: Phorose
properties.description: Phorose was a planet located in the Colonies.

properties.name: Phosphura Belt Nebula
properties.description: The Phosphura Belt Nebula was a nebula located within the Atravis sector in the Outer Rim region of the galaxy which contained the makeshift starport known as Zirtran's Anchor. The Phosphura Belt Pirates took their name from the nebula.

properties.name: Phracas
properties.description: Phracas was a planet in the Galactic Core.

properties.name: Phraetiss
properties.description: Phraetiss was a planet in the Farrfin sector of the Galactic Core with thick and very tall grasslands.

properties.name: Phu
properties.description: Phu was a world inhabited by the Phuii species of aliens. It was located in the Colonies, near the Aur system. Phu was a planet famous for its gambling industry.

properties.name: Pickerin
properties.description: Pickerin was a planet under the control of the Galactic Empire. In 0 ABY, Pickerin was visited by the Hand of Judgment stormtrooper team after hearing word that the government there had enslaved local artisans.

properties.name: Picutorion
properties.description: Picutorion was a planet which rebelled against the Galactic Empire during the Kwymar Suppressions.

properties.name: Pieldi
properties.description: Pieldi was a planet in the Juvex sector of the Mid Rim. It was a thriving port located at the intersection of the Agarix Trade Route and the Senex-Juvex Loop.

properties.name: Pii
properties.description: Pii was a planet in the Pii system, located near the Gulf of Tatooine. It was the location of the Galactic Empire's Imperial marshaling station Pii. Fourteen years before the Battle of Yavin, an Imperial convoy planned to travel there from Desolation Station, via a moon coreward of the Gulf of Tatooine, and then jump to Sentinel Base and Geonosis. These plans were interrupted, however, when the convoy was attacked by a rebel cell run by former Republic Intelligence Captain Berch Teller.

properties.name: Pil Diller
properties.description: Pil Diller was a forested planet in the Quelii sector of the Outer Rim. According to records, this planet was once home to the extinct singing fig trees.

properties.name: Piluvia
properties.description: The Piluvia system was a star system located within the Torch Nebula, a sector of the Outer Rim Territories. It shared its name with the phenomenon known as the Piluvian salamander-storm.

properties.name: Pinett
properties.description: Pinett was a moon in Elrood sector. It was a mining colony.

properties.name: Pinoora
properties.description: Pinoora was a planet located into the Pinoora system of the Gordian Reach sector between Torque and Selitan. It was located at the junction of the Pinooran Spur and the Junction-Tierell Loop just north of the Denarii Nebula. It served as one of the most strategic trade worlds in the Gordian Reach and was known as an active entertainment hub for spacers between hyperspace jumps.

properties.name: Pirik
properties.description: Pirik was a temperate planet that was located in the Pirik system, in the Divis Arm of the galaxy.

properties.name: Pirin
properties.description: Pirin was a planet in Locris sector. It was the headquarters of Kontag.

properties.name: Piroket
properties.description: Piroket was a trading planet, located within the Arkanis sector of the Outer Rim, controlled by a Bothan shipping company. It had a large population of Hutts and Bothans, which led to many schemes and intrigues. The rebel Riij Winward deposited a stolen droid which contained technical readouts for the Hammertong on the planet.

properties.name: Pirralor
properties.description: Pirralor was a planet located in the Pirralor system of the Juvex sector, in the Mid Rim of the galaxy. It was the homeworld of House Pilor, and its spaceports were thick with outsiders from the Ninth Quadrant and the Agarix sector. Imperial Captain Dor Reder hailed from Pirralor.

properties.name: Pitann
properties.description: Pitann was a desert planet in the Kathol Outback, two days travel from Dayark.

properties.name: Piton
properties.description: The planet Piton was the homeworld of the species Piton. It was affiliated with the Galactic Republic.

properties.name: Pitrillistia
properties.description: Pitrillistia was a remote terrestrial planet situated on the galactic periphery. It was a part of the Pitrillistia system, located in the Mieru'kar sector within the New Territories portion of the Outer Rim Territories. Pitrillistia was the homeworld of the sentient, bipedal Pitrillistian species, members of which spoke a mostly musical language produced by their small wings.

properties.name: Pits of Plooma
properties.description: The Pits of Plooma was a deep space formation near the Galactic Rim. Han Solo once went past there while delivering rock ivory to Grambo.

properties.name: Pizilis
properties.description: Pizilis was a gas giant–type planet. It was located within the Pizilis system of the Terr'skiar sector, a part of the Kashyyyk Region in the Slice portion of the Mid Rim. The Dauntless Run hyperlane connected the planet to the world of Rorgam while the hyperspace route known as the Nightroad linked Pizilis to the worlds of Mytaranor and Terr'skiar.

properties.name: Pizkoss
properties.description: Pizkoss was a planet in the Core sector. Two months after Order 66, the Uhumele stopped there to get a new transponder, and Janks was taken into custody by stormtroopers.

properties.name: Pkihantri
properties.description: Pkihantri was a planet in the Core and the site of a Rebel base. The base was destroyed following an Imperial infiltration using a SB-20 Slicer Droid.

properties.name: Pleem's Nexus
properties.description: Pleem's Nexus was a planet located in the Mid Rim.

properties.name: Pleida
properties.description: Pleida was a planet located in the Tovosh system of the Outer Rim Territories.

properties.name: Plesstil
properties.description: Plesstil was an astronomical object located in the Plesstil system, a part of the Outer Rim Territories' Veragi sector. A hyperlane linked Plesstil to the Veragi system as well as the northern reaches of the galaxy.

properties.name: Plexis
properties.description: Plexis was an astronomical object located in the Plexis system, a part of the Southern Core portion of the Core Worlds. The home offices of House Neuvalis, a chapter house of the Bounty Hunters' Guild, were located on Plexis, leading to the celestial body being considered the homeworld of the house. Plexis was listed as the Neuvalis headquarters in an entry for the house included in the Bounty Hunters Guild Handbook.

properties.name: Ploo
properties.description: Ploo was an astronomical object located in the galaxy's Expansion Region.

properties.name: Plooriod
properties.description: Plooriod may refer to any of the following:

properties.name: Plunder Moon
properties.description: Plunder Moon was a moon in the Unknown Regions, located in the Plunder Moon system within the Black Hole sector. It contained an Infinity Gate.

properties.name: Plympto
properties.description: Plympto was the primary star of the Plympto system.

properties.name: Poderis
properties.description: Poderis was a planet in the Orus sector of the Inner Rim.

properties.name: Polanis
properties.description: Polanis was an agriworld in the Core Worlds of the galaxy, within the Corellian sector. It was known for the Polanis ale and the Polanis Wine produced on the planet.

properties.name: Polis Massa
properties.poi: Polis Massa Research Base, The Local Dig,
properties.description: Polis Massa was once an arid, habitable, barren planetoid and originally the homeworld of the origin of the little-known Eellayin civilization, which dwelt in underground cities such as Wiyentaah. Polis Massa was later struck by a mysterious cataclysm. This natural disaster destroyed the planet and formed a field of asteroids which remained known as Polis Massa, especially the largest of them. The Eellayin civilization disappeared.

properties.name: Pollillus
properties.description: Pollillus was a Core Worlds planet. It was the homeworld of the two-headed sentient Troigs, including the famous sportscaster Fodesinbeed Annodue. By 32 BBY, the planet had only recently been discovered by the galactic community. A decade later, HoloNet News reported on the efforts of one of the heads of the Pollillus Troig Dwuirsintabb to become surgically separated from the other head.

properties.name: Polmanar
properties.description: Polmanar was a textile-manufacturing world located in the Anoat sector of the Greater Javin region. In addition to textiles, farmers on-planet grew reedug narcotic among Polmanar's warm hills.

properties.name: Polneye
properties.description: Polneye was a Grannan colony world in the Farlax sector, established under the Galactic Empire. It was taken over by the Yevetha during the Yevethan Purge, then admitted as an empty world to the New Republic as a memorial to the Yevethan atrocities.

properties.name: Polomie
properties.description: Polomie was a terrestrial astronomical object located in the Polomie system, a part of the Mid Rim's Oriolan sector. During the Galactic Civil War, a Rebel Alliance stronghold was located on Polomie.

properties.name: Polus
properties.description: Polus was an ice world orbiting the binary star Avindia of the Avindia system in the Outer Rim Territories. A frigid, mountainous planet, it had a massive frozen ocean and blizzards as well as ice storms that would frequently scour the planet's surface. Its average day temperature was 50 degrees below freezing. Polus was the homeworld of the Pyn'gani, a near-Human species.

properties.name: Porchello
properties.description: Porchello was a planet in the Elbaran sector of the Mid Rim.

properties.name: Porpor
properties.description: The Porpor system was located in the Grohl sector, a part of the Slice portion of the Outer Rim Territories. It was home to the sentient species known as Porporites, which was exterminated by Gank mercenaries in 4800 BBY.

properties.name: Port Bianco
properties.description: Port Bianco was a shadowport on Lammax.

properties.name: Port Evokk
properties.description: Port Evokk was the homeworld of con artist and gambler Tord Gamb. The locals of this planet would use the hides of the native Ansmul to make boots and jackets. The bounty hunter Sirenas Firil worked with a small guild out of Port Evokk.

properties.name: Port Jerrell
properties.description: Port Jerrell was a planet located in the Outer Rim Territories.

properties.name: Porus Vida
properties.description: Porus Vida was a planet located in the Inner Rim and famous for its beauty and its culture. Despite its reputation as a peaceful world of museums, Porus Vida saw conflict throughout its history, including several sieges during the Alsakan Conflicts, and was devatasted by the Imperial Remnant in 12 ABY.

properties.name: Poseidenna
properties.description: The Poseidenna system was a star system located in Mon Calamari Space, within the Slice portion of the Outer Rim Territories. It lay at the terminus of a hyperlane branching off from the Minntooine system, where the Giblim Route and Minntooine Spur converged.

properties.name: Pothor
properties.description: Pothor was a planet in the Mid Rim. During the Galactic Civil War between the Galactic Empire and the Alliance to Restore the Republic, the Alliance was forced to retreat from its failed Mid Rim Offensive, an operation by the Alliance and the Mid Rim revolutionaries to take control of the Mid Rim. The Alliance was forced to retreat from many worlds including Jeyell, Durkteel, Ord Tiddell, Charros IV, and Trasse. Several revolutionaries evacuated with Alliance forces, although many remained on their planets to harass the Empire, who was expected to take quick control over the former Alliance territories. The Imperial II-class Star Destroyer Overseer participated in an engagement at Pothor, that won it distinction.

properties.name: Pouffra
properties.description: Pouffra was a planet in the Rolion sector of the Outer Rim.

properties.name: Povanaria
properties.description: Povanaria was a planet in the Gordian Reach. It was located on the Junction-Tierell Loop, between Durgen's Star and Bronsoon. Povanaria was windswept, and most of the world was covered by low grasses and mosses. It was also home to a sentient species, the Povanarians.

properties.name: Poviduze
properties.description: The Poviduze system was a star system located in the Expansion Region.

properties.name: Poytta
properties.description: Poytta was a planet in Hutt Space used by many slavers and smugglers as a refueling stop. It also served as Tuga SalPivo's base of operations.

properties.name: Pozzi
properties.description: The Pozzi system was a star system located in the Tapani sector's Mecetti Province, on the Leozi Route.

properties.name: Praesitlyn
properties.poi: Intergalactic Communications Center, , Eliey, Izable, Judlie, Kaudine,
properties.description: Praesitlyn was a planet in the Sluis sector of the Outer Rim. It was the location of the Intergalactic Communications Center, a major HoloNet hub in the galaxy. The Communications Center became a strategic asset during the Clone Wars, leading to the fierce Battle of Praesitlyn.

properties.name: Praidaw
properties.description: Praidaw was the planet where the Fallanassi parents of Akanah first met.

properties.name: Prakith
properties.poi: Andeddu's Keep, Asonel Caves, Citadel Inquisitorius, Geddis mine, Herkeath mine, Mother Lode Cantina, Rilkean mine, Work Zone sector,
properties.description: Prakith was a mountainous fortress world located in the Prakith system of the Deep Core that, thanks to its unstable terrain and its isolation, was a difficult location to conquer by force. The planet was a powerful Sector 5 fortress world during the Galactic Civil War and later the personal empire of Moff Foga Brill.

properties.name: Pral
properties.description: Pral was a planet that was conquered by the Imperial forces under the command of General Bentilais san Sk'ar. It is possible that the planet was located near the Jahilid Drift.

properties.name: Praven Prime
properties.description: Praven Prime was a planet that contained the nations of L'Xing and the Gu-vandi Collective. It is strongly implied that the Gu-vandi Collective controlled the star system containing Praven Prime itself. The two nations were incited into a civil war by HK-47 at some point after 3959 BBY, a conflict lasting many years, and continuing at least up until the re-emergence of the Jedi Exile . The civil war forced the Republic out of Gu-vandi space, and the planet itself seceded from Republic control, which was viewed by many as the most practical step—maintaining a diplomatic and military presence there would have been token gestures of control, at best.

properties.name: Praxlis
properties.description: Praxlis was a planet within the area of space that the Galactic Empire assigned to Black Sword Command.

properties.name: Praya
properties.poi: Sea Base 2000, Sea Castle Resort Hotel, Unidentified sunken ship ,
properties.description: Praya was an ocean planet located in the Praya system, within the Clacis sector of the galaxy's Outer Rim Territories. By the year 4.3 ABY, it was home to the luxurious Sea Castle Resort Hotel. The Star Tours travel agency facilitated transit to Praya through their Deluxe Undersea Package.

properties.name: Prazhi
properties.poi: Cantinas, Docking areas, Refueling stations, Repair shops,
properties.description: Prazhi was an Expansion Region planet located in the Cyrillian Protectorate. It was the homeworld of the Zexx species. A member of the galactic community since at least 5000 BBY, a millennium later Prazhi was situated on an important hyperspace trade route. By the time of the Galactic Empire's reign, Prazhi had become a trade world the economy of which was revitalized by Imperial efforts to resettle the Expansion Region.

properties.name: Prefsbelt
properties.description: Prefsbelt IV, also known simply as Prefsbelt was a planet of the Outer Rim Territories that housed a naval academy.

properties.name: Prekaz
properties.description: Prekaz was a planet in the Core Worlds.

properties.name: Presbalin
properties.description: Presbalin was a planet in the southern Gordian Reach, across the Denarii Nebula from such worlds as Pinoora, Yavin Prime and Torque. It was located on the Junction-Tierell Loop and was part of the Loop Worlds. Presbalin became one of the Loop Worlds' primary commercial hubs after Humans settled onto the planet. It was discovered to be dotted with abandoned alien cities with strange architecture.

properties.name: Presteen
properties.description: Presteen was a trade world located in the Presteen system of the Senex sector, a part of the Senex-Juvex region in the Western Reaches portion of the Mid Rim. The Senex-Juvex Loop hyperlane linked it to the Caltinia and Veron systems. Presteen was under the control of the lesser nobles of House Araba, based on the nearby planet of Cyimarra.

properties.name: Prexiar
properties.description: Prexiar was a planet in the Steniplis sector of the Outer Rim.

properties.name: Pria
properties.description: Pria was an aquatic planet located within the Pria system and was considered one of the Core Worlds.

properties.name: Prildaz
properties.description: Prildaz was the Yevethan name of the third planet in the ILC-905 system in the Farlax sector in the Galactic Core. It was a barren dustball orbited by the Imperial shipyard Black Nine. The New Republic defeated the Yevethan defense of Black Nine.

properties.name: Primtara
properties.description: Primtara was a location in the galaxy.

properties.name: Prine
properties.description: Prine was a mostly-uninhabited desert-covered planet situated on the way between Telerath and Vondarc. It also possessed grasslands where agriculture was possible.

properties.name: Priole Danna
properties.description: The Priole Danna Festival was a celebration of parades and music in Gryle City on the planet Lamuir IV in Tapani sector's Freeworlds Territory. Held annually, it began in 2367 BBY. In 23 BBY, the master of ceremonies was Diva Arroquitas. In 22 BBY, Arroquitas refused to travel during the Separatist Crisis, and there was speculation the festival would be canceled. The Festival Director, Eizzam Stachrini, claimed the festival would carry on without the Diva, but it was eventually canceled after several artists withdrew.

properties.name: Prishardia
properties.description: Prishardia was a backwater agriworld that was located on the Outer Rim Territories of the galaxy near Chad.

properties.name: Prishella
properties.description: Prishella was a celestial body located in the regions known as the Outer Rim Territories and the Slice, in grid square T-10 of the Standard Galactic Grid. It was connected by the Pabol Sleheyron hyperspace route to the astronomical objects Formos and Little Kessel.

properties.name: Procopia
properties.poi: Estalle Island, Lalos Island, Destato Island, Crispos Isle,
properties.description: Procopia was a planet located in the Tapani sector, on the Procopian Shipping Lane. It was one of the wealthiest worlds in the Tapani sector. It was the sector capital since Shey Tapani united the Tapani sector, and remained the capital when the sector joined the Galactic Republic.

properties.name: Prospera Jang
properties.description: Prospera Jang was a planet located in the Kurost sector of the Mid Rim.

properties.name: Protazk
properties.description: Protazk was a planet in the Kwymar sector of the Outer Rim Territories.

properties.name: Protobranch
properties.description: Protobranch was the homeworld of the Bivall species. During the latter years of the Galactic Republic, the Bivall business mogul Usk Haffa was the largest owner of commercial real estate on Protobranch.

properties.name: Protogeyser
properties.description: Protogeyser was an astronomical object located in the Inner Rim's Protogeyser system. Known to the wider galaxy by the Ruusan Reformation of 1000 BBY, the fractal urchins, a non-sentient species that lacked cellular structures and thus midi-chlorians, life-forms that lived symbiotically inside cells and allowed their symbiont to detect the Force, originated from Protogeyser. This distinction earned the fractal urchins, along with Protogeyser, a mention in the "Galactic Bestiary" section of the Jedi trainee guidebook The Jedi Path: A Manual for Students of the Force, where the Jedi biologist Bowspritz used the species as an example of animals that were connected to the Force despite their lack of midi-chlorians.

properties.name: Proxima Dibal
properties.description: Proxima Dibal was the primary star of the Proxima Dibal system.

properties.name: Pulassas Minor
properties.description: Pulassas Minor was a terrestrial celestial body located in the Pulassas Minor system, a part of the Outer Rim Territories' Koradin sector. At some point prior to the Battle of Yavin, a Galactic Empire TIE fighter squadron was ordered to bombard civilian targets on Pulassas Minor. Horrified of the order, the squadron's pilot Nozzo Naytaan deserted from the Imperial Military, going on to join the Empire's enemy in the Galactic Civil War, the Rebel Alliance.

properties.name: Puloorn
properties.description: Puloorn was a snow-covered planet located in the Outer Rim Territories's Spinward sector. It was the site of an ancient, ruined Sith temple that was inhabited both by creatures twisted by the dark side of the Force and by a group of cultists. At some point, Galactic Republic's Supreme Chancellor Palpatine dispatched a team of agents on a mission to investigate the rumored existence of Puloorn's temple.

properties.name: Purnham
properties.description: Purnham was a planet that was the target of attacks by BloodScar. It was located in the Purnham system and along the Purnham Run.

properties.name: Pursin
properties.description: Pursin was a planet home to the Pursian species, that was constantly at war with Yugami and its inhabitants.

properties.name: Pusat Station
properties.description: Pusat Station was a space station on the Mid Rim's Lesser Lantillian Route, in the Bortele Cluster. The M'hendosat berthed there in 0 ABY.

properties.name: Pybus
properties.description: Pybus was a planet located in the Bootana Hutta region of Hutt Space.

properties.name: Pygorix
properties.description: Pygorix was a planet in the Gordian Reach of the Outer Rim Territories.

properties.name: Pyjridj
properties.description: Pyjridj was a planet where a pickpocket once told Lando Calrissian that four out of every five belt pouches he stole contained passcodes, and it typically took less than a minute to find them.

properties.name: Pypin
properties.description: Pypin was one of the Trianii colony worlds within the disputed border of the Corporate Sector.

properties.name: Pyros
properties.description: Pyros, originally known as Ord Pyros, was a planet located in the Colonies.

properties.name: Pzandias
properties.description: Pzandias was a planet. During the Clone Wars, the Confederacy of Independent Systems established a training facility on the world.

properties.name: Pzob
properties.poi: Pzob Forest Battle Yard, Stormtrooper base,
properties.description: Pzob was a planet in the Herios sector of the Outer Rim Territories, settled by Gamorreans from the world of Gamorr a long period of time prior to the Battle of Yavin. The settlers, organized into various clans, constantly waged war on each other. All other concerns were secondary to the fighting, and as a result Pzob's inhabitants had a nearly non-existent relationship with advanced technology. The planet was covered in dark, dense forests with tall trees, an environment that greatly appealed to the colonists. Pzob's remote location, combined with the relative primitiveness of its inhabitants, led to it being considered a backwater world. However, this also contributed to the planet going untouched by all major galactic conflicts.

properties.name: Q'Maere
properties.description: Q'Maere was a planet located within the Kathol Rift. The planet had a deadly, poisonous atmosphere, full of chlorine, and the sky was a sickly green. The majority of the surface was a caustic ammonia ocean interspersed with volcanic salt-caked islands. The planet was the location of the Q'Maere Research Facility.

properties.name: Q'mara
properties.description: Q'mara, located in the Q'mara system of the Juvex sector, was a desert planet with a number of shabby spaceports, where all manner of smugglers and thugs sought illicit employment. Juvex nobles frequented Q'mara's houses of ill repute; foolish ones were drawn into its subterranean gambling and spice dens, sometimes never to return. Qellrin was attacked by pirates near Q'mara.

properties.name: Qalita Prime
properties.description: Qalita Prime was a planet located in the Inner Rim that was represented in the New Republic Senate. The Right Earl was the leader of this planet.

properties.name: Qalydon
properties.description: Qalydon was a planet in the Outer Rim.

properties.name: Qaras
properties.description: Qaras was the homeworld of the Jessar species as well as the Minyavish. In 44 ABY, the Minyavish were revolted against by the Jessar, led by Rokari Kem. The Minyavish were then forced to leave the planet. Qaras was then accepted into the Galactic Alliance, with Rokari Kem serving as the planet's Senator.

properties.name: Qat Chrystac
properties.poi: New Republic outpost, Imperial orbital siege platform
properties.description: Qat Chrystac was a volatile, radioactive, and volcanic world that was a point of contention between Rebel  and Imperial forces for over ten years.

properties.name: Qeimet
properties.description: Qeimet was a location in the galaxy's Juris sector. In 3 ABY, the Galactic Empire's Death Squadron was stationed near Qeimet when they received news from an Imperial probe droid of a Rebel Alliance base on Hoth.

properties.name: Qexis
properties.description: Qexis was a planet located in the Outer Rim Territories. It was a high-security research planet with only one spaceport. Few knew it existed.

properties.name: Qi Lozar
properties.description: Qi Lozar was a desert world that was located in the Grumani sector, in the Outer Rim Territories. It served as a haven for hermits, refugees and other individuals who were trying to escape their pasts.

properties.name: Qiaxx
properties.description: Qiaxx was a planet in the Cor'ric sector of the Outer Rim Territories.

properties.name: Qiilura
properties.description: Qiilura was a temperate planet in the Mid Rim, 40 light-years away from Ord Mantell. It was the home world of the Gurlanins—a race of shapeshifting intelligent predators, but by the time of the Clone Wars, Human colonization had been well established, with a population of two hundred thousand farmers. The economy of the planet mostly revolved around agriculture, specifically the production of barq, kushayan, and other luxury foodstuffs, merlie meat was a known export and source of income and food for the farmers of this planet. Qiilura produced a large proportion of the luxury foodstuffs and beverages in the galaxy. However, the planet was controlled by the Neimoidian merchant Lik Ankkit who passed little of the profit on to the farmers, thus most inhabitants lived in squalor and would sell information and outlaws to the warlord Ghez Hokan and his militia for a couple of credits or a bottle of urrqal.

properties.name: Qina
properties.description: Qina was a cool, lush moon that orbited the planet Hanchin of the Outer Rim Territories' Moddell sector. It featured forests, mountain peaks, and river valleys on its surface and was home to the creatures known as dochinie, pech, and rujo. Qina was inhabited by approximately two million Humans as well as members of the Ayrou and Vashan species, and Qinan landholders kept herds of the local pechs and rujos.

properties.name: Qixoni Nebula
properties.description: The Qixoni Nebula was located in the Southern Core portion of the Colonies. The nebula shared its name with the Qixoni crystals, a type of crystal that had formed on a planet before its star exploded as a supernova and destroyed it millennia before 3951 BBY.

properties.name: Qlothos
properties.description: Qlothos was a cloudy planet. It was attacked by TIE Bombers sent from the Interrogator when it was thought to hold a Rebel garrison.

properties.name: Qonto
properties.description: The Qonto were a sentient species from the Qonto system, which was located in Wild Space just outside the Braxant sector. Although generally not known for their perception, some exceptional Qonto had senses considerably sharper than the Human standard. During the Galactic Civil War, Lina Adonais was a Qonto space urchin who worked aboard the Kuari Princess, a giant luxury liner, while she traveled the galaxy. She considered joining the Alliance to Restore the Republic, and while on a tour of the Relgim Run, she encountered a group of Rebels disguised as Anomids. She immediately saw through their disguise and questioned them about what they were doing aboard the Princess. Adonais was also present on the cruise when it was attacked by pirates while passing through the Maelstrom.

properties.name: Qoribu
properties.description: Qoribu was a ringed gas giant in the Gyuel system with 55 moons, including Jwlio, Eyyl, Zvbo, Ruu, Nrogu, and Kr.

properties.name: Qotile
properties.description: Qotile was a planet that was devastated by the Stark Hyperspace Conflict.

properties.name: Qretu
properties.description: Qretu was the primary star of the Qretu system in the Inner Rim.

properties.name: Quadrant Seven
properties.description: Quadrant Seven was a planet which was not part of the Galactic Republic. The planet's last war took place in about 612 BBY. It was a rocky world with canyons, caves, and hills.

properties.name: Quaensan Prime
properties.description: Quaensan Prime was a Gendius sector, Mid Rim world on the Cerean Reach, near the Jiroch system. Its inhabitants were wiped out by the Reslian Purge, similar to what happened to the Tunroth.

properties.name: Quamar
properties.description: The Quamar system was located in the Bruanii sector, a part of the Western Reaches portion of the Mid Rim. The super-hyperroute known as the Corellian Trade Spine linked it to the Mugaar system as well as the Jiroch system in the Yushan sector. The Quamar system shared its name with the luxury liner Quamar Messenger.

properties.name: Quanducial
properties.description: Quanducial was an Outer Rim planet known to the wider galaxy by the last millennium of the Galactic Republic. It was located in the Quanducial system of Gordian Reach at the galactic grid coordinates of Q-6.

properties.name: Quanton
properties.description: Quanton was a terrestrial astronomical object located in the Quanton system, a part of the Obtrexta sector in the New Territories portion of the Outer Rim Territories. During the Galactic Civil War, Rebel Alliance General Airen Cracken was captured by the Imperial Security Bureau of the Galactic Empire on Quanton. Cracken was subsequently subjected to the truth serum Bavo Six and later mentioned both his capture and his experience with Bavo Six in the Cracken's Rebel Field Guide, a datafile he had composed that documented various pieces of equipment utilized by Rebel Alliance agents.

properties.name: Quarzite
properties.description: Quarzite was a planet composed of crystalline caves and with a surface that was strained by strong atmospheric pressure, with the ability to crush starships and flatten beings. During the Clone Wars, the planet was ruled by the tyrannical Belugan Otua Blank, who was involved in a battle with the natives on the planet, the Kage Warriors.

properties.name: Quas Killam
properties.description: Quas Killam was a planet on the edge of the Mid Rim. Its people were the Killam. Quas Killam was a world of weapons manufacturing factories and trinium mines, and so was conquered by the Trade Federation early in the Clone Wars. Throughout the war the planet changed sides several times.

properties.name: Queel
properties.poi: Queel Republic forward command postQueel Confederate base
properties.description: Queel was a swamp-covered Mid Rim planet. The planet was one of the many worlds to see action in the early months of the Clone Wars.In 22 BBY it was the site of a battle between the Galactic Republic and the Confederacy of Independent Systems.

properties.name: Quelii
properties.description: Quelii was a planet in the Outer Rim Territories, which maintained a population of Humans who lived in villages. Quelii was devastated by a Mandalorian attack in the years leading up to the Mandalorian Wars, although some natives managed to escape the onslaught and make it to Republic space. One of these refugees grew to become the infamous Dark Lord of the Sith Darth Malak, who led a Sith army against the Republic in the Jedi Civil War.

properties.name: Quell
properties.description: Quell was the principal planet of the Quell system in the Outer Rim.

properties.name: Quellor
properties.description: Quellor was a planet in the Colonies region of the galaxy.

properties.name: Quermia
properties.description: Quermia was a terraformed planet and the homeworld of the Quermian species. It was located near the end of the Perlemian Trade Route.

properties.name: Ques
properties.description: Ques was a planet in the Ques system in Hutt Space. It was a motley spaceport planet at the edge of Hutt Space, typically used by ships heading for the Si'Klaata Cluster. Outlanders landing at Ques were interrogated extensively.

properties.name: Quesaya
properties.description: Quesaya could refer to one of the following:

properties.name: Quesh
properties.description: Queshː  was a world riddled with toxic waste within Hutt Space, due to a period of geological instability in the past dubbed the Quake. It was discovered by the Galactic Republic during the Great War, but was promptly abandoned due to its poisonous atmosphere.

properties.name: Questal
properties.description: Questal was a planet in Questal sector, infamous during the Galactic Civil War as the stronghold of the sadistic Moff Bandor.

properties.name: Quethold
properties.description: Quethold was a planet located in the Unknown Regions. It was also the homeworld of the insectoid Quesoth species, and Quesoth resided within three cities on the world: the Black City, the Red City and the White City. In about 8 ABY, the Queen of the Red, the reigning Quesoth Queen, allied herself with the alien warlord Nuso Esva. However, the planet was subsequently attacked by the Empire of the Hand, who defeated the Quesoth and killed Esva.

properties.name: Queyta
properties.description: Queyta was a planet in the Outer Rim's Danjar sector.

properties.name: Quian
properties.description: Quian was a planet with a sizable Human population. Natives were known to have light brown hair, aqua-green eyes, and extremely dark skin. Natives of Quian were called Quians.

properties.name: Quilken
properties.description: Quilken was a planet located within the Quilken system of the Outer Rim Territories. After Mungo Baobab, heir of the Baobab Merchant Fleet and Auren Yomm, a girl from the planet Roon got married, the couple settled on Quilken. They found new sources of roonstones on the planet and set up facilities to process it. The also opened the Club Baobab casino for visitors to the nearby Roon system. The security of the facilities was increased to guard the precious gems. Mungo was busy arranging roonstone shipments to planet Sim'char'ser and other Outer Rim worlds.

properties.name: Quint
properties.description: Quint was the Quint homeworld.

properties.name: Quintar Nebula
properties.description: The Quintar Nebula was a nebula once navigated by Tron Nixx using the Force.

properties.name: Quockra
properties.description: Quockra was the Quockra system's primary star.

properties.name: Quooria
properties.description: Quooria was a terrestrial astronomical object located in the Quooria system, a part of the Farstey sector in the Trans-Hydian portion of the Expansion Region. It was the homeworld of the Quoorian marshsucker, a species of creature similar to, but much more deadlier than mosquitos. In addition, creatures that were related to Quoorian marshsuckers eventually went extinct on Quooria and became preserved in the sap of the celestial body's trees.

properties.name: Quyste
properties.description: Qusyte was a planet in the Quyste system within the Thesme sector of the Outer Rim Territories on which Talon Karrde had a training center. The smuggler sent H'sishi there before 18 ABY to study starship operations.

properties.name: R-Duba
properties.poi: Red Asteroid Bar, The Droid Store,
properties.description: R-Duba was a desert and ocean planet located in the R-Duba system, within the Quiberon sector of the galaxy's Outer Rim Territories. A minor trade world, it was located in a backwater province of the Galactic Empire.

properties.name: R'alla
properties.description: R'alla was a planet in the Corporate Sector, located on the Solenbaran Merchant Route between Bonadan and Kir. R'alla was home to many of the Corporate Sector Authority's top media companies, and its lush, green landscape had many farms and bubbling water springs. R'alla mineral water—which was found in underground caverns below a mountain town also called R'alla— was widely exported throughout the Corporate Sector and beyond, and was often smuggled to nearby, drought-ridden Rampa II. The short route between R'alla and Rampa II was heavy policed by Authority gunships, and was popularly referred to as the Rampa Rapids.

properties.name: R'terleD'er
properties.description: R'terleD'er was a planet located in the Kriz sector of the Outer Rim Territories.

properties.name: Raamen
properties.description: Raamen was a planet located in the Expansion Region.

properties.name: Vladet
properties.description: Vladet was a planet in the Colonies. It was the sector capital of Rachuk sector. An Imperial base was located on Grand Isle. Without vaccination, any visitor to the planet would catch Rachuk Roseola. When Rogue Squadron attacked the planet, Imperial Admiral Devlia was killed.

properties.name: Radama Void
properties.description: The Radama Void was an area of the galaxy that surrounded the planet of Ord Radama. It was once at the western edge of Xim's empire. It was separated from the Sith Worlds by the Stygian Caldera.

properties.name: Raddan
properties.description: Raddan was a planet in the galaxy.

properties.name: Radnor
properties.description: Radnor was a small, sea-covered planet with a small main landmass, and prevailing winds. It was located in the same system as Avon. Radnor had two capitals: the Twin Cities of  Aubendo and Tacto. Each of the cities had their own governing ministers. Radnor was known for its research and development of high-tech weapons systems.

properties.name: Rafa
properties.description: Rafa IV was a temperate planet in the Rafa system of the Centrality, located in the Outer Rim Territories. It was a colony world of the Sharu species.

properties.name: Rafft
properties.description: Rafft was a planet in the Inner Rim.

properties.name: Rago
properties.description: Rago was a planet located near the border of Wild Space and the Mid Rim that anchored the Rago Run to the Unknown Regions. It was the closest Galactic Alliance planet to the Colony of the Killiks.

properties.name: Ragoon
properties.description: The Ragoons were the native sentient species of the planet Ragoon VI. A short species with brown, leathery skin, they had long and pointed ears. Ragoon society was pre-industrial, as the species preferred to keep the environment of their homeworld pristine and free from exploitation. In order to achieve that, they forbade colonization of Ragoon VI, and, when their numbers dwindled through sickness, entrusted their planet to the Galactic Republic Senate for safekeeping. Offworld visitors were then restricted, although members of the Jedi Order and the inhabitants of the neighboring planet Aaeton were allowed to visit more frequently. The Jedi Qui-Gon Jinn and Obi-Wan Kenobi encountered a group of Ragoons during a training mission to the world.

properties.name: Rainboh
properties.description: Rainboh was a terrestrial planet located in the Rainboh system of the Inner Rim's Hapes Cluster. Positioned among the Hapan Rim Worlds, Rainboh could be reached from the Great Rim Route or the Rynmar Trail hyperlanes via the planet Rynmar itself.

properties.name: Rainbow Nebulae
properties.description: The multicolored Rainbow Nebulae were located "between Naboo and nowhere."

properties.name: Rainos Cluster
properties.description: The Rainos Cluster was a strategic location in the Expansion Region. The Galactic Empire placed a Baas-class space station there, to serve as a deep-space supply depot.

properties.name: Raithal
properties.description: Raithal was a planet in the Colonies, on the Perlemian Trade Route near the border with the Inner Rim.

properties.name: Rakaa
properties.description: The Rakaa system was a Core system that contained the planet Rakaa IV.

properties.name: Rakata Prime
properties.description: Rakata Prime, also known as Lehon, was the homeworld of the long-extinct Rakata species, who were rumored to be the first to develop hyperspace travel, and was one of the few navigable worlds located in the Unknown Regions. At some point, the Resistance pilot Venisa Doza visited the planet along with her astromech droid, Torch. The Zabrak pirate Tryki was also once arrested for attempting to board a First Order cruiser near Rakata Prime.

properties.name: Rakhuuun
properties.description: Rakhuuun was a planet that was located in the Rakhuuun system of the Mytaranor sector. It was a part of the Kashyyyk Region, in the Slice portion of the Mid Rim. The Randon Run hyperlane connected the planet to the worlds of Chamble and Kashyyyk.

properties.name: Rakrir
properties.description: Rakrir was the homeworld of the Rakririan species. A highly refined and meticulous species, few left their homeworld, finding the rest of the galaxy to be too unsophisticated. The planet was sometimes known as Ballikite.

properties.name: Ralltiir
properties.poi: Cambriele Exploration Auditorium, Grallia Spaceport, High Ontis,
properties.description: Ralltiir was a planet in the Ralltiir system of the Darpa sector in the Core Worlds. The second planet in orbit of the star Rallt, Ralltiir had twenty-eight moons and three continents that wrapped around the planet. A major financial center in the galactic economy, Ralltiir was a member world of the Galactic Republic but remained largely neutral in galactic politics to ensure that the finances of its inhabitants remained safe from political influences and war. Located in the Ringali Shell, a string of planets along the Perlemian Trade Route that lay near the Ringali Nebula, Ralltiir was one of the only planets in the Darpa sector to remain independent from the Esselian Empire. Besides its financial services, Ralltiir was also a major source of marble, as the planet's mountain ranges featured large deposits of marble and were riddled with quarries, and its population of 10 billion sentients was almost entirely Humans.

properties.name: Ralme
properties.description: The Ralme system was a system in Brak sector of the Expansion Region. It contained at least four planets, including Ralme IV, where Lant Mining Corporation conducted surface, underground, and asteroid mining operations to extract metals.

properties.name: Raltac
properties.description: Raltac may refer to one of the following:

properties.name: Ramoa
properties.description: Ramoa was a planet, and the homeworld of the Ramoan species, including Bazel Warv, a Jedi Knight.

properties.name: Ramodi
properties.description: Ramodi was a Galactic Alliance planet with a baradium smuggling ring, rimward of Borao.

properties.name: Ramook
properties.description: Ramook was an agriworld located just beyond the far end of the Chiloon Rift.

properties.name: Rampa
properties.description: Rampa II, also known as Rampa, was an astronomical object in the Corporate Sector of the Outer Rim Territories, connected to Panna in the Cronese Mandate by the smugglers' hyperlane Bubble Wink. The former pirate Queen Maz Kanata marked it as a point of interest on a map she included in the book that would become known as the Smuggler's Guide.

properties.name: Ramsir
properties.description: Ramsir may refer to one of the following:

properties.name: Randa
properties.description: Randa was a planet in the Outer Rim which hosted a small Rebel base during the Galactic Civil War. That led it to be targeted by Imperial Admiral Gaen Drommel, who decimated the Rebels on Randa during the war.

properties.name: Randon
properties.description: Randon was a planet from which the Randoni originated. It was a large business world with crowded bazaars and elegant corporate towers. It was at the intersection with several major trade routes, including the Trax Tube, Ootmian Pabol, Pabol Sleheyron, and the Randon Run.

properties.name: Rangorah
properties.description: Rangorah was a planet in the Outer Rim's Calaron sector and the location of the Event Horizon cantina.

properties.name: Ranklinge
properties.description: Ranklinge was a planet in the Shelsha sector of the Colonies.

properties.name: Rannon
properties.description: Rannon was a forested planet that was located in the Outer Rim Territories' Instrop sector. It was settled centuries before the reign of the New Republic and was inhabited by a population of ten million Humans and Rodians, who governed their settlements via cooperative council.

properties.name: Ranroon
properties.description: Ranroon was a planet located within the Mortex sector of the Outer Rim Territories. It was particularly known for its legendary Queen Indrexu.

properties.name: Rantine Space Station
properties.description: The Rantine Space Station was a space station located in the Tamarin sector of the Outer Rim Territories. Rantine Space Station was located on the edge of the sector, six days hyperspace travel from Kwenn Space Station in the Mid Rim.

properties.name: Raquish
properties.description: Raquish was a planet located in the Lambda sector of the Mid Rim.

properties.name: Rashfond
properties.description: Rashfond was the site of the Battles of Rashfond involving the Jedi Order. During the Clone Wars, the battles were recalled by the architect droid Huyang.

properties.name: Raskane
properties.description: Raskane IV, also known as Raskane Four, was an Expansion Region planet located in the Sepan sector. Political tensions nearly led to a civil war on the planet around 3643 BBY, but the situation was diffused by an individual affiliated with one of the sides in the ongoing struggle between the Galactic Republic and the reconstituted Sith Empire. During the Galactic Civil War, the Rebel Alliance agent Matt Talon once claimed that he had caused the agony and death of an alien on Raskane IV.

properties.name: Rasterous
properties.description: Rasterous was a planet with a shipyard belonging to Kuat Drive Yards.

properties.name: Rata Nebula
properties.description: The Rata Nebula was located in the Unknown Regions inside the core territory of the Chiss Ascendancy, the government of the Chiss species. The nebula contained the Rhigar system, which was linked to the Csaus system by the hyperlane known as the Path of the Houses and to the Csilla and Colonial Station Chaf systems by another hyperspace route.

properties.name: Ratamesh
properties.description: Ratamesh was a terrestrial astronomical object located in the Ratamesh system, a part of the Farstey sector in the Trans-Hydian portion of the Expansion Region. It was the site of the Thisspias alcazar, a structure which shared its name with the Farstey sector planet Thisspias.

properties.name: Rathalay
properties.description: Rathalay was a planet in the Mid Rim known for its vast private beaches. The planet exported Rathalayan firestones.

properties.name: Rattatak
properties.description: Rattatak was an Outer Rim world unknown to the Galactic Republic at the time of the Clone Wars.

properties.name: Ravaath
properties.description: Ravaath was a planet within the Ravaath system in the Pacanth Reach of the Outer Rim Territories.

properties.name: Raxus Prime
properties.poi: Raxus Sewer System, Sienar Refinery, Junk TempleConfederacy base,
properties.description: Raxus Prime, once known as the Circlet of the Tion and Nikato's Shining Gem, was a waste-covered planet in the Raxus system in the Tion Hegemony sector of the Outer Rim Territories. Once a beautiful world of lagoons and islands, over many centuries it became heavily-industrialized, until by the time of the Clone Wars it had become totally covered with toxic debris and had a poisonous surface.

properties.name: Raxxa
properties.description: Raxxa was a planet represented in the New Republic Senate by Dall Thara Dru.

properties.name: Raydonia
properties.description: Raydonia was a planet in the Outer Rim Territories. The Human colonists who lived there were known as Raydonians.

properties.name: Rbollea
properties.description: The Rbollea system was located in the Interior Region, an area of the Hapes Cluster in the Slice portion of the Inner Rim. It was connected via hyperlane to the Tinta system. The Rbollea system was the origin point of the substance known as Rbollean petal-oil.

properties.name: Reaper's World
properties.description: Reaper's World was a planet in the Nilgaard sector. It was the sector capital, colonized c. 5000 BBY; at the time it was idyllic, with green oceans and blue mountains. Nilgaard Bioprocessing used up the planet's natural resources, leaving it in an ice age of glaciers. The planet had urban cityplexes.

properties.name: Rearqu Cluster
properties.description: The Rearqu system, also known as Rearqu 10 and the Rearqu Cluster, was located in the Mid Rim's Taldot sector.

properties.name: Reboam
properties.description: Reboam was a planet located within the Hapes Cluster which was noted for being a small world with a harsh climate that was relatively uninhabited and was comparable to Tatooine.

properties.name: Recopia
properties.poi: Base Delta-Nine, Hinder Market, Mallif Cove, Tuldok Ranch,
properties.description: Recopia was a planet in the Recopi system in the Core Worlds, between the Corellian Run and the Hydian Way. It was the site of the annual Bandercamp Auctions in the Hinder Market.

properties.name: Red Nebula
properties.description: The Red Nebula was a nebula on the outskirts of the galaxy, that was slowly drifting away from the galactic disk. It contained a single inhabited planet, a multitude of stars, and a deadly meteor field. The planet boasted a race of red humanoids with pointed ears, who protected their homeworld from asteroid bombardment with mystical red jewels.

properties.name: Redcap
properties.description: Redcap was a planet that was located in the Outer Rim Territories, situated near Socorro, Tatooine, and Issor. It was a barren, rainy world of fluid mud lakes, mud plains, canyons, and mountains that hosted a small-scale mining colony. The planet was populated by impoverished Human descendants of the mining colonists and lived in settlements at the bases of the mountain chains. Starships would sink in Redcap's thick mud, so landings were made in Tyma Canyon, which ran for several hundred kilometers across the planet's surface. Travel was conducted on olai, beasts of burden originally brought from a nearby moon.

properties.name: The Redoubt
properties.description: The Redoubt, formally the Chiss Redoubt, was a remote star cluster that was located in Chiss space, near the Utegetu Nebula, and that contained at least ten habitable planets and hundreds of stars. Discovered over 200 years prior to 22 ABY and claimed by the Chiss Expansionary Defense Force, the cluster was to be used as a refuge in the event that the Chiss Ascendancy was overrun by any foreign invader. Exploration of the Redoubt by the Chiss only began in earnest around 27 BBY. The Redoubt contained high radiation levels, and the proximity of stars to each other made navigation difficult. There were only a few safe routes into The Redoubt, and they were all guarded by Chiss fortifications, which prevented foreign intrusions. A planetoid in The Redoubt was the resting place of the ill-fated Outbound Flight Project, which crashed there in 27 BBY.

properties.name: Reecee
properties.description: Reecee was a planet in the Inner Rim, located near the Utegetu Nebula.

properties.name: Reega
properties.description: The Reega system was a star system located within the Demetras sector of the Outer Rim Territories.

properties.name: Reena
properties.description: Reena was a planet in Tapani sector's Reena system. It was the capital of Reena Province and throneworld of House Reena. It had a local day of 25 standard hours and a local year of 360 local days. It had warm, shallow oceans and small continents, largely urbanized. It was the location of Reena University. Three HX.6 Turbolaser Batteries on its single moon protected the planet.

properties.name: Refgar
properties.description: Refgar was a planet located within the Refgar system of the Core Worlds.

properties.name: Refnar
properties.description: Refnar was a celestial body located in the Refnar system, a part of the Pakuuni sector in the Slice portion of the Outer Rim Territories. During the early Galactic Civil War, it was the site of a Rebel Alliance base. At some point by 1 BBY, the Galactic Empire discovered the facility and launched an attack on it. During the ensuing confrontation between the Alliance and Imperial forces that became known as the "Last Stand at Refnar," most of the Rebel freighters, troop transports, and starfighters were able to escape from the Refnar system.

properties.name: Refrax
properties.description: Refrax was a planet in the Mortex sector of the Outer Rim Territories. The planet contained an Imperial-controlled spaceport that served as a stop-over point for ships traveling through Mortex sector during the Galactic Civil War.

properties.name: Regellia
properties.description: Regellia was a planet that was located in the Regellia system of the Minos Cluster. It was the homeworld of Lieutenant Nozzo Naytaan, a male Human starfighter pilot in the Rebel Alliance.

properties.name: Reginard
properties.description: Reginard was the location of a hidden Rebel base called Reginard Base.

properties.name: Regolith
properties.description: Regolith was the Regolith system's primary star.

properties.name: Regulgo
properties.description: Regulgo was a planet located in the Regulgo system, a part of the Ryndellian sector within the Mid Rim and Trailing Sectors regions. Months after Han Solo departed Kamar in approximately 2 BBY, Kamarians tracked him down on Regulgo. While there, the Kamarians attacked Solo and took him captive; however, Solo eventually escaped.

properties.name: Rehemsa
properties.description: Rehemsa was a Core Worlds planet.

properties.name: Rehn
properties.description: Rehn VII was a planet located within the Rehn system of Brak sector, situated in the Expansion Region. The world was capable of foodstuff production and had manufacturing capabilities.

properties.name: Reigalius
properties.description: Reigalius was the Reigat homeworld. It was located in the Yucrales Sector of the Mid Rim near Leritor.

properties.name: Rekkiad
properties.poi: Twin Spears, First Spear, Dramath the Second's tomb,
properties.description: Rekkiad was a planet in the remote Rekkiad system, located in the Outer Rim region of the galaxy. A desolate world covered in ice and snow, it was where the Jedi Knights Revan and Malak hid Mandalore's Mask following the Mandalorian Wars.

properties.name: Relarr
properties.description: The Relarr system was a star system located within the Kuat sector in the Core Worlds region of the galaxy. It was near the Kuat system.

properties.name: Relatta
properties.description: Relatta was a location in the galaxy.

properties.name: Relephon
properties.description: Relephon was a gas giant in the Hapes Cluster orbited by the Relephon Moons, of which several were populated.

properties.name: Relkass
properties.description: Relkass was an Outer Rim Territories planet that featured an equatorial region of grasslands. The grasslands were home to the cactus known as the Relkass sentinel plant, which contained a powerful narcotic compound in its juice.

properties.name: Rellio
properties.description: Rellio was a planet in located the Tapani sector's Rellio system.

properties.name: Rellnas
properties.description: The gas giant Rellnas was the sixth planet in the Rell system. Its sole moon, Rellnas Minor, was the homeworld of the Rellarin people.

properties.name: Reltooine
properties.description: Reltooine was a gas giant in the Tingel Arm. It was a part of the Corporate Sector and a member world of the Corporate Sector Authority.

properties.name: Remitik
properties.description: Remitik was a planet located near the Hoth system, in the Outer Rim. In 3 ABY, a Alliance to Restore the Republic repair yard was located near the planet. In preparation for the Battle of Hoth, the Galactic Empire launched an attack on the yard. After the repair yard was destroyed, the Imperial forces ambushed the Rebel craft retreating from Hoth.

properties.name: Remmon Nebula
properties.description: The Remmon Nebula was an orange and red nebula. In 5000 BBY, Jedi Master Relin Druur and his Padawan, Drev Hassin, passed through the nebula in their Infiltrator starfighter while hunting down the Sith Lord Saes Rrogon.

properties.name: Rena
properties.description: Rena was a planet home to the predatory Renan bloodwolves and known for its wine. Imperial Governor Wilek Nereus once visited Rena during his career collecting dental specimens.

properties.name: Renatasia
properties.description: Renatasia was the Renatasia system's primary star. It was a medium-sized yellow star.

properties.name: Rend
properties.description: Telekinesis, abbreviated TK, was a neutral ability that most Force-sensitives had which allowed them to move and otherwise manipulate physical matter in a variety of ways, all with the power of the Force. The ability was virtually ubiquitous among Force-sensitive individuals and organizations, though the techniques could differ greatly. It had a tremendous number of applications, both combative and utilitarian.

properties.name: Rendili
properties.description: Rendili was a planet in the Core Worlds and one of the Core Founders of the Galactic Republic. The planet was ruled by an Arch-Provost. It was the headquarters of Rendili StarDrive, founded in 20,000 BBY, and was affiliated with the starshipwrights Rendili Hyperworks, Rendili/Vanjervalis Drive Yards and Golan Arms joint venture. At some point during the Mandalorian Wars a Republic Military installation housing thousands of troops, vehicles, and starfighters was stationed outside of the major cities, though by the time of the Clone Wars the installation had been all but forgotten.

properties.name: Renforra
properties.description: Renforra was the site of an Alliance to Restore the Republic base during the height of the Galactic Civil War. Jon Vander led the BTL Y-wing starfighters of Specter Squadron from this headquarters.

properties.name: Renillis
properties.description: The Renillis system was located in the Trailing Sectors portion of the Inner Rim. The system lay on the Corellian Trade Spine super-hyperroute, which linked it to the Mechis and Yag'Dhul systems.

properties.name: Rennokk
properties.description: Rennokk was a moon of Cularin. It was a molten planetoid, its glow visible on Cularin. Reidi Artom's survey of the moon indicated there were minerals of interest in the lava of the planet, but nobody had attempted to reach those minerals by 31 BBY.

properties.name: Rentalles
properties.description: Rentalles was a planet located in the D'Astan sector of the Outer Rim Territories.

properties.name: Rentean
properties.description: Rentean was a planet in the Jjannex sector of the Outer Rim Territories.

properties.name: Rentor
properties.description: Rentor was a terrestrial planet located in the  Rentor system of the Unknown Regions' Chiss Space. It was linked via hyperlanes to the Csilla and Jamiron systems. Rentor's surface featured oceans as well as icebergs that slowly cruised the currents of the open seas. The sentient Chiss of the Chiss Ascendancy had colonized Rentor, establishing settlements atop the world's icebergs.

properties.name: Reo
properties.description: Reo was a male Lieutenant Commander in the Galactic Federation of Free Alliances. In 36 ABY, he was serving as part of the engineering staff aboard the Victory I-class Star Destroyer Admiral Ackbar during the blockade of the Utegetu Nebula.

properties.name: Reopi
properties.description: Reopi was a planet in the Core Worlds known for its equatorial deserts. Native creatures included the Reopi sand crusher and the magus, which was hunted for its hide.

properties.name: Repea
properties.description: Repea was an Outer Rim planet near the Cron Drift in the Auril sector. The planet was protected by the Crimson Aces until politicians on the planet feared the squadron might turn on them. The politicians sought aid from the Galactic Empire in razing the Aces' planet-side base.

properties.name: Resh 9376
properties.description: Resh 9376 was a comet in the Outer Rim Territories that was host to a secret shadowport called Point Nadir.

properties.name: Resilon
properties.description: Resilon was a mining world located in the Bortele sector of the Mid Rim.

properties.name: Resti Kel
properties.description: Resti Kel was a planet located in the Resti Kel system of the Juvex sector, in the Mid Rim of the galaxy.

properties.name: Reuss
properties.description: Reuss was an astronomical object in the Outer Rim Territories of the galaxy, linked to Socorro and Spice Terminus by hyperspace routes. It was positioned at the coordinates P-18 on the Standard Galactic Grid.

properties.name: Revery
properties.description:
Revery was a planet known for being inhabited by rich beings, as well as its beaches, mountains, and privacy. It appeared blue from space, and on the planet, there were aquamarine seas, green and gold land, and pink clouds could be seen in the sky.
Astri Oddo and Clive Flax visited this planet looking for Eve Yarrow's estate.

properties.name: Revyia
properties.poi: Revyia Imperial base, Revyia smuggler base , Revyia temple,
properties.description: Revyia was a planet in the Veragi sector of the Outer Rim, located halfway between the Pits of Plooma and the Galactic Rim. It was the homeworld of the Revwien species. In 30 BBY, the Tyia Force tradition was brought to the planet by a missionary aboard an independent freighter.

properties.name: Reyna
properties.description: The Reyna was an Imperial-class Star Destroyer assigned to the Tapani sector. It was assigned to the planet Mrlsst. The ships assigned to the planets Mrlsst and Achillea, protected by the Leonides, were strategically located to control the only routes in and out sector.

properties.name: Reynon
properties.description: Reynon was a planet. Rebel agent Harovan Toth was a native of Reynon.

properties.name: Reytha
properties.description: Reytha was one of the most productive agriworlds of the Galactic Republic and later the Galactic Empire. At the time of the Battle of Yavin, Reytha was governed by Governor Antes Belladar.

properties.name: Rhamalai
properties.description: Rhamalai was an agriworld near Seitia Prime, to which the Cherishites fled following persecution by the Galactic Republic.

properties.name: Rhamsis Callo
properties.poi: Galactic Empire base, Rhamsis Callo Spaceport,
properties.description: Rhamsis Callo was an Outer Rim Territories planet located in the Danjar sector. It was the homeworld of the Force-sensitive and militaristic Schenor species, which allowed the Galactic Empire to construct a base on the planet despite remaining neutral in the Galactic Civil War. During that conflict, a team of Rebel Alliance agents delivered a young survivor of an Imperial massacre of a Schenor colony to Rhamsis Callo. When the Schenor noble B'karitz learned about the massacre, he led an insurrection that attempted to drive the Imperial forces off Rhamsis Callo.

properties.name: Rhelg
properties.description: Rhelg was one of the only agricultural worlds in the Sith Worlds region of the Outer Rim Territories' Esstran sector. Falling between Khar Delba and the Sith homeworld of Korriban on the looping Nache Bhelfia hyperlane, Rhelg was considered one of the five sacred Sith planets, along with Ziost, Khar Delba, Krayiss II, and Korriban. A primitive world covered in vast expanses of arable land, Rhelg was the private world of the Sith Lord Ludo Kressh as well as the site of his palace during the Great Hyperspace War.

properties.name: Rhen Var
properties.poi: Jedi Monument, Ancient Jedi ruins, Bravo Base, Imperial listening outpost, Harbor, Citadel, Ross Mysliwiec's tombDarth Mekhis' fortress, Forgotten Rakatan Temple,
properties.description: Rhen Var was a planet situated near the Tion Cluster in the Outer Rim Territories and one of the former Thanium Worlds. It was the first planet in the Tobali system. Throughout the history of the Galactic Republic, Rhen Var was covered in ice, rendering it almost uninhabitable. Remains of an ancient civilization and old Jedi artifacts were found beneath the ice on the planet, remnants of a former population.

properties.name: Rhigar
properties.description: Rhigar was a snowy planet located in the Rata Nebula of the Unknown Regions, with three moons: an inner forest moon, a large satellite known as Asdroni, and the outermost, ocean-covered Rhigar 3.

properties.name: Rhilithan
properties.description: Rhilithan was a lifeless planet located within the Indrexu sector of the Outer Rim Territories.

properties.name: Rhinnal
properties.poi: Jedi chapter house, Jedi enclave, Rhinnal State Medical Academy, Zirfan glacier,
properties.description: Rhinnal was a planet in the star system of the same name in the Darpa sector of the Core Worlds. Orbited by two moons and located in the Ringali Shell, the region of space along the Perlemian Trade Route near the Ringali Nebula, Rhinnal possessed almost no axial tilt and a near-circular orbit, giving the planet very little seasonal variations. Encased in a planet-wide ice age tens of thousands of years before the Galactic Republic's collapse, Rhinnal had begun to thaw by the time it was one of the Core Founders of the Republic in 25,053 BBY, having been settled by Humans from Notron. A colony of nearby Esseles for much of its history, Rhinnal soon gained a reputation as a medical wonderworld, with a Jedi chapter house and the Rhinnal State Medical Academy in the capital of Rhire producing some of the galaxy's best doctors.

properties.name: Rhommamool
properties.description: Rhommamool was an impoverished mining world in the Expansion Region, along the Corellian Run. It was in the same system as Osarian.

properties.name: Rianon
properties.description: The Rianon system was a star system located in the Tapani sector's Melantha Province, between Shella and Shindra systems.

properties.name: Ricaldi
properties.description: The Ricaldi system was a star system located in the Tapani sector's Melantha Province, between the Tocco and Cauper systems.

properties.name: Riesa
properties.description: The Riesa was an Imperial-class Star Destroyer assigned to the Tapani sector. It was assigned to the planet Tallaan and the Tallaani Shipyards. The shipyard was also defended by Golan Arms defense platforms and various other cruisers. In addition there was usually at least another Star Destroyers in dock undergoing repairs that could add additional defensive capability.

properties.name: Riflor
properties.description: Riflor was a tectonically active Mid Rim planet located in the trinary star system of Riflorii on the Cerean Reach with a tendency to change its gravitational pull. The native population was known for its bureaucracy and engineering accomplishments.

properties.name: Rigel
properties.description: Rigel can refer to:

properties.name: Rigoron
properties.description: Rigoron was a planet located in the Dimean sector of the Expansion Region.

properties.name: Riileb
properties.description: Riileb was a planet in Hutt Space and the homeworld of the Riileb species. This planet was one of the few worlds within Hutt Space other than the Sakiyan worlds to maintain independence against Hutt influence. It was a hot and torrid world which supported a wide range of flora and fauna. Much of the planet was covered in oceans with islands being the only landforms.

properties.name: Rim
properties.description: The Rim was a region that existed beyond the boundaries of the Galactic Republic around 22,000 BBY.

properties.name: Rimcee Station
properties.description: Rimcee Station was an Imperial space station in the Rimcee system. In 19 ABY it was the location of imprisonment of Fleet Admiral Gilad Pellaeon's aide, Colonel Meizh Vermel, who had been captured by order of Moff Disra in his attempt to foil Pellaeon's peace proposal.

properties.name: Rimma
properties.poi: Ancient ruins, Imperial garrison, Norsec shanty town, Teirra Parko,
properties.description: Rimma was an astronomical object in the Core Worlds, situated on the super-hyperroute known as the Rimma Trade Route. The city of Recardeon was located on Rimma, as was a set of ancient ruins. Several scrolls discovered in the latter by 3637 BBY noted the existence of the artifacts known as the Three Great Works.

properties.name: Rindao
properties.description: Rindao was a drab training station in the days of the Galactic Empire, close to the Outer Rim Territories. When the Empire arrived to take over the planet, the local populace had not resisted outright, and so avoided any significant persecution by the new regime. An exception to this was when an Imperial officer heard an old woman singing songs of the glorious days of the Galactic Republic and the Jedi Knights. The old woman was swiftly executed by blaster rifles for her perceived slur on the glory of the Empire.
