However, her legacy was continued through her granddaughter, Tionne Solusar, who saved her double viol and fled the planet. She later became a Jedi Knight herself.

properties.name: Rindia
properties.description: The Rindia system was located in the Nembus sector of the Outer Rim Territories. It was home to the sentient species known as Rindians.

properties.name: The Ring
properties.description: The Ring was an astronomical object found within the Anoat sector of the galaxy's Outer Rim Territories. It was situated inside the Ivax Nebula and was positioned relatively close to the planets Gerrenthum and Nothoiin.

properties.name: Ringali Nebula
properties.description: The Ringali Nebula was a nebula that curled around the Perlemian Trade Route at its intersection with the Hydian Way. Several nearby planets included Corulag, Chandrila, Brentaal, Esseles, Rhinnal, and Ralltiir.

properties.name: Ringo Vinda
properties.description: Ringo Vinda was a planet located in the Ringo Vinda system, within the Eucer sector of the galaxy's Mid Rim. An important industrial production center, it was encircled by a massive space station that served as a distribution point for all incoming and outgoing resources.

properties.name: Rinn
properties.description: Rinn was a backwater planet in the Outer Rim Territories and the homeworld of the Tintinna.

properties.name: Rintonne
properties.description: Rintonne was a Mid Rim planet in the Lambda sector. A member of the Galactic Republic, Rintonne was the homeworld of Rasit Brun, the sectorial Senator representing Lambda in 32 BBY.

properties.name: Rion
properties.description: Rion was a planet located in the Kessel sector of the Outer Rim Territories.

properties.name: Rior
properties.description: Rior was the Riorian homeworld. It was located in the Outer Rim Territories.

properties.name: Rirsack
properties.description: Rirsack was a planet located in the Belsmuth sector of the Outer Rim. Lieutenant Lar Ndigo of the New Republic bravely fought there sometime during or prior to 13 ABY.

properties.name: Risban
properties.description: Risban was a planet in the Tion Hegemony, and the location of the river town Keremark. The town was ruled by the Neolsse family, who opposed Imperial subjugation from Fortress Keremark.

properties.name: Rishi
properties.poi: Razorback Island, Rishi Base, , Sky Ridge Island, Tracyn Island, Wozwashi Street,
properties.description: Rishi was a tropical planet in the Rishi system which was located in the Outer Rim Territories. The planet was the homeworld of the avian Rishii.

properties.name: Rivoria
properties.description: The Rivoria system was a star system located within the Outer Rim Territories' Tunka sector. It was home to the rodents known as Rivorian grain-bandits.

properties.name: Rivvidu
properties.description: On the planet of Rivvidu, Boba Fett once chased a female Iotran mark. After the capture, Fett acquired his Silver Speeder. Its Imperial governor employed a Kubaz spy.

properties.name: Rocantor
properties.description: Rocantor was a planet located in the Expansion Region of the galaxy.

properties.name: Roche
properties.description: Roche was a location in the galaxy's Mid Rim, in grid square Q-8 on the Standard Galactic Grid, situated between Lantillies and Abhean on the Perlemian Trade Route. It shared its name with the Verpine Roche Hive, a droid manufacturer,  and the Roche Foundation Prize award. During the Clone Wars, a sneak attack on Roche occurred, a battle which the Dressellian smuggler Has Obitt was caught in the middle of.

properties.name: Rodaj
properties.description: Rodaj was a planet in the Inner Rim located near Wroona.

properties.name: Rodia
properties.poi: An'yettu IslandsBetuEncheekoFlip of the Credit, Kay-Tap squareNext ChanceSenatorial Palace
properties.description: Rodia, a rainforested, industrial planet in the Tyrius system in the Outer Rim, was the homeworld of the Rodians.

properties.name: Rodis
properties.description: Rodis was the homeworld of the Rodisar species. It was a primitive planet that was once the site of a conflict known as the Winter Wars, in which Nilo was a general.

properties.name: Rokaria
properties.description: The Rokaria system was located in the Tynquay sector of the Outer Rim Territories. It was home to the creatures known as Rokarian dirt-fish.

properties.name: Rol
properties.description: Rol can mean:

properties.name: Roldalna
properties.description: Roldalna was a celestial body located in the Expansion Region's Kira sector. Shortly after the formation of the New Republic, it was the site of a cantina.

properties.name: Romar
properties.description: Romar was the sector capital of Galov sector. It was home to Moff Antoll Jellrek's base.

properties.name: Romin
properties.description: Romin was a small Mid Rim planet. It was the homeworld of the Romins.

properties.name: Ronyards
properties.description: Ronyards, also known as the Body of the Living God by its droid inhabitants, was a junkyard planet located in the Ronyards system of the galaxy's Inner Rim. Ronyards was a common dumping ground for obsolete, inoperative and unwanted droids, and was covered in metal piles that could reach up to five miles deep. Ronyards was home to a large population of active droids who worshipped Ronyards itself—and their "living god" was known to defend its inhabitants when they were threatened by outsiders.

properties.name: Roon
properties.poi: Bantha GraveyardRoon Sea, Tawntoom province, Fortress of TawntoomThe TriadUmboo province, Pinnacles of Felth
properties.description: Roon was a planet located in the nearly impenetrable Cloak of the Sith. Known for its Roonstones, the planet was constantly sought after by treasure hunters for years.

properties.name: Roona
properties.description: Roona was a planet in the Expansion Region and the homeworld of the Roonans. In the final years of the Galactic Republic, Roona was represented in the Galactic Senate by Edcel Bar Gane in 32 BBY and later by Gane and Aang in 22 BBY.

properties.name: Roost
properties.description: The Roost was a space station that served as the base of a crew of mercenaries led by Ranzar Malk. The Mandalorian bounty hunter known as Din Djarin visited the space station to join a team of mercenaries, who had been tasked by Malk into rescuing the prisoner Qin from the Bothan-5, a New Republic Correctional Transport. The team betrayed Djarin and left him for dead, but he escaped and returned to the station with Qin, the latter unknowingly carrying a tracker from the prison ship. Malk paid Djarin and let him leave, but ordered a gunship to shoot him down. However, a New Republic X-wing squadron followed the tracker's distress signal, and opened fire on the station.

properties.name: Ropagi
properties.description: Ropagi was the primary star of the Ropagi system.

properties.name: Roqoo Depot
properties.description: Roqoo Depot was a refueling station and supply base located in the Hapes Cluster. It was here that Jedi Masters Luke and Mara Jade Skywalker dueled the Sith Lady Lumiya and her apprentice, Alema Rar.

properties.name: Rorak
properties.description: Rorak was an astronomical object located in the Hutt Space region of the galaxy. It was connected to Ylesia, Nal Hutta and Circumtore, also of Hutt Space, by hyperspace routes. Rorak was located at galactic coordinates S-12.

properties.name: Rordak
properties.poi: Alpha TR-8, Azkulkt, Deggaruls, Dreggusom, Whosk,
properties.description: Rordak was a planet in the Rordak system. It was an Imperial penal colony with an orbital nightcloak. A battle was fought there between 3681 BBY and 3653 BBY between the Sith Empire and the Galactic Republic. The battle ended in a Republic victory when Bouris Ulgo personally boarded Moff Ceptor's battlecruiser.

properties.name: Rorgam
properties.description: Rorgam was a Mid Rim planet whose population consisted mainly of immigrants from other planets. Many of the world's elite were known to wear wrapped cloth headpieces.

properties.name: Rothana
properties.description: Rothana was a remote planet in the Rothana system located in Quiberon sector, near the edge of the Outer Rim Territories, most famous for being the headquarters of Rothana Heavy Engineering and the source of the Grand Army of the Republic's military materiel during the Clone Wars.

properties.name: Roundtree
properties.description: The Roundtree system was located in the Trailing Sectors portion of the Inner Rim. At some point by 2 BBY, the Human male Rekkon was born in the Roundtree system as the only child in a middle class family.

properties.name: Roxuli
properties.description: Roxuli was a Republic member world in the Roxuli system, near the frontier with the Unknown Regions.

properties.name: Rrulinn
properties.description: Rrulinn was a Mid Rim world in the Yushan sector. Its population fell victim to the Reslian Purge, much as did the Tunroth.

properties.name: Rseik
properties.description: Rseik was a terrestrial astronomical object located within the Rseik system, a part of the Outer Rim Territories' Rseik sector. It was the homeworld of the sentient Rseikharhl species. At some point following 214 BBY, the Kett family maintained investments on Rseik, a fact which was noted in the memoirs of the Trade Defense Force captain Firmus Kett.

properties.name: Ruac
properties.description: Ruac Outpost was a base in the Ruac system in times of the Old Republic.

properties.name: Ruan
properties.poi: Refugee Facility 17, Noob Hill, Ryn City,
properties.description: Ruan was an agriworld in the Core Worlds.

properties.name: Rudrig
properties.description: Rudrig was a planet located within the Tion Hegemony of the Outer Rim.

properties.name: Rugosa
properties.description: Rugosa, also known as the coral moon, was a temperate moon in the Sanbra sector. It was one of the worlds that made up the Infinite Empire, a galactic power led by the Rakatan species in approximately 30,000 BBY. The moon was later discovered by Toydarian scouts working near the Balmorra Run, and because of its attractive climate and warm oceans, it became a Toydarian vacation spot that they kept secret from their Hutt masters. Once the Hutts discovered the Toydarians' duplicity, they punished them by releasing a plague onto the moon, drying up all its oceans and exposing vast expanses of coral.

properties.name: Ruhe
properties.description: Ruhe was a planet that was allied with the Confederacy of Independent Systems during the Clone Wars. Dooku maintained a citadel on Ruhe, situated on the edge of a massive volcanic or meteoric crater. Half a month after the Battle of Boz Pity, a strike team including Anakin Skywalker, Obi-Wan Kenobi, and Jenks was shot down on Ruhe while trying to capture Dooku; it was later revealed that it was a trap set by Dooku in the hopes of capturing Skywalker and Kenobi.

properties.name: Ruisto
properties.description: Ruisto was a planet located in the Calamari sector of the Outer Rim Territories.

properties.name: Rulaar
properties.description: Rulaar was a planet in the Mid Rim's Senex sector. The Rulaarian pleasure yacht existed in the galaxy by the time of the Galactic Civil War.

properties.name: Rullag
properties.description: Rullag was an astronomical object located in the Cadma sector of the Outer Rim Territories. Dark Jedi Nax Cirvan claimed to have killed eight Jedi and their Padawans on the plains of Rullag during the Clone Wars.

properties.name: Runaway Prince
properties.poi: Yorik coral and villip production facilities
properties.description: Runaway Prince, called Lordunkee Wanpolla in Huttese, was an uninhabited planet in Hutt Space which the Hutts gave to the Yuuzhan Vong. The origin of its peculiar name was lost in history.

properties.name: Rustibar
properties.description: Rustibar was a Mid Rim planet subjugated by the Galactic Empire.

properties.name: Rutal
properties.description: Rutal IV was a planet located in the Fferon system. It was the headquarters of Ry-Kooda.

properties.name: Rutan
properties.description: Rutan was a planet in the Outer Rim Territories, on the Hydian Way.

properties.name: Ruul
properties.description: Ruul was a Dathomirian Zabrak male from the planet Dathomir who was part of a clan of the Nightbrothers during the Clone Wars. Prior to the Second Battle of Dathomir of 19 BBY, Ruul met with Mak Eak, a Nightbrother leader, in a warehouse-like building on a mission for the runaway Nightbrother Arzo Suun to help steal supplies for Eak. Ruul and Eak were eventually caught by a group of Nightsisters led by Nelsel, who detected the Nightbrothers' presence through the Force.

properties.name: Ruuria
properties.description: Ruuria, on the Hydian Way, was the homeworld of the insectoid Ruurians. The planet was located near the Corporate Sector. It featured tropical jungles, manufacturing centers, and universities. Ruuria was a member of the Unified Ruurian Colonies.

properties.name: Ruusan
properties.description: Ruusan was a planet in the Mid Rim most famous for the Ruusan campaign, the last stand of the Brotherhood of Darkness under Lord Kaan and the birthplace of Darth Bane's Order of the Sith Lords. The planet lent its name to the Ruusan Reformations enacted after the battle.

properties.name: Ruweln
properties.description: Ruweln was the homeworld of Galactic Alliance Admiral Nek Bwua'tu, located in Bothan space.

properties.name: Rya
properties.description: Rya was a planet inhabited by Humans such as Cinto Alaras.

properties.name: Ryborea
properties.description: The Ryborea system was located within the Ryborean sector, in the Outer Expansion Zone sub-region and the Northern Dependencies portion of the Expansion Region. A hyperlane connected the Ryborea system to the Aramal system and Station 88.

properties.name: Rychel
properties.description: Rychel was a planet located within the Rychel system of the Dalonbian sector in the Outer Rim Territories.

properties.name: Rydonni Prime
properties.poi: Rilvvan K'ntarr's mansion, Royal Zoos, Rydonnian Imperial Consulate, Rythani Products Building,
properties.description: Rydonni Prime was the only habitable planet in the Namaryne system and home to Rythani Products, headed by the K'ntarr family. Moff Caerbellak ruled the planet during the Galactic Civil War and the early years of the New Republic. It was very wealthy and had very few disenfranchised inhabitants, which made it very loyal to the Galactic Empire.

properties.name: Ryloon
properties.description: Ryloon was Outer Rim Territories planet in Velcar sector, Ryloon systemand the site of several Imperial controlled orbital factories where captured prisoners were sent to work. The world remained part of the Imperial Remnant following its peace agreement with the New Republic.

properties.name: Ryloth
properties.poi: Bright LandsCrater SeaFloating Rock GardensFungus PitGreat TusksLeb'ReenHunvar's SpireJoreiknaJunkardLohemaLonely Five RangeNightlandsSith AcademyThe EnclaveThe Brightlands Podracing Track
properties.description: Ryloth, also known as Twi'lek, and Twi'lek Prime, was the harsh, rocky homeworld of the Twi'leks, an Outer Rim Territories world located on the Corellian Run and forming one endpoint of the Death Wind Corridor. One side of the planet perpetually faced its sun and the other remained in darkness, a phenomenon known as tidal locking. The dayside was referred to as the Bright Lands and the night-side was known as the Nightlands.

properties.name: Ryndellia
properties.description: Ryndellia was a neutral planet in the Ryndellia system, close to the Outer Rim Territories. It was also close to the Kaliida Shoals Medical Center and the planet Naboo.

properties.name: Rynmar
properties.description: Rynmar was a planet located in the Hapes Cluster and home of the rare creature known as a hover beak.

properties.name: Ryoone
properties.description: Ryoone was a dismal planet in the Outer Rim characterized by a "seemingly permanent suspension of ash in the upper atmosphere." It was inhabited by six sentient species, including the Lyunesi.

properties.name: Ryvellia
properties.description: Ryvellia was a planet located in the Avhn-Bendara system. Its capital city, V'eldalv, was the site of a brutal uprising that was crushed by the Galactic Empire via orbital bombardment.

properties.name: Ryvester
properties.description: Ryvester was a planet in the Meridian sector. Imperial Admiral Kosh Teradoc was presumed dead on the planet during a Wraith Squadron mission in 13 ABY. Kosh Teradoc kept a personal yacht in the bay to the east of his naval base.

properties.name: Ryyk Nebula
properties.description: The Ryyk Nebula was a nebula located near the planet Myrkr in the Trans-Vulta sector of the Mid Rim, somewhere along the space lanes between the planets Serroco and Telerath. In 3963 BBY, during the Mandalorian Wars between the Galactic Republic and the Mandalorian warrior clans, Admiral Saul Karath attempted to reach the Ryyk Nebula after retreating from the Mandalorian destruction of Serroco and link his forces up with the Tremendous battle group in the area. However, Karath never reached his destination, as his flagship, the Courageous, was boarded and destroyed.

properties.name: Saarn
properties.description: Saarn was an isolated and hidden Outer Rim Territories planet with vast, green grasslands.

properties.name: Sab Rufo
properties.description: The planet Sab Rufo was home to the Academy at Sab Rufo.

properties.name: Saberhing
properties.description: Saberhing was a planet in the Corellian sector which manufactured starships. Han Solo and Chewbacca worked as mechanics in a factory on Saberhing before becoming smugglers when Han was 20 years old.

properties.name: Saclas
properties.description: Saclas was an Ocsin colony in the Corporate Sector. The planet was at the intersection of the Tertiary Solenbaran and the Solenbaran Merchant Route.

properties.name: Sacorria
properties.poi: Dorthus Tal Island, Cobble Stone Square, Dorthus Tal Prison, Watchtower Base, Sacorria Central SpaceportSacorria clone medical and rehabilitation facility
properties.description: Sacorria was an agriworld in the Sacorrian system, located on the fringe of the Corellian sector.

properties.name: Saffa
properties.description: Saffa was a female Twi'lek who worked for the Graf family at Everbloom, the family estate.

properties.name: Saffalore
properties.description: Saffalore was a planet in the Corporate Sector, at one end of the Lucaya Cross. It was one of the Sector's most recent boomworlds. It remained neutral in the Galactic Civil War.

properties.name: Sagar
properties.description: The Sagar system was a star system located in the Inner Rim that contained the Blackstar wheelworld. It was situated along the Hydian Way.

properties.name: Sagma
properties.description: Sagma was a planet in the Outer Rim Territories and the site of the Battle of Sagma. In 18 BBY, Imperial forces led by Admiral Wullf Yularen and Captain Bannidge Holt defeated the Sikurdian pirates at Sagma. Captain Ganig and Sergeant Stecker were highly propogandized Imperial veterans of the battle, considered heroes.

properties.name: Saheelindeel
properties.description: Saheelindeel was an agricultural world that was located in the Tion Hegemony, within the Outer Rim of the galaxy. It was a backwater world inhabited by the Saheelindeeli, a species of intelligent, green-furred primates.

properties.name: Saijo
properties.description: Saijo was an Outer Rim Territories fortress world near Cantros 7. It had green river valleys.

properties.name: Saila Na
properties.description: Saila Na was an astronomical object in the Greater Javin Region of the galaxy's Outer Rim Territories.

properties.name: Saki
properties.description: Saki was a planet located in the Hutt Space region of the galaxy's Outer Rim Territories that was conquered by the Hutt Cartel, which was controlled by the Hutts from the neighboring world of Nal Hutta, who turned the native Sakiyans into slaves or vassals.

properties.name: Sakidopa
properties.description: Sakidopa, which could be translated as "Second Saki," was a planet located in the Bootana Hutta region of Hutt Space.

properties.name: Sakiduba
properties.description: Sakiduba, which could be translated as "Third Saki," was a planet located in the Bootana Hutta region of Hutt Space.

properties.name: Sakifwanna
properties.description: Sakifwanna was a planet that was located within the Sakifwanna system in Hutt Space, a region of the galaxy controlled by the Hutt species. The planet lay on the Elgit–M'Hanna Corridor hyperlane that connected it to the worlds of Elgit and M'Hanna. A smaller hyperspace route linked Sakifwanna to the Cyax system, and another hyperlane connected the world to the planet of Saki.

properties.name: Sakuub
properties.description: Sakuub was a world located in the Sakuub system of Pelgrin sector in the Outer Rim Territories. It was the homeworld of the Sakuubians.

properties.name: Saleucami
properties.poi: Blackwind Crater, Lawquane farmstead, Magma Caverns, Saleucami Cloning Complex,
properties.description: Saleucami  was a dim, arid world in the Suolriep sector of the Outer Rim Territories. An economic powerhouse and major trading center in the Outer Rim, Saleucami was politically powerful during the Great Galactic War and a strategically held world within the Confederacy of Independent Systems during the Clone Wars. Controlled by the Techno Union throughout the Separatist Crisis, the world was liberated by the Grand Army of the Republic before the rise of the Galactic Empire and was spared the retribution demanded of other former Separatist worlds. Located between Kegan and Handooine along the Talcene Transit, the planet was supplied by cargo ships off of the Perlemian Trade Route that were headed to the Kuthic Worlds.

properties.name: Salin
properties.description: Salin was a planet in the Outer Rim Territories that was part of the Kwa holdings during the Pre-Republic era. With the ascendancy of the Rakatan Infinite Empire, Salin was annexed and the Kwa species were annihilated and driven back to Dathomir.

properties.name: Salissia
properties.description: Salissia was an astronomical object that was attacked by the Nihil marauder organization following the Battle of Kur. In the time leading up to the Republic Fair, Senator Vaadu of the Galactic Republic cited the attack on Salissia as one piece of evidence that the Nihil in operation, thought to be remnants of the group, were still a threat.

properties.name: Salliche
properties.description: Salliche was an agricultural world in the Core Worlds region. It was the headquarters of the Salliche Agricultural Corporation. The planet was one of 18 planets on the Agricultural Circuit.

properties.name: Salteract
properties.description: Salkeract was a planet located in the Outer Rim's Rayter sector.

properties.name: Salvara
properties.description: Salvara was a planet located in the Tennuutta sector of the Mid Rim. During the Clone Wars, the planet was located within Separatist space. It was the site of a battle between the Galactic Republic and the Confederacy of Independent Systems during the Clone Wars.

properties.name: Samaria
properties.poi: Hall of MinistersTalo SquareTwilight FountainsCrystal Forest
properties.description: Samaria was a small desert planet in the Leemurtoo system, in a strategic part of the Core Worlds.

properties.name: Samhar
properties.description: Samhar was a forest-covered world that was located in the Grumani sector, in the Outer Rim Territories. It was inhabited by the Samhari, a Near-Human species.

properties.name: Sanbra
properties.description: Sanbra was the location of the University of Sanbra. It also the location of the Shoapy Hostel.

properties.name: Sanctuary
properties.description: Sanctuary, a small, island-dotted oceanic planet located in Mon Calamari Space, was one of the oldest and most well-known Rebel Alliance safe world colonies, predating the Declaration of Rebellion. Sanctuary was originally settled by religious pacifists dodging an Imperial draft. These colonists joined the Alliance on the condition that they would not have to fight in the war against the Galactic Empire. So began a mutually beneficial relationship, in which Sanctuary accepted all manner of Rebels and political exiles seeking asylum from Imperial oppression in exchange for equipment that would boost the planet's agricultural capability.

properties.name: Sanjin
properties.description: Sanjin was a gas giant located in the Colonies region of the galaxy.

properties.name: Sanrafsix
properties.description: Sanrafsix was an Outer Rim Territories world located in the Grumani sector. Situated on the Duros Space Run and Sanrafsix Corridor hyperlanes, during the New Sith Wars Sanrafsix was a cosmopolitan trade hub, a fact which doomed the world when it could not maintain quarantine during a Candorian plague outbreak and was forced to isolate its groundside population, all of whom eventually succumbed to the lethal disease.

properties.name: Santarine
properties.description: Santarine was a planet that was located within the Hook Nebula, along the Outer Rim of the galaxy.

properties.name: Sanyassa
properties.description: Sanyassa was an astronomical object located in the Moddell sector of the Outer Rim Territories in grid square H-16 of the Standard Galactic Grid. It was situated on the Bakura Trace hyperspace route, which linked it to the celestial body Ast Kikorie as well as the Endor system. The Moddell sector's hyperspace anomalies sometimes transported starships to the Endor system from as far away as Sanyassa. Sanyassa was eventually depicted on a map of the Moddell sector included with the Rebel Alliance collection of non-electronic documents known as The Rebel Files.

properties.name: Sanza
properties.description: Sanza, also known as Krish, was a Mid Rim world dedicated to casinos, race tracks, arenas, agriculture, and manufacturing. It was the home of the Krish species.

properties.name: Sapella
properties.description: Sapella was a planet located in the Kathol Outback. Remote even by Outback standards, the planet was five days travel from Timbra Ott. Not many merchants plied the route, since more profits were to be had at Jangelle and the Kathol Republic. Around 8 ABY, Sapella was in the early stages of an ice age. The polar ice-caps covered much of the northern and southern hemispheres, and a temperate band at the equator was the only habitable part of the planet. Temperatures ranged from icy to frigid, but the colony's placement allowed it to avoid the worst of the weather. The colony was located on hilly coastland islands, and produced hindian pears, sihan peaches, grains and livestock. Wine was also produced, which merchants traded for needed supplies from Timbra Ott and Jangelle.

properties.name: Sappire
properties.description: Sappire was a planet in the Outer Rim Territories.

properties.name: Saqqar
properties.description: Saqqar was an icy planet that was located within the Saqqar system in Hutt Space, a region of the galaxy controlled by the Hutt species. The planet lay on the hyperlane called The Dead Road, which connected it to the worlds of Tisht and Usk. A smaller hyperlane linked the planet to the world of Nar Haaska.

properties.name: Sarapin
properties.description: Sarapin was a volcanic world in the Sarapin system, between Neimoidia and the Treskov system. It had ashy soil and streams of lava flowing across its surface.

properties.name: Sarconia
properties.description: Sarconia was the homeworld of green fleas.

properties.name: Sardoran
properties.description: Sardoran, originally known as Ord Sardoran, was a planet in the Core Worlds.

properties.name: Sareet
properties.description: Sareet was a planet within the Sareet system in the Outer Rim Territories. It was the homeworld of the Sareeta species.

properties.name: Sargon
properties.description: Sargon was a male Imperial Army Captain who lived during the Galactic Civil War.

properties.name: Sarka
properties.description: Sarka was a Mid Rim planet and the homeworld of the Sarkan species.

properties.name: Sarko
properties.description: Sarko was a male Human bounty hunter who tried to capture Quinlan Vos on Ord Mantell in 30 BBY.

properties.name: Sarlucif
properties.description: Sarlucif was a planet in Wild Space and home to the outlaw tech base run by Klaus Vandangante and his daughter, Jessa.

properties.name: Sarm
properties.description: Sarm was a yellow world which had been inhabited by an unknown species which built a vast irrigation canal network across the planet. When the Utegetu Nebula erupted, however, it scoured the planet clean of its population, leaving only the canal network behind. The Killik fleet would later mass above it, setting the stage for the Battle of Sarm.

properties.name: Sarnus
properties.description: Sarnus was a world in the Chiloon Rift. In 45 ABY, Lando Calrissian had established a refinery on the world to mine the plentiful asteroids present in the rift.

properties.name: Sarrahban
properties.description: Sarrahban was a planet in the Sarrahban system, located within the Cyrillian Protectorate of the Expansion Region. It hosted a native species, and attempted to remain neutral in the Galactic Civil War between the Alliance to Restore the Republic and Galactic Empire despite both sides attempting to persuade them to join. The Empire, however, got tired of Sarrahban's neutrality and launched an invasion of the world. During the battle, Alliance to Restore the Republic members from the local partisan force attempted to escape aboard the Harvest Moon, a grain freighter. It was shot down by Imperial forces, but Alliance agents managed to repair the ship and escape, taking Rebel refugees and the planet's reserve of stabilized ytterbium with them.

properties.name: Sarranket
properties.description: Sarranket was a planet located in the Expansion Region.

properties.name: Sarrassia
properties.description: Sarrassia was a world in the Sarrassia system, in the Grumani sector. It was a known source of Sarrassian iron.

properties.name: Sarrelon
properties.description: Sarrelon was the orange star of the Sarrelon system in the Expansion Region.

properties.name: Sarrish
properties.description: Sarrish was a planet in the Vensensor sector, and homeworld of the Sarrish people.

properties.name: Sartoy
properties.description: Sartoy may refer to one of the following:

properties.name: Saruwen Station
properties.description: Saruwen Station was a Bengel Shipbuilders XQ2 Platform, operating as a trading post in deep space.

properties.name: Sarvchi
properties.description: Sarvchi was a planet of the Chiss Ascendancy in the Unknown Regions. It was home of the Chaf family, one of the Chiss Ruling Families. Like other homeworlds of Ruling Families, Sarvchi was located on the Path of the Houses. It was a neutral world where lived the few non-Chiss that populated the Ascendancy. Chaf'orm'bintrano sent a message to the Jade Sabre from Sarvchi in 22 ABY.

properties.name: Sathiemon
properties.description: Sathiemon was an arid desert world located in the galaxy, where Boba Fett was presumed dead by a hit squad during the Imperial era, while the latter was hunting a bounty. Sathiemon had numerous holes and burrows, that the natives used.

properties.name: Savareen
properties.poi: Pnakotic Coast, Emerald Sea, Dry Gulch,
properties.description: Savareen was a planet that was located at one spur of the Kessel Run, in the galaxy's Outer Rim Territories. The planet consisted of sandy landmasses and huge oceans. Savareen was also known for its famous brandy drink. The Crimson Dawn once had a business there and they chopped off the tongues of the natives. The former pirate Queen Maz Kanata marked it as a point of interest on a map she included in the book that would become known as the Smuggler's Guide.

properties.name: Sayblohn
properties.description: Sayblohn was a planet located in the Mid Rim's Quess sector. It was occupied by the Galactic Empire, and a group of pirates had a hidden base in the planet's badlands. During the Galactic Civil War, a Rebel Alliance team of operatives traveled to Sayblohn in order to retrieve a stolen art object. After several run-ins with the local pirates, the team was ultimately successful in its mission.

properties.name: Scarl
properties.description: Scarl was the name of starship construction facilities located in the Scarl system, just parsecs from Fondor. Scarl was located on the restricted Gandeal-Fondor Hyperlane.

properties.name: Schesa
properties.description: Schesa was a planet located in the Schesa system of the Unknown Regions' Chiss Space. The hyperlane known as the Path of the Houses linked it to the Noris system, and it was also situated at the endpoint of the Way of Schesa hyperspace route, which connected it to the Pesfavri system and the Redoubt. Schesa was an outlying colony of the sentient Chiss species and was home to one of the Ruling Families that ruled over the Chiss Ascendancy, the government of the Chiss.

properties.name: Scillal
properties.description: Scillal may refer to one of the following:

properties.name: Scipio
properties.poi: InterGalactic Banking Clan Main Vault, Frigia Canyons,
properties.description: Scipio was an ice- and snow-covered planet in the Outer Rim Territories' Albarrio sector. The homeworld of the Muuns and the InterGalactic Banking Clan, the world had frozen peaks dotted with towering columns and graceful arches.

properties.name: Sebaddon
properties.description: Sebaddon was a small world in the Mid Rim above the galactic plane, located near a black hole.

properties.name: Sebiris
properties.description: Sebiris was a planet located in the Sebiris system of the Outer Rim Territories' Kathol sector. A hot jungle world, it was the homeworld of the Sebiri, a primitive species of scaly-hided humanoids. At some point, Sebiris had been visited by an advanced species that the Sebiri referred to as "those who came before," whom they believed created the jungle and performed miracles through the use of glowing charms. The only evidence of their passing was the ruins of a stone temple located within the planet's equatorial region.

properties.name: Secundus Ando
properties.description: Secundus Ando was the homeworld of the Harch species. It was located in the Mid Rim of the galaxy.

properties.name: Sedesia
properties.description: Sedesia was a high-gravity Mid Rim world with harsh terrain and rough weather.

properties.name: Sedratis
properties.description: Sedratis may refer to the following items:

properties.name: Sedri
properties.description: Sedri was a water planet in the Sedri system. It was the homeworld of the Sedrians and the Golden Sun, a living coral used as a power source.

properties.name: Seezar's Planet
properties.description: Seezar's Planet was a planet where the "Chanteuse of the Stars", Shirley, once performed.

properties.name: Sefon
properties.description: The Sefon system was located in the Freeworlds Territory of the Tapani sector, between the Lamuir and Fondor systems.

properties.name: Seftek
properties.description: Seftek was a planet located in the Vorzyd Cluster of the Outer Rim.

properties.name: Seidhkona
properties.description: Seidhkona was a planet in the galaxy's Wild Space. During the Galactic Civil War, the mind-witch S'ybll used the planet as the base of her operations.

properties.name: Seikosha
properties.poi: Event Horizon, Seikoshan rebel camp, Serap's Fortress, Serap's landing strip,
properties.description: Seikosha was a planet in the Breago system which remained neutral during the Galactic Civil War.

properties.name: Seitia Prime
properties.description: Seitia Prime was a planet in the Seitia system, near Rhamalai.

properties.name: Selab
properties.description: Selab was a planet in the Hapes Cluster famed for its trees of wisdom. The crystal domes on the Star Home came from Selab.

properties.name: Selaggis
properties.description: Selaggis was the Selaggis system's primary star. It was the site of the Battle of Selaggis.

properties.name: Selenius
properties.description: Selenius may refer to one of the following:

properties.name: Seline
properties.description: Seline was a remote outpost planet—cold, rocky, harsh and barren—with a Jedi starport, located in the Dalonbian sector of the galaxy's Tingel Arm.

properties.name: Selitan
properties.description: Selitan was a mining planet in the Gordian Reach.

properties.name: Sellasas
properties.description: Sellasas was a planet with an Imperial and civilian presence soon after the Battle of Yavin.

properties.name: Selnesh
properties.description: Selnesh was a notorious Imperial prison planet orbiting a pale blue star in the Mid Rim. It was a barren, gray, rocky world devoid of vegetation or color. It had a single white, domed building, the Selnesh Imperial Detention Center from which the Rebel Alliance rescued Gebnerret Vibrion.

properties.name: Selsor
properties.description: Selsor was a terrestrial astronomical object located in the Selsor system, a part of the Zarracina sector in the Trailing Sectors portion of the Expansion Region. It featured several continents.

properties.name: Seltaya Major
properties.description: Seltaya Major was a planet in the Mieru'kar sector of the Outer Rim.

properties.name: Seltos
properties.description: Seltos was a planet in the Mid Rim. Its Sommin City was home to the largest Tarro remnant. Its primary industries included agriculture, lumber production, and mining of valuable ores. Visitors to Seltos' nature preserves provided a small boost to the economy as well. Natives of Seltos were considered congenial and pleasant.

properties.name: Selvaris
properties.description: Selvaris was a backwater planet of little significance during the Galactic Civil War. It was the closest inhabited planet to the Bilbringi system.

properties.name: Sembla
properties.description: Sembla, historically known as Utavurk, was an oceanic Outer Rim planet that was the homeworld of the nomadic Vurk, including Coleman Trebor. It was in the Outer Rim Territories near the Tion Hegemony, at the far end of the Perlemian Trade Route.

properties.name: Senex
properties.description: Senex was an agriworld in the Senex sector. Offworlders were restricted to the planet's space stations and a small number of spaceports.

properties.name: Sennatt
properties.description: Sennatt was a world located within the Bothan sector, on the Mid Rim of the galaxy. Colonized by the Bothans, it was one of their industrial hubs. Publictechnic's main manufacturing plant was located on Sennatt.

properties.name: Sennex
properties.description: The Sennex or Sennex Pirates were slave traders from the Sennex system. They were considered among the most despicable pirates in the galaxy during the time of the Galactic Civil War.

properties.name: Seoul
properties.description: Seoul was an astronomical object located in the galaxy's Wild Space.

properties.name: Serat
properties.description: Serat was the Seratian homeworld. The aggressive nocturnal Tymps were native to Serat, and considered pests.

properties.name: Seregar
properties.poi: Callamvor Hotel, Cather Taan's Gun Shop, CrossWind Saloon, Sutloo's Trading Post, Trigdale refinery,
properties.description: Seregar was an Outer Rim jungle planet with a breathable atmosphere and green and blue vegetation. The planet's flora included a carnivorous plant, while an example of its fauna was the predator known as the ravenbeast. Years before the Battle of Endor, several corporations ran mining operations on Seregar; however, once the natural resources they were harvesting ran out, the companies abandoned the jungle world. Eventually, the planet attracted smugglers, with locales in the settlement of Storrd Township, such as the CrossWind Saloon and Cather Taan's Gun Shop, catering to their needs.

properties.name: Serenity
properties.description: Serenity was the leader of the Force Priestesses.

properties.name: Serenno
properties.poi: Aparian WastesBelsallian SeaBorgin CastleBoxCarannia SpaceportDooku's palaceGreat Assembly HouseThe Spike
properties.description: Serenno was a planet in the Outer Rim Territories. It was known for its aristocratic Counts, the most famous of them being Dooku. It was also well known for its long history of resisting authority.

properties.name: Sermeria
properties.description: Sermeria was an agriworld in the Expansion Region.

properties.name: Sern Prime
properties.description: Sern Prime was a planet located in the Sern sector, in relative proximity to the world of Ghorman. Sern Prime was located in the Colonies region. The leader of Sern Prime held the title of president.

properties.name: Sernpidal
properties.poi: Business district, Darth Zhorrid's Sernpidal estate, Scherp's Estate, Sernpidal starport,
properties.description: Sernpidal, the fifth planet in the Julevian system, was the adopted home planet of the Sernpidalian species, and one of the first planets attacked by the Yuuzhan Vong during their invasion of the galaxy. Orbiting only 115,000 kilometers from its sun, it was the most populous world of its sector. Rango Tel was from the world.

properties.name: Serpine
properties.description: Serpine was a planet known for gambling palaces. It was ruled by an "emperor-governor."

properties.name: Serroco
properties.description: Serroco, the homeworld of the Stereb species, was a planet in the Ploo sector of the Expansion Region. A muddy world, Serroco was constantly buffeted by ferocious storms and tornadoes that often forced the Stereb to retreat to underground shelters and catacombs. The world was dotted by the grand stone Stereb cities and newer settlements populated by Humans from the Galactic Republic. Serroco was a full member of the Republic, and when the galactic government went to war with the Mandalorian warrior clans in 3963 BBY, the planet became a flashpoint in the growing conflict.

properties.name: Sesid
properties.description: Sesid was a planet in the Sesid system, and home to the Draedan. During the Galactic Civil War, it was run by Governor Arvel Trace.

properties.name: Sespe
properties.description: The Sespe system was a star system located within the Tharin sector in the Outer Rim region of the galaxy, on the Sisar Run. The system contained the planet Topa and its moon, Torega.

properties.name: Sestina
properties.description: Sestina may refer to one of the following:

properties.name: Sestooine
properties.description: Sestooine was an Imperial world. It was located in the Outer Rim Territories.

properties.name: Sestria
properties.description: Sestria was a banking world in the Testarr sector. It was considered corrupt and not as trustworthy as Muunilinst.

properties.name: Seswenna
properties.description: Seswenna was an Outer Rim Territories planet located in the Seswenna sector. By 3699 BBY, Seswenna lay on what would eventually become the Hydian Way super-hyperroute. However, the Hydian Way had shifted by 1004 BBY to go through the Eriadu system instead. During the late period of the Galactic Republic's rule, Seswenna served as the sector capital, but that status would similarly pass to the planet Eriadu over time.

properties.name: Setolio
properties.description: Setolio was a planet in Tapani sector's Setolio system.

properties.name: Setor
properties.description: Setor was a Colonies world. A group of colonists were persecuted on, and then exiled from, Setor nearly a decade before the Battle of Yavin. The colonists intended to settle the Outer Rim Territories world Wetyin's Colony but changes in financial support from the Galactic Empire left them virtually abandoned. The colonists then searched for a new homeworld, and the scout Lile Gorsek eventually became convinced that the moon Yavin 4 would over time allow the Wetyin's Colony's inhabitants to rival and even surpass their original home, Setor.

properties.name: Sev Tok
properties.description: Sev Tok was a planet in the Mid Rim's Kurost sector.

properties.name: Sevarcos
properties.description: Sevarcos was a planet in the galaxy's Outer Rim Territories that was the site of a battle in the months after the Battle of Endor. During the battle, the New Republic successfully liberated at least one spice mine that had been operating on slave labor under the control of the Empire. The area of the spice mine was dry, dusty, and surrounded by canyons, and at least one of the slavemasters was Zygerrian.

properties.name: Sevari
properties.description: The Sevari were the Human native habitants of the spice rich Sevarcos II. Not much was known of their history, but it was speculated that they were the descendants of an expedition that took place early in the history of the Galactic Republic. Historical data suggest a connection between the Sevari and a colony ship called the Sevari Cabal which was lost.

properties.name: Seven Flames
properties.description: Seven Flames was a planet located in the Rayter sector of the Outer Rim Territories. During the Galactic Civil War, the Alliance to Restore the Republic established a support base on the planet, which the Rebels used to launch a diplomatic operation to the planet Karra in an attempt to gain an alliance with the native Karrans. However, the mission was unsuccessful, though the Rebel diplomatic team was able to return to the base on Seven Flames with Karra's Imperial Governor Darryn Edalm in custody.

properties.name: Sevetta
properties.description: Sevetta was a planet with an atmosphere toxic to Humans.

properties.name: Seylott
properties.description: Seylott was the homeworld of the Seylott species. It was covered in dense forests and home to the Disciples of Shaa.

properties.name: Seyugi
properties.description: Seyugi was an astronomical object located in the Seyugi system of the Arrowhead, a region in the Slice portion of the Core Worlds. Seyugi fell within the borders of the Galactic Republic around 22,000 BBY.

properties.name: Shadda Nebula
properties.description: The Shadda Nebula was a collection of gases in the Toblain sector of the Outer Rim Territories, at galactic coordinates O-18. It was formed by the star Shadda sometime before 43 ABY, when it expanded to become a red giant—a post-main sequence star, which, along with the other red giants, formed than less than one percent of the total stars in the galaxy—and shed its outer layers. Shadda then began to cool into a white dwarf, a compact white star, whose type constituted seven percent of all stars in the galaxy.

properties.name: Shadda-Bi-Boran
properties.description: Shadda-Bi-Boran was an Outer Rim planet destroyed by a supernova in 38 BBY.

properties.name: Shador
properties.description: Shador was a Mid Rim planet on the Gamor Run. It was the Shadorian homeworld and had such a foul atmosphere, that it was painful for Humans to breathe. The planet was dominated by swamps, and the various towns were built on pylons rising above the wet terrain.

properties.name: Shadren
properties.description: Shadren V was a planet in the Outer Rim's Shadren system. It had an Imperial naval base, which was attacked by Alliance to Restore the Republic during the Galactic Civil War.

properties.name: Shafr
properties.description: Shafr was a planet in the Toblain sector of the Outer Rim.

properties.name: Shalam
properties.description: Shalam was a planet bombarded by the Emperor's Disciple under Ishin-Il-Raz during the height of the Galactic Empire.

properties.name: Shallow March
properties.description: Shallow March was an Outer Rim planet.

properties.name: Shalm
properties.description: Shalm was the planet where Mount Ganton was located, the highest mountain in its range. An Imperial garrison on the western face of Ganton was abandoned after the Battle of Endor, only to become the base of the Pendarran's Revenge, led by Kolor Delan.

properties.name: Shalyvane
properties.description: Shalyvane was a planet in the Outer Rim Territories and the homeworld of the Em'liy.

properties.name: Shar'Ack
properties.description: Shar'Ack was a planet located in the Shar'Ack system, a part of the Atrivis sector in the New Territories portion of the Outer Rim Territories.

properties.name: Sharb
properties.description: Sharb was a planet located in the Sharb system of the Unknown Regions' Chiss Space. The hyperlane known as the Path of the Houses linked it to the Noris and Ornfra systems. An outlying colony of the sentient Chiss species, Sharb was home to one of the Ruling Families that ruled over the Chiss Ascendancy, the government of the Chiss.

properties.name: Sharlissia
properties.description: Sharlissia was an astronomical object located in the Outer Rim Territories and Trailing Sectors regions, in grid square N-18 of the Standard Galactic Grid. A hyperspace route linked it to the celestial body Kabal.

properties.name: Shasa
properties.description: Shasa was a Force-sensitive Selkath female who lived during the Jedi Civil War, a conflict initiated by the Dark Lord of the Sith Darth Revan and his Sith apprentice, Darth Malak. In the war's final year, Shasa and other Selkath youth were lured into the Sith Empire's Embassy on the Selkath homeworld of Manaan by an Iridonian mercenary. Shasa and her friends joined the Sith, who brainwashed them using mind tricks. The Selkath learned the ways of the dark side under the Embassy's Dark Jedi Master.

properties.name: Shasfath
properties.description: The Shasfath Cluster was an Inner Rim star cluster. Following the Imperial occupation of Cloud City on the planet Bespin in 3 ABY, the Rebel Alliance was forced to search for other sources of the important Tibanna gas. Alliance Captain Eedan therefore tasked a group of Rebel agents with surveying gas giant planets in several star systems, as well as in the Shasfath Cluster. The exploration of the star cluster eventually proved fruitless, and the Rebel scouts continued with their search on the planet Taloraan.

properties.name: Shatuun
properties.description: Shatuun was a planet in the Kathol Outback region of the Outer Rim Territories. The planet was covered in towering mountains and plagued by fierce electrical storms. It was an isolated planet, seldom visited by travelers en route to Danoor.

properties.name: Shaum Hii
properties.description: Shaum Hii was a planet in Tragan Cluster of the Outer Rim Territories.

properties.name: Shawken
properties.description: Shawken was a Core World. It boasted one of the most ancient civilizations in the known galaxy, and was the home of the Shawkenese. Shawken was connected to Coruscant by the Shawken Spur.

properties.name: Shawti
properties.description: Shawti was an agriworld where the Desilijic kajidic bred Klatooinian slaves, such as Umpass-stay.

properties.name: Shaylin
properties.description: Shaylin 18 was a celestial body located in the Shaylin system, a part of the Pakuuni sector in the Slice portion of the Outer Rim Territories. The hyperlane known as the Overic Griplink linked it to the Pakuuni and Turkana systems. At some point between 0 ABY and 2 ABY, the military forces of the Rebel Alliance fought the Battle of Shaylin 18 there.

properties.name: Shaymore
properties.description: The planet Shaymore was located in the Immerian Outback of the Expansion Region. It was the homeworld of Sessehshellah, and was mined by the Empire for hydrocarbon-based fossil fuels. The native Sessehshellah, with help from the Alliance to Restore the Republic, took up arms against the Imperial invaders.

properties.name: Shedu Maad
properties.description: Shedu Maad was a planet in the Hapes Cluster, located within its Transitory Mists region. It was used as a hidden base for the Jedi Coalition after they evacuated their temporary base at Endor. It was here that the Coalition defeated Darth Caedus and ended the Second Galactic Civil War. A Jedi academy was established on the planet after the war and was still in use as of 44 ABY.

properties.name: Shelkonwa
properties.poi: Catacombs, Greencliff Regional Spaceport, Makrin Main Spaceport, Shelkonwa governor's palace,
properties.description: Shelkonwa was a planet in the Shelsha sector of the Colonies.

properties.name: Shella
properties.description: Shella could refer to any of the following:

properties.name: Sheris
properties.description: Sheris was a planet in the Belsmuth sector of the Outer Rim.

properties.name: Shesharile
properties.description: Shesharile was a gas giant world that was located within the Shesharile system, in the Minos Cluster.

properties.name: Sheva
properties.description: Sheva was a planet in the Sheva system in Tapani sector. It was a backwater in the Freeworlds Territory. It had a liberal government that did little to threaten smugglers and other criminals.

properties.name: Shi'kar Straits
properties.description: The Shi'kar Straits was an asteroid belt formed after a comet hit the homeworld of the Shi'kar species, obliterating it into many pieces. It was located in the Nembus sector of the Outer Rim Territories.

properties.name: Shibric
properties.description: Shibric was an Inner Rim planet situated on the Hydian Way. The crew of the Hopskip claimed that Shibric was their destination when they were captured by the Galactic Empire.

properties.name: Shifa
properties.description: The Shifa system was a star system located in the Tapani sector's Calipsa Province, near the Calipsa system.

properties.name: Shiffrin
properties.description: Shiffrin was an Outer Rim Territories planet located in the Tammuz sector. Constable Kallin Bremen maintained law and order in a small village there. At one point, a Shiffrin farmer discovered what turned out to be large deposits of the valuable ore hfredium, and the Galactic Empire subsequently established a garrison there and began confiscating the properties of local landowners. Bremen was eventually executed after planning a peaceful demonstration against the confiscations, and his son, Jak Bremen, went on to leave the planet.

properties.name: Shihon
properties.description: Shihon was a terrestrial planet located in the Shihon system of the Unknown Regions' Chiss Space. A hyperlane linked the world to the Ool and Oyokal systems. The planet's surface featured several oceans.

properties.name: Shili
properties.description: Shili was the homeworld of the Togrutas located in the Ehosiq sector.

properties.name: Shimia
properties.description: Shimia was the Pacithhip homeworld and was located in the Outer Rim Territories, near the Corellian Run. It was represented directly in the Galactic Senate 19 BBY. Following the rise of the New Republic, increasing numbers of Pacitthip left their homeworld to "seek their own path" and find a career in the galaxy abroad, rather than a career on Shimia determined by caste.

properties.name: Shimmer
properties.description: Shimmer was a planet located in the Rayter sector.

properties.name: Shinbone
properties.description: Shinbone was a hardscrabble mining world in Wild Space. It was hit by the Hardan plague. Beilert Valance was born on Shinbone.

properties.name: Shindra
properties.description: The Shindra system was a star system located in the Tapani sector's Melantha Province, between the Procopia and Rianon systems.

properties.name: Shintel
properties.description: Shintel was a planet located in the Shintel system of the Kathol sector, which was part of the Outer Rim Territories. A remote, muddy, and wet world, Shintel's only distinction was that it was the location of a supply depot established by Warlord Moff Kentor Sarne as part of his military forces. Commanded by veteran Imperial Army officer Colonel Heget, the depot was intended to be used by Sarne in the event that the Galactic Empire ever decided to attempt to reabsorb the Kathol sector.

properties.name: Shiva
properties.description: Shiva IV was a planet in Wild Space that was noted for its extremely remote location, far from the auspices of the Galactic Empire. A world with a history soaked in blood, Shiva IV was marked by generations of warfare between the Human Calian Confederacy and the Twelve Tribes of T'Syriél, which forged both peoples into extremely formidable fighters. In 2 ABY, that conflict was finally brought to an end when Calian Warlord Aron Peacebringer signed the Concordat of Peace with T'Syriél Demarch Kéral Longknife. Although the Galactic Empire attempted to conquer Shiva IV one year later, Peacebringer and elements of the Rebel Alliance repelled the invasion.

properties.name: Shogun
properties.description: Shogun was a planet conquered by and aligned with the Mandalorians.

properties.name: Shola
properties.description: Shola was a volcanic planet, with constant groundquakes and corrosive air. Its core was a chamber of icy gas while the outside was searing hot. The planet was also almost impossible to explore, with falling volcanic ash and dangerous mining shafts.

properties.name: Shoon
properties.description: Shoon was a planet in the Senex sector of the Mid Rim.

properties.name: Shopani
properties.description: The Shopani system was a star system located in the Tapani sector's Cadriaan Province, between Gilliana system and Pavia system.

properties.name: Shotem
properties.description: The planet Shotem was the mining site for specialized lightsaber crystals which pulsed and caused the lightsaber to be more powerful. The Jedi of the planet were known to wear visors, robes, gloves, and boots which were unique to the planet in addition to using a different type of lightsaber hilt to that of other Jedi.

properties.name: Shownar
properties.description: Shownar was a paradise planet near the Torch Nebula. At night, the planet was illuminated by the nebula. Wind blowing through the vertag crystals created the Shownar Lullaby. It was an Imperial planet, though de facto ruled by the crime lord Oro Freatt.

properties.name: Shramar
properties.description: Shramar was a planet that was controlled by the Imperial Remnant during the time of the Yuuzhan Vong War.

properties.name: Shrokaan
properties.description: Shrokaan was a planet located in the Baroli sector of the Expansion Region. During the Great Jedi Purge, Darth Vader executed a Jedi Master on the twelve-bladed satellite of Shrokaan by exposing him to the void of space, as he was too dangerous to capture alive.

properties.name: Shuldene
properties.description: Shuldene was a planet in the Yarith sector of the Outer Rim Territories' Greater Javin region. Formerly a waterworld with abundant aquatic life, Shuldene froze solid after undergoing an orbital shift. Tourists occasionally visited the planet to amaze at the carcasses of massive sea creatures poking through the glassy ice surface.

properties.name: Shulxi
properties.description: Shulxi was a Galactic Core world known for its beachside resorts.

properties.name: Shumari
properties.description: Shumari was a planet in the Parmel sector of the Outer Rim Territories. The Tusken Raider KkH'Oar'Rrhr was rumored to have traveled to this planet to confront the Demon Outlander who wiped out his village, otherwise known as Darth Vader.

properties.name: Shumavar
properties.description: Shumavar was a planet located in the Outer Rim Territories.

properties.name: Shumogi
properties.description: Shumogi was a planet located in the Core Worlds.

properties.name: Shusugaunt
properties.description: Shusugaunt was a high-gravity planet located in the Outer Rim Territories' Raioballo sector. It was the homeworld of the warlike Shusugaunt species. Millennia before the Battle of Yavin, the spacefaring Shusugaunt encountered the sentient Anx of the nearby planet Gravlex Med. The former conquered and enslaved the latter, relocating many Anx to Shusugaunt. The Anx could not survive the planet's high gravity, however, and eventually perished.

properties.name: Shuxl
properties.description: Shuxl was a star located in the Shuxl system of the Yarith sector, near the Ivax Nebula. There were no planets or asteroids in orbit around this star, only a series of dust-filled rings.

properties.name: Sibisime
properties.description: Sibisime was a planet in the Mid Rim. The slicer Zakarisz Ghent was living there, in Saraban City in 4 ABY when he was approached by a man who offered him a job if he went to Chibias and gave him a spaceliner ticket. On Chibias, Ghent failed to make his connection with the mysterious man and got caught up in a plot involving stolen government secrets, only to be rescued by Mara Jade. After a few days adventuring with the ex-Hand, Ghent and Jade parted company and the youth finally made his connection with his mysterious employer—Talon Karrde.

properties.name: Sif-Alula
properties.description: Sif-Alula was an Expansion Region astronomical object located in the Trestis sector. It was the namesake of the Sif-Alulan process, in which the Sisters of the Machinesmith studied and upgraded Galactic Republic technology in the build-up of the Waymancy Storm of 7811 BBY. During that conflict, the Republic captured weapons and starship power generators of the Signatories of Waymancy at Sif-Alula, allowing the Republic to study the military technology of its enemy.

properties.name: Sif-Uwana
properties.description: Sif-Uwana was a planet within the Colonies area of the galaxy. It was the homeworld of the individuals known as Sif-Uwani and was administered by the Sif-Uwana Council. The planet was controlled by Alsakan during the Alsakan Conflicts but was eventually lost to the Galactic Republic. At some point, the Emperor's agent Mara Jade visited the world.

properties.name: Sifuchi
properties.description: Sifuchi was the home planet of Tan Dicium.

properties.name: Sigil
properties.description: Sigil was a planet in the Sigil system. The Sith Terrak Morrhage trained there.

properties.name: Sika
properties.description: Sika was a planet in the Expansion Region that was invaded by opportunistic Chekut forces during the Second Galactic Civil War. It was home to the Sikan.

properties.name: Sikurd
properties.description: Sikurd was a planet located in the Sikurd system within the Tynquay sector in the Outer Rim Territories, and it was the homeworld of the Sikurdian species. It was also where Sikurdian battle-axes were made.

properties.name: Sil'Lume
properties.description: Sil'Lume was the name of the primary star in the Sil'Lume system.

properties.name: Siluria
properties.description: Siluria III was a planet in the Siluria system of the Atravis sector in the Outer Rim Territories.

properties.name: Silver Station
properties.description: Silver Station, previously known as Machenry Station, was a hidden resistance space station outpost drifting near the Dragonflower Nebula in the Doldur sector, in the Mid Rim.

properties.name: Silversisi
properties.description: Silversisi was a planet located in the Inner Rim. It was known for the Library of Silversisi.

properties.name: Silvestri
properties.description: Silvestri may refer to:

properties.name: Sim'char'ser
properties.description: Sim'char'ser was a planet in the Outer Rim Territories. It received shipments of Roonstones from the mines of Quilken.

properties.name: Simbarc
properties.description: Simbarc was an Outer Rim Territories mining planet located in the Cadma sector. It had both rich ore deposits as well as several famous casinos, at one of which around 1 BBY, the smuggler Han Solo was caught cheating. The casino's security team pursued Solo and his partner, Chewbacca, in a speeder chase that ended with the two smugglers ultimately escaping to the hangar where their starship waited for them.

properties.name: Simento-Threk
properties.description: Simento-Threk was a planet in the Meram sector of the Outer Rim. It was the homeworld of mOKDAR 15.

properties.name: Simocadia
properties.description: Simocadia was a planet located in the Inner Rim and the homeworld to the Mosciive species.

properties.name: Simoom
properties.description: The Simoom was a Maelstrom-class battle cruiser that, along with the rest of its class, was in service to the Republic Navy during the Clone Wars between the Galactic Republic and the Confederacy of Independent Systems. After the Republic transitioned into the Galactic Empire, the remaining Maelstrom-class battle cruisers complemented the Imperial Navy until they were either broken up, used as test beds, or mothballed. The Simoom was one of the starships to be mothballed, but was later under the control of the Rebel Alliance, who deployed it as part of the Alliance Navy during the Galactic Civil War against the Empire.

properties.name: Simpla
properties.description: Simpla was the Simpla system's primary star.

properties.name: Sinded
properties.description: Sinded was a terrestrial astronomical object located in the Sinded system of the D'Aelgoth sector, a part of the Western Reaches portion of the Mid Rim. By 7 ABY, New Republic General Crix Masst was present on Sinded. While there, the assassin Morteos wired a bomb into the repulsorlift generator of Masst's personal speeder, which resulted in the death of the general. When Morteos attempted to escape Sinded aboard his modified freighter, Y-wing starfighters on patrol opened fire, nearly shooting the assassin's vessel down. Morteos was ultimately able to escape, however. New Republic General Airen Cracken later mentioned the assassination on Sinded in an entry of the datafile Wanted by Cracken dedicated to Morteos.

properties.name: Sinjan
properties.description: Sinjan was a planet located in the Albarrio sector of the Outer Rim.

properties.name: Sinkar
properties.description: Sinkar was a planet in the Lawreys system in Fakir sector, its surface covered in frozen oxygen. It was the Sinkar homeworld. The Galactic Empire established a garrison on the planet during the Galactic Civil War

properties.name: Sinsang
properties.description: Sinsang was an industrious world located in the Sinsang system, a part of the Raioballo sector in the New Territories portion of the Outer Rim Territories. It was situated on the hyperlane known as the Veragi Trade Route, which connected it to the Anx Minor and Dantooine systems.

properties.name: Sintheti
properties.description: Sintheti was a terrestrial astronomical object located in the Sintheti system, a part of the Noonian sector in the New Territories portion of the Outer Rim Territories. Its surface featured crags.

properties.name: Sinton
properties.description: The planet Sinton was located in the Sinton system, a part of the Mid Rim's Rago sector. It lay along the Rago Run hyperlane, which connected it to the Moro and Gilatter systems. Sinton was populated by non-Humans, and at some point by 3 ABY, the planet was subjugated by the Galactic Empire, which subjected the planet's inhabitants to slave labor.

properties.name: Sionia
properties.description: Sionia was home to the Sionian Skups, a near-human species. The planet was noted for the number of master thieves it produced.

properties.name: Sirdar
properties.description: Sirdar was a planet in a remote region of the galaxy. At some point, a small population of the insectivorous winged xendrites was placed on Sirdar to help with insect control. The xendrites reproduced at an astounding rate and soon overran the planet.

properties.name: Sirpar
properties.poi: Arctic Environments Combat RangeDeep Ocean Operations CampNonessential Equipment Storage and Disposal Facility 456,
properties.description: Sirpar, a large planet with little natural resources, was an Imperial high-gravity training center and the Eklaad homeworld. It was near Tatooine. It was the primary Imperial training facility in its sector. Stories about Sirpar—usually not good ones—were known throughout the Empire, even by soldiers that were trained elsewhere.

properties.name: Sisk
properties.description: Sisk was a planet that orbited a red dwarf star. It was the homeworld of the Sic-Six. It cooled when its star suffered partial atomic collapse.

properties.name: Siskeen
properties.description: Siskeen was a planet located in the Hunnoverrs sector of the Outer Rim Territories.

properties.name: Sittana
properties.description: Sittana was a planet with rivers and falls of fire. Holographic information of Sittana was stored in the Anywhere Room at Hologram Fun World, so that visitors to the attraction could be virtually transported to the locale. Sittana marble was used as a building material.

properties.name: Sivoria
properties.description: Sivoria was a planet located in the Hapes Cluster of the Inner Rim. It was the homeworld of the Sivorian species.

properties.name: Skako
properties.poi: Clouds of Cormelish, Power Mounds of the Elders,
properties.description: Skako was an ecumenopolis on the Hydian Way in the galactic core and homeworld to the Skakoan species. Though most of Skako was covered by urban sprawl, some examples of the planet's original ecosystem had been preserved in the form of vast fields of sprawling vines.

properties.name: Skann
properties.description: Skann was a terrestrial planet located in the Skann system, a part of the Outer Rim Territories' Astal sector. It was inhabited by farmers who grew crops such as Dust-Corn and Dry Gene Wheat. The farmers made the unique beverage Skannbult Likker, which was possibly the most volatile fire-water in the galaxy, from surplus crops, distilling it in rock basins.

properties.name: Skarpos
properties.description: Skarpos was a barbaric world under the sway of the Sith Lord Malakite. It was located in the Grumani sector. It was a stormy planet with many trenches, and a forbidding-looking mesa. In 1032 BBY, the planet was invaded and occupied by rival Sith Lord Odion's Odionate military forces. Later, Aunt Zoojoo revealed to Jedi Knight Kerra Holt that Skarpos was the location of the Helm of Ieldis, an ancient Sith artifact created prior to the Great Hyperspace War which was the target of Odion's Project Pandemonium. Disguised as a Novitiate named "Mercy", Kerra and the other Novitiates returned to Skarpos and were immediately besieged by Malakite's reinforcements and Sith Lord Daiman's forces.

properties.name: Skartis
properties.description: Skärtis was a resort world located in the Senex sector that was maintained by House Araba. Its seven moons were famous for their complicated orbits. Seeing all seven in the sky at once was said to be a lucky omen.

properties.name: Skeebo
properties.description: Skeebo, also known as the Jewel of the Five Systems, was a rocky Outer Rim Territories planet located in the Shadola sector. At some point long before 10 ABY, the Skeebos of Skeeb erected pyramidal stone funeral palaces in a region of the planet known as the sacred valley. On their honeymoon that year, the Hutts Gorga Desilijic Aarrpo and Anachro visited Skeebo. During the pair's tour, the Skaver swoop gang kidnapped Anachro, holding her hostage for a one-million-credit-large ransom. In response, Gorga hired the bounty hunter Boba Fett to rescue his wife, while Anachro's father, Orko, also traveled to Skeebo with the same goal in mind.

properties.name: Skine
properties.description: Skine was a planet in the Outer Rim Territories and the location of the Skine Bounty Hunter College. During the Cold War, the xenophobic Advozse Hegemony used the prototype Hammer Station battle station to bombard Skine's capital city when the planet refused to surrender to the Hegemony.

properties.name: Skone
properties.description: The Skone system was a system in Brak sector of the Expansion Region. It contained the planet Skone II, which was capable of foodstuff production as well as a degree of manufacturing capabilities.

properties.name: Skor
properties.description: Skor may refer to the following items:

properties.name: Skorrupon
properties.description: Skorrupon was a planet located in the Trans-Vulta sector of the Mid Rim. Skorrupon was the site of several notable battles: during the early Imperial Period, anti-Imperial agents Arani Korden, Rorworr, and Deel Surool intercepted High Inquisitor Volytar's shuttle outside of his personal Star Destroyer over the world. The three thus became known as the Heroes of Skorrupon. Later, in 0 ABY, Rebel forces attempted to ambush the newly christened Super Star Destroyer Executor above Skorrupon, in one of the Rebellion's first encounters with the powerful flagship. The Rebel force was utterly destroyed, with fleeing pilot Vrad Dodonna the only survivor. Skorrupon was also attacked by the Yuuzhan Vong during the Yuuzhan Vong War.

properties.name: Skustell Cluster
properties.description: The Skustell Cluster was a star cluster located within the Tarabba sector in the Outer Rim region of the galaxy which contained the planet Skustell.

properties.name: Skuumaa
properties.description: Skuumaa was a planet contested during the Clone Wars. Delta Squad traveled there ahead of the main Republic assault in order to sabotage strategic targets and "prepare the battlefield", shortly after their involvement in an anti-terror operation on Coruscant.

properties.name: Skye
properties.poi: Canaitith Mountain, Skye Citadel, Entyrmion, Highlands, S'kytri Council Tower, Mount Krisklar,
properties.description: Skye, designated Marat V by the Galactic Republic, was a terrestrial planet in the Outer Rim Territories and the home of the S'kytri people. Remaining isolated from the wider galaxy, the world attempted to gain admittance into the Council of Neutral Systems during the Clone Wars but was interrupted by an invasion led by Zeta Magnus.

properties.name: Skynara
properties.description: Skynara was an astronomical object located in the Skynara system, a part of the Outer Rim Territories' Skine sector. It was situated at the endpoint of the hyperlane known as the Five Veils Route.

properties.name: Sleheyron
properties.description: Sleheyron was a planet in Hutt Space. Although it was based on slave trade, its powerful economy made Sleheyron one of the most important Hutt worlds.

properties.name: Slession
properties.description: Slession may refer to one of the following:

properties.name: Sljee
properties.description: Sljee was the Sljee homeworld.

properties.name: Sloogaria
properties.description: The Sloogaria system was a star system that was located within the Rseik sector, in the Outer Rim Territories region of the galaxy. The system was home to the sentient Sloogarian species.

properties.name: Slotern
properties.description: Slotern was a world where a battle was fought between the Galactic Empire and a resistance group sometime between the years 19 BBY and 1 BBY. The world was located in the Slotern system of the Wazta sector, which was located in the Outer Rim Territories.

properties.name: Sluis Van
properties.poi: Sluis Van Shipyards, , Sluis Van Orbit Dock V-475, Outer Starfighter Base, Sluis Control, Sluis Van Central space station, ,
properties.description: Sluis Van was the primary planet in the Sluis sector of the Outer Rim Territories. It was the homeworld of the Sluissi race and the location of the famous Sluis Van Shipyards.

properties.name: Sluudren
properties.description: Sluudren was a planet in the Outer Rim. It was the homeworld of the Sludir. It was located in the Chorlian sector of the galaxy.

properties.name: Smarck
properties.description: Smarck was a planet in Outer Rim Territories, Cademimu sector, Smarck system.

properties.name: Smarteel
properties.description: Smarteel was a desert planet in Wild Space.

properties.name: Smuggler's Run
properties.description: Smuggler's Run was a treacherous asteroid field that harbored a plethora of smugglers and illegal activities, located near Wrea.

properties.name: Sneeve
properties.description: Sneeve was the homeworld of the Sneevel species. It was located in the Kastolar sector of the Mid Rim.

properties.name: Snevu
properties.description: Snevu was a planet in the Unknown Regions where the Battle of Snevu was fought between the Killiks and the Chiss.

properties.name: Sochi
properties.description: Sochi was an Imperial vacation world, located in the Sochi system. It was the location of the stormtrooper retirement home, Troopers' Rest.

properties.name: Soco-Jarel
properties.description: Soco-Jarel Spaceport was a large spaceport on the planet Socorro administered by Aquato Boliscon. It rivaled Vakeyya in size.

properties.name: Socorro
properties.poi: Doaba Badlands, Rym MountainsJudges of the DeadMadraRazoor MountainsJedi AcademyImperial Mission temple, Crimson Axe, Killee Wasteland, Black Dust TavernGolden Gorg Cantina, Soco-Jarel SpaceportSarlacc's PeakCarbon Score Wastes
properties.description: Socorro was a planet in the Outer Rim Territories with a reputation as a smuggler haven. It was the homeworld of Lando Calrissian.

properties.name: Sojourn
properties.description: Sojourn, also known as "the Hunters' Moon," was a satellite moon of an unknown planet in the Carrion sector of the Outer Rim Territories. It was also the ancient-fortress home and personal retreat of the Sith Lord Darth Plagueis.

properties.name: Solacton
properties.description: The Solacton system was in a remote part of the Periphery. However, a number of hyperspace routes did pass through the system en route to the Iotran system.

properties.name: Solaest
properties.description: Solaest was the site of the Solaest Uprising against the Galactic Empire, which was suppressed by the Imperial Navy. The Rebel Alliance and Princess Leia Organa, aboard her cruiser the Tantive IV, secretly aided those fleeing the Empire.

properties.name: Solanus
properties.description: Solanus was a planet in the Solanus system, located within the Outer Rim's Dominus sector. Solanus was home to a sentient ocean that covered it, a murky sea so rich in chemicals that it could perform billions of thought processes within its depths, which classified it as a super-brain. However, like other super-brains, the ocean was too large to move around independently and kept to itself, often contemplating its own existence. It refrained from participating in galactic affairs, instead spending its time playing with itself by shaping and reforming intricate crystal structures.

properties.name: Solarine
properties.description: Solarine was a location in the galaxy. Ziro the Hutt and Sy Snootles had planned to go there to share the rest of their lives together, but Snootles killed Ziro as an act of revenge for abandoning her.

properties.name: Solay
properties.description: Solay was the main planet in the Solay system in the Dominus sector of the Outer Rim Territories. Home to a variety of species, Solay remained in the hands of a despot for half a century, before the Rebel Alliance hero Luke Skywalker came to the assistance of the resisters. The Rebel victory was only short-lived, however, as the Galactic Empire quickly gained control over Solay, forcing Skywalker to flee.

properties.name: Solem
properties.description: Solem was a planet in the Outer Rim Territories and the homeworld of an unidentified species.

properties.name: Solloops
properties.description: The solloops hairstyle, also known as the solloop style, was a wild hairstyle popular on Coruscant in 22 BBY. It was easily recognizable, as each lock of hair ascended from the wearer's head before terminating in a wild loop. Nyrat Agira had this hairstyle. The solloops hairstyle originated from the Solloops system.

properties.name: Somavva
properties.description: Somavva was a planet located in the Tharin sector of the Outer Rim.

properties.name: Somov Rit
properties.description: Somov Rit was a sparsely populated green world with a native Human population.
