During the New Sith Wars, Jedi scout Torr Snapit came to the planet seeking Force-sensitive recruits, but his only luck was with three young children: Rain, Tomcat and Bug. Rain later helped rebuild the Sith Order as Darth Bane's apprentice, Darth Zannah.

properties.name: Sondarr
properties.description: Sondarr was a planet in the Sertar sector of the Outer Rim Territories.

properties.name: Sonn Vilmari
properties.description: Sonn Vilmari was a planet in the Colundra sector of the Outer Rim.

properties.name: Sontor
properties.description: The Sontor system was located within the Tungra sector, a part of the Western Reaches portion of the Outer Rim Territories. The system shared its name with the freighter Sontor Skipper.

properties.name: Sooma
properties.description: Sooma was a planet of grassy plains and an oxygen-filled atmosphere. It was homeworld to the Soomans.

properties.name: Sorella
properties.description: Sorella was a planet in the Sorella system in Tapani sector. Sorella was also one of the Freeworlds Territory. Also, it was a member of the Three Ellas, with a liberal government looser about crime and smuggling than most Tapani worlds.

properties.name: Sorfina
properties.description: Sorfina was a planet. Occasionally, gaudy artworks were requested by buyers on Sorfina.

properties.name: Sorimow
properties.description: Sorimow was a planet within the Sorimow system in the Pacanth Reach of the Outer Rim Territories.

properties.name: Sorjus
properties.description: Sorjus was the Basic name for the home planet of the Paaerduag. The true name was only pronounceable and understandable by the Paaerduag. The planet was far off from the Perlemian Trade Route.

properties.name: Sorl
properties.description: The planet of Sorl was Jedi Master Noor R'aya's homeworld.

properties.name: Sorotarr
properties.description: Sorotarr VI was a planet in the Mid Rim's Sorotarr system. It was the location of The Game, a luxurious casino.

properties.name: Sorrus
properties.description: Sorrus was a planet in the Sorrus system located in the Outer Rim Territories. Its terrain consisted of mountain ranges and large deserts. The planet also had many sprawling cities. It had three capitals, one of which was Yinn La Hi. The Sorrusian people were xenophobic, and known for being unfriendly to outsiders. Jenna Zan Arbor once had her scientific lab located on Sorrus.

properties.name: Soruus
properties.description: Soruus was a star in the Core Worlds region of the galaxy. Cal-Seti was one of its planets.

properties.name: Soterios
properties.description: Soterios was a dry planet in Tapani sector's Melantha Province. Most of the world was scoured by windswept canyons and vast expanses of wastelands. There were few settlements and the indigenous flora and fauna had been driven to extinction by species introduced from elsewhere in the galaxy.

properties.name: Soullex
properties.description: Soullex was a Wild Space planet in the Fardon system near the Oplovis sector. After the Battle of Tantive V, it was garrisoned as the headquarters of Fleet Admiral Gaen Drommel. Drommel was betrayed and killed by Colonel Niovi, who surrendered the Guardian to the New Republic.

properties.name: Soun
properties.description: Soun could refer to one of the following:

properties.name: Space Station Scardia
properties.description: Scardia Station, also Space Station Scardia, was a cubical space station in the Null Zone.

properties.name: Space Station Trenchant
properties.description: Space Station Trenchant was located in the Trax sector in the Mid Rim. It was the scene of the battle between Asajj Ventress, Durge and General Grievous. Grievous's victory ensured that it was he who became Supreme Commander of the Droid Armies of the Confederacy of Independent Systems.

properties.name: Spaceport THX1138
properties.description: Spaceport THX1138 was a space station that was used as a starliner terminal by travel agencies that were members of the Galactic Tourist Bureau, including Star Tours. It was located in the Earth system, within the Fath sector.

properties.name: Spangled Veil Nebula
properties.description: The Spangled Veil Nebula was a nebula located in the Meridian sector of the Outer Rim.

properties.name: Spawn Nebula
properties.description: The Spawn Nebula was located in the Corva sector, approximately a thirty minute hyper-jump away from Betha II.

properties.name: Speco
properties.description: Speco was a planet aligned with the Galactic Empire during the Galactic Civil War, located in the Bon'nyuw-Luq sector of the Outer Rim Territories. It was ruled by an unnamed Imperial governor, but it was rumored that his mistress, a Falleen named Miaxi, really had control by manipulating him with her charms.

properties.name: Spee
properties.description: Spee was a planet located within the Spee system of the Outer Rim Territories' Saijo sector. It was visited by the smuggler Roark Garnet during the Galactic Civil War.

properties.name: Spefik
properties.description: Spefik was a barren, rocky planet in the Atrivis sector of the Outer Rim Territories. The planet was home to a Rebel base during the Galactic Civil War; however, the base was destroyed by Imperial forces in the battle of Spefik around 0.5 ABY. Imperial pilot Ranulf Trommer distinguished himself in that battle.

properties.name: Sperin
properties.description: Sperin was a planet in the Bajic sector.

properties.name: Spice Terminus
properties.description: Spice Terminus was a space station in Parmic sector, at the end of the Llanic Spice Run.

properties.name: Spindrift
properties.description: Spindrift was a planet in the Spindrift system, located in the Outer Rim's Rseik sector. An isolated world, Spindrift was home to an Imperial outpost called Spindrift Station during the era of the Galactic Civil War. In 3 ABY, Spindrift Station was attacked by a Rebel squadron flying repurposed TIE starfighters, who captured the station in order to obtain route coordinates for an Imperial armada carrying a unique creature called a teezl.

properties.name: Spintir
properties.poi: Caves of Light and Shadow, Dawn Temple, Frostwall Village, Imperial garrison, Mount Tellec, Museum of Spintir, University of Reles, Wolf Den,
properties.description: Spintir was a planet in the Spadja sector of the Outer Rim that was home to a Jedi temple known as the Dawn Temple, and an unusually high number of mammals. Spintir was a wealthy trade world.

properties.name: Spira
properties.poi: Ataria Island, Shinkai Abyss, The Point, The wreck,
properties.description: Spira was a popular resort world of beautiful beaches. It had a low axial tilt, which gave it a large temperate zone over much of its surface.

properties.name: Spirador
properties.description: Spirador was the capital planet of the Tandon sector and the site of Moff Harlov Jarnek's palace.

properties.name: Spirana
properties.description: Spirana was a planet in the Inner Rim Territories. It was situated along the Corellian Run.

properties.name: Sposia
properties.description: Sposia was a planet located in the Sposia system of the Unknown Regions' Chiss Space. The hyperlane known as the Path of the Houses linked it to the Csilla and Naporar systems. Sposia was home to House Sabosen, one of the Ruling Families of the sentient Chiss species, and it was the site of the Chiss Ascendancy's top academies and medcenters.

properties.name: Sprizen
properties.description: Sprizen may refer to one of the following:

properties.name: Spuma
properties.description: Spuma was a medium sized planet in the Seswenna sector of the Outer Rim. It had a number of prairies, mountains, and jungles located along its surface.

properties.name: Spunchina
properties.description: Spunchina was a planet in Wild Space known for its wild orgies. Jabba Desilijic Tiure once participated in one of these orgies and survived.

properties.name: Sran
properties.description: Sran was a rocky planet situated within the Ash Worlds. It was prone to storms that kicked up dust. The Nihil Strike Andrik Keller visited Sran after he escaped the Battle of Galov, in which the Galactic Republic and Jedi Order captured numerous Nihil marauders, including Tempest Runner Lourna Dee. In a cantina on Sran, Keller encountered a Dowutin; unbeknownst to Keller, the Dowutin was former Tempest Runner Pan Eyta, who sought revenge on Dee. After learning of Dee's status, Eyta killed Keller and departed Sran.

properties.name: Sriluur
properties.description: Sriluur was a planet in the Tharin sector of the Outer Rim. Homeworld to the sentient Weequay species, Sriluur held a key position along the Sisar Run, one of the many important hyperlanes connecting Hutt Space with the rest of the Outer Rim. The planet was orbited by five moons, most notably Ruul, the only one of the five able to support life. It was an arid world covered in deserts, volcanoes and acidic seas. Despite this, the planet was almost entirely self-sufficient thanks to an unlikely but very productive agricultural sector. The planet had enormous reserves of copper, but this resource went largely untapped by miners. Historically, the planet was part of Hutt Space, which meant Hutt crime lords and representatives of the Black Sun criminal organization were a common sight on Sriluur.

properties.name: Sronk
properties.description: The Sronk were a species from the planet Sronk. They spoke Basic using hand-based metaphors, such as "seeing things full-left-handed" for "seeing things first-hand" and "full slamming brunt of the closed right hand" to describe a large-scale military offensive.

properties.name: Stalimur
properties.description: Stalimur was an Outer Rim Territories world located in the Tion Hegemony sector. The stormy world featured moors inhabited by a population of farmers known as the Stalimurans, who observed a Tionese winter holiday known as the Devouring. The world was also home to the vicious Stalimur pirates.

properties.name: Stalsinek
properties.description: Stalsinek IV was a planet in the Corsair Outback region of the Hapes Cluster, the fourth world in the Stalsinek system. It had impassable rainforests which hid an ancient temple with a fountain with incredible healing powers. Its sentient species guarded the temple.

properties.name: Star Station 12
properties.description: Starstation 12 was a space station in orbit around the planet Vestar, full of thriving trade and crime. Boba Fett pursued the Imperial deserter Abal Karda to the station while on assignment for Darth Vader.

properties.name: StarForge Nebula
properties.description: The StarForge Nebula was a nebula located in Ado sector in the Mid Rim, along the Ado Spine hyperlane. StarForge Station was hidden in the nebula. Although its name was similar to that of the Star Forge, an ancient automated shipyard built by the Rakata, no relation existed; the nebula took its name from the large number of stars undergoing stellar formation within it.

properties.name: Starlyte Station
properties.description: Gateway Space Station was a facility orbiting Tshindral III. The space station was at one time an Imperial Transfer Post, supplying starships on their way into the Outer Rim; though it was never completed. Talandro Starlyte eventually purchased the station and renamed it Starlyte Station.

properties.name: Starswarm Cluster
properties.description: The Starswarm Cluster was a dense cluster of stars that was located within the Deep Core region of the galaxy. In the year 5000 BBY, the out-of-luck hyperspace explorers Gav and Jori Daragon of the planet Koros Major attempted to discover a new hyperspace route through the Starswarm Cluster. However, the radiation at the core of the densely-packed grouping of stars proved to be too damaging to their starship, the Starbreaker 12, and, after barely managing to exit the cluster with their transport intact, the Daragons had to return to Koros Major for much-needed repairs.

properties.name: Stassia
properties.description: Stassia was a planet located in the Core Worlds. Its inhabitants were very tolerant under any circumstances. During the Galactic Civil War, Stassia was ruled by the Galactic Empire under the governorship of Tren Pergallis.

properties.name: Station 88
properties.description: The Station 88 Spaceport, or simply Station 88, was a large spaceport founded by the rulers of Delaluna, Junction V, Bezim and the Vicondor systems. Located along the Celanon Spur in the Mid Rim's Vorc sector, it was a key strategic area for the Confederacy of Independent Systems, for it was the gateway to the Mid Rim star systems.

properties.name: Steelious
properties.description: Steelious was a Core Worlds planet that was located near the world Yarrv. The Hervack Spaceport on Steelious served as an important port for Rebel Alliance smuggling. Shortly after the Battle of Yavin, diplomats from Steelious traveled to Yarrv in order to negotiate a trade agreement with the latter planet's ruling royal family. Yarrv's Baron Karin, in the hopes of subjugating Steelious, planned to assassinate the diplomats, causing a war between the two planets that would benefit the military conglomerate owned by the baron.

properties.name: Stellan
properties.description: Stellan was a human male case officer at the Imperial Security Bureau for Bracchia, a Koorivar spy for the Galactic Empire. He and Bracchia were interrogated by Emperor Palpatine himself in an attempt to find conspirators within the Imperial security apparatus.

properties.name: Stennaros
properties.description: Stennaros was a planet in the Stennaros system, within the Expansion Region's Har Worlds sector. The homeworld of the Near-Human Stennes species and its Force-sensitive, shape-shifting Stennes Shifter offshoots, millennia of both species' persecution led to Stennaros being pock-marked with artillery craters and otherwise scarred. With prejudices against the Stennes Shifters leading to many members of both species being killed, the baseline Stennes were a closed xenophobic society, albeit being socially and culturally advanced within their own system. The Stennes further persecuted their Shifter offshoots, resulting in the latter being a homeless species not welcome on their own planet, with the considerably reduced Shifter population attempting to blend in or assimilate with their baseline species.

properties.name: Stenness
properties.description: Stenness was a planet in the Stenness system. It may have been the homeworld of the hssiss, although hssiss were also found on Ambria, Vjun, and Korriban.

properties.name: Stenos
properties.description: Stenos was a planet located in the Spadja sector of the Outer Rim Territories. It was homeworld of the Stenax race.

properties.name: Stensen's Colony
properties.description: Stensen's Colony was the home of Ghothian Slime.

properties.name: Stic
properties.description: Stic was a barren planet in the Xappyh sector, on the Outer Rim of the galaxy. It was subject to severe climate changes.

properties.name: Stieg
properties.description: Stieg was a planet in the Outer Rim. It was populated by the Stieg-Fan, who ran a peaceful government. During the planet Kegan's isolationist period, The Learning taught that Stieg was a dangerous place to visit, surrounded in war and without any governing body.

properties.name: Stobar
properties.description: Stobar was a dark and shadowy planet in the Boeus sector of the Expansion Region, and was known for being a very violent planet, for its many criminals.

properties.name: Stoga
properties.description: Stoga was a planet in the Outer Rim Territories. A dry, desert world of large canyons and craggy rock formations, Stoga was largely overlooked by the galactic governments due to its remote location—making it a haven for smugglers, outlaws and mercenaries to keep a low profile.

properties.name: Storinal
properties.poi: Revos LibertyRevos SpaceportBunker Aleph-OneBunker Twenty-two AlephStorinal spaceport bunkerRevos-Scohar railwayScohar Xenohealth InstituteLevel A-FourSunfruit PromenadeThe Howler
properties.description: Storinal was an Outer Rim world. The Imperial Remnant defeated the New Republic at the Battle of Storinal. The planet was artistically landscaped with lush green countryside, rivers, hills, tropical flower gardens, beaches and seas, and graceful cities. Because of its inherent beauty, the planet's chief economic resource was tourism. The planet was the homeworld of Storini glass prowlers. Ithorian starfruit was grown on the planet.

properties.name: Storthus
properties.description: Storthus was a desolate planet in the Churba sector of the Mid Rim. It was the homeworld of the giant stone eels, an indigenous species composed of living rock.

properties.name: Stovax
properties.description: Stovax was a planet located in the Core Worlds that the Obroan Institute and Kroddok Stopa intended to excavate.

properties.name: Stribos
properties.description: The Stribos system was a star system located within the Core Worlds that contained the planet Butler's Cove.

properties.name: Stronghold
properties.description: The Stronghold was a Quasar Fire-class cruiser-carrier in service to the Imperial Navy during the Imperial Era. At some point, the cruiser-carrier sustained damage to its hull and lay in a debris field with two TIE/ln space superiority starfighters. The 340-meter-long ship was equipped with sublight engines and four hangar bays.

properties.name: Stygian Caldera
properties.description: The Stygian Caldera was a large nebulosity that surrounded the Sith Worlds region of the galaxy. As it acted as a hyperspatial breakwater, it was difficult to navigate, and protected the Sith Empire from attack.

properties.name: Styx
properties.description: The Styx was a captured pirate starship.

properties.name: Suarbi
properties.description: Suarbi was an astronomical object located in the Outer Rim Territories of the galaxy, and linked to Vohai, Spice Terminus and Svivren. It was positioned at the coordinates O-19 on the Standard Galactic Grid.

properties.name: Subterrel
properties.description: Subterrel was a planet within the Subterrel sector beyond the Outer Rim Territories, widely known for its extensive mining operations.

properties.name: Sucharme
properties.description: Sucharme was a planet affiliated with the Trade Federation prior to the Invasion of Naboo. The Federation's primary garrison, Tallaga Garrison, was located in the city of Tallaga.

properties.name: Sufezz
properties.description: Sufezz was a planet located in the Outer Rim Territories. It had a Shrine of Kooroo.

properties.name: Sukkult
properties.description: Sukkult was a planet in the Inner Rim. Residing there was a Herglic collector of Tritonite documents. During the Clone Wars, the planet was located within Separatist space.

properties.name: Suliana
properties.description: Suliana was an Agriworld in the Senex sector where fields of virgin cotton grew.

properties.name: Sullust
properties.poi: Keff BaseLavaRide, SoroSuub Facility, Slime Sea, Sullustan shrine,
properties.description: Sullust was the primary planet of the Sullust system, located in the Outer Rim Territories at the conjuncture of the Rimma Trade Route and the Silvestri Trace. It was the homeworld of the Sullustans.

properties.name: Sulorine
properties.description: Sulorine was a planet in the Sulorine system of the Suolriep sector. Obi-Wan Kenobi was scheduled to attend to this world, before being reassigned to the Outbound Flight Project in 27 BBY.

properties.name: Sumarin
properties.description: Sumarin was a planet located within the Sumarin system of the Outer Rim Territories.

properties.name: Sump
properties.description: Sump was the humid, impoverished homeworld of the Nuknog, located in the Koradin sector of the Outer Rim Territories.

properties.name: Sunaj
properties.description: Sunaj was the Sunaj system's primary star.

properties.name: Sunin
properties.description: Sunin was a world located in the Tharin sector of the Outer Rim Territories. Many gunrunners of the Sendavé Shared Interest Collective were from Elkkasinn and Sunin.

properties.name: Suolriep
properties.description: Suolriep was the sector capital of the Suolriep sector.

properties.name: Surcaris
properties.description: Surcaris was a planet in the Mid Rim's Trans-Vulta sector where a group of Mandalorian mercenaries, possibly under Munin Skirata, fought. It was also the located where Munin found a young Kal Skirata.

properties.name: Surdapan Station
properties.description: Surdapan Station was a space station located in the Ojoster sector of the Outer Rim.

properties.name: Suria
properties.description: Agent Suria was a Twi'lek female who worked for the Republic Strategic Information Service during the Galactic War. Holding the rank of Field Agent, she was stationed on Quesh in 3642 BBY where she tasked a fellow Republic citizen with checking on her subordinate Agent Meldo, who missed two scheduled comm checks.

properties.name: Surron
properties.description: Surron was a planet in the Expansion Region. It was the headquarters of Surron StarTech. The Surronians, which lived on this planet, had a guild-based society.

properties.name: Suurja
properties.description: Suurja was an agrarian planet with a breathable atmosphere that was located within the Suurja system of the galaxy's Outer Rim Territories region and harbored both a native species called Suurjans and a colonist population of 16 million. By the year 3966 BBY, Suurja served as a resource world for the nearby city-covered planet of Taris.

properties.name: Svivren
properties.description: Svivren was a mountainous Outer Rim Territories planet not far from Andasala. It was at the terminus of the Five Veils Route, which connected it to Suarbi. Despite the harsh climate of the world and its severe seasonal variation, the native Svivreni thrived and made it an important regional trading port. Its population of more than eight billion included large colonies of Humans, Sullustans and Ewoks. The source of Svivren's Ewok population was unknown. The importance of trade was reflected in the planet's Festival of Great Trade.

properties.name: Svolten
properties.description: The Svolten system was a star system located in the Esstran sector of the Outer Rim Territories.

properties.name: Swarquen
properties.description: Swarquen was a planet in the Swarquen system. It was the homeworld of Mol Hedron.

properties.name: Swedlan
properties.description: Swedlan was one of the three primary planets that made up the Pimbrellan League. Located in Kathol sector within the Outer Rim Territories, Its atmosphere could not sustain most forms of humanoid life. Sealed domed cities were built in underground cave systems, financed with the profits gained from trade with nearby Dolstan.

properties.name: Sy Myrth
properties.description: Sy Myrth, formerly known as Far Barseg, was a planet located in the Jospro sector of the Outer Rim Territories. It was the homeworld of the Sy Myrthians.

properties.name: Syboona
properties.description: Syboona was the Syboona homeworld.

properties.name: Symbia
properties.description: The Symbia system was located in the Deep Core. It was the origin point of the Symbian language.

properties.name: Syndaar
properties.description: Syndaar was the sector capital of the Thrasybule sector, near Celanon. It was the location of the Syndaar Military Prep School.

properties.name: Syned
properties.description: Syned was an ice-covered planet in the Syned system, in Grumani sector. During the Republic Dark Age, Syned was under the control of Sith Lord Chagras, but after his death, it fell into the hands of his daughter Arkadia Calimondra.

properties.name: Syngia
properties.description: Syngia was a planet in the galaxy, located in the Sertar sector of the Outer Rim Territories. Syngia was also where the ancient Sith Lord Remulus Dreypa practiced his mastery over the creation of life, and where he left behind his mysterious Genesis pool.

properties.name: Syni
properties.description: Syni was the Syni system's primary star.

properties.name: Syvris
properties.description: Syvris was a moon in Hutt Space. It was a favorite haunt of spice smugglers. Many of the moon's residents were smugglers, who lived and worked at a shadowport located in its largest crater.

properties.name: T'olan
properties.description: T'olan was an astronomical object in the Wuun system. Early in the Clone Wars, a terrible battle was fought at T'olan.

properties.name: T'surr
properties.description: T'surr was a cold and windswept high-gravity planet in the Expansion Region's Nuon e Safyd sector. Most of the planet's lifeforms had excellent low-light vision, and the harsh conditions of the world gave rise to a predatory sentient species also known as the T'surr. T'surr males often left their homeworld for the wider galaxy, but their planet was never represented in the Galactic Republic or the New Republic.

properties.name: Taanab
properties.poi: Arcon Multinode Hybrid Plantings, Banthal Company Docks, Jedi chapter house,
properties.description: Taanab was a planet of green meadows in the Taanab system of the Inner Rim Territories. It was primarily used for agriculture and farming. Its populace was known for always maintaining an air of formality. Taanab had problems with seasonal pirate raids from bandits striking from the planet Norulac for millennia prior to the Battle of Taanab.

properties.name: Tabiid
properties.description: Tabiid was a planet located in the Tabiid system of the Mid Rim that served as a base for the Antarian Rangers during the reign of the Galactic Empire.

properties.name: Taboon
properties.description: Taboon was a gas giant in the Aweris system. It was the source of Taboon hardwood. Bogga the Hutt's palace was on Vo Dasha, the moon orbiting Taboon.

properties.name: Taborin
properties.description: The Taborin system was a star system located within the Mayagil sector of the Outer Rim Territories.

properties.name: Tahlboor
properties.description: Tahlboor was a planet in the Thanium sector. It was home to the Tahlbooreans, who were divided into two castes: the Troobs and the Hobors, perpetually at war. In the past, an ancient Tahlboorean civilization had constructed the Sky cannon, an awesome weapon that had resulted in the destruction of both their civilization and one of the world's twin moons.

properties.name: Tal Nami
properties.description: Tal Nami was a planet located in Hutt Space and was the homeworld of the Tal Nami species.

properties.name: Tala
properties.description: Tala was the Tala system's primary star.

properties.name: Talasea
properties.description: The fourth planet in the Morobe system, Talasea orbited the yellow primary star in a red/yellow binary group. A cool, moist, forested, and fog-shrouded world, Talasea had a higher gravity than standard and was lashed by severe thunderstorms during the rainy season. Island continents made up its land masses. Animal life included native insects and reptiles, along with feral mammals descended from those brought for an early farming colony, including banthas and rycrits. Indigenous plant life included green ivy, tendril-moss, and the kaha tree. It was the site of several minor conflicts from multiple entities in the galaxy.

properties.name: Talay
properties.description: Talay was a oceanic planet located in the Mid Rim.

properties.name: Talcene
properties.description: Talcene was a planet located along the Perlemian Trade Route. It was the homeworld of Shea Hublin and a world with notoriously competitive commerce guilds.

properties.name: Talcharaim
properties.description: Talcharaim could refer to one of the following:

properties.name: Talcim Cluster
properties.description: The Talcim Cluster was an asteroid field in the Cegul sector of the Outer Rim Territories that had a mining facility that was abandoned and forgotten.

properties.name: Talesia
properties.description: Talesia was a planet known for manufacturing some of the galaxy's deadliest thermal detonators.

properties.name: Talfaglio
properties.description: Talfaglio was a reddish-orange planet in the Corellian sector.

properties.name: Talhovi
properties.description: Talhovi was a planet located in the Talhovi system of the Juvex sector, in the Mid Rim of the galaxy. It was homeworld of House Mekuun. The Talhovian ale was from this planet.

properties.name: Talir
properties.description: The Talir system was a star system located within the Tharin sector.

properties.name: Tallaan
properties.poi: Soun-Giju, Tallaani Shipyards, Heatherdowns Hotel and TrackCMG Guildhouse
properties.description: Tallaan was a planet in Tapani sector's Freeworlds Territory at the confluence of the Giju Run, the Procopian Shipping Lane, and the Shapani Bypass. It was best known for its starship production.

properties.name: Tallaso
properties.description: Tallaso was a planet ruled by Imperial Governor Riggins Delahrg. It was ignored by the Galactic Empire after the Battle of Endor, allowing Delahrg to be overthrown in a coup. He fled to Vandron.

properties.name: Tallek
properties.description: Tallek was a planet once plagued by thorn fever. The Galactic Empire rounded up anyone who caught the disease and let them die in isolation camps.

properties.name: Talofan
properties.description: Talofan was the capital planet in the Bajic sector. It was the headquarters of Grand Moff Kintaro.

properties.name: Taloraan
properties.description: Taloraan was the largest planet in the Kelavine system of the Expansion Region, with a diameter of 100,000 kilometers.

properties.name: Taloron
properties.description: The Talorons were a species of sentient, blue-skinned humanoids native to the Wild Space Taloron system. For much of their existence, the Talorons were peaceful farmers and merchants. However, when pirate groups set up operations in the Taloron system and began preying upon its peaceful denizens, the Talorons were forced to regroup and militarize, lest they be wiped out completely from the predations. The resulting war, the Taloron Pirate Conflict, completely reshaped Taloron society and birthed the infamous Taloron Hunters, distinguished by their trademark armor.

properties.name: Talravin
properties.description: Talravin was one of the planets of the Core Worlds. It was also Bastila, Helena Shan, and Bastila's father's home planet.

properties.name: Talu
properties.description: Talu was the planet in Zsinj space where Han Solo executed the Talu insertion mission during the hunt for Zsinj.

properties.name: Tamazall
properties.description: Tamazall was a New Republic prison planet located in the Boeus sector of the Expansion Region. Zurga Pass was in its foothills. The planet was protected by the Tamazall Militia. Prisoners were transported via monorail.

properties.name: Tamban
properties.description: Tamban was an inhabited planet in Core Worlds from which the Koornacht Cluster could be observed through a telescope. It was ruled by Emperor Preedu III before Palpatine rose to power.

properties.name: Tamber
properties.description: The Tamber system was in the Freeworlds Territory of the Tapani sector, on the Shapani Bypass.

properties.name: Tamboon
properties.description: Tamboon was a planet located in the Tungra sector of the Outer Rim Territories.

properties.name: Tambor Station
properties.description: The Tambor Deep Space Centre, or simply Tambor Station, was a mobile shipyard created by the Geonosians who used it as a workship for repairing starships.

properties.name: Tammar
properties.description: Tammar, originally known as Lelrais, was the Tammarian homeworld. This planet had an unusually thin atmosphere, which caused native Tammarians to evolve a chemical pouch called a chaghizs torm to store oxygen. This allowed them to survive in the vacuum of space for short periods. Tammar also had no standing water.

properties.name: Tammuz-an
properties.poi: Inn, Outer Territories, Royal castle, Tower, Unit B-6,
properties.description: Tammuz-an was a double-ringed planet. The planet's inhabitants, called Tammuz-an, were tall blue- or purple-skinned humanoids governed by a monarchy. The planet was the homeworld of Mon Julpa.

properties.name: Tancon
properties.description: Tancon was a planet located in the Koradin sector of the Outer Rim. The planet was the location of a Rebel base. A group of rebels left this base in 0 ABY in the Arion Star headed for Greyman's Planet.

properties.name: Tanda
properties.description: The Tanda system was a star system located in the Tapani sector's Mecetti Province. It was an endpoint of the Leozi Route.

properties.name: Tandankin
properties.description: Tandankin was a planet located in the Spadja sector of the Outer Rim Territories.

properties.name: Tandgor
properties.description: Tandgor was a planet in the Outer Rim Territories of the galaxy. It was known for its expensive gemstones.

properties.name: Tandun
properties.description: Tandun III, also known as Tandun Three, was a youthful planet that occupied a young star system in the Outer Rim Territories.

properties.name: Tangar
properties.description: Tangar was a site of CIS activity during the Clone Wars. A flotila of starships dropped out of hyperspace off Tangar, then jumped again.

properties.name: Tanger
properties.description: Tanger was a planet located in the Tapani sector's Tanger system.

properties.name: Tangrene
properties.description: Tangrene was a planet in the Morshdine sector of the Outer Rim Territories.

properties.name: Tanquilla Beach
properties.description: Tanquilla Beach was a shadowport located in the Kathol sector during the early years of the New Republic. It was situated within a nebulae on the edge of the sector, and was one day's travel from Shintel. It gained its name because of the vast amount of light the station received from all directions from the nebulae.

properties.name: Tanta Aurek
properties.description: Tanta Aurek was the sun of the Tanta Aurek system in the Grumani sector of the Outer Rim Territories. The name of the star and the system derived from the fact that it and the sun of the Tanta Besh system, Tanta Besh appeared to form a double star in the sky of the planet Obica. It was orbited by the planet Scelepas.

properties.name: Tanta Besh
properties.description: Tanta Besh was the star of the Tanta Besh system in the Grumani sector of the Outer Rim Territories. An unstable blue giant, it had varying luminosity and pulsed erratically, making it a raw material for diviners on many planets in the sector. It was located off the Hydian Way, slightly coreward of the Tanta Aurek system.

properties.name: Tantara
properties.description: Tantara was a planet located in the Inner Rim.

properties.name: Tanthior
properties.description: Tanthior was a planet located in the Corellian sector of the Core Worlds.

properties.name: Tantiss Station
properties.description: Tantiss Station was a HoloNet node destroyed by the Yuuzhan Vong in 28 ABY. It was located in the Dalonbian sector.

properties.name: Tantive
properties.description: Tantive may refer to

properties.name: Tantra
properties.description: Tantra was a planet in the eponymous Tantra sector on the Outer Rim. It lay on the major hyperlane known as the Rimma Trade Route was located at a hyperspace junction, where the Route joined the subsidiary Coyn Run.

properties.name: Tanya
properties.description: Tanya was a planet located in the Tapani sector's Tanya system. The rebel cell known as Shimper Ale maintained a manor house on Tanya. The planet produced vast harvests of grain and vegetables each year and was an important agricultural producer of the sector.

properties.name: Tanzis
properties.description: The Tanzis system was a star system located in the Tapani sector's Mecetti Province, on the Leozi Route.

properties.name: Tao-Grant
properties.description: Tao-Grant was a gas giant, the sole planet in the Tao-Grant system. It was orbited by at least two moons.

properties.name: Tar Morden
properties.description: Tar Morden was a planet in the Expansion Region, located on the Corellian Trade Spine. It possessed a Techno Union factory. At the end of the Clone Wars, the Galactic Republic seized the factory and acquired many crab droids, which were sent to Carida.

properties.name: Tarabba Prime
properties.description: Tarabba Prime was a planet located in the Tarabba sector. It was a center of communication and commerce of the sector.

properties.name: Taraloon
properties.description: Taraloon was an uncharted planet that served as base of operations of the pirate, Drek Drednar and his crew, who had built a base there. Native to the planet were the reptilian Gornalak.

properties.name: Tarawa
properties.description: Tarawa was a planet located in the Steniplis sector of the Outer Rim. It was the site of a battle during the Galactic Civil War.

properties.name: Tarchalia
properties.description: The Tarchalia system was a star system located in the Shiwal sector of the galaxy's Mid Rim and New Territories regions. It was home to the creatures known as Tarchalian gazelles.

properties.name: Targonn
properties.description: Targonn was a planet located in the Outer Rim Territories. This mountainous planet was the homeworld of the sentient Targonnian species. It was ruled by Dictator-Forever Craw until it was liberated by the Revoltists with the help of C-3PO and R2-D2.

properties.name: Tarhassan
properties.description: Tarhassan was a planet in the Expansion Region. It was controlled by the Confederacy of Independent Systems during the Clone Wars.

properties.name: Taria
properties.description: Sei Taria was a Human female from the planet Spira who served as Finis Valorum's Staff Aide during the latter's tenure as Supreme Chancellor of the Galactic Republic. Taria worked for the Office of the Supreme Chancellor on the galactic capital world of Coruscant as early as 37 BBY, a post in which she helped Valorum follow the Republic's myriad bureaucratic policies and procedures. Taria became Valorum's lover, and she often accompanied him to social events as well as on diplomatic missions. In 37 BBY, she helped the Chancellor prepare for a visit to the capital by Baroness Omnino of the planet Vena by arranging a Jedi escort for the woman.

properties.name: Taris
properties.poi: Pre-Jedi Civil War:Davik Kang's Estate, Tarisian Military Base, Taris Academy, Swoop Track, Taris Dueling Ring, Sewers of Taris,
properties.description: Taris was an urban planet in the fifth orbit of its star, located in the Taris system, within the Ojoster sector, of the Outer Rim Territories, in turn Taris was orbited by four moons, including Rogue. The term Tarisian was used to describe people and products from the planet, which took over a millennium to build, after being settled by Human colonists from unknown origins. Eventually Alien species settled or visited the city and before long the Republic took notice of the world and the planet's ecumenopolis quickly developed over a century of prosperity, and as a result the planet suffered from massive overpopulation. Once a galactic nexus that earned great wealth from its strategic position on hyperspace routes, Taris' importance declined with the discovery of improved trade routes, and the planet rapidly fell into decay with a slow mass migration of its residents across the galaxy. The remainder of the planet's history was wrought with civil disorder and social unrest. As it turned to industry as a means of compensation for its economic troubles, its oceans became polluted, eliminating the planet's main food source. After a century of the planet's ecosystem dying off, famine spread among the lower classes while the rich hoarded what few supplies remained. The resulting strife led to the Tarisian Civil War, the start of lasting prejudices between the Humanocentric Tarisian nobles and the largely alien underclass. The city became segmented, the lower classes were banned from living in the upper levels of Taris and the planet became the poster child of a economically dying world.

properties.name: Tarkin's Fang
properties.description: Tarkin's Fang was a secret Imperial base planet located in the Deep Core, near the Treskov system. The Empire abandoned it at the end of the Galactic Civil War, sealing it up well stocked for use as a base should another war with the New Republic break out.

properties.name: Tarnith
properties.description: Tarnith was a planet in the Outer Rim along the Jebble-Vanquo-Tarnith line. A resource world for Taris, it was threatened by the Mandalorian Neo-Crusaders in 3966 BBY, which compelled Lhosan Industries to obtain a seat for Taris in the Galactic Senate.

properties.name: Tarnoonga
properties.description: Tarnoonga was an ocean-covered planet located in the Arkanis sector.

properties.name: Taronda
properties.description: Taronda was a remote mining world. During the Clone Wars, Jedi Knight Anakin Skywalker and his padawan, Ahsoka Tano were sent by the Jedi Council to negotiate a trading agreement with the miners of the planet for raw materials for the Republic. Before negotiations could start however, the planet was attacked by the Separatists. Outnumbering the Republic forces, the Separatists had them pinned down under their own deflector shield. The Republic forces were saved by the arrival of a Venator-class Star Destroyer.

properties.name: Taroon
properties.description: Taroon was a male Rutanian and the son of King Frane of Rutan.

properties.name: Tarsa
properties.description: Tarsa was a forested planet in the Tarsa system, which was located in the Mid Rim.

properties.name: Tarshan
properties.description: Tarshan may refer to one of the following:

properties.name: Tarsunt
properties.description:
The Tarsunt were a species of furry sentients. They had long pelts of fur.
One member of this species was the engineer Brill, who aided the Alliance to Restore the Republic in the Battle of Endor. Another was Lanever Villecham, who served as Chancellor of the New Republic 30 years after the Battle of Endor. Blik ran a gladiatorial arena where droids fought each other. Another member of the tarsunt species was senator Colandrus.

properties.name: Tartaglia
properties.description: Tartaglia was a Mid Rim planet in close proximity to the Fusion Cloud nebula. The legendary Nova Vaults were buried beneath the planet.

properties.name: Tas-La
properties.description: Tas-La was a planet in the Si'Klaata Cluster of Hutt Space.

properties.name: Tasariq
properties.description: Tasariq was a planet in the Inner Rim. It was a barren world with atmosphere-filled craters and tasar crystals. Tasariq joined the Republic 22 BBY. It was later part of the Galactic Empire. Barimoq Industries, a Tasari-run corporation that produced a variety of personal projectile weapons, was based on Tasariq.

properties.name: Tascollan Nebula
properties.description: The Tascollan Nebula was a nebula in the Outer Rim Territories.

properties.name: Tashtor Seneca
properties.description: Tashtor Seneca was a location in the Tashtor Seneca system, a part of the Mid Rim's Tashtor sector. During the Galactic Civil War, the forces of the Galactic Empire destroyed the Croc of Gold, the freighter of the Rebel Alliance operative Devon Fuller, over Tashtor Seneca.

properties.name: Taskeed
properties.poi: Wasted Plains, Saber's Tooth, Pentakus Crater,
properties.description: Taskeed was a planet located within the Outer Rim Territories. Originally known as Taskored, it was absorbed into Xim's empire as he expanded his borders from the Kingdom of Cron. During his campaigns, Xim tested a powerful weapon on Taskeed, leaving behind a massive crater that became known as the Pentakus Crater. Taskeed was located in Hutt Space as of the Great Sith War, but by 52 BBY, the Hutts had tightened their borders, leaving the world behind.

properties.name: Tasrin
properties.description: Tasrin was a planet located in the Colonies.

properties.name: Tatooine
properties.poi: Mos Espa Grand ArenaBeggar's CanyonImperial Station Bravo Jabba's PalaceWald's Parts Teemo the Hutt's palaceMos Eisley CantinaDune SeaTusken Raider campJawa campLars homesteadBen Kenobi's hutGreat Pit of CarkoonJundland WastesJawa Mountain FortressSunfire OutpostHubba HeightsPalace of Gorga the HuttTerk StreetMochot Steep,
properties.description: Tatooine ) was a desert world and the first planet in the binary Tatoo star system. It was part of the Arkanis sector in the Outer Rim Territories. It was inhabited by poor locals who mostly farmed moisture for a living. Other activities included used equipment retailing and scrap dealing. The planet was on the 5709-DC Shipping Lane, a spur of the Triellus Trade Route, which itself connected to the Sisar Run. The planet was not far from the Corellian Run. It had its own navigation system. The planet acquired a bad reputation, often being viewed as the cesspool of the galaxy due to the large number of criminals who could be found there. However, it would nevertheless play a role in major galactic events throughout the millennia, most notably being the homeworld of Anakin Skywalker. It was here that Jedi Master Qui-Gon Jinn recognized Anakin's potential to become a Jedi and where he introduced him to Obi-Wan Kenobi, his future master and mentor. Tatooine was also the home of Anakin's son, Luke, where he lived until his early adulthood.

properties.name: Tauber
properties.description: Tauber was an Inner Rim world that lay on the Rimma Trade Route super-hyperroute. In 214 BBY, an antidote to the disease known as the Bordal Contagion was created on Tauber. Two centuries later, a hospital on Tauber was where the A4 laboratory assistant droid designated EV-A4-D began his service, while Neuro-Saav Corporation ran material-design laboratories on the world by 2 ABY. Doctor Cinto Alaras and the undercover Rebel Alliance Agent Sommen both worked at the Neuro-Saav facilities.

properties.name: Taul
properties.description: Taul was a swamp planet in the Gunthar system of the Outer Rim.

properties.name: Tavitz
properties.description: The Tavitz system was a system in the Tapani sector's Reena Province under the control of House Reena. It was an endpoint of the Caloria Run.

properties.name: Tavya
properties.description: The Tavya system was in the Freeworlds Territory of the Tapani sector, on the Procopian Shipping Lane; it was also an endpoint of the Three Ellas Run.

properties.name: Tay'ah'loo
properties.description: Tay'ah'loo was a planet in Imperial Space. In 1 ABY, an unscheduled capsule carrying Bledsoe's disease landed on the planet. The plague was released and decimated the population of Tay'ah'loo within days. Stormtroopers soon arrived to cart away the dead and disinfect the planet.

properties.name: Tazan
properties.description: Tazan was a planet in the Expansion Region.

properties.name: TD-10036-EM-1271
properties.description: TD-10036-EM-1271 was a star in the Expansion Region. It was destroyed by the Sacorrian Triad using Centerpoint Station, though Thrackan Sal-Solo claimed credit as a power play.

properties.name: Te Hasa
properties.description: Te Hasa was a desert planet with a Type II atmosphere that was located within the Gree Enclave, a part of the Outer Rim Territories region of the galaxy. A hidden planet that had been terraformed by members of the sentient Gree species into a harsh desert world with bioengineered predators, Te Hasa was used for thousands of years to store many pieces of ancient Gree technology that the cephalopoid species had forgotten how to use.

properties.name: Teagan
properties.poi: Teagan Tech Consortium headquarters, Kwymar Automaton Ltd. factory,
properties.description: Teagan was a planet in the Kwymar sector of the Outer Rim.

properties.name: Teardrop
properties.description: Teardrop was a planet located in Shelsha sector. It contained Por'ste Island and was near Briston.

properties.name: Tebru
properties.description: Tebru was a rocky planet that was located within the Tebru system, a part of the Outer Rim Territories' Juris sector. By the year 3 ABY, the droid inventor and historian Toria Tell maintained a large residence with a workshop and a massive library on the planet. Tell kept her extensive droid collection, which contained many of the galaxy's oldest and rarest robots, at her home. When not traveling off-world aboard her stock light freighter in order to expand her droid collection, the inventor quietly tinkered at her Tebru home.

properties.name: Tedel
properties.description: Tedel was a planet. It was home to the besiioth.

properties.name: Teedio
properties.description: Teedio was the lone primary star in the Teedio system.

properties.name: Teevan
properties.description: Teevan was a planet with silvery seas located within the Teevan system of the Outer Rim Territories. It was the homeworld of the Teevan species. Jedi Padawan Tru Veld came from this world.

properties.name: Tefau
properties.description: Tefau was a location in the Tefau system of the Outer Rim Territories' Suolriep sector. Soth Petikkin, a Tefaun who worked as a recruiter for the Alliance to Restore the Republic during the Galactic Civil War, was from Tefau.

properties.name: Tegrat
properties.description: Tegrat was a planet located within the Tegrat system of the Outer Rim Territories. Many of its inhabitants fled to Tatooine shortly before an Imperial invasion meant to flush out Rebels.

properties.name: Teirasa
properties.description: Teirasa was a planet located in the Mid Rim of the galaxy. It was the homeworld of the Teirasans. The Pius Dea-ruled Galactic Republic attacked Teirasa in 11,660 BBY after the Teirasans demonstrated their outrage for the Republic's orbital bombardment of Zarracina III.

properties.name: Tekurr'k
properties.description: Tekurr'k was a planet located within the Tekurr'k system of the Mid Rim's Senex sector.

properties.name: Tel
properties.description: Tel was a white dwarf and the primary star of the Tel Minor system, a system within the Brak sector. The star was orbited by four planets, Tel I, Tel II, Tel III, and Tel IV.

properties.name: Telaris
properties.description: Telaris was a location in the Telaris system. During the early rebellion against the Galactic Empire, the Alliance to Restore the Republic utilized the UT-60D U-wing starfighter/support craft as a cargo and VIP escort between Mon Cala and Telaris. The information was on a report that was later incorporated into The Rebel Files.

properties.name: Telepan
properties.description: Telepan was a planet located within the Telepan system of the Core Worlds.

properties.name: Telerath
properties.description: Telerath was an Inner Rim banking world, the home of the Telerath Interstellar Banking Initiative. It was created as an experiment in face-to-face customer service by an interstellar bank. Customers were guaranteed to meet with living bank representatives, did not need to make scheduled appointments, and were offered a fantastic variety of comforting recreational activities and accommodations.

properties.name: Telkadis
properties.description: Telkadis was an inhabited planet located within the Telkadis system of the Expansion Region that contained taku forests which were harvested for wood. The Telkadis hiding tree spider was native to this world.

properties.name: Telkur Station
properties.description: Telkur Station was a space station hidden inside the Transitory Mists in the Hapes Consortium. Han and Leia Solo visited it in 40 ABY with the bounty hunter Nashtah during the Second Galactic Civil War and met with Jagged Fel who warned them of the trap they had walked into set by the Hapans. It contained a cantina.

properties.name: Tellanroaeg
properties.description: Tellanroaeg was an Outer Rim Territories astronomical object. It was located on the Corellian Run super-hyperroute in the Gaulus sector. During the Clone Wars, Tellanroaeg became the site of a battle between the forces of the Galactic Republic and the Confederacy of Independent Systems. In 19 BBY, Order 66, a contingency order issued to the clone commanders of the Grand Army of the Republic, reached Tellanroaeg.

properties.name: Tellivar
properties.description: The Tellivar system was a star system located within the Colonies region.

properties.name: Teloc Ol-sen
properties.description: Teloc Ol-sen was a desert planet located within the Teloc Ol-sen system of the Mid Rim that was inhabited by the Teloc Hunters. At some point before 2 ABY, the vigilante group known as the Zulirian Swordmasters fought and massacred a Rebel cell on Teloc Ol-sen. Members of Alliance Intelligence later wrote a report on this event.

properties.name: Telos
properties.description: Telos was an astronomical object located in the galaxy's Outer Rim Territories, along the Hydian Way. During the campaign at Salient, an Imperial battle group was stationed at Telos under the command of Admiral Utu. Moff Wilhuff Tarkin requested that Utu dispatch whatever vessels she could spare from Telos to Salient, and was later informed by a commander that Utu hoped to send two Star Destroyers.

properties.name: Telti
properties.description: Telti was a moon located in the Inner Rim.

properties.name: Tenara
properties.description: Tenara was a planet that was located in the Tenara system. It was situated in the Back Reach area of the Gordian Reach sector, within the Trans-Hydian portion of the Outer Rim Territories. A small hyperlane connected Tenara to the planet Korphir.

properties.name: Tendo
properties.description: Tendo was a Mobquet medium transport in the service of the Imperial Navy during the Galactic Civil War. The vessel was part of the Imperial II-class Star Destroyer Corrupter's resupply convoy, which was lead by the EF76 Nebulon-B escort frigate Monitor to where the Corrupter lay damaged in the Mev system. The ship, which bore a cargo of engineering droids, was then attacked by Rebel Alliance raiders and was destroyed along with the rest of the convoy.

properties.name: Tentator
properties.description: Tentator was a planet located within the Tentator system of the Colonies, used as a prison by the Galactic Republic. The Slam gang escaped from the Greylands Security Complex on-planet, but were recaptured and returned to the poorly-maintained high-security prison, along with their ship, an Ubrikkian star yacht.

properties.name: Tentrix
properties.description: Tentrix was a vast, beautiful blue planet located within the Tentrix system of the Expansion Region.

properties.name: Tenupe
properties.description: Tenupe was a mountainous and tropical planet located within the Tenupe system on the Sparkle Run. It was orbited by the Shattered Moon. It had multiple inland seas and was controlled by the Killiks; however the planet was captured by the Chiss during the Battle of Tenupe of the Swarm War in 36 ABY. Jagged Fel and Alema Rar spent two years marooned on the planet after the Dark Nest Crisis taking away a Twi'lek story-chain from there.

properties.name: Tepasi
properties.description: Tepasi was a planet located within the Tepasi system of the Core Worlds. A forested world situated on the Commenor Run, it was colonized by Humans before 26,000 BBY and was already emerging as a hub of commerce when it became a founding member of the Galactic Republic. In 200 BBY, Tarzen Tagge provided aid to the planet after it experienced a series of groundquakes, precipitating the crime lord's founding of the Tagge Company. Tepasi remained loyal to the Republic during the Clone Wars, and after the death of Emperor Palpatine it was the site of the crumbling Tagge Company's only remaining facility.

properties.name: Teptixii
properties.description: Teptixii was a blue-green planet in the Unknown Regions. Imperial forces commanded by Captain Voss Parck fought against elements of the warlord Nuso Esva's navy near Teptixii in 0 ABY.

properties.name: Ter Abbes
properties.description: Ter Abbes was a grim industrialized planet located within the Ter Abbes system of the Expansion Region, just off the Perlemian Trade Route. Its government was democratically elected, but prone to instability, as was proven when Nom Anor contracted Mandalorian mercenary Goran Beviin to assassinate Tholote B'Leph, an opposition politician just prior to an election. The civil war ignited by his death was still in progress in 25 ABY.

properties.name: Terephon
properties.description: Terephon was a planet in the Hapes Cluster, located in the Transitory Mists. The Mists, which blocked all long-range and holocomm transmissions, ensured Terephon's isolation and helped shape its reputation as a backwater in the Consortium. Nevertheless, rising from the marshy plains of the planet were Hapan cities and mountain ranges; the world became popular for hunting, and wealthy nobles often built retreats on Terephon.

properties.name: Tergamenion
properties.description: Tergamenion was a world that was located in the Grumani sector, in the Outer Rim Territories. It was a darkworld and during the Republic Dark Age the planet was the site of Daimanite military research and production complexes.

properties.name: Terman
properties.description: The Terman system was a star system located in the Periphery, a sector in the Outer Rim near Hutt Space, that contained the Terman Station.

properties.name: Terminus
properties.description: Terminus was a planet located within the Terminus system of the Outer Rim Territories. Terminus sat on the juncture of two of the galaxy's most important trade routes, the Hydian Way and the Corellian Trade Spine making it a highly trafficked port despite its remote location on the edges of the Outer Rim's Western Reaches. Its proximity to Wild Space and the Unknown Regions meant that strange and unfamiliar ships were a common sight in Terminus' skies.

properties.name: Terr'skiar
properties.description: Terr'skiar was a trade world located in the Terr'skiar system, a part of the Kashyyyk Region's Terr'skiar sector in the Slice portion of the Mid Rim. The hyperlanes known as the Nightroad and the Ootmian Pabol linked it to the Pizilis and New Apsolon system, respectively, while the Terr'skiar Pass route connected it to the Trax sector's Bissillirus system. Terr'skiar served as the capital of the Terr'skiar sector.

properties.name: Terra Sool
properties.description: Terra Sool was a planet located within the Terra Sool system of the Expansion Region. It was liberated from the Confederacy of Independent Systems by Anakin Skywalker and Obi-Wan Kenobi in 22 BBY, during the Clone Wars.

properties.name: TerraAsta
properties.description: TerraAsta was a planet located within the TerraAsta system of the Colonies.

properties.name: Terrelia
properties.description: Terrelia was a planet located in the Terrelia system at coordinates L-14 in the galaxy's Inner Rim. It was also the homeworld of Cassie Cryar, a Terrelian Jango Jumper Thief.

properties.name: Tertiary Fujar
properties.description: The Tertiary Fujar system was a part of the Outer Rim Territories' Tamarin sector. Around 214 BBY, the Fujari pirate gang operated out of an asteroid base in the system. Following the Bordal Contagion of that year, the Fujari forced a Kett Shipping convoy to emerge from hyperspace into an ambush in the Tertiary Fujari system, but both the pirate starships and their base were destroyed by the Trade Defense Force escort of Kett Shipping's new parent organization, the Trade Federation.

properties.name: Tertiary Kesmere
properties.description: Tertiary Kesmere was a cloudy, storm-wracked world located in the Tertiary Kesmere system, a part of the Raioballo sector in the New Territories portion of the Outer Rim Territories. It was the homeworld of the winged hornagaunt species, including the wing-clipped pet Grendel. Between 4 ABY and 12 ABY, Tertiary Kesmere fell within the borders of the Pentastar Alignment.

properties.name: Tervissis
properties.description: Tervissis was a planet located within the Tervissis system of the Outer Rim Territories. It was the homeworld of two sentient species, the Tervigs and the Bandies. The two species were at war with one another, with the Tervigs subjugating the Bandies.

properties.name: Teth
properties.poi: B'omarr MonasteryZiro Desilijic Tiure's father's grave1137-4265
properties.description: Teth was the third planet orbiting the star of the same name and had two moons that orbited the planet itself. It was located within the Teth system of the Baxel sector in the outer border of the Outer Rim region of the galaxy that crossed over into the Wild Space region.

properties.name: Tetso
properties.description: Tetso was a planet located within the Tetso system of the Core Worlds.

properties.name: Teyr
properties.description: Teyr was a bureaucratic and tourism planet located in the Surric system of the Colonies.

properties.name: Th'irus
properties.description: Th'irus was a planet located within the Th'irus system of the Wild Space.

properties.name: Thabit
properties.description: Thabit was a planet located within the Thabit system of the Inner Rim. Local Maiferri Tag was a Rebel spy arrested and executed by the Galactic Empire shortly before the suicide of Keth Beamis.

properties.name: Thaere
properties.description: The Thaereian system was a Expansion Region star system centered around a dying yellow star, near the Cularin system. Planets in the system included Odae Ripp, Thaere Privo, Zham Hlar.

properties.name: Thakwaa
properties.description: Thakwaa was a temperate planet dominated by grassy plains that was located in the Thakwaa system of the Tunka sector in the Outer Rim Territories. It was an isolated world that attracted little attention from the Galactic Empire until the end of the Galactic Civil War. The Empire gave up trying to take over this planet due to its native species' unpredictable nature's as well as their size and strength, not because the planet was useless.

properties.name: Thalassia
properties.description: Thalassia was a planet located within the Thalassian system of the Outer Rim Territories. It was the location of the Thalassian slavers' base of operations and the home planet of the Thalassians.

properties.name: Thaldo
properties.description: Thaldo was a planet located within the Thaldo system of the Mid Rim.

properties.name: Thandon Nebula
properties.description: The Thandon Cluster, also known as the Thandon Nebula, was a star cluster located within the Corporate Sector in the Outer Rim region of the galaxy. The cluster included the Dostra system, and the only habitable world within the Cluster was the planet Brosi.

properties.name: Thandruss
properties.description: Thandruss was a terrestrial planet located in the Expansion Region's Thand sector. It was the homeworld of the Krytollaks, warm-blooded sentients with hard outer shells. Krytollaks had a society consisting of a worker class and a royal class and were ruled by a global absolute monarchy.

properties.name: Thanium
properties.description: Thanium was a planet located within the Thanium system of the Outer Rim Territories. It was absorbed into Xim's Empire as he expanded his borders from the Kingdom of Cron.

properties.name: Thanta Zilbra
properties.description: Thanta Zilbra was a smuggler who crashed on a planet with a native fungus with tremendous healing properties. Obtaining sponsorship from the New Republic, Zilbra established a colony on the planet, now known as Thanta Zilbra to harvest Zilbra fungus. Zilbra was killed when the planet was destroyed during the Corellian Crisis, but did insist his four sons and two daughters evacuate.

properties.name: Thape
properties.description: Thape was an astronomical object located in the Thape system, a part of the Lambda sector in The Slice portion of the Mid Rim. It lay on a hyperlane between Ando and Leritor. It was a place of origin of the Order of Dai Bendu, a mystic Force tradition that preceded the birth of the Jedi Order.

properties.name: Tharados
properties.description: Tharados was a small, cold planet that was located within the Tharados system of the Mid Rim. The Zabrak Haast Aath ran a slave compound there for Riboga the Hutt. Twelve clone troopers were also sent there during the Clone Wars, due to an administrative error.

properties.name: Tharkos
properties.description: Tharkos was a planet located in the Tharkos system of the Outer Rim Territories. It was the headquarters of Millennium Astro-Engineering. Millions of its people died in the Stenax Massacres invasion of 5 ABY.

properties.name: Thassalia
properties.description: Thassalia was a planet located within the Thassalia system of the Outer Rim Territories that had a Blood Prince.

properties.name: Theal
properties.description: Theal was a planet located within the Theal system of the Mid Rim.

properties.name: Thearterra
properties.description: Thearterra was a planet of the Chiss Ascendancy in the Unknown Regions. An insignificant world, Thearterra was perpetually wracked by volcanoes, hailstorms, and groundquakes.

properties.name: Thela
properties.description: The Thela system was located in the Aparo sector, in the Trans-Hydian portion of the Outer Rim Territories. It shared its name with the starship Pride of Thela.

properties.name: Themis
properties.description: Themis was a planet located in the Themis system of the Inner Rim. It was the homeworld of the Themians. Themis was orbited by a moon which contained an explosive ore that was capable of acting as a power source.

properties.name: Thennqor
properties.description: The Thennqor system was a star system that was located within the Sarka sector, a part of the galactic regions known as the Mid Rim and the Slice. It was home to the sentient Thennqora species.

properties.name: Thermon
properties.description: Thermon was a planet located within the Thermon system of the Mid Rim with many moons that spewed methane gas from geysers.

properties.name: Theselon
properties.description: The Theselon system was located in the Interior Region, an area of the Hapes Cluster in the Slice portion of the Inner Rim. It was connected via hyperlanes to the Baldavia and Millinar systems. The Theselon system was the origin point of the article of clothing known as the Theselonian bridal gown.

properties.name: Thesme
properties.description: Thesme was a planet located within the Thesme system of the Outer Rim Territories. An industrial world, it served as the lackluster sector capital of Thesme sector, on the Thesme Trace.

properties.name: Thila
properties.description: Thila was a small planet in the Thila system of the Outer Rim Territories, located in the Gordian Reach. It was home to a major Alliance to Restore the Republic base, Thila Command. The planet had relatively huge mountain ranges, of which the peaks of its gigantic mountains were visible from orbit.

properties.name: Thisspias
properties.description: Thisspias was an Expansion Region planet located in the Farstey sector. It was home to the creatures known as cygnats and was the homeworld of the sentient reptilian Thisspiasians. The Thisspiasians were governed by a millennia-old absolute monarchy that was complemented by a democratically elected parliament. The Thisspiasians, an ancient species of warriors, joined the Galactic Republic early in its history, becoming instrumental in averting both external and internal threats to that government. Between 3959 BBY and 3956 BBY, the planet fell within the borders of Darth Revan's Sith Empire.

properties.name: Thoadeye
properties.description: Thoadeye was an astronomical object located in the galaxy's Deep Core.

properties.name: Thobek
properties.description: Thobek was a planet located within the Thobek system of the Core Worlds. It was situated on the Widek Bypass.

properties.name: Thodia
properties.description: The Thodia system was a star system located within the Mid Rim. It was home to the sentient Thodian species.

properties.name: Thokos
properties.description: Thokos was a planet located within the Thokos system of the Core Worlds. Colonists from Thokos settled Ammuud.

properties.name: Thokosia
properties.description: The Thokosia system was located in the Maerdocian sector, a part of the Slice portion of the Mid Rim. It was situated on the hyperlane known as the Gamor Run, which connected it to the Shador system as well as the Daalang system of the Daalang sector.

properties.name: Tholatin
properties.description: Tholatin was a planet located within the Tholatin system of the Mid Rim. It was the location of Esau's Ridge, a thin crevasse in a towering rock wall inhabited by smugglers. The planet's chief of security was Plaan in 25 ABY. Tholatin was conquered by the Yuuzhan Vong some time during the latter's onslaught into the galaxy. The planet was eventually liberated from the invaders by the Mandalorian Protectors under Boba Fett in 29 ABY.

properties.name: Tholaz
properties.description: Tholaz was a planet located within the Tholaz system of the Core Worlds.

properties.name: Tholian
properties.description: Tholians were one of many species previously portrayed by the holovid actor Palleus Chuff prior to 20 BBY. The actor seemed to hold having played the species in high regard though why that was is unknown. Little is known about the Tholians, their culture, or even what they looked like. Considering Chuff's short stature, they were probably a diminuitive race if Chuff effectively portrayed one of them. They presumably originated from the Tholian system in the Meram sector of the Outer Rim Territories.

properties.name: Tholon
properties.description: Tholon was a Wild Space planet located within the star system of the same name. A desolate rock world with rich deposits of various ores, it was the first planet discovered by the Human scout Casti Tholon by 2 ABY.

properties.name: Tholoth
properties.description: Tholoth was a planet located within the Tholoth system of the Colonies.

properties.name: Thomork
properties.description: A Core Worlds astronomical object, Thomork was the site of an Imperial Military shipyard. Shortly before the Battle of Endor, the facility produced Imperial-class Star Destroyers. Years before 10 ABY, the Empire spread the rumor that the Thomork shipyard was closed due to a hive virus outbreak and, to lend credence to the rumor, killed over 450 people there. The shipyard was then secretly re-opened and used for Imperial construction projects such as the first World Devastator superweapon.

properties.name: ThonBoka Nebula
properties.description: The ThonBoka, also known as the ThonBoka Nebula, was a sack-shaped nebula in the Centrality full of gases, organic molecules, carapace creatures and interstellar plankton. Its name translated into Basic as "StarCave Nebula." It was home to the sentient Oswaft species, manta ray-like creatures that fed on the nutrients inside the ThonBoka.

properties.name: Thonner
properties.poi: Ayrou holding cells, Firagh, Greater Zoun Archipelago, Korraj's base, Lesser Firagh Peninsula, Mollusk arches,
properties.description: Thonner was an Outer Rim Territories planet located in the Moddell sector. It was covered in shallow oceans and seas that were broken by strings of sandy islands. Freshwater vents also dotted Thonner's surface, and lichen imported from the planet Maya Kovel grew on the world's islands. Thonner's Lesser Firagh Peninsula was home to dangerous fauna such as the Zoun mauler.

properties.name: Thoran
properties.description: Thoran was a planet located within the Bothan sector of the Mid Rim.

properties.name: Thorgeld
properties.description: Thorgeld I, also known as Thorgeld, was a Core Worlds planet. The mansion of Fabritech, Inc. head Kvarn Mandel and his family was located on the planet, in the underground city of Fabrin. During the Galactic Civil War, the crew of the light freighter Dorion Discus visited Thorgeld I. Shortly after the freighter left the planet, the Imperial Customs Frigate Assessor attempted to board the vessel for a customs inspection, but the Dorion Discus eventually escaped into hyperspace.

properties.name: Thornhedge Nebula
properties.description: The Thornhedge Nebula was a nebula located within the Terr'skiar sector of the Mid Rim and known for its brilliance in space.

properties.name: Thorsgild
properties.description: Thorsgild was a planet where a cantina known as the Blood Bucket was located. Simms Jonndril frequented the Blood Bucket in his youth.

properties.name: Thosa
properties.description: Thosa was a planet of barren rock orbiting Dostra Major in the Dostra system. It was the fifth planet in the system, and was orbited by two moons.

properties.name: Thousand Moons
properties.description: Thousand Moons could refer to one of the following:

properties.name: Thovinack
properties.description: Thovinack may refer to one of the following:

properties.name: Thracior
properties.description: Thracior was a planet located within the Thracior system of the Core Worlds. The planet was ruled by tribal Warlords. Wars would periodically take place amongst the clans. Rival clans forbade interclan marriage, which could subject to capital punishment. The two best known tribes were Hnsi and Tantt.

properties.name: Thrago
properties.description: Thrago was a small moon located in the Thrago system of the Unknown Regions with a swirling atmosphere of yellow sulfuric clouds. It was little more than a hubba-shaped lump of rock, barely ten kilometers from end to end and so blanketed in dust that its thousands of craters had a soft, almost featureless look from orbit. It was the location of Supply Depot Thrago, belonging to the Chiss. Jacen Solo tricked a number of Jedi Knights, including Jaina Solo, Zekk, Tahiri Veila, Tesar Sebatyne and Lowbacca, into believing the Chiss were planning a preemptive strike on the Killiks. The Jedi used StealthXs to help Jacen attack Thrago, provoking the Chiss to attack the Killiks, as Jacen intended.

properties.name: Thraisai
properties.description: Thraisai was a planet located in the Thraisai system of Wild Space. At some point between 17 BBY and 0 ABY, the Human bounty hunter Beilert Valance led a group of mercenaries in capturing a ring of slavers on Thraisai, a mission that helped Valance attain the status of an elite hunter.

properties.name: Thrakia
properties.description: Thrakia was a planet with large land masses and rich in natural resources located in the Hapes Cluster. It was the homeworld of the Thrakians, an intelligent insect species.

properties.name: Thrantin
properties.poi: Zero-G, Ammonia Ocean, Heavy Grav Mountainous Zones,
properties.description: Thrantin, or OM813, was the planet headquarters of Barosa Warren and the Galactic Outdoor Survival School. It was located in the Ollonir Boundaries of the Colonies.

properties.name: Threfal
properties.description: Threfal was a world located in the Threfal system, a part of the Mid Rim's Iska sector. Threfal had a Type I breathable atmosphere, and it was the homeworld of the plant known as the meatvine, which could be used as food.

properties.name: Thrugii
properties.description: Thrugii was a planet located within the Thrugii system of the Outer Rim Territories. A desolate, rocky planet near an asteroid field, it has been the home of many failed miners. The residents were considered claim jumpers by the sector authorities, who said that they controlled all the rights to Thrugii and the asteroid belt. After the authorities locked down the planet, the miners found themselves out of supplies. Smuggler Kaine Paulsen was killed while trying to deliver supplies to them.

properties.name: Thrynka
properties.description: Thrynka may refer to one of the following:

properties.name: Thule
properties.poi: Armory, Droid factory, Sith Arts Academy, Hurom's Sith Temple, Kessiak's Sith Temple,
properties.description: Thule was a dry and arid Force nexus steeped in the dark side of the Force that lay upon the western flanks of the Stygian Caldera in the Esstran sector. A hidden Sith fortress world for most of its history, Thule consistently served as a redoubt and resource for many generations of Sith over a protracted period of millennia.

properties.name: Thull's Vault
properties.description: Thull's Vault was a planet with luminescent sands that was located within the Thull's Vault system, in the Juvex sector of the Mid Rim. According to legend, an ancient fleet of treasure ships was hidden beneath the planet's sands.

properties.name: Thustra
properties.poi: Alaric's garden, Alaric's palace, Thustra Republic command center,
properties.description: Thustra was a planet located within the Thustra system, Sumitra sector of the galaxy's Expansion Region. It was also the homeworld of a Near-Human race known as the Sephi. Until the advent of the Clone Wars, Thustra was a member world of the Galactic Republic, and was thus represented in the Galactic Senate by a senator. By 21 BBY, approximately nine months into the civil war, the Sephi betrayed the Republic and joined Thustra with the rebellion of the Confederacy of Independent Systems.

properties.name: Thyferra
properties.poi: Dlarit estateDocking Bay 72Morbo's PlacePlastoid PittSeeqov Thranx's apartmentXucphra Corporate HeadquartersVrelnid
properties.description: Thyferra was a hot, humid planet located in the Polith system on the Rimma Trade Route, on which most of the galaxy's bacta was produced. It was also a major political power as bacta production was an essential commodity.

properties.name: Thyrsus
properties.description: Thyrsus was a planet located in the Thyrsus system of the Inner Rim and the homeworld of the Thyrsians, an Echani offshoot that originated the Sun Guard.

properties.name: Tibrin
properties.description: Tibrin  was a planet located within the Mid Rim and the homeworld of the Ishi Tib.

properties.name: Tibro
properties.description: Tibro was an astronomical object located in the Tibro system, a part of the Baronos sector in the Slice portion of the Colonies. The Human male Beyla Rus was born on Tibro in 24 BBY. Tibro was also the homeworld of the Human female Maxig Kress.

properties.name: Tiems
properties.description: Tiems was a city on the planet Tiems in the Tiems system of the Outer Rim Territories. During the Galactic Civil War, several thousand Alliance to Restore the Republic prisoners were held in the city. They were liberated by Alliance forces under the command of General Carlist Rieekan during the Battle of Tiems. The city was connected to other settlements by the Tiems Road, and was located near the Gopps Forest and the Blue River.

properties.name: Tieos
properties.description: Tieos was a planet located in the Tieos system, a part of the Abrion sector within the Slice portion of the Outer Rim Territories. The planet featured several oceans on its surface, and its landmasses were completely covered in grasslands. Shortly following the Battle of Yavin, Tieos held massive future potential as an agriworld.

properties.name: Tierell
properties.description: Tierell was a planet located in the Tierell system within the Thesme sector of the Outer Rim Territories.

properties.name: Tierfon
properties.description: Tierfon was a small planet in the Tierfon system of the Sumitra sector, located in the Expansion Region. Its surface was dotted with mountain ranges, huge gorges, and rock cliffs.

properties.name: Tifnyl
properties.description: Tifnyl was the fourth planet of the the Tifnyl system. It was a gas giant located in the Elrood sector of the Outer Rim Territories. Its moon was the location of an Imperial listening post during the Galactic Civil War.

properties.name: Tiisheraan
