properties.description: Tiisheraan was a planet located in the Tiisheraan system, a part of the Southern Core portion of the Core Worlds. It was the homeworld of the Human Galactic Republic Senator Galen Derlin and the birthplace of his son, Bren.

properties.name: Tikath
properties.description: Tikath was a planet located in the Tikath system of the Outer Rim Territories. It was a fortress world with a notoriously strong defense. A group of rebel operatives traveled to the planet in pursuit of Imperial scientist Etha Naru.

properties.name: Till Chorios
properties.description: Till Chorios was a planet located within the Till Chorios system of the Outer Rim Territories. It was represented in the Galactic Senate by Bufus Ritsomas. Ritsomas allowed Thalassian slavers to operate in Meridian sector in exchange for a share of their profits, until he was exposed and arrested 22 BBY, shortly before the Clone Wars.

properties.name: Tillo
properties.description: The Tillo system was a star system located within the Tapani sector of the Colonies. It was located in Reena Province on the Caloria Run.

properties.name: Timbra Ott
properties.description: Timbra Ott was a planet located in the Kathol Outback, at the end of the Galtea Run.

properties.name: Timora
properties.description: Timora was a planet located in the Timora system of the Outer Rim Territories and the inner endpoint of the Shiritoku Way. It was the closest planet in the Empire "proper" to Bakura. Its people exported sunpetals. It also served as a shipping point for repulsorlift products from Bakura.

properties.name: Tinallis
properties.description: Tinallis was a planet located within the Tinallis system of the Mid Rim. Though it was an industrialized planet, it was noted for the wildlife in its oceans, seashores, and rainforests. One of its native creatures, the tresher, was a lucrative but illegal trade item.

properties.name: Tinoon
properties.description: Tinoon was a planet located within the Tinoon system of the Outer Rim Territories relatively close to the Zephry Asteroid field. The planet's orbit was home to a customs check point and a Cargo Facility. It was raided by pirates after the Battle of Hoth.

properties.name: Tinta
properties.description: Tinta first appeared as a prop in the film Rogue One: A Star Wars Story, which was released in North America on December 16, 2016. The prop was not identified in the film, but received a name in the Star Wars: Rogue One: The Ultimate Visual Guide, which was written by Pablo Hidalgo and released alongside the film.

properties.name: Tintel
properties.description: Tintel was a planet located within the Tintel system of the Expansion Region.

properties.name: Tion
properties.description: Tion, sometimes referred as Tion Proper, was a planet located within the Tion Hegemony of the Outer Rim Territories, considered as the original center of the Hegemony.

properties.name: Tirac Munda
properties.description: Tirac Munda was an astronomical object located in the Tirac Munda system, a part of the Hevvrol sector in the Trailing Sectors portion of the Mid Rim. It was the homeworld of the Human thief Merc Sunlet.

properties.name: Tiragga
properties.description: Tiragga was a planet of the Tiragga system, in the Mieru'kar sector, located within the Outer Rim of the galaxy. The planet was orbited by at least two moons. The second moon was home to a Rebel Alliance outpost during the Galactic Civil War, a large conflict between the Alliance and the Galactic Empire. At some point during the conflict, the base personnel became infected with the Direllian Plague, a fatal disease that could only be cured with the administration of Shiarha Root, a rare plant found on the world of Kirtania.

properties.name: Tirahnn
properties.description: Tirahnn was a bustling trade world in the Inner Rim's Zeemacht Cluster, that served as an important stop along the Perlemian Trade Route. A mercantilist society essentially ruled by super-rich "merchant princes," Tirahnn was known across the galaxy for its massive bazaars and markets, the largest of which stretched for miles and were bigger than entire nations on other planets. This made Tirahnn a popular destination for rich tourists, with the annual Great Fair especially drawing a vast number of visitors to the world. Among the offworlders who stopped by for the Great Fair were famed Rebel leaders Luke Skywalker and Leia Organa, who visited the event in 0 ABY. Tirahnn's importance as a trade nexus made it occasionally a target during wartime: during the Clone Wars it changed hands multiple times between the Galactic Republic and the Confederacy of Independent Systems.

properties.name: Tirsa
properties.description: Tirsa was an industrial planet located within the Tirsa system of the Outer Rim Territories. It was home to the Tirsa Wargear armaments company that manufactured the Leviathan submersible carrier.

properties.name: Tisht
properties.description: Tisht was a planet that was located within the Tisht system in Hutt Space, a region of the galaxy controlled by the Hutt species. The planet lay on the hyperlane called The Dead Road, which connected it to the worlds of M'Hanna and Saqqar.

properties.name: Tiss'sharl
properties.description: Tiss'sharl was a planet in the Xappyh sector, located in the Outer Rim Territories. It was home to the Tiss'shar, a species of intelligent therapods.

properties.name: Tizon
properties.description: Tizon was a planet located within the Tizon system of the Core Worlds and one of the original 13 planets of the Duskhan League.

properties.name: Tlactehon
properties.description: A trade world lying on the Corellian Run super-hyperroute, Tlactehon was located in the Expansion Region's Kailion sector. A delegation from Tlactehon that was in reality a front for a gang of smugglers once traveled to the planet Muunilinst, where it was scheduled to meet with representatives of the InterGalactic Banking Clan. As part of the conquest of the galaxy by the extragalactic Yuuzhan Vong, the invaders held the Tlactehon system until at least 27 ABY.

properties.name: Tlönia
properties.description: Tlön was a planet located in the Tlönia system of the Demetras sector in the Outer Rim. It was the homeworld of the Tlönian species. It was depopulated and incinerated by the 6100s BBY.

properties.name: Tocco
properties.description: The Tocco system was a star system located within the Tapani sector. It was part of the Melantha Province, situated near the Lupani and Ricaldi systems.

properties.name: Tocoya
properties.description: Tocoya was a planet located within the Tocoya system of the Inner Rim and the homeworld of the Tocoyan race. Neb Dulo, a disciple of the religion Davrilat, was from the planet. The rock wart was also found here.

properties.name: Todirium
properties.description: Todirium III was a planet located within the Todirium system of the Outer Rim Territories. Located near warlord Zsinj's territory, it was a bleak iron mining colony that refined durasteel. Wraith Squadron raided the planet in the guise of Rogue Squadron during their campaign against Zsinj.

properties.name: Togominda
properties.description: Togominda was a planet located within the Outer Rim Territories and known for its salt geysers.

properties.name: Togoria
properties.description: Togoria was a planet in the Mid Rim and the homeworld of the Togorians.

properties.name: Tokmia
properties.description: Tokmia was a mostly icy, snow-covered planet in the Anoat sector of the Outer Rim Territories. Home to the primitive, barely-sentient Oku species, Tokmia featured bountiful crystal and ore deposits, from which the Figg Excavations mining company earned a fortune before abandoning the planet. In 3 ABY, during the Galactic Civil War, Tokmia was one of three worlds in the Anoat sector, including Hoth, to which the Galactic Empire sent reconnaissance probe droids in search of the hidden Rebel Alliance base.

properties.name: Tol Ado
properties.description: Tol Ado was a planet located within the Tol Ado system of the Outer Rim Territories.

properties.name: Tol Amn
properties.description: Tol Amn was a murky, stormy planet that was located within the star system of the same name, in the Hutt Space region of the galaxy. The planet lay on the hyperlane called the Oktos Route that connected it both to the planet Toydaria and the hyperspace route known as the Trax Tube.

properties.name: Tolan
properties.description: Tolan was a planet located within the Tolan system of the Colonies. It was the location of the Tolan Navy Shipyards, near Dankayo and probably within a few sectors of Ralltiir.

properties.name: Tolfrania
properties.description: Tolfrania was a planet located within the Tolfrania system of the Inner Rim. Eero Iridian had to work on a Tolfranian brief while working at the Galactic Senate. Dooku offered to help him on it in exchange for access to Iridian's Senate security code.

properties.name: Tomark
properties.description: Tomark was a location in the galaxy that served as an Alliance to Restore the Republic regional headquarters and operations sector during the early rebellion against the Galactic Empire. Tomark was included in a map of the galaxy that listed safe worlds, starfighter hubs at level five or higher, regional headquarters and operations sectors, and deep space caches.

properties.name: Tomo-Reth
properties.description: Tomo-Reth was an astronomical object located in the Tomo-Reth system, a part of the Trailing Sectors portion of the Inner Rim. It was the site of the Caliginous Automaton of Tomo-Reth, a famous, more than fifty meters–high droid that sat on a brick throne and breathed fire at visitors, causing them to become amazed.

properties.name: Ton-Falk
properties.description: Ton-Falk was a planet located within the Ton-Falk system of the Outer Rim Territories.

properties.name: Toola
properties.poi: Great Ice Floes, Ithaqua StationToola SpaceportNew Republic embassy
properties.description: Toola was a cold planet located in the Kaelta system. It was the homeworld of the Whiphids and was located in the Slice.

properties.name: Toong'l
properties.description: Toong'l was an astronomical object located in the Outer Rim Territories of the galaxy, positioned at the coordinates T-7 on the Standard Galactic Grid.

properties.name: Toprawa
properties.poi: Ansharii Caverns, Foothill, Imperial Research Station, Mountain Home, Toprawa Relay Station,
properties.description: Toprawa was a remote, forested planet in the Toprawa system of the Kalamith sector in the Bright Jewel Oversector, located in the Outer Rim Territories near the Hydian Way.

properties.name: Torch Nebula
properties.description: The Torch Nebula, also known as the Torch sector, was a large nebula within the Outer Rim Territories. It formed a sector that contained the Piluvia system and was crossed by the Llanic Spice Run and Five Veils Route hyperlanes.

properties.name: Torina
properties.description: Torina was a terraformed planet located in the Torina system of the Elrood sector.

properties.name: Torize
properties.description: The planet Torize was located in the system of the same name on the Trition Trade Route in the Kathol sector of the Outer Rim Territories. A major trade and industrial hub, the planet was orbited by numerous space stations, and spaceports littered the surface. A naturally volcanic planet with high levels of activity, Torize's atmosphere was hazardous to most beings, and a breath mask was required. The atmosphere was worsened by an industrial accident in 5 ABY that released toxic pollutants into the air. In 8 ABY, the sector capital, Kal'Shebbol, was liberated by New Republic forces, forcing the local Imperial warlord, Moff Kentor Sarne, into retreat. The planet subsequently faced an internal power struggle between Imperial loyalists intent on holding the planet, and New Republic sympathizers who wished to overthrow them.

properties.name: Torn Station
properties.description: Torn Station was a space station located in a star system within the Mytaranor sector. The sector was part of the Kashyyyk Region in the Slice section of the Mid Rim. The station was connected to the Kashyyyk and Quas Killam systems through the hyperlane known as the Great Kashyyyk Branch.

properties.name: Torolis
properties.description: Torolis was a Bothan colony world located within the Torolis system of the Mid Rim.

properties.name: Torpris
properties.description: Torpris was a planet located within the Torpris system of the Core Worlds.

properties.name: Torque
properties.description: Torque  was a planet located within the Torque system of the Outer Rim Territories and the sector capital of the Gordian Reach. A lackluster industrial world, it was the headquarters of Bwahl the Hutt.

properties.name: Tortali
properties.description: Tortali may refer to one of the following:

properties.name: Torve
properties.description: Torve was a human male lieutenant and CO of the Deadeyes, a Republic Army sniper squad. He was the former XO of Aric Jorgan.

properties.name: Tosste
properties.description: Tosste was a uninhabited rocky planet located within the Outer Rim Territories.

properties.name: Tothis
properties.description: Tothis was a middling industrial planet located in the Tothis system of the Corporate Sector.

properties.name: Tovarskl
properties.description: Tovarskl was a terrestrial planet in Wild Space and a colony world of the Yam'rii.

properties.name: Toydaria
properties.description: Toydaria was a large, muddy planet located in the Toydaria system of Hutt Space, and home to the mind trick-resistant Toydarians.

properties.name: Tozeer
properties.description: Tozeer was a planet located within the Tozeer system of the Outer Rim Territories. Tozeer was a desert world with Jawas and Tusken Raiders living on it.

properties.name: Tragrud
properties.description: Tragrud was the only planet in the Tragrud system, a star system located in the Periphery, a sector in the Outer Rim Territories near Hutt Space.

properties.name: Trailia
properties.description: Trailia was a low-tech planet, located in the Trailia system of the Outer Rim Territories, on the fringes of known space. It was the homeworld of the Trailians. It was a technologically unadvanced world with thick jungles.

properties.name: Tralfin
properties.description: Tralfin was tropical resort world located in the Outer Rim Territories' Xappyh sector. In 28 BBY, the Human Qan Gindoch was born on Tralfin. Shortly after the Battle of Yavin, Moff Crin Harson of the Galactic Empire was murdered on Tralfin. A group of Rebel Alliance agents with which Harson had been acquainted was implicated in the crime, but eventually the real killer was discovered and the Rebels were cleared of the murder charges.

properties.name: Trallan
properties.description: Trallan was a planet located within the Trallan system of the Colonies and the homeworld of Captain Theb Tobbra.

properties.name: Tramanos
properties.description: Tramanos was a watery moon located within the Tramanos system of the Spumani sector. Due to the large percentage of cyanogen in the moon's atmosphere, it was the site of a Celegian colony during the Republic Dark Age. However, since the air also contained oxygen, other, oxygen-breathing species lived there, too, although they had to use hazard masks. It was visited by the Sith Lord Saaj Calician.

properties.name: Trammen
properties.description: Trammen was a heavily-populated planet that was located in the Trammen system of the Harron sector. It contained an Imperial Army garrison; all the line squads of the Imperial Army stationed there were re-equipped with light repeating blasters.

properties.name: Trammis
properties.description: Trammis was the primary star of the Trammis system.

properties.name: Tran Mariel
properties.description: Tran Mariel was a planet located within the Tran Mariel system of the Core Worlds and the homeworld of the Runyip.

properties.name: Trancret
properties.description: Trancret was a planet in the Trancret system and the sector capital of the Perkell sector. It was home to the Human Trancretes. The Trancret Stock Exchange Swindle was pulled off by the Red & Black League of Herstell V.

properties.name: Transel
properties.description: Transel was a planet located within the Transel system of the Colonies, where the Ebon Hawk was originally registered.

properties.name: Tranthellix
properties.description: Tranthellix was a planet in the Tranthellix system, located in the Tangles of the Senex sector in the Mid Rim. The rugged, mountainous planet was controlled by the Human noble family House Petro. Like many worlds in the Senex-Juvex, House Petro had conquered the planet's native species and consigned them to slavery.

properties.name: Trantor
properties.description: Trantor was an ecumenopolis located within the Trantor system of the Core Worlds and the homeworld of Trantor pigeons.

properties.name: Traptoforia
properties.description: The Traptoforia system was a star system that was located within the Thrasybule sector, which was a part of the galactic regions known as the Outer Rim Territories and the Trans-Hydian. The system was home to the creatures known as Traptoforian razor slugs.

properties.name: Trascor
properties.description: Trascor was a terrestrial planet located in the Trascor system, a part of the Corva sector in the New Territories portion of the Outer Rim Territories. It featured the large island continent Klypash.

properties.name: Trasemene
properties.description: Trasemene was an Outer Rim Territories celestial body located in the Phelleem sector. A part of the Confederacy of Independent Systems during the Clone Wars, in 19 BBY it saw a battle where the navy of the Galactic Empire defeated that of the Separatist holdout led by Toonbuck Toora. Trasemene also shared its name with the Siege of Trasemene.

properties.name: Trasse
properties.description: Trasse was a barren, isolated asteroid located within the Trasse system of the Mid Rim that was heavily protected by Imperial forces.

properties.name: Trassitan
properties.description: Trassitan was an astronomical object located in the Trassitan system, a part of the Veragi sector in the New Territories portion of the Outer Rim Territories. The Veragi Trade Route hyperlane linked Trassitan to the Veragi system as well as the Dubrillion system in the Myto sector.

properties.name: Traval-Pacor
properties.description: The Traval-Pacor system, also known as the Traval-Parcor System, lay in the Mid Rim's Pacor sector. By 1 BBY, it was the site of the Traval-Parcor System Institute of Technology, which was attended by the Ho'Din Yansan. The Galactic Empire used a shipyard in the system to produce Imperial-class Star Destroyers in 4 ABY. Eight years later, the New Republic triumphed over the Imperial Remnant in a battle fought within the system.

properties.name: Travnin
properties.description: Travnin was a moon which orbited a gas giant in the double-star Travnin system. It was the sector capital of the Minos Cluster, covered in deserts and mountains with intense winds. The local day was 26 standard hours; the year was 325 local days. The main settlement was Travnin Spaceport.

properties.name: Trebela
properties.description: Trebela was a terrestrial astronomical object located in the Trebela system, a part of the Altier sector in the Slice portion of the Expansion Region. A city on Trebela served as its capital.

properties.name: Treffani
properties.description: The Treffani system was a star system located within the Expansion Region.

properties.name: Tregillis
properties.description: Tregillis was a planet located within the Tregillis system of the Expansion Region.

properties.name: Trellen
properties.description: Trellen was a planet at the junction of the Hydian Way and the Trellen Trade Route.

properties.name: Trendivar
properties.description: Trendivar was a planet in the Hunnoverrs sector of the Outer Rim. A skirmish occurred here between the forces of the Vanderijar kajidic and the bounty hunters of Grim Destiny.

properties.name: Trenwyth
properties.description: Trenwyth was a planet located within the Trenwyth system of the Outer Rim Territories.

properties.name: Tresidiss
properties.description: Tresidiss was a planet located in the Tresidiss system of the Outer Rim Territories. It was owned by Herglic criminals who ran massive gambling establishments and usurious banking operations on the planet. As a result of its deliberately lax tariff laws, Tresidiss attracted intelligence agents of every stripe.

properties.name: Trevi
properties.poi: Fizzi's Slightly Used Starships, Galactic Empire post,
properties.description: Trevi IV, also known as Trevi, was a dry planet of barren plains and deserts. It was situated along several hyperlanes and lay in the Mid Rim's Quess sector. A Truishii trader starship was forced to land on Trevi IV at some point to make repairs. The Truishii subsequently decided to establish a colony at the landing site, which quickly developed into the large spaceport settlement known as Trevi City. The planet itself eventually became a trade world inhabited by thirty-five million sentients of various species.

properties.name: Trevura
properties.description: Trevura was an Imperial-controlled Inner Rim planet with a prominent droid population. At some point between 0 BBY and 5 ABY, an underground droid resistance group on Trevura hired the assassin droid S-R6 to kill the local governor, Merno Blask. In response, Blask arranged for a recently developed anti-droid inhibit setting for blasters to be field-tested in Voma, the planet's capital.

properties.name: Trian
properties.description: Trian was a planet located within the Trian system of Wild Space.

properties.name: Trif
properties.description: Trif was a planet located within the Trif system of the Outer Rim Territories. It was under the control of the Galactic Empire as of the Black Fleet Crisis.

properties.name: Triffis
properties.description: Triffis was a planet located within the Triffis system of the Mid Rim, along the Duros Space Run It was the homeworld of the Triffians, including Podracer pilot Ebe E. Endocott and Senator Eelen Li.

properties.name: Trigalis
properties.description: Trigalis was a swamp-covered planet located within the Outer Rim Territories' Juris sector. Long before the Clone Wars, the trading post of New Coronet was founded on Trigalis, but over time the city degenerated into a busy center of various illegal activities.

properties.name: Trigaskian Blur
properties.description: The Trigaskian Blur was a location in space that was situated within the galaxy's Wild Space, relatively far from the Inner Rim planet Mindor. When the Mindor resistance leader Aeona Cantor asked her fellow insurgent Tripp about the status of subspace jammers that the Imperial warlord Shadowspawn had installed on Mindor in the year 5 ABY, Tripp replied that the jammers were inoperative, adding that the resistance could send a subspace signal across the considerable distance between the planet and the Trigaskian Blur if they wanted to.

properties.name: Trindello
properties.description: Trindello was a moon located within the Trindello system of the Outer Rim Territories. It was home to the kargul. Clusters of Trindellan oak covered the moon.

properties.name: Trinovat
properties.description: Trinovat was a planet located within the Trinovat system of the Outer Rim Territories. It was a verdant world of small farms and mines, homeworld of the Trinovates.

properties.name: Trinta
properties.description: Trinta was a swamp planet located within the Yartiv system of the Outer Rim Territories near Kwenn Space Station. It was home to a dark side nexus that was occupied by an insane Halagad Ventor during the height of the Galactic Empire.

properties.name: Triton
properties.description: Triton was a small, almost lifeless planet in the Mayagil sector of the Outer Rim Territories. It was orbited by the three Triton Moons. The moons were nefariously used by many in the galaxy to describe a dead thing—as dead as a Triton moon, due to the ban of stimulants of any kind.

properties.name: Trogan
properties.description: Trogan was a planet located within the Trogan system of the Outer Rim Territories, known for its strong tides, natural beauty, terrible weather, and lush vegetation springing from desolate wasteland. The planet's residents hoped to turn it into a tourist attraction, in order to compete with rival Berchest, but despite spectacular oceanic activity, the hoped-for tourism never materialized, and the planet's economy stagnated at a subsistence level.

properties.name: Troiken
properties.poi: Hormick Range, Lycinder Plain, Mount Avos,
properties.description: Troiken was a planet located in the Troiken system of the Outer Rim Territories, and the homeworld of the Xexto.

properties.name: Troos
properties.description: Troos was a planet located within the Gordian Reach of the Outer Rim Territories.

properties.name: Trosh
properties.description: Trosh was a planet located within the Trosh system of the Outer Rim Territories. It was one of many planets where the Galactic Empire enslaved the native people, claiming that it was protecting the rights of the inhabitants.

properties.name: Troska
properties.description: Troska was a forested planet located within the Troska system of the Outer Rim Territories.

properties.name: Troxar
properties.description: Troxar was a planet located within the Troxar system of the Expansion Region and the Troxan homeworld.

properties.name: Trunska
properties.description: Trunska was a planet located within the Trunska system of the Colonies.

properties.name: Truuine
properties.description: Truuine was an Inner Rim waterworld planet. It featured an equatorial belt of islands as well as a polar region with mountains and glaciers. By 4000 BBY, the planet was the site of the Truuine Jedi Praxeum, a training facility established by Jedi Master Mroon Jassa. Around that time, the Gotal Kith Kark visited Truuine and encountered Jassa, which eventually led to the former taking up Jedi studies at the Praxeum. During the reign of the Galactic Empire millennia later, Truuine's islands were home to Karkarodon and Patrolian settlers.

properties.name: Truuzdann
properties.description: Truuzdann was a planet in the Corellian sector. It was primarily visited for its small spaceport.

properties.name: Tsoss Beacon
properties.description: Tsoss Beacon was an asteroid in the Tsoss Beacon system of the Deep Core, containing an Imperial communications relay station built in 3 BBY.

properties.name: Tsukkia
properties.description: Tsukkia was a planet located within the Tsukkia system of the Colonies and housed the manufacturer of Tsukkian water freighters.

properties.name: Tsyk
properties.description: Tsyk was a murky, polluted planet in the Tsyk system. It was the homeworld of the Tsyklen.

properties.name: Tuerto
properties.description: Tuerto was a planet located within the Tuerto system of the Outer Rim Territories.

properties.name: Tujiamoor
properties.description: Tujiamoor was an Inner Rim astronomical object. It was the site of the Talecalle volcano chain. Around 11 ABY, Doctor Ils Ee visited Tujiamoor after stealing the Gree artifact known as the Sharka'k Noor. Shortly after that, the Talecalle volcanoes, which had remained dormant for 3,000 years, suddenly erupted, killing 400,000 colonists. Later, the xenoarchaeologist Corellia Antilles speculated that it was the artifact that had activated the volcanoes on Tujiamoor.

properties.name: Tulatharri Junction
properties.description: Tulatharri Junction was an astronomical object located within the Tulatharri Junction system of the Outer Rim Territories' Veragi sector. During the Clone Wars, fought between the Galactic Republic and the Confederacy of Independent Systems, Republic colonel Hurst Romodi participated in military actions at Tulatharri Junction and was later decorated for his efforts while fighting there.

properties.name: Tumani
properties.description: The Tumani system was located in the Interior Region, an area of the Hapes Cluster in the Slice portion of the Inner Rim. It was connected via hyperlanes to the Ediorung and Tinta systems. The Tumani system was the origin point of the gemstones known as Tumanian pressure-rubies.

properties.name: Tumus
properties.description: The Tumus system was a star system located within the Tapani sector's Mecetti Province. It was situated on the Procopian Shipping Lane, in the Colonies region of the galaxy.

properties.name: Tun Wala
properties.description: Tun Wala was a manufacturing center located on the planet Arda-2. The T-6 diodem was manufactured here during the Galactic Civil War. Its massive trade shows were visited by S'kytri who performed dramatizations of Initiation Hunts and sold trinkets from Skye.

properties.name: Tund
properties.description: Tund was a verdant terrestrial planet and potent Force nexus situated upon the north-eastern borders of the Open Sea in the Centrality sector. A remote colony world of the Sith species first settled around 27,700 BBY, Tund saw use as a prison for heretics and exiles prior to the collapse of the old Sith Empire, and subsequently came to serve as both the headquarters of the Sith-blooded Sorcerers of Tund and the adopted homeworld of the Toong species. The planet was destroyed in 5 BBY by a biological warhead released by the Croke Sorcerer of Tund Rokur Gepta.

properties.name: Tungra
properties.description: Tungra was the primary planet of the Tungra system.

properties.name: Turkana
properties.description: Turkana was a sparsely populated planet located within the Turkana system near the Pakuuni sector of the Outer Rim Territories.

properties.name: Tusken's Eye
properties.description: The Tusken's Eye was a G-class star in the Tusken's Eye system, orbited by a cloudy planet where the Dark Nest resided following the destruction of Kr. It was here that fifteen nest ships were built: one for Gorog and one for each of the fourteen nests that abandoned the Utegetu Nebula in 36 ABY.

properties.name: Twin Nebulae
properties.description: The Twin Nebulae were a pair of nebulae in the Javin sector, the Ivax Nebula and Kiax Nebula.

properties.name: Twin Sun Station
properties.description: Twin Sun Station, also known as Twin Sun Service Station and Twin Sun Station, was a service platform in the Garis sector's Roccus system, owned and operated by the Azzameen family and used by the family's shipping company Twin Suns Transport Services. Often, the family referred to the station as the "family repair yard".

properties.name: Twith
properties.description: Twith was a planet located within the Twith system of the Core Worlds on one end of the Hyabb-Twith Corridor. It was constantly at war with Hyabb.

properties.name: Tyan
properties.description: Tyan was a planet in the Mid Rim represented in the Galactic Senate by Galim Eddawan.

properties.name: Tyberious
properties.description: Tyberious was a planet located within the Tyberious system of the Inner Rim Territories.

properties.name: Tyed Kant
properties.description: Tyed Kant was an inhabited gas giant in the Core Worlds, near Demophon. It was the only planet in the Kantel system.

properties.name: Tyluun
properties.description: Tyluun was a gloomy planet located in the Tyluun system of the Juvex sector. It was the homeworld of the Night-Soarers.

properties.name: Tyne Albamon
properties.description: Tyne Albamon was an astronomical object located within the Tyne Albamon system, a part of the Outer Rim Territories' Rseik sector. Within a decade after extending its operations to the Rseik sector following the Bordal Contagion of 214 BBY, the Trade Federation established at Tyne Albamon a depot for storing various goods. Tyne Albamon was eventually mentioned in the memoirs of the Trade Defense Force captain Firmus Kett.

properties.name: Tyne's Horky
properties.description: Tyne's Horky was an ore-rich mining world in the Teraab sector. Its streets were full of mining and service droids, used to mine Keschel and Nergon-14.

properties.name: Tynna
properties.poi: Tynna Central Government Building, Lutris Lake, Tanallay Surge complex, Tanallay Surge posting agency,
properties.description: Tynna was a planet located within the Tynnani system of the Expansion Region and the home to the Tynnan species.

properties.name: Tyria
properties.description: Tyria was a planet located within the Tyria system of the Mid Rim. It was the location of the manufacturing plant that built the scoops Anakin Skywalker used for his podracer. The planet was also famous for its expensive Tyrian cloth.

properties.name: Tyrusia
properties.description: The Tyrusia system was a star system located within the Inner Rim Territories.

properties.name: Tyshapahl
properties.description: Tyshapahl was a planet located within the Tyshapahl system of the Outer Rim Territories.

properties.name: Tythe
properties.description: Tythe was a planet located in the Tythe system of the Outer Rim Territories, near Nelvaan.

properties.name: Tython
properties.poi: Belia Darzu's fortress, Je'daii Temples, Jedi Temple, Masters' Retreat, The Rift, Silent Desert, Tansa Reach,
properties.description: Tython was a planet in the Tython system of the Deep Core that played a pivotal role in the histories of the Je'daii Order and its successor, the Jedi Order. A verdant world that was incredibly rich in the Force, Tython was inhabited by an unknown species hundreds of thousands of years before the rise of the Galactic Empire, and it was visited by both the Gree and Kwa, two of the earliest species to have achieved interstellar travel. In 36,453 BBY, the great pyramid ships known as the Tho Yor brought pilgrims from over a dozen species from across the galaxy to Tython, where the pilgrims learned to harness the Force and established the Je'daii Order, basing their philosophy of balance upon Tython's two moons, Ashla and Bogan. The Je'daii soon realized that Tython was unsafe for those who could not sense the Force, and as a result, the Tythans spread out to settle the other worlds of the Tython system.

properties.name: Tyus Cluster
properties.description: The Tyus Cluster was a cluster of black holes located in the Tyus sector of the Mid Rim.

properties.name: Tyybann
properties.description: Tyybann was a world located in the Inner Rim.

properties.name: Tzarib
properties.description: Tzarib was a planet located in the Inner Rim. Quaghens could be caught there.

properties.name: U-Tendik
properties.description: U-Tendik was a planet in the Mid Rim used as a refuge by the Rodian Tetsu Clan. The landscape was dominated by tall Tendril trees, which bore large nuts of the same name. The Rodians Nok and Teeku herded arboreal creatures known as "Tree-Botts" for milk and meat. Other native creatures included bo-toads and manka cats.

properties.name: U'Dray
properties.description: U'Dray was a planet located within the U'Dray system of the Outer Rim Territories. It was the location of the Assault of U'Dray during the Galactic Civil War.

properties.name: Uaua
properties.description: Uaua was an Outer Rim Territories planet located in the Centrality sector. It was the homeworld of the Quor'sav, a species of tall, flightless sentients with avian and monotreme traits. After a virus accidentally introduced by off-world colonists nearly eliminated the Quor'sav, they developed a distrust for members of non-avian species.

properties.name: Uba
properties.description: Uba was an astronomical object located in the galaxy's Mid Rim.

properties.name: Ubertica
properties.description: Ubertica was a planet located within the Ubertica system of the Mid Rim. While habitable, it had a relatively low level of atmospheric oxygen.

properties.name: Ubrikkia
properties.description: Ubrikkia was a Mid Rim industrial world situated in the Kastolar sector. Located on the Ootmian Pabol hyperlane, for millennia it fell under the influence of Hutts from nearby Hutt Space, directly constituting a part of that domain around 5000 BBY. Ubrikkia was the site of the headquarters of the company Ubrikkian Industries and its subsidiaries and shared its name with the ornament known as the Ubrikkian tail spiral ring.

properties.name: Ubuuga
properties.description: Ubuuga was a planet located in the Ubuuga system and the homeworld of the Ubuugans and the Ubuugan fleshborers. Ubuuga was well-known for its caviar.

properties.name: Ucret
properties.description: Ucret was a planet located within the Ucret system of the Core Worlds.

properties.name: Udnil
properties.description: Udnil may refer to one of the following:

properties.name: Udrin Cara
properties.description: Udrin Cara was a secret Imperial military design center in the Mid Rim. Jeres Moridon was stationed there as a researcher, where he was exposed to Maladeria II, a toxic gas that was being researched at the facility for possible military applications.

properties.name: Uhltenden
properties.description: Uhltenden was a planet located within the Thrasybule sector of the Outer Rim Territories. Surrounded by a debris ring from many wrecked starships, the planet had an atmosphere toxic to life, and no natural life resided on the planet.

properties.name: Ukatis
properties.description: Ukatis was the ruling planet of the Ukatis system of the Inner Rim.

properties.name: Ukio
properties.description: Ukio was a well-known agriworld in the Ukio system of the Abrion sector and the homeworld of the Ukians. It served as one of the top producers of foodstuffs for the Core Worlds.

properties.name: Ulda Frav
properties.description: Ulda Frav was a tropical Expansion Region planet located in the Hangshan sector. Located in widely explored space by 5000 BBY, by 3998 BBY the world was visited by both a group of Jedi who arbitrated a treaty there and the Nazzar Crown Prince Qrrrl Toq. On the planet, the Jedi informed Toq of his potential for becoming a Jedi, which he eventually did. Millennia later, Vlaydm Churhee served as a sharpshooter on Ulda Frav before forming the Churhee's Riflemen mercenary unit.

properties.name: Ulicia
properties.description: Ulicia was an industrial planet located in the Ulicia system of the Outer Rim Territories' Corporate Sector, which was governed by the Corporate Sector Authority. It was positioned along the hyperlane known as the Shaltin Tunnels. In 0 ABY, the CSA executive Hart-and-Parn Gorra-Fiolla recovered a prisoner named Naven Crel from the headquarters of the Commex corporation located on Ulicia.

properties.name: Ulkantha
properties.description: The Ulkantha asteroids were located in the Ulkantha system, a part of the Tharin sector in the Slice portion of the Outer Rim Territories. At some point between 0 ABY and 3 ABY, the Galactic Empire carried out a raid in the Ulkantha asteroids. As a result, the Empire's Star Destroyer fleet known as the Death Squadron learned about an extensive Sakiyan smuggling ring based at the Syvris shadowport in the Al'Nasrl sector's Syvris system. The Death Squadron subsequently carried out a devastating attack on the shadowport.

properties.name: Ulmatra
properties.description: Ulmatra was a minor trade world that was located within the Ulmatra system of the galaxy's Hutt Space region. It lay at the intersection of the Pabol Sleheyron and The Dead Road hyperlanes. The former connected Ulmatra to the planets Sleheyron and Randa, while the latter linked the planet to the worlds of Kafane and Zisia. Ulmatra was home to the creature known as the Ulmatran condor, and the planet lay within the sphere of influence of the Kajidier kajidic, a clan of the Hutt species.

properties.name: Ultaar
properties.description: Ultaar was a planet in the Mid Rim Bortele sector, covered in jungles of towering giant blossoms that covered the world with a thick scent. Ultaar was home to the four-armed sentient species known as the Ultaarian Greenback. During the Galactic Civil War, Ultaar became host to a small Rebel presence, which was wiped out in 0 ABY by cyborg bounty hunter Beilert Valance.

properties.name: Umaren'k
properties.description: Umaren'k was a planet located in the Umaren'k system of the Unknown Regions.

properties.name: Umbara
properties.poi: Sith Academy, , Bunker GrekBunker UskBunker Krill
properties.description: Umbara, informally known as the Shadow World due to the rays of its sun never completely reaching its surface, was a perpetually dark planet within the reaches of the Ghost Nebula. It was home to the Umbarans, a species of pale Near-Humans. It was also the site of a large battle during the Clone Wars.

properties.name: Umgul
properties.description: Umgul was a mist-covered planet in the Mid Rim. Its capital was Umgul City. The planet's climate was humid and cool, while dense fog and deep hanging clouds were almost omnipresent. Though it was once a conquest of the Infinite Empire, the planet's natural resources were of no relevance and it was of little strategical importance. Nevertheless, the planet was famous throughout the galaxy as a center for gambling and sports attractions, most notably the Umgullian Blob Racing.

properties.name: Umthyg
properties.description: Umthyg was a planet in the Juvex sector of the Mid Rim. It was a lackluster industrial world.

properties.name: Unagin
properties.description: Unagin was a minor trade planet. It was located within the Unagin system of the Al'Nasrl sector, a part of the Slice portion of the Outer Rim Territories. The planet lay on the hyperlane called the Hollastin Run, which connected it to the worlds of Tsyk and Syvris. A smaller hyperspace route also connected Unagin to the planet Riileb. Due to Unagin's location near Hutt Space, starships that prepared to enter or leave that region frequently stopped at the planet.

properties.name: Uogo'cor
properties.description: Uogo'cor was a planet located within Trax sector, just off the Trax Tube. Its port often serviced the pirates that preyed on the Trax Tube. The name translated from the language of the native Uogo meant "home of the suffering ones".

properties.name: Upekzar
properties.poi: Circle of Visions, High Rites cave system,
properties.description: Upekzar was a small terrestrial planet counted among the Sith Worlds of the Esstran sector that was unique among the mostly barren worlds of the Stygian Caldera for its diversity of verdant biomes. The planet was most notable for the Circle of Visions, a circular ring of islands and seashore locations concentrated in the planet's southern hemisphere that hosted expansive volcanic cave systems.

properties.name: Uphrades
properties.description: Uphrades was a planet located in the Uphrades system of the Inner Rim. Originally a green and fertile agriworld during the years leading up to the Galactic War between the Galactic Republic and the reconstituted Sith Empire, Uphrades supplied the Republic capital planet of Coruscant with much of its food supplies. This earned it the nickname "Coruscant's Granary" until the Sith Lord Darth Angral targeted the agriworld during his campaign of vengeance in 3643 BBY. As part of his revenge against the Republic and the Jedi Order for the death of his son, Tarnis, Angral tested the Desolator superweapon on Uphrades and devastated its surface, killing millions and trapping the few hundred survivors on the planet by ionizing its atmosphere. Thanks to the efforts of Doctor Senessa and the crew of the Republic medical frigate Daybreaker, the survivors endured the several months it took for the ion field to dissipate, but the planet itself remained a desolate and barren world.

properties.name: Upper Brightday
properties.description: Upper Brightday was a terrestrial astronomical object located in the Upper Brightday system. It was a part of the Expansion Region's Trestis sector, being located both in the Outer Expansion Zone sub-region and the Northern Dependencies portion of that region. Upper Brightday shared its name with the Inner Rim celestial body Brightday.

properties.name: Uquine
properties.description: Uquine was a planet in the Uquine system of the Colonies.

properties.name: UR-1060
properties.description: UR-1060 was a star located within the UR-1060 system. It lay within the Outer Moddell systems area of the Moddell subsector, one of the subsectors making up the Inner Zuma Region within the Outer Rim Territories' Zuma sector.

properties.name: UR-2650
properties.description: UR-2650 was a star located within the UR-2650 system of Monsua Nebula of the Outer Rim Territories.

properties.name: UR-3741
properties.description: UR-3741 was a star located within the UR-3741 system of Monsua Nebula of the Outer Rim Territories.

properties.name: UR-8827
properties.description: UR-8827 was a star located within the UR-8827 system of Monsua Nebula of the Outer Rim Territories.

properties.name: UR-9353
properties.description: UR-9353 was a star located within the UR-9353 system of Monsua Nebula of the Outer Rim Territories.

properties.name: Urce
properties.description: Urce was a Mid Rim planet located in the Lesser Plooriod Cluster. A member of the Galactic Republic since at least the Clone Wars, during the Galactic Civil War Urce served the Galactic Empire as a regional seat of power and was the site of the palace of High Inquisitor Mox Slosin. In 12 ABY, the Imperial Remnant was victorious over the New Republic at a confrontation at Urce.

properties.name: Urdur
properties.description: Urdur was a remote planet in the Urdur system. It was located so far from its sun that it was perpetually frozen. It was the site of an outlaw tech base run by Klaus "Doc" Vandangante after his escape from Stars' End.

properties.name: Uridia
properties.description: Uridia was one of the many lifeless moons which orbited the single gas giant in the Uridia system.

properties.name: Uriek
properties.description: Uriek was a planet located in the Ash Worlds sector of the Outer Rim Territories.

properties.name: Urkupp
properties.description: Urkupp was a planet located within the Urkupp system of the Outer Rim Territories. The homeworld of the Dashade race, Urkupp was destroyed in 3996 BBY by the creation of the Cron Drift during the Great Sith War. However the Dashade survived by having offworld colonies.

properties.name: Uru
properties.description: Uru was a planet located within the Uru system of the Outer Rim Territories, and was the homeworld of the sentient Oni species.

properties.name: Urun
properties.description: Cragmoloids were a rare sentient species of intimidating pachydermoids with massive builds. They had big, flat ears, manipulative trunks and a number of tusks that could be used in combat—and that were valued by hunters. They also had less pachydermoid traits, including hands with five nailed fingers. Although prone to attacking in a rage, particularly when facing subterfuge, Cragmoloids disliked gratuitous violence and were a proud, peaceful people. Cragmoloids loved their families and tended to get depressed if separated from them.

properties.name: Usean
properties.description: Usean II was an Outer Rim Territories world located in the Tunka sector. It was home to the rocket grass plant and the herbivore lrashtash, which had large incisor-like teeth to frighten predators. At some point, when the Imperial Wilek Nereus was stationed on Usean II, he added a set of lrashtash teeth to his dental collection. Later, when Nereus was asked about the origin of the teeth, he claimed they were from an "Useani camnzin," a predator he invented for his own entertainment and that of his inquirers.

properties.name: Ushmin
properties.description: Ushmin was a small world just on the borders of the Imperial Remnant.

properties.name: Usk
properties.description: The letter  was the twenty-first letter of the Aurebesh alphabet. It was pronounced "usk", and had the value of /U/.

properties.name: Usnia
properties.description: Usnia was a forested planet, located in the Usnia system of the Senex sector. It was made into a nature reserve by House Petro.

properties.name: Usta
properties.description: Usta was a mining world located on the Feena Run in the Gordian Reach sector. It was run as a joint venture between the Ardans of the Arda system and the T'sarki of Kalishik. Energy mining on Usta left the world cratered, and rendered it poisonous.

properties.name: Ut
properties.description: Ut was a planet located in the Ut system of the Hapes Cluster. It provided a song to Leia Organa Solo when the Hapes Consortium sent a diplomatic envoy to Coruscant in 8 ABY.

properties.name: Utapau
properties.poi: Grottoes of CoranthImperial storehouses, Promenade of Seven Guilds, Pahum Cultural Center,
properties.description: Utapau  was an arid sinkhole world in the Utapau system of the Tarabba sector in the Outer Rim Territories. Utapau was the homeworld of the Pau'ans and the Utai, more commonly referred to collectively as Utapauns. These species lived in the many giant sinkholes that dotted the planet's scrub-covered surface.

properties.name: Utaruun
properties.description: Utaruun was a terrestrial planet located in the Utaruun system, a part of the Arkanis sector in the Slice portion of the Outer Rim Territories. Utaruun was located on the Old Corellian Run hyperlane between the Austan and Tatoo systems.

properties.name: Utegetu Nebula
properties.description: The Utegetu Nebula was a shell nebula created by a supernova located within the Wild Space, between Reecee and Adumar, and Chiss space and the Rago Run.

properties.name: Utharis
properties.description: Utharis was a planet located within the Utharis system of the Core Worlds.

properties.name: Uthtara
properties.description: Uthtara was a Mid Rim astronomical object located in the Eucer sector. During the Tionese War, it was the site of a Galactic Republic hyperspace jump-beacon that facilitated commercial interstellar travel to the celestial body Okator VIII. At some point during the conflict, warships affiliated with the Republic's enemy, the Honorable Union of Desevro & Tion, attacked Uthtara, damaging the jump-beacon.

properties.name: Utor
properties.description: Utor could refer to one of the following:

properties.name: Utozz Prime
properties.description: The Utozz Prime system was located in the Tarabba sector of the Outer Rim Territories. It shared its name with Utozz Prime Brewery, a corporation that manufactured Utozz, a brand of the beverage known as Utoz.

properties.name: Utrost
properties.description: Utrost was a cosmopolitan planet located a few light-years from Coruscant within the Utrost system of the Core Worlds. It was Pash Galae's homeworld.

properties.name: Uukaablis
properties.description: Uukaablis was the fourth planet of the Uukaablis system, and home to the Uukaablians.

properties.name: Uvadala
properties.description: Uvadala was an astronomical object located in the Uvadala system, a part of the Ividal sector in the Slice portion of the Mid Rim. At some point during the Clone Wars, Uvadala was the site of a military operation which saw the participation of several starfighter squadrons of the Galactic Republic.

properties.name: Uvena
properties.description: Uvena was the primary star of the Uvena system.

properties.name: Uviuy Exen
properties.description: Uviuy Exen was a heavily populated planet in the Colonies' Shwuy sector. It lay at the intersection of the Hydian Way and Shwuy Exchange hyperlanes, which led various starships traveling along those routes to pass through the Uviuy Exen system.

properties.name: Uyter
properties.description: Uyter was a planet located within the Uyter system of the Mid Rim. It was an agriworld with an independent-minded people.

properties.name: V'shar
properties.poi: A cavern, Ni'Shaw-Dak Ministry headquarters, University of Timb,
properties.description: V'shar was a Wild Space planet that was the homeworld of the sentient Ka'hren species. A tradition-bound, religious, and isolationist people, the Ka'hren had a system of government in which their many organized faiths had a direct influence. Centuries before 2 ABY, V'shar was home to the Unfyr warrior culture, which was known for its use of the rantok sword.

properties.name: Va'art
properties.description: Va'art was a planet located within the Va'art system of the Mid Rim. It was orbited by a jungle moon known as the Jungle moon of Va'art.

properties.name: Vaal
properties.description: Vaal was a warm, grassy planet in the Gordian Reach in the Outer Rim Territories. The planet was dominated by large savannas and was home to several ferocious predators.

properties.name: Vaathkree
properties.description: Vaathkree was an astronomical object located in the regions known as the Outer Rim Territories and the Slice. It was also situated in the grid square S-8 of the Standard Galactic Grid. A hyperspace route linked Vaathkree to the celestial body Boonta and the planet Klatooine.

properties.name: Vaced
properties.description: Vaced was a planet located within the Vaced system of the Mid Rim beyond Bilbringi.

properties.name: Vactooine
properties.description: Vactooine was a mining colony in the Arkanis sector of the Outer Rim Territories. Its dense jungles made it a suitable habitat for the Elix.

properties.name: Vaenrood
properties.description: Vaenrood was a planet in the Vaenrood system, which was located in the Pakuuni sector of the Outer Rim Territories. Several months before the liberation of Kal'Shebbol, capital of the Kathol sector, the New Republic fought the Galactic Empire on Vaenrood.

properties.name: Vagar Praxut
properties.description: Vagar Praxut was a planet located within the Vagar Praxut system. It lay in the Kharmort's Miasma nebula, a part of the galaxy's Unknown Regions. Vagar Praxut was the homeworld of the sentient Vagaari species.

properties.name: Vagneria
properties.description: The Vagneria system was a Core Worlds star system. It was the origin point of the meal known as the Vagnerian canapé.

properties.name: Vagran
properties.poi: Estainia Hunting GroundsEstainia Resort IslandsVagran Zoological Preservation Habitat
properties.description: Vagran was a planet located in the Corellian sector with different temperate zones all varying in temperature and precipitation. Its climates and its favorable sunlight enabled Vagran to support a great deal of life.

properties.name: Vahaba
properties.description: Vahaba was the primary star of the Vahaba system, orbited by the Vahaba asteroid belt. The ores found in the belt formed the backbone of the system's economy.

properties.name: Vakkar
properties.description: Vakkar was a planet located within the Vakkar system of the Colonies.

properties.name: Vaklin
properties.poi: Howling Ruins, Northward Park, Imperial Education Center, Temple of Imperfect Repose,
properties.description: Vaklin was a planet located in the Vaklin system of the Inner Rim Territories and the homeworld of Shula Shevu. A world deeply-seated in pro-Jedi tradition, the planet was initially resistant to anti-Jedi propaganda by the Galactic Empire, but eventually succumbed to pressures from Darth Vader.

properties.name: Valahari
properties.description: Valahari was an Outer Rim planet that claimed neutrality in the Clone Wars, but gave newer and advanced ships to the Confederacy of Independent Systems that gave the CIS an advantage over the Galactic Republic.

properties.name: Valc
properties.description: Valc was an astronomical object located in Wild Space.

properties.name: Vale
properties.description: Vale was a planet located in the Atravis sector of the Outer Rim.

properties.name: Valera
properties.description: Valera was an astronomical object located in the Valera system, a part of the Southern Core portion of the Colonies. At some point between 19 BBY and 3 ABY, an uprising against the Galactic Empire took place on Valera. Although the insurrection was quelled by the Imperial Star Destroyer Stalker under the command of Captain Akal Zed, the Imperial forces lost several support vessels during the fighting due to flawed planning on Zed's part.

properties.name: Valgauth
properties.description: Valgauth was one of three planets in the Valgauth system of the Expansion Region, and the only one to support any life. It was covered in barren wastelands and junk fields.

properties.name: Validusia
properties.description: A planet was the planet that Naval Station Validusia, a Naval refitting station owned by the Galactic Empire, was orbiting. It had a bluish atmosphere, and was located in the Validusia system, which was itself located in the Bes Ber Bikade sector.

properties.name: Vallusk Cluster
properties.description: The Vallusk Cluster was a cluster of protostars near the Roil in the Gordian Reach sector of the Outer Rim Territories. It lacked habitable planets.

properties.name: Valnoos
properties.description: Valnoos was a world in the Chiloon Rift. In 45 ABY, it was home to several casinos which were attended by miners in the rift, including Tharston Kharl. The most notable of the casinos on Valnoos was the Blue Star, which was the site of an assassination attempt on the lives of Han Solo and Luke Skywalker by the Columi brothers, Craitheus and Marvid Qreph.

properties.name: Valorsi
properties.description: Valorsi was a planet located within the Valorsi system of the Juvex sector in the Mid Rim. Its native inhabitants, who came from many species, were known as Valorsians. Spacers told rumors of the pleasure world, which was said to have something to please even the most depraved lusts. The world's harems, where beings of both sexes and of innumerable species were kept and carefully bred for their beauty, were whispered about in taverns across the galaxy. Valorsian harems were rumored to be carefully guarded. Only high-ranking nobles from the Senex and Juvex houses and their attendants could travel to the world.

properties.name: Valrar
properties.description: Valrar was a planet located within the Valrar system of the Mid Rim. Its dense canopy forests blocked most sunlight from reaching the planet's surface. Khabarakh was reassigned here by Thrawn after his failure to capture Leia Organa Solo on Kashyyyk.

properties.name: Valtha Divide
properties.description: The Valtha Divide was a distant space location where a living Teezl was found and captured by the Galactic Empire. Admiral Mils Giel later used the Praetor Mark II-class battlecruiser Helmsman to transport it to Coruscant.

properties.name: Vanahame
properties.description: Vanahame was a moon in the Grumani sector in the Outer Rim Territories. During the Republic Dark Age, Vanahame was part of the Odionate, a Sith rump state ruled by the Sith Lord Odion. The moon also housed a Cloister, a large planet-sized orphanage where children throughout the Odionate were indoctrinated into slaves and warriors for Odion's war effort. There were twelve such other facilities scattered throughout the Odionate. The moon had no atmosphere, but consisted of a large spaceport which housed the Cloister underneath.

properties.name: Vanan
properties.description: Vanan was a terrestrial astronomical object located in the Atravis sector's Vanan system in the Western Reaches portion of the Outer Rim Territories. In 4 ABY, when members of the slaver group known as the Herdessan Guild working for the Dark Adept Lumiya captured a miscreant, Finn, one of them suggested selling the offender as a slave to work in the lava mines on Vanan.

properties.name: Vandelhelm
properties.description: Vandelhelm was a planet located in the Vandelhelm system, inside of the Vandelhelm Cloud within the Expansion Region. It was known for its starshipwrights, and manufacturing capabilities.

properties.name: Vandos
properties.description: Vandos was a planet located in the Vandos system of the Outer Rim Territories. It was controlled by the Separatists during the Clone Wars.

properties.name: Vandron
properties.description: Vandron may refer to one of the following:

properties.name: Vandyne
properties.description: Vandyne was an industrialized planet located within the Vandyne system of the Outer Rim Territories. As Vandyne was within the region of the Ciutric Hegemony and was located in the same "corridor" of space as Axxila, it was a target for the space pirates known as Kavil's Corsairs. During the Clone Wars, the Ciutric Hegemony joined the Confederacy of Independent Systems, and so the planet became a member of the Separatist Alliance.

properties.name: Vanik
properties.description: Vanik was a world located within the Vanik system of the Inner Rim.

properties.name: Vanjervalis
properties.description: The Vanjervalis system was located in the Slice portion of the Colonies. It shared its name with the computer conglomerate Vanjervalis Systems as well as the starship manufacturer Rendili/Vanjervalis Drive Yards, the latter of which was based at the Core Worlds planet Corellia.

properties.name: Vannix
properties.description: Vannix was a planet located within the Vankalay system of the Core Worlds, in a sector bordering the Kuat sector. It was represented in the New Republic Senate by Addath Gadan until she advocated appeasing the Yuuzhan Vong during the Yuuzhan Vong War.

properties.name: Vanqor
properties.description: Vanqor was the largest planet in the Uziel system. It was located about 6 parsecs away from Florrum.

properties.name: Vanquo
properties.description: Vanquo was a mining world in the Outer Rim's Meerian sector that became the site of one of the early battles of the Mandalorian Wars. A mountainous planet, Vanquo was a resource world for the nearby ecumenopolis of Taris and a haven for refugees from the early conquests of the Mandalorian armies. When Taris was threatened by the Mandalorians, Vanquo became part of a Republic security cordon known as the Jebble-Vanquo-Tarnith line. In 3964 BBY, Vanquo was attacked by the Mandalorians in force, commanded by Mandalore the Ultimate and his lieutenant, Cassus Fett. After a heated space battle with Republic Navy forces led by Captain Saul Karath, the Mandalorians conquered Vanquo, giving them a stronghold that they did not relinquish during the war.

properties.name: Varadan
properties.description: Varadan was a desert mining world located in the Senex sector of the Mid Rim.

properties.name: Varic
properties.description: Varic was a terrestrial celestial body situated in the Varic system, a part of the Chorlian sector of the Outer Rim Territories. Its climate featured significant sand storms, which affected the skin complexion of the Trandoshan mercenary Nakaron upon his visit to the astronomical object at some point by the time of the New Republic's existence. The effect of the Varic sand storms on Nakaron was eventually noted by the New Republic General Airen Cracken in an entry of the datafile Wanted by Cracken—the initial version of which was published in 7 ABY—dedicated to the Trandoshan.

properties.name: Varl
properties.description: Varl was the original homeworld of the Hutts, t'landa Til, and possibly the Rybets. According to Hutt legend, it was devastated in a cataclysm that vaporized its atmosphere and obliterated its moons, as well as all other planets in its star system. The planet was located in the Ardos system, in the Hutt Space oversector. It was the original capital of the Hutt Empire, from the empire's formation in 25,200 BBY, to the planet's destruction in 15,000 BBY, where the Hutts relocated to Nal Hutta, as the sector and empire's new capital.

properties.name: Varlinaar
properties.description: Varlinaar was a planet located within the Varlinaar system of the Outer Rim Territories. Rorworr once smuggled a team of Rebels into the Imperial base on the planet under the pretense of bringing the Imperials rare foods.

properties.name: Varn
properties.description: Varn was a water planet in the Quelii sector of the Outer Rim Territories.

properties.name: Varonat
properties.description: Varonat was a planet located in the Anoat sector of the Outer Rim Territories, situated along the Ison Corridor. It was a steaming jungle and adopted home of the Morodin species.

properties.name: Varristad
properties.description: Varristad was a small mining planet located in the Varristad system within the Abrion sector of the Outer Rim Territories.

properties.name: Vartos
properties.description: Vartos was a planet, located in the Tharin sector of the Outer Rim Territories, which was orbited by at least two moons.

properties.name: Varvrona
properties.description: The Varvrona system was located in the Obtrexta sector, a part of the New Territories portion of the Outer Rim Territories. It was connected via hyperlanes to the Dolis and Jaemus systems.

properties.name: Varvva
properties.description: The Varvva system was a star system located in the Barsa sector of the galaxy's Mid Rim and New Territories that was home to the sentient Varvvan species. A hyperlane connected the system to the Bars Barka and Iridonia systems, and it fell within the borders of the New Republic in 12 ABY.

properties.name: Vasar
properties.description: The Vasar system was a star system located within the Corellian sector of the Core Worlds region.

properties.name: Vasch
properties.description: Vasch was a planet located within the Vasch system of the Outer Rim Territories. An agriworld of lush green, rolling hills, it was the source of Vaschean rye, and was possibly the homeworld of Sam Heggs.

properties.name: Vasha
properties.description: Vasha was a desert planet located in the Outer Rim Territories' Moddell sector. It was the homeworld of the insectoid Vashan species, which governed itself through a system theocratic castes and members of which were prized as workers across the Moddell sector. After it experienced a series of religious wars that ended when contact was established with the Galactic Republic, Vasha came to be dominated by the Ayrou species from the planet Maya Kovel, with Ayrou administrators overseeing deep-delving mines from which Vashan miners retrieved valuable ores and minerals.

properties.name: Vassek
properties.description: Vassek was a planet in the Vassek system of the Outer Rim Territories. The planet was located within Separatist space during the Clone Wars. As a matter of fact, General Grievous maintained a castle on its third moon.

properties.name: Vasuuli
properties.description: Vasuuli may refer to one of the following:

properties.name: Vatleria
properties.description: Vatleria was a foggy planet located within the Vatleria system of the Outer Rim Territories.

properties.name: Vaykaaris
properties.description: Vaykaaris may refer to one of the following:

properties.name: Vaynai
properties.poi: Boiling SeaDistant PeaksShrines of KoorooVaynai spaceport
properties.description: Vaynai was a resort planet located within the Vaynai system of the Outer Rim Territories on the Perlemian Trade Route.

properties.name: Veccacopia
properties.description: Veccacopia was an astronomical object located within the Veccacopia system, a part of the Outer Rim Territories' Tunka sector. It was the homeworld of the sentient Cacop species.

properties.name: Vectinia
properties.description: The Vectinia system was located in the Hewett sector, a part of the New Territories portion of the Mid Rim. It was linked via hyperlanes to the Hewett system as well as the Tartaglia system in the Hollan sector.

properties.name: Veil Nebula
properties.description: The Veil Nebula was a nebula in the Outer Rim Territories. It was inhabited by giant neebray, and no hyperroutes ran through it. During the Clone Wars, Tofen Vane kept the secret headquarters of his squadron, Harko Station, within it.

properties.name: Velabri
properties.description: Velabri was a planet located within the Velabri system of the Outer Rim Territories. It was conquered by the Galactic Empire.

properties.name: Velanaria
properties.description: Velanaria was a planet located within the Velanaria system of the Outer Rim Territories.

properties.name: Velex
properties.description: Velex City was a city. Expeditor Minas Derel had a contact in Velex City that would transport Beyla Rus to the Seswenna sector if Moxin Tark was interested in taking the bounty on him.

properties.name: Velga
properties.description: Velga was a planet located within the Velga system of the Mid Rim and orbited by the moon Velga Prime.

properties.name: Vellas Pavo
properties.description: Vellas Pavo was a planet that was located in the Grumani sector, in the Outer Rim Territories. Before and during the Republic Dark Age the world was a known source of gadolinium.

properties.name: Vellity
properties.description: Vellity was a planet in the Trax sector's Vellity system, located in the Mid Rim. An agrarian world, it was the homeworld of the Near-Human Borneck.

properties.name: Velmor
properties.poi: Tol Velmoc mountains, Great Forest of Lorac,
properties.description: Velmor was the third, terrestrial planet in the Velm system in the Mid Rim near Myrkr, Obroa-skai and Aquaris.

properties.name: Velusia
properties.description: Velusia was a planet in the Velus system of the Core Worlds. Largely oceanic, it supported a wide variety of life. Rocky, volcanic islands near the equator supported a population including the Aquar, a native Near-Human species.

properties.name: Velx-Shel
properties.description: Velx-Shel was a planet located within the Corellian sector of the Core Worlds.

properties.name: Vena
properties.description: Vena was a planet located within the Vena system of the Expansion Region and ruled by Baroness Omnino.

properties.name: Venaari
properties.poi: Binary Bar, Docking Bay 18Herak SquareSouthern ReachVen-Kavi Starport
properties.description: Venaari was a Mid Rim world, and the third planet in the Vellakiya system. It was the headquarters of Venaari Enterprises. The Galactic Empire increased its presence on the planet following the Battle of Endor due to Project Orrad, which was exposed by Shandria L'hnnar. The heightened Imperial security made it difficult for the New Republic to gain a foothold on Venaari.

properties.name: Vendara
properties.description: Vendara was a planet located within the Vendara system in the Kwymar sector of the Outer Rim region of the galaxy. It was home to the Vendaran species and the predatory mollusks called skeeg.

properties.name: Vendaxa
properties.description: Vendaxa was a planet located within the Vendaxa system of the Expansion Region.

properties.name: Venestria
properties.description: Venestria was an astronomical object located in the Venestria system, a part of the Clacis sector in the New Territories portion of the Outer Rim Territories. It lay on the Braxant Run hyperlane between the Muunilinst and Kwevron systems, and another hyperspace route linked it to the Cezith system.

properties.name: Vengler
properties.description: Vengler was a planet located within the Vengler system in Wild Space. Imperial scouts discovered it a few years before 7 ABY. It had a very primitive spaceport in which there was Varno Market, the principal point of interest of the planet. The inhabitants were mostly farmers and had a life of subsistence. Otherwise, the planet was seemingly not highly regarded. Vengler was also the home of the Scitrok Warriors.

properties.name: Venir
properties.description: Venir was a planet located in the Kuat sector of the Core Worlds.

properties.name: Venjagga
properties.description: The Venjagga system was a star system located within the Colonies that contained the planets Jagga II and Jagga VII.

properties.name: Vento
properties.description: The Vento system was a star system that was located within the Core Worlds region of the galaxy. The system contained the Vento system shipyards.

properties.name: Ventooine
properties.description: Ventooine was a planet located within the Ventooine system of the Outer Rim Territories. It was ruled by the Satabs until their line was ended by Han Solo and the local Tieress, Chrysalla. The planet exported sansanna spice, crystals, and a mineral named Shadeshine.

properties.name: Ventruun
properties.description: Ventruun was a Grumani world in the Grumani sector that was located on the Hydian Way and was noted for canny merchants and frenzied deal-making.

properties.name: Ventrux
properties.description: Ventrux was a planet located within the Ventrux system within the Thesme sector of the Outer Rim Territories. It was the homeworld of Jenna Zan Arbor and original headquarters of Arbor Industries, although the laboratories were closed down when Jenna relocated to Simpla-12.

properties.name: Verdanth
properties.description: Verdanth was a rainforest planet in the Verdanth system. It was located on a strategic position on the Duros Space Run and the Sanrafsix Corridor and near the intersection of the Grumani, Sanbra, and Bon'nyuw-Luq sectors. Verdanth's indigenous species included rimebats. During the New Sith Wars, the planet was frequently fought over by Sith Lords, while, during the Galactic Civil War, Darth Vader tried and failed to capture Luke Skywalker on the world.

properties.name: Verdi
properties.description: The Verdi system was a star system located within the Rayter sector of the Outer Rim Territories.

properties.name: Vergill
properties.description: Vergill was a planet located within the Vergill system of the Inner Rim. It was an influential member of the Hapes Consortium. In 25 ABY, the planet's archon was Beed Thane.

properties.name: Verig
properties.description: Verig was a primitive planet home to a group of native nomadic hunters. During the Galactic Civil War, Rebel Alliance tactician Beryl Chiffonage traveled to Verig and drew inspiration from the planet's nomads, who used a bola-like weapon to trip the large Pryss-creatures, to develop a similar maneuver for use against Imperial All Terrain Armored Transport walkers.

properties.name: Verisin
properties.description: Verisin was a world located within the star system of the same name, a part of the Outer Rim Territories' Bajic sector. Around the year 10 ABY, it served as the homeworld of the Tenloss Coalition, a criminal organization specializing in contract kidnapping.

properties.name: Verkuyl
properties.description: Verkuyl was a planet located within the Verkuyl system of the Outer Rim Territories where alazhi was grown.

properties.name: Vernet
properties.description: Vernet was an agriworld located within the Vernet system of the Expansion Region.

properties.name: Veroleem
properties.description: Veroleem was a planet in the Unknown Regions.

properties.name: Veron
properties.description: Veron was an agriworld located in the Veron system of the Senex sector, a part of the Senex-Juvex region in the Western Reaches portion of the Mid Rim. The Senex-Juvex Loop hyperlane linked it to the Cyimarra and Presteen systems, while the Veron Route connected it to the New Cylimba system of the D'Aelgoth sector.

properties.name: Veron Minor
properties.poi: Broken Trees IslandsHengin Ki-Tapp Wett Gon-farDistt DokGazzt So-Terr Aggul Meztim-SiBurll-ikem-Tiz-Sah
properties.description: Veron Minor, also known as simply Veron, was a planet located within the Mektrun Cluster; it was the second planet in the Veron Minor system. The native Gazaran were ruled by the ancient noble house of Araba. The planet attracted many tourists. Ferlem Kie'hintack was at one time Imperial Governor of the planet.

properties.name: Veronia
properties.description: The Veronia system was a star system located within the Oricho sector of the Outer Rim Territories.

properties.name: Vertseth
properties.description: Vertseth was the home planet of Vertseth Automata, a company that manufactured techno-service droids. Most notable of these droids was Todo 360, the personal droid of Duros bounty hunter Cad Bane.

properties.name: Vessitoar
properties.description: Vessitoar was a planet located within the Vessitoar system of the Mid Rim with a New Republic military training facility.

properties.name: Vestar
properties.description: Vestar was the Icarii homeworld located within the Vestar system of the Outer Rim Territories.

properties.name: Vestor Nebula
properties.description: The Vestor Nebula was a nebula located within the Trans-Nebular sector. It was the location of the Vestor Pulsar.

properties.name: Vestral
properties.description: Vestral was one of the many planetary haunts that Captain Ellin Lah and the crew of the Woebegone frequented.

properties.name: Vex
properties.description: Vex was an astronomical object located in the Moddell sector of the Outer Rim Territories in grid square H-16 of the Standard Galactic Grid. A hyperspace route linked it to the celestial body Vasha. Vex was depicted on a map of the Moddell sector included with the Rebel Alliance collection of non-electronic documents known as The Rebel Files.

properties.name: Vexar
properties.description: Vexar was a gas giant of the Vexar system located in the Corporate Sector of the Outer Rim Territories. It was orbited by at least three moons, including the third moon of Vexar.

properties.name: Viamarr
properties.description: Viamarr was a world within the Galactic Empire. The Leonis family once lived on this planet and during Zare Leonis's fifteenth birthday, laughed over stories of their time on this world and other worlds half-forgotten.

properties.name: Vicondor
properties.description: Vicondor was a planet located in the Vicondor system of the Mid Rim. Its inhabitants joined with the people of Junction V, Delaluna, and Bezim to build the Station 88 Spaceport. This coalition of planets chose to remain loyal to the Galactic Republic during the Clone Wars.

properties.name: Viidaav
properties.description: Viidaav was a planet located in the Bryx sector of the Mid Rim. It was inhabited by the Viidaav species.

properties.name: Vilosoria
properties.description: Vilosoria was a planet located within the Vilosoria system of the Mid Rim. It was conquered by the Galactic Empire, but the Alliance of Free Planets liberated the planet due to the heroism of Koedi Raef and Toozy. The planet had a cold and a warm season.

properties.name: Vindalia
properties.description: Vindalia was a planet located within the Vindalia system of the Colonies and the homeworld of the Vindalian species.

properties.name: Vinsoth
properties.description: Vinsoth was the home planet of the Chevin and Chev species in the Quelii sector of the Outer Rim Territories. It was a temperate planet with zones of grasslands and prairies, arctic ice, and deserts.

properties.name: Vintrus
properties.description: Vintrus was a planet that was known to host the Semi-summer festival.

properties.name: Viraanntesse
properties.description: Viraanntesses were ten-legged crustacean-like aliens from the Viraanntesse system. Jedi Master Jmmaar was a Viraanntesse.

properties.name: Virgillia
properties.description: Virgillia was a world located in the Virgillia system. It was orbited by a forested moon.

properties.name: Virmeude
properties.description: Virmeude was a planet in the Mayagil sector. It was the headquarters of Issham Mining Corporation, which was actually a cover for a Rebel Alliance base.

properties.name: Virujansi
properties.description: Virujansi was a planet in the Virujansi system of the Inner Rim. The planet's populace had a complex hierarchy.

properties.name: Vispil
properties.description: Vispil was a planet located within the Vispil system of the Outer Rim Territories. It refused warlord Zsinj's bribes and fought against him.

properties.name: Vizcarra
