properties.description: Vizcarra was a Imperial prison planet located within the Vizcarra system of the Outer Rim Territories. It was where smuggler Tait Ransom was scheduled to be sent after he was arrested for weapons smuggling on Omman.

properties.name: Vjun
properties.poi: Bast Castle, Bay of TearsChâteau Malreaux, River Weeping
properties.description: Vjun  was a dark, almost lifeless planet in the Vjun system, known for its acidic rainfalls and resultant lack of plant life. It was also renowned for its expensive hand-woven tunics. It was the location of Bast Castle, a fortress used by Count Dooku, and later a place where Darth Vader studied the dark side of the Force.

properties.name: Vlemoth Port
properties.poi: Vlemoth Station, Smoker spires, Talz villages,
properties.description: Vlemoth Port was a planet located within the Instrop sector of the Outer Rim Territories. An uninhabited world once known only as P1S15IS0079, Vlemoth Port was purchased from the Galactic Republic by Vlem Hill, and developed by the Muuns into an industrial center. Scattered tribes of displaced Talz could also be found on Vlemoth Port, in addition to an enclave of Mandalorian immigrants centered around the settlement of Arumorut.

properties.name: Vo Tunbren
properties.description: Vo Tunbren was a planet in the Tadra sector a subsector of the Cegul sector in the Outer Rim Territories. It was the location of an Imperial communications research facility where Jeres Moridon was stationed.

properties.name: Vob
properties.description: Vob was a gas giant planet located within the Vob system of the Inner Rim Territories that was famous for its atmospheric storms.

properties.name: Vodran
properties.description: Vodran was a murky, humid planet in the Si'Klaata Cluster, on the Ac'fren Spur of Hutt Space. Its surface featured jungles and swamps, and was home to the reptilian Vodran. It was also the original planet where the garbage-eating dianoga evolved, a pest that eventually spread throughout the galaxy.

properties.name: Vohai
properties.description: Vohai was a planet located within the Vohai system of the Outer Rim Territories, covered with industrial sites, that were interspersed with residential towers and parkland. The Vohai Unirail encircled the entire planet from pole to pole, two kilometers above the planet's surface. The Arkanian company Arkanian Microtechnologies's headquarters were on Vohai.

properties.name: Void of Aogros
properties.description: The Void of Aogros was an expansive region of space located within Wild Space beyond the Outer Rim Territories' Tunka sector. The region did not contain any star systems with the exception of the Quintarad, a system of five stars orbiting each other. The Quintarad was believed to have been constructed by members of the sentient Celestial species, who had disappeared from the galaxy by 30,000 BBY.

properties.name: Void Station
properties.description: Void Station was a palace-like space station built on an asteroid, located near an unidentified planet.

properties.name: Voidfire Nebula
properties.description: The Voidfire Nebula was an ionized nebula in the Expansion Region that stretched across a vast region of space, covering as much space as a medium-sized star system. It was located at the junction of the Hydian Way and two other hyperlanes , as well as being near Crystal Web Station. The Lucents claimed that their homeworld was located somewhere in the nebula, which could account for their peculiar crystalline technology.

properties.name: Voktunma
properties.description: Voktunma was a planet in the Voktunma system of the Core Worlds.

properties.name: Volgax
properties.description: Volgax was a planet located within the Volgax system of the Core Worlds.

properties.name: Volik
properties.poi: Akriva Falls, Jolee Falls, Mount Vorena, Wavelength Gale's hidden cove,
properties.description: Volik was a temperate planet with rocky terrain that was located within the Unknown Regions' Volik system. The planet's surface was dominated by expansive grasslands and small mountain ranges, as well as numerous canyons and waterfalls. Volik's plant life included the bannak and tanna trees and the mumau root, while the reyko was the most frequently encountered example of the planet's fauna.

properties.name: Voltare
properties.description: Voltare was a spaceport planet in the Voltare system of the Inner Rim.

properties.name: Von-Alai
properties.description: Von-Alai was a planet in the Von-Alai system of the Expansion Region, polluted by Kontag factories.

properties.name: Vonak
properties.description: Vonak was a planet home to the Cilare species which subscribed to martial values and savored combat around 25 ABY. It had wide open grassy plains and was home to canine and a reptillian species which were hunted by the warriors.

properties.name: Vondarc
properties.description: Vondarc was a planet located within the Vondarc system of the Mid Rim, that served as one of the endpoints of the Enarc Run hyperroute.

properties.name: Voniss
properties.description: Voniss was an astronomical object located in the Voniss system, a part of the freestanding subsectors portion of the Mid Rim. The meteorological phenomena of the celestial body included dust storms.

properties.name: Vontor
properties.description: Vontor was a planet located in the Si'Klaata Cluster within the boundaries of Hutt Space. Vontor was a huge source of kiirium.

properties.name: Voon
properties.description: Voon was a Core Worlds planet. A part of the Krenher sector, it was situated on the Hyabb-Twith Corridor hyperlane, a zone long embroiled in conflict between the worlds Hyabb and Twith. Decades before 4050 BBY, the Nelori Marauders established their main base on Voon. The planet's location in the contested area allowed the Nelori to carry out raids against starships and worlds both along the Corridor and in the nearby star systems without any fear of pursuit or reprisal.

properties.name: Voorlach
properties.description: Voorlach was a planet located within the Voorlach system of the Colonies with a Klatooinian Trade Guild presence. It was here that Platt Okeefe became impressed with the workings of the Trade Guild and resolved to join them in order to earn her first freighter.

properties.name: Voorsbain
properties.description: Voorsbain was a planet located within the Voorsbain system of Senex sector of the Mid Rim. It was an industrial world where House Picutorion-funded research into advanced technology was conducted.

properties.name: Vor Deo
properties.description: Vor Deo was a terrestrial planet located in the Vor Deo system, a part of the Arkanis sector in the Slice portion of the Outer Rim Territories. Vor Deo was located on the Old Corellian Run hyperlane and on the tip of the Cranan-Excarga Route.

properties.name: Vornax
properties.description: Vornax was a barren planet located within the Vornax system of the Outer Rim Territories. The planet itself was covered in abandoned droid factories and piles of rusted scrap and garbage. The factories had been left disused for centuries. The only beings who ever visited the abandoned world were those attempting to escape law, or bounty hunters looking to collect a bounty.

properties.name: Vorpa'ya
properties.description: Vorpa'ya was an agriworld in the Outer Rim Territories of the galaxy, located within the Mandalore sector's Vorpa'ya system, not far from the neighboring world of Concord Dawn. A terrestrial planet with a breathable atmosphere, Vorpa'ya was conquered by the Mandalorians, and became part of Mandalorian space.

properties.name: Vorrnti
properties.description: Vorrnti was a planet located in the Vorrnti system in the Inner Rim contained Vorrnti City.

properties.name: Vorsia
properties.description: The Vorsia system was a star system that was located within the galactic regions known as the Inner Rim and the Slice. The system was the origin point of the Vorsian crystal.

properties.name: Vortex
properties.description: Vortex was a Mid Rim planet in the Glythe sector. The planet was the homeworld of the Vors, a race with wings, but no emotion.

properties.name: Vorusku
properties.poi: Hyperdrive Cantina, Jalla Spree's headquarters, Slaver camp,
properties.description: Vorusku was a waterworld located within the Outer Rim Territories' Juris sector. It was the site of a volcano city as well as a floating bar named the Hyperdrive Cantina. The Kaminoan Jedi Kina Ha once lived on Vorusku. While there, she had a vision of the future in which the cloners of the planet Kamino would create an army for the dark side of the Force.

properties.name: Vorzyd
properties.description: Vorzyd was the primary of the Vorzyd system. It was orbited by five planets.

properties.name: Voss
properties.poi: Gormak Lands, Nightmare Lands, Old Paths, Pelath-Ri Marches,
properties.description: Voss was a terrestrial planet in the Voss system located in Allied Tion sector of the Outer Rim Territories. Originally only having one native sentient species known as Gormak, the planet was discovered by the ancient Sith who used Voss for its resources, until the Jedi arrived to drive them off. Seeking allies among the natives, the Jedi taught some of the Gormak tribes on how to use the Force, but the Gormak were unprepared and those tribes radically evolved into a different looking species named the Voss. The Sith were exterminated, while the Jedi left or died out, and the Voss settled on the mountain peak, establishing the city of Voss-Ka. The Voss society turned to Force-sensitives for guidance, as Voss Mystics received Force visions that proved true without exception, Interpreters made sure each vision's meaning was understood correctly, and the Three governed the entire Voss people. Nomadic Gormak came to view the Voss as abominations and became exceptionally hostile to them, attempting to purge them from the world. In return, all Voss spend time serving as Voss commandos, ensuring their survival against millions of Gormak, while the Mystics developed healing rituals to heal grave wounds.

properties.name: Vosteltig
properties.description: The Vosteltig ship yards were a ship-building facility located in the Vosteltig system, a part of the Oplovis sector in the New Territories portion of the Outer Rim Territories. In 7 ABY, the Galactic Empire maintained a high level of security at the shipyards, where the Sluissi engineer Ten Dorne, who had deserted from the Rebel Alliance years prior, was stationed.

properties.name: Vrakolia
properties.description: The Vrakolia system was located in the Southern Core portion of the Core Worlds. It was home to the sentient Vrakolian species.

properties.name: Vryssa
properties.description: Vryssa was a planet located within the Vryssa system of the Outer Rim Territories that hosted an Imperial garrison base. Buldobeasts were commonly found on this planet. At some point in 1 ABY, the entire garrison was wiped out by Boba Fett while pursuing the bounty on Rivo Xarran.

properties.name: Vuchelle
properties.description: Vuchelle was an orange-colored astronomical object located in the Outer Rim Territories' Atrivis sector. Situated along the Braxant Run hyperlane, Vuchelle in 22 BBY became the site of attempted negotiations between a Jedi-led Galactic Republic task force and the pirates of Iridium, who had been committing raids against Republic convoys. The pirates attacked the Jedi task force but were eventually defeated, with one of their starfighters believed to have reentered Vuchelle's atmosphere and burned up as a result.

properties.name: Vulcar
properties.description: Vulcar was a baleful orange, sulfurous planet located in the Vulcar system, within the Juvex sector of the galaxy's Mid Rim. A hyperlane branching off the Senex-Juvex Loop connected it to the worlds of Tinallis and Tyluun. Home to the eponymous Sulphur Pits of Vulcar, its acrid atmosphere made employing humanoid workers to extract the world's oridium deposits barely cost-effective. Instead, Vulcar was primarily worked by droids of all types, including crab droids, reprogrammed to serve as miners until they froze up and rusted into scrap. In 15 BBY, an Intergalactic Droid Agency shuttle traveled to the Sulphur Pits of Vulcar after delivering the droids R2-D2 and C-3PO to the planet Dodz.

properties.name: Vulcusion
properties.description: Vulcusion may refer to one of the following:

properties.name: Vulderania
properties.description: The Vulderania system was a star system located within the Core Worlds that contained the planet of Vulderania.

properties.name: Vulpter
properties.description: Vulpter was the third planet of the Vulpter system in the Deep Core, and the homeworld of the sentient Vulptereen species. Originally an unspoiled world with a wide array of flora and fauna, Vulpter was transformed over the millennia into a massively polluted globe covered in waste and factories. This meant that the planet was unable to sustain itself in terms of agriculture, and was thus entirely reliant on importing foodstuffs from other worlds. Vulpter was a noted producer of starships, and was home to one of the galaxy's largest podracer factories. Several corporations, such as Viper Sensor Intelligence Systems and Arakyd Industries, operated facilities on the planet.

properties.name: Vulta
properties.poi: Karson's ParkSilver FalconSpiral GalaxyUnidentified warehouseYinta Lake spaceport
properties.description: Vulta was a planet located within the Atreyis system of the Mid Rim. It was the homeworld of the Vultan species, as well as Greff-Timms Industrial and Oss Wilum.

properties.name: Vultar
properties.description: Vultar was the main planet of the Vultar system, brought into the system artificially by the Celestials using the Cosmic Turbine. In 4250 BBY, the planet was accidentally destroyed in the Vultar Cataclysm by Dark Jedi who activated the Cosmic Turbine.

properties.name: Vulvarch
properties.description: Vulvarch was a planet located within the Vulvarch system of the Colonies, not far from Atzerri. Luke Skywalker discovered the Star Morning docked at Vulvarch while en route to retrieve the Fallanassi from Farlax sector.

properties.name: Vuma
properties.description: Vuma was a planet located within the Vuma system of the Core Worlds.

properties.name: Vundaria
properties.description: Vundaria was a planet located within the Vundaria system of the Inner Rim Territories which exported fire lamps.

properties.name: Vun'Hanna
properties.description: Vun'Hanna was a location in space, situated within the Unknown Regions of the galaxy. At some point by 27 BBY, it was the site of an encounter between the military forces of the sentient Chiss and Yuuzhan Vong species that resulted in a battle, in which the Chiss were victorious. In the year 55 ABY, the author Lenang O'Pali mentioned the encounter at Vun'Hanna in the publication Mitth'raw'nuruodo Reconsidered: A Patriot's Perspective.

properties.name: Vurdon Ka
properties.description: Vurdon Ka was a planet located within the Vurdon Ka system of the Inner Rim. It was an idyllic world of mosses and inhabited by the peaceful Vuvrians. It was located along the Perlemian Trade Route. The planet joined the Galactic Republic by 22,000 BBY, and later went on to be a member-world of the Galactic Empire. It was conquered by the Yuuzhan Vong prior to the fall of Duro during the Yuuzhan Vong War.

properties.name: Vuzsa
properties.description: Vuzsa was an Outer Rim Territories world located in the Arkanis sector. It served as a refueling point for starships traveling along the Trans Gulf Route hyperlane. During the Galactic Civil War, the Rebel Alliance maintained a safehouse at Vuzsa, at which the Rebel agent Tiree once hid in order to evade capture by the Galactic Empire.

properties.name: Vvaw
properties.description: Vvaw was a planet located in the Vvaw system, a part of the Calaron sector in the Slice portion of the Outer Rim Territories. Jedi Master Jmmaar, a member of the Viraanntesse species that originated in the Expansion Region's Viraanntesse system, hailed from Vvaw.

properties.name: Vycinyth
properties.poi: Tapani Arts and Sports Complex, Orbital casinos,
properties.description: Vycinyth was a forested resort planet in the Barnaba Province of the Tapani sector. Its Tapani Arts and Sports Complex accommodated swoop races, shockboxing, and Cracian thumper races. The planet was orbited by four space casinos and the moon Vilhon.

properties.name: Vykos
properties.description: Vykos was a planet located within the Vykos system of the Outer Rim Territories. It was a stopping point on the Relgim Run of the luxury liner Kuari Princess, a planet of fast-flowing rivers  which attacted white-water rapid rafters and deep canyons .

properties.name: Wakeelmui
properties.description: Wakeelmui was a planet located in the Colonies.

properties.name: Wakiza
properties.description: Wakiza was a planet located within the Wakiza system of the Core Worlds. One of the original thirteen planets of the Duskhan League, it was located within the Koornacht Cluster that sat on the border of the Core Worlds and the Deep Core of the galaxy. Wakiza was orbited by the Imperial Navy shipyard Black Eight. "Sleepy" Nagelson was shot down while flying a reconnaissance mission over Wakiza for the New Republic.

properties.name: Walalla
properties.description: Walalla was a planet located within the Walalla system of the Inner Rim.

properties.name: Walin'or
properties.description: Walin'or may refer to one of the following:

properties.name: Wann Tsir
properties.description: Wann Tsir was a planet located in the Wann Tsir system, a part of the Sepan sector in the Slice portion of the Expansion Region. During the Galactic Civil War, Wann Tsir was protected by a planetary shield.

properties.name: Waskiro
properties.description: Waskiro was a mountainous world in the Jospro sector of the Outer Rim. The planet was heavily involved in trade, namely mining. At some point in history, the contact with the mining colony was lost.

properties.name: Wayland
properties.poi: Mount Tantiss, , Imperial Research Station 61, Dukha clan center,
properties.description: Wayland was a lush, semi-tropical planet in the Outer Rim Territories.

properties.name: Waymancy
properties.description: Waymancy may refer to one of the following:

properties.name: Wazta
properties.description: Wazta was a planet located within the Wazta system of the Outer Rim Territories. It was a planet where Imperial Army infantry units defected to the Alliance to Restore the Republic around 0 ABY. The situation was reported in Imperial Communique 2734.19g.

properties.name: Weerden
properties.description: Weerden was an Imperial planet located within the Weerden system of the Core Worlds, near Coruscant. It was here that an assassin droid killed Grand Inquisitor Laddinare Torbin by crashing his shuttle, Sark-I into Torbin's palace.

properties.name: Wehttam
properties.description: Wehttam was a planet located within the Wehttam system of the Core Worlds. Wehttam was the Wehttam homeworld. It was located in the Farlax sector.

properties.name: Wen'he'dinae
properties.description: Wen'he'dinae was a terrestrial planet located in the Wen'he'dinae system, a part of the Eidoloni sector in the Western Reaches portion of the Mid Rim. The planet had several seasons and was home to a multitude of carnivorous creatures.

properties.name: Werncin
properties.description: Werncin 3 was a slaving planet located within the Werncin system of the Outer Rim Territories, on the Listehol Run.

properties.name: Werta
properties.description: The Werta system was a star system located within the Mid Rim.

properties.name: Wetyin's Colony
properties.description: Wetyin's Colony was the main settlement on the moon Yavin 4 that was established when settlers traveled from the planet Setor to become farmers. In the months after the Battle of Endor, when Shara Bey and Kes Dameron settled in a new home there after completing their service in the Alliance to Restore the Republic. Having their own home had been their dream after being separated from one another, as well as their son, Poe, for much of the Galactic Civil War. Upon moving into their new home, the couple planted one of two remaining fragments of a Great Tree that had once dwelled in the heart of the Jedi Temple, after Bey and Luke Skywalker recovered them from the Galactic Empire.

properties.name: Weytta
properties.description: Weytta was a planet located within the Weytta system of the Outer Rim Territories, near Murkhana. It was the homeworld of the Jedi Master Roan Shryne and his parents, Jula and Jen.

properties.name: Whelori
properties.description: The Whelori system was located in the Southern Core portion of the Colonies. It was home to the creatures known as Whelorian snake-eaters.

properties.name: Whinndor
properties.description: Whinndor was a world that was located in the Grumani sector. It had a sulphuric atmosphere and seas that were abundant with organic molecules. During the Republic Dark Age the planet was located in a Sith-contested space, with the mercenary Rusher's Brigade once fighting on its surface. The Whinndorian gorsk-plant was a plant species native to Whinndor.

properties.name: Widek
properties.description: Widek was a planet located within the Widek system of the Core Worlds. It was also the terminus of the Widek Bypass.

properties.name: Wielu
properties.poi: Alekie Island, Alekie Island menagerie, Market Ward, Traygura's hideout, Wielu beach resort,
properties.description: Wielu was a planet in the galaxy with two suns, and was well known for its famous beaches and thriving black market. During the Clone Wars, Obi-Wan Kenobi, Anakin Skywalker and Ahsoka Tano briefly vacationed here.

properties.name: Wilpiet
properties.description: Wilpiet was a planet located within the Wilpiet system of the Outer Rim Territories near Granse Space.

properties.name: Wistril
properties.description: Wistril was a planet in the Wistril system, located in the Outer Rim Territories. It was known for its smugglers.

properties.name: Wizar
properties.description: Wizar II was a planet located within the Wizar system of the Wild Space. It was the homeworld of a species of sentient cephalopoids known as Uroths. It was a terrestrial planet, largely unknown to the outside galaxy.

properties.name: Wodan
properties.description: The Wodan system was located in the Rifle Worlds, an area of the Hapes Cluster in the Slice portion of the Inner Rim. It was connected by the hyperlane known as the Great Rim Route to the Divora and Relephon systems and by another hyperspace route linked it to the Algnadesh system. The Wodan system was home to the creatures known as Wodanian wood-sprites.

properties.name: Wodenstam
properties.description: Wodenstam was a world located within the star system of the same name, a part of the Outer Rim Territories' Skine sector. Around 10 ABY, it served as the homeworld of Lucross Collections, a loan sharking and credit laundering operation and member of the criminal Tenloss Syndicate.

properties.name: Wol Cabassh
properties.description: Wol Cabassh was a planet located within the Wol Cabassh system of the Outer Rim Territories. It was the homeworld of the Wol Cabasshite species and the plasma leech.

properties.name: Womrik
properties.description: Womrik was a planet located within the Womrik system in the Dufilvian sector of the Mid Rim, near New Cov. The sights of its ice-capped mountain peaks, which were second to none, attracted many tourists and were a source of pride the planet's inhabitants.

properties.name: Woostri
properties.description: Woostri was a planet in the Expansion Region known for its HoloScan Database, tourism, and automated manufacturing.

properties.name: Woqua
properties.description: Woqua was a planet located within the Woqua system of the Core Worlds.

properties.name: Wor Tandell
properties.description: Wor Tandell was the primary planet of the Tandell system in the Dolomar sector. Its surface was covered with an array of oceans and landmasses.

properties.name: Worru'du
properties.description: Worru'du was a planet located within the Worru'du system of the Core Worlds and known for its grass fields. The grass from Worru'du could be used for basket weaving.

properties.name: Worxer
properties.description: Worxer, also called Yablon, was a planet in the Degan Gas Clouds of Elrood sector. It was destroyed when its sun went supernova around 198 BBY. The Galactic Republic only managed to evacuate a few of the native Spiners, and by the time of the Galactic Civil War, most people believed the species extinct, a mistake not far from the truth.

properties.name: Woteba
properties.description: Woteba was a planet located in the Utegetu Nebula, in Wild Space between Reecee and Adumar.

properties.name: Wranag
properties.description: Wranag was a planet located within the Wranag system of the Outer Rim Territories.

properties.name: Wrea
properties.description: Wrea was an inhabited planet located within the Wrea system of the Outer Rim Territories near the Smuggler's Run. When Kueller's explosive droids decimated the inhabitants of the Run, the Wreans offered medical assistance. Wrea also contained a Republic outpost during the Clone Wars.

properties.name: Wroona
properties.poi: Wroona Stardock, Starship Outfitters, Palestro's Wholesale Firearms,
properties.description: Wroona was the homeworld of the near-Human Wroonians, located in the Wroona system.

properties.name: Wukkar
properties.description: Wukkar was a heavily-populated planet located within the Wukkar system of the Core Worlds. Part of Galactic Republic space since the Republic's inception, Wukkar became a part of the Galactic Empire until surrendering to the New Republic. It was later occupied by the Yuuzhan Vong species during their invasion of the galaxy.

properties.name: Wxtm
properties.description: Wxtm was a planet located in the Wxtm system of the Outer Rim Territories. One of its native creatures was an avian called a ravenscreecher, which had six legs.

properties.name: Wyloff
properties.poi: Wyloff sector Imperial Intelligence ExComm facility,
properties.description: Wyloff was a terrestrial astronomical object located in the Wyloff system, a part of the Wyloff sector in the Northern Dependencies portion of the Colonies. The capital city of Wyloff was surrounded by middle class suburbs. Wyloff was also the location of the Wyloff sector Imperial Intelligence ExComm facility.

properties.name: Wyndigal
properties.description: Wyndigal 2, originally known as Huronom, was a swampy planet located within the Wyndigal system in the Ash Worlds in the Outer Rim Territories.

properties.name: Wynth
properties.description: Wynth was an astronomical object located in the Wynth system, a part of the Wyloff sector in the Northern Dependencies portion of the Colonies. Shortly after the Battle of Yavin, the Rebel Alliance operative and Imperial defector Colonel Vin Northal was stationed at Wynth.

properties.name: Wyveral
properties.description: Wyveral was a planet located within the Wyveral system of the Mid Rim where many advances in forensic medicine were made.

properties.name: Xa Fel
properties.description: Xa Fel was a populated planet in the Kanchen sector of the Core Worlds. It was the homeworld of the Xa Fel. The planet readily supported all forms of life.

properties.name: Xagobah
properties.description: Xagobah was a planet located in the Xagobah system, just inside the border with the Outer Rim Territories, and was the homeworld of the Xamster race.

properties.name: Xal
properties.description: Xal was the Xal system's primary star, located on the Outer Rim.

properties.name: Xanas
properties.description: Xanas was a planet located within the Xanas system of the Xan sector. It had one major city called Xanas City.

properties.name: Xantar
properties.description: Xantar was a planet located within the Xantar system of the Outer Rim Territories. Located in the Corva sector, it included green forests, and was the homeworld of a gray-skinned sentient species. Luke Skywalker visited the world as the guest of a native pilot, and met another human visitor, Indiana Jones.

properties.name: Xartun
properties.description: Xartun was an Outer Rim Territories planet in the Ojoster sector that was involved in manufacturing. A New Republic world, it was near warlord Zsinj's territory. Although the planet was a signatory to the New Republic, a deal brought about by a previous planetary leader, the governor of Xartun during 7 ABY, Nojin Koolb, had it secretly allied with Warlord Zsinj.

properties.name: Xend
properties.description: Xend was a planet located within the Xend system of the Inner Rim Territories. It was a forested world that was primarily inhabited by various species of insects and the winged xendrites that preyed upon them.

properties.name: Xeron
properties.description: Xeron was a planet located within the Xeron system, a part of the Trailing Sectors portion of the Inner Rim. Xeron was the site of a battle between the Rebel Alliance and Galactic Empire during the Galactic Civil War circa 3 ABY, where the Imperial Army attacked Rebel ground troops with a new warbot to devastating effect.

properties.name: Xerxes
properties.description: Xerxes was a Core World planet located within the Xerxes system. It possessed an atmosphere compatible with Human physiology, and was once visited by the smuggler Roark Garnet, whom the local planetary police wanted.

properties.name: Xifal
properties.description: Xifal was a planetoid located in Xifal system, within the Allied Tion sector of the galaxy's Outer Rim Territories.

properties.name: Xilxash
properties.description: Xilxash was an agricultural planet that applied for and was granted Galactic Alliance membership in 44 ABY. It was a small backwater world, known for its delicious brul fruit.

properties.name: Xiunsrus
properties.description: Xiunsrus was a planet located in the Quence sector of the Outer Rim Territories. It was the site of the first known criminal act committed by the swoop gang known as the Bloodsniffers. The Bloodsniffers demanded 10,000 credits from a village of farmers and when its inhabitants refused to appease them, the gang destroyed the village.

properties.name: Xo
properties.description: Xo was a planet located within the Xo system of the Outer Rim Territories. It was the adopted Zanibar homeworld, where the inhabitants practiced ritual sacrifice. It was constantly bathed in red light and had a rocky terrain. It was home to a variety of spiked, carnivorous plants, and reptilian species.

properties.name: Xobome
properties.description: Xobome was the Xobome system's primary star. The planet Xobome 6 orbited this sun.

properties.name: Xochtl
properties.description: Xochtl was a planet in the Xochtl system of the Gordian Reach in the Outer Rim. It was a rocky world of crags and spires, and with gravity that was slightly lighter than normal. It was the homeworld of the Bagmims.

properties.name: Xoemefel
properties.description: Xoemefel was a planet in the Xoemefel system of the Mid Rim. It was the site of Ops Post, a New Republic Scout Service base.

properties.name: Xolu
properties.description: Xolu was a planet that was located within the Xolu system in Hutt Space, a region of the galaxy controlled by the Hutt species. It was connected to the worlds of Hollastin and Far Pando by the hyperlane called the Pando Spur.

properties.name: Xorth
properties.description: Xorth was a agriworld located within the Xorth system of the Core Worlds.

properties.name: XT987
properties.description: XT987 was an uninhabited moon. Ferus Olin and resistance leaders part of Moonstrike stopped here on their way to Ferus' base when it was discovered that Eve Yarrow, known as Flame, was an Imperial spy.

properties.name: Xuaquarres
properties.description: Xuaquarres was a planet located within the Xuaquarres system of the Outer Rim Territories. It was the location of both the Graveyard of the Dragons and a secret storehouse of Emperor Palpatine.

properties.name: Xxan
properties.description: Xxan was a water-covered planet that was located in the Outer Rim Territories. The underwater city Acquos was located on the world, and was connected to a small spaceport on the surface of the planet, via a turbolift.

properties.name: Xyquine
properties.poi: Capitol Park, Millennial Forum, Mount Vissa, Strangling Sea, Umber Jungles, Xyquine base
properties.description: Xyquine II was a planet located within the Xyquine system of the Corellian sector. The world boasted a diverse array of life.

properties.name: Y'nybeth
properties.description: Y'nybeth was a planet located within the Y'nybeth system of the Expansion Region. It was the homeworld of the Plasmar.

properties.name: Y'Trella
properties.description: Y'Trella was a planet located within the Y'Trella system of the Outer Rim Territories.

properties.name: Yablari
properties.description: Yablari was an agrarian planet located within the Vorzyd sector's Yablari system of the Outer Rim Territories. Located along the Perlemian Trade Route, Yablari's agricultural technology was highly advanced and prolific.

properties.name: Yabol Opa
properties.description: Yabol Opa was a Colonies planet located on the Perlemian Trade Route. A member of the Galactic Republic since at least 22,000 BBY, Yabol Opa allied itself with the planet Alsakan during its long struggle against the Republic's capital world, Coruscant. By 22 BBY, the University of Yabol Opa stretched across the entire surface of the planet, which had become a part of the Galactic Empire by five years later.

properties.name: Yabosta
properties.description: Yabosta was a planet located in the Yabosta system of the Expansion Region. It was orbited by at least two moons, the second of which was called Skalokor. Port Kalla was one of the largest cities on the planet, and its primary spaceport.

properties.name: Yag'Dhul
properties.poi: First Temple of Prime, Givin Senatorial Tesseract, Yag-prime, Yag'Dhul shipyards,
properties.description: Yag'Dhul was a small and barren planet located in the Inner Rim. It was the homeworld of the Givin.

properties.name: Yaga Minor
properties.poi: Preparation Center, Yavvitiri Spaceport, Yaga Minor shipyards, Ubiqtorate base,
properties.description: Yaga Minor was the Galactic Republic member world from which the Outbound Flight project departed into the Unknown Regions in 27 BBY. The planet's primary native species were the Yagai, insectoids with a hive-caste society. Yaga Minor was known throughout the galaxy for its major starshipbuilding facilities.

properties.name: Yaka
properties.description: The Yaka were a race of Near-Human cyborgs hailing from the Yaka system. Centuries before the rise of the Galactic Empire, the neighboring Arkanians, known for their genetic experiments, implanted the naturally dim-witted species with cybernetic implants. Some Arkanians saw this effort as beneficial to the Yaka, while other socially-conscious Arkanians questioned the ethical implications of such an act.

properties.name: Yalara
properties.description: Yalara was a primitive planet located within the Yalara system of the Wild Space.

properties.name: Yalln
properties.description: Yalln was a planet located within the Yalln system of the Outer Rim Territories. It was an industrial Imperial world inhabited by Humans  and their pet tals. Outside of the industrial complexes were vast, unsettled regions.

properties.name: Yanibar
properties.description: Yanibar was a planet in Wild Space known for its blistering, dry summers and wet, frigid winters. Barely habitable by Humans and other similar species, it was nevertheless colonized by a group of Jedi and their relatives seeking refuge from the predations of the Sith. The planet remained isolated for years, as it was forgotten by the Jedi who remained in the galaxy. At the same time, many of the colonists did not survive Yanibar's harsh conditions. Those who did survive formed their own Force tradition, Zeison Sha, which developed decidedly anti-Jedi traits.

properties.name: Yarille
properties.description: Yarille was a planet located within the Yarille system of the Outer Rim Territories.

properties.name: Yarnil
properties.description: Yarnil was a planet located within the Yarnil system of the Outer Rim Territories. It was a homeworld to farmers and merchants.

properties.name: Yaronn
properties.description: Yaronn was a Wild Space waterworld whose only significant landmass was a 200–square kilometer–large, forest-covered continent. During the Galactic Civil War, the Claw, a bounty hunter carrying a grudge against a group of smugglers, sent a message inviting them to Yaronn. There, the Claw prepared to hunt on the group, offering to cease hostilities against the smugglers if they evaded capture.

properties.name: Yarrv
properties.description: Yarrv was a tropical Core World planet of dense jungles, warm oceans and wide, sandy beaches.

properties.name: Yashuvhu
properties.description: Yashuvhu was a planet on the near fringes of the Unknown Regions. It was a lush and temperate world that featured mountains and jungles, including the Yashaka Mountains. Sometime during the Old Republic era, Human settlers had landed on the planet but lost contact with the galactic community. The descendants of the settlers, known as the Yashuvhi, also had an established Force tradition which dated to the descendants of a legendary Jedi who crashed on the planet sometime during the years of the Galactic Republic.

properties.name: Yasilor
properties.description: Yasilor was a world located within the star system of the same name, a part of the Outer Rim Territories' Bajic sector. Around the year 10 ABY, it served as the homeworld of the Palkandi Brokerage House, a front organization for the criminal Tenloss Syndicate.

properties.name: Yavin
properties.description: Yavin 4 was one of three habitable moons orbiting the gas giant Yavin. It was mainly covered in jungle and rainforest, and despite being remote and unheard of, it would play an important role in galactic events, including the seduction of Jedi Knight Exar Kun to the dark side and the destruction of Sith Lord Freedon Nadd during the Great Sith War, the site of the eventual final death of the maddened Jedi Revan in the waning days of the Galactic War, a ferocious duel between Jedi and Sith during the Clone Wars, and serving as the base of the Alliance to Restore the Republic during the Battle of Yavin and as a battlefield in other battles of the Galactic Civil War. An attack was launched on the Death Star from this moon. It also became the base for a Jedi Academy after the war ended.

properties.name: Ychthyton
properties.description: The Ychthyton system was a star system located in the Belderone sector of the galaxy's Outer Rim Territories. It was home to the sentient Ychthytonian species.

properties.name: Yde
properties.description: Yde was an astronomical object located in the Yde system, a part of the Nicandra sector in the New Territories portion of the Mid Rim.

properties.name: Yelsain
properties.description: Yelsain was a planet in the Minos Cluster.

properties.name: Yerphonia
properties.description: Yerphonia was a planet located within the Yerphonia system of the Core Worlds. It was known for its prestigious universities, such as the famous All Science Research Academy.

properties.name: Yeshocq
properties.description: Yeshocq was a planet located within the Yeshocq system of the Mid Rim. It was a colonized, forested, temperate planet with a local year that lasted 13 standard months: the local year was divided into 455 local days. Yeshocq was the homeworld qormot species.

properties.name: Yetnis
properties.description: Yetnis was a planet located within the Yetnis system of the Inner Rim Territories.

properties.name: Yetoom
properties.description: Yetoom Na Uun was a planet located within the Yetoom system of the Senex sector. Positioned at the sector's edge, Yetoom was a shadowport controlled by gangs of Senex-Juvex slave species, and was the headquarters of Fargednim P'taan. It was often visited by disreputable nobles from the Senex and Juvex Houses.

properties.name: Yhifar
properties.description: Yhifar was a Mid Rim gas giant located in the Juvex sector. It was the site of the Gas Vortex, the eye of an immense, millennia-old storm. The Gas Vortex provided living beings with tolerable atmospheric pressure and breathable air, allowing the construction of settlements in that area. Reckless gas miners dived into the high-pressure depths of Yhifar in armored submersibles tethered to mining platforms in the Gas Vortex.

properties.name: Yhuli
properties.description: Yhuli may refer to one of the following:

properties.name: Yinchorr
properties.poi: Imperial baseImperial Royal Guard AcademyThe Squall
properties.description: Yinchorr was the Yinchorri homeworld. It was first charted c. 500 BBY.

properties.name: Yir Tangee
properties.description: Yir Tangee was a planet in the Yir Tangee system of the Colonies. It was represented in the Galactic Senate by Havriso Looruya, who was appointed to the Loyalist Committee. However he was then censored and expelled for having Separatist ties. Under the New Order, it received medical supplies from the Carosite freighter Sudden Restoration.

properties.name: Yirt-4138-Grek-12
properties.description: Yirt-4138-Grek-12 was an asteroid in the Yirt-4138-Grek-12 system of the Fakir sector. It was the site of an industrial espionage training center wiped out by Corporate Alliance NR-N99 Persuader-class Droid Enforcers.

properties.name: Yisgga
properties.description: Yisgga was a colony planet located within the Yisgga system of the Inner Rim Territories which the Star Morning had visited.

properties.name: Yitabo
properties.description: Yitabo was a minor agriworld located in the Yitabo system, at the intersection of the Pabol Sleheyron and Durkteel Loop in the Kastolar sector. It was the home to Borneck, Saurin, and Wookiee colonists.

properties.name: Yityl
properties.description: Yityl was a planet located within the Yityl system of the Outer Rim Territories. It was an Imperial planet inhabited by Humans such as Imperial Customs Agent Hewat and her daughter Kora Hewat.

properties.name: Ylesia
properties.poi: Altar of Promises, Gachoogai River, Mountains of Faith, Mountains of the Exalted, Palace of Peace, Zoma Gawanga,
properties.description: Ylesia was a tropical world located in Hutt Space. It was controlled by the Besadii Hutts. The planet was used as a slave colony dedicated to spice production covered up as a religious retreat.

properties.name: Ylix
properties.description: Ylix was a backwater Mid Rim planet located in the Ylix system between Anobis and Ithor. It was a long-time rival of nearby Goelitz, which it finally defeated in battle. It was also the home of the mercenary Gallandro.

properties.name: Yn
properties.description: Yn was a planet located within the Yn system of the Inner Rim. It was represented in the New Republic Senate by Wwebyls, a tiny humanoid.

properties.name: Yntrann
properties.description: Yntrann was a terrestrial astronomical object located in the Yntrann system, a part of Wild Space. During the Galactic Civil War, after the Scandium Team of the Rebel Alliance's Special Forces was disbanded, the Ebranite former member of the team Rith Tar'ak was transferred to Yntrann, where she briefly commanded a small yet highly decorated desert warfare task force as part of one of the early Special Forces wilderness regiments. Since leadership did not appeal to Tar'ak, she eventually requested a transfer to another branch of the Alliance and was stationed off-world.

properties.name: Yoberra
properties.description: Yoberra was a planet located within the Yoberra system of the Outer Rim Territories and the home to the eight-legged species of which Jomo was a member.

properties.name: Yoggoy
properties.description: Yoggoy was a planet in the Unknown Regions. It was covered in mounds similar to the Castle Lands, with flowers imported from Alderaan. The Tachyon Flier crashed on Yoggoy in 27 ABY in the location known as the Crash. It was home to the Killiks of the Yoggoy hive and the capital of the Colony.

properties.name: Yoon Cloud
properties.description: The Yoon Cloud was a nebula situated within the galaxy's Wild Space region. Its center contained a star system that was home to a species of 12-armed glider. While returning from the system shortly after its exploration, a Nova scout carrying a specimen of the species visited the University of Sanbra and left the glider there for the researchers to study. Professor Tem Eliss later mentioned the visit of the scout from the Yoon Cloud in the publication The University of Sanbra Guide to Intelligent Life.

properties.name: Yorgraxx
properties.description: Yorgraxx was a planet located in the Prefsbelt sector of the Outer Rim.

properties.name: Yoribuunt
properties.description: Yoribuunt was a beautiful, swirling gas giant in the Yoribuunt system of the Tharin sector near Hutt Space. It was a popular stop for sight-seers on luxury liners.

properties.name: Yorn Skot
properties.description: Yorn Skot was a gas giant in the Yorn Skot system near Dargulli. It was a natural source of non-spinsealed tibanna gas. It was not part of the Galactic Republic.

properties.name: Yout
properties.description: Yout was a planet located within the Yout system of the Mid Rim. It had at least twelve moons, including one known as Yout 12, where the assassin droid KRONOS-327 was sent to assassinate a Black Sun Vigo, a task which KRONOS-327 failed.

properties.name: Ytha'ac Cluster
properties.description: The Ytha'ac Cluster was a cluster of asteroids in the Airam sector of the Outer Rim Territories at galactic coordinates M-20. It was located within the Ytha'ac system.

properties.name: Yuga
properties.description: Yuga 2 was the second planet in the Yuga system. It was covered in rain forests. The world played host to the popular Yuga Planetary Park, a tourist destination visited by Galaxy Tours. It was the site of a raid on a Galaxy Tours cruiser by Callow Batta prior to the Battle of Hoth.

properties.name: Yugami
properties.description: Yugami was a planet located within the Yugami system of the Outer Rim Territories. Its people were in a constant state of conflict with the Pursian species of Pursin.

properties.name: Yulant
properties.description: Yulant was an agricultural planet in the Core Worlds owned by the Salliche Agricultural Corporation who sued Dasobo Meats, a meat shipping company based on the planet. It was one of the worlds on the Ag Circuit.

properties.name: Yunkor
properties.description: Yunkor may refer to:

properties.name: Yurb
properties.description: Yurb was an arid planet located within the Yurb system of the Outer Rim Territories. It was the homeworld of the razor-tailed tiger of the Dust Pits.

properties.name: Yutusk
properties.description: Yutusk was a temperate backwater planet in the Yutusk system subjugated by the Galactic Empire. It was the homeworld of chef Vimran Trell, whom was conscripted in the Imperial Navy. His parents Tranira Trell and Francill Trell were killed when Imperial forces rounded up and executed suspected Rebel sympathizers on Yutusk.

properties.name: Yuvern
properties.description: Yuvern was an Outer Rim Territories planet located in the Oplovis sector. It was the homeworld of the two-headed, snakelike Yuvernians. One young Yuvernian, Cane Adiss, dreamed of leaving his homeworld and becoming an explorer, and he was eventually taken offworld by the trader Kal'Falnl C'ndros. By 2 ABY, the Yuvernian had become a spice smuggler for the crime lord Jabba the Hutt, whose first assignment took Adiss back to Yuvern. Arriving in-system, the Yuvernian encountered the Imperial Oplovis Sector Fleet. Subsequently, an unexpected Rebel Alliance attack on the fleet prevented Imperial inspectors from discovering Adiss's illegal cargo, and the smuggler was later able to finish his mission to Yuvern.

properties.name: Yvara
properties.description: Yvara was the homeworld of the Yvarema species. It was located just inside the Kathol Rift. The planet had a varied topography, with ice and snow capped poles, vast desert plains, and fungal-covered fields. Three oceans covered the planet, and each of the continents were ringed by mountain ranges to create a natural barrier. The planet's indigenous species, the Yvarema, lived in underground warrens just north of the planet's equator.

properties.name: Ywllandr
properties.description: The Ywllandr system was a star system located within the Prefsbelt sector of the Outer Rim Territories.

properties.name: Z'fell
properties.description: Z'fell was a planet in the Z'fell system of the Koornacht Cluster. It was one of the original 13 planets of the Duskhan League. The planet was attacked by the New Republic during the Battle of N'zoth.

properties.name: Z'trop
properties.description: Z'trop was a planet located in the Tamarin sector of the Outer Rim Territories.

properties.name: Zaadja
properties.description: Zaadja was an icy planet with snowy plains surrounded by impervious mountains.

properties.name: Zadaria
properties.description: The Zadaria system was located in the Gateworlds, an area of the Hapes Cluster in the Slice portion of the Inner Rim. It was connected via hyperlanes to the Febrini and Phelope systems. The Zadaria system was the origin point of the beverage known as Zadarian brandy.

properties.name: Zaddja
properties.description: Zaddja was a barren planet located in the Zaddja system of the Trilon sector, beyond the most inhabited regions of the galaxy. It was orbited by a small asteroid shroud.

properties.name: Zalori
properties.description: The Zalori system was located in the Hapan Rim Worlds, an area of the Hapes Cluster in the Slice portion of the Inner Rim. It was connected by the hyperlane known as the Great Rim Route to the Rynmar and Terephon systems.

properties.name: Zaloriis
properties.poi: Camp Culroon, Fondor II, Fantain Mountains
properties.description: Zaloriis was an Expansion Region planet colonized by Humans from Fondor. By 0 ABY it was home to Camp Culroon, a hidden Galactic Empire research base. That year, the planet attempted to join the Rebel Alliance, but Darth Vader led a strike force to recapture the planet.

properties.name: Zalso
properties.description: Zalso was a human-inhabited planet in the Zalso system where a battle during the Galactic Civil War was fought.

properties.name: Zamael
properties.description: Zamael was an astronomical object located in the galaxy's Deep Core.

properties.name: Zanbar
properties.description: Zanbar was a swamp moon in the Outer Rim Territories' Mandalore sector. The Mandalorian Death Watch relocated to Zanbar and established a camp there shortly after leaving Carlac.

properties.name: Zaraksander
properties.description: Zaraksander was an astronomical object in the Expansion Region's Imberlin sector. It was the site of the Fioer desert, and an Eloinie Petro-Munitions munitions factory was located on the celestial body's southern continent.

properties.name: Zaria
properties.description: Zaria was a terrestrial world located in the Zaria system of the Juvex sector, a part of the Senex-Juvex region in the Western Reaches portion of the Mid Rim. The Senex-Juvex Loop hyperlane linked it to the Anstares and Malador systems.

properties.name: Zardossa Stix
properties.description: Zardossa Stix was a desert moon located in the Zardossa Stix system of the galaxy's Colonies region. It was the site of an ancient temple built in honor of Malmourral, the Bardottan demon of war. In 19.1 BBY, the Frangawl Cult kidnapped Queen Julia of the nearby planet Bardotta and brought her to the temple, where she was to be sacrificed in order to empower Mother Talzin. However, she was rescued by Jedi Master Mace Windu and Junior Representative Jar Jar Binks.

properties.name: Zarsteck
properties.description: Zarsteck was a planet located within the Zarsteck system of the Core Worlds.

properties.name: Zchtek
properties.description: The Zchtek worlds of the Mid Rim were home to the Jin. Subjugated by the Galactic Empire, they were the site of a genocide perpetrated by that regime.

properties.name: Zebitrope
properties.description: Zebitrope may refer to one of the following:

properties.name: Zeenada
properties.description: Zeenada was a marshy planet primarily covered in jungles.

properties.name: ZeHeth
properties.description: ZeHeth was a Mid Rim planet that was home to the sentient ZeHethbra species. The natives of ZeHeth lived in urban areas as well as in dens amid the roots of the planet's large trees. ZeHeth was a part of the Galactic Republic during the Clone Wars and became a member of the Galactic Empire afterward.

properties.name: Zekulae
properties.description: Zekulae was a planet located at the heart of the Zeemacht Cluster within the Zekulae system of the Inner Rim. It was a barren world, noted for its dark, rich mineral soil, which was studded with blue crystals. Its soil was extremely fine and so was everpresent on the planet. Its inhabitants were known as the Zeku. It sat outside the globular cluster known as Cosm's Well.

properties.name: Zelaba
properties.description: Zelaba was a planet in the Outer Jalor sector of the Mid Rim.

properties.name: Zelos
properties.description: Zelos was the primary sun of the Zelos system. It was orbited by three planets.

properties.name: Zeltros
properties.description: Zeltros was a planet in the Inner Rim, and the homeworld of the Zeltron race. An opulent world, hedonism was the doctrine encouraged by the empathetic Zeltrons, and Zeltros was continuously in a state of never ending revelry. The Zeltron appreciation of beauty in its many forms led to luxurious art and architecture covering the world, and the galaxy's most wealthy favored Zeltros as a vacation destination. Many who came to the planet were taken in by the celebratory atmosphere and the powerful pheromones of the Zeltron people to the point they found it difficult to leave, and even planetary invasions often floundered in the face of Zeltros' planet-wide festivities.

properties.name: Zenox Cluster
properties.description: The Zenox Star Cluster was a star cluster located within the Colonies region of the galaxy and was part of the Galactic Empire.

properties.name: Zephry
properties.description: Zephry was an astronomical object in the Greater Javin Region of the galaxy's Outer Rim Territories.

properties.name: Zerm
properties.description: Zerm was a planet located in the Kessel sector of the Outer Rim Territories.

properties.name: Zeta 0-9
properties.description: Zeta Zero Nine was a planet located in the Wastes, beyond the Obtrexta sector.

properties.name: Zhann
properties.description: Zhann was a planet located within the Zhann system of the Colonies and known for its puppet shows.

properties.name: Zhanox
properties.description: Zhanox was a mining world located in the Zhanox system, in the heart of the Ivax Nebula. It was covered in rocky spires and inhabited by Humans and Ugnaughts.

properties.name: Zhina
properties.description: Zhina was one of the original 13 planets of the Duskhan League. It was orbited by the Imperial shipyard Black Eleven.

properties.name: Zigoola
properties.description: Zigoola was a planet and a potent dark side vergence in The Force located in Wild Space, near the Calamari sector.

properties.name: Zin Taal
properties.poi: First Sun Mobile Regiment command base,
properties.description: Zin Taal was an Outer Rim Territories world located in the Carrion sector. By 11 ABY, the mercenary First Sun Mobile Regiment established a command base there. The New Republic, intending to capture the base, dispatched a New Republic Special Forces strike force that was dropped onto the world. The team's mission on Zin Taal was eventually complicated by an unforeseen circumstance.

properties.name: Ziost
properties.poi: Sith Citadel, Ziost Analysis Services Center, Ziost AbyssZiost's breeding pens, Emperor's Eye, Orbital Defense Command CenterMinistry of LogisticsA camp, A small citadel,
properties.description: Ziost , sometimes referred to as the "Gateway to the Empire" in the days of the Old Republic, was a rocky world and potent focal point of the dark side of the Force located in the Ziost system, a star system in the Sith Worlds region of the Outer Rim Territories's Esstran sector. It was an adopted homeworld of the Sith species. Connected to other nearby worlds by the Nache Bhelfia hyperlane, Ziost was considered one of the five sacred Sith planets and served as a capital of Adas's Sith Empire and the Old Sith Empire.

properties.name: Zircon
properties.description: Zircon was a planet located within the Zircon system of the Outer Rim Territories.

properties.name: Zirulast
properties.description: Zirulast was a terrestrial backwater planet located in the Zirulast system, a part of the Belasco sector in the Slice portion of the Expansion Region. Orbiting the white dwarf star of the same name, Zirulast was situated on the Ootmian Pabol hyperlane, which connected it to the Belasco system as well as the New Apsolon system in the Mid Rim. Zirulast was a dry and dusty world encircled by rings of ice particles. The Temolaks, sentient humanoids speaking the Temolish language, were native to the planet, evolving redundant internal organs in order to survive the rigors of their homeworld.

properties.name: Zisia
properties.description: Zisia was a rich planet that was located within the Zisia system in Hutt Space, a region of the galaxy controlled by the Hutt species. The planet lay on the hyperlane called The Dead Road, which connected it to the worlds of Elgit and Ulmatra. Zisia was the homeworld of the sentient Zisian species, members of which served as pliant slaves for millennia.

properties.name: Zissh
properties.description: Zissh was a planet located within the Zissh system of the Expansion Region. It was a frozen world where Jedi Knight Aven Rolk planned to establish a new Jedi Temple and rebuild the Jedi Order. However, his proclamation drew the attention of the Galactic Empire, and Rolk was later found dead in an ice cave.

properties.name: Ziugen
properties.description: Ziugen was a slave colony world that was located within the Ziugen system in Hutt Space, a region of the galaxy controlled by the Hutt species. The planet lay on the hyperlane called the Shag Pabol that connected it to the world of Ylesia and the Outland Transit Station. A smaller hyperspace route also linked Ziugen to the planet of Poytta. The inhabitants of Ziugen were equally devoted to industry and agriculture.

properties.name: Zolan
properties.description: Zolan was a planet that was the homeworld of the Zolander species and its Clawdite offshoot.

properties.name: Zongorlu
properties.description: Zongorlu was a Galactic Republic planet in the Outer Rim Territories. It was conquered by the Mandalorian Neo-Crusaders during the Mandalorian Wars, shortly after the bombing of Serroco. The Mandalorians launched their assault on Zongorlu from Taris.

properties.name: Zonju
properties.description: Zonju was the Zonju system's primary star.

properties.name: Zoraster
properties.description: Zoraster was a planet located within the Zoraster system, a part of the Outer Rim Territories' Zoraster sector. It was the homeworld of the Human male Condi. At some point by 28 BBY, the slaver Krayn captured Condi, taking him off-world and forcing him to work aboard his starship among other slaves.

properties.name: Zorb
properties.description: Zorb was a planet located in the Zorb system of the Outer Rim Territories.

properties.name: Zorbia
properties.description: Zorbia was an astronomical object located in the Moddell sector of the Outer Rim Territories in grid square H-16 of the Standard Galactic Grid. It was situated on the Ovise Reach hyperspace route, which linked it to the Endor and Trindello systems. The Moddell sector's hyperspace anomalies sometimes transported starships to the Endor system from as far away as Zorbia. Zorbia was eventually depicted on a map of the Moddell sector included with the Rebel Alliance collection of non-electronic documents known as The Rebel Files.

properties.name: Zosha
properties.description: Zosha was a planet located in the Unknown Regions.

properties.name: Zrak
properties.description: Zrak, also known as Zrak the Twisted, was the name of a terentatek living on Voss during the Cold War. It was killed around 3640 BBY.

properties.name: Zuggit
properties.description: Zuggit was a planet located within the Zuggit system of the Inner Rim Territories that was inhabited by a twelve foot tall, twin-headed, and magenta-skinned sentient species.

properties.name: Zuliria
properties.description: Zuliria was a planet that was located within the Eucer sector of the Mid Rim region of the galaxy.

properties.name: Zygerria
properties.poi: East Province, Drukarg highlands, Zygerrian Royal Palace,
properties.description: Zygerria was the homeworld of the near-Human Zygerrian species.

properties.name: Zygia
properties.description: The Zygia system was located in the Manda sector, a part of the Slice portion of the Mid Rim. The hyperlane known as the Manda Merchant Route linked it to the Holess system as well as the Thoran system in the Bothan sector.

properties.name: Zyluria
properties.description: Zyluria was a world located in the Zyluria system of the Juvex sector, a part of the Senex-Juvex region in the Western Reaches portion of the Mid Rim. A hyperlane linked it to the Carsanza system. Zyluria's surface featured gentle plains, and it was the homeworld of the Zylurians, a sentient species that, by 43 ABY, had long served the aristocratic Ancient Houses of the Senex-Juvex.

properties.name: Zznza
properties.description: Outer Zznza was a location in the Zznza system, a part of the Yminis sector in the Slice portion of the Outer Rim Territories. The Besalisk chef Dexter Jettster claimed in the menu for Dex's Diner, his restaurant on the Core Worlds planet Coruscant, that nerf steak was a breakfast staple throughout the galaxy, including such locations as Coruscant and Outer Zznza.

properties.name: Korriban
properties.poi: Valley of the Dark Lords, Eternal Pyre, Valley of GolgSith AcademySith CitadelShyrack caveKorriban Arrival Port
properties.description: Korriban, known as Pesegam during the reign of Xim, and also known as Moraband by the time of the Clone Wars, was the sole planet in the Horuset system, located across the galaxy from Koros Major. It was the original homeworld of the Sith species and a sacred planet for the Sith Order, housing the tombs for many ancient and powerful Dark Lords of the Sith, and containing immense dark side power.

properties.name: Oba Diah
properties.description: Oba Diah was a planet located close to Kessel, in the Kessel sector of the galaxy's Outer Rim Territories. The homeworld of the Pyke species, it was the base of operations the Pyke Syndicate, a criminal organization of spice dealers.

properties.name: Adega
properties.description: Adega, a planet located in the Moddell sector, was where the earliest lightsaber crystals came from. The three most common varieties were still referred to as Adegan crystals even after the planet Ilum succeeded Adega as the crystals' primary source.

properties.name: The Wheel
properties.poi: Golden Star casino, Toran's Resort, IsoTech offices, Retreat, Dented Droid , Farlander's Outfitting and Supply, Sonou's Apparel, High Stakes and Hyperspace, Hal's Parts Store, Tasia's Tapcafé, Blasted Asteroid ,
properties.description: The Wheel was a large space station located in the Besh Gorgon system of the Mid Rim along the Perlemian Trade Route.

properties.name: Kiffu
properties.description: Kiffu was a planet in the outermost reaches of the Inner Rim. It was  the homeworld of the Kiffar species.
